(34, 1, 'Business India', '&lt;table border=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;1790&quot;&gt;\n	&lt;colgroup&gt;\n		&lt;col width=&quot;1790&quot; /&gt;\n	&lt;/colgroup&gt;\n	&lt;tbody&gt;\n		&lt;tr height=&quot;22&quot;&gt;\n			&lt;td class=&quot;xl64&quot; height=&quot;22&quot; style=&quot;height:16.5pt;width:1343pt&quot; width=&quot;1790&quot;&gt;BUSINESS INDIA is India''s first and foremost business magazine. Launched in February 1978, this business fortnightly pioneered the market for business journalism, in India. Through the years, despite new entrants in the field, BUSINESS INDIA enjoys the enviable reputation of being India''s most respected and credible business magazine.&lt;/td&gt;\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\n	&lt;/tbody&gt;\n&lt;/table&gt;\n', 'Business India', 'Business India', 'Business India'),
(35, 1, 'Business Week', '&lt;table border=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;1790&quot;&gt;\n	&lt;colgroup&gt;\n		&lt;col width=&quot;1790&quot; /&gt;\n	&lt;/colgroup&gt;\n	&lt;tbody&gt;\n		&lt;tr height=&quot;22&quot;&gt;\n			&lt;td class=&quot;xl66&quot; height=&quot;22&quot; style=&quot;height:16.5pt;width:1343pt&quot; width=&quot;1790&quot;&gt;Business Week was first published in September 1929, only weeks before the Stock Market Crash of 1929. Its original purpose was to provide information and opinions as to what was happening in the business world, at the time. Initially, the magazine published sections that included topics such as marketing, labor, finance, and management, among others.Consequently, Business Week pioneered the action of covering national political issues that directly impacted the business world. In 1950, the magazine published its first executive pay survey, which it still does today.&lt;/td&gt;\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\n	&lt;/tbody&gt;\n&lt;/table&gt;\n', 'Business Week\n', 'Business Week\n', ''),
(36, 1, 'Computational Optimization and Applications', '&lt;table border=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;1790&quot;&gt;\n	&lt;colgroup&gt;\n		&lt;col width=&quot;1790&quot; /&gt;\n	&lt;/colgroup&gt;\n	&lt;tbody&gt;\n		&lt;tr height=&quot;22&quot;&gt;\n			&lt;td class=&quot;xl66&quot; height=&quot;22&quot; style=&quot;height:16.5pt;width:1343pt&quot; width=&quot;1790&quot;&gt;This journal publishes research on the analysis and development of computational algorithms and modeling technology for optimization. It examines algorithms either for general classes of optimization problems or for more specific applied problems, stochastic algorithms as well as deterministic algorithms.&lt;/td&gt;\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\n	&lt;/tbody&gt;\n&lt;/table&gt;\n', 'Computational Optimization and Applications\n', 'Computational Optimization and Applications\n', ''),
(40, 1, 'Computational Particle Mechanics', '&lt;table border=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;1790&quot;&gt;\n	&lt;colgroup&gt;\n		&lt;col width=&quot;1790&quot; /&gt;\n	&lt;/colgroup&gt;\n	&lt;tbody&gt;\n		&lt;tr height=&quot;22&quot;&gt;\n			&lt;td class=&quot;xl66&quot; height=&quot;22&quot; style=&quot;height:16.5pt;width:1343pt&quot; width=&quot;1790&quot;&gt;Computational Particle Mechanics (CPM) is a quarterly journal with&amp;nbsp;the goal of publishing full-length original articles addressing the modeling and simulation&amp;nbsp;of systems involving particles and particle methods. The goal is to enhance communication&amp;nbsp;among researchers in the applied sciences &amp;nbsp;who &amp;nbsp;use &quot;particles'''' in one form or another in their research.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\n	&lt;/tbody&gt;\n&lt;/table&gt;\n', 'Computational Particle Mechanics\n', 'Computational Particle Mechanics\n', ''),
(42, 1, 'Computational Statistics', '&lt;table border=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;1790&quot;&gt;\n	&lt;colgroup&gt;\n		&lt;col width=&quot;1790&quot; /&gt;\n	&lt;/colgroup&gt;\n	&lt;tbody&gt;\n		&lt;tr height=&quot;22&quot;&gt;\n			&lt;td class=&quot;xl66&quot; height=&quot;22&quot; style=&quot;height:16.5pt;width:1343pt&quot; width=&quot;1790&quot;&gt;Computational Statistics (CompStat)&lt;font class=&quot;font0&quot;&gt; is an international journal that fosters the publication of applications and methodological research in the field of computational statistics. The journal provides a forum for computer scientists, mathematicians, and statisticians working in a variety of areas in statistics, including biometrics, econometrics, data analysis, graphics, simulation, algorithms, knowledge-based systems, and Bayesian computing.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/td&gt;\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\n	&lt;/tbody&gt;\n&lt;/table&gt;\n', 'Computational Statistics\n', 'Computational Statistics\n', ''),
(44, 1, 'Computer Science - Research and Development', '&lt;table border=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;1790&quot;&gt;\n	&lt;colgroup&gt;\n		&lt;col width=&quot;1790&quot; /&gt;\n	&lt;/colgroup&gt;\n	&lt;tbody&gt;\n		&lt;tr height=&quot;22&quot;&gt;\n			&lt;td class=&quot;xl66&quot; height=&quot;22&quot; style=&quot;height:16.5pt;width:1343pt&quot; width=&quot;1790&quot;&gt;Computational Optimization and Applications&lt;font class=&quot;font0&quot;&gt; covers a wide range of topics in optimization, including: large scale optimization, unconstrained optimization, constrained optimization, nondifferentiable optimization, combinatorial optimization, stochastic optimization, multiobjective optimization, and network optimization. It also covers linear programming, complexity theory, automatic differentiation, approximations and error analysis, parametric programming and sensitivity analysis, management science, and more.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/td&gt;\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\n	&lt;/tbody&gt;\n&lt;/table&gt;\n', '', '', ''),
(46, 1, 'Computer Supported Cooperative Work (CSCW)', '&lt;table border=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;1790&quot;&gt;\n	&lt;colgroup&gt;\n		&lt;col width=&quot;1790&quot; /&gt;\n	&lt;/colgroup&gt;\n	&lt;tbody&gt;\n		&lt;tr height=&quot;22&quot;&gt;\n			&lt;td class=&quot;xl66&quot; height=&quot;22&quot; style=&quot;height:16.5pt;width:1343pt&quot; width=&quot;1790&quot;&gt;Computer Supported Cooperative Work (CSCW) disseminates innovative research results and provides an interdisciplinary forum for the debate and exchange of ideas concerning theoretical, practical, technical, and social issues in CSCW. The journal encompasses the diverse nature of research within the field and its related areas. Coverage ranges from ethnographic studies of cooperative work to reports on the development of CSCW systems and their technological foundations.&lt;/td&gt;\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\n	&lt;/tbody&gt;\n&lt;/table&gt;\n', '', '', ''),
(47, 1, 'Business Today', '&lt;table border=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;1790&quot;&gt;\n	&lt;colgroup&gt;\n		&lt;col width=&quot;1790&quot; /&gt;\n	&lt;/colgroup&gt;\n	&lt;tbody&gt;\n		&lt;tr height=&quot;22&quot;&gt;\n			&lt;td class=&quot;xl66&quot; height=&quot;22&quot; style=&quot;height:16.5pt;width:1343pt&quot; width=&quot;1790&quot;&gt;Business Today is India’s No. 1 Business Magazine with the highest readership amongst all business magazines in the country. A child of liberalization, the magazine was founded in 1992 to chronicle the changing business topography of the New India. Since then, it has set new benchmarks in both reportage-led stories and survey-led listings. Its ability to capture trends as they break and the mathematical rigor it brings based on research-based analysis has made Business Today the most respected business features magazine in the country.&lt;/td&gt;\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\n	&lt;/tbody&gt;\n&lt;/table&gt;\n', '', '', ''),
(48, 1, 'Business World', '&lt;table border=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;1790&quot;&gt;\n	&lt;colgroup&gt;\n		&lt;col width=&quot;1790&quot; /&gt;\n	&lt;/colgroup&gt;\n	&lt;tbody&gt;\n		&lt;tr height=&quot;22&quot;&gt;\n			&lt;td class=&quot;xl66&quot; height=&quot;22&quot; style=&quot;height:16.5pt;width:1343pt&quot; width=&quot;1790&quot;&gt;Stay ahead of the curve with exclusive business news and analysis every week&lt;/td&gt;\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\n	&lt;/tbody&gt;\n&lt;/table&gt;\n', '', '', ''),
(49, 1, 'Forbes India', '&lt;table border=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;1790&quot;&gt;\n	&lt;colgroup&gt;\n		&lt;col width=&quot;1790&quot; /&gt;\n	&lt;/colgroup&gt;\n	&lt;tbody&gt;\n		&lt;tr height=&quot;22&quot;&gt;\n			&lt;td class=&quot;xl66&quot; height=&quot;22&quot; style=&quot;height:16.5pt;width:1343pt&quot; width=&quot;1790&quot;&gt;Forbes is the world’s leading business magazine and since its inception in 1917 its mission has been clear and unchanging: to provide insights and information that ensure the success of those who tap into Forbes. In India, Forbes is launched in partnership with Network18, India''s biggest full play integrated media network. Every fortnight, Forbes India will help you connect the dots, form patterns and see beyond the obvious. It will bring to light ideas and the people generating them, allowing you to get an edge as a professional and needless to say, it will also open up the potential for wealth creation. Our sharp, in-depth and engaging stories will look at global and domestic issues from an Indian prism, giving you a completely different perspective. Subscribe to Forbes India today and stay ahead of the curve.&lt;/td&gt;\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\n	&lt;/tbody&gt;\n&lt;/table&gt;\n', 'Forbes India\n', 'Forbes India\n', ''),
(50, 1, 'Cup Race Technology', '&lt;p&gt;FROM THE PUBLISHER Although stock-appearing, running oval tracks at 200 mph the Cup car generates huge aerodynamic forces. Under the skin the Cup car is purpose-designed for racing albeit around some mandatory components that are strangely archaic. It all adds up to a fascinating engineering challenge. Published annually, Cup Race Technology explains in depth how some of the finest minds in motorsport rise to this fascinating and unique challenge. Contents are: · Intro: The Editor - Technical innovation in NASCAR continues apace · Grid - The latest technical news from the world of stockcar racing · Dossier: Chevy SS - Lawrence Butcher charts the development of GM’s latest Cup entrant · Insight: Aero - Despite tight controls, Cup engineers can still find gains in aero performance, as Lawrence Butcher explains · Digest: Dirt Super Late Model - An insight into the technology of dirt racing · Focus: Manufacturing - Lawrence Butcher investigates the resources and equipment teams in NASCAR use to get their cars from drawing board to grid · Tech Review - Lawrence Butcher looks at the latest component developments in NASCAR, and some from outside the sport with potential stockcar applications · Insight: Tires - Dr Diandra Leslie Pelecky gets under the skin of the Cup tire to find technology of surprising complexity · Paddock - NASCAR has made its system of penalties for rule-breakers simpler and more consistent. · PS - Where does NASCAR go next?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '', '', ''),
(51, 1, 'Drag Race Technology', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nBehind the astonishing spectacle of professional drag racing is extreme engineering that is ultra-tightly focussed but compared to other forms of motorsport no less complex for that. If anything the puzzle gets harder, the fewer are the variables that make the difference between winning and losing. The challenge of engineering and controlling the fastest accelerating vehicles in the world is thus a fascinating one that is revealed annually by Drag Race Technology.\n\nThis publication uniquely gets to the nuts and bolts of a range of drag race cars, bikes and boats from around the world representing the state of the art in straight-line engineering and reveals the technologies that provide the winning edge.\n\nIntro: THE EDITOR - Variety is the spice of life\n· Grid: IN THE NEWS - A suspension revolution in Pro Stock\n· Dossier: PRO MOD CAMARO -The UK’s fastest Pro Mod investigated\n· In Conversation: JIMMY PROCK - Anne Proffit speaks to successful Funny Car crew chief\n· Focus: SUSPENSION, STEERING AND BRAKES - Jon Scoltock looks at drag race suspension, tires and steering systems\n· Profile: PRO STREET HAYABUSA - What does it take to build the fastest street legal bikes in the world\n· Focus: POWER ADDERS - Lawrence Butcher investigates blowers, turbos and nitrous oxide\n· Digest: BEETLE DOORSLAMMER - This diminutive VW is taking the fight to the V8s\n· PS: FOUR WHEEL DRIVE DRAGSTER - Tommy Ivo’s four engined monster remembered\n', '', '', ''),
(52, 1, 'F1 Race Technology', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nF1 Race Technology puts the role of the engine in context with its analysis of the whole car environment. F1 Race Engine Technology is a unique, high quality review of contemporary racing powertrain technology.\n\nFeaturing input from many of today’s top F1 technical directors and written by Ian Bamsey, this technical report presents a unique in-depth insight into the engineering and mechanics of contemporary Grand Prix racing cars.\n\nIt is widely read by design and development engineers and others involved professionally in this worldwide industry and just as avidly by those interested in a subject that has a huge ‘enthusiast’ following.\n\nF1 Race Technology reaches the majority of all competition engine builders right across the globe – the heart of its readership. Contents Include:\n· INTRO: THE EDITOR - A new era has begun in Formula One\n· GRID - The latest news from the Formula One Grid 12 Tech review: Formula One 2014 New regulations have brought new cars and powertrains of unprecedented complexity\n· INSIGHT:CFD - Are regulations stifling innovation in CFD?\n· FOCUS: SENSORS - What type of sensors do F1 teams utilise for data collection?\n· TECH REVIEW: FORMULA ONE 2013 - Ian Bamsey investigates the technical challenges of the 2013 season\n· FOCUS:ALM - David Cooper looks at the emerging technology of additive layer manufacturing\n· PADDOCK - A round-up of technical personnel changes through the 2013-14 seasons\n· DIRECTORY - The F1 services resource\n· PS - Lawrence Butcher looks at new entrant Haas Formula\n', '', '', ''),
(53, 1, '24 Hour Race Technology', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\n2Officially endorsed by the ACO, 24 Hour Race Technology provides an annual review of the engineering spectacle that is Le Mans, highlighting why certain technologies are to the fore. Both Prototype and GT cars are analysed in depth in this uniquely focussed appraisal of the world’s greatest twice-around-the-clock race, revealing many secrets of performance.\n\nIntro: THE EDITOR · Grid: IN THE NEWS - Audi triumphs, Corvette brings a new racer to GTE\n· Insight: STRATEGY AND TECHNOLOGY - Paolo Catone’s take on the strategy and technology of LM P1\n· In Conversation: THOMAS LAUDENBACH - Audi’s head of electronics and hybrid systems gives an insight in to challenges of Le Man\n· Digest: AUDI R18 - Christopher Reinke on Audi’s winning car\n· Digest: PORSCHE 919 HYBRID - Alex Hitzinger talks about Porsche’s new challenger\n· Focus: POWERTRAIN - Lawrence Butcher looks at powertrain innovation at Le Mans\n· Profile: ZEOD - The first car to complete an EV lap of Le Mans examined\n· Focus: CHASSIS - What does it take to build a chassis for Le Mans?\n· Profile: STRAKKA-DOME S103 - The newest LM P2 on the block investigated\n· Directory - The endurance racer’s resource\n· PS - The legend of the Carrera\n', '', '', ''),
(54, 1, 'Cocktails', 'COCKTAILS from the Bars of the Leading Hotels of the World. 52 Bars. 6 continents. 156 cocktails. Leading bartenders from some of the most prestigious, luxurious and unique hotels across the globe share personal insights on bartending along with their signature cocktails. Be it classics, exotic blends, or the best bars to sample local concoctions at your next holiday destination, you’re sure to find something that will suit your tastes in this premium coffee table book.', '', '', ''),
(55, 1, 'The 100 Greatest Photographs Of The Paranormal', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThey say seeing is believing. Here are 100 of the most startling and intriguing photographs you are ever likely to see. If you don’t already believe in the paranormal – they may convince you! The photos cover the entire range of the unexplained, from possible ghosts and spirit manifestations, through psychic powers and weird creatures to UFO sightings. There are no tossed hubcaps, stray camera straps or oddly illuminated bits of dust here – contained within these pages are 100 of the best-attested photographs in the history of the paranormal. Each has been personally selected by Janet Bord of the Fortean Picture Library, the world’s most extensive collection of imagery of the strange and the unexplained. Janet, who has published widely on the subject of the supernatural, provides concise but informative introductions to the photos to explain their origin and to put them in context. It’s up to you to decide whether these photos provide proof of the paranormal, but we can guarantee that they are as close to proof as you can get – without seeing the phenomena take place for yourself.\n', '', '', ''),
(56, 1, 'Royal Britain Issue 2', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nHello and welcome to a very special second issue of Royal Britain magazine. Can there be any better time to be in Great Britain than this amazing year, which sees us celebrating both the Olympic Games and the glorious 60 years of Queen Elizabeth II’s reign? The Diamond Jubilee celebrations were packed with pomp and pageantry and every bit as magical as we had hoped. Even Her Majesty herself seems to have been overwhelmed, and after four days of being cheered by millions, The Queen responded with a landmark address to the nation during which she described events as “a humbling experience.”\n\nYou can relive that experience right here, in our special, picture-packed Diamond Jubilee supplement, which captures memories that will live forever in the minds of those who were there. Elsewhere we look forward to the London Olympics and chart the many Royal connections to the event. Royal Britain is all about celebrating our grand national heritage and you’ll find other fascinating features on the history of both the Royal Borough of Greenwich and The Thames.\n', '', '', ''),
(57, 1, 'Royal Britain Issue 3', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nHello and welcome to another fine issue of Royal Britain, the magazine that celebrates Britain''s rich Royal heritage. What an amazing year 2012 has been, both for our monarchy and for Great Britain as a whole. We all needed a boost in these austere times, and the timing was perfect to remind us all, and the rest of the world, of what makes Britain Great.\n\nFirst came the unforgettable pomp and pageantry of the Diamond Jubilee, and then the sporting spectacle of the London Olympics, an event that saw British athletes carrying away a record 29 gold medals, reflecting the glory of the best performance by a British team in 104 years. And what about Danny Boyle''s awesome £27 million opening ceremony? The Slumdog Millionaire director even managed to persuade Her Majesty Queen Elizabeth II to give her first – and we can safely assume, only – acting appearance!\n\nWas staging the Olympic Games money well spent? The way it has turned out, it certainly seems so. Britain is currently riding high on a surge of national patriotism, and the impressive way that the Games were staged has certainly been a boost to GB PLC''s world standing. It remains to be seen what will happen to some of the Olympic venues in the future, but we do know the 2.5 square kilometre Olympic Village site will be reopening in summer 2013 as the Queen Elizabeth Olympic Park. The £3bn scheme is at the centre of the east London regeneration effort and will include 8,000 homes, a university, a commercial hub, a children?s playground and sporting facilities. That''s all to look forward to, but in the meantime we hope you enjoy our Olympic coverage in this issue and the many other fascinating picture-packed articles with a Royal and historical theme.\n', '', '', ''),
(58, 1, 'A Celebration Of The Life Of Nelson Mandela', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nNelson Mandela was a true 20th century icon, a former prison inmate from humble beginnings who emerged to lead the African National Congress political party to victory in the nation’s first truly democratic election in 1994.\n\nIn the process he showed mercy and magnanimity toward the country’s racist former rulers, despite the fact that they condemned him to spend nearly three decades in prison.\n\nOn the sad occasion of Nelson Mandela’s passing, Legacy Magazines celebrates the amazing, inspirational life of the Nobel Peace Prize winner, detailing his early encounters with the evils of apartheid and the many trials he had to endure before emerging triumphant. Packed with fascinating text and rare and exclusive photographs, this high quality magazine special will become a collector’s item in years to come and serves as a fitting tribute to a man who really did change the world.\n', '', '', ''),
(59, 1, 'Fusion Flowers Weddings', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Fusion Flowers Weddings Magazine?\n\nPublished just once a year, this eagerly anticipated magazine leads the way when it comes to showcasing adventurous, contemporary flower arrangements for weddings. Bringing you stunning photo spreads from the most prestigious floristry designers in the world, a subscription to Fusion Flowers Weddings magazine is perfect if you''re looking for inspiration for floral bouquets and centrepiece arrangements that are genuinely out of the ordinary. Each issue typically features collections from a variety of designers from around the world, plus step-by-step arrangement guides and features on floral wedding accessories such as corsages, cake decor and hair decoration.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nFusion Flowers Weddings magazine are delighted to announce the contributors to this years’ bridal Collections. This year there will be Collections from Gary Kwok, Ilka Siedenburg, Harijanto Setiawan, Svetlana Chernyavsky, Holly Chapple, Jackie Smith Johns, Annette von Einem, Gillian Wheeler, Linnéa Bergqvist, Gregor Lersch, Elly Lin, Wally Klett and, in a ground-breaking move, Stein Are Hansen (current holder of the Interflora World Cup) will release his Collection of commercial bouquets all of which he created for his clients! In fact, a high proportion of the Collections feature purely commercial, contemporary floristry. We made the decision to request designers to share their commercial designs for even more inspiration in your work.\n\nThe 9th edition of this annual publication not only features cutting edge design but new floral recommendations in a 4-page reference guide, 7 step-by-step instructions and a full list of materials and suppliers too.\n\nThe stories cover a wide range of topics including the work of the amazing New York City based Event Designer David Beahm and how he used the latest Trend for paper flowers to create stunning designs and we even have images from The White House Christmas designs too! We report from Singapore on the work of a remarkable Event company - Boenga. Discover the Trend for creating decorated bridal cars and where to source the mechanics. And find out more about the international self-help, self-motivating Event Design group called Chapel Designers.\n\nYes - it''s another information and inspiration packed issue of Fusion Flowers Weddings magazine!\n', '', '', ''),
(60, 1, 'S Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nS MAGAZINE presents only the crème de la crème of imaginative, slightly erotic art &amp; fashion photography, for the more discerning voyeur.\n\nS MAGAZINE exists to remove the boundaries set by mainstream fashion journals and open a window to a world where superlative fashion photography meets high-class pornography.\n\nS MAGAZINE is dedicated to promote the edge of fashion photography and the industry''s most creative talents.\n\nS MAGAZINE''s appeal is the thrill of what the world imagery presents. The audience is the practitioners of the fashion scene and the leaders who pave the way for new ideas and groundbreaking innovation. The exclusiveness provides appeal for the high street shopper and provides glimpses of glamour and provocative fashion to everyday life.\n', '', '', ''),
(61, 1, 'Aie Magazine', '&lt;p&gt;FROM THE PUBLISHER AÏE is a bi-annual magazine that is dedicated to exposing the talents of an emerging generation of artists, photographers and designers, whilst at the same time breathing new life into existing brands, styles and creative channels AÏE was jointly founded by Fashion Stylist Alexandra Birchall-White, Palaeontologist Isabella Kruta and Philosopher Emilie Prattico. It was conceived as the interaction between their disciplines and interests with the aim of showing the world in a new light. The team''s shared curiosity for fashion, art, design, research, engineering, philosophy and scientific anthropology resulted in the shape of a magazine. From X-Ray scans to counting the rings marking a tree''s life span, the editorial team found inspiration - interested in how these varied aesthetics can become launch pads for creativity.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '', '', ''),
(62, 1, 'Exhibition', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nExhibition is really big for fashion! Each issue focuses on a single subject and its place in fashion, art and culture. It has contributions from some of Europe s foremost fashion writers and photographers and is sure to be a collector s item.\n', '', '', ''),
(63, 1, 'Maison De Campagne', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMaison de Campagne is an annual edition featuring fascinating residencies in the Greek islands and the Greek countryside, designed by the most notable architectutral offices.\n', '', '', ''),
(64, 1, 'Yvi-Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nYvi magazine is a new English language art magazine from Holland. Each issue of Yvi magazine focuses on a central (social) theme seen from the perspective of art. A wide range of artistic visions on a pertinent social theme are brought together in the form of photography, design, architecture and visual art.\n', '', '', ''),
(65, 1, 'Lindys Pro Baseball', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe insiders guide to the season. Profiling players as well as team analysis'', position by position.\n', '', '', ''),
(66, 1, 'Lindys Pro Basketball', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPreseason NBA magazine; includes team previews and features.\n', '', '', ''),
(67, 1, 'Ozon', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nOZON is an urban fashion magazine. This is an innovative publication with strong editorial content and intriguing imagery, reflecting the mood of the moment through the world of urban youth culture, fashion, music, art and design. OZON focuses on the newest tendencies, mixing both men s and women s lifestyles. OZON magazine has been active in and reported about the international urban culture centres since 1996 ', '', '', ''),
(68, 1, 'Girl Time Presents One Direction 13', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nWe know you LOVED the 50% extra pages in the last issue, so guess what...it''s here to stay! This issue we''ve managed to cram in Harry and Liam''s tour of Machu Picchu, all the latest One Direction ''Where We Are'' Tour pictures, plus everything else One Direction!\n\nWe also have tour dates and news on The Vamps and 5 Seconds of Summer, including the first pull-out poster of 5SOS!\n\nWhat could be better you ask? Well we''ve also managed to squeeze in Pharrell Williams, Little Mix, Miley Cyrus, Selena Gomez and a WHOLE lot more! Make sure you get your copy now!\n', '', '', ''),
(69, 1, 'Girl Time Presents One Direction Issue 9', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n2013 has been all about One Direction and our latest issue is perfect for any Directioner! Packed full with all the latest on Niall, Liam, Harry, Zayn and Louis, their premiere''s, after parties, engagements, football appearances, new girlfriends and more! Plus all the latest news, reviews and of course a 1D quiz, what more could you ask for? Get your copy now!\n', '', '', ''),
(70, 1, 'Girl Time Presents One Direction 12', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nIt’s finally here! The latest issue of One Direction by Girl Time Presents, and guess what? We have 50% MORE pages! Now you have absolutely no excuse not to be completely up to date with everything One Direction, plus we’ve even managed to squeeze in some Little Mix, The Vamps, Selena Gomez, and 5 Seconds of Summer!! And that’s not all, the mag is still jam packed with all your other favourites, news, gossip, quiz and those awesome pull-out posters! So don’t miss this fabulous issue where you get 50% more for the same old price!\n', '', '', ''),
(71, 1, 'Girl Time Presents One Direction &amp; The Hunger Games Issue 10', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nAsk anyone what the two biggest things are in 2013 and they''ll say One Direction and The Hungers Games! And we''ve got BOTH right here!\n\nGirl Time presents brings you ALL the latest news, gossip and info on the biggest boy band in the world, One Direction! Check out their latest song, Story Of My Life, plus all you need to know about 1D Day, tour dates and future releases!\n\nNot only do we have your favourite five, we also have all the stars from The Hunger Games: Catching Fire! Get to know Katniss, Peeta and Gale, plus other tributes and cast members! This issue is still packed with all your favourites, news, pull-out posters and our popular quiz! Get your copy today!\n', '', '', ''),
(72, 1, 'Girl Time Presents One Direction 11', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nFrom 3D movie''s to a whole day dedicated to them, One Direction seem to have dominated 2013! Make sure you haven''t miss a thing with the latest Girl Time magazine! Packed with all the latest news and gossip, plus Midnight Memories'' track reviews, all the details from 1D Day, Zayn''s stag party, McBusted, Little Mix and so much more. We still have all your favourites, with a pull-out poster section and 1D quiz! Get your copy today!\n', '', '', ''),
(73, 1, 'Girl Time Presents One Direction 5', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAre you a true Directioner? Want to know more about Niall, Liam, Zayn, Harry and Louis? Then this is the magazine for you! Packed fill of posters of your favourite five, plus news, quiz, girlfriends and much, much more! Also includes a pull out poster section. Grab your copy now!\n', '', '', ''),
(74, 1, 'Girl Time Presents One Direction 6', '', '', '', ''),
(75, 1, 'Girl Time Presents One Direction Issue 8', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThis is the BEST magazine EVER! ON SALE NOW! Get all the latest on One Direction, celebrate their 3 BEST years together, their BEST song ever, their BEST tattoo''s and much, much more! Packed full of news, features, posters and quiz! With all your favourite popstars, One Direction, Little Mix fashion, Union J, Olly Murs, Selena Gomez, Miley Cyrus and MORE! Includes as always, a pull-out poster section!\n', '', '', ''),
(76, 1, 'Girl Time Presents One Direction Issue 9', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n2013 has been all about One Direction and our latest issue is perfect for any Directioner! Packed full with all the latest on Niall, Liam, Harry, Zayn and Louis, their premiere''s, after parties, engagements, football appearances, new girlfriends and more! Plus all the latest news, reviews and of course a 1D quiz, what more could you ask for? Get your copy now!\n', '', '', ''),
(77, 1, 'Girl Time Presents Summer Time Special', '&lt;p&gt;FROM THE PUBLISHER This summer is off to a sizzling start with all your favourite stars jammed into one magazine! Want to know more about The Wanted? Mix it up with Little Mix, Join Union J and make sure you Come and Get It from Selena. It''s all here! Plus One Direction news and gossip and hot, hot, hot posters!! Also includes quiz, tour dates, fashion, news, quiz and pull-out poster section!&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '', '', ''),
(78, 1, 'Snow-Search Japan', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLet Snow-search Japan take you on an incredible journey, uncovering over 70 resorts and telling you the best places to visit no matter what your style of skiing or riding is.\n\nCombine this with expansive reviews of the ski towns and major gateway cities, plus culture, food and language guides, and you have the most comprehensive book on skiing and snowboarding in Japan ever produced.\n\nFrom the makers of the critically acclaimed World Snowboard Guide, comes the first book in a new series of guidebooks, focused upon independent reviews with meticulous detail, written by professional writers, snowsport experts and knowledgeable locals.\n\nFEATURES\n\n•A5 size, 256 pages full in colour\n•Country, area and city maps\n•In-depth resort reviews and piste maps\n•Hundreds of exclusive colour photographs\n•Access town / city reviews\n•Comprehensive travel guide\n•Language and culture guide\n•Backcountry information\n•Working and doing a season in Japan\n', '', '', ''),
(79, 1, 'Rally Race Technology', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSnow, gravel, tarmac: today’s rally car has to be capable of coping with a huge variety of terrain. Where racecars are engineered to exploit the billiard table smooth surfaces of today’s racetracks, the rally car has to be far more versatile. It has to cope with some of the most demanding environments in motorsport and to endure not hours but days of gruelling competition. Rally Race Technology opens up this fascinating world of engineering for a global sport that makes demands like no other. Never has the rally car been more deeply analysed as we provide a unique insight into a world where the engineering is nothing if not radical.\n\nIntro: THE EDITOR - Rally technology is in rude health\n· Grid - The latest news from the world of rally\n· Dossier: HYUNDAI I20 WRC - Lawrence Butcher talks to Michel Nandan about Hyundai’s rookie WRC racer\n· In-conversation: FX DEMAISON - VW’s WRC project manager on the challenges of the WRC\n· Profile: LDM CITROEN DS3 WRX - UK racer Liam Doran’s DS3 rallycross machine examined\n· Focus: CORNERS - Jon Scoltock investigates the state of the art in rally car suspension and brakes\n· Digest: TOYOTA GT86 CS-R3 - Toyota coupe sees a welcome return of RWD to rallying\n· Digest: JRM GROUP N IMPREZA - What goes into creating a modern Group N racer\n· Digest: PRODRIVE GOLF SCRC - How did Prodrive develop an all-new rally car in only four months?\n· In-conversation: CHRIS WILLIAMS - Lawrence Butcher talks to M-Sport’s Chris Williams about the company’s latest developments\n· Insight: TYRES - Rally tyre technology explained\n· Digest: 911 GT3 RGT - Jon Scoltock looks at the development of the latest Tuthill developed Porsche 911 to hit the rally stages\n· Tech review: DRIVER AIDS - How technology is revolutionising the driver/co-driver environment\n· PS: THE LAST HURRAH - Lancia’s divine 037 remembered\n', '', '', ''),
(80, 1, 'Bernoulli', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Bernoulli Magazine?\n\nIf you love extreme engineering sports like Formula One and NASCAR, a subscription to Bernoulli magazine offers you a great way to learn all about the processes involved in creating these incredible motors. Bernoulli covers all the latest developments in race car engineering, with news from the fields of aerodynamics, wind tunnel design and operation. You can also read great features on race testing instrumentation, learn how vehicle design is used to optimise performance at the very highest level, and get insights into the world of automobile aerodynamics from leading professionals in the field.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBERNOULLI is a journal that explores in unprecedented depth the theory and practice of road and race car aerodynamics.\n\nIts incisive content includes road and race car aero design and development studies and insights into wind tunnel design and operation, the use of CFD and on-track aero testing techniques.\n\nClearly, Bernoulli is essential reading for all involved in the operation of wind tunnels, wind tunnel developers and suppliers of rolling roads, instrumentation and flow visualisation technology. It is equally vital for model makers and testing service providers and for suppliers of CFD software and design and manufacturing software.\n', '', '', ''),
(81, 1, 'Fieldsports: Essential Guide To Game Guns', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe Fieldsports Essential Guide to Game Guns showcases 148 pages of the finest guns from both the UK and the Continent, the gunmaking process and advice from top instructors on choosing a suitable gun.\n\nThis special edition of Fieldsports studies some of the premium gunmakers and their craft: James Purdey &amp; Sons, Boss &amp; Co, Holland &amp; Holland, Browning, Beretta, Boxall &amp; Edmiston and Perazzi. Chris Batha puts a selection of high bird guns to the test at Brigands, discovers the artistry behind the making of a Best gun is a truly fascinating display of intricate hand craftsmanship, and addresses the side-by-side versus over-under debate.\n\nPlus: Richard Rawlingson considers the vast over-under options, the world''s most expensive guns, the revival of the hammer gun and the Fieldsports 1st XI, there is something for every Shot or shooting enthusiast within these pages.\n', '', '', ''),
(82, 1, 'Fieldsports: The World''S Ultimate Fly Fishing Destinations', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nWhether it''s searching the flats for a Bahaman bonefish, hunting trophy trout in New Zealand or doing battle with mighty Atlantic salmon in Norway or Russia that gets your heart racing, our bumper fly fishing guide will take you there. Featuring 22 of the world''s finest fresh and saltwater destinations and with indispensable fishing tips, travel advice, tackle recommendations and stunning photography, this special 148-page edition of Fieldsports is not to be missed.\n\nBoasting outstanding photography and copy from the likes of Matt Harris, Henry Gilbey, Tarquin Millington-Drake, Gerhard Laubscher, Paul Procter, David Profumo, Orri Vigfusson and Brian O''Keefe, the quality of production will be of the highest standards.\n', '', '', ''),
(83, 1, 'Alternative Race Technology', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nMotorsport is undergoing a revolution, the most substantial of its long history. Widespread concern over consumption of fossil fuel and greenhouse gas emissions have led the industry to exploration of alternative fuels and hybrids and even all-electric vehicles. Motorsport is following suit, to the extent that alternative fuelled hybrids have already won prestigious events against conventional racecars. Alternative Race Technology is a new addition to High Power Media''s Race Technology Report stable, dedicated to the analysis of the new technologies that are starting to change the face of motorsport. The future is here now; explore its exciting novelties through this unique technical publication!\n\nIntro:\n· THE EDITOR - A new age of racing dawns · Grid - The latest technical news from the alternative racing world\n· Insight: ALTERNATIVE FUELS - John Coxon recalls a decade of experimentation with motorsport propellants, from diesels through alcohols and gases to batteries\n· Insight: INNOVATION AND REGULATION - How do leading hybrid and EV engineers expect alternative motorsport technology to develop in the future?\n· Focus: ENERGY STORAGE - As electric vehicles in motorsport become more widespread, David Cooper examines the energy storage options\n· Profile: EV100 DRAG BIKE - Lead chassis designer and rider Rob Moon explains what’s gone into the development of this contender for the quarter-mile record\n· Profile: JAGUAR C-X75 - Lawrence Butcher talks to the companies involved in the design and development of this hybrid supercar\n· Profile: FORZE FUEL CELL RACER - Delft University’s development of a full-sized EV racecar has entailed finding some innovative solutions. Lawrence Butcher reports\n· Focus: ELECTRIC MOTORS - Jon Scoltock highlights the key issues when designing an electric/ hybrid powertrain and integrating it into a race vehicle\n· Profile: FORMULA E - Formula E’s success will hinge on whether the technology can provide a decent race experience and therefore whether the public will support it. Richard Jordan reports\n· Insight: FLYBRID FLYWHEEL - Matthew Grant charts the development of Flybrid’s pioneering KERS technology, and assesses its potential for motorsport\n· Insight: HYDROGEN PRACTICALITIES - Hydrogen holds a lot of promise as an automotive fuel but, as Phil Barker explains, various obstacles have to be overcome first\n· PS - There is no such thing as a new idea\n', '', '', ''),
(84, 1, 'So It Goes', '&lt;p&gt;FROM THE PUBLISHER SO IT GOES is an international biannual arts and current affairs magazine that features original voices across film, music, art, photography and journalism. It promotes more imagination and less advertising in print. The Issue.2 cover feature sees indie film queen and star of Frances Ha, Greta Gerwig, shot by fashion legend Helena Christensen. Also included in the ‘Actors’ section is heartthrob of a generation Adam Driver from hit US TV show Girls’, set to explode in the upcoming Coen Brothers film, Inside Llewyn Davis. Elsewhere, there is a mix of established names and vibrant new voices. Music legends Gilles Peterson and Edward Sharpe and the Magnetic Zeros, king of New York street photography Saul Leiter and Drive director Nicolas Winding Refn are all interviewed. There are also a series of portraits of model-actress Clara Paget while visionary artist Richard Mosse’s infra-red photos of the Congo confuse and shock. Readers will find travel journalism from Oslo, Cartagena, Burma and a West African pygmy village. More than just an arts magazine, the second issue of SO IT GOES exclusive reportage includes a haunting travelogue on West African voodoo; a fly-on-the-wall exposé of life in the Flying Squad – London’s armed response unit; and a personal, time-capsule letter to a future digital child. In the Latest Issue: Two covers, the same but new So It Goes. - acclaimed Irish actor Cillian Murphy shot by Vassilis Karidis, one of the leading men in world cinema (Dark Knight, Inception, 28 Days Later) and British actress Imogen Poots (Knight of Cups, Look of Love) - directors Wes Anderson (Grand Budapest Hotel) and Terry Gilliam (Monty Python, Fear and Loathing) with original illustrations - musicians including Canadian prodigy Black Atlass, London''s blissful SOHN and LA''s new vanguard Guy Blakeslee shot by Eliot Lee-Hazel - world-famous Magnum photographer Bruce Davdison, revered visual artist John Stezaker and breakthrough FOAM exhibitor Heikki Kaski - a fashion story with model of the moment Camille Rowe shot by Guy Aroch as well as modern skater pin-up and emblem of cool Dylan Rieder shot on Venice Beach - journalism on ill-starred Haiti, artist colonies in Naoshima, everyday life in Syria, Venetian fishermen and the way that we digest war photography&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '', '', ''),
(85, 1, 'V&amp;Oak', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nV&amp;OAK is a bi-annual magazine devoted to vintage, handmade and upcycled style.\n\nV&amp;OAK stands for Vintage &amp; One of A Kind, and the team here selectively curates each issue to only include the very best in unique fashion, interiors, weddings, and everything in between.\n\nThe 196-page magazine is your handbag-sized guidebook to living a chic life. Our second issue (Spring/Summer 2014) is packed full of inspiring images and articles. In your next copy of V&amp;OAK, you will find:\n\n- Our interview with Dawn O''Porter, presenter of This Old Thing, Channel 4''s upcoming show all about vintage!\n-Over 200 timeless vintage fashion pieces available to buy right now.\n-A handy full-page stockist list packed tight with the very best vintage and handmade retail websites and boutiques.\n-Fascinating articles that shine a light on how fashion and beauty has evolved over the years.\n-Four breathtaking fashion shoots, each with its own unique spin on vintage style.\n-Wedding tips and suppliers to help make your Big Day truly one of a kind.\n-Stunning properties available to buy right now\n– and the perfect handcrafted and vintage homewares to fill them with!\n- Our interview with Drew Pritchard, the decorative antique dealer star of Salvage Hunters on Quest.\n-Comprehensive listings of over 200 of the biggest and best vintage fairs and festivals taking place in the UK this year.\n\nSubscribe now to receive an issue packed with all these and more every 6 months direct to your door.\n', '', '', ''),
(86, 1, 'Hope Street', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHope St is a new biannual publication focusing on the latest fashion, art and trends.\n\nOur magazine is driven by strong editorials, our love of cool edgy girls, weird looking boys and bold iconic images; daring to be different, but always a beautiful reflection of youth culture in our celebration of new and upcoming designers and artists. The magazine is aimed at the fashion conscious market aged between 18 and 36.\n\nOur readers range from those in the fashion industry to those editorial addicts following the trends.\n\nOur readers are consumers of niche and luxury branding, trendy Londoners looking for the new and different must have. We offer our advertisers a unique opportunity to be seen in a new and exciting fashion publication.\n', '', '', ''),
(87, 1, 'Under The Influence', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nUnder the Influence has been implementing creative collaborations to produce highly inspired, influential commissions and projects through which to communicate the disciplines of fashion, photography, design, writing, art and music at their purest level, without the constraints and filters of mainstream mass marketing\n', '', '', ''),
(88, 1, 'Fireworks', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Fireworks magazine provides information, news and views about fireworks; includes nostalgic pictures of fireworks of the past and stunning display pictures. History and nostalgia feature in articles as well as the information you need to use fireworks. Recognised by the firework trade, articles are authoritative and written by the best writers. Fireworks magazine has been supplying information to enthusiasts and the trade since 1982. Regular features include... Information: legislation updates, investigative editorial; news from around the world; essential advice; history and nostalgia, including nostalgic pictures, many in colour, throughout the magazine; an annual directory of UK firework companies, how to contact them and what they provide; letters; reviews of books, videos, DVDs etc.; cartoons and fun. Britain''s premier pyrotechnist has praised Fireworks. In his book, Fireworks: Principles and Practice, Rev. Ronald Lancaster makes the following reference to Fireworks: ''I am grateful to... John Bennett, the Editor of the excellent U.K. magazine Fireworks. This magazine has done so much to encourage an interest in fireworks and to keep some of the history intact’.\n', '', '', ''),
(89, 1, 'Noi Se', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNOI.SE is a magazine which resisted the banality and glibness of the glossies, and yet also resiled from the cool for cool''s sake ethos espoused by independents preferring instead to interpret beauty, through an eclectic mix of fashion, culture and design. ', '', '', ''),
(90, 1, 'Papier Mache', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPapier   Mache  A very cute children s magazine  is a magazine full of children s fashion and things to make. Originally launched as an online magazine, from issue No5 this much celebrated publication will be available in print for the very first time. Papier Mache is a magazine that will inspire and deliver some fantastic clothes designs but will also give ideas for decorating their room and just about anything fashionable for younger children. ', '', '', ''),
(91, 1, 'Highlights Plus', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHighlights Plus, a bi-annual magazine for independent hairdressers. It keeps you updated on all aspects of running a business and of changes in the law as and when they occur. It reports on new products, offers sound technical advice, advises on new treatments you may like to offer to your clients. ', '', '', ''),
(92, 1, 'Oyster', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nOyster is an Australian style magazine featuring fashion, music, film and art, as well as exclusive international fashion editorial. Oyster showcases the work of leading photographers and young up-and-coming talent from around the world, and is renowned for its avant-garde approach to style.\n', '', '', ''),
(93, 1, 'And Men Plus', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAND MEN Plus is a hair fashion magazine which acknowledges a market as yet undeveloped and unrealised, despite the interest in men''s fashion and lifestyle.\n\nYour Subscription will begin with the next available issue. Please expect delivery in the next 4-6 weeks.\n', '', '', ''),
(94, 1, 'Kurv', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nKurv is a high quality glossy, mens &amp; womens fashion, arts, beauty and culture magazine.\n\nStunning international fashion photography. Kurv focuses on providing readers with current trends within the fashion, beauty &amp; arts world.\n', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `oc_product_description` (`product_id`, `language_id`, `name`, `description`, `meta_description`, `meta_keyword`, `tag`) VALUES
(95, 1, 'Crust', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCRUST is an editorial project created by stylist and photographer and a list of contri-butors.\n\nThe magazine has been created out of a common obsession and passion for putting fashion in perspective..\n\nWhile working in a world so much concerned about first impressions and often objectionable topics, it shows people that it’s only a picture, it’s only clothes, it’s only random subjects..\n\nBut yet, (and often forgotten, over¬seen, or neglected by some) putting them together, they can melt into a one-of-a-kind view without any restrictions or boundaries. .\n\nBy combining visual arts (graphic design, collage, illustrations, painting) with interviews and articles from young creatives who share the same vision on these topics, creating a new sense of imag\n', '', '', ''),
(96, 1, 'Misc', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMISC is a collection of posts over the past twenty-four months from internet blog Innovation Playground. The content is organized around four key concepts: Movement / Intuition / Structure / Complexity. It s a magazine about art. It s a magazine about design. It s a magazine about business. So when does a blog become a magazine? It is quite amazing that blogs can bridge the gap between tangible and virtual, centralized and networked. Many popular blogs have become a large part of the streaming information that pushes the boundaries between media forms. How do theories of medium specificity (determinations of traits that define art, photography, and games) differentiate blogs from other existing modes of representation. ', '', '', ''),
(97, 1, 'Private Islands', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPRIVATE ISLANDS is the world s only publication devoted exclusively to luxury private island real estate. Extraordinary properties for the independent, entrepreneurial personality, those who want to make their mark. This is the essential guide book to purchasing, developing and selling private islands. An invaluable resource for the discerning real estate investor. Each issue features a select collection of over 60 islands for sale worldwide.\n', '', '', ''),
(98, 1, 'Hobo Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHOBO MAGAZINE is a bi-annual, avant-garde magazine. Through collections of essays and photo stories, HOBO interviews celebrities and other media figures.\n', '', '', ''),
(99, 1, 'Frische', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFRISCHE is a way of life. It’s a subculture for the young and young at heart. It’s for any fashion junkie who believes making a statement is more exciting than being conventional. FRISCHE is totally into creativity, freedom and individuality, a magazine that wants to inspire and be inspired.\n\nFRISCHE is an independent self-published digital/print magazine reaching out to the style crazed 18-39 year old age demographic. 60/40 ratios for women/men are drawn to its edgy subculture.\n\nFRISCHE is dedicated in producing a primarily fashion (bridged with its bold style) magazine through rebellious fashion editorials featuring women and men’s high fashion mixed with contemporary labels and vintage pieces. Furthermore, and of course, FRISCHE will always showcase the young, new and fresh designers of this brave generation. The editorials are generated through both FRISCHE team efforts and international contributor\n', '', '', ''),
(100, 1, 'Glassbook', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBeauty as Art. It showcases creativity and innovation in fashion through outstanding visual and written content.\n\nGLASSbook’s content blur the lines between fashion and art. Achieved not only through extraordinary imagery, but also through incorporating illustrations and graphics, written word and poetry.\n\nGLASSbook features both up-and-coming, and established artists through personal interviews. Artists who include but are not limited to, designers, illustrators, musicians, and photographers.\n\nGLASSbook is not afraid of the controversial, or to push boundaries. Constantly challenging what makes up a fashion magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(101, 1, 'Dansk', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSince the very first issue DANSK Magazine has inspired, informed and captivated a target audience of trendsetters and trend followers across the globe.\n\nDANSK is Denmark¹s first international fashion magazine and represents unsurpassed graphic creativity, and presents an exclusive and stimulating look at current fashion and lifestyle trends.\n\nIn collaboration with some of the world¹s leading photographers, models and movers and shakers in the fashion and lifestyle industry, DANSK passionately and actively seeks the most exciting, innovative and groundbreaking current fashion and lifestyle trends.\n', '', '', ''),
(102, 1, 'Fat Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFAT Magazine is an innovative Scandinavian magazine with an international outlook and global scope.\n\nFAT stands for Fashion, Art, – contemporary genres that offer mutual inspiration.\n\nFAT magazine seeks to challenge all three creative disciplines from a style and fashion perspective focusing on their correlations and commonalities.\n\nThe magazine will feature internationally acclaimed creative contributors who are to offer new inspiring visions and quirky takes on the arts, graphic design and fashion.\n', '', '', ''),
(103, 1, 'Revs Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nREVS is a publication that brings together outstanding professionals as well as up and coming reckless talents. All artists works corated with strong concepts and themes that reflect a contemporary view on fashion, style and attitude, REVS magazine does in fact appeal to a broad public, it stands by strong imagery and powerful visual ideas, it all comes together by the guidance of a talented and experienced group of art directors that bring honest stories of real people and their real lives. The aim of REVS magazine is to inspire and encourage you to pursue a more inclusive future in fashion as the art form, not only the industry.\n', '', '', ''),
(104, 1, 'Ssaw', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSSAW is a fashion magazine that introduces the best of Finnish fashion to a truly international audience. The Finnish fashion scene is at an interesting stage where the younger generations are taking the reins aiming directly internationally and SSAW will be at the forefront. SSAW brings you some truly stunning photography, interesting articles fleshing out the inspirations, interests and influences of the featured designers. Produced to the highest quality SSAW will be truely influential and is sure to appeal to any fashionista!\n', '', '', ''),
(105, 1, 'Blush Dream', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBlush magazine is a fun and informative magazine for women.\n\nBlush magazine is a modern woman’s must have as it includes tips on fashion, romance, health and beauty.\n', '', '', ''),
(106, 1, 'Clam', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCLAM is a unisex magazine whose goal is to promote creativity, concepts and ideas in fashion, architecture, the arts, travel and design. These themes are approached in two main areas: lifestyle and trends. Each subject is part of an original and conceptual artistic direction. The concepts are presented through the expression of artists and creators from very different horizons. The place accorded to image is central: CLAM is unusual as it creates a constant surprise for the readers. Experimentation is one of the characteristics of CLAM which explains its layout: always changing, never fixed. Each issue of CLAM is designed as a totally new magazine, it encourages creative reflection. ', '', '', ''),
(107, 1, 'Lofficiel Voyage Fr', '&lt;p&gt;FROM THE PUBLISHER L''OFFICIEL VOYAGE is a French travelling magazine.&lt;/p&gt;\n', '', '', ''),
(108, 1, 'Dealer Deluxe', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDEALER DELUXE is a French magazine which covers everything you need to know about luxury goods.\n', '', '', ''),
(109, 1, 'Vogue Hommes Int Fr', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVOGUE HOMMES INTERNATIONAL (FR) is the fashion bible for the man of the 90''s, with over 200 pages packed full of the latest fashions, with full colour photography throughout.\n', '', '', ''),
(110, 1, 'Vogue Hommes International Mode', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVOGUE HOMMES INTERNATIONAL MODE is a fashion bible for men. It has over 200 pages packed with the latest fashions, on its full colour glossy pages. This is a high-quality magazine, a must-have for the fashion conscious man.\n', '', '', ''),
(111, 1, 'Numero Homme', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNumero Homme is a magazine in contrast with the traditional men''s magazines. Looking to appeal to men with a pointed and keen interest in art, fashion, beauty, photography, design and architecture.\n', '', '', ''),
(112, 1, 'Decoration Internationale', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDecoration Internationale is a unique vision of architecture and design. Bilingual French and English, Decoration International invites you to discover the most innovative achievements in international decoration.\n\nDecoration Internationale includes photographs and text on interior design, as well as architecture, from all around the world.\n', '', '', ''),
(113, 1, 'Double', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDOUBLE is a French and English language fashion and lifestyle magazine. Inside readers will find unusual topical features on subjects such as absurd decision making, grevious bodily harm, the new breed of random text generators, the art of architecture and more . In addition DOUBLE features fashion spreads, jewellery accessories and interviews with high profile names from within the industry such as Karl Lagerfeld\n', '', '', ''),
(114, 1, 'French Revue De Modes', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\nFrench Revue de Modes is a high-end fashion magazine geared toward the luxury market. It features the most prestigious design companies, photographers and models that the fashion world has to offer.\n\nIts editorial team features names synonymous with the top French fashion magazines and fashion industry.\n\nFrench Revue de Modes is published bi-annually to coincide with the launch of the Spring and Autumn Collections.\n', '', '', ''),
(115, 1, 'Encens', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe focus of ENCENS is on fashion as an artform from the perspective of the Designers rather than the current trends.\n\nIt offers to readers to unlock the best from both the exciting worlds of fashion and art.\n\nMoving from present to past, creating maps of the hallmarks that captivate our times as well as constantly referring to the aesthetics of the past that still have a major influence.\n\nENCENS stands for an independent and long-term approach.\n', '', '', ''),
(116, 1, 'Ad Collector', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThis French interior design magazine (with English translations alongside French text) takes a deep seated passion for interior decoration and encapsulates it within this tightly bound tome.\n\nTwo hundred pages of stylish wisdom furnished alongside lavish photography and illustrations of all the best home design tips from the masters rest neatly between its twin covers. Alongside help on selecting the nuts and bolts of your interior design plans, from wallpapers to rugs and fabrics, is input from AD Collector’s own top 100 designers list on the most chic and suave layouts ever devised!\n', '', '', ''),
(117, 1, 'Antidote', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHovering between a book and a fashion magazine, Antidote is a precious object to be kept collected: 360 pages with a hard cover.\n\nAntidote is a bi-annual fashion magazine with an international scope, designed to build a semestral literary and artistic landmark around a specific topic from the world of fashion. A new way of interpreting the fashion scene, looking at it from a timeless perspective that marks a complete contrast to the ephemeral nature of fashion press of today.\n\nThus, the team at Antidote magazine has taken the concept of icon to highlight it in the context of each one of its subjects. Not only women, but also accessories, perfume, beauty and other fashion icons.\n', '', '', ''),
(118, 1, 'Vogue Collections', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThis is a twice yearly collection of fashion show/designer reviews from Vogue.\n\nThis magazine is from France although it''s less about the written word and more the thousands of fashion images from catwalks around the world.\n\nIf you are looking for inspiration and need to keep up to date with what is happening at the fashion shows, Vogue Collections magazine really is the ultimate reference publication\n\nVogue Collections is a must to subscribe to for anyone in the industry\n', '', '', ''),
(119, 1, 'Purple Fashion Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPURPLE FASHION is a French fashion, art and culture magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(120, 1, 'Show Details World', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSHOW DETAILS WORLD is a Magazine that focuses on catwalk and fashion models and shows the latest fashion instead of just focusing on one designer.\n', '', '', ''),
(121, 1, 'Boat Exclusive', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPrinted in English, BOAT EXCLUSIVE combines yacht expertise with great writing: the best water sports writers and correspondents from seven countries provide an in-depth coverage that is unrivalled in the market.\n\nThe team provides exclusive coverage of construction projects, brand-new yachts, developments and people. Technology, design and background studies are presented compellingly and informatively in a style that transcends pure lifestyle reporting.\n\nThe magazine''s print and paper quality make the photos and stories a feast for the eyes. Seeing the exciting world of super yachts presented on the pages of BOAT EXCLUSIVE is almost as good as experiencing them in person.\n', '', '', ''),
(122, 1, 'Husk', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHUSK magazine is controversial. Today s youth are deadened by the thoughtless, insatiable banter from modern media. Through taboo subjects and gutsy controversy, we hope to spark a conversation among those interested in fashion and art. To hell with one-way conversations with Anna Wintour. Do away with boring blog posts and front row fakes. HUSK will sting the sleep out of any reader and bring a fresh quality that cannot be ignored. We are relevant, we are testing, but above all, we are controversy in all its forms. FEATURING: Alexander McQueen, Blandine Bardeau, Michael Schmidt, Léos Carax, Chickenshit Clothing, Fabric London, Toddla T, Daniel Sannwald, Hamansutra, Adriano Sack, Nils Dunkel, My Girlfriend is better than Yours, Frittenbude, UhOh, Marquis de Sade, baby!, uvm\n', '', '', ''),
(123, 1, 'Gq Style German', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe popular mens style magazine in German.\n', '', '', ''),
(124, 1, 'Nomas', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNOMAS is a black and white photographic album, enriched with the words and the sacred thoughts of great poets, authors and travellers.\n\nInspired by the adventurous spirit of the nomadic culture, NOMAS aspires to have no fixed residence and to continually move from place to place, as a true wanderer, searching for Life itself. .\n\nNOMAS will be in a constant search of the Road and it’s ephemeral yet so fascinating scenes and curiosities. This Bi Annual publication will be a collectors MUST have for those with a passion for creative free spirited photography\n', '', '', ''),
(125, 1, 'Naked But Safe', '&lt;p&gt;FROM THE PUBLISHER Naked But Safe is a new type of magazine! 100% recycled eco friendly paper, CO2 Emission free, airbrush free, relevant and natural. This is a new type of photographic art magazine featuring real photos and real illustrations from emerging artists, masters, past and present. Naked But Safe does not carry any naked body photos, Naked But Safe just shows photographic images in their natural state, no make-up, no airbrushing, no additives! Photography in Naked But Safe comes from the world of Art, Design and Fashion.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '', '', ''),
(126, 1, 'Image In Progress', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nImage in Progress is an innovative magazine where the themes outlined above are discussed in an original way and in a manner that appeals to a demanding international audience, a group for which the art of contemporary photography is a passion, a business, a choice, a medium, a philosophy and a cult to be preserved through collections. ', '', '', ''),
(127, 1, 'Vogue Complementos', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA title from Italy. The latest fashions, styles and products\n', '', '', ''),
(128, 1, 'Tar Magazine', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTAR is an English-language magazine from Italy that is proud of its Western identity, with features from across the globe.\n\nIt is published by a ‘bunch of angry dreamers’ who are lovers of art, science and peace…. And well-connected worldwide.\n\nTAR believes in the importance of aesthetics, science and ethics. It covers a wide range of subjects including art, architecture, design, fashion, science and social responsibility – and how they all come together.\n', '', '', ''),
(129, 1, 'Zoom On Fashion Trends', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe research magazine with its very own way of supplying information to fashion professionals. The colours, inspirations, materials and lines of the macro trends more than a year ahead of the market. In-depth features on sociological themes, tips on colours and trends from major international brands, all the latest trends on the web and the hottest news from the sector. It is a useful work tool and an invaluable travel companion as your collection is put together.\n', '', '', ''),
(130, 1, 'Previous', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPREVIOUS For the first time ever, a magazine presents the public what only a selected group of buyers could admire.With it´s far foreward looking insights and images featuring the creations of the most prestigious international brands, PREVIOUS will elate and inspire fashion professionals months before seeing their shows. A large format, high-quality photos, enlargements of the finest details as well as an introductory text on trends and colours of every brand make PREVIOUS an extremely useful working tool for designers and creatives but especially for buyers looking for the first guidelines of the season\n', '', '', ''),
(131, 1, 'Book Moda', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBOOK MODA is full of exclusive fashion photos, the most important labels, the hottest trends and the coolest accessories from the world''s exclusive runways, including New York, London, Tokyo, Dusseldorf, Barcelona, Madrid, Paris and Milan. In addition every issue of BOOK MODA is chock-full of all the latest news and information.\n', '', '', ''),
(132, 1, 'The Gentlewoman', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The Gentlewoman Magazines From Abroad?\n\nThis magazine not only brings you the latest in modern fashion and design, but it''s also brimming with purpose and ambition.\n\nFeaturing famous and admirable women from across the globe in compassionate interviews with beautiful, original photographs, this magazine''s cover stars have included everyone from Adele and Beyoncé, to Angela Lansbury.\n\nThis great mix of forward-thinking independent journalism with glamour, personality and warmth, means you''ll be itching to join in the conversation on the way women live, work and dress.\n\nSubscribe to The Gentlewoman magazine for a bi-annual dose of intelligent escapism aimed at the independent and affluent woman.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCheck out The Gentlewoman, a new womens magazine that heralds a new decade for female personal style and journalism of the highest quality. The Gentlewoman is launched by the acclaimed founders of Fantastic Man and edited by Penny Martin, creative directed by Jop Van Bennekom, with fashion direction from Jonathan Kaye. The Gentlewoman is an elegant publication for and about women of note. The Gentlewoman challenges the traditional representation of female style with more sophisticated and in-depth oriented content. With its intelligence, quick wit and independent eye, The Gentlewoman offers something entirely new to its readership, something the womens market has long been missing. The readers are more ambitious, confident, widely traveled and fiercely proud of their financial independence. They also have a deep love of fashion, which they display through their own personal style.\n', '', '', ''),
(133, 1, 'Rika Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRIKA this new magazine is shot and edited by and the brain-child of Ulrika Lundgren. It offers an exciting insight into the lives of models as well as inspiration for those who would like to stay in the fashion industry once they have passed their modeling prime, by taking a new route behind the lens, in the showroom, or publication headquarters. Just as the aging actress hopes to someday direct, perhaps the new model dream will be to edit?\n', '', '', ''),
(134, 1, 'Bare', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBARE is a publication which tells you stories about the world in which we all live.\n\nEveryone has a point of view, and the aim of BARE is to both show and speak to its readers about the important things in life – which are both familiar and revealing, but ultimately inspiring.\n\nWhile BARE creators devote much of its energy to certain aspects of modern life such as fashion, culture, art, society, they are by no means restricted by conventions.\n\nBARE is a global journal of fashion, culture and arts dedicated to the beauty of realism and simplicity. The artfully produced publication provides international photographers, artists, stylists and writers a place to explore new ideas with no creative brief, no client, no artifice, no shimmer, no retouch – no rules.\n\nIn these pages, free-form visual and cultural explorations reveal the raw, soulful beauty of bare, unmediated truth.\n', '', '', ''),
(135, 1, 'Hercules', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHERCULES is a male fashion and people magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(136, 1, 'Bon International', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBon International is one of Sweden''s leading fashion magazines.\n\nA contemporary magazine that takes a serious look at innovation and couture fashion aimed at both men and women.\n\nIt discusses in depth the latest trends and up and coming designers to look out for, as well as features and interviews with the industries newest, oldest and most treasured names.\n\nBon also features some striking and potentially shocking artwork, photography and ideas which are analysed closely by expects. We also see the favourite fashion and art collections making their way into the limelight''\n', '', '', ''),
(137, 1, 'Dorade', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDorade is a very high quality photographic art magazine published in Switzerland. Dorade is full of energy and covers art old and new and is produced to the highest quality as can be seen on the media kit. ', '', '', ''),
(138, 1, 'Novembre', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNovembre is a cutting edge, high quality, high profile fashion and art magazine from Switzerland with a monster 256 pages of stunning photography and editorial content published Bi-Annually in June and December. Novembre is a tri-lingual title with editorial in English, French and German making it a truly international magazine. ', '', '', ''),
(139, 1, 'Biker', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBIKER is the sister magazine to Easyriders. BIKER magazine is the ultimate lifestyle magazine for Harley Davidson owners. Readers will find the latest models and the most spectacular customised machines. BIKER also covers many of the Harley shows from around the world. As well as featuring up to date information, BIKER magazine includes great features, reviews, product tests and much more!\n', '', '', ''),
(140, 1, 'Sovereign History Presents', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSovereign History Presents is an exciting read for all World War II enthusiasts and details main information and facts about the war. Each issue will include reviews, people''s perspectives, main personalities in the war and much more!\n\nEvery issue has dozens and dozens of rare photographs, colourfully crisp paintings and meticulously detailed drawings culled from the biggest and best archives in the world.\n\nPrinted on thick, glossy paper, with book-style binding, which allows you to store your collection on your shelves with the rest of your history library.\n', '', '', ''),
(141, 1, 'Bhg Quilt Sampler', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBHG QUILT SAMPLER lists hundreds of delightful shops in North America every year. The top 10 shops for the year contribute exclusive designs to the profile projects.\n', '', '', ''),
(142, 1, 'Wedding-Style', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWedding Style has built an enviable reputation in the wedding industry for creating the platforms for wedding specialists to showcase products and services while offering prospective brides and grooms a multitude of choices, ideas and alternatives for planning their wedding. The magazine has consistently made creativity and innovation its number one priority.\n', '', '', ''),
(143, 1, 'The Fashionisto', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBased in New York City, THE FASHIONISTO was established in 2008 as a website to personally showcase the latest menswear featured in photo shoots as the ultimate buyer’s guide. The website has since grown into a platform for industry insiders, fashionistos and consumers alike! THE FASHIONISTO is an already established brand, with over 24,000 Twitter followers and 20,000 Facebook ‘likes’.\n\nFollowing its successful online launch, its natural progression was to become available in printed format. Working with international talents, the aim of each issue is to capture the season through images that visually stimulate; engaging readers in a way that highlights those fashions that they simply cannot live without.\n', '', '', ''),
(144, 1, 'Pattern Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPATTERN Magazine is a bi-annual FASHION Publication, uniting the Creators &amp; Consumers of Fashion.\n\nAmong the near-infinite world of fashion magazines, PATTERN differentiates by synthesizing its focus on American talent with international Trends &amp; Movement.\n\nPATTERN Magazine loves Fashion - providing style-smart individuals an inclusive, fashion-focused awareness and appreciation.\n\nPATTERN Magazine presents, with style &amp; flair, the singular tastes, style skills &amp; designs of a diverse cross-section of designers, photographers, models, makeup &amp; hair artists, writers and stylists, and everyone in between &amp; beyond!. Showcasing the best of American Fashion &amp; Design.\n', '', '', ''),
(145, 1, 'Esquire Black Book', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEverything the discerning Esquire reader needs to know from bars to shopping\n', '', '', ''),
(146, 1, 'Dossier', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDOSSIER s content draws upon a wide range of subjects, including fashion features, art and photography portfolios, fiction, poetry, critical essays, interviews, recipes, crossword puzzles, articles on film, architecture, music and culinary pursuits.\n', '', '', ''),
(147, 1, 'Pin Up', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe magazine for architectural entertainment from the US.\n', '', '', ''),
(148, 1, 'Tank', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTANK combines cutting edge women''s fashion with world renowned photography providing an artistic look at events in fashion.\n', '', '', ''),
(149, 1, 'Vs Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVs. Magazine is an American high-end fashion and lifestyle magazine published 2 times a year. It is known for featuring some of the most sought-after actresses, celebrities and models and manages to unite luxury fashion with cutting edge design. The magazine stands out in the media landscape with its captivating, cinemascope format and its fresh and visionary take on fashion and pop culture.\n\nEvery issue has four different covers and provides the subscriber with artistic creativity along with a keen sense of style and integrity.\n', '', '', ''),
(150, 1, 'Capricious', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSwedish photographer Sophie Mörner founded CAPRICIOUS MAGAZINE in 2004. This bi-annual publication is dedicated to showcasing emerging fine art photography. Its contributors and subject matter span the globe and it comprises almost entirely of images. Capricious collaborates with guest editors and chooses a new theme for each edition, so the material is never lackluster. Whilst constant change is a primary Capricious trait, there are also definite common visual threads running throughout its history. Capricious has an affinity for a very broad-range of subject matter, from animals, androgyny, opposition, reclaimed life, lust, natural to urban life, intimacy, revolution and nostalgia.\n\nAs a leading fine art photography journal, CAPRICIOUS MAGAZINE occupies a rare and whimsical space between commercial and fashion photography; it operates as both a tool for discovering new talent and as an artists’ oasis.\n', '', '', ''),
(151, 1, 'Dash', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWith some great fashion photography, DASH Magazine is devoted to the fabrication of images, concepts and articles with a high level of depth and aesthetics.\n\nIntended for opinion formers, DASH Magazine is a London-based high fashion editorial, lifestyle, illustration and art print.\n\nStyle, media and the creative industry is what we are, and we are inspirational in our own way. We strive to create an altogether aesthetic experience, where the reader finds his lifestyle needs fulfilled. Buy a single copy of Dash Magazine or a subscription of your desired length. If you choose the current issue before 3pm, we will even send it out the same day, first class\n', '', '', ''),
(152, 1, 'The Mushpit', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTHE MUSHPIT is a ‘teen magazine for grown up girls’ that provides a cynical alternative to women’s monthlies. THE MUSHPIT features real girls with real interests, no fake smiles or stories in this publication. It takes tried and tested content and tailors it to suit its varied audience. Features include agony aunt columns, relationship science and advice, DIY beauty and fashion and of course a ‘hot’ centrehold in every issue.\n\nTHE MUSHPIT reader is forward-thinking, often the first of her friends to try new fashion and beauty ideas. She has individual style and is the trend-setter amongst her peer group. She is inspired by the nostalgia of her youth and likes to use fun products to reflect this. She re-blogs, re-posts and re-tweets, maintaining a constant online presence.\n\nThe editorial team already has a well-established publishing background, contributing regularly to titles that include i-D, Dazed &amp; Confused, POP, Vogue, Nylon….\n\nTHE MUSHPIT provides a platform for both up-and-coming and established London talent. It prides itself on creating a widespread network of like-minded females, worldwide….\n', '', '', ''),
(153, 1, 'We Are Collision', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWE ARE COLLISION is a London based Bi-Annual publication that focuses on the discussion of both fashion and culture. With a bold aesthetic and inquisitive editorial tone, WE ARE COLLISION welcomes its audiences to a new way of thinking, one without limits where anything is attainable.\n\nWE ARE COLLISION delivers news fast and at a time when quick coverage is essential; its up to the minute coverage of fashion and culture events enables it to compete with top brands within the sector.\n\nWE ARE COLLISION is aimed at a fashion-conscious demographic, with the primary target being 18-28 years of age. Its readers aspire to and are proud customers of niche and luxury brands, and are generally looking to pursue careers within fashion and creative industries\n', '', '', ''),
(154, 1, 'Dapper Dan', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDapper Dan is a new, independent proposition in the men s magazine market. Devised and published in Athens, Greece, by an international team in English. Dapper Dan is a bi-annual title focused on fashion, culture and style. In addition to its extensive coverage of the best new products and lines, the magazine will also embody the distinct sensibility of the contemporary menswear scene in its aesthetic and its mood. The magazine will not only to showcase the best photographic, styling and writing talent in fashion, but also reflect the ways in which men make their buying choices   whether obsessing over tailoring de tails or taking inspiration from dapper style icons from down the ages. Dapper Dan s fusion of high-end imagery, carefully selected archive material and real people combine to create a genuinely different and timely title. ', '', '', ''),
(155, 1, 'Out There Style', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nOUT THERE STYLE is the new bi-annual “FASHION SPECIAL” from the publishers of OUT THERE magazine, in response to our audience of rich, cultured and fashion-conscious readers demanding a pure-fashion magazine.\n\nOUT THERE STYLE is a super luxurious, yet cutting-edge consumer fashion journal, published 2 times annually.\n\nSomething truly unique, it is the answer to the unending cliche’s in men’s publishing. We’re all about celebrating the many fascinating expressions of fashion-artculture, delivering strong and creative fashion stories with a strength of voice, great (award-winning) photography, stunning art direction and indepth features.\n\nOur targeted marketing activities involve interacting with our core readers through a range of activities, from live events, to brand partnerships and most importantly, social media - all to raise awareness, drive interest and ultimately deliver readers into stores to purchase.\n', '', '', ''),
(156, 1, 'Exit', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Worlds Only True Art, Fashion, Photography and Travel Bi-Annual Inspirational, aspirational and hugely influential.\n\nEXIT is an exclusive and timeless portfolio of the world s most talented photographers and artists. Since its inception as a leading art, fashion and photography periodical nine years ago, EXIT finds itself uniquely positioned at the forefront of art, design, travel, culture and fashion publishing.\n\nEXIT is a boundless source of passion, creative energy and inspirational works. As much a creative journey for those who contribute as for those who read it, EXIT is wholly unique in this marketplace and as such defies simple genre definitions. It is as challenging and thought-provoking as it is beautiful. A lovingly crafted and luxurious shot of contemporary culture.\n\nEXIT won the award for Best Use Of Photography at the 2010 Magazine Design Awards.\n', '', '', ''),
(157, 1, 'Alvar', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nALVAR is a magazine about style. In addition to fashion editorials, we will be writing about style, culture and society, and how these things interlink.\n\nThough fashion is an important part of ALVAR, we are not just after trends, but something that lasts.\n\nWe aim to dig deeper than your ordinary style magazine, and we always have an opinion.For us, style is so much more than what you wear. It''s how you are and what you believe in. It''s how you see the world; it''s how the world sees you. London and Helsinki are full of wonderful people with inspiring attitudes and unique styles. We want to tell their stories. We are firmly rooted in London, but have a Nordic twist..\n\nWe consider style a huge part of popular culture and want to explore and examine the relationships between fashion and other art forms, as well as find out the inspirations and influences of people that have interesting style and presence.\n', '', '', ''),
(158, 1, 'Vinyl Riot', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVinyl Riot is a women s lifestyle publication focusing in on cutting edge fashion, art and photography. Each issue will focus on a different theme. Vinyl Riot has commissioned a series of photographers, artists, models, bloggers, designers and writers from all over the world to create travel photo diaries and other interesting features staying true to the Vinyl Riot''s youthful and raw aesthetics.\n', '', '', ''),
(159, 1, 'Contributor', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nContributor Magazine creates a world where fashion, life, art and culture are logically combined. The articles all have a personal, slightly dreamy style to them, and they often come across like sections from a short story, a snippet from the writers’ lives.\n\nAside from these lengthy and intriguing pieces, there is a goldmine of striking couture fashion features.\n\nFrom elegant tailoring to utterly mental colour collaborations, anyone could find inspiration from within these pages. There are also interviews with designers, sculptors, actors and even chefs, acupuncturists and bi-polar sufferers. Contributor is unapologetic about every aspect of life, ranging from the ordinary to the downright strange.\n', '', '', ''),
(160, 1, 'The Rutzou Chronicle', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Chronicle is the magazine from renowned Scandinavian fashion house Rützou, a new visual orientated bi-annual publication of the highest quality. The idea behind the magazine is to give something to the creative world that Rützou have been part of for more than a decade by presenting what the editorial team and contributors find interesting within art, photography, people and places.\n', '', '', ''),
(161, 1, 'Assistant', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nASSISTANT is a fashion magazine that covers all realms of fashion – from the past to the present and most importantly it focusses on the future.\n\nThe ‘Assistants’ of the greatest minds and creatives in the fashion world of today are at present standing in the background, but they will without a doubt feature amongst the stars of tomorrow and will be the ones to watch closely. .\n\nASSISTANT uncovers their worlds by discovering and inspiring younger generations (and the not so young) - and the talents that they possess – who aspire to be a part of the fashion industry\n', '', '', ''),
(162, 1, 'Sheer', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSHEER is an independent magazine based in London and will appeal to both female and male readers. The aim is to be a platform to showcase up and coming talent in the form of high-end, high fashion publication and these will be from such areas as Fashion, Photography, Illustration, Art, Music, Film and much more. SHEER will feature new talent from around the globe. SHEER s aim is to be a well-recognised magazine for its quality of visual aesthetics and striking features and the development of its own personal style. ', '', '', ''),
(163, 1, 'I Love Fake', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nI LOVE FAKE Magazine is a bi-annual print magazine, 184 pages thick of fashion, art &amp; culture. We publish upcoming and established artists from around the world in our magazine as well as in our digital playground and online blog and take pride in celebrating the spirit of youth in all its glory. We love working with upcoming as well as established artists &amp; photographers from all over the globe. We are not afraid of experimenting and share a passion for those with a punk rock way of life, or with a Do It Yourself mind-set. We strive to continually represent a fresh batch of raw talent. I LOVE FAKE is proud of publishing the ones who dare to break rules an average of 184 pages, consisting out of exclusive photographic stories, always a handpicked selection of invited contributors. Every issue is given a particular theme. The fashion stories feature classic and vintage designer pieces from high end brands as well as pieces from upcoming designers. We will aim to integrate content with fashion stories by incorporating emerging personalities from the worlds of fashion, film, photography, art, music and models. We publish related interviews with these individuals to present them to our readers. ', '', '', ''),
(164, 1, 'Garagisme', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGaragisme is a graphic art magazine for lovers of cars, a car kulture magazine! Produced to the higest standards on high quality paper, Garagisme contains stunning photographic and excellent editorial content. Garagisme is a car lovers delight and is sure to grace many coffee tables around the world.\n', '', '', ''),
(165, 1, 'Blag', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIntelligent, conversational, inspirational, humourous and down-to-earth long form features. Intimate portfolio style photoshoots. A product that simply cannot live online alone. Think of it as a drama, comedy and documentary all wrapped up in print\n', '', '', ''),
(166, 1, 'Blown', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBLOWN offers a uniquely passionate take on art, fashion, music, contemporary photography and literature. HIDDEN last issue 12/10 sw\n', '', '', ''),
(167, 1, '7Th Man', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n7TH MAN is an already established, high-end luxury men’s fashion magazine dedicated to the style conscious man of today – whose aim is to present an original perspective on the ever-changing landscape of men’s fashion.\n\n7TH MAN seamlessly blends the heart of British style with an injection of the most cutting-edge international design..\n\nThe 7TH MAN is the quintessential cosmopolitan gentleman of today. He is unique in his approach to life with an appreciation for luxury fashion goods. .\n\nWell-travelled, well-educated and cultured, this is a man that likes the finer things in life. .\n\nHe is fashion conscious and aware of his aesthetics and uses the wide range of sources now available to build his stylish and desirable wardrobe..\n\nWHY 7TH MAN? What sets 7TH MAN apart from other publications of this genre is its bold emphasis on imagery, 7 TH MAN takes a unique and sophisticated art-directional approach that appeals to the visual intelligence of the reader on a new and refreshing level.\n', '', '', ''),
(168, 1, 'Industrie', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA magazine dedicated to the culture of fashion. Snapshots of the personalities and the moments which shape our industry. ', '', '', ''),
(169, 1, 'Eclectic', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nECLECTIC is a magazine passionate about discovering and dispensing inspiration through fashion, beauty, art, music and culture. It looks beyond trends to be inspired, and offers a curated view on fashion and lifestyle from diverse sources.\n\nECLECTIC aims to reach an audience that embraces various interests – from the latest runway to up-and-coming independent films, dive bar concerts in Paris to the newest, hip eatery in Berlin… .\n\nECLECTIC features original, insightful content that pushes the boundaries of geography - introducing new designers, stunning editorials, city guides, music, movies, art, original editorials, fashion and beauty features from different corners of the world. .\n\nECLECTIC supports new, up-and-coming talents, with a group of skilled collaborators who are innovative, experimental and outspoken. The goal is to create a platform to give these talents a voice.\n', '', '', ''),
(170, 1, 'Ten Men', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTEN is a high profile mens fashion magazine containing collection previews, gossip, music, books and much more!\n', '', '', ''),
(171, 1, 'Lula', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLULA is created for the real girls of the world who love fashion, music, art, &amp; make believe. LULA is gentle, whimsical and ethereal in tone, mixing high fashion to fall in love with and interviews that feel like late night chats with people you wish you knew.International stylists, photographers, musicians, artists, illustrators and journalists work towards creating a gorgeous magazine that is not only a forum for beautiful work and fresh ideas, but that reads like the honest, funny, and aspirational best friend you dream of. ', '', '', ''),
(172, 1, 'Oak-The Nordic Journal', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nOak is a new Danish magazine with an international aim. The magazine deals with Nordic culture, cuisine, and design and focuses on the Nordic way of life and the people behind it.\n\nThe magazine addresses an international target audience, consisting primarily of women aged 25-45. The printed version will be published biannually in Scandinavia and internationally.\n\nOak – The Nordic Journal is an exclusive printed magazine paying tribute to the authentic life, the lived life, focusing on the people who live in the Nordic countries and inspiring readers with design, interiors, portraits, reports, and culture. Moreover, One of a Kind Journal will contain a Design Directory that selects the 50 top Scandinavian brands in the design and life-style fields\n', '', '', ''),
(173, 1, 'Ten Women', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTEN is a high profile fashion magazine, providing all the gossip from the world of fashion. Featuring the ten must-have make up buys, extracts from best selling novels, top ten essential fashion accessories, male and female fashion spreads and more!\n', '', '', ''),
(174, 1, 'Man About Town', '&lt;p&gt;FROM THE PUBLISHER Man About Town is an independently produced publication that appeals to the confident, intelligent, luxury-conscious man of today. Man About Town is a guide to the season featuring comprehensively detailed, uniquely presented articles, which provide a full, distinctive view of their subjects. The fashion truly matters to the reader and all content is created by the most prominent, contemporary stylists, photographers and journalists. Man About Town is the modern journal for the man who is already trend and news savvy but wants greater depth than other media currently offers.&lt;/p&gt;\n', '', '', ''),
(175, 1, '125', '&lt;p&gt;FROM THE PUBLISHER 125 showcases exciting and innovative work by a cross section of photographers, designers, artists and image-makers. Displaying the inspirational work of new and established talents alike, 125 is exciting and refreshingly diverse. 125 allows readers to experience the best showcase magazine available whilst supporting creative talents across the UK, Europe and the rest of world.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '', '', ''),
(176, 1, 'Infur', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\nINFUR, a world of luxury – a discriminating magazine that picks up and reports on trends, embraces the taste of luxury inherent in even the tiniest detail and strikes the perfect balance between classical and avant-garde, establishment and new establishment in its blend of Luxury Lifestyle ingredients.\n', '', '', ''),
(177, 1, 'Odda', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nODDA is a bi-annual boutique fashion magazine that directly connects aspirational readers with the lifestyle of those at the core of the fashion and creative industries through interviews, artwork, illustrations and reviews.\n\nODDA prides its self on its access to resources of the highest calibre: This allows it to celebrate selections of the most beautiful and inspirational artefacts of contempory luxury.\n\nBased in London but working worldwide, ODDA is truly an international endeavour: With permanent correspondents and creative collaborations in London, Madrid, New York and Paris.\n', '', '', ''),
(178, 1, 'Self Service', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSELF SERVICE is a fashion and lifestyle magazine that covers styling, writing, photography, graphics. Using a variety of typography and layouts in order to present an adventurous and unusual publication.\n', '', '', ''),
(179, 1, 'A10 - New European Architecture', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA10 New European Architecture Magazine is a new architecture magazine with European focus. Six times a year it presents the later architecture on the ancient continent.\n', '', '', ''),
(180, 1, 'Classic Massey &amp; Ferguson Enthusiast', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nClassic Massey and Ferguson Enthusiast is an independent Ferguson and Massey Ferguson magazine and totally devoted to the red and grey tractor. The full colour 100 page monthly magazine is packed with practical editorial and interviews with Massey Ferguson enthusiasts and active Massey Ferguson users. Containing news from across the country and heaving with a variety of different models Classic Massey and Ferguson Enthusiast Magazine will captivate collectors, owners, and enthusiasts both young and not so young alike! Anyone interested or involved in Massey Ferguson will be enthralled by this new MF dedicated magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(181, 1, 'Triumph World', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Triumph World Magazine?\n\nIf you want to relive fond memories of owning a Spitfire, or you''re just keen to find out more about the heyday of British car-manufacturing, then a subscription to Triumph World magazine could be perfect for you.\n\nEvery issue of this classic car magazine features profiles of a number of different timeless Triumph models, from the Stag to the TR7, as well as offering practical guides to buying and maintaining Standard-Triumph vehicles.\n\nThis magazine makes a great read for all vintage motoring fans, as it also includes updates from the international classic car scene, bringing you reports of recent car exhibitions and previews of upcoming events.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIf you are a Triumph enthusiast, then a magazine subscription to Triumph World is the one for you.Triumph World magazine caters for anyone who is passionate about of all Triumphs - including the TR series, Vitesse, Herald, Spitfire, GT6, Stag and saloons - plus the much-cherished Standards. A subscription to Triumph World offers feature cars, technical help, memories of the factory days, news, views and show reports. In essence it captures the whole of the Triumph scene in one easy to read monthly magazine.By subscribing to Triumph World means that you will receive news on up and coming events, where you will be able to showcase your vehicle, look at others and meet fellow Triumph Enthusiasts.\n', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `oc_product_description` (`product_id`, `language_id`, `name`, `description`, `meta_description`, `meta_keyword`, `tag`) VALUES
(182, 1, 'Twist &amp; Go', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Twist &amp; Go Magazine?\n\nWhether you’re a dedicated moped enthusiast or just about to head out on your scooter for the very first time, a subscription to Twist &amp; Go magazine will give you access to regular riding guides to help you stay safe on the roads.\n\nFormerly focusing on just scooters, this motorcycle magazine now also covers quads, motorbikes and minimotos, with its classifieds section making it easy to find the vehicle you''re looking for.\n\nEvery issue features profiles of new bikes and scooters, plus helpful buying guides to make sure that you get the best value for money when purchasing a new two-wheeler.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTwist &amp; Go has the latest news from the current scooter and light motorcycle markets. The best new models are selected and tested in each issue to help you keep pace with innovations in every aspect of riding, from commuting to customising. There are technical tips, product tests and lifestyle features. The comprehensive ''What Scooter'' section gives full details of every new model available today, while the ''Used Scooter Price Guide'' gives a clear indication of second hand prices. No other riding and lifestyle magazine comes close in this corner of the market.\n', '', '', ''),
(183, 1, 'Far Eastern Agriculture', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFar Eastern Agriculture is the only broad based agricultural magazine covering the entire region by reviewing the changing patterns in farming throughout South East Asia. Machinery and equipment, grain and crops, irrigation, agri-chemicals, livestock breeding and processing are all featured in depth, with regular coverage of news and events in each product area. ', '', '', ''),
(184, 1, 'African Farming And Food Processing', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA leading magazine for agricultural and primary food processing industries. It contains news articles on the development and technical aspects of new agricultural materials, equipment and systems. Editorial also included articles on crops, livestock, weed and pest control, irrigation, agricultural equipment and primary food processing techniques and coverage of special events, as well as the annual suppliers directory and poultry review. ', '', '', ''),
(185, 1, 'Airports Of The World', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Airports of the World Magazine?\n\nDedicated to in-depth reporting on the world''s gateways, Airports of the World includes real life accounts from airport staff, as well as airport history features and coverage of the most important aviation news stories. Subscribe to Airports of the World magazine for tips on the best places to spot aeroplanes within various airports, updates on future airport extension plans and great travel advice for when you fly to your destination. You''ll also find interesting pieces on technological innovations in air travel and reviews of the latest travel and aviation related products, including book and DVD releases.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nToday''s Gateways To The World...\n\nAirports of the World is a bi-monthly magazine which provides an in-depth look at the layout, activities, aircraft, airlines and people at a wide selection of the world''s airports. Reporting on airports large and small around the world, it includes articles on both major city hubs and smaller regional airports to leisure and low cost airports. Topics covered include current operations, airline operators, and future plans.\n', '', '', ''),
(186, 1, 'Envirotec', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPublished every second month Envirotec is aimed at readers who are involved with technology in the environment. If you or your company has waste or pollution issues Envirotec can show you the solution. Envirotec will give you:\n\n•6 issues delivered direct to your door\n\n•Ability to stay abreast of the latest legislative requirements\n\n•Knowledge of the latest techniques in the environment industry\n\n•Innovations and trends in the sector\n\n•What your peers and competitors are up to\n\n•The latest products on the market for the environmental technology sector\n\n•Comment from the industry figures\n', '', '', ''),
(187, 1, 'Technical Review Middle East', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTechnical Review Middle East is published in English and in Arabic to serve the requirements of management and technical readership across business and industry in the Middle East.\n\nIn a year, the editorial content covers telecommunications and IT, banking and finance, oil, gas and petrochemicals, transport and logistics, travel, power, construction and manufacturing, plus articles on new products and developments.', '', '', ''),
(188, 1, 'Financial Sector Technology', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFinancial Sector Technology (aka FST) is the leading bi-monthly B2B magazine for IT decision makers within the UK financial sector.\n\nIt bridges the gap between business and technical publications as it examines the business benefits of implementing new IT. The editorial consists of news, product news, in-depth features and each issue contains a detailed supplement focusing on a hot topic for the sector.\n\nThere are also a number of other regular sections such as Bright Ideas, a Security column, Appointments page as well as others.\n', '', '', ''),
(189, 1, 'Continuity Insurance &amp; Risk', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nContinuity Insurance &amp; Risk is the UK''s leading bi-monthly risk management and insurance journal.\n\nLaunched in 1996, the magazine has rapidly established itself as a key weapon in the risk and insurance professional''s armoury. The magazine comprises news, industry views and regular guest columns as well as articles on the latest topics in business insurance and risk management and business continuity.\n\nStories are relevant to both the public and private sector and to companies of all size and industry-type. Each issue contains a wide range of relevant editorial with perspectives from respected professionals.\n', '', '', ''),
(190, 1, 'Oil Review Middle East', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nOil Review Middle East was launched in 1997 to reflect the development and importance of the region’s oil, gas and petrochemicals industry. A quarterly magazine, it covers the E&amp;P, upstream and downstream petroleum industry, from the GCC states and Iran to North Africa and the Caspian. ', '', '', ''),
(191, 1, 'Pc Pilot', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO PC Pilot Magazine?\n\nPC Pilot magazine offers an in-depth look at the realistic world of computer flight simulators from the best voices in the industry, including pilots, programmers and aviation professionals.\n\nSubscribe to PC Pilot for reviews of the latest simulation software and add-ons, plus expert interviews with publishers and developers.\n\nEach issue comes with a free CD containing the latest patches, demos, videos and updates, and you''ll love the helpful tutorials and beginner''s guides on everything from aircraft electrical systems to reading NDB approach charts.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe World''s Favourite Flight Simulation Magazine...\n\nPC Pilot brings sense and expert opinion to the exciting and often daunting world of flight simulation. Contributors include many real-world pilots and aviation professionals to ensure that what you read is as real as it gets! Published bi-monthly, each issue of the magazine is packed with detailed news, advice, reviews, features and views on all aspects of flight simulation. Each issue also includes a FREE CD!&lt;\n', '', '', ''),
(192, 1, 'Sc', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nInformation security moves fast. And it’s vital to keep up. A single breach could cost your business a fortune – or even bring it to a grinding halt. That’s why, every month your peers read SC (Secure Computing) – the magazine that’s led the field on this complex subject for over 15 years.\n\nThere''s plenty to look forward to with each issue including:\n\n•The latest information security threats and how to tackle them\n\n•Security product reviews and group tests of IT hardware and software allowing you to make better buying decisions\n\n•User case studies, major-player interviews and round-table discussions so you can capitalise on the experience of others\n\n•The latest hot topics in IT security , from corporate issues to strategy, helping you increase your expertise with each feature\n\n•Legal updates and guidance on the latest rules and regulations – both in the UK and overseas\n', '', '', ''),
(193, 1, 'The Selfbuilder', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Selfbuilder magazine is the must have renovation bible. As a selfbuilder or if you’re renovating your home you need literally hundreds of products from drains to curtains, and dozens of suppliers from architects to TV aerial installers. Selfbuild Update will bring you all the suppliers in one place. We know you all like to compare prices, performance and specifications – SELFBUILD UPDATE is easily accessible and makes information gathering very easy. Selfbuilder magazine is updated every month with all of the latest products to make your renovation project go as smoothly as it possibly can.The Selfbuilder magazine is an exclusive publication to the market of homebuilding and renovating. A subscription will be delivered to your door monthly jam packed with all of the tools you need to renovate a property. The Selfbuilder will provide you with all the inspiration, how to guide and information you need to make your building project a success.Subscribe to The Selfbuilder today and receive all the necessary tools you need for your building project.\n', '', '', ''),
(194, 1, 'Pinstriping &amp; Kustom Graphics Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIf you are interested in the world then a subscription to Pinstriping, Airbrushing, Tattooing, Kustom Art and Lifestyle is the magazine for you.It doesn''t matter if you just want to check out the latest cool looks, learn how to achieve them or find the right equipment or people to do the job, this magazine is for you.P&amp;KG is packed full of features, interviews, Hints and Tips and How To''s from the best artists. Showcasing the best in UK &amp; EU pinstriping &amp; airbrush talent P&amp;KG is designed to be the definitive source of information &amp; inspiration for both artists and their prospective customers.\n', '', '', ''),
(195, 1, 'Sleeper', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Sleeper magazine brings you six stunning issues per year of the very best work in international hotel design, development and architecture. Each bi-monthly issue in a subscription to Sleeper magazine is filled from front to back with exclusive coverage of the hottest new locations, the latest openings and penetrative interviews and profiles of the biggest names in the business. The hotel industry is one of the fast growing sectors worldwide, with new developments and many new trends launched in the industry all the time. A subscription to Sleeper magazine includes all latest news, in depth and informative features, exclusive and interesting interviews, authoritative and independent reviews, essential and expert advice. Along with all these essential elements the magazine also contains stunning and fascinating photographs. The entire team working on Sleeper magazine has in depth knowledge about the industry. Hotel owners, operators and developers, interior designers, architectures, contractors, consultants, senior managers, and other executives related to the industry find a subscription to Sleeper magazine an essential read.\n', '', '', ''),
(196, 1, 'The Art Of Design', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to The Art Of Design Magazine brings you articles by the world’s leading designers and showcases the very latest trends from a wide range of design solutions from the modern world. The Art of Design is a high class publication that has been fashioned for the person who understands what true design &amp; lifestyle is….\n\nEvery Issue of The Art of Design magazine brings together a varied range of editorial and feature content that you will not see anywhere else, from Beautiful Homes, Boutiques, Hotel Design, &amp; Luxury Lifestyle.\n\nBeautifully presented, inspirational and insightful, the art of design magazine goes in depth to get under the skin of design culture.\n', '', '', ''),
(197, 1, 'Design Buy Build', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to the Design Buy Build magazine is an indispensable tool for any Architect, House Builder, Property Developer, Local Authority and member of the design community.\n\nAs a regular reader, you are rewarded with up to date knowledge and unique insights from Building &amp; Design professionals. You will receive in-depth features on the latest and greatest architecture projects in the UK and internationally.\n\nPartnering with the UK’s major building exhibitions and trade shows throughout 2014 the magazine provides in depth previews and reviews of essential networking events. PLUS there''s our on-going CPD (Continuing Professional Development) features giving the professional access to a directory of essential seminars and conferences.\n\nWith more than 84 pages packed with latest launches, innovations, inspiring projects, and inspirational editorial features dedicated to kitchens, bathrooms, lighting and much more… it''s an essential read whether you''re embarking on a total new build, refurbishment or redesign; the magazine provides simple solutions that make the readers everyday life easier.\n', '', '', ''),
(198, 1, 'Craft &amp; Design', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Craft &amp; Design Magazine?\n\nProviding an insight into a huge range of different crafts and hobbies from across the country, this magazine is a fascinating monthly snapshot of British creativity. Individual issues cover crafts as diverse as glass-blowing, pottery, beadwork and basket-making, accompanied by articles and business advice from leading experts in their fields. With details of courses and workshops included in each edition, this is a great way to get involved in crafting or add a new skill to your existing repertoire. Galleries and exhibitions are also listed, keeping you up-to-date with the exciting work being produced and displayed by artists and craftsmen near you.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\ncraft&amp;design is a full colour bi-monthly magazine featuring contemporary and traditional crafts, that was originally launched in 1983 as Craftsman Magazine. In 2007 it was revamped and relaunched as craft&amp;design magazine, to reflect and represent the contemporary design-led UK craft industry. A subscription to craft&amp;design magazine features work in all media by British and Irish designer makers, news, directories, listings and information about craft fairs, galleries &amp; exhibitions, suppliers of materials &amp; equipment, courses &amp; workshops, guilds &amp; associations. With Business News &amp; Tips for designer makers, from students and graduates through to experienced professionals, craft&amp;design offers up to the minute advice in a practical, down to earth way. Trade and private buyers of hand crafted work will find the comprehensive listings of events &amp; exhibitions, the Makers Gallery pages and the variety of features in the magazine an invaluable source of fine British craft and design. craft&amp;design magazine is produced by a private, independent company owned and run by husband and wife, Paul and Angie Boyer. Their unrivalled experience and knowledge of crafts, design, photography, advertising, marketing and promotion give them a unique understanding of the UK crafts industry and the needs of the people working in it. craft&amp;design magazine is published by a small creative business with small creative businesses in mind. Subscribe to Craft and Design magazine today and be inspired.\n', '', '', ''),
(199, 1, 'Sc', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nInformation security moves fast. And it’s vital to keep up. A single breach could cost your business a fortune – or even bring it to a grinding halt. That’s why, every month your peers read SC (Secure Computing) – the magazine that’s led the field on this complex subject for over 15 years.\n\nThere''s plenty to look forward to with each issue including:\n\n•The latest information security threats and how to tackle them\n\n•Security product reviews and group tests of IT hardware and software allowing you to make better buying decisions\n\n•User case studies, major-player interviews and round-table discussions so you can capitalise on the experience of others\n\n•The latest hot topics in IT security , from corporate issues to strategy, helping you increase your expertise with each feature\n\n•Legal updates and guidance on the latest rules and regulations – both in the UK and overseas\n', '', '', ''),
(200, 1, 'Black Static', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nBlack Static was founded in 1994 and is the UK''s only professional horror fiction magazine, publishing new stories by some of the finest writers working in the field today: Christopher Fowler, Stephen Volk, Lisa Tuttle, Nicholas Royle, Conrad Williams, Steve Rasnic Tem, Cody Goodfellow, Mélanie Fazi, Michael Marshall Smith, Simon Clark, Graham Joyce, Gary McMahon, to name just a few. Every story is accompanied by very striking illustrations\n\nEvery issue contains a dazzling array of non-fiction, with in-depth reviews of the latest horror/dark fantasy/crime books, interviews with authors and filmmakers, film reviews, regular comment columns from the likes of screenwriter Stephen Volk (Ghostwatch, Afterlife) and novelist Christopher Fowler (Roofworld, Bryant &amp; May series). There are often easy-to-enter draws to win books and DVDs/Blu-rays.\n\nThe magazine is 96 pages, beautifully designed, with a spine and laminated cover. Reviews are invariable extremely positive, and the magazine has won several awards, including four British Fantasy Awards and an International Horror Guild Award.\n', '', '', ''),
(201, 1, 'Classic Pop', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Classic Pop Magazine?\n\nWhether you''re into synth-pop, New Romantic, indie pop or ska, Classic Pop is a refreshing monthly reminder of just how great the ''70s and ''80s were for music.\n\nIn each issue you''ll get to read interviews with all of your favourite acts, find out current news and tour dates, and hear the amazing true stories behind the gigs, gossip and break-ups of each band.\n\nIf you''re looking to find some modern artists that can just about live up to the classics, there''s even a regular ''Shock of the New'' feature with profiles of upcoming acts who are openly inspired by the music you love.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nClassic Pop is the music magazine everyone''s been waiting for. If you grew up to the explosion of New Wave sounds in the late-70s to mid-80s with the excitement of synth-pop, New Romantic, ska and indie-pop casting away the turgid rock stereotypes - Classic Pop is the magazine for you.\n\nThe magazine features interviews with icons of the era, label profiles, classic albums, and much, much more.\n', '', '', ''),
(202, 1, 'Little White Lies', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Little White Lies Magazine?\n\nA film magazine that gives you all the information you need on both mainstream and independent movies, Little White Lies also has amazing illustrations and photography all focused on the world of cinema. Every issue is based on a particular feature film, with artwork on the cover reflecting the movie''s themes or depicting the lead actor.\n\nIn addition to the the cover story and articles inspired by the chosen film, you''ll get theatre reviews, comments from the editor and a look forward at future releases. Little White Lies also has its own special film ranking system, with markings out of five for Anticipation, Enjoyment and In Retrospect tracking their critical reactions to each movie.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBuy a magazine subscription to Little White Lies magazine and receive the hippest movie magazine there is!Little White Lies is a pioneering film magazine that combines beautiful design with the sharpest new writing to radically redefine the limits of popcorn culture.\n\nRecognising that movies don''t exist in a vacuum, it embraces the totality of the cinematic experience, bringing together life, truth and movies.Little White Lies magazine is a film and entertainment magazine, coming with film reviews, film festival news, interviews, and much much more. Every issue of this magazine will entertain anyone who loves films.\n\nRegular features include music, fashion, current events, travel, etc. With facscinating interviews with directors and stars alike, giving you all the detail about their aspirations, efforts and lines of thinking on variety of issues. If you love the films featured, you will love the interviews too.Subscribe to Little White Lies magazine toady and receive this truly unique and beautiful publication through your door every other month.\n', '', '', ''),
(203, 1, 'Blackhair', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBlackhair is a vital source of information for the style-conscious black women of today. Editorially, the magazine focuses on hair and beauty issues and features hundreds of inspirational hairstyle ideas to keep our readers looking and feeling fabulous, including looks for natural hair and haircare advise from the top names in Afro hairstyling.\n', '', '', ''),
(204, 1, 'Scottish Woman', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Scottish Woman Magazine?\n\nEvery issue of this women''s magazine brings you an exclusive interview with a successful female Scottish celebrity, covering a wide range of topics, from their career to their personal interests and relationships. The ideal magazine for elegant, broadminded Scottish ladies, a bi-monthly subscription to Scottish Woman magazine will not only bring you fashion and lifestyle tips, but it will also offer travel features on beautiful destinations across the globe. With expert advice on how to improve your home in its popular ''Homes &amp; Interiors'' section, as well as tasty recipe guides, this mag makes a great read for anyone looking to make the most of life at home.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nTake out a subscription to Scottish Woman magazine, Scotland''s most glamorous glossy magazine. Every issue in a subscription to Scottish Woman magazine is packed with inspiration, fashion and beauty, fascinating features on real women, ideas for the home, wonderful travel destinations and an acclaimed food and wine section. Within the pages of every issue in a subscription to Scottish Woman magazine you will find all the style, wit and wisdom you''d expect from a magazine published in Scotland for women of the world. Each issue in a subscription to this magazine comes with great and exciting features, new product launches, wonderful travel destinations, food and wine, inspirational ideas, expert tips, and lots more. One of the major attractions of this magazine is the stunning and fascinating pictures. With all these ingredients this magazine has become very popular and special among all readers.\n', '', '', ''),
(205, 1, 'Slink', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSLiNK magazine is the UK''s only aspirational fashion and lifestyle glossy aimed at women size 14+. SLiNK magazine uses curvaceous models to showcase the latest fashion trends and where to shop for the latest looks for women size 14-32. From high street to high end, there is something for every budget.\n\nSLiNK culture and lifestyle features keep our readers in the know of upcoming events, while our short, sharp and witty articles are entertaining and to the point. There are great in season recipes rustled up by our head chef for you to try at home. Incredible beauty features with industry professionals, product launches and tried and tested treatments ensure that SLiNK has all your beauty needs met. While we do talk health and fitness we DON''T talk diets &amp; bikini bodies. SLiNK encourages, inspires and empowers our readers to be who they are.\n', '', '', ''),
(206, 1, 'Scotland Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Scotland Magazine Magazine?\n\nThis magazine is a fantastic read for anyone with an interest in Scottish culture, as well as an informed guide to some truly stunning lesser-known holiday destinations. With your subscription to Scotland magazine, you can read features about the country''s dramatic and intriguing history as well as enjoying interviews with some of the modern Scots hitting the headlines. You''ll hear all the local news and get comprehensive hotel and restaurant directories with plenty of ideas on where to visit at which time of year. You can even find listings of upcoming events and occasions, including details of unmissable Whisky Live tasting events.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCelebrate the world’s best small country with a subscription to Scotland magazine. Scotland magazine is the superb guide to everything Scottish. From exploring the great history to travelling the length and breadth of the country - there''s something for everyone in Scotland Magazine.\n\nWhether your interests lie with historic castles and homes, wild and rugged countryside, famous Celts, breathtaking walks, architectural heritage, city chic or the finest food and drink – within the pages of Scotland Magazine you’ll be transported to a magical land.\n\nScotland Magazine; celebrating the world’s best small country. Great reasons to subscribe to Scotland magazine: •Get free delivery to your door •Never miss an issue •Save off the cover price Discover the dream, explore the legend with a Scotland Magazine subscription for you or a friend today.\n', '', '', ''),
(207, 1, 'Skin Shots', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFancy a tattoo? Not sure what you want? Then get yourself a subscription to Skin Shots International magazine and see the vast array of talent and styles available worldwide today. Also included is a directory of UK tattoo artists. Skin Shots International magazine is a sister title to Skin Deep, which is meant as a ''reference'' magazine featuring top quality tattoo work from around the globe. Also included is a Directory of many UK and International tattoo studios to help you hunt down your next masterpiece. Being a ''Pictorial'' magazine, Skin Shots breaks down the language barriers. Published bi-monthly, Skin Shots International magazine aims at helping reader’s pick their tattoos by providing stunning tattoo art from around the world!\n', '', '', ''),
(208, 1, 'Mycornwall', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nmyCornwall magazine regularly features the best of Cornwall whether it is local culture, language, history and heritage, countryside and wildlife, town and village features, country shows, local art, sports and leisure.\nCornish gardens and gardening and the biggest listings in Cornwall are beautifully featured in each bi-monthly issue.\n', '', '', ''),
(209, 1, 'Interzone', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nInterzone is Britain''s longest running science fiction and fantasy magazine. It has helped launch the careers of many important authors and continues to publish new fiction by some of the world''s best known writers. Amongst those to have graced its pages are Brian Aldiss, Michael Moorcock, Bruce Sterling, William Gibson, M. John Harrison, Stephen Baxter, Iain M. Banks, J.G. Ballard, Kim Newman, Alastair Reynolds, Harlan Ellison, Greg Egan, Gwyneth Jones, Geoff Ryman, Rachel Pollack, John Brunner, Paul McAuley, Ian R. MacLeod, Christopher Priest, Chelsea Quinn Yarbro, Aliette de Bodard, Lavie Tidhar... and we continue to publish some of the brightest new stars around.\n\nAs well as world class original fiction each issue also contains in-depth news and reviews of the latest science fiction/fantasy, books, films and DVD/Blu-rays.\n\nThe magazine is 96 pages, with a spine and laminated cover, beautifully presented in full colour throughout. It has won many prestigious awards, including the Hugo Award and British Fantasy Award.\n', '', '', ''),
(210, 1, 'Sorted', '&lt;p&gt;WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Sorted Magazine? If you''re looking for a publication that combines traditional values with an inquisitive eye on our ever-changing society, then a Sorted magazine subscription is perfect for you. This Christian men''s magazine is bursting with news, sport, motoring and reviews, whilst also taking an insightful look at topics including faith, finance, addictions and mentoring from a range of different perspectives, including celebrities and leading businessmen. This combination of a forward thinking attitude to style and culture, together with a religious sensibility, makes a subscription to Sorted magazine a great option for the conventional 21st Century man. FROM THE PUBLISHER The UK''s only Christian lifestyle magazine for men - a huge success story. Described by the Telegraph as ''the lad''s mag with morals'', Sorted has proved to be a remarkable success. The only Christian lifestyle magazine of its kind for me, Sorted has established a strong and loyal following in rapid time. The magazine looks at success, faith, finance, passion and purity, motoring, movies, tons of football and other sports, good books, DVD''s, addictions, accountability and mentoring. Sorted has an eminent team of writers including Bear Grylls, Steve Chalke and Rob Parsons. Sorted also has a Gadgets expert and a motoring correspondent as well as a ''60 Second Life Coach'' and a ''Sex Doc''. &quot;Down to earth, real, ''un-religious''- that''s why sorted has helped my Christian faith so much!&quot; - Bear Grylls. Sorted... the men''s mag... for life.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '', '', ''),
(211, 1, 'Traction', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTRACTION magazine is the leading railway periodical that focuses purely on the classic period of diesel and electric traction on Britain’s railways. This was the time from the mid 1950s through to the last years of the twentieth century, when most trains were locomotive hauled or operated by the first generation of diesel and electric multiple units. The content of the magazine reflects this interesting period, with articles on a wide range of topics by former professional railwaymen, railway historians and enthusiasts. Features covering railway operation, locomotives and multiple units, as well as the day-to-day experiences of railway enthusiasts appear in each issue. In addition, the magazine has a watching brief to cover the remaining operation of those ‘classic’ locomotives that are still at work on the national network. The preservation scene is covered in detail, as enthusiasts try to recreate the golden days of locomotive and multiple unit operation on the numerous heritage lines up and down the country. TRACTION also has a section devoted to modelling Britain’s railways in the ‘blue and green’ period of British Rail. Features are aimed at both the railway modeller and also the enthusiast whose interest is primarily in the prototype. Photographic coverage is a feature of the magazine and, with a large library of colour and black and white images to draw upon, is one of the hallmarks of TRACTION. At present publication is bi-monthly but it is expected that in the near future the magazine will revert to being a monthly periodical.\n', '', '', ''),
(212, 1, 'Fusion Flowers', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nWith the weather being as bad as it is just now, it’s time to settle down to read Issue 82 of Fusion Flowers magazine and to be inspired by the gorgeous step-by-step designs there. There’s something for everyone – from the quick and easy through to the intricate and delicate and we welcome a new designer to the team. Morna Fell, who is based in Iceland, takes you through her chilly design!\n\nMark Pampling reports from the Asia Cup in Japan and we drool over some of the stunning design work on display there. In fact our front cover was created there by Hideyuki Niwa of Japan! There is also another report from Japan on the first ever Japan World Cup in floral design held at Huis Ten Bosch.\n\nLooking for fresh inspiration in table design? We have fresh inspiration for that too – this time from The Netherlands in their ‘Dining Al Fresco’ exhibition held at their huge plants and flowers event. From IPM Essen we find some inspiration for spring designs from 3 very different designers.\n\nAnd there’s more! Take a look inside Finnish Master Florist Pirjo Koppi’s new book on the subject of floral jewellery with a difference and in the process get some fresh inspiration!\n\nPlus we have all the usual favourites together with a feature of lots of recommendations for new cut roses that we discovered in The Netherlands.\n', '', '', ''),
(213, 1, 'Posability', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPosAbility Magazine is a fresh and innovative publication that focuses on the opportunities available to disabled people today.\n\nPosAbility Magazine aims to inspire, encourage and motivate disabled people to live life to the full, to grab opportunities and most importantly to have fun. Every issue brings new ideas for activities and holidays and tips on leading a fit and healthy life, along with the latest products, personal stories, humorous columns and exclusive competitions.\n', '', '', ''),
(214, 1, 'History Ireland', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nHistory Ireland is a high quality full colour illustrated bi-monthly magazine that aims to bring the best of contemporary history scholarship to a general audience. We belive that history can be communicated by good writing and attractive presentation.\n\nPublished since 1993, each issue features a wide variety of topics from the earliest times to the present day giving the reader a sense of the distant past when offering a contemporary edge.\n\nEvery article is illustrated with photographs, maps or paintings to provide a vivid impression of the topic.\n', '', '', ''),
(215, 1, 'Philosophy Now', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPhilosophy Now is a lively and readable magazine for everyone interested in ideas. It isn''t afraid to tackle all the major questions of life, the universe and everything. Published every 2 months, it tries to corrupt innocent citizens by convincing them that philosophy can be exciting, worthwhile and comprehensible, and also to provide some enjoyable reading matter for those already ensnared by the muse, such as philosophy students and academics.\n\nEach issue contains articles and features on all aspects of philosophy, as well as book reviews, film reviews, letters, competitions, news, cartoons, and the occasional short story.\n\nIt attracts contributions by well-known thinkers, and regular columnists include Prof. Raymond Tallis (\n', '', '', ''),
(216, 1, 'Scottish Islands Explorer', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Scottish Islands Explorer Magazine?\n\nOff the coast of Scotland you''ll find 790 different islands, with the Shetlands, Orkneys and Hebrides just some of the better known archipelagos.\n\nIf you want to know more about these amazing remote landscapes and communities, you need a subscription to Scottish Islands Explorer magazine. Each issue is printed in glossy full colours, with stunning photography capturing all the natural beauty of these secluded islands.\n\nFrom the history of Iona Abbey to sailing around Barra, you can read amazing stories from islanders and visitors alike, and even get information on planning your own trip with activities, hotels, and restaurant listings included in every issue.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nScottish Islands Explorer is the UK''s only magazine devoted to exploring Scotland''s many off-shore islands. It encourages interest in their structure, history and current ways of life.\n\nThe publication tries to blend the attractions of informative writing with compelling photography. It is now in its 13th year and appears bi-monthly as a 52 page, full-colour production. There are regular features on matters and events of immediate interest, recently published books and advice on travelling as well as a dozen articles in each issue in which writers take an objective view of places, people or phenominon.\n\nThe magazine stimulates families and individuals to journey to the islands on the ferries and airline routes. It also helps link like-minded people with fellow travellers who appreciate some of the most entrancing scenery and places in Britain.\n', '', '', ''),
(217, 1, 'British Archaeology', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO British Archaeology Magazine?\n\nOne of the best archaeological history magazines around, this award-winning title is produced once every two months by the Council for British Archaeology. This authoritative magazine focuses on archaeological endeavours across the UK, and features articles from the most respected names in the field. As well as bringing you all the latest news and findings in an enjoyable and easy to read format, you’ll also find listings of archaeological events and reviews of exhibitions and books. Subscribe to British Archaeology magazine for regular travel updates from Mick Aston, plus expert knowledge on the secrets and mysteries that are uncovered in digs throughout the country.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDo you know someone who loves archaeology? A year''s subscription to British Archaeology, the magazine of the leading UK archaeology charity is the perfect present. It will suit anyone with a passion for delving further into our past - whether they enjoy watching the latest archaeological TV documentaries, visiting historic buildings or digging on ancient sites! Birthday, Christmas, graduation, thank you - whatever the reason, subscribe to British Archaeology magazine today! British Archaeology is an authoritative, in-depth source of information and comment on what’s new, interesting and important in the world of archaeology. It is published bi-monthly by the Council for British Archaeology (CBA), an environmental charity whose sole purpose is to promote the appreciation, care and understanding of the historic environment. Written by archaeologists and historians with an eye on the present and something to say about the past, it is the largest, brightest, most forward-looking and talked about UK archaeology magazine ever published. With regular features by the UK’s leading archaeologists and cutting-edge news as it breaks, British Archaeology’s regular features include: •News •Letters •Science •Mick’s Travels •One the Web •Books •In View •Spoilheap •CBA correspondent •My Archaeology •Briefing – archaeological events listing, with exhibition reviews Enjoy the benefits of British Archaeology magazine whilst supporting the CBA’s mission to improve awareness and enjoyment of archaeology for the benefit of all and helping to safeguard its future.\n', '', '', ''),
(218, 1, 'Royal Britain Presents Royal Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nHello and welcome to our first Royal Life issue of 2015, a year that is shaping up to be quite a momentous one for fans of the British royal family.\n\nIn this issue we report on the Duke and Duchess of Cambridge''s whirlwind tour of New York and Washington, plus the Duchess'' enviable style throughout both pregnancies. We also celebrate Prince George''s second Christmas, looking at official photo''s taken of the youngest heir to the throne. Other features include Prince Charles and Camilla''s tour of Mexico, Prince Harry''s tour of the Middle East and his recent visit to Lesotho, plus the Queen''s latest engagements and all the best royal news.\n', '', '', ''),
(219, 1, 'Sen', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSEN Magazine is the UK’s leading magazine for special educational needs (SEN). Providing extensive news coverage and authoritative features across the whole spectrum of SEN, it is essential reading for all those who live and work with children and young people with disabilities and special needs. Every issue of SEN Magazine includes a wide range of features and articles covering major conditions, such as autism, Asperger’s, dyslexia, ADHD, Down’s, hearing and visual impairments, PMLD and cerebral palsy. Topics like literacy, numeracy, speech and language, communications, mobility, multi-sensory therapy and behaviour are also covered in detail, and there are regular features on educational issues, including statements, IEPs, inclusion, SEN law and transition. In addition, a comprehensive CPD and training section offers listings of useful courses, exhibitions, conferences and events for both professionals and parents/carers. With regular articles from top SEN experts, alongside contributions from parents, teachers and professionals, SEN Magazine provides an invaluable mix of practical advice, information and thought provoking features. This is not an academic journal, but a lively, informative magazine written for busy parents and professionals and designed to keep you up-to-date with the latest thinking, guidance, products and best practice from the world of SEN. Established over eight years ago, SEN Magazine utilises the popular glossy, full colour A4 format. It normally runs to at least 116 pages, so you’ll always find plenty in every issue that’s interesting and relevant to you.\n', '', '', ''),
(220, 1, 'Cambria - 2013', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCambria is Wales''s National Magazine covering Welsh Culture, Lifestyle, Politics and interviews and articles on leading figures in Wales.\n\nEssential reading for Welsh people and those interested in Wales. A celebration of all things Welsh.\n', '', '', ''),
(221, 1, 'Cornucopia Turkey For Connoisseurs:', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCornucopia is the magazine for connoisseurs of Turkey – gorgeous enough for subscribers'' coffee tables, serious enough for academic libraries.\n\nCornucopia is a truly remarkable publication – beautiful, uncompromising and independent – offering subscribers an ever-growing compendium of all things Turkish.\n\nEach issue offers stunningly illustrated and well-informed articles on all things Turkish, from history, art, archaeology and architecture to people, travel guides, restaurant reviews and recipes. A subscription to Cornucopia is a must for anyone planning to travel to Turkey or keen to explore its past and equally fascinating present.\n\nTo Craig Brown of the Daily Telegraph, Cornucopia is ‘surely one of the most intelligent and beautiful glossy magazines in the world’.\nIn the words of The Sunday Times Travel Magazine, Cornucopia ‘delves into Turkey’s rich heritage, with beautiful photography, in-depth features and diary dates’.\n‘It’s a truism that the measure of a travel magazine’s success is whether it makes you yearn to visit the destinations it depicts,’ writes Brian Patrick Eha in The New York Review of Magazines. ‘Cornucopia goes one better. It is a vacation in itself.’\n\nFor the entire world of Turkish culture in one beautiful magazine, make sure of your subscription to Cornucopia now.\n\nThe subscription will start with the current issue\n', '', '', ''),
(222, 1, 'The Green Parent', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The Green Parent Magazine?\n\nIf you care about the environment and raising children in an eco-friendly way, then a subscription to The Green Parent magazine will give you plenty of food for thought.\n\nFull of insightful features on everything from biodegradable planting to attachment parenting, you''ll find inspiration for making your life greener and cultivating a great relationship with your children.\n\nThere are tips on topics you might not find elsewhere, like babywearing, alternative therapy and homeschooling, as well as relationship advice and money-saving hints.\n\nWritten and published in Britain, Green Parent is also the only parenting magazine to bring you regular columns on green travel, seasonal food and drink, ethical fashion and organic gardening.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe Green Parent magazine covers every stage of your family''s life. From pregnancy to birth, education to nutrition, gorgeous eco fashion to health and beauty, every issue is packed with 116 pages of ideas and articles, bringing you an exciting, vibrant take on green living.\n\nWhat readers say about the magazine:\n\n''My children range from 14 years old down to six years old and there is so much information I can put into practice.'' Joanne\n\n''I have finally found a magazine that reflects, inspires, supports and gives me strength and hope to raise our family in a loving and joyful way.'' Dawn\n\nSubscribe to The Green Parent magazine today for an excellent read and plenty of inspiring practical advice that you can use to make your family home a happier, healthier place.\n', '', '', ''),
(223, 1, 'Slimming World', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Slimming World Magazine?\n\nWhy should you buy a subscription?\n\nIf you want to find out how to become a successful slimmer, then Slimming World magazine offers great ideas, expert advice and news and features on weight loss. It''s packed with delicious recipes and celebrity features, plus fashion and beauty tips. This health and fitness magazine is also the perfect source of inspiration, with dozens of accounts from real slimmers of all ages and weights, detailing and sharing their weight loss journey with you. Advice on feel-good food that won''t stop you slimming along with exclusive 7-day eating plans make this mag an indispensable guide to helping you enjoy your diet and maintain your ideal weight.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Slimming World Magazine, the inspiring, glossy magazine from Slimming World, the UK’s most advanced weight loss organisation. Slimming World is dedicated to making your slimming journey as easy and enjoyable as possible, and helping you maintain your dream weight for life. In every issue of Slimming World you’ll find: • Amazing success stories from women and men of all ages to inspire you to success. • An exclusive 7-day eating plan to super-charge your weight loss and take the hard work out of menu planning. • 40+ pages of fabulously filling family-friendly recipes for the extra special and the everyday. • Take-charge tactics and savvy seasonal strategies to help you stay on track. • The very latest nutrition and health information to help you make informed choices. • Fitness ideas, road tested by real slimmers, to help speed up your weight loss. • Expert fashion and beauty advice to help you love the body you’ve got now, as well as the one you’re working towards. The principles of Slimming World are that members lose weight through a combination of the ‘Food Optimising’ eating plan, moderate activity through the ‘Body Magic’ programme and group support and shared experience with other slimmers, which all help to encourage behaviour change. Subscribe today and find out why Slimming World is the UK’s fastest-growing slimming magazine!\n', '', '', ''),
(224, 1, 'Radio Bygones', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nWhether your interest is in vintage domestic radio and TV or amateur radio, military, aeronautical, or marine communications, radar and radio navigation, audio and recording, broadcasting, or professional radio systems (fixed or mobile), Radio Bygones is the magazine for you.\n\nPublished every other month, each issue contains articles on vintage radio restoration and repairs, histories, circuit diagrams, nostalgic memories and adverts by specialists. Valve sets (vacuum tubes) as well as early transistor designs all have a place in the magazine. Radio Bygones also features museums and private collections and a full-colour photo-feature in every issue.\n', '', '', ''),
(225, 1, 'Rc Jet International', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRC Jet International covers events internationally and airframes reviews and engine tests of products made anywhere in the world. RC Jet International is the only magazine to run regular turbine engine tests and publish comparison performance information. There are regular features devoted to new products/developments, High Power Electric Ducted Fan, and tips. Each issue we try to maintain a balance between reviews of kits, scratch built models, engine tests and reports on meetings.\n', '', '', ''),
(226, 1, 'Cross Stitch Card Shop', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Cross Stitch Card Shop Magazine?\n\nWhether you’re a seasoned cross-stitcher or a complete novice, you’ll find beautiful patterns for all ability levels in this great crafts magazine. In every issue of Cross Stitch Card Shop you''ll get over 60 card designs, so whoever you need to congratulate, send ''get well'' wishes to or celebrate the birthday of, you''ll find the perfect pattern to suit them inside. You can read hints and tips from other expert stitchers, and there''s even a free cross-stitch card kit included so there''s no delay between your subscription arriving and getting started on some fantastic projects.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nCross Stitch Card Shop is the only cross stitch magazine entirely devoted to cards. With over 60 card designs in every issue you''ll have a collection of specific designs for every occasion.\n\nSuitable for every level of stitcher. Plus, in every issue, enjoy essential stitching advice from the UKs top experts and a free cross stitch card kit to get you started!\n', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `oc_product_description` (`product_id`, `language_id`, `name`, `description`, `meta_description`, `meta_keyword`, `tag`) VALUES
(227, 1, 'Complete Cardmaking', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Complete Cardmaking Magazine?\n\nThis magazine helps you get to grips with digital card design, letting you create professional-looking cards for your friends and family that can be completely personalised. Every issue of Complete Cardmaking comes with a free CD with top quality design software, plus a handy set of kit instructions, so whether you''re a tech wizard or a digital design rookie, you''ll easily follow the instructions. With your subscription to this crafts magazine you''ll get access to a wide range of fantastic fonts, paper and digital stamps to create beautiful cards for all occasions. You can read letters from fellow fans, and will be the first in line to hear about the latest techniques from popular blogs and websites.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMake beautiful cards with your PC! Complete Cardmaking magazine is the UK''s first magazine dedicated to digital crafting.\n\nIt''s published every two months, and each issue gives you:\n\n• A free CD-ROM worth over £15, jam-packed with craft kits and software\n• 68 pages of stunning cards YOU can make using your free CD-ROM, plus easy-to-follow instructions for how to make them • The latest digital news, where to buy your digital stash, the best blogs offering digital freebies and much, much more!\n', '', '', ''),
(228, 1, 'Love Sewing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nEach issue of Love Sewing is full of high-quality practical sewing projects. Be part of a close-knit community of makers who are discovering the joy of creating more for themselves.\n\nFeaturing a free monthly pattern, easy-to-follow step-by-step guides and using the latest fabrics you will be able to create fabulous contemporary accessories for your home, family and wardrobe, with even basic sewing skills.\n\nWhether you’re a complete beginner or already an avid maker, every issue will inspire and build your skills from mastering your machine to perfecting your sewing technique.\n\nWhy subscribe?\n• Never miss an issue\n• Free delivery direct to your door\n• Be the first to read Love Sewing\n• Beautiful and contemporary projects for all skill levels\n• Learn and master sewing techniques\n• Every issue includes a FREE pattern AND a FREE gift\n• FREE access to the VIP lounge – exclusive craft offers, projects, downloads and more!\n', '', '', ''),
(229, 1, 'Fleur Creatif', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Fleur Créatif magazine shows you how to create beautiful flower arrangment with inspirational designs from the best florists. If you have a passion for flower arranging then a Fleur Créatif magazine subscription is for you! Fleur Créatif magazine provides inspirational designs from top floral designers across Europe. In every of the six issues of Fleur Créatif magazine master florists show you the latest trends and reveal arrangement techniques step by step. (90 pages)\n', '', '', ''),
(230, 1, 'Bead &amp; Button', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBead and Button is the US original and billed as most comprehensive beading magazine you grasp in your crafty little hands.\n\nPublished six times a year, Bead&amp;Button offers a variety of beautiful jewellery projects for every skill level. If you love bead crochet work,stringing , bead weaving, wirework projects, polymer clay and other jewellery making techniques, you should apparently try Bead &amp; Button.\n', '', '', ''),
(231, 1, 'Beadwork', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBeadwork magazine brings you the whole world of beads – with everything from how-tos, inspiring and unique beading patterns and projects for all skill levels, insider hints and tips, and inspirational interviews with the experts in the industry.You will also enjoy articles on the history and legacy of beadworking and reviews of the best beading books and products, and all the techniques you need to be an expert beader.\n', '', '', ''),
(232, 1, 'Landlove', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO LandLove Magazine?\n\nIf you prefer homemade food to supermarket shopping, then a LandLove magazine subscription will teach you all you need to know about growing your own produce, with guides covering which vegetables are in season and ways to keep your garden in top condition, whatever the weather. It''s much more than just a gardening magazine, however, with a number of wildlife and bird-watching features to help you spot the local creatures in your outdoor space, as well as tasty recipes to transform your homegrown greens into marvellous meals.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nLandLove is a unique new magazine which celebrates a more traditional way of life and the beauty of the British countryside, its flora and fauna. It offers recipe ideas using seasonal British produce from the market, garden and hedgerows. It explores the most interesting places in the British Isles and rediscovers its most fascinating local customs and traditions. It includes practical advice and inspiration for those who garden and love crafts as well as celebrating the work of traditional craftsmen. Most of all it’s a treat, an escape into a better world.\n\nThe LandLove reader is a female homeowner who either dreams of a slower paced, more traditional life, and the romantic ideal of living in the country, or who is already living this life. She has a desire to live the good life at a gentler pace and sees the green fields, fresh air and the open space the countryside can provide as the way to access this.\n', '', '', ''),
(233, 1, 'Landscape And Urban Design', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Landscape &amp; Urban Design is essential for any Landscaping &amp; Urban Design Professionals working within landscape design and management, garden design, the built and natural environment, public space, green space, open space and environmental sustainability.\n\nThe magazine is both inspirational and educative and showcases the very best of Landscaping, Garden Design &amp; Urban Design, in public and private gardens as well as public spaces.\n\nEvery monthly issue features beautiful editorial articles written by the UK’s leading landscaping professionals, and concise clear presentation of product information and is packed with:\n\n•technical advice, techniques and best practices\n•plants in design\n•garden showcases\n•sustainable, environmental &amp; ethical design options\n•event reports\n•industry news &amp; comments\n•designer profiles &amp;... much, much more!\n', '', '', ''),
(234, 1, 'Homes And Interiors Scotland', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Homes and Interiors Scotland Magazine?\n\nIf you love looking at images of breath-taking Scottish architecture, creative interiors and stunning Scottish gardens, a Homes &amp; Interiors Scotland subscription is perfect for you. Each issue of this home interest magazine includes feature articles on both indoor and outdoor design with a Scottish twist. It also offers the latest in Scottish art and property news, as well as a bringing you the best in Scottish interior decoration through illustrations and high-quality photography. This home interest magazine is ideal for anyone looking to take inspiration from beautiful Scottish homes to update their own home decor.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA Homes and Interiors magazine subscription is ideal for anyone looking for tips and ideas to make their home beautiful and luxurious. Every issue of Homes and Interiors magazine is brimming with lavish house features and Scottish treasures along with the best tips and ideas on how you can make your home striking and contemporary. From inspiring colour schemes to the latest in contemporary and classic design, a subscription to Homes &amp; Interiors Scotland magazine is sure to satisfy the most curious minds.\n', '', '', ''),
(235, 1, 'International Property &amp; Travel', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEstablished 22 years, a subscription to the bi-monthly magazine focuses on high quality homes for sale from the UK and around the world in desirable locations. In addition a subscription to International Property Luxury Collection magazine features many interests related to the lifestyle owning beautiful homes provides. In each edition of a subscription you will also find coverage on travel, holiday destinations and resorts, interiors, cars, the latest exclusive fashion accessories, even super yachts and private jets occasionally feature. Whether you are looking for a highly desirable main home or a perfect second or holiday home, you will find page after page of inspiration with a subscription to International Property Luxury Collection magazine. Readers homes also appear and those with particularly interesting homes for sale are covered in great detail. Features are both informative and interesting, offering advice from leading property experts on current market conditions around the word as well as specific information on each destination. This includes suggestions on the type of leisure activities that can be enjoyed in the area, where to find the best hotels and restaurants and where best to indulge in a little retail therapy with guidance on superior shopping opportunities. We also have a regular spotlight on four selected luxurious resorts in the most amazing locations imaginable. Here the emphasis is on pure indulgence with money being no object – magical retreats where you can relax, recharge and escape from the helter-skelter of normal daily life. Unsurprisingly, International Property Luxury Collection attracts a discerning readership and can be found in-flight and in the first class and business class lounges of British Airways, Emirates, American Airlines and many more leading flight operators. The magazine is also proud to be a media partner of the widely acclaimed International Property Awards and International Hotel Awards. The world’s biggest and richest competition for leading property developers, interior designers architects and consultants – established in 1994. The award winning developers, interior designers and property agents appear in “The World’s Best” and up to 4 editions of International Property magazine carries this showcase magazine as an insert free of charge.\n', '', '', ''),
(236, 1, 'A To B Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to A to B magazine specialises in folding bicycles, electric bicycles, bicycle trailers and car-free alternatives of all kinds.\n\nEstablished in August 1997, A to B magazine has over 1,200 subscribers worldwide. A to B magazine explore new ways of travelling from point A to point B.\n\nNaturally, as the most efficient transport integrator, the folding bicycle continues to feature strongly in the magazine however A to B magazine also covers electric bikes, bike trailers and public transport.\n\nWith more than 2,500 magazines sold by subscription every two months, A to B magazine has an estimated readership of 4,000 worldwide.\n\nSubscribers include public utilities, train operating companies and bike manufacturers and distributors.\n\nBuy a subscription to A to B magazine today for only £13.80 and receive each issue straight to you door.\n', '', '', ''),
(237, 1, 'Jets', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nJets is a fresh and feature-packed bi-monthly publication that focuses on our civil aviation heritage from the 1950s onwards, reflecting the birth of jet-engined aircraft and the subsequent dominance of our skies.\n\nAside from iconic civil planes such as Concorde, the magazine also looks at memorable military jets such as the Harrier and Hurricane.\n\nThe in-depth articles will look at the people behind the planes, the airlines, the military campaigns, the technology and the history.\n\nJets is the perfect subscription for those interested in aviation, with gripping features and iconic photography. Subscribe for you or a friend today and you will be consistently entertained, looking forward to the next issue.\n', '', '', ''),
(238, 1, 'Ford And Fordson Tractors', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFord &amp; Fordson Tractors is a club devoted to lovers of the most popular tractor in Britain and Ireland and many other parts of the world.\n\nIs your interest Ford and Fordson and New Holland tractors? Well if it is, take out a subscription today, and receive each issue delivered to your door.\n\nEach issue features Down in the Workshop, Members Tractors, News, Collectors Across The World, FFA Model Corner, Memory Lane, Association information, membership discounts and much more!\n', '', '', ''),
(239, 1, 'Coastal Shipping', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nCoastal Shipping magazine was established in 1994 by Bernard McCall, who at that time had published several maritime books and contributed to other shipping magazines\n\nCoastal Shipping has grown into a hugely popular magazine and is read by shipping professionals and coastal shipping enthusiasts alike.\n\nIt is a bi-monthly magazine, A5 landscape format, for all who are interested in coastal ships and their trades.\n\nFrom 2013 each issue will have 48 pages of news and views, with articles varying from nostalgia to the very latest news. Each issue is well illustrated with colour photographs. Regular features include &quot;Coaster of the Past&quot;, which looks at the career of a once-familiar vessel; &quot;Port Panorama&quot;, which is a pictorial review of coastal vessels in a specific port setting; and &quot;Name Check&quot;, which has news of recent sales and renamings of coasters. This is all in addition to news updates on the activities of coastal vessels from various parts of the UK. Some information on European coastal shipping activity is included, and occasional world wide features are incorporated.', '', '', ''),
(240, 1, 'French Entrée Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFrench Entrée Magazine (formerly called French Magazine) is the UK''s biggest and most beautiful title on all things French. Pick up a copy and you have the best of France at your fingertips, including inspirational travel ideas for your next trip to France, delicious French recipes to try and wine recommendations from our sommelier. You''ll also find all the latest news, travel deals as well as book and film reviews. Our property section is second to none, with great advice from industry experts on where to buy, how to renovate your French home and legal and financial pitfalls to avoid, plus the biggest selection of homes to buy and rent anywhere. If you are looking for a place in France, look in French Entrée Magazine first!\n', '', '', ''),
(241, 1, 'Locomotives International', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nLocomotives International is a high quality bi-monthly publication, and is the only UK-based magazine devoted to railways around the world. The title has recently expanded following the integration into its pages of the &quot;Continental Railway Journal&quot;, and it continues to grow and develop with each issue. All issues contain a mixture of colour and black and white images, which supplement the well researched articles and news items.\n\nThe emphasis in Locomotives International is on ‘the different and the unusual’. Our historical angle means that steam traction is prominent, but diesels and electrics also feature where appropriate, as well as within the news pages.\n\nIf you have fond memories of travelling by train overseas in years gone by, if you want to learn more about our worldwide railway heritage – ancient and modern, or if you simply want to read about different railways and locomotives, you will enjoy reading Locomotives International.\n\nSo, for a new perspective on railways around the world, subscribe to Locomotives International today!\n', '', '', ''),
(242, 1, 'Ink Pellet', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nInk Pellet is the only arts magazine for teachers. Published (since 1998) six times a year to coincide with the start of each new school term, Ink Pellet aims to keep English and Drama teachers updated on the latest news and views from the worlds of theatre, arts, dance and literature. Informative features assist in organising theatre and gallery trips, lesson planning, advice for school drama productions and for students looking to further their studies in the arts. Ink Pellet brings together interviews with the very best authors from Michael Rosen to Anthony Horowitz, showcasing the most talked about exhibitions and includes a comprehensive What’s On section, plus theatre and book reviews, written by our growing band of teacher-reviewers.\n', '', '', ''),
(243, 1, 'Process Engineering Control And Maintenance', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe leading source for innovators in technology, manufacturing and Maintenance within the Engineering &amp; Processing industry worldwide.\n\nPublished bi- monthly, a subscription to PECM magazine is essential for Process Engineers, Chemical Engineers, Instrumentation Engineers, Mechanical Engineers, Plant Engineers, Precision Engineers, Environmental Engineers &amp; General Engineers, Companies and Organizations in the Food, Dairy, Beverage, Brewing, Semiconductor, Pharmaceutical, Biotechnology, Chemical, Oil &amp; Gas, as well as all UK''s major manufacturing units.\n\nEvery issue of the magazine contains the latest news, in-depth features, together with product innovations and case studies showing how process engineers are implementing new technologies to reduce costs and impact on the environment.\n\nWith over 100,000 readers worldwide the publication is widely read, recognized, and well respected within the Process, Engineering &amp; maintenance industries.\n\nA subscription to PECM magazine is the industry''s ''must have'' publication.\n', '', '', ''),
(244, 1, 'Internet Retailing', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nInternet Retailing is written by experts in retail, technology, customer insight and logistics and is a source of ideas, competitive intelligence and business information on the sector\n\nThe magazine is themed around certain key aspects of online multi-channel business and takes and in-depth look at the different areas of retail operation. If you work in this ecommerce and multichannel retail sector or have an interest in it, then you should read Internet Retailing.\n\nBy subscribing today you save 20% off the cover price and you will get 6 issues plus:\n\n•Twice weekly e-newsletters\n•Free seminars and webinars\n•Digital Research Reports\n• Six in-depth topical supplements\n•Annual Procurement Guide\n•Invitations to our annual Conference, IR Expo and the Awards\n', '', '', ''),
(245, 1, 'Oil Review Africa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nOil Review Africa, launched in 2006, is published six times a year. A subscription to Oil Review Africa magazine covers the Exploration &amp; Production, upstream and downstream petroleum industry across the entire continent.\n\nEach issue of Oil Review Africa magazine contains industry news, country reports, sector surveys, technical feature articles, exhibition and conference reviews and news of the latest industry developments and product launches.\n\nOil Review circulation of over 8,000 copies combines authoritative editorial content with an unrivalled circulation throughout the region and has become the magazine of choice among the industry’s advertisers. Oil Review Africa magazine also covers the continents oil, gas and petrochemicals industries. The magazine is distributed to senior, technical and general management within the government ministries, national and international oil companies and leading industry contractors and suppliers.\n\nBuy a subscription today to Oil Review Africa magazine today and receive each issue free to your door.\n', '', '', ''),
(246, 1, 'Equine Health', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nEquine Health is dedicated to professionals involved in the care, treatment and general wellbeing of horses, such as veterinary surgeons, grooms, farriers, physiotherapists, equine dental technicians, breeders and competitive riders. Subscribe to Equine Health today to benefit from:\n\n•Research written by expert authors and professionals\n•Comprehensive coverage of all equine health and welfare issues, including nutrition, farriery, veterinary and reproduction\n•The latest best practice guidance, treatment protocols and procedures\n•News from across the industry\n•Book reviews of modern relevant texts and new product profiles\n•Thought-provoking comment from respected industry leaders.\n\nEquine Health provides a strong link between industry professionals, veterinary surgeons and horse owners, supporting all in the sharing of knowledge to improve equine welfare and wellbeing.\n', '', '', ''),
(247, 1, 'Nursery Management Today', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNursery Management Today (NMT) is a bi-monthly publication aimed at all staff with a management role within nurseries. It recognises the important responsibilities and demands placed upon these professionals, who would be better placed to meet the challenges if they had access to a high quality publication specifically published for them. NMT has a strong editorial commitment to helping management staff raise the quality of childcare provided within nurseries and to achieve their own professional goals.\n', '', '', ''),
(248, 1, 'British Journal Of Neuroscience Nursing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nBritish Journal of Neuroscience Nursing is the only journal in the UK dedicated specifically to neuroscience nursing. The journal publishes articles on all aspects of clinical practice in neuroscience nursing including neurosurgery and critical care, and long-term neurological conditions. It addresses both paediatric and adult care, and endorses inter-professional working with members of the multidisciplinary team. Subscribe to the British Journal of Neuroscience Nursing today and benefit from: •Peer-reviewed content from leading authorities in the field to ensure the highest quality of evidence-based clinical reviews, original research and professional information •Articles presenting and interpreting information in an accessible way that can be easily applied to practice •Primary research papers on all aspects of neuroscience nursing practice, education and management •Reports of innovations in practice, audits and service development pilots •Updates on the implications for neuroscience nurses of the latest developments in health policy, plus a summary of all the latest neuroscience research published in other journals British Journal of Neuroscience Nursing is the official journal of the British Association of Neuroscience Nurses and works in partnership with BANN to promote the educational and professional interests of neuroscience nurses in the UK. The journal is endorsed by the Neuroscience Nursing Benchmarking Group. NB: This subscription also includes access to content on the British Journal of Neuroscience Nursing website, www.bjnn.co.uk. Subscribers will be emailed login details for their account within three working days of the subscription being taken out.\n', '', '', ''),
(249, 1, 'Livestock', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nLivestock is the only dedicated, peer-reviewed veterinary livestock journal that covers cattle, sheep, pig and equine. The journal is authoritative and accessible, and offers a comprehensive resource for veterinary practitioners caring for large farmyard animals.\n\nSubscribe to Livestock today for:\n\n•A dedicated journal that exclusively looks after the needs of livestock practitioners who care for cattle, sheep, pigs and horses\n•The latest in clinical developments in your field\n•An invaluable resource and platform for CPD assessment\n•A professional voice for livestock practitioners, both supporting and sometimes challenging\n\nLivestock is a must-read publication for livestock practitioners wanting to keep up-to-date with clinical developments that enhance their practice. Livestock provides large animal vets with flexible CPD, which can be carried out at a time that suit you.\n', '', '', ''),
(250, 1, 'Journal Of Renal Nursing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nAs the leading renal nursing journal, uniquely positioned to be dedicated solely to nurses and other health professionals involved in renal care, Journal of Renal Nursing aims to facilitate effective patient-centred multidisciplinary care to improve the lives of patients and carers.\n\nSubscribe to Journal of Renal Nursing for:\n\n•Evidence-based clinical articles written by experts in the field to keep you up-to-date\n•Information highlighting the current debates in the field of nephrology\n•Examples of best practice and guidance on all renal replacement options\n•‘Back-to-basics’ practice articles to serve as refreshers for all aspects of renal care\n•Management and teamwork articles to strengthen the multidisciplinary team\n•Research roundups to highlight studies relevant to renal nurses\n\nEnsure you keep up-to-date with the best practice in renal nursing, including high-quality, peer-reviewed clinical articles, practice articles and other renal-related information to meet your professional and training needs.\n', '', '', ''),
(251, 1, 'The Journal Of Dementia Care', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to The Journal of Dementia Care is essential for all those working with people with dementia. The Journal of Dementia Care, launched in 1993, is at the forefront of a modern approach to care for people with dementia. It is a multi-disciplinary, bi-monthly journal aimed at all professionals working with people with dementia. It recognises that professional carers working with people with dementia have their own special demands which deserve a specialist publication. The Journal of Dementia has the following aims: - To provide a strong editorial commitment to improving the quality of care provided for people with dementia in hospitals, residential and nursing homes, daycare and homecare settings. - To raise the profile of all professionals working in this specialist field. - To present the ideas and opinions of professionals working with people with dementia. - To emphasise the value and importance of training and staff development to achieve high quality care. Take out a subscription to The Journal of Dementia to ensure you never miss an issue!\n', '', '', ''),
(252, 1, 'Retail Systems', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRetail Systems is the leading title for technology decision makers in the UK retail sector. The bi-monthly magazine keeps its readers up-to-date with the latest technologies, products and market trends, and the implications these have in business terms. Retail Systems covers new developments, trends and their implications for UK retailers. The title also addresses how technology is changing the world in which our readers live and work.\n', '', '', ''),
(253, 1, 'Continuity Insurance &amp; Risk', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nContinuity Insurance &amp; Risk is the UK''s leading bi-monthly risk management and insurance journal.\n\nLaunched in 1996, the magazine has rapidly established itself as a key weapon in the risk and insurance professional''s armoury. The magazine comprises news, industry views and regular guest columns as well as articles on the latest topics in business insurance and risk management and business continuity.\n\nStories are relevant to both the public and private sector and to companies of all size and industry-type. Each issue contains a wide range of relevant editorial with perspectives from respected professionals.\n', '', '', ''),
(254, 1, 'Powerboat &amp; Rib Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPowerboat &amp; RIB is the largest UK magazine dedicated to the world of power boating and water sports. Published with some 140 pages of highest quality full colour articles and features, the magazine’s content includes; boat tests, multiple equipment reviews, cruising and events reports, features on boat handling and specialist subjects, industry news, professional reports, leading interviews plus a whole lot more! PBR is widely known for being the best read of its genre. Brutally honest, daring and entertaining, its content is written by the world’s most renowned experts and journalists. PBR is the first boating magazine to debut 3D technology on the printed page.\n', '', '', ''),
(255, 1, 'Custom Tattooz', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCustom Tattooz gives young, talented and emerging artists the chance to shine alongside age old classic masters that still tastefully colour our world. Custom Tattooz in house artists travel the world to participate in the biggest tattoo conventions worldwide in search of the unique, unseen and for topics that make interesting and innovative reads, giving you nothing short of the elite. Custom Tattooz is printed on quality paper stock and is therefore seen as a collectable book rather than a throw away magazine. ', '', '', ''),
(256, 1, 'Australian Gourmet Traveller Wine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSix times a year, Australia''s leading wine publication, The Wine Magazine, pours a generous measure of the latest news and events, places and personalities from the world of wine. Appealing to everyone from keen beginners to knowledgable enthusiasts, The Wine Magazine is an unmissable read. By subscribing to the Wine Magazine, you can ensure that you will receive every issue delivered right to your doorstep six times a year. Why not send a gift-subscription to that special friend who loves their wine?\n', '', '', ''),
(257, 1, 'Nexus Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNEXUS is an international bi-monthly alternative news magazine, covering the fields of - Health Alternatives;Future Science; Earth''s AncientPast; UFOs &amp; the Unexplained; and Government Cover-Ups.\n', '', '', ''),
(258, 1, 'Bars &amp; Clubs', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBars &amp; Clubs magazine focuses on the significant investment being channelled into the ever-increasing bars, clubs and nightclub market. Designed to promote the industry and generate ideas, Bars &amp; Clubs covers interviews with the leading identities in the industry and all the latest news. It also focuses on the innovative designs and gives readers the low down on the industry''s promotions, campaigns and fab functions.\n', '', '', ''),
(259, 1, 'Heavy Duty', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHEAVY DUTY magazine is a single brand, bi-monthly motorcycle magazine established in Melbourne in 1991. It is dedicated exclusively to HARLEY-DAVIDSON motorcycles and their owners, riders and enthusiasts. HEAVY DUTY has established an enviable reputation for its wealth of technical expertise. The magazine currently has seven different models on our test fleet which cover the five major platforms manufactured by the Harley-Davidson factory. All these bikes are owned by the magazine and staff. They are used to evaluate products as well as provide an ongoing analysis of the models themselves. The staff are actively involved in riding, racing, rebuilding and restoring H-Ds. HEAVY DUTY is actively involved in the readers lifestyle as well. We sponsor custom bike shows and various readers rides throughout the year. The HEAVY DUTY ESCAPE is a week long ride, through three Australian states, held each February. The ESCAPE is a sell-out every year. HEAVY DUTY attracts the mature, enthusiast rider. We do not indulge in the tatts or gratuitous drug taking that other so-called\n', '', '', ''),
(260, 1, 'Vogue Living Australian', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVOGUE LIVING is about interior design, the home and the garden, with an emphasis on architecture and art.VOGUE LIVING thinks global. Readers are invited into the world''s most beautiful homes, focusing on details and practical elements to spark inspiration.VOGUE LIVING is about turning your fantasy home into a reality, showing you how to act on your dreams.\n', '', '', ''),
(261, 1, 'Belle', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFor more than 30 years, belle has delivered the best in Australian and international home design. belle is a bi-monthly magazine which delivers the hottest in design and luxury news every issue. belle is committed to portraying the best Australian and international design and creates a seamless expression of taste at the intersection of design, decor, architecture, knowledge and fashionable living. Our discerning, affluent readership appreciates that if it''s in belle, they need to know about it. Belle is one of the fastest growing titles in Australia today. ', '', '', ''),
(262, 1, 'Australian Birdkeeper', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAustralian Birdkeeper magazine is published in six glossy, colourful and informative issues per year. Each issue contains regular features and articles on all popular cage/aviary birds.\n\nEach issue of your subscription to Australian Birdkeeper contains articles written by top breeders/aviculturists and veterinarians from all over the world and includes veterinarian reports and tips on where, what, who and when.\n\nFlicking through the magazine you will find all the helpful information, tips and guidelines that every bird keeper could wish to be informed about.\n\nA subscription to Australian Birdkeeper magazine entertains you with focus on particular types of birds, news on birds spotted in the wild,\n\nWith easy to read and informative content on housing, feeding and looking after your birds, including product reviews on new and existing bird brands, no doubt you will be the best birdkeeper around with an Australian Birdkeeper subscription.\n', '', '', ''),
(263, 1, 'Country Craft &amp; Decorating', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAustralian Country Craft and Decorating features inspirational projects, talented craftspeople and a stunning Living with Craft home. This issue is brimming with projects that will have you reaching for your craft basket again.\n', '', '', ''),
(264, 1, 'Soccer 360 Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nFeaturing the best of Premier League, Serie A, Bundesliga, La Liga and MLS Soccer . Plus complete coverage of the world’s biggest soccer events including the Champion’s League, Europa League, World Cup qualifying, and so much more. Tons of full color pictures, great interviews, team and player profiles, stats and so much more. The best in print quality: *Soccer 360 offers a unique Extra Large format size at 9.5” x 13.5” *features large format beautiful photos from the world’s best soccer photographers. *Plus most issues feature a 28” x 13” large full color Poster of the best players, teams and tournaments.\n\n', '', '', ''),
(265, 1, 'Scenario', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEvery day companies and organisations make decisions, that is, strategic decisions of great importance for the future. Decisions that often have to be made quickly. Contributing with knowledge and inspiration, the Copenhagen Institute for Futures Studies supports decision-making. We identify and analyse trends that influence the future nationally and internationally. Through research, analyses, seminars, presentations, reports, and newsletters, we give advice on the future. The objective of the Copenhagen Institute for Futures Studies is to strengthen the basis for decision-making in public and private organisations by creating awareness of the future and highlighting its importance to the present. Our work methods range from statistically based analysis and the identification of global trends, to more subjective emotional factors of importance to the future. The work of the Institute is interdisciplinary. The staff represents various fields of academic and professional backgrounds such as economics, political science, ethnography, psychology, engineering, PR and sociology. ', '', '', ''),
(266, 1, 'Fashizblack', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nMotivated by the will to create an alternative to the traditional Fashion media, and pushed forward by an extremely dynamic community, the FASHIZBLACK team decided to live up to its online audience expectations and to produce its first ever on-paper glossy issue in January 2012.\n\nAs a High-end magazine that talks about Fashion (African Fashion in particular), black Beauty and culture, this concept already gather 200.000 uniques readers a month online, and on social networks like Facebook, more than 30.000 fans. It is a bilingual magazine (French AND English texts), so it is perfect for international Fashionistas. Beauty &amp; Fashion tips, trends, culture, the latest news... We''re dealing with everything close to Fashion through our global and multicultural vision.\n', '', '', ''),
(267, 1, 'Tennis Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTENNIS USA covers the latest tour events from around the world with in-depth features on the top tennis stars.\n', '', '', ''),
(268, 1, 'Campagne Decoration', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCampagne Decoration is a collection of the latest and best innovations in countryside living interior design.\n\nIf you adore shabby chic, vintage designs and farmhouse boutiques then this is the magazine for you.\n\nWritten in French, it is riddled with beautiful design ideas for those with a budget, furniture suggestions and articles on how various things such as wool and fabric are made, alongside recipes and even gardening tips.\n\nDesign your own sanctuary and have a read on those who already have! There are loads or articles, shopping pages and gorgeous pictures of some of the loveliest homes I’ve even seen.\n', '', '', ''),
(269, 1, 'Elle-A-Table', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIn every issue of ELLE A TABLE you get new ideas about cooking and hosting dinner parties as well as the newest, most delicious recipes.\n', '', '', ''),
(270, 1, 'Vertical', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe international magazine for the amateurs and experts with an interest in climbing. Providing advice on equipment and clothing, the magazine features articles on climbs internationally as well as practical tips and advice.\n', '', '', ''),
(271, 1, 'Ideat (Fr)', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIdeat is a French language interior design and architecture magazine packed with great on how to decorate you home\n\nIdeat has examples of architecture and interior design from Paris and other regions in France, as well as design examples from around the globe.\n\nIdeats special features on how to tailor your home to your individual needs is inspirational and exciting.\n', '', '', ''),
(272, 1, 'Mod Zik', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n''Quand la Mode parle de Musique'' - this sums up perfectly the contents of this exciting French language magazine, which offers a fusion between the worlds of fashion and music. Referred to as the ''Uber Cool'' French magazine, MOD''ZIK features the hottest and most stylish names in music and fashion, from Jessie J and Lana del Rey to Carine Roitfeld.\n', '', '', ''),
(273, 1, 'Residences Decoration', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nInterior Design Magazine - Residence Decoration is a French-language publication featuring French modern interior design.\n', '', '', ''),
(274, 1, 'Graffiti Art', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGraffiti Art is a bilingual ''Urban Contemporary Art'' magazine - the first ever globalised art movement.\n\nSubscribe to Street Art for images and articles on some of the best graffiti and urban art from around the world. Features both French and English text.\n', '', '', ''),
(275, 1, 'Polka', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPolka is a French Language photography magazine for both amateurs and professionals alike.\n\nSubscribe to Polka Magazine for some awe inspiring photographs from all over the world, as well as tips and ideas, gadgets and more.\n', '', '', ''),
(276, 1, 'Maison Cote Ouest', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMAISON COTE OUEST is a magnificently illustrated magazine featuring the art of living in the regions of France from Brittany over Normandy to the Atlantic coastline. You will discover beautiful interiors of houses with an avant-garde appeal as well as those with a certain undeniable charm.\n', '', '', ''),
(277, 1, 'Marie Claire Idees', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Marie Claire Idées, printed in French, focuses on fashion and beauty and home decoration.\n\nThis bi monthly magazine subscription is packed full of easy to follow instructions for a wide range of crafts and projects. Seasonal recipies and ideas to decorate your home feature throughout along with great little hints and tips.\n', '', '', ''),
(278, 1, 'Marie Claire Maison', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPart of the Marie Claire family of magazines, Marie Claire Maison is designed to help women decipher the newest information on fashion, beauty, health, home decorating and the many other facets of the daily life of women in the 21st century. Printed in French language.\n', '', '', ''),
(279, 1, 'Maison Francaise', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMAISON FRANCAISE is a French magazine with exclusive furniture and design articles with modern and classic elements.\n', '', '', ''),
(280, 1, 'Art Et Decoration', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nART ET DECORATION, printed in French, is filled with ideas and how-to information for decorating all areas of the home and garden, including dinner table displays, flower arrangements, arts and crafts, and interior design tips for all rooms of the house.\n', '', '', ''),
(281, 1, 'Intramuros', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIntramuros Magazine analyses and processes all actuality of international design in all applications, objects architectural fashion and technology.\n\nIntramuros Magazine anticipates new tends of the market and enhances the impact of economic and creative industry\n', '', '', ''),
(282, 1, 'Maison Cote Sud', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMAISON COTE SUD is an international architecture and living magazine from France.\n', '', '', ''),
(283, 1, 'Demeures-Chateaux', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEvery 2 months, discover the cultural richness, the inheritance and the art of living in an area of France. Keep yourself informed on the last top-of-the-range real estate market trends and choose the residence of your dreams among our vast selection.\n', '', '', ''),
(284, 1, 'L''Architeccture D''Aujord''Hui', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nL’Architecture d’Aujourd’hui is the oldest French architectural magazine.\n\nIt was created during the economic crisis, in November 1930, by the architect, sculptor,painter and publisher Andre Bloc (1896 to 1966).\n\nL’Architecture d’Aujourd’hui from its first issue promoted the avant-garde and different movements and personalities of the architectural thinking behind “modernity” among whom Le Corbusier, who contributed to severalissues.\n\nL’Architecture d’Aujourd’hui also offers a cross disciplinary vision of period architecture mixing featured subjects,architecturalcreation, interviews with architects, urban and technical resources.\n', '', '', ''),
(285, 1, 'Burda Style Special', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBurda Fashion magazine brings you Burda Style special (previously Burda Plus Fashion) magazine, a magazine in the knitting and crochet section, with dozens of patterns for home sewing, projects, and tutorials for making clothes for women.\n\nWritten in English but published in Germany, Burda Style Special is issued eight times a year and also features fashion news, techniques and how-tos for European sizes 32-50.\n\nIt has loads of creative inspiration for women who love to sew, whatever their skill level', '', '', ''),
(286, 1, 'Spiegel Geschicht', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSPIEGEL GESCHICHT is a German history magazine. Examples of the SPIEGEL GESCHICHT topics have been Germany s past, a review of the life of Pope John Paul I and the background to the terrorist attacks of 11 September 2001 five years later. Unique about SPIEGEL GESCHICHT are the photo essays, explanatory timelines and clear diagrams provide a striking framework for editorial content.\n', '', '', ''),
(287, 1, 'Elle Decoration German', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nELLE DECORATION (GERMAN) showcases the very best of what''s modern, new, and beautiful in the world of interior design, whether it is high street or designer.\n', '', '', ''),
(288, 1, 'Idn Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIdN is a digital design magazine published bi-monthly and primarily catering to content creators and aesthetes throughout the world. It is currently available in four editions in two languages, English and Chinese.\n', '', '', ''),
(289, 1, 'Vogue Bambini It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVOGUE BAMBINI is an Italian magazine for Mums and Dads who like to dress their children in the latest fashions. VOGUE BAMBINI is packed full of stylish outfits and accessories for children.\n', '', '', ''),
(290, 1, 'Auto &amp; Design', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAUTO &amp; DESIGN is a beautiful quality publication for those interested in cars and their designs.\n', '', '', ''),
(291, 1, 'Area It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAREA IT is an Italian magazine which deals with architecture and design.\n', '', '', ''),
(292, 1, 'Wargames, Soldiers And Strategy', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIt''s time to play with history From the makers of Ancient Warfare, comes a new version of Wargames, Soldiers &amp; Strategy. Launching in April 2011, subscriptions are now available for pre-order. A new look, revamped content and gorgeous unique illustrations are all reasons to give this new old magazine a try.\n', '', '', ''),
(293, 1, 'Gup Guide To Unique Photography', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGUP is short for Guide to Unique Photography and assembles the most talked about and innovative Dutch photography of both prolific photographers and young talent in an unconventional, refreshing manner.\n', '', '', ''),
(294, 1, 'Mark', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMARK is fascinated by what''s going on in architecture. Mark has a radically international perspective. Mark is visually oriented. Mark offers context and opinions free of jargon. Mission: Mark wants to shake up the world of architectural publishing.\n', '', '', ''),
(295, 1, 'Frame', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFRAME is an international magazine of interior architecture and design. Each issue is devoted to innovative ideas and looks at a variety of creations situated both at home and in the workplace. FRAME features book reviews, lists upcoming events and fairs and recommends new products on the market.\n', '', '', ''),
(296, 1, 'Alef', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nAlef is an independent magazine published our of Doha, Qatar. Printed bi-monthly in a bilingual format (English and Arabic)the magazine focuses on cultural topics that are indigenous to the gulf region. Alef is for anyone who has a vested interest in Middle Eastern culture. Whether you are an artist or a doctor, a journalist or a tourist. Alef aims to educate both residents and visitors from all walks of life.\n', '', '', ''),
(297, 1, 'Winq', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWINQ INTERNATIONAL is the leading Dutch gay magazine.\n\nWINQ INTERNATIONAL has a specific Made In Amsterdam signature that is popular with gay men all over the world. This glossy men''s magazine focuses on popular topics like fashion, personal gadgets, entertainment, politics, culture, travel, interior design, health, cars and personal finance. It is considered common knowledge that gay men have great interest in such items.\n\nWINQ INTERNATIONAL is an upscale Gay lifestyle magazine. Similar in size , look and feel to Esquire - written from a Gay perspective - but with a strong element of fashion and very high production values.\n', '', '', ''),
(298, 1, 'Yishu Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nYishu is the journal of contemporary Chinese art and is published bi-monthly. Yishu is a leading journal in the coverage of contemporary Chinese art and culture. Each bi-monthly issue with over 112 pages presents scholarly and topical essays by the most knowledgeable writers in the field of Chinese art. Cultural commentary, featured artists, interviews, conference proceedings, and exhibition reviews provide a stimulating forum for dialogue and debate around the most important issues affecting contemporary Chinese culture and its position in the world today. Since its inauguration in 2002, Yishu has raised its profile internationally to become one of the most respected journals devoted to Chinese art, appealing to professionals in the academic fields, as well as art enthusiasts in general.\n', '', '', ''),
(299, 1, 'Brain Games', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGreat new magazine full of weird and wonderful logic and brain puzzles.\n\nIf you are bored of all the words and numbers involved in the other puzzle magazines, try a copy of this. It''s brilliatly different and will keep you busy for hours.\n', '', '', ''),
(300, 1, 'Original Sudoku', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDell magazine is pleased to introduce the hugely popular SUDOKU puzzles with the launching of ORIGINAL SUDOKU. It''s your chance to get in on the fun with the first news-stand magazines devoted exclusively to these captivating puzzles.\n', '', '', ''),
(301, 1, 'Step By Step Wire', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nStep By Step Wire Jewelry is all about beading and wire jewelry projects.\n\nEach issue shows you how to make stylish, fashionable jewelry, showing you designs with easy step by step photos and instructions.\n\nStep By Step Wire will keep you up to date on the latest jewelry designs and help create your own one of a kind jewelry.', '', '', ''),
(302, 1, 'Mad Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMAD USA takes a comical look at current stories hitting the headlines. None of the current movies and stars in the headlines escape MAD''s uniquely funny comments.\n', '', '', ''),
(303, 1, 'Hoop Nba', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNBA INSIDE STUFF now known as HOOP NBA features the latest news and articles on basketball stars and their winning games. It gives an insight into the stars, their special tips and skills which make them famous in the basketball world.\n', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `oc_product_description` (`product_id`, `language_id`, `name`, `description`, `meta_description`, `meta_keyword`, `tag`) VALUES
(304, 1, 'Aviation History', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAVIATION HISTORY features interviews with leading experts wihin the field, articles on aerobatic displays, plane reviews, readers letters, aerial oddities, upcoming events, an aviation marketplace featuring items such as military prints, video tapes and collectible models in addition to superb, high quality photography and editorial. AVIATION HISTORY is a must buy for any enthusiast.\n', '', '', ''),
(305, 1, 'Electric Flight', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nElectric Flight magazine attracts new model aviators into the hobby. Electric Flight covers all the new developments and product innovations in this Breakout RC market\n\nElectric Flight includes essential tips for proper plane assembly plus critical steps to first flight success.\n\nElectric Flight gives troubleshooting tips to keep planes running right and in depth and unbiased model reviews.\n', '', '', ''),
(306, 1, 'Archaeology', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nArchaeology magazine is published by the Archaeological Institute of America. The subscription for Archaeology magazine is bimonthly and seeks to combine worldwide archaeological findings with photography, specially rendered maps, drawings, and charts. Articles cover current excavations, recent discoveries, and special studies of ancient cultures. Regular features include timelines, news briefs, film and book reviews, current museum exhibits, The Forum. The subscription also offers travel and planning advice for Archaeological trips.\n', '', '', ''),
(307, 1, 'Craft Ideas', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCrafts Ideas is the only general craft magazine on the market at the moment which incorporates lots of different types of crafts into every issue.\n\nEach magazine will include a variety of methods and project ideas including sewing, needlework, paper crafts, stamping, painting, flower arranging, clay and beading.\n\nCrafts N Things magazine will offer readers useful resources as well as essential tips and guides. These are essential for any budding crafter who wants some more inspiration for their next project.\n', '', '', ''),
(308, 1, 'Film Comment', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFILM COMMENT appears bi-monthly and offers reviews of the latest blockbusters.\n', '', '', ''),
(309, 1, 'Fly Fisherman', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFLY FISHERMAN is the leading fly fishing magazine. Each issue is packed with features, news and practical advice. Tips include improving fishing skills, the best equipment to use and which waters are best for certain types of fish. FLY FISHERMAN features the latest innovations in materials for fresh and saltwater flies, readers own stories, letters and classified adverts. It also covers farawary fishing destinations for the more adventurous enthusiasts! For everything there is to know about fly fishing, FLY FISHERMAN has it all.\n', '', '', ''),
(310, 1, 'Kung Fu Tai Chi', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nKUNG FU is the ultimate magazine on this ancient art. It covers the latest tournaments from around the world in this ever-developing form of self-defence.\n', '', '', ''),
(311, 1, 'Mother Jones', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMother Jones is an independent magazine rooted in liberal and progressive political values. It is widely known for its investigative reporting. The winner of national Magazine Awards for General Excellence in 2001 and 2008 The stated mission of Mother Jones is to produce revelatory journalism that in its power and reach informs and inspires a more just and democratic world.\n', '', '', ''),
(312, 1, 'Tae Kwon Do Times', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTAE KWON DO TIMES is the leading martial arts publication devoted to the traditional martial art and Olympic sport of Tae Kwon Do. Covering all aspects of the art and including articles on self defence: the latest training techniques, world-renowned masters, instructors and competitors, health &amp; fitness, Eastern thought, philosophy, history and weaponry.\n', '', '', ''),
(313, 1, 'Todays Black Woman', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTODAYS BLACK WOMAN is an essential buy for the black woman of today offering advice on relationships and love. Eash issue features fashion, hot beauty tips, health issues, food, travel, book reviews and more.\n', '', '', ''),
(314, 1, 'Truck Trend', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTRUCK TREND is written for the total truck enthusiast and covers the full spectrum of activities enjoyed by the owners of pickup trucks, sport utility vehicles and vans. A variety of feature articles include single and multi-vehicle tests, road trips, reports on future designs and trends, and a look at the latest in personal accessories for work and play.\n', '', '', ''),
(315, 1, 'Upscale Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA magazine for the sophisticated and successful, UPSCALE celebrates black culture while informing and entertaining its readers with compelling profiles and articles about travel, health and fitness, beauty and fashion, business, relationships and more.\n', '', '', ''),
(316, 1, 'Biblical-Archaeology-Review', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBiblical Archaeology Review is a bi-monthly magazine whose aim is to connect the more academic study of archaeology to a more general audience.\n\nIts focus examines the archaeological record and ongoing excavations that sheds light on the word of the Bible.\n\nIn particular this leads it to focus on the near and middle-east which holds the greatest wealth of Biblical treasure troves just waiting to be uncovered. History lurks buried within the sands, and Biblical Archaeology Review is the first stop for those with a thirst to know the true history of the world and how it and Biblical scripture are intertwined .\n', '', '', ''),
(317, 1, 'Big City Rhythm &amp; Blues', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBLUES Magazine builds bridges between the Music, the Artists, the Industry, and the Fans of Legendary Rhythm &amp; Blues.\n\nThe recipient of numerous music industry awards, including the &quot;Keeping the Blues Alive&quot; Award in Print Media, BIG CITY BLUES is devoted to listeners and musicians whose musical passion is the full spectrum of R&amp;B..\n\nBIG CITY BLUES presents articles and interviews on today’s leading blues musicians in ALL the great Blues Cities, historical features on Blues Greats, calendar of events &amp; Blues Festivals worldwide..\n\nThe magazine creates incomparable CD samplers of the best in R&amp;B music, and is a true ''cure for the blues'' with every issue..\n\nBeing a truly American creation, ''the Blues'' laid the groundwork for all contemporary music - from Rock N’ Roll to Jazz..\n\nBIG CITY BLUES is compiled by leading blues musicians, researchers and musicologists. The foremost authority covering the world''s famous Blues cities, BIG CITY BLUES is the essential &amp; required resource for R&amp;B listeners and musicians alike.\n', '', '', ''),
(318, 1, 'Cooks Illustrated', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAll you need to know about cooking, with useful tips, tricks and methods. Not to mention some mouth watering recipes!\n', '', '', ''),
(319, 1, 'Quiltmaker', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nQuiltmaker magazine is a step-by-step, how-to quilt magazine devoted to beginning and intermediate quilters.\n\nQuiltmaker magazine helps quilters of all skill levels develop the necessary skills to succeed at making beautiful quilts. Each issue of Quiltmaker rates the complexity of each project and features a variety of styles and techniques. The projects within Quiltmaker magazine provide clear instructions, accurate yardages, as well as tips, shortcuts and additional colors patterns. Quiltmaker also reviews new products of interest to quilt makers.\n\nQuiltmaker is one of America''s top needlework/quilting magazines for craft fans. Colour pictures and free patterns make this a must-read for all fans of home made quilts. Subscribe today!\n', '', '', ''),
(320, 1, 'Running Times', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nRunning Times magazine is written to help runners improve their performance. A subscription to Running Times magazine is the dedicated runner''s best source for expert information on training, racing, sports medicine, inspiration, news, profiles and more.\n\nRunning Times magazine also features a comprehensive events calendar as well as features and columns on training, injury prevention, running apparel, exercise physiology and nutrition.\n\nRunning Times is written by runners for runners!\n', '', '', ''),
(321, 1, 'Tribal Tattoo One', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe ultimate guide to tattooing with hundreds of ideas for your perfect tattoo\n', '', '', ''),
(322, 1, 'Woodworkers Journal', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWoodworker''s Journal Magazine features page after page of great sort after projects, patterns and drawings that eliminate guesswork. Step-by-step instructions and full-size patterns are valuable for beginners and veteran woodworkers alike, and you''ll stay up-to-date on the latest equipment and products with it''s shop tests and tool reviews. The tips and techniques featured in every issue of Woodworkers Journal will help enhance your skills.\n', '', '', ''),
(323, 1, 'Art Jewelry', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAn Art Jewelery magazine subscription offers readers an outstanding gallery of some of the most outstanding work by highly skilled artisans. The pieces on display in this Art Jewelery magazine subscription vary in the techniques of creation and also in the level of difficulty. All of the pieces displayed in this Art Jewelery magazine subscription offer both originality and grace.\n', '', '', ''),
(324, 1, 'Beadstyle', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFor those who have some free time and are looking for a project to keep them busy, Bead Style magazine contains plenty of innovative design ideas in jewellery making with instructions suitable for all levels of skill. Whether it’s a way to express yourself or even to make a little money from, jewellery making can be brilliant fun.\n\nLearn how to co-ordinate styles, trends and colours, as well as how to manipulate metal and thread to create stunning designs.\n\nA brilliant artistic outlet for anyone who thinks they may have a creative eye for style\n', '', '', ''),
(325, 1, 'Bust Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBust magazine is according to the publication’s front cover, ‘for women with something to get off their chests’.\n\nIt is a lifestyle and fashion publication which is ideal for the independent women out there who want a unique magazine with interesting thought provoking articles as well as all the usual features which women love in other lifestyle magazines.\n\nThere will be celebrity interviews, real life stories and features on arts and crafts.\n', '', '', ''),
(326, 1, 'Crochet World', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCrochet World bills itself as “The Magazine For Crochet Lovers” and it certainly is that.\n\nWith comprehensive and clear how-tos and step-by-step instructions, Crochet World is a useful and practical American publication that guarantees to dazzle crochet lovers everywhere.\n\nIt carries full colour photos, pattern suggestions, as well as news of the crochet community, useful products to help you crochet, and projects you can undertake\n', '', '', ''),
(327, 1, 'Flight Journal', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFLIGHT JOURNAL captures the vital spirit, the drama and the evolution of aviation. Includes rare aircraft, extraordinary people and remarkable stories.\n', '', '', ''),
(328, 1, 'Psychology Today', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPsychology Today magazine offers a unique perspective on total health - total health being attained by achieving balance, which is the direct result of a healthy perspective on life. A subscription to Psychology Today magazine will help you to explore the emotional, physical, and spiritual aspects of daily life.\n\nWritten by the foremost professionals in the field of human behavior, each bimonthly issue of Psychology Today delivers articles on a wide variety of topics.\n', '', '', ''),
(329, 1, 'Quick Quilts', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nQuick Quilts magazine comes from the same publisher as the popular magazine McCall''s Quilting.\n\nQuick Quilts magazine features traditional and contemporary patterns, with an emphasis on modern quilting. The magazine has broad appeal with its fresh approach and content.\n\nQuick Quilts is the perfect resource for quilting beginners containing beautifully photographed, well-designed quick and easy quilting projects with complete how-to instructions. Each issue of Quick Quilts magazine shows readers how to use the latest tools, fabrics and techniques to complete their quilting projects beautifully. Quick Quilts magazine provides the quiltmaking fundamentals and techniques, step-by-step instructions and color diagrams of patterns for rotary cutting and machine quilting.\n\nEach issue of your Quick Quilts magazine subscription is stylish with original ideas and includes free pattern designs in every issue. A guide not to be missed by any quilting enthusiast.\n', '', '', ''),
(330, 1, 'Quilters Newsletter', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nQUILTERS NEWSLETTER is one of America''s top quilting magazines. It provides practical advice and fantastic free patterns. Accessible to all quilting enthusiasts.\n', '', '', ''),
(331, 1, 'Switchback', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSwitchback features in-depth product and gear reviews, dirt culture, travel/destination stories and the long-form features and inspiring photography. Buy a subscription to this great cycling magazine today.\n', '', '', ''),
(332, 1, 'American Songwriter', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAmerican Songwriter is a source of inspiration for passionate music fans and songwriters alike.\n\nAmerican Songwriter covers every aspect of the craft and art of song writing, from how and why writers give birth to their songs, to engaging and information assessments of our sing writing culture as a whole.\n\nAmerican Songwriter includes in depth interviews with up and coming established and legendry song writers as well as producers and other industry representatives who cover all genres of music.\n', '', '', ''),
(333, 1, 'Bhg Do It Yourself', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEverything you need to know to make magnificent memory pages. You''ll find hot new techniques along with scrapbooking basics and tools. Step-by-step instructions, snapshot savvy, and try-it techniques in every issue.\n', '', '', ''),
(334, 1, 'Clean Eating', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCLEAN EATING magazine is like having your very own dietician, cookbook and instruction manual rolled into one beautiful magazine. Each issue is filled with the tools, tips, facts, tricks, inspiration and advice you need to get started on your clean-eating lifestyle. Clean Eating works!\n', '', '', ''),
(335, 1, 'Electronic Gamimg Monthly', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nElectronic Gaming Monthly is a bi-monthly American video game monthly\n\nElectronic Gaming Monthly offers video game news, coverage of industry events, interviews with gaming figureheads, editorial content, and products reviews.\n\nPrior to the 2010 re launch we have widened its coverage to the PC and mobile gaming markets.\n', '', '', ''),
(336, 1, 'Video Watchdog', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHorror, science fiction, mystery, film noir, animation, exploitation, sleaze, martial arts, fantasy from ''Beauty and the Beast'' to the BOND series, even the most dreamlike examples of European and Asian art and the BOND series, even the most dreamlike examples of European and Asian art and action cinema ~ if it stands\n\nOutside the Mainstream,&quot; if it takes film afficionados outside the bounds of their own imaginations, Mainstream,&quot; imaginations, it''s VIDEO WATCHDOG material! Mainstream,&quot; if it takes film afficionados outside the bounds of their own imaginations\n', '', '', ''),
(337, 1, 'Military History', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMilitary History Magazine subscription features the most authoritative, in-depth articles on the history of warfare from ancient times to the 20th century. Articles focus on military tactics, strategy, wartime leaders and famous campaigns.\n\nEach issue of your Military History magazine subscription provides compelling, incisive accounts from top writers and historians of land, naval and air warfare, all illustrated with the world''s finest artwork, photography and battle maps.\n', '', '', ''),
(338, 1, 'Threads', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO THREADS Magazines From Abroad?\n\nA must-read if you''re interested in sewing, a subscription to Threads magazine will keep you up to date with the most exciting new trends, whilst also offering step by step troubleshooting guides to help you overcome common sewing issues.\n\nLearn more about how you can achieve the perfect fit for the items you sew, how to tailor your own designs, the best way to select the right patterns and how you can find the right fabric to make your own masterpieces at home.\n\nThis knitting and sewing magazine will be a valuable source of inspiration when you''re looking to create your own clothes, curtains and accessories.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThreads magazine is packed with a wide variety of brilliant tips, exciting ideas, up to date news and the latest products from the stitching world. Threads Magazine is an inspirational sewing magazine focused on sewing and embellishing fashionable garments and sewn home furnishings. Perfect for beginners or novices, a subscription to Threads magazine shows you clearly how to master each step of the sewing process.\n', '', '', ''),
(339, 1, 'American Patch And Quilt', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAn American Patch and Quilt magazine subscription focuses on highly detailed patchwork projects that are laid out in each particular issue. A subscription to American Patch and Quilt magazine is a must for anyone with a real passion for quilting and patch work.\n\nThe subscription for American Patch and Quilt magazine is great for providing tips, inspiration and ideas for your next quilting project.\n', '', '', ''),
(340, 1, 'Car Kulture Delux', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThis magazine is for fans of the best vintage cars and related products. Car Kulture Deluxe is filled with articles about a variety of vintage cars and their life stories recounted by their owners.\n\nThere are also features about a range of car shows and events. The magazine has regular ‘deluxe girls’ in every issue, who are not only pretty to look at but also share their vintage car passions with the reader.\n', '', '', ''),
(341, 1, 'Just Cross Stitch', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nJUST CROSS STITCH is made for cross-stitchers by cross-stitchers who share a love for this needle art. Each issue contains wonderful designs for all levels of expertise and regular features that teach the basics and specilaity stitches. Articles are both entertaining and informative. All needlework designs are presented in full colour.\n', '', '', ''),
(342, 1, 'Motorcycle Classics', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMOTORCYCLE CLASSICS: dedicated to the greatest motorcycles of all time and the people who ride them. Every page of MOTORCYCLE CLASSICS is tailored to the readers'' interests, providing owners, riders and enthusiasts the insight and information they want about their favourite classic motorcycles from around the world. From Aermachhis to Ariels and Hondas to Harleys, MOTORCYCLE CLASSICS covers it all!\n', '', '', ''),
(343, 1, 'Ol Skool Rodz', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nOl'' Skool Rodz is a hot rod magazine for the builders and drivers of the cars. The tech articles don''t feature purchased bolt-on items. This magazine has a huge cult following and is considered an informative view of the Modern Kustom Culture lifestyle. Many of its articles are often written in a humorous style, often sending up the high-end car enthusiasts, legislators and even Kustom Kulture itself.\n', '', '', ''),
(344, 1, 'Photo Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPHOTO LIFE features photographic knowledge reflecting an appreciation of the art, culture and science of photography. Each issue is packed with readers letters, photo news, book reviews, advice, imaging product reviews, field test reports and more!\n', '', '', ''),
(345, 1, 'Popular Woodworking', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPopular Woodworking magazine is one of America''s best project magazines. Popular Woodworking magazine includes projects using techiques such as chip carving, product reviews and advice, reviews popular woodworking books and recommends woodworking shows where there are free demonstrations and showcases of new tools. Popular Woodworking magazine even suggests where to take woodworking classes!\n\nEach issue of your Popular Woodworking subscription is packed with at least 15 projects all presented using clear instructions, detailed diagrams, and accurate cutting lists.\n', '', '', ''),
(346, 1, 'Skin Art', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n100''s of different tattoo ideas in every issue.\n', '', '', ''),
(347, 1, 'Smooth', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSMOOTH is a magazine which casts an unflinching eye toward anything and everything of interest to young men of colour. A lifestyle magazine, SMOOTH fits a gap in the urban market, providing smart commentary on issues that affect today''s black man. Inside, readers will find a wide breadth of coverage with 60% of its editorial focusing on entertainment, including music, movies, television and technology. The rest of the magazine''s glossy pages are dedicated to both light and hard news, culture, humour and politics. In addition, each issue of SMOOTH will feature a photo album of the sexiest black models and actresses in the world.\n', '', '', ''),
(348, 1, 'American Scientist', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAmerican Scientist is an illustrated bimonthly magazine about science and technology. Each issue is filled with feature articles written by prominent scientists and engineers, reviewing important work in fields that range from molecular biology to computer engineering\n\nThe articles are carefully edited and accompanied by illustrations that are developed to enhance the reader''s understanding and enjoyment..\n', '', '', ''),
(349, 1, 'Hairdo', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSpectacular hairstyles to suit all, with handy tips on ''how to''. Packed with helpful articles and great pictures.\n', '', '', ''),
(350, 1, 'Iphone Life Smart Phones', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe ultimate destination for iPhone and iPod touch users, featuring iPhone Life, the only print magazine for iPhone and iPod touch users.\n', '', '', ''),
(351, 1, 'Mccalls Quilting', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nOne of America''s leading quilting magazines, McCALL''S QUILTING, offers practical advice, beautiful colour pictures and regularly features free quilting patterns. Each issue offers a broad wealth of knowledge and is a must-read for all quilting enthusiasts.\n', '', '', ''),
(352, 1, 'Pilates Style', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPILATES STYLE is the only magazine devoted to Pilates and the Pilates lifestyle with essential information and tips for a healthy, active lifestyle.\n', '', '', ''),
(353, 1, 'Tattoos For Men', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n100''s of tattoos especially geared towards men\n', '', '', ''),
(354, 1, 'Tattoos For Women', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n100''s of tattoos especially geared towards women\n', '', '', ''),
(355, 1, 'Electric Bike Action', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe sudden growth of these unique bikes will have enthusiasts all over looking for a copy.\n\nWhether you are looking for e-bikes for recreational fun, weekday commuting, or just the technological and environmental solutions they offer.\n\nWe think you will find something here that will no doubt act as a catalyst to draw you deeper into the world of e-bikes. It is time to discover the wild frontier of e-bikes.\n', '', '', ''),
(356, 1, 'Pro Wrestling Illustrated', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPRO WRESTLING ILLUSTRATED is the definitive guide to the world of wrestling. Regular features include interviews with top wrestlers and personality profiles of who is making it big.\n', '', '', ''),
(357, 1, 'Cloth Paper Scissors', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCloth Paper Scissors was first published in the US in October 2004. Published six times a year, Cloth Paper Scissors covers all types of fibre arts and collage work, including mixed media, rubber stamping, creative embroidery plus assemblage, altered books, art dolls, visual art journals, and book arts.\n', '', '', ''),
(358, 1, 'Freshly Inked', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThis high quality quarterly features hundreds of design ideas as well as acting as a platform for fresh new tattooist art talent.\n', '', '', ''),
(359, 1, 'Nail It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNAIL IT! shows that nails are a stunning accessory and more - they are an essential part of an overall fashion statement.\n\nFrom red carpets to runways, from hair and makeup to health and lifestyle issues..\n\nA subscription to NAIL IT! connects nail lovers with the professional nail products and services that make up this glamourous, creative, daring segment of the world of beauty.\n', '', '', ''),
(360, 1, 'Quilting Arts', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nQuilting Arts magazine covers the latest techniques in art quilting, embellished quilting, wearable arts, mixed media, surface design and other textile arts.\n\nYour subscription to Quilting Arts magazine will cover a wide range of skills, includes exceptional how-to articles, answering readers'' questions, guest artists and teachers.\n\nQuilting Arts magazine addresses a wide range of skills including surface embroidery, thread painting, stamping, beading, silk ribbon embroidery and fabric painting.\n', '', '', ''),
(361, 1, 'Rebel Rodz', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGet ready to burn rubber on the ride of a lifetime. Every issue of REBEL RODZ is jam packed with the best and most creative builders, fabricators and artists in the wild worlds of wicked rides, seductive skin art, custom paint and graphics, music and more. The magazine also includes product reviews, technical articles and coverage from hot rod, bike and tattoo shows.\n', '', '', ''),
(362, 1, 'Road Runner', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRoad Runner magazine is produced by motorcycle enthusiasts passionate about riding, for other enthusiasts equally passionate about riding and touring on their bikes. The intention is to scout out the roads less travelled and share them with you.\n', '', '', ''),
(363, 1, 'Ufc Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nUFC gives fight fans a deeper look into the world of UFC athletes than any other media property today.\n\nOur unfettered access to fighters and events allows us to produce behind the scenes photos and stories that readers cannot find anywhere else..\n\nThe magazine covers all aspects of the UFC athletes but also gives readers the latest information on consumer electronics, video games, music, cars, celebrities and fashion. .\n\nUFC provide a look at pop culture and general men''s interest as seen through the lens of the Ultimate Fighting Championship. Subscribe to UFC Magazine, dispatched worldwide.\n', '', '', ''),
(364, 1, 'Black Belt', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBlack Belt magazine is produced in the US. The magazine is one of the world''s leading magazines for self defence.\n\nIt was started in 1961 and since then it has been offering readers the most authoritative coverage of all aspects of the traditional fighting arts.\n\nIt will give readers helpful new techniques to improve their moves as well as interviews with inspirational champions in the sector.\n', '', '', ''),
(365, 1, 'Kitchen &amp; Bath Ideas', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nKitchen &amp; Bath Ideas is full of ideas, inspiration and information about the latest products and trends you need when planning a kitchen or bath project. Featured kitchens and baths showcase a range of styles from traditional to contemporary. Beautiful, full-color photographs convey a real-people/real-solutions approach to home design.\n', '', '', ''),
(366, 1, 'Shambhala Sun', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nShambhala Sun is today''s most widely-read Buddhist magazine. You''ll find real wisdom for the real world applied to all the important issues in life - from livelihood, parenting, and relationships to politics, social action, and the arts.\n', '', '', ''),
(367, 1, 'Tattoo Society', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTATTOO SOCIETY is a art magazine which focus is on tattoo art and artists and gives a perfect look inside the tattoo society.\n', '', '', ''),
(368, 1, 'Creative Machine Embroidery', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEach issue provides current trends, techniques and step-by-step instructions to the home embroiderer. Through detailed information, easy-to-read print and web formats, Creative Machine Embroidery magazine brings embroidery to life.\n', '', '', ''),
(369, 1, 'American Photo', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAn American Photo is the essential magazine for everyone who is passionately interested in the art, craft and culture of photography at its highest level.\n\nEach issue provides a showcase of inspiring imagery, tells the stories behind the photographs, and identifies the trends, people, themes and tools that photography enthusiasts must know about now.\n', '', '', ''),
(370, 1, 'Vegan Health &amp; Fitness', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVegan Health &amp; Fitness is a health and fitness magazine geared specifically toward plant-based health and good living.\n', '', '', ''),
(371, 1, 'Natural Health Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNATURAL HEALTH introduces you to a world of natural foods, self care, alternative medicine, spiritual well being, herbal remedies, vitamins and supplements, and the remarkable healing power of natural health.\n', '', '', ''),
(372, 1, 'Sew Beautiful', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFor over 15 years SEW BEAUTIFUL has captivated sewing enthusiasts from around the world. Treasured for the pages filled with expert information, inspiration and a free pattern included in each issue. SEW BEAUTIFUL has opened up an entirely new world of creativity for countless readers, offering pages of designs, techniques and ideas.\n', '', '', ''),
(373, 1, 'Small Business Opportunities', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAs the title suggests, SMALL BUSINESS OPPORTUNITIES is aimed at budding businesspeople and contains practical suggestions on ways of making money and gaining a competitive edge.\n', '', '', ''),
(374, 1, 'The Source', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe Source magazine covers all the latest news from the world of Hip Hop, Rap and Soul. The Source is the leading magazine in the Hip Hop sector and has the advantage of bringing the latest news from the Hip Hop world to the market first. As hip-hop continues to drive youth culture, dominate the charts and redefine rock &amp; roll, The Source magazine has become it''s driving force. Being the pioneers for this genre, more than 5 million readers come to The Source each month for the most reliable, respected and credible coverage of hip-hop music.\n', '', '', ''),
(375, 1, 'Garden Railways', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGARDEN RAILWAYS has 140 pages packed with fantastic features on making a great garden railway with minimal cost and loads of varied garden design ideas. Includes great new product testing and essential maintenance tips.\n', '', '', ''),
(376, 1, 'Nylon Guys', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNYLON GUYS is a custom blend of what guys want: from gadgets, gizmos, and gear, to cool jeans, celebrity and music coverage, super-scents, and grooming. The latest sneakers, cars, and tech-toys are showcased in a street-chic format that avoids the pandering tone of other men.s magazines. NYLON GUYS has all the style and substance of the original NYLON, but with its sleeves rolled up, the windows, down, and the music cranking.\n', '', '', ''),
(377, 1, 'Otaku Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEach issue of OTAKU USA will include one of the top serialised Manga series, coverage of the latest Anime releases, coverage of popculture trends in japan and games.\n', '', '', ''),
(378, 1, 'American-Craft', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAn American Craft magazine subscription provides a feast for any creative spirit interested in traditional crafts. The subscription to American Craft magazine celebrates contemporary craft and artisans as well as focussing on achievements within the craft media industry. This is a bimonthly magazine subscription for American Craft magazine celebrates all things made by hand - and stays true to its core values of ''community, sustainability, quality and authenticity''.\n', '', '', ''),
(379, 1, 'Classic Motorsports', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nClassic Motorsports, for car enthusiasts of all types and interests\n', '', '', ''),
(380, 1, 'Diabolique', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEngage your heart, your mind and your taste for terror as you enter the realm of the fantastic within the pages of Diabolique magazine.\n\nDiabolique is a lavishly illustrated, bimonthly print and digital magazine exploring every aspect of horror film, literature and art..\n\nThe magazine’s focus on critical perspectives brings fresh analyses to subjects old and new, foreign and domestic – from ancient folklore and Gothic classics to contemporary film releases and modern literary gems..\n\nEach issue brims with insightful commentary, criticism and engrossing information complemented by photos, illustrations and handsome, full-color design. .\n\nPast issues have included contributors from such horror luminaries as Jonathan Rigby, David Del Valle, David Huckvale, Paul Murray, and Elizabeth Miller.\n', '', '', ''),
(381, 1, 'Dub', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDUB is the magazine where Car &amp; Driver meets The Source. If you are interested in the hottest rides and the celebrities who drive them, you have come to the right place. From the worlds of music, sports and film, including Shaquille O''Neal, Ice-T, Tony Hawk, Brian McKnight, and many more, DUB readers will see all the biggest stars and their luxurious cars.\n', '', '', ''),
(382, 1, 'Knit &amp; Style', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHundreds of Knitting patterns in every issue\n', '', '', ''),
(383, 1, 'Designs In Machine Embroidery', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDesigns in Machine Embroidery Magazine is the leading resource for machine embroidery enthusiasts. The magazine motivates readers of all abilities with wonderfully creative how-to projects and insightful columns. Every issue contains four departments: Wearables, Home Decor, Crafts and Quilts. With features that both instruct and inspire, Designs in Machine Embroidery is the definitive reference for the machine embroidery industry.\n', '', '', ''),
(384, 1, 'Digital Photopro', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDIGITAL PHOTOPRO is filled with detailed gear reviews, articles on technique and the best inspiring images, Digital Photo Pro is the professional''s guide to going digital.\n', '', '', ''),
(385, 1, 'Just For Black Men', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHere''s THE magazine for black men! JUST FOR BLACK MEN is for the man who wants to be the best he can be in all areas.\n\nIt''s about health, sports, living, loving, grooming, business, fashion and women!\n', '', '', ''),
(386, 1, 'Fitness Rx For Men', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFITNESS RX FOR MEN is the ultimate prescription for the perfect body. It is where science meets reality, enabling every man to look good, feel good and surpass his expectations of a healthy and fulfilling lifestyle.\n', '', '', ''),
(387, 1, 'Wooden Boat', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWooden Boat Magazine has been published since 1974, and is written for wooden boat owners, builders, and designers. This publication provides readers with a dynamic editorial environment that combines emerging technologies with traditional methods of boat design, construction and repair. The magazine is about craftsmanship in wood, and its active boating audience works at all levels of expertise to build, restore, and maintain their boats.\n\nRegular articles offer intelligent exploration into wooden boat design and restoration, ranging from simple skiffs to Gold Cuppers. Practical advice from experts around the world give Wooden Boat''s hands-on readership workable solutions to the challenges presented by wooden boat construction.\n', '', '', ''),
(388, 1, 'Animal Wellness Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nAnimal Wellness is North America''s top natural health and lifestyle magazine for dogs and cats. This educational and highly respected bi-monthly publication provides consumers with everything they need to know from the best natural foods and products to integrative veterinary advice, book reviews and healthy recipes! Now with a bonus section dedicated to everything feline!\n', '', '', ''),
(389, 1, 'Equine Wellness Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nEquine Wellness magazine is a well-respected and sought-after resource, appealing to horse enthusiasts in all disciplines. Each issue highlights the products and services that help give horses a longer and better quality of life. Empower yourself with leading edge information on integrative health, natural diet, supplements, natural horsemanship, complimentary therapies, barefoot hoof care and so much more.\n', '', '', ''),
(390, 1, 'Ivc Journal Integrative Veterinary Care Journal', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nIVC Journal bridges the gap between the worlds of allopathic and holistic veterinary care. Thousands of veterinarians and vet technicians are interested in ways to enhance their practice and integrative health is what their clients are asking for. IVC Journal discusses market trends in health treatments, new product features, industry news, leading modalities, nutrition education as well as Tech Talk focused on keeping vet technicians on top of alternatives and opportunities within the veterinary industry.\n', '', '', ''),
(391, 1, 'Show', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThis title covers various areas of men s interest such as cars gadgets and predominantly showcases black women through tasteful, high quality portraits of beautiful women.\n', '', '', ''),
(392, 1, 'Home Shop Machinist, The', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Home Shop Machinist Magazine is loaded with machining projects, techniques and improvements for the metalworking hobbyist. Home Shop Machinist includes topics ranging from machine repair to the building and operation of CNC-controlled equipment. With Home Shop Machinist, novice machinists can learn valuable procedures, while advanced machinists can find involved projects to challege their skills.\n', '', '', ''),
(393, 1, 'Collectable Automobile', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCOLLECTABLE AUTOMOBILE features informative editorial from a team of experienced motoring journalists who take a no-nonsense approach to everything from vintage and veteran through to modern day classics.\n', '', '', ''),
(394, 1, 'Fine Woodworking', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nFINE WOODWORKING is an exceptionally high quality publication covering the practical, creative and artistic aspects of this popular craft.\n', '', '', ''),
(395, 1, 'Fine Homebuilding', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFINE HOMEBUILDING is full of tips, techniques and wonderful ideas for all D.I.Y. fanatics. It provides expert advice on the finest materials and the best tools. FINE HOMEBUILDING also includes detailed reviews, letters and answers readers'' D.I.Y. questions.\n', '', '', ''),
(396, 1, 'Surface', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSURFACE is the only magazine that gives sophisticated, style-conscious young consumers a genuinely entertaining look at the world of style, fashion and design. SURFACE reports first and in-depth on what''s happening at the cutting edge of culture. The stunning, surprising visuals and fast paced storytelling takes the readers beyond the surface and into the substance of style.\n', '', '', ''),
(397, 1, 'Guitar Aficionado', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWelcome to Guitar Aficionado, the magazine for passionate people who enjoy the guitar in all it s timeless and functional beauty. As the greatest vintage guitars become rarer, love for the guitar and for what it represents continues to transcend generations\n', '', '', ''),
(398, 1, 'Dupont Registry Boats', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDU PONT REGISTRY BOATS is a buyers gallery of fine boats. It features the best traditional boats and beautiful yachts with a spirit of tradition. Packed with useful ideas and information, as well as classified ads, DU PONT REGISTRY BOATS is a must-read for any boat owner.\n', '', '', ''),
(399, 1, 'Fitness Rx For Women', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFITNESS RX takes a refreshing new scientific approach to enable every woman to become the very best she can be. Each issue will feature authoritative well-researched articles on everything from diet, nutrition and exercise to general fitness, health and cosmetic enhancement.\n', '', '', ''),
(400, 1, 'Teddy Bear Review', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTeddy Bear Review Magazine celebrates the joy of collecting by introducing readers to the best teddy bears from around the world, along with the artists and designers who create them.\nWith hundreds of beautiful full-color photographs of new and vintage teddies, Teddy Bear Review offers easy-to-read, informative articles to help collectors select the best buys.\n\nTeddy Bear Review visits major museum collections throughout the world showing readers how they can assemble quality collections.\n\nAs an important member of the teddy bear industry, the magazine sponsors an annual competition, the prestigious Golden Teddy Awards. Competitors are nominated by independent judges and voted on by subscribers. Winners are announced at the annual Doll and Teddy Bear Expo held every August in Washington, D.C.\n', '', '', ''),
(401, 1, 'The Golfer', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Golfer Magazine is a bi-monthly publication celebrating the lifestyle of the game. Each issue of The Golfer includes photography of classic courses and articles about the greatest golfing destinations. The Golfer provides the hottest and finest equipment on the market including reviews and information on the latest wheels for the course. Also included in each issue of The Golfer are interviews and facinating accounts with the most intriguing personalities from the golf course. The Golfer keeps readers on top of the latest trends both on and off the course, including stylish accessories, books, related arts and technology. The Golfer is the magazine for golfers whose lifestyles are shaped by their passion for the game.\n', '', '', ''),
(402, 1, 'Women''S Basketball', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWomen''s Basketball is a magazine covering women''s hoops. It interviews standout players, looks back on pioneers of the game, tracks WNBA, college, and high school action, and delivers exciting photos in every quarterly issue.\n', '', '', ''),
(403, 1, 'Field Artillery Journal', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nField Artillery is a bimonthly magazine published by the US Army Field Artillery, Fort Sill, Oklahoma, for Army and Marine Field Artillerymen stationed around the world. As stated in the Field Artillery Journal, first published in 1911, the purpose of the magazine is to disseminate professional knowledge and furnish information as to the artillery''s progress, development and best use in campaign; to cultivate with the other arms a common understanding of the power and limitations of each; to foster a feeling of interdependence among the different arms and of hearty cooperation by all; and to promote understanding between the regular and militia forces by forging a close bond--all of which objects are worthy and contribute to the good of our country.\n', '', '', ''),
(404, 1, 'Yachts International', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nYACHTS INTERNATIONAL IS THE WORLDWIDE LEADER IN THE MEGA YACHT CATEGORY with its sophisticated global editorial reach, superior distribution, high-profile events, digital presence and exclusive partnership with the industry’s leading boat shows.\n\nThe magazine is written for the knowledgeable and passionate yachtsman and is designed to inform readers so they are better able to make educated decisions on purchasing, servicing or outfitting a yacht.\n\nDiversified and timely subject matter is recorded by some of the most talented writers and photographers in marine media and presented through recurring features such as industry news, yacht features, sea trials, boat show reviews, technical files, shipyard visits, designer profiles, captains’ interviews and destinations annual\n', '', '', ''),
(405, 1, 'Foreign Policy', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFOREIGN POLICY contains in-depth articles from the world''s leading political and social commentators on global foreign policy and affairs. It contains all the latest news and devleopments from around the world, keeping the reader up to date on the current situation.\n', '', '', ''),
(406, 1, 'The Fader', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTHE FADER is a New York Music lifestyle magazine, with an eclectic mix from The Clash to The Strokes, Hip Hop to Indie by way of the Reggae scene. THE FADER gets exclusive interviews with world famous celebrities and underground stars alike.\n', '', '', ''),
(407, 1, 'Print', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPRINT is a general-interest magazine, engagingly written by cultural reporters and critics who look at design in its social, political, and historical contexts. From newspapers and book covers to Web-based motion graphics, from corporate branding to indie-rock posters, from exhibitions to cars to monuments, PRINT shows its audience of designers, art directors, illustrators, photographers, educators, students, and enthusiasts of popular culture why our world looks the way it looks, and why the way it looks matters. PRINT''s design matters too: In 2005 it unveiled a sweeping, cohesive redesign that gracefully embodies its sharp, elegant analysis and reporting\n', '', '', ''),
(408, 1, 'Rat Rod', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nExperience the stunning visuals and high-quality production that has earned Rat Rod Magazine worldwide renown. Think rat rods are an underground fad? Think again. Dive into the automotive world''s fastest growing scene and discover why rats are capturing the attention (and imagination) of car lovers everywhere.\n', '', '', ''),
(409, 1, 'Adbusters', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nADBUSTERS is a magazine of the cerebral environment. Each issue looks at the political news of the present, offering different perspectives and opinions on where the future of America and indeed the world as a whole lies. Are we about to enter another world war or can we reach world peace? ADBUSTERS is a debate about focal, current issues which affects us all in some form or other.\n', '', '', ''),
(410, 1, 'Cigar Aficionado', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThis US based magazine is as it says about all things associated with Cigars. Cigar Aficionado magazine is filled with interviews and profiles of celebrities and personalities that enjoy them. &gt;br/&gt;\nIt also includes articles on the latest places to travel, the best drinks and other related men’s lifestyle articles.\n\nThis magazine stands out because it is oversized and contains much larger pages than any other average magazine. Readers will feel like they are holding something unique and unusual in their hands.\n', '', '', ''),
(411, 1, 'Watchtime', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWatchtime is Americas No1 watch magazine, ranking among the best selling lifestyle magazines in the US.\n\nWatchtime’s editorial independence and expertise has made it America’s most respected watch magazine.\n\nWatchtime is best known for it’s in depth cover stories, striking photography and watch test and reviews. The magazine is aimed at informing and entertaining watch aficionados.\n', '', '', ''),
(412, 1, 'Veranda', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLove of the home is intrinsic to VERANDA readers and they are most discriminating in their appreciation of quality decoration, fine art, lush gardens and elegant entertaining. VERANDA celebrates the singular spirit of the home through its pursuit of innovative designs, showcasing the best creative collaborations across America and the rest of the world.\n', '', '', ''),
(413, 1, 'Bridal Guide', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBridal Guide is one of the most comprehensive bridal magazines around at the moment in the US, the magazine provides up-to-the-minute advice on styles and trends plus in-depth information that will help any reader plan the wedding of their dreams.\n\nThere is also honeymoon advice and relationship tips to prepare the reader for their new life with their future partner.\n', '', '', ''),
(414, 1, 'Foreign Affairs', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFOREIGN AFFAIRS is a magazine for today''s businessman looking to keep abreast of current affairs. FOREIGN AFFAIRS is America''s leading magazine on international affairs. For more than 75 years, FOREIGN AFFAIRS has been providing government, business leaders and international affairs students with insightful and thought-provoking analysis of world events. FOREIGN AFFAIRS can do more to inform public opinion by a broad hospitality to divergent ideas than it can by identifying itself with one school.\n', '', '', ''),
(415, 1, 'Bhg Wood', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMagazine dedicated to wood working. Containing various projects, including detailed descriptions and information on machinery used in woodworking.\n', '', '', ''),
(416, 1, 'Victoria', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLifestyle magazine on anything Victorian. Furnishings, clothing, decorative touches around the home. Cooking and entertaining\n', '', '', ''),
(417, 1, 'Diabetic Living', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDiabetic Living magazine is designed to be a support to those readers who are diabetic and need to watch their sugar and fat intake.\n\nThe magazine provides useful articles on the best meal plans as well as ways to lose weight while still maintaining a healthy lifestyle.\n\nThe magazine will also provide useful diabetic dessert recipes so readers don’t have to deny themselves dessert as long as they eat sensibly.\n', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `oc_product_description` (`product_id`, `language_id`, `name`, `description`, `meta_description`, `meta_keyword`, `tag`) VALUES
(418, 1, 'Rides', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRIDES is an urban automotive enthusiast magazine that represents the worlds of ''Street, Speed, Sound and Style''. Unlike any other magazine in the market place, RIDES bridges the worlds between enthusiast and consumer magazines and captures the automotive lifestyle that appeals to both Dame Dash and Donal Trump.\n', '', '', ''),
(419, 1, 'Snowboarder', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSnowboarder magazine is a publication of incredible value to its readers. Each issue of a Snowboarder magazine subscription takes a progressive look at the culture of snowboarding through mind-blowing photography, intelligent and entertaining words and groundbreaking design. Each issue is packed with killer photos, exotic travel, trick tips and hot products.\n', '', '', ''),
(420, 1, 'No Cigar Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNO CIGAR MAGAZINE an obsession with finding quality and individuality........ The name comes from the phrase ''Close, but No Cigar''. NO CIGAR is a bi-monthly lifestyle magazine, dedicated to showcasing the finest talents that the world has in fashion, photography, music and art. It is a lifestyle magazine for everyone. NO CIGAR includes unique, exclusive interviews and features on the new faces and talents in fashion, photography and music.\n', '', '', ''),
(421, 1, 'Ours Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nOURS is a multicultural magazine of artistic and social expression for the conscious and critical citizen.\n\nAt OURS we invite you to join us in sharing, exploring, and discovering various people, places, creations and ideas. To do this, every two months OURS addresses a thought provoking theme that sparks conversation with a sharp and studied point of view, delivering an inventive and sophisticated experience to its audience. .\n\nOURS showcases exceptional talent through artistic expression, discusses social, economic and political issues, individuals and organisations with mindful ideas for a better world, and acts as an open minded diary for the art of living and travel. .\n\nThe magazine is dedicated to accepting cultures, sharing talent, challenging ideas and encouraging social examination.\n', '', '', ''),
(422, 1, 'The Chap', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The Chap Magazine?\n\nThis is the perfect magazine for lovers of moustaches and monocles. A subscription to The Chap magazine gives you a unique look into the world of dandies and gentleman throughout the ages, with a charmingly satiric writing style to keep you entertained for hours. This men''s magazine offers thoughtful views on the fashions and habits of the modern man and his place in contemporary society, with interviews from some of the most sophisticated celebrities and businessmen in the world. This mag is the champion of the gentleman''s revolution, keeping an eye on sporting and cultural events with a uniquely old-fashioned flavour.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nFounded in 1999, The Chap takes a satirical look at the modern world through the steamed-up monocle of an English gentleman. The Chap seeks to maintain decorum and correct dress by celebrating the great dandies and gentlemen of the past, as well as casting a critical eye over the rather disappointing dress habits of today. We also celebrate cricket, horse racing, grooming, pipe smoking and drinking.\n', '', '', ''),
(423, 1, 'History Scotland', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO History Scotland Magazine?\n\nA truly illustrious publication, History Scotland magazine was launched in Edinburgh in October 2001 by Historiographer Royal Professor Christopher Smout.\n\nIts expert features and detailed articles make this the perfect history magazine subscription for those looking to develop their knowledge of Scottish history and immerse themselves in the country''s rich heritage.\n\nScholarly and trustworthy, subscribe to History Scotland magazine for informative pieces on all aspects of local history, from archaeology to maritime, military to socio-economic, along with excellent writing and stunning photography taking you behind the scenes of some of the most important periods in Scottish history.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGet a subscription to History Scotland, Scotland''s lavishly illustrated and beautifully produced history and archaeology magazine. Every issue of a subscription features stimulating and informative in-depth articles on Scottish history by leading historians and archaeologists. A varied mix of material from the earliest times to the 20th century. Also: current excavations and archaeological discoveries, book reviews, museums and heritage sites, news, internet sources, events. An essential read for anyone with an interest in Scottish history. History Scotland magazine introduces you to the history of Scotland, as revealed by historians of all times. A team of writers who have studied the history of Scotland and do a lot of research on this country provides the best of new research and historical writing. The glossy magazine comes with beautifully illustrated pages, specially designed for everyone who has an interest in Scottish history. Full of fascinating features and excellent photographs, a subscription to History Scotland magazine is a must-have.\n', '', '', ''),
(424, 1, 'Oh Comely', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Oh Comely Magazine?\n\nIf you want a magazine filled with stories, craft ideas and interviews to brighten your day and get you excited about the world, you need a subscription to Oh Comely.\n\nYou''ll receive six issues a year, each filled with inspiring personal stories and suggestions for a huge range of projects.\n\nWhether it''s rainy-day baking and crafts or outdoor explorations, you''ll love the quirky suggestions for activities to make sure you''re never bored again.\n\nEvery page is beautifully illustrated with photography of everything from gorgeous sunsets to delicious food, and their interviews with all sorts of creative types are certain to get your dusting off your old hobbies and rediscovering why you loved them.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Oh Comely magazine is ideal for young women looking for something unusual, inspiring and special.\n\nOh Comely is an intelligent magazine to inspire your creativity. Printed every two months on high-quality paper, Oh Comely will make you smile and remember to pull out a drawing pencil, a guitar or a pair of old roller skates.\n\nBeautiful, dreamy photography accompanies honest and thought-provoking personal stories. Interviews with passionate makers cover all sorts, from musicians to tea towel designers to circus performers. Playful features ponder questions like: How much fun is it possible to have for a pound? Will the Royal Mail mind if you put cheese in the post?\n\nOh Comely is a beautiful object to treasure on your shelf or cut up and stick on the wall. It’s more than just a magazine: it’s a reminder of the potential inside everyone to enjoy a creative life.\n', '', '', ''),
(425, 1, 'Northern Ireland Homes And Lifestyle', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Northern Ireland Homes &amp; Lifestyle - The largest selling home interest title for Northern Ireland. Northern Ireland Homes &amp; Lifestyle is an up-market magazine showcasing homes in Northern Ireland from one-off self build projects to refurbished terraced houses reflecting the tastes and style in Northern Ireland''s homes. Each issue also focuses on the local lifestyle, local people, local artists, designers, places, and arts &amp; crafts, reflecting on the positive aspects of life in Northern IreIand. The interiors features take a look at the latest and greatest in bathrooms, fireplaces &amp; stoves and designer sofas. So, if you’re considering giving your home a makeover, a subscription to Northern Homes &amp; Lifestyle magazine will be sure to spark a few ideas.\n', '', '', ''),
(426, 1, 'You &amp; Your Wedding', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO You &amp; Your Wedding Magazine?\n\nGet unique ideas for a fabulous wedding reception, find a breathtaking dress and discover innovative ways to set your big day apart with a You &amp; Your Wedding magazine subscription. With stunning photos, eye-catching colour schemes and budgeting tips, this fabulous bimonthly mag will help to inspire everything from your choice of venue to your flower arrangements, plus exciting ways to reward your bridesmaids on the big day. You''ll also find hundreds of useful tips to help you find the best bakers, as well as guides to getting flawless makeup and finding the very best wedding gift registry.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe definitive guide to what''s new and stylish in weddings, You &amp; Your Wedding is every bride-to-be''s new best friend. Every issue you''ll find inspirational fashion, beauty and reception style, with in-the-know tips on etiquette, planning and budgeting, plus romantic real weddings, gorgeous gift ideas and heavenly honeymoons. So whether you''re planning a city-chic party, a classic stately home wedding, a bunting-and-vintage-tea party or a floaty-dress and flip-flops on the beach, You &amp; Your Wedding can help you every step of the way, from ''Will you?'' to ''I do''\n', '', '', ''),
(427, 1, 'Posability', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPosAbility Magazine is a fresh and innovative publication that focuses on the opportunities available to disabled people today.\n\nPosAbility Magazine aims to inspire, encourage and motivate disabled people to live life to the full, to grab opportunities and most importantly to have fun. Every issue brings new ideas for activities and holidays and tips on leading a fit and healthy life, along with the latest products, personal stories, humorous columns and exclusive competitions.\n', '', '', ''),
(428, 1, 'Choir &amp; Organ', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nChoir &amp; Organ is the leading independent magazine for all professionals and amateurs in the choral and organ worlds – whether you are an organist, choral director or singer, organ builder, keen listener, or work in publishing or the record industry, Choir &amp; Organ is a must-read wherever you live and work.\n', '', '', ''),
(429, 1, 'International Piano', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nInternational Piano is essential reading for the piano world. Each issue brings you interviews with the world’s leading pianists and rising talent, and retrospectives on the piano greats of the past. You will find exclusive tutorials by international concert artists, in-depth articles on piano repertoire, and a regular masterclass series on piano technique and interpretation.\n', '', '', ''),
(430, 1, 'Pianist Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Pianist Magazine Magazine?\n\nWhether you enjoy playing the piano in your spare time or have made a career out of performing, Pianist magazine has features and articles to appeal to anyone who loves the instrument, regardless of ability.\n\nYou''ll read inspiring interviews with the world’s best players, exploring their careers and training, and the reviews of instruments and accessories help you choose the right pieces for you.\n\nWith your subscription, you''ll also receive plenty of pages of sheet music covering everything from classical music to jazz, with features on technique and effective practice to help you keep improving as well as a CD of all the featured pieces making it easy to listen and learn.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIf you love the piano, then a subscription to the Pianist magazine is for you.\n\nPianist magazine is the magazine for people who love to play the piano. Apart from all the top features and reviews you’d expect from a top music publication, each issue contains approx 40 pages of sheet music, from classical to jazz.\n\nThere’s a specially recorded CD that comes with every issue of Pianist magazine, so that you can get to hear the pieces before you play them.\n\nThere are many articles inside our pages that aim to help readers improve their playing. For those readers who need expert advice on particular technical problems, there’s always Tim Stein to answer your questions in his much-loved ‘Q&amp;A’ column.\n\nIt’s a magazine to read, to hear and to play!\n', '', '', ''),
(431, 1, 'Vintage Rock', 'WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Vintage Rock Magazine?\n\nThis is the ideal magazine for nostalgic rock fans, with features on all the greatest recording artists of years gone by. With your Vintage Rock subscription you''ll get answers to all your questions about pop music''s golden age, and the stories behind each break-up and reunion. You''ll be the first to hear about any comeback tours or revival gigs, as well as getting listings of the best tribute acts around. Whether you screamed at Beatles concerts yourself back in the day, or are just discovering these amazing vintage bands, this music magazine will be your perfect guide to all things rock and roll.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVintage Rock celebrates a time when music really did change the world - 45s, youth culture and the odd thrusting pelvis. We chronicle all the stellar artists and music, the enduring legacy of those early pioneers - and why it''s still the best way to live.\n\nSpanning the dawn of the 50s to early Beatles (pre Eastern mysticism!), Vintage Rock covers a time of Mods and Rockers, crinoline skirts and blue jeans, rock star movies and screaming-girl concerts. This special magazine rejoices in the music and verve of Elvis, The Shadows, Buddy Holly, Chuck Berry, Gene Vincent and a host more, and speaks to a contemporary audience that relishes the vitality and flair of the era.\n\nVintage Rock is the perfect magazine for any Rock’n’Roll fan – celebrating the music, the stars and the lifestyle.', '', '', ''),
(432, 1, 'The Mother', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe Mother Magazine is one of the original independent parenting magazines - a natural, holistic mothering publication read in over 30 countries worldwide, for over 12 years. The Mother Magazine has broken new ground publishing cutting edge long-form articles that are openly honest and sincere written by passionate and experienced writers.\n\nEvery aspect of natural parenting is explored; fertility awareness, conception, peaceful pregnancy, gentle childbirth, full term breastfeeding, co-sleeping, natural immunity, attachment parenting, education, parenting teenagers, and finally, nurturing one’s self on the path of motherhood.\n\nWhilst the main focus is to deliver inspiring content the publishers strive to make the magazine as beautiful as possible with a very strong focus on images and art- this a beautiful magazine that is as good to look at as it is to read.\n', '', '', ''),
(433, 1, 'Small Furry Pets', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Small Fury Pets magazine provides coverage of all aspects of choosing and caring for all types of small animals including rabbits, guinea pigs, hamsters, gerbils, chinchillas, mice, rats, and more recent arrivals on the scene such as degus, reflecting the dynamic nature of this sector. Each quarter Small Furry Pets magazine includes news, health care, breeder profiles, reader competitions and more, with the emphasis throughout being placed firmly on responsible ownership.\n', '', '', ''),
(434, 1, 'Selvedge', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Selvedge Magazine?\n\nIf you have a passion for textiles and fabric, or are a professional interior or fashion designer, a subscription to Selvedge magazine is a real essential. With features on contemporary art exhibitions, innovative textile designs and industry shows from around the world, this mag keeps you up-to-date on the most exciting happenings in the world of fabric and design. In each issue, you''ll find craft project ideas for around the home, interior design advice, textile-related book reviews and interviews with prominent designers and artists. With its beautiful photography, this magazine makes a fantastic coffee table read as well as a source of inspiration for design professionals and people looking to rejuvenate their decor.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Selvedge Magazine subscription provides key inspiration for all who are passionate about photography, textiles and design. This unique magazine is a one of its kind.Selvedge Magazine... offers the world’s finest Open a copy of Selvedge and you sense there is something else on offer besides the subtle design, quality writing and beautiful photography; there''s a philosophy that Selvedge readers subscribe to. A belief system based on a cerebral and sensual addiction to textiles in all forms. Readers share a belief in the importance of their material surroundings and a passion for the beautiful and beautifully made.Purchase a subscription to Selvedge and over the next twelve months we will aim to bring you the latest news and reports from the world of textiles, take you to amazing destinations across the globe, uncover the textile history of nations and individuals, examine developments in fine art, show you the finest fashion and furnishings and introduce you to the people you make them.\n', '', '', ''),
(435, 1, 'Narrow Gauge Rail', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Narrow Gauge Rail Magazine?\n\n?Narrow Gauge Rail magazine has all the information professionals, enthusiasts and modellers need to know about narrow gauge railways here and around the world. In any one issue, you can read about working trains in countries as diverse as Wales, Brazil and Thailand, with news on all the most exciting restorations, extensions and anniversaries. Thanks to the incredible detail of its photography and descriptions, this railway magazine also has a large following of scale modellers, which it recognises with regular features and tutorials on every aspect of building these amazing machines in miniature.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPublished six times a year, Narrow Gauge World is the only magazine of its type, focusing on a subject that plays a much larger role in the railway scene than many realise.\n\nIn Narrow Gauge World narrow, gauge railways in Britain and across the globe are firmly at the forefront, rather than in the background behind larger mainline railways as in other railway magazines.\n\nThe narrow gauge provided the first railway preservation project 60 years ago, and is producing the most exciting preservation project today- both have been featured prominently in Narrow Gauge World.\n\nThe magazine reflects the wide diversity of its subject. A network of dedicated and enthusiastic correspondents produces up-to-date news and in-depth features on today’s narrow gauge. These are combined with detailed historical studies, all illustrated with top-quality photography, used to its best benefit. Whether it be the narrow gauge ‘hot-bed’ of Wales, the Harz mountains of Germany, or forgotten backwaters in Australia or India, Narrow Gauge World magazine will cover it.\n\nMany Narrow Gauge World readers are heavily involved in today’s narrow gauge and a detailed diary, together with event previews, helps them be in the right places at the right time. A Narrow Gauge World subscription also features the latest modelling news and the latest in books, DVDs and memorabilia complete a package that no enthusiast of narrow gauge railways can afford to be without.\n', '', '', ''),
(436, 1, 'Resurgence &amp; Ecologist', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Resurgence &amp; Ecologist Magazine?\n\nThis excellent science and nature magazine covers the latest and most pressing ecological issues facing our planet today, with talented journalists taking an intelligent look at the driving factors behind key political, cultural and environmental trends. You''ll find a whole mix of opinions and insights from regular guest contributors, as well as exclusive interviews with people as diverse as the Dalai Lama and environmental activist Vandana Shiva. Each issue also comes with dozens of gardening tips and world recipes, as well as stunning images and a contemporary design, making a Resurgence &amp; Ecologist magazine subscription a great choice for anyone interested in getting to grips with the most important issues facing the world.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nDiscover Resurgence &amp; Ecologist magazine – covering issues from Gaia to Greenpeace, Peace to Politics and Organic to Occupy.\n\nFollowing the merge between The Resurgence Trust and the Ecologist, the joint publication Resurgence &amp; Ecologist magazine is now available.\n\nIn Resurgence &amp; Ecologist you’ll find positive, informed and original perspectives on environmental issues, engaged activism, philosophy, arts and ethical living. Plus, an extensive book review section, green living, poetry, stunning images and contemporary design.\n\nWith an intriguing mix of ideas, insights and commentary on environmental issues that can’t be found anywhere else, Resurgence &amp; Ecologist is a magazine not to be missed.\n\nWhy not join our regular readers and ensure you receive Resurgence &amp; Ecologist every two months?\n', '', '', ''),
(437, 1, 'Living Woods', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nLiving Woods is for anyone interested in trees, woodlands and timber, particularly green woodworking, using wood for burning and heating, low impact building and carving with chainsaws or whittling.\n\nWe campaign for the sustainable management of woodlands, and promote the use of local timber. You will find ideas for simple projects using wood, how to introduce coppicing to your garden, and how to buy and manage your own woodland.\n\nThere are regular features on building with wood, cooking food from woodlands and learning country woodcrafts. In every issue there are reviews of courses and we produce a Course Directory and The Complete Guide to Woodfuel.\n', '', '', ''),
(438, 1, 'Classic Truck', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nAs the UK’s only magazine dedicated to lorries dating from the 1970s to early noughties, Classic Truck covers a golden era of trucking. It’s a time when the rise of the independent private hauliers took shape. In each issue expert contributors look back at the vehicles, the companies and, of course, the personalities behind the trucks. There are fascinating features about, for example, classic models and old haulier routes.\n\nClassic Truck is an authoritative and compelling for HGV drivers, operators and enthusiasts.\n', '', '', ''),
(439, 1, 'Lakeland Walker', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Lakeland Walker Magazine?\n\nIf you can''t imagine a better holiday than exploring the beautiful Lake District, a subscription to Lakeland Walker is perfect for you. Arriving at your door six times a year, you''ll read all about the best routes to give you even more motivation to get out on those hills. Lakeland Walker has helpful suggestions for hikers just starting out, as well as new challenges for more experienced visitors. This walking and trekking magazine also gives you trustworthy reviews of gear and equipment to help get you properly kitted out, and local contributors can tell you where to grab a pint, enjoy a good meal or find a bed for the night after a hard day''s hiking.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPlanning your next walking weekend? Let Lakeland Walker inspire and guide you.\n\nWhether it’s a hike across the high fells or a lakeside ramble you enjoy most, let Lakeland Walker guide you along the way.\n\nLakeland Walker is the ONLY walking magazine that focuses SOLELY on the Lake District – by far the UK’s most popular walking destination. Every issue contains at least 10 walks in the region.\n\nLakeland Walker is a bi-monthly publication packed full of easy-to-follow walks in the Lake District illustrated with stunning photography. There’s also regular news from the National Park, events, gear reviews and exclusive reader offers.\n\nMost of the magazine’s enthusiastic contributors live in the Lakes and know the National Park like the back of their own hands and every walk they recommend includes precise, step-by-step directions and an accurate map.\n\nThe wide range of walks featured in the magazine vary from easy lakeside rambles to harder walks for the more adventurous.\n\nLakeland Walker - your essential guide to walking in the Lakes.\n', '', '', ''),
(440, 1, 'Trail Running', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Trail Running Magazine?\n\nFor all the latest information on trail and multi-terrain running across Britain''s best landscapes, from Snowdonia to the Peak District, a Trail Running magazine subscription is for you.Take inspiration for your next off-road adventure with stunning photos of the best outdoor running locations around, or try out one of many great outdoor weekend trail routes mapped out in each issue. You can also read expert features on training and nutrition advice from veteran trail runners, and enjoy the bonus of free access to all the best routes with Ordnance Survey Landranger mapping when you subscribe.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTrail Running is the UK’s only magazine dedicated to off-road running, so if you’re fed up with pounding the pavement next to the traffic, breathing in fumes, or sweating away on a treadmill, this quarterly magazine will get you running in the fresh, gorgeous UK countryside and loving every minute of it.\n', '', '', ''),
(441, 1, 'Huck', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Huck magazine subscription is a bi-monthly, pan-European lifestyle magazine rooted in surf, skate and snowboarding. Huck magazine is published in three languages - English, French and German. Holding a firm belief that many of our heroes have incredible stories to tell, we have enlisted some of the world’s best photographers and writers to get those stories out to you, with every issue of a subscription to the magazine. Packed with a rich assortment of features, a subscription to Huck brings you the magazine that represents the paradigm-shifting notion that there’s a wider dimension to life, and that many of us have a powerful interest in art, pop culture, the environment, fashion and the world at large. Huck magazine’s June/July cover was the winner of The Maggies 2009 in the Sport’s &amp; Men’s category. Don’t hesitate, invest in a subscription to Huck magazine today!\n', '', '', ''),
(442, 1, 'Classic Racer', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Classic Racer Magazine?\n\nNo publication captures the adrenaline fuelled, high-octane world of classic motorsport like Classic Racer magazine.\n\nWith unbeatable archive features and in-depth profiles of the legends of the track, Classic Racer is the perfect motorsports magazine if you''re looking to take a nostalgic look at the sport''s thrilling history. With a subscription to Classic Racer magazine, you’ll never miss a single minute of the action, bringing you all the latest news on classic bike shows and the future of the sport.\n\nYou''ll also find reviews on all the latest bikes and gear, plus reports from championships around the world.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nClassic Racer gives a passionate insight into the golden days of motorcycle racing.Legendary riders are interviewed about their highs and lows in the saddle, their teams are profiled and the high-powered machines they rode are examined in exacting detail.Reviews and reports from the world of classic racing are beautifully illustrated with dozens of rare period photographs and carefully reproduced original documents from the vast Mortons Archive.There’s all the latest news about the growing racing revival movement right across the globe too and details of the festivals dedicated to the glory of classic two-wheeled motorsport.\n', '', '', ''),
(443, 1, 'Classic Scooterist Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nClassic Scooterist turns back the clock through the golden ages of the scooter lifestyle.There’s news and reviews plus reports from rallies both past and present. Painstakingly prepared readers’ rides get in-depth coverage complete with photographs and historical details where available.Restoration tips and easy-to-follow technical advice gives readers the help they need to perfect their own projects. CSM covers the scene inspired by classic scoots too, including the nostalgic lifestyle and the passion that turned the heads of generation after generation.It’s a nostalgic look back, illustrated with an eclectic mixture of rare period pictures and modern images.\n', '', '', ''),
(444, 1, 'Bushcraft &amp; Survival Skills', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Bushcraft &amp; Survival Skills Magazine?\n\nWhether you''re taking up bushcraft as a new hobby or you''re a seasoned outdoor survivor, a magazine subscription will ensure you keep up-to-date with the best features on survival kit essentials, tips on how to make the most of nature''s resources, and essential info on upcoming events about wilderness living. Inside Bushcraft &amp; Survival Skills you''ll find an informative series of &quot;how-to&quot; features written by trained survivalists, so that you can improve your essential foraging, tracking and camping expertise when out and about in Britain''s woodland or countryside. For those interested in further reading about all things survival and bushcraft, this magazine also includes a reviews section with the latest books on the subject.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Bushcraft &amp; Survival Skills Magazine is perfect for anyone with an interest bushcraft.\n\nBushcraft &amp; Survival Skills Magazine is the UK''s FIRST Bushcraft Magazine. Knowledge is power; contained within the pages of each issue you will find a wealth of articles written by experts, taking you on a ''Bushcraft Adventure'' even when you can''t get to the woods!\n\nWith an interest in bushcraft is at an all time high, its profile has been raised by the new availability of information and of course the Ray Mears television series. Bushcraft &amp; Survival Skills Magazine is a valuable resource; enhancing your existing knowledge, teaching you new skills, answering your questions and keeping you up to date with courses and equipment suited to bushcraft use.\n\nThroughout the pages of Bushcraft &amp; Survival Skills magazine you will find Regular and Feature Articles on subjects such as Tracking, Knives &amp; Axes, Foraging, Flint Knapping, Fire Lighting, Wood Lore and Surviving in the Wild, alongside ''How to...'' articles showing you how to make your own kit and projects that use nature''s resources. Bushcraft &amp; Survival Skills Magazine also features Book Reviews, Course Reviews &amp; Kit Reviews to help readers select and buy wisely, Course, Schools &amp; Store Directories advising about what''s happening- along with where to go for training and kit. The magazine also has reader giveaways and competitions enabling you to get hold of some great kit.\n', '', '', ''),
(445, 1, 'Fish Farmer', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n''''Fish Farmer is the UK''s leading aquaculture magazine - bringing all the latest international industry research and news to readers. Published bi-monthly, this highly-regarded magazine has been serving the aquaculture industry for 30 years and enjoys a worldwide distribution.\n\nEstablished at the beginning of commercial aquaculture in the UK, Fish Farmer has documented the industry''s growth into a major source of seafood for the world''s consumers. Fish Farmer covers the full range of world-farmed species, from salmon and trout to scallops and seaweed. It is so highly regarded that many subscribers keep their copies as useful reference libraries, while academics vie to have their work featured in its pages, with some using ''publication in Fish Farmer'' on their academic CVs''''\n\nThis magazine is available on subscription only.\n', '', '', ''),
(446, 1, 'World Of Cruising', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nWorld of Cruising is Europe’s longest serving cruise publication. Since 1998 we have been inspiring, informing and engaging our readers across all the elements of cruise holidaying – luxury, river, adventure and ocean. Our unrivalled collection of features, reviews, opinion, insight and practical advice is invaluable for first-timers and regular cruisers alike.\n\nWe feature the best writers who travel the globe and have years of cruising experience under their belts. Their insights and knowledge will help readers plan the right destinations, cruise lines and ships for them, and help them make the most of their cruise holiday experience.\n\nNow under the stewardship of editor, John Honeywell, the magazine has grown steadily providing an even greater depth of coverage and insight for cruise enthusiasts. John, a self-confessed cruiseaholic and ocean-travelling addict, is well renowned as one of the country’s leading travel writers and has written for many years for a host of publications and websites, including the Daily Mirror, as his alter ego Captain Greybeard.\n\nJohn captains an elite crew of writers and contributors with years of experience bringing the world of cruising, travel, cuisines, spas and international destinations to life for our readers in every issue.\n\nPublished six times a year, and with an additional indispensable annual cruise directory, no other cruise publication has the combination of insider information, expert advice and comprehensive coverage than World of Cruising.\n\nDiscover the World of Cruising now, and join our loyal and ever-growing band of subscribers looking to get the most out of their cruise experiences. World of Cruising also makes the perfect gift for friends and family, who either love going on cruises, or are looking to start their voyage of discovery on a cruise holiday.\n', '', '', ''),
(447, 1, 'Communications Africa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCommunications Africa magazine is an essential subscription for anyone who is interested in knowing everything there is to know within the area of telecommunications in Africa.Communications Africa is published in both English and French and delivers full coverage of the communications and broadcast sectors across the continent. Communications Africa magazine contains aspects relating to telecommunications, broadcasting and information technology with regional relevance to both the public telecommunication authorities and the private sector. Each issue of Communications Africa magazine includes regional news reports, a country focus, new technological trends, market updates and exhibition previews and round-ups.Subscribe to Communications Africa magazine today and stay up to date with all of the goings on from the world of African telecommunications and information technology.\n', '', '', ''),
(448, 1, 'Cable &amp; Satellite International', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCable &amp; Satellite International is the leading technology magazine for the cable, satellite and broadcast sectors. We report on the standards, technology trends and products that shape this market, monitor the activities of network operators, and keep readers informed about the finances and activities of key suppliers. Our editorial focus is on the practical application of technology to current and future business needs.\n', '', '', ''),
(449, 1, 'Mondo Arc', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAimed at lighting designers, architects, specifiers, manufacturers and distributors, Mondo arc is read by the real decision makers in the architectural lighting industry. With features on the most exciting projects and installations from around the world including urban regeneration, retail outlets, cultural centres, office space and leisure venues, interviews with leading industry personalities, technology reports, product news and reviews.\n', '', '', ''),
(450, 1, 'Ancient Egypt Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nTake out a subscription to Ancient Egypt magazine, which is researched and written by specialists in the field of Egyptology.\n\nAncient Egypt magazine, with its lively and informed style appeals to experts, students and the many thousands of people fascinated by this early civilisation.\n\nPublished six times a year (October; December; February; April; June; August) a subscription to Ancient Egypt magazine brings you editorial that covers a wide range of subjects and are not limited to ‘ancient’. As part of your subscription, articles occasionally feature Coptic and Islamic Egypt while useful tourist information is also included. Profusely illustrated throughout, a subscription to Ancient Egypt magazine will provide the reader with the latest news and research information. So if you are interested in this fascinating period in time, don’t hesitate, treat yourself to a subscription to Ancient Egypt magazine today!\n', '', '', ''),
(451, 1, 'World Of Cruising', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nWorld of Cruising is Europe’s longest serving cruise publication. Since 1998 we have been inspiring, informing and engaging our readers across all the elements of cruise holidaying – luxury, river, adventure and ocean. Our unrivalled collection of features, reviews, opinion, insight and practical advice is invaluable for first-timers and regular cruisers alike.\n\nWe feature the best writers who travel the globe and have years of cruising experience under their belts. Their insights and knowledge will help readers plan the right destinations, cruise lines and ships for them, and help them make the most of their cruise holiday experience.\n\nNow under the stewardship of editor, John Honeywell, the magazine has grown steadily providing an even greater depth of coverage and insight for cruise enthusiasts. John, a self-confessed cruiseaholic and ocean-travelling addict, is well renowned as one of the country’s leading travel writers and has written for many years for a host of publications and websites, including the Daily Mirror, as his alter ego Captain Greybeard.\n\nJohn captains an elite crew of writers and contributors with years of experience bringing the world of cruising, travel, cuisines, spas and international destinations to life for our readers in every issue.\n\nPublished six times a year, and with an additional indispensable annual cruise directory, no other cruise publication has the combination of insider information, expert advice and comprehensive coverage than World of Cruising.\n\nDiscover the World of Cruising now, and join our loyal and ever-growing band of subscribers looking to get the most out of their cruise experiences. World of Cruising also makes the perfect gift for friends and family, who either love going on cruises, or are looking to start their voyage of discovery on a cruise holiday.\n', '', '', ''),
(452, 1, 'France Today', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFirst published in 1985, France Today magazine is one of the most established titles serving the international Francophile audience. Now under new ownership France Today is being re-launched in May 2013 with a beautiful new design and lots more editorial showcasing “the very best of France”. Our editors and writers are experienced French market specialists, many based in Paris and the French regions. France Today is written to inspire and educate international Francophiles on a range of popular topics. Every issue contains news, features and columns covering: TRAVEL – discover both classic and new destinations in France as well as exciting vacation ideas, travel news ART &amp; CULTURE – museums, galleries, festivals, new exhibitions FOOD &amp; WINE – restaurants and wine reviews, tours and activity holidays ACCOMMODATION – deluxe and authentic places to stay including hotels and rentals SHOPPING &amp; ENTERTAINMENT - great shops and classic brands, online shopping, TV channels, movie news and must-see shows FASHION &amp; DESIGN – covering fashion, interior design and art de vivre REAL ESTATE – market highlights, featured properties and upcoming investment areas.\n', '', '', ''),
(453, 1, 'Wedding', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Wedding Magazine?\n\nThis magazine has a number of excellent editorial features on the hottest new bridal fashion trends, plus delicious cake ideas and expert tips and advice from newlyweds every other month, giving you plenty of inspiration to help you plan the perfect wedding. If you find that you''re baffled by the invitations and seating plans or need help picking the best dress, a subscription to Wedding magazine will give you a friendly wedding planner, fashion guru, etiquette coach and travel agent all in one. There''s also hundreds of tips to help you create the wedding of your dreams, as well as interesting features on everything from meal planning to getting the right DJ. \nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Wedding magazine is a must have ‘bible’ for all brides to be. Wedding magazine provides the best resources for brides-to-be, from inspiring photographs and reader wedding stories to crucial information regarding retailers and honeymoon destinations. Easily tucked into a purse, bag, or briefcase, bridal magazines can assist even the busiest bride.From fabulous dresses to elegant reception ideas, every issue of Wedding magazine is packed with essential advice for brides, along with expert tips on fashion, beauty, receptions and travel to make planning your stylish wedding as stress-free as possible.Wedding magazine is easily tucked into a purse, bag, or briefcase, bridal magazines can assist even the busiest bride. Wedding will guide you through every step of planning your big day – from choosing your invitations to finding a dream honeymoon destination.\nA subscription to Wedding magazine is the perfect gift to aid a person close to your heart with all their wedding plans. Subscribe today and no doubt you will enjoy your own beautiful day.\n', '', '', ''),
(454, 1, 'Wedding Flowers', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Wedding Flowers Magazine?\n\nEvery issue of Wedding Flowers magazine offers a great selection of practical tips and advice from leading florists and wedding designers, together with stunning photos of the best displays around. \n\nWhether you''re a wedding planner looking for centrepiece inspiration, a florist keen to keep up to date with the hottest floral trends, or a bride-to-be who wants to find the most beautiful arrangements to complement her colour scheme on that all-important wedding day, this mag is a great addition to your reading list.\n\nWhen you subscribe to Wedding Flowers magazine, you''ll get a bimonthly source of wedding inspiration, with over 130 pages of incredible floral creations in every issue.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nedding Flowers is the UK''s only consumer magazine devoted to big day blooms. Every issue is brimming with beautiful ideas alongside practical and expert advice, making it the ultimate sourcebook for both brides-to-be and the nation''s florists.\n\nThe latest flower trends are interpreted to create show-stopping bridal bouquets, chic tablecentres, floral-embellished cakes and delicate buttonholes, along with plenty of inspirational real-life weddings. Wedding Flowers is now available bi-monthly, offering more than 130 pages of stunning floral creations to endlessly inspire and excite.\n', '', '', ''),
(455, 1, 'Indian Journal Of Educational Assessment', 'Indian Journal of Educational Assessment is a bi-annual journal which aims to inform educators, administrators, policy-makers and educational researchers about research or literature reviews on issues of contemporary concern regarding educational assessment relevant to India and South and South East Asia. In addition to publishing papers addressing research or literature reviews on educational assessment, it also publishes articles addressing educational assessment in practical terms.', '', '', ''),
(456, 1, 'Architectural Digest', 'Architectural Digest is the international authority on design and architecture. AD provides exclusive access to the world’s most beautiful homes and the fascinating people who live in them, bringing its audience a wealth of information on architecture and interior design, art and antiques, travel destinations, and extraordinary products; its AD100 list of top architects and designers is one of the industry’s most relied-upon indexes of talent. ', '', '', ''),
(457, 1, 'Xbhp', 'The xBhp magazine is aimed to be more than just a bunch of pages on motorcycles. This magazine will aim to be one of the highest quality two wheeler magazines in the world nurtured entirely by motorcyclists, for motorcyclists. The magazine, although targets Indians, will be a sensory delight to read and feel to any one across the world. Focusing on the powerful concept of i,the Biker which places the man before the machine and not vice versa.', '', '', ''),
(458, 1, 'Economy And Industry', 'India’s Only Magazine For Industry, Management &amp; Entrepreneurs....enables readers to be ahead of the curve through varied interactions with real practitioners, top industry leaders and successful entrepreneurs.\nPresenting insightful analysis of economic issues\nHighlighting industry perspectives on key policy matters\nOffering strategies for meeting future challenges\nIdeating on cutting-edge competitiveness space\nInnovating on quality, sustainability, governance and globalisation.', '', '', ''),
(459, 1, 'The Smart Manager', 'The Smart Manager was launched in 2002 by Dr. Gita Piramal with the mission of updating. Managers and business practitioners in India with the latest thought provoking strategic ideas from experienced world class managers, academics and consultants from across the Globe, ideas which are useful, well-researched and actionable, enabling the reader to produce results in an era of transition and disruptive technologies.\n\nThe magazine aims to present implementable ideas for the world class professional. Managers are the best teachers of managers, and The Smart Manager aims to capture insights from their experiences. The ‘Smart’ in The Smart Manager is an acronym for Strategy, Marketing, Analysis, Resources and Technology. Truly useful knowledge when you need it 24 x 365. Year after year.\n\nOver the years, The Smart Manager has been privileged to carry articles authored by illustrious. Management gurus such as CK Prahalad, Gary Hamel, Jagdish Seth, Lynda Gratton, Nirmalya Kumar, Nitin Nohria and the late Sumantra Ghoshal. The magazine also endeavors to live. Up to its credo of “managers are the best teachers of managers” by featuring articles on or authored by leading business persons from across the globe.', '', '', ''),
(460, 1, 'Bbc Knowledge', 'The first edition of BBC Knowledge, launched in the United States in August 2008, was an instant success; the magazine was voted among the Top 10 newly-launched magazine''s of 2008 by Library Journal, USA. It is also available internationally in the United Kingdom, Brazil, Singapore and Bulgaria. The Indian edition was launched in India in November 2010. With its unique content and style, BBC Knowledge holds the key to the mysteries of the world. Written by renowned academics and experts in the fields, BBC Knowledge''s wide-range of features provide riveting and up-to-date information on subjects ranging from treasure hunting in the 21st century, Darwin''s theory of evolution, the atomic bombing of Japan, global warming to the rivers of the Amazon. With material that is meant to stimulate the mind, this magazine looks to empower a young generation of readers.\n\nPrice includes posting &amp; handling charges of Rs. 60 per publisher policy', '', '', ''),
(461, 1, 'Dogs And Pups', 'A bimonthly magazine we celebrate eternal love. Each issue makes you understand your pet better, become a responsible pet parent, get acquainted with pooch and kitty needs, ensure great health, get information on training , agility &amp; grooming. Share fun- n- frolic, gear up to enjoy stardom, find out what’s hot what’s new. The magazine is also for a cause wherein we promote awareness for strays and abandoned dogs/cats and the people/organizations who help them. Become a RESPONSIBLE PET PARENT.', '', '', ''),
(462, 1, 'Food Service', 'Food Service India is an extremely informative Bi-monthly trade journal. It covers the entire spectrum of F&amp;B Topics &amp; will help Food Service industry to keep up-to-date with the coverage on latest products &amp; services in Food Service Industry (HoReCa).Food Service India aim at : Supporting the globalization process with management &amp; marketing know how. Developing India into an international marketplace, that enhances the knowledge &amp; information of products &amp; services.', '', '', ''),
(463, 1, 'Platform', 'Platform is one of India''s only contemporary arts and entertainment magazine that promotes talent, initiates progressive thought and explores the world of innovation! It serves as an open canvas for like-minded people to connect from all over the world. It encourages contemporary art and caters to the creative industry as well as appreciators and critiques of the same. Stylish and edgy, it is a space where innovation and substance intersect through popular culture today. A creative lifestyle magazine targeted at creative professionals, and appreciators of the same, platform provides fresh, relevant and visually stunning features on art, photography, music, film, theatre, fashion, literature, design and the other creative arts.', '', '', ''),
(464, 1, 'Adorn Magazine', 'Adorn, a luxury jewellery magazine. The bi-monthly magazine will feature product research and lifestyle reporting. India has a hoary tradition of jewellery and gemstones, being the home of the famed Kohinoor. It''s maharajas and royalty were renowned for their collection of jewellery, and international jewellers made pilgrimages to the courts of Indian royalty. It is a travesty that with such a history of the finest in craftsmanship, India did not have a publication to continuously chronicle and record its jewellery design capabilities', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `oc_product_description` (`product_id`, `language_id`, `name`, `description`, `meta_description`, `meta_keyword`, `tag`) VALUES
(465, 1, 'Geointelligence', 'GeoIntelligence is a bi-monthly magazine catering to the IT and geospatial news and information needs of defence and internal security forces. Through high-quality technical articles, case studies and interviews, GeoIntelligence is a rich source of highly specialised information. A young and unique product from Geospatial Media and Communications Pvt Ltd, GeoIntelligence enjoys a subscription base of 3000 professionals.', '', '', ''),
(466, 1, 'Sign And Graphics', 'Published bi-monthly with its extensive coverage of Indian signage industry and the world as well, Sign &amp; Graphics contains wealth of information and features about the industry, products and technology. This magazine is an info-center of large-format digital printers, display printers, advertising agencies, point-of-sale, sign makers, etc.', '', '', ''),
(467, 1, 'Asia Spa India', 'Asia Spa India is dedicated to the concept of Spa &amp; Wellness and targeted at up-market urban professionals, who are brand conscious, stylish and sophisticated decision makers leading a life of luxury. As you flip the pages you will find a treasure trove of information on spas, health, wellness, beauty and luxurious lifestyles. Our features go behind the scenes and look into treatment, products and accessories and interviews with people who have contributed to shaping the wellness industry for growth.', '', '', ''),
(468, 1, 'Diabetic Living', 'Diabetic Living is a magazine aimed at 32 Million Indian people and their families who bravely live with diabetes every day. Diabetes is a reality and there are ways to live a fulfilling, healthy and normal life with it- the magazine tells the reader in a reassuring fashion that Diabetes can be lived with and lived with style. Diabetic Living is the only lifestyle magazine that demonstrates how to live fully each and every day while managing diabetes. Each issue provides the reader with delicious diabetic friendly recipes, easily implemented exercise ideas and medical breakthroughs for readers who want to take responsibility for their diabetic condition. Guided by an independent board of nationally recognized health experts, Diabetic Living is a magazine that communicates with the reader.', '', '', ''),
(469, 1, 'All About Book Publishing', 'ALL ABOUT BOOK PUBLISHING (AABP) is a bi-monthly trade journal exclusively dedicated to book publishing industry in India. All About Book Publishing aims to informatically serve the industry associates and enable them to perform effectively. It is a reliable information source for the book publishing industry, encompassing all the facets of the trade.', '', '', ''),
(470, 1, 'All About Newspapers', 'Newspaper industry paves the way for better exchange of ideas and technology in the segment. Every quarterly edition of All About Newspapers narrates all the trends in this industry, the new technologies, the expanse of the industry, etc.', '', '', ''),
(471, 1, 'Print And Publishing', 'Being the single most trusted magazine in the field of printing, publishing and packaging industries of India, Print &amp; Publishing offers its readers the most precise and latest news, views, and technologies updates. This bi-monthly publication has been acclaimed all over India and the world over for its value and accuracy.', '', '', ''),
(472, 1, 'Shopping Centre News', 'Shopping Center News has been incepted with a vision that is far-reaching. Chiefly, the magazine will strive to be a knowledge resource center that collects, analysis and disseminates information on the Indian shopping center industry in all its aspects of operation; build up - and inspire - a body of focused research into the architecture and design aspects of shopping centres; encourage the development of sophisticated management paradigms and maintenance methods, keeping in context global benchmarks; and be a bridge between shopping center developers and the retail community, to help forge a mutually profitable relationship.', '', '', ''),
(473, 1, 'Elle Decor', '&quot;Reaching out to a lifestyle conscious audience, the ELLE DECOR reader is a discerning consumer. With a keen sense of design and fine living, the reader enjoys high inspirational levels and makes independent decisions on maintaining a certain standard of living. Whether its entertaining often or doing up the home in a stylish manner, the ELLE Decor consumer is a fashionable person who keeps abreast of the latest trends and styles prevalent in homes and interiors; and is constantly looking to enhance the home environment by imbibing these trends. ELLE Decor as a design expert unveils limitless opportunities in the design arena.The ELLE Decor magazine profile: With fashion integrating seamlessly into home decor, the industry is going through a sea change. ELLE Decor renders this in the pages through its many sections. By profiling upcoming product designers and established names, or with pages dedicated to new materials and innovative design concepts ELLE Decor provides a keen insight into developments in the design industry. The only decor magazine in the country to forecast trends in home decor, ELLE Decor provides readers with a continuous update. With art increasingly becoming an intrinsic part of decor, &quot;&quot;the new art consumers&quot;&quot; are looking for information on art and its various mediums. In its section profiling artists, ELLE Decor unfolds art in all its creative expressions. &quot;', '', '', ''),
(474, 1, 'Forbes Life', 'Forbes - Life : Driven by a dedicated team of renowned lifestyle voices and experts, each quarterly edition of Forbes India Life will curate ideas and experiences that cover every aspect of life in the visible divisions: think, work, live, play. The magazine would showcase the latest trends in design and lifestyle - from watches to wine, from cars to gadgets, with acclaimed experts on style giving a complete lowdown on the best of life.', '', '', ''),
(475, 1, 'Millionaire Asia', 'Millionaire Asia India is for the intelligent, suave and the ultra glamorous Millionaire. The magazine lures with its fun, playful and a bold attitude. Its about living life to the fullest, spending lavishly, creating memories and relishing experiences that last a lifetime.', '', '', ''),
(476, 1, 'G2 Gujarati', 'Dynamic and ingenious, Owners of 70% of India''s businesses, Architects of empires across the world, Devout in spirit, yet secular in thought, With an inimitable zest for life. They are none other than Gujaratis and the Parsis. G2 - THE GLOBAL GUJARATI carries a cache of success stories that define their insatiable taste for luxury. A trove that waxes eloquent on the spirit to defy the odds.A collection of what they treasure and what they love.', '', '', ''),
(477, 1, 'Marwar', 'In the last 13 years, Marwar has moved from being a community chronicler to one of India''s premium lifestyle magazine. The magazine''s focus is on shining the spotlight on the achievements, traditions and heritage of the Marwari community. Renowned for their financial acumen, Marwar celebrates the spirit of resilience within the Marwari community, while keeping in step with the aspirations of an affluent people. Marwar has adapted itself to suit its globe-trotting audience by showcasing the best in every sphere, be it people, trends, lifestyle and gadgets. The popularity of the magazine reflects in the numbers, with the circulation being over 50,000 copies and a readership of over 330,000. The subtle opulence of the magazine is aimed at the community and the Diaspora, an audience that wants to own and use the best products in the world and possess the power of being decision makers leaders in business and society. ', '', '', ''),
(478, 1, 'Parentedge', 'ParentEdge is a bi-monthly magazine for discerning Indian parents who care deeply about their children’s education, intellectual enrichment and stimulation. The magazine’s premise is that learning is a continuous process, and needs to happen both in and outside of school; thus parents have an important role to play in shaping their children’s interests and intellect. ParentEdge will primarily cater to the needs of parents of school going children from ages 3 to 18. The magazine aims to help parents adapt from the latest trends in learning across the world to their context, gain exposure to the growing choices before today’s children, as well as develop a more holistic view on moulding their children’s futures. Progressive parents will find a wealth of information in the magazine to help them steer their children towards well-rounded life perspectives as they grow. Many features are designed to be shared with children. Readers can look forward to thought provoking articles that combine professional advice from experts, insights from contemporary research, and personal anecdotes from fellow parents as well as viewpoints from children.', '', '', ''),
(479, 1, 'The Progressive Teacher', 'Bi-Monthly Resource Magazine to Empower School Educators.', '', '', ''),
(480, 1, 'Creative Gaga', 'Creative Gaga is a knowledge-rich publication about the best in graphic design, animation, contemporary art and illustration. Unbiased, appreciative and focused, it is about the latest trends in the trade and expert-speak.', '', '', ''),
(481, 1, 'Conde Nast Traveller India', 'This is Traveller, inviting you to join me on another journey into the realm of mystery and suspense. This time the trip is to be made in the pages of a magazine, rather than on the air. This Conde Nast Traveller Magazine is the answer. Some of the stories are real retold for your enjoyment in fiction form by the finest writers of today.', '', '', ''),
(482, 1, 'Asia-Pacific Boating India', 'Asia-Pacific BOATING India Edition prides itself on delivering the highest standards in luxury sea faring. Boating news from India and across the region with articles are focused to help readers get a hold of cutting edge technology and of course, generate leisure time to enjoy the inputs and guidance - on and off water.', '', '', ''),
(483, 1, 'Selling World Travel', 'SWT offers unparalleled information to the Travel Trade on destinations and travel related products. Undoubtedly, an interesting read for travel lovers across India, Selling World Travel works in collaboration with definitive sources at destinations to aspire and excite the readers to explore the world. It is the country’s only consumer and travel trade magazine to help the travel operators increase their business. SWT also serves as a perfect source for consumer to know the destination.', '', '', ''),
(484, 1, 'Sanctuary Asia', 'Sanctuary Asia, India''s leading wildlife, conservation and environment magazine.Sanctuary is at the fulcrum of several wildlife conservation campaigns and serves as a network for wildlife groups, concerned individuals and non-profit organisations. It is also a source of information for press and television reporters.', '', '', ''),
(485, 1, 'Adorn Magazine', 'Adorn, a luxury jewellery magazine. The bi-monthly magazine will feature product research and lifestyle reporting. India has a hoary tradition of jewellery and gemstones, being the home of the famed Kohinoor. It''s maharajas and royalty were renowned for their collection of jewellery, and international jewellers made pilgrimages to the courts of Indian royalty. It is a travesty that with such a history of the finest in craftsmanship, India did not have a publication to continuously chronicle and record its jewellery design capabilities', '', '', ''),
(486, 1, 'Image Reports', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIf you work within the European wide-format print industry or use its services, you need to know about the latest developments in the digital wide-and grand-format arena. Image Reports contains the latest news and advice on this sector, addressing the business, technological and environmental issues that affect you. Image Reports magazine helps wide-format printers strategies to grow and develop their business.\n\nSubscribe today and save up to 20% off the cover price\n\nYour subscription includes:\n•10 issues per year in print and digital formats\n•Twice-weekly email newsletters\n•Annual Widthwise Report\n•Think Bigger Report\n•Additional supplements', '', '', ''),
(487, 1, 'Printweek ', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPrintWeek is the highest-circulating and most widely read printing industry magazine in the UK, with an unrivalled reputation for the best news and analysis of print and associated sectors, including paper and pre-media. It provides key decision-makers with more information on contracts, plant and technology than any other title.\n\nSubscribe now and receive:\n\n•Fortnightly copies of PrintWeek magazine delivered direct to your desk?\n•The Annual PrintWeek Directory (worth £50) - the complete guide to print manufacturers, suppliers and service providers\n•The Annual Buyers Guide (worth £70) - the best source of buying advice for machinery in the industry\n•The Top 500 2013 in print and online – out December 2013 (worth £75) - a full breakdown of the financial performance of the top companies\nKey PrintWeek magazine features: •Fourteen days in print – a roundup of the news from the website, featuring who’s bought what kit, that week’s poll findings and Hot topics\n•Briefing – fortnightly in-depth analysis of key issues impacting the industry, featuring expert comment from the sector\n•Me &amp; My… – warts and all product reviews from actual users\n•Star Product – price, performance, service support and USP of a different piece of kit every fortnight\n•Sector specials – dedicated feature and product reviews specific to a market, from books to consumer print', '', '', ''),
(488, 1, 'Profi Tractors And Farm Machinery', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nProfi Tractors and Farm Machinery magazine is the only monthly magazine assessing, scientifically testing, comparing and advising on tractors, machinery and ancillary equipment.\n\nProfi Tractors and Farm Machinery also advises on buying used equipment, and includes a wealth of practical and technical features to help readers get more from their existing machinery.\n\nProfi magazine now has a new workshop tips section and expanded classifieds! A subscription to Profi Tractors and farm machinery delivers you 11 issues per year (July &amp; August combined issue)\n', '', '', ''),
(489, 1, 'Autocar Professional', 'Autocar Professional is a twice-monthly B2B publication targeted at the Indian automotive industry.\nIt''s delivered to key executives and decision-makers, and provides in-depth analysis of this booming market through its concise news, incisive interviews and accurate data.\nIt also gives the latest information on the automotive markets of China, Taiwan, Indonesia, Malaysia and Thailand.\nAutocar Professional also publishes an annual Directory, a comprehensive guide to almost 2000 products and companies.', '', '', ''),
(490, 1, 'Auto Bild India', 'Auto Bild is the highest circulated car magazine in the world and is published in over 30 countries. Its philosophy is to personally get its hands dirty with various cars to give its readers unbiased reviews. Auto Bild sells more than 5 million copies in 29 countries. The magazine does a lot of stories differently, but the main idea behind each of these is to make you, the reader and the car enthusiast, more aware. The magazine provides professional appraisal of used cars, and news from the world of wheels and motorsports. What really sets Auto Bild apart is its test regime. The test procedures and rating system employed for each car evaluation is the most scientific, rigorous and unbiased. Auto Bild also provides you with an opportunity to read the reviews from experts who don''t mince words.', '', '', ''),
(491, 1, 'Local Transport Today', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nLocal Transport Today is the leading fortnightly journal, packed with well-informed incisive comment and analysis on the news and issues affecting transport in the UK today. As the UK’s leading journal on transport policy and planning, Local Transport Today keeps readers up-to-date on the fast-changing nature of service delivery, including the latest procurement, delivery, materials and techniques, resourcing and financing. Make sure you receive the business-critical information throughout the year by subscribing to Local Transport Today.\n\nLocal Transport Today can provide you with a one-stop-shop for all your information needs every fortnight. Every subscription includes full online access to TransportXtra.com, comprehensive weekly news bulletins, plus breaking news.\n\nLocal Transport Today can provide you with a one-stop-shop for all your information needs every fortnight. Every subscription includes full online access to TransportXtra.com, comprehensive weekly news bulletins, plus breaking news.\n', '', '', ''),
(492, 1, 'Campaign India', 'Campaign India magazine was launched in September 2007 and has since grown to be the authoritative voice of India’s media, marketing and advertising community.\nEvery fortnight, Campaign India brings readers news on the latest developments, thought-provoking and timely analysis and informed debate on issues that confront practitioners in the country.\nThe magazine draws heavily on its heritage as the sister title to Campaign in the UK and Media in Hong Kong. This parentage allows Campaign India access to the finest articles and features and brings those that are relevant to the Indian environment to readers of Campaign India. The title, within seven months from launch, was the official newsletter to the Goafest 2008, the annual three-day celebration of advertising.\nFollowing the tradition of its sister titles, Campaign India will bring readers of the Indian edition supplements that will focus on particular aspects of the industry from time to time.', '', '', ''),
(493, 1, 'Outlook Business', 'Outlook Business, the new fortnightly business magazine packs in credible, detailed information and analysis for decision makers - enabling them take profitable business decisions. A composite package covering all factors that influence business movements from Indian and global perspectives. With expert views providing that an insight of the current business dynamics also analyzing the impact &amp; implications that these would have on your business.', '', '', ''),
(494, 1, 'Business World', 'Stay ahead of the curve with exclusive business news and analysis every week', '', '', ''),
(495, 1, 'Business India', 'BUSINESS INDIA is India''s first and foremost business magazine. Launched in February 1978, this business fortnightly pioneered the market for business journalism, in India. Through the years, despite new entrants in the field, BUSINESS INDIA enjoys the enviable reputation of being India''s most respected and credible business magazine.', '', '', ''),
(496, 1, 'Business Today', 'Business Today is India’s No. 1 Business Magazine with the highest readership amongst all business magazines in the country. A child of liberalization, the magazine was founded in 1992 to chronicle the changing business topography of the New India. Since then, it has set new benchmarks in both reportage-led stories and survey-led listings. Its ability to capture trends as they break and the mathematical rigor it brings based on research-based analysis has made Business Today the most respected business features magazine in the country.', '', '', ''),
(497, 1, 'Outlook Business', 'Outlook Business, the new fortnightly business magazine packs in credible, detailed information and analysis for decision makers - enabling them take profitable business decisions. A composite package covering all factors that influence business movements from Indian and global perspectives. With expert views providing that an insight of the current business dynamics also analyzing the impact &amp; implications that these would have on your business.', '', '', ''),
(498, 1, 'Dalal Street Investment Journal (Print )', 'India''s No 1 investment magazine, the one and only complete Resource guide for a wide loyal base of over 5 lacs HNI readers.Dalal Street Investment Journal is a one-stop-shop for all investment related opportunities and is the most widely referred and accepted journal in the finance and investment space. Reader Surveys and regular Feedback reveal that over 75 % of our readers act and profit from our advice and analysis which is the result of 24years of continuous study and research of the Indian stock market.Dalal Street Investment Journal is the only investment magazine in the country, which has well-researched analysis with clear cut guidance to investors on stocks whether to Buy, Hold or Sell.A regular score card on the best performing Mutual Funds.Useful articles on Insurance policies, Housing Loan Schemes and even on Credit Card offers.', '', '', ''),
(499, 1, 'Forbes India', 'Forbes is the world’s leading business magazine and since its inception in 1917 its mission has been clear and unchanging: to provide insights and information that ensure the success of those who tap into Forbes. In India, Forbes is launched in partnership with Network18, India''s biggest full play integrated media network. Every fortnight, Forbes India will help you connect the dots, form patterns and see beyond the obvious. It will bring to light ideas and the people generating them, allowing you to get an edge as a professional and needless to say, it will also open up the potential for wealth creation. Our sharp, in-depth and engaging stories will look at global and domestic issues from an Indian prism, giving you a completely different perspective. Subscribe to Forbes India today and stay ahead of the curve.', '', '', ''),
(500, 1, 'Fortune India', 'Forbes is the world’s leading business magazine and since its inception in 1917 its mission has been clear and unchanging: to provide insights and information that ensure the success of those who tap into Forbes. In India, Forbes is launched in partnership with Network18, India''s biggest full play integrated media network. Every fortnight, Forbes India will help you connect the dots, form patterns and see beyond the obvious. It will bring to light ideas and the people generating them, allowing you to get an edge as a professional and needless to say, it will also open up the potential for wealth creation. Our sharp, in-depth and engaging stories will look at global and domestic issues from an Indian prism, giving you a completely different perspective. Subscribe to Forbes India today and stay ahead of the curve.', '', '', ''),
(501, 1, 'Filmfare - English', 'For over 6 decades, Filmfare has been the official handbook on Bollywood for their die–hard fans with its exclusive interviews, classy photo shoots, insider stories, sneak peeks, Bollywood fashion coverage, movie reviews and special features. Filmfare captures Bollywood’s biggest stars and divas at their colourful, candid, beautiful, quirky and even spoilt best.', '', '', ''),
(502, 1, 'Child Friendly News', 'Child Friendly News is a fortnightly newspaper for children in the 7-13 age group. Our aim is to make hard news available for young minds, using language and format that can capture their attention and hold it. Each issue is eight pages long and every page is filled with colourful stories, vocabulary helpers and news context builders that keep children up to date with the world around them. The newspaper is tabloid size and is printed on glossy art paper, making it easy and attractive to read.\nOn a regular basis, the newspaper carries the following:\n·   India, Regional and International news\n.   Special sports coverage\n·   Articles on science and technology\n·   ‘Deep-dive’ sections that take up current news topics in depth\n·   A section on books, where books for different age groups\n   are reviewed. We also regularly carry a Top 10 Reading list\n·   A ‘Fun Page’ that educates and entertains                                    \n\nThere are a total of 20 issues each year, with no issues distributed during the summer, Christmas and Easter breaks.', '', '', ''),
(503, 1, 'Champak - Marathi', 'Champak is one of the oldest children stories magazine. Since its inception champak has adhered to inculcating moral values in the growing children. Champak is a name children swear by. Published in 8 languages, Champak is a bouquet of short stories, comic strips, puzzles, brain teasers and jokes that sets the child''s imagination free. It is the largest read children''s magazine in the country.', '', '', ''),
(504, 1, 'Champak Cd', 'Now in the form of a CD, for those who want to read on their systems. Champak (English) Fortnightly is one of the oldest children stories magazine. Since its inception champak has adhered to inculcating moral values in the growing children. Champak is a name children swear by. Published in 8 languages, Champak is a bouquet of short stories, comic strips, puzzles, brain teasers and jokes that sets the child''s imagination free. It is the largest read children''s magazine in the country.', '', '', ''),
(505, 1, 'Champak English', 'Champak (English) Fortnightly is one of the oldest children stories magazine. Since its inception champak has adhered to inculcating moral values in the growing children. Champak is a name children swear by. Published in 8 languages, Champak is a bouquet of short stories, comic strips, puzzles, brain teasers and jokes that sets the child''s imagination free. It is the largest read children''s magazine in the country.', '', '', ''),
(506, 1, 'Champak - Hindi', 'Champak is one of the oldest children stories magazine. Since its inception champak has adhered to inculcating moral values in the growing children. Champak is a name children swear by. Published in 8 languages, Champak is a bouquet of short stories, comic strips, puzzles, brain teasers and jokes that sets the child''s imagination free. It is the largest read children''s magazine in the country.', '', '', ''),
(507, 1, 'Nursery World ', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nNursery World is the leading print and online title for the early years community, providing the best information to help every child fulfil their potential. Packed with ideas, resources, and the latest news and developments, Nursery World is every professional’s essential guide to the Early Years Foundation Stage.\n\nNursery World magazine, published since 1925 and still at the forefront of early education and childcare, is a fortnightly mix of news, opinion, best practice, management and jobs. Top experts contribute series linking in to the four themes of the EYFS.\n\nSubscribe now and receive:\n\n•Fortnightly copies of Nursery World magazine, delivered direct to you or your setting\n•Unrestricted access to NurseryWorld.co.uk featuring a fully searchable archive of 28,000 articles you can download and print\n•Exclusive subscriber access to our online Practice Centre and Management section where you''ll find regular extra content that’s not available in the magazine\n•Supplements received as part of your subscription include: Training Today, Nursery Management, Nursery Chains and Nursery Equipment\n•Unrestricted access to a choice of email bulletins direct to your inbox: Nursery World Update, Nursery Practice and Nursery Management\n\nNursery World features:\n\n•Unrivalled news coverage with in-depth reports and updates on the frequent changes in Government policy\n•Professional advice from early years experts and key insights into childcare practice\n•Features linked to the four themes of the Early Years Foundation Stage: A Unique Child, Positive Relationships, Enabling Environments, Learning and Development\n•Activity ideas across all areas of learning, including monthly A2 activity poster\n•Management advice on running your setting and the updates on policy guides affecting your business\n', '', '', ''),
(508, 1, 'Dataquest', 'Referred to as the bible of Indian IT, DATAQUEST has constantly endeavored to highlight the major issues faced by the industry and users, publishing in-depth analysis of market trends and fast changing technologies. As the pioneer and leader of IT media in India since 1982, the magazine has consistently kept track of new developments in the IT industry and the corresponding information needs of the corporate user.', '', '', ''),
(509, 1, 'Farm N Food', '&quot;Farm ''N'' Food&quot; will, through its write-ups &amp; news stories, make farmers, Agro-industry/Livestock industry aware of new techniques in Farm and Food sectors like agricultural products, IPR, agricultural credit &amp; insurance, agricultural trade, agricultural machinery &amp; equipment, agricultural research, dairy development technology &amp; products, food processing, food storage &amp; preservation, fertilizers, marine products, grains &amp; land management, crop production, sericulture, globally Agri-events, home science, forestry, Agro-forestry, economics of crops, hill agriculture, seed science &amp; technology, post-harvest technology, Bio-technology, Agri-business, soil science, genetics &amp; plant breeding, plant protection, Agri-statistics, environmental science, co-operative societies, fertilizers, vegetables &amp; fruits, floriculture, animal health, dairy, poultry, fisheries, micro-finance and other schemes for farmers so that the farmers, food processors and traders get benefited with &quot;Farm n Food&quot;.', '', '', ''),
(510, 1, 'My Weekly Pocket Novels', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA My Weekly Pocket Novel Plus subscription will sweep you away for adventures and intrigue through its pages of thrilling story. Each issue will leave you feeling like you’ve been on a rollercoaster ride with strong themes of drama and romantic encounters.\n\nWhen you pick up a copy of My Weekly Pocket Novel, you will not want to put it down…subscribe now so you don’t have to!\n', '', '', ''),
(511, 1, 'Femina - Hindi', 'Femina reached out to the modern Indian, hindi-speaking woman by launching its Hindi edition in November 2008.The magazine speaks to the reader in the language and style she is most comfortable with. With its stylish look &amp; feel and fresh content, Femina Hindi speaks to the evolved and upmarket Hindi reader like no other magazine.', '', '', ''),
(512, 1, 'Femina - English', 'For over 50 years now, Femina, India’s first and largest read women’s English magazine has long been the definitive life and lifestyle guide for progressive woman. In this brave new age of the multi-faceted, multitasking woman, Femina still remains the referral point for women who are expanding their roles, and exploring new frontiers. And continues to talk to forward- thinking women on issues that matter most to them.', '', '', ''),
(513, 1, 'London Review Of Books', 'WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO London Review Of Books Magazine?\n\nThe London Review of Books is widely considered as one of the best literary magazine on topics of literature, the arts, culture, history, politics and philosophy published in the world today.\n\nBreadth is key for this title as it prides itself on covering the most seminal current debates with a scholarly approach and never shies away from challenging a conventional viewpoint. Each issue has up to 15 long form essays on diverse topics and encourages its contributors to develop ideas; you can enjoy writing from leading thinkers including Alan Bennett, Hilary Mantel, Mary Beard and John Lanchester.\n\nThe LRB is fiercely independent and unashamedly outspoken. Make sure you are part of the conversation by subscribing to the London Review of Books.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe London Review of Books is the most widely-circulated literary magazine in Europe. An LRB subscription is perfect for anyone with a passion for literature, politics, history, philosophy, poetry, biography, opinion pieces, film and the arts. Alan Bennett calls the London Review of Books magazine &quot;the liveliest, most serious and most radical literary magazine we have&quot;. Readers of the London Review of Books have come to expect inspired matches of writer and subject. Often provocative and always original, LRB writers do more than just review books- they use recently published books as a catalyst to interrogate and analyse world culture; the end point is a collection of independent, originally-crafted essays. As well as the print title, each LRB subscription also comes with access to the entire LRB archive. Every article every published (over 13,500 articles, poems and reviews) is available in our searchable online archive. A London Review of Books magazine subscription also makes a great gift for anyone with a love of literature.', '', '', ''),
(514, 1, 'Yours', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Yours Magazine?\n\nThis magazine is the ideal way for women to make sure they stay on top of the trends, with flattering fashion edits that won''t try and dress you up as your daughter. With a subscription to Yours magazine, you can read inspiring interviews with women like Helen Mirren and Twiggy, guaranteed to remind you that life doesn''t end at fifty, as well as fascinating real-life stories and nostalgic features looking back at the world you grew up in. You''ll enjoy expert health advice, diet and recipe suggestions, and if you''ve got grandchildren, you can read fab ideas on fun things to do with them to really make the most of every visit.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nYours is Britain’s leading magazine for the over-50s. It’s a friendly community where you can share stories and laughter, and find all kinds of advice on topics that matter to your life today – health, beauty, travel, fashion, finance and consumer issues. If it matters to you, you’ll find it in Yours magazine!\n\nIn every issue, we bring you:\n\n•Star chat with celebrities who matter to you.\n\n•Health &amp; Diet – if you’re 50, 60 or 70-plus, we’ll help you stay healthy and feel younger for longer.\n\n•Fashion &amp; Beauty – we’ll help you look younger and feel more confident.\n\n•Puzzles &amp; prizes.\n\n•Amazing real-life stories.\n\n•Nostalgia – we love to look back at the fashions we wore and your childhood summers.\n\n•Expert advice – useful solutions to your everyday problems.\n\n•Fun with the Grandkids – make the most of the precious time you spend together\n', '', '', ''),
(515, 1, 'People''S Friend Pocket Novels', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPeoples Friend Pocket Novels are the perfect accompaniment to The Peoples Friend Magazine. Each issue contains one complete romantic story that’s always gentle and uplifting.\n\nSubscribe and receive 2 issues per month delivered directly to your door.\n', '', '', ''),
(516, 1, 'Gp ', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nGP magazine is essential reading for the UK''s family doctors. In an NHS that''s constantly changing, GP brings you in-depth news and analysis of the issues affecting general practice and primary care.\n\nUnrivalled clinical coverage and guidance, award-winning columnists, practical business and financial advice, plus expert opinion and humour mean that GP covers all aspects of a busy doctor''s working life.\n\nSubscribe to GP today and you will benefit from the following key features:\n\n•The latest medical news, opinion and analysis from expert columnists\n\n•An in-depth clinical section, including a detailed clinical review, a weekly review of the journals, plus a range of articles covering key clinical areas\n\n•An education section covering GP training and the new RCGP curriculum\n\n•Regular articles for dispensing GPs\n\nWhat''s more, the magazine also carries hundreds of GP and Practice Manager jobs from across the UK.\nPlus – FREE access to our exciting new fortnightly iPad edition.\nSubscribe today to GP magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(517, 1, 'British Journal Of Nursing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nBJN brings you closer to the forefront of nursing practice. If you are looking for a journal that contains the latest clinical developments, original research and evidence-based practice you should be reading BJN.\n\nSubscribe to BJN for:\n•Cutting edge, peer-reviewed clinical research\n•Articles covering education and professional issues to keep nurse educators and general, specialist and student nurses up to date with care on the coalface\n•Innovations in nursing to keep you abreast on current professional developments and informed about how you can impact your own practice\n•In-depth patient safety, healthcare and legal analysis to help you guide clinical decision making and inspire the best in evidence-based practice and outcomes for your patients\n•Top-quality original research and comment in specialist nursing areas\n•Jobs, courses and events in nursing to support your continuing professional development\n\nArticles in BJN are written by nurses and subject to peer review by leading authorities in the profession. It is highly regarded by practitioners in the field, and has been called &quot;the most up-to-date clinically focused journal available&quot; and an &quot;essential companion to my studies&quot; by our readers. Ensure that you have access to the best clinical papers and original research in BJN.\n', '', '', ''),
(518, 1, 'Project Reporter', 'PROJECT REPORTER is a fortnightly project magazine available both in print &amp; electronic format. Project Reporter covers more than 100 projects across 45 diversified sectors from India which are in Conceptual and Implementation Stage along with Project Updates, Commissioned Projects, Contract Awards. It also provides the contact details of the projects and purchase heads.', '', '', ''),
(519, 1, 'Independent Nurse', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nIndependent Nurse is a fortnightly magazine that champions primary care and community nurses.\n\nNews and opinion The latest clinical and political news for primary care and community nurses and opinion from leading figures within healthcare\n\n•Authoritative, unbiased and targeted coverage\n•In-depth analysis of key health news stories\n\nClinical Clinical features that focus on real-life medicine, specifically relevant to the everyday needs of frontline primary care and community nurses\n•Covering the practical management of clinical conditions\n•Written by experts, in a concise and readable format\n•Providing updates on the latest clinical research\n\nProfessional Non-clinical features and resources to enhance nurses’ professional development, supporting them in their expanding roles\n\n•In-depth analysis of NHS organisational change\n•Case-studies of primary care nurse-led initiatives\n•Advice on career progression and education\n•Guidance on employment issues\n•Profiles of inspiring practice and community nurses\n•Professional resources\n', '', '', ''),
(520, 1, 'Caring Times', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Caring Times Magazine is a must have for anyone working in the social care sector. Published since 1988, Caring Times reflects the opinions of the social care sector, focusing on news affecting the private, public and not-for-profit provider''s of nursing and residential care. Caring Times contains news, analysis, business and financial pages, property market information, expert professional advice, people and quality care company profiles, reviews of government policy, general features and much, much more! Published monthly, Caring Times is distributed by post to key industry personnel including Nursing and Residential Home Managers, Senior Management of Multiple groups, Directors of Social Services, Heads of Inspection and other Professionals involved with the industry. Take out a subscription to Caring Times today and have each issue delivered direct to your door.\n', '', '', ''),
(521, 1, 'Nursery World', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nNursery World is the leading print and online title for the early years community, providing the best information to help every child fulfil their potential. Packed with ideas, resources, and the latest news and developments, Nursery World is every professional’s essential guide to the Early Years Foundation Stage.\n\nNursery World magazine, published since 1925 and still at the forefront of early education and childcare, is a fortnightly mix of news, opinion, best practice, management and jobs. Top experts contribute series linking in to the four themes of the EYFS.\n\nSubscribe now and receive:\n\n•Fortnightly copies of Nursery World magazine, delivered direct to you or your setting\n•Unrestricted access to NurseryWorld.co.uk featuring a fully searchable archive of 28,000 articles you can download and print\n•Exclusive subscriber access to our online Practice Centre and Management section where you''ll find regular extra content that’s not available in the magazine\n•Supplements received as part of your subscription include: Training Today, Nursery Management, Nursery Chains and Nursery Equipment\n•Unrestricted access to a choice of email bulletins direct to your inbox: Nursery World Update, Nursery Practice and Nursery Management\n\nNursery World features:\n\n•Unrivalled news coverage with in-depth reports and updates on the frequent changes in Government policy\n•Professional advice from early years experts and key insights into childcare practice\n•Features linked to the four themes of the Early Years Foundation Stage: A Unique Child, Positive Relationships, Enabling Environments, Learning and Development\n•Activity ideas across all areas of learning, including monthly A2 activity poster\n•Management advice on running your setting and the updates on policy guides affecting your business\n', '', '', ''),
(522, 1, 'Nursing Children And Young People', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nChildren &amp; Young People Now brings together the latest policy and practice to improve young lives and to support families. It provides vital information on child protection, safeguarding and social work; childcare provision; children’s health; education; youth services; youth justice; and multi-agency working.\n\nIt is essential reading for managers and senior practitioners involved in delivering services for children, young people and families across the public, voluntary and private sectors. Our best value premium subscription package enables you to receive the magazine plus all website content.\n\nThe magazine is published every fortnight and contains:\n\n•Essential roundup of news from across the sector\n•In-depth analysis of policy developments and their implications for practice\n•Investigations and surveys\n•Evidence-based case studies of good practice\n•Updates on working with children and the law\n•Examination of Ofsted inspection reports\n•Features based on visits to settings across the country\n•Special thematic reports\n•Interviews with decision makers, innovators and campaigners\n•Expert advice on working with children and on managing teams\n•Special supplements, including the flagship annual ‘Children in Care’ supplement\n\nThe cypnow.co.uk website gives online subscribers access to:\n\n•Directory of funding streams and grants for working with children, young people and families\n•Court reports on significant judgments affecting case law\n•Archive of evidence-based, good-practice case studies from across the UK\n•Archive of research reports on interventions with children and families\n•Careers information and tips for continuous professional development\n•Reviews of books and resources aimed at children’s professionals\n•Resource packs for youth workers\n•Conference and seminar listings\n•Unlimited access to the entire Children &amp; Young People Now archive of more than 54,000 articles', '', '', ''),
(523, 1, 'Planning ', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPlanning is the only fortnightly magazine for professionals concerned with economic development, communities, energy and environment, regeneration and housing.\n\nEvery issue of Planning includes sections committed to the environment, all the latest news and insight on energy efficiency, making towns and cities more pedestrian and cycling friendly, renewable energy sources and green infrastructure.\n\nSubscribe to Planning today and you will benefit from the following key features:\n\n•The latest appeals decisions in The Development Control Casebook - for key court judgements, ministerial rulings, and appeal decisions\n\n•The largest selection of jobs and tenders every week - to help you keep your career on track and an eye on tenders as soon as they are published\n\n•11 pages of news with expert analysis, policy and legislation updates, research and opinion from the people shaping the sector - keeping you in the know.\n\n•Incisive comment, practical advice and case studies - helping you perfect your skills.\n\n•Visuals, maps, charts and graphs to support the information presented -giving you a better understanding of all things Planning through imagery.\n\n•Regular features designed to highlight and share good practice - showcasing a particular piece of planning work plus a review by a third party expert.\n\n•Dedicated segments containing regular interviews with key politicians and policy makers - keeping you up to date with the political world.\n\nPlus…\nExclusive access as a paid subscriber to www.planningresource.co.uk, providing you with all the breaking stories, news and jobs in your area, daily news bulletins and a stack of useful resources – all helping you do outstanding work and make a real difference.\n', '', '', ''),
(524, 1, 'Children &amp; Young People Now ', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nChildren &amp; Young People Now brings together the latest policy and practice to improve young lives and to support families. It provides vital information on child protection, safeguarding and social work; childcare provision; children’s health; education; youth services; youth justice; and multi-agency working.\n\nIt is essential reading for managers and senior practitioners involved in delivering services for children, young people and families across the public, voluntary and private sectors. Our best value premium subscription package enables you to receive the magazine plus all website content.\n\nThe magazine is published every fortnight and contains:\n\n•Essential roundup of news from across the sector\n•In-depth analysis of policy developments and their implications for practice\n•Investigations and surveys\n•Evidence-based case studies of good practice\n•Updates on working with children and the law\n•Examination of Ofsted inspection reports\n•Features based on visits to settings across the country\n•Special thematic reports\n•Interviews with decision makers, innovators and campaigners\n•Expert advice on working with children and on managing teams\n•Special supplements, including the flagship annual ‘Children in Care’ supplement\n\nThe cypnow.co.uk website gives online subscribers access to:\n\n•Directory of funding streams and grants for working with children, young people and families\n•Court reports on significant judgments affecting case law\n•Archive of evidence-based, good-practice case studies from across the UK\n•Archive of research reports on interventions with children and families\n•Careers information and tips for continuous professional development\n•Reviews of books and resources aimed at children’s professionals\n•Resource packs for youth workers\n•Conference and seminar listings\n•Unlimited access to the entire Children &amp; Young People Now archive of more than 54,000 articles', '', '', ''),
(525, 1, 'Motor Transport', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Motor Transport magazine provides comprehensive news of the industry covering all the latest operational, legal and technical issues.\n\nMotor Transport is the newspaper of the UK haulage, distribution and logistics industry. MT produces annual tables of operating costs, a Fastest Growing and Top 100 listing, and regular features on technology, warehousing, commercial property, vans, as well as road tests of commercial vehicles.\n\nMotor Transport is full of short sharp focused information as well as contract wins, losses, business developments, management moves and technical news. It is aimed at truck fleet managers who need to keep up to date with events in the industry.\n\nBuy a Motor Transport magazine subscription today and get every issue delivered direct to your door!\n', '', '', ''),
(526, 1, 'Shop Til You Drop', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nShop Til You Drop is the modern girl’s fashion and beauty bible.\n\nIt aims to make shopping easier and more accessible for time-challenged women.\n\nWith a focus on shopping, it covers the entire market of fashion, beauty and homewares, providing the reader with the ultimate edit of what she needs this minute, mixing high-end fashion with chain-store must-haves; luxury beauty buys with pharmacy products..\n\nShop Til You Drop is a magazine based entirely on the rush of shopping. It makes fashion easy, cleverly translating trends so they work in real life and the unique captioning system lets the reader shop directly from the page, before you even set foot in a store you know where to get what you want, if it comes in your size and whether you can buy it online.\n', '', '', ''),
(527, 1, 'Tv Today', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGerman language, fortnightly, TV listings magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(528, 1, 'Tv Spielfilm', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTV SPIELFILM is a fortnightly llistings magazine for German television.\n', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `oc_product_description` (`product_id`, `language_id`, `name`, `description`, `meta_description`, `meta_keyword`, `tag`) VALUES
(529, 1, 'Auto Motor Und Sport', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAUTO MOTOR UND SPORT is one of Germany''s leading automobile magazines. Fortnightly you can read everything about the newest models and test-drives, reports over the motor sports. Other focal points are new technologies, used cars, traffic, environment and economy.\n', '', '', ''),
(530, 1, 'Freundin', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFREUDIN is the womens magazine for the working woman. It covers issues on careers and jobs as well as readers advice in sections of beauty, fashion, decorating, entertainment, and travelling.\n', '', '', ''),
(531, 1, 'Brigitte German', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBRIGITTE GERMAN is one of Germany''s biggest and most successful magazines for women. Treat yourself every two weeks with the newest information on fashion, culture, medicine, environment, business and politics.\n', '', '', ''),
(532, 1, 'Cbs Soaps In Depth', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCBS Soaps In Depth Magazine is the only magazine that gives readers the detailed scoop behind all of their favorite CBS soaps! Every issue of CBS Soaps In Depth has up-to-the-minute news, exciting sneak previews, and photo-filled features for The Young and the Restless, The Bold and the Beautiful, As the World Turns, and Guiding Light!\n', '', '', ''),
(533, 1, 'Hip Hop', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHIP HOP is a celebrity news and lifestyle publication featuring musicians, actors and models that appeal to the hip hop culture. Each issue will feature exclusive interviews, photos, reviews and articles that will appeal to a wide audience that crosses the traditional boundaries of rap into the hip hop culture.\n', '', '', ''),
(534, 1, 'Rolling Stone', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO ROLLING STONE Magazines From Abroad?\n\nThis magazine is the pop culture bible for music fans who also care about staying informed on world events.\n\nRolling Stone has run some truly legendary stories, interviews and photoshoots over the years and can still make headlines today, so if you want a magazine with an impressive political history as well as impeccable music taste, a subscription is definitely for you.\n\nYou''ll get exclusive access to the biggest names in music, film and television, as well as in-depth reports on important issues from financial ethics to drug laws.\n\nYou can also enjoy album and concert reviews and all the news from festivals across America and beyond.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nRolling Stone remains one of the most famous brands in the world. Rolling Stone magazine features all the latest news, reviews, interviews with major Rock bands, gossip from the USA, as well as covering serious topics such as global warming and War.\n\nRolling Stone magazine is the chronicle of more than one generation, covering music, celebrities, politics and pop culture. Each issue of your Rolling Stone magazine subscription features the very best reviews of music, film and books written with style, wit and humor.\n\nStay informed with the up-and-coming artists, as well as the new works of pop icons with each issue of Rolling Stone magazine. Rolling Stone sets the pace of what''s hot in the music world.\n', '', '', ''),
(535, 1, 'Governance Now', 'A fortnightly magazine with a daily updated website. It covers the various issues pertaining to governance in India. Governance Now is India’s pioneer Governance Magazine and its stands for accountability &amp; transparency. The Governance Now Website is a participatory forum &amp; is one-of-its-kind, with its highly interactive content on Governance in India.Since all aspects of the public lives of Indians are impacted and related to the quality of Governance in this country, the vision of the company is a country where good governance prevails. To bring that vision into reality we seek to provide a public platform for information sharing and discussion on all inclusive aspects of Governance.', '', '', ''),
(536, 1, 'Outlook - Hindi', 'Outlook has rewritten the way news and and general interest magazines are presented in India. It is comprehensive yet concise and crisp, investigative and bold in its approach. Outlook covers an array of topics ranging from current affairs, socio-economic issues, politics, lifestyle, entertainment, sports, international features, etc. Outlook reaches out to over 16 lakh upmarket, urban focused readers. Outlook has won a myriad of awards including the prestigious &quot;International Press Institute&quot; Award for Excellence in Journalism in 2007. Outlook encourages little known people who speak out loud against oppression, corrupt systems and social issues by instituting “Speak Out Awards”. Outlook also triggers young minds through an all India School debate called ‘Speak Out Debate” by reaching out to over 300 schools in 18 cities in India. Students who win the Indian round are sponsored by Outlook for international debates held in Korea, South Africa, etc', '', '', ''),
(537, 1, 'The Football League Paper', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The Football League Paper Newspapers?\n\nNo other publication gives as much coverage to the Football League as the Football League Paper, with details of all the action from the week''s biggest games and talking points. You''ll find a weekly round-up and recap of individual football league matches, together with photos, news and transfer rumours from the journalists and fans in the know. This paper covers the Championship, League One and League Two, with guest columnists, bloggers and former players taking you through key strategies, statistics and decisions. There''s also plenty of gossip and trivia to keep you entertained each week of the season, as well as reviews of the latest footy gear.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe Football League Paper offers fans of football outside the Premier League their own dedicated newspaper. It offers extensive coverage for all 72 Football League clubs with news, features and gossip plus comprehensive match reports.\n\nThe Football League Paper is published every Sunday but takes a two/three month summer break from the middle of May. All subscriptions remaining at the end of the current season will be transferred to each new season when the newspaper resumes every August for a new football campaign.\n\nPLEASE NOTE: price per issue includes delivery costs. The newspaper will be sent by First Class Post in the first available Royal Mail delivery.\n', '', '', ''),
(538, 1, 'Model Engineer', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Model Engineer Magazine?\n\nModel Engineer magazine is a great way for you to stay informed on everything to do with building working mechanical models. With over a hundred years of experience to draw on, this modelling magazine covers everything from classic steam locomotives to cutting-edge modern developments in scale engineering. Regular content includes constructional articles, features on the best techniques and tools available and profiles of full-size modelling subject prototypes.  You’ll also get all the benefits of the magazine''s historic links with the Model Engineer Exhibition at Olympia, London, as well as reviews of local and national events.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Model Engineer magazine offers it all, on various engineering subjects. Established for over 100 years, Model Engineer magazine features practical advice on construction model, articles and reviews. A subscription to Model Engineer magazine is now available in both printed and digital editions. Printed Subscription: • Every issue, Delivered conveniently to your door for FREE • View the full range of content on www.model-engineer.co.uk • Gain access to the complete back catalogue of Model Engineer Magazine Digital Editions Online Subscription: • Model Engineer magazine digital archive online 2001 – 2007 • Access to subscriber competitions on Model-Engineer.co.uk • Access to premium web articles on Model-Engineer.co.uk • Regular email newsletters Why not save more by also taking out a subscription to our other leading engineers’ magazine Model Engineer''s Workshop\n', '', '', ''),
(539, 1, 'The Cricket Paper', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Cricket Paper, is the UK’s only all cricketing newspaper covering cricket matches from around the world, from elite level to local domestic cricket.\n\nChief correspondent is Peter Hayter, the award-winning writer with The Mail on Sunday.\n\nOne of the unique aspects of The Cricket Paper’s coverage of the cricket scene is its depth - with more than 60 match reports, round-ups from all 25 ECB county leagues and comprehensive results service during the domestic season. Off-Season, The Cricket Paper becomes more feature-led carrying more in-depth interviews and focusing on the issues of the week.\n\nPLEASE NOTE: price per issue includes delivery costs. The newspaper will be sent by First Class Post in the first available Royal Mail delivery.\n', '', '', ''),
(540, 1, 'The Non-League Paper', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The Non-League Paper Newspapers?\n\nThis weekly football newspaper focuses exclusively on football outside of the big leagues, keeping you up-to-date with everything going on in the Blue Square Bet Premier and below. With a subscription to The Non-League Paper, you''ll get match reports and the latest news from leagues like the Ryman Premier and the Evo-Stik Northern Premier Division, as well as coverage of the FA Cup, from the early rounds right up to the final, with all the goals and action on the way to Wembley. Every issue also offers the latest tables and fixture lists, and previews of upcoming games, making sure that non-league football fans are prepared for the next week''s action.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe Non-League Paper is the only paper that covers Non-League football from top to bottom and is the recognised authority on non-league football.\n\nEstablished since 2000 as the pre-eminent publication dealing with the national game below the Football League, covering football from the Conference Premier down to grass-roots.\n\nPublished every Sunday throughout the year.\n\nPLEASE NOTE: price per issue includes delivery costs. The newspaper will be sent by First Class Post in the first available Royal Mail delivery.\n', '', '', ''),
(541, 1, 'The Rugby Paper- English', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe Rugby Paper, the UK''s number 1 selling rugby title, brings you exclusive stories, reports and features on a weekly basis.\n\nIt contains renowned journalists such as Nick Cain and Peter Jackson, and famous former players as columnists including Jeremy Guscott and Jeff Probyn.\n\nPublished every Sunday, The Rugby Paper covers Rugby Union from national teams and Premiership / Rabo Direct down to grass roots.\n\nPLEASE NOTE: price per issue includes delivery costs. The newspaper will be sent by First Class Post in the first available Royal Mail delivery.\n', '', '', ''),
(542, 1, 'The Rugby Paper -Welsh', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe Rugby Paper, the UK''s number 1 selling rugby title, brings you exclusive stories, reports and features on a weekly basis.\n\nIt contains renowned journalists such as Nick Cain and Peter Jackson, and famous former players as columnists including Jeremy Guscott and Jeff Probyn.\n\nPublished every Sunday, The Rugby Paper covers Rugby Union from national teams and Rabo Direct / Premiership down to grass roots.\n\nPLEASE NOTE: price per issue includes delivery costs. The newspaper will be sent by First Class Post in the first available Royal Mail delivery.\n', '', '', ''),
(543, 1, 'Fulham Fc - Official Matchday Programme', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe official Fulham matchday programme provides 84 pages of up-to-the-minute news, views and interviews, covering everything from the Club’s colourful history, right through to the very latest events at Craven Cottage and Motspur Park.\n\nThe ideal accompaniment to each fixture, the publication is written and designed in-house in partnership with industry leaders ProgrammeMaster. Each issue features player interviews, insightful columns, a detailed look at the visiting side, pages for kids, puzzles and much, much more. Supporters can interact with the publication by sending in photos for the messageboard, being a Featured Fan or seeing their Fulham-related Tweets picked up and published.\n\nWith all the usual news and views from in and around the training ground, plus much more besides, the official programme really is the essential matchday accessory.\n', '', '', ''),
(544, 1, 'Trav Talk', 'TravTalk is South Asia''s leading travel trade news magazine and the only fortnightly travel magazine distributed in the subcontinent. TravTalk was established in 1991 and is a trusted source of information for all the tourism and hospitality industry leaders and decision makers. Over the years, TravTalk has become a renowned brand with a nose for news and an unparalleled reach. Trav Talk provides the quickest, most well researched and comprehensive news with exclusive interviews and analytical pieces on the latest trends in the industry. It is the only Travel Trade Publication which has an opportunity and situations vacant column. ', '', '', ''),
(545, 1, 'Grihshobha', 'Grihshobha is a Hindi-medium magazine aimed at Indian women. The magazine was started in 1979 as a monthly by the Delhi Press Group in Hindi. Since its inception, Grihshobha has enjoyed wide readership in the Hindi belt of the country It carries features on housekeeping, cookery, knitting, interior decoration, beauty care, dress designing, hobbies and handicraft, besides helping women understand social, national as well as universal issues. It focuses on women''s issues, and often features racy short stories, fashion, recipes, advice columns, and comments on socialites and current events. The total readership is estimated to be about 98, 63,000.', '', '', ''),
(546, 1, 'Saras Salil - Hindi', 'Saras Salil is a popular Indian fortnightly magazine in Hindi language. It contains unique mix of commentaries on social and political issues, and varied articles on society, sex, fiction and entertainment. Saras Salil is published in 5 languages (including Hindi) and has a highest readership according to IRS 2009 R1 in India in Hindi magazines. Incidentally, Saras Salil is placed second in the all magazines chart.', '', '', ''),
(547, 1, 'Sarita', 'Sarita is the critical voice of the group on matters of political and social importance. For more than 6 decades, Sarita has been at the forefront of a crusade against, religious obscurantism political authoritarianism.Each issue carries a distinctive mix of articles on politics, social issues, business, fiction and humor.', '', '', ''),
(548, 1, 'Woman''S Era', 'Woman''s Era represents the aspirations of the contemporary Indian woman. Covering subjects that range from health, lifestyle, relationships, grooming and social issues to the latest trends and topics around the world, it has earned for itself tremendous credibility amongst its readers.', '', '', ''),
(549, 1, 'U', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nU magazine continues to be Irelands leading Women''s Magazine and is the first stop every second week for celebrity news and gossip, beauty buys, the best fashion from high end to high street, features, travel, advice, horoscopes and brilliant competitions.\n', '', '', ''),
(550, 1, 'Bird Watching', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nShare your passion for wild birds with a Bird Watching magazine subscription. Each issue of Bird Watching magazine, is dedicated to bringing you everything you need to know on birdwatching. Packed full of stunning photography and advice every month. Bird Watching magazine will inform and inspire you for the month ahead, with advice on how to get the most from your birding, whether you''re a beginner, an improver or an expert. We''ll tell you what''s been seen, reveal some fabulous bird walks, and entertain you with some of the world''s best photography. We’ll inspire you with brilliant photography, exciting locations, expert product tests, informative identification guides and all the latest sightings. Just add binoculars for your ultimate birdwatching experience. Each issue of Bird Watching Magazine is packed with features including: - Practical advice on getting more from your hobby. - Indispensable identification guides on difficult species. - Inspirational bird photography from the world''s best photographers. - 10 easy walks with a great chance of seeing exciting birds. - News and reviews of all the latest birdwatching products. - Rare sightings from all across the country. - Thought provoking features from world-renowned experts. The Direct Debit Guarantee The minimum subscription term for the direct debit offer is 12 months. The amount paid by Direct Debit may change over time. If and when it does you will be notified in advance by at least 10 days. If an error is made by Bauer Media Ltd or by bank/building society, you are entitled to a full and immediate refund. You can cancel the Direct Debit at any time by writing to your bank/building society and send a copy to Bauer Media Ltd at: Magazine Subscriptions, Tower House, Sovereign Park, Market Harborough, Leicestershire LE94 7ZT. Please note that banks and building societies may not accept Direct Debit instructions from some types of account.\n', '', '', ''),
(551, 1, 'Animals And You', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Animals and You Magazine?\n\nThe direct debit price is based on 3 issues for the first quarter and then 4 issues per quarter thereafter, totalling 15 issues per yearThis is one of the best magazines for young animal lovers, with hundreds of fascinating facts and activities to help introduce your daughter to the animal kingdom.\n\nYour child will learn about all types of furry critters with an Animals and You magazine subscription, with pictures of the cutest pups and adorable big cats, as well as exciting adventures into the world of safari.\n\nEvery issue will give your child hours of girly fun, with animal puzzles, fun competitions and a fabulous &quot;reader''s pets&quot; section, giving her the chance to have her very own puppy published.\n\nThere''s also a funky free gift in every issue, as well as dozens of cute pull out posters.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Animals and You magazine is the perfect gift for girls aged between 7 and 11 who love everything to do with animals and pets. Animals and You is the original and best animal magazine.Every three weeks, this magazine is full of the cutest posters, sad rescue stories with happy endings, fascinating animal facts, puzzles, cool competitions and adorable readers’ pets pictures! There’s also a free gift with every issue!Animals and You magazine is girly, gorgeous and full of fabulous stuff. In each issue of your subscription you will find, the sweetest pet posters, cool competitions, animal facts, freebies and varying things to make and do.Animals and You magazine is the magazine for you if you love everything to do with animals – big and small, common and exotic. This magazine is for young children, who have a love of animals – not just for the pups and kittens, but also to the wild animals, dangerous animals and any animal you can think of. The magazine also reaches your hands with some kind of freebie or gifts with every issue. This one magazine is one worthy read, to ignite the love to animals in the minds of young girls.Animals and You is published by DC Thomson and Co who are based in Scotland and is aimed at young girls who adore animals. Animals and You is published every three weeks and you will find a free gift with every issue of your subscription. A subscription to Animals and You will keep all animal lovers entertained for hours!\n', '', '', ''),
(552, 1, 'Domus', ' Domus is a monthly international magazine on architecture, interiors, art and design from Italy, with a long and distinguished history of over eight decades.The Indian edition of Domus will be a space for the dissemination of original and rigorous thought in architecture and design. It will provide a sharp critical focus on the zeitgeist and the possible resultant futures for architecture and design in the Indian Sub-continent.Domus was conceived in 1928 by architect Gio Ponti who, from 1929 on, was supported by the publisher Gianni Mazzocchi with Editoriale Domus, created specifically to publish the magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(553, 1, 'Architect And Interior India', 'Architectural and Interior design professionals will find design inspiration and business insights through the magazine''s combination of industry news, cutting edge designs, local and global case studies. There are business features as well. ', '', '', ''),
(554, 1, 'Architecture+Design', 'A+D is a leading national monthly of architecture for architects, designers, students of architecture, construction industry, building promoters and planners. Based on a very contemporary format, it portrays the modern trends in building technology, research and development in the process of design, project profiles, conservation and environmental issues, product and material information, etc. Focused at an entirely new segment of readers, A+D makes good business sense for those who are looking at promoting their products to an industry, which could add to their institutional sales substantially. A+D, is also instrumental in constituting the only national awards &quot;A+D &amp; Spectrum Foundation Architecture Awards&quot; which has generated tremendous response from the leading architects and professional bodies of the country.  A+D has a circulation of 58,000 copies with a readership of 3,50,000 plus readers indicates the depth and penetration of the magazine nationally.', '', '', ''),
(555, 1, 'Antique Collecting', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Antique Collecting Magazine?\n\nWhether you''re a serious collector or a fine art amateur, you''ll love this comprehensive guide to the world of antiques.\n\nWritten by specialists in the field, an Antique Collecting magazine subscription will provide you with hours of entertainment each month, with pages of expert advice and opinion on the growing trends in the world of fine art, museum displays and historical artefacts.\n\nThis subscription-only title will improve your antiques knowledge, and point you towards the best fairs, auctions and dealer sales from around the country.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n''''If I had to recommend one antiques magazine to the general collector, it would be Antique Collecting'''' David Battie, BBC Antiques Roadshow.\n\nAntique Collecting is the quintessential British publication for enthusiasts and collectors. Written by experts, it offers invaluable advice and information on a wide range of antiques and decorative objects, from everyday artefacts to fine art and museum pieces.\n\nEach issue includes details of forthcoming auctions and fairs, sale results, and exhibition news. Noted for its high-quality illustrations and accurate descriptions, Antique Collecting is only available by subscription. No compatible publication can be found on the newsagent''s shelves.\n\n''''By far the most informative magazine on antiques'''' Paul Davidson, Bonhams.\n', '', '', ''),
(556, 1, 'Apollo', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Apollo Magazine?\n\nWhen you take out an Apollo magazine subscription you''ll enjoy a wonderful mix of art reviews, as well as the latest news from the art world and a number of in-depth feature articles in every issue.\n\nYou''ll get an exclusive look at some of the most prestigious public and private art collections in the world, with an interesting insight into the mind of the collector and the driving force behind their assortment of diverse pieces.\n\nThere''s also a number of captivating interviews with industry experts, giving you tips on how to start your very own collection, regardless of your preferred period and style.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFor over eighty years Apollo has been delivering a wealth of informed news, analysis and debate from the art world. We open the door on significant collections – both public and private – and reveal how they have been built and what drives the collectors.\n\nYou will also find reviews of the best exhibitions from around the world, highlights of what the galleries are featuring, and reports on the latest trends and prices from the global art market.\n', '', '', ''),
(557, 1, 'Period Living', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Period Living Magazine?\n\nThis is Britain’s best selling magazine for tips on maintaining and decorating period homes.\n\nYou can flick through colourful feature articles on renovation and restoration projects, and read bundles of advice at every stage of a development.\n\nA Period Living magazine subscription will provide anyone with a passion for period properties with a monthly dose of design and decorating ideas, with each issue featuring exquisite photographs of timeless interiors and exteriors, along with antiques and vintage-inspired accessories.\n\nThis leading mag is a great way to keep you up to date with the latest ideas and trends on how to bring a little period style into your home.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Period Living magazine is for anyone who appreciates the timeless qualities of classic style and elegance, but are not afraid to add a new twist of their own for individuality to their home. Renovating and decorating a period home, whether it''s in the town or country, is an exciting journey of discovery and Period Living magazine is here to help you, offering expertise and inspiration. In every issue of Period Living, you''ll find four beautiful homes, from Tudor to Edwardian, restored with love. You''ll discover inspirational decorating schemes, full of tips on how to create the look, and well-researched buyer''s guides, advice on interior decorating and redesigning your home, tips on antiques and collecting, gardening, travel, real food and much, much more. Period Living magazines unique renovating section is packed with practical advice and in-depth knowledge on all aspects of traditional homes, to help you tackle jobs yourself, and find all the specialist suppliers you need. Make sure you never miss and issue, Subscribe today and have your copy delivered to your home each month.\n', '', '', ''),
(558, 1, 'Leisure Painter', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Leisure Painter Magazine?\n\nPacked with handy painting and drawing tutorials for both beginner and advanced artists, Leisure Painter is the ideal art magazine to help you explore your creative side. Each issue will inspire, guide and encourage you to enhance your art work, helping you to create stunning pieces at home.\n\nContributors include some of the country''s leading art tutors, and you''ll find tips on everything from the best art holidays to the latest courses, giving you the chance to constantly improve and develop your technique.\n\nYou''ll also be able to take part in dozens of competitions and prize draws every month, helping you to get your art out to the wider community.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLeisure Painter is the UK’s best-selling learn-to-paint magazine and is essential reading for beginners and hobby painters. Leisure Painter is passionate about teaching its readers to draw and paint, publishing easy-to-follow demonstrations by the best-known, most experienced art tutors in the UK, in every issue. Leisure Painter can help anyone to learn to draw and paint, and have fun learning a new, lifelong hobby, whilst making new friends with a similar passion. Simple step-by-step demonstrations, in every issue, make it easy for anyone to create drawings and paintings to be proud of! Readers will also learn about which art materials to buy and how to use them, courses and holidays to go on, books to read, events to attend and how to progress once the basics have been accomplished. All subjects are covered, from simple landscapes, to how to paint your dog, or cat, or a successful portrait of a loved one. Plus enter the many encouraging competitions for beginners, and get involved with a local art club. Whatever, or however you would like to draw or paint, Leisure Painter is here to help!\n', '', '', ''),
(559, 1, 'Practical Photography', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Practical Photography Magazine?\n\nThis photography magazine has loads of advice on the art of taking the perfect picture, with plenty of stunning high-definition shots included in each issue to remind you of exactly what you''re working towards. Their writers have experience of shooting in a huge range of conditions, and can give you tips on everything from tricky lighting to camera maintenance. With your subscription to Practical Photography magazine, you''ll get useful guidance through the whole process, from choosing the right lens for each set-up to perfecting your creations on Photoshop. Readers'' photographs are extensively featured every month, so once you''ve captured the perfect image, you can send it in to be printed in their ''Hotshots'' section.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Practical Photography brings a mix of inspiration and advice valued by people who want to improve and experts alike. Practical Photography magazine is packed full of fantastic images, photographic tips, photoshop techniques, advice and inspirations to get you out and about creating stunning photographs. Each issue of Practical Photography... * Unveils the best new products first with Gear News * Informs you with How to... * Showcases your best pictures every month in Hotshots * Unravels your photographic questions in Photo Answers * Advises you on your buying decisions with Gear Guide * Inspires you with what and where to shoot this month in Now is the time to... Plus top value reader offers, loads of big prize competitions and much, much more. Practical Photography magazine also hosts an annual ''Photographer of the year'' competition between January and July, in which readers may enter. Don’t miss out, subscribe now and have all this conveniently delivered to you every month.\n', '', '', ''),
(560, 1, 'N-Photo', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO N-Photo Magazine?\n\nThis is the only photography magazine designed specifically for Nikon DSLR users, so if that''s your camera of choice, this is the magazine for you.\n\nWith a subscription to N-Photo, you''ll get monthly access to all things Nikon, from ''Nikopedia'' reference articles to tutorials on the newest programmes and features.\n\nThere are detailed shopping guides to help you figure out which lens is the right choice for you, with the in-house ''test team'' conducting extensive trials of all the featured products before letting you in on their professional opinions.\n\nYou''ll even get a free CD in every issue, guiding you through simple steps guaranteed to improve your photography.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nN-Photo is the independent magazine for Nikon photographers. Every month N Photo is packed full of 132-pages of step-by-step advice on how to get the best results from your Nikon digital SLR. The camera skills section will show you how to shoot great pictures and also how to edit them to make them even better! Find inspiration from the beautiful images shot by top photographers and readers. Learn the basics through our Nikopedia reference pages – picking up tips from the pros with our exclusive interviews and masterclasses. N-Photo comes each month with our exclusive Nikon Skills video disc. Packed with practical advice, exciting photo projects and with lessons to help you master Photoshop and Nikon''s own Capture NX2.\n', '', '', ''),
(561, 1, '3D World', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIf you are serious about 3D, you need a subscription to 3D World magazine.\n\n3D World magazine is the world''s biggest-selling monthly title for the 3D artist covering all aspects of the CG creation, including animation, visual effects, video games and architectural visualisation and includes expert training in apps such as 3ds max, Maya, Cinema 4D, ZBrush, LightWave, Vue, Photoshop and After Effects.\n\nEvery issue of 3D World magazine features an artist showcase and reviews of new products. It also provides analysis of the latest trends in the market, artistic and technical advice and exclusive behind-the-scenes articles on the making of key projects in this fast-paced industry. .\n\nTake out a subscription to 3D World today and have all the practical tips, tricks and advice you’ll ever need to help improve your 3D skills direct to your door every month.\n', '', '', ''),
(562, 1, 'Computer Arts', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nTake out a subscription to Computer Arts, the best selling title for digital creatives and digital artists.\nEvery issue of Computer Arts magazine delivers the practical skills and expert advice to help you become a better designer. It showcases the best illustration, graphic design, typography and web design along with advice from agencies and digital artists.\nOur workshops will help you create an iconic brand, design your own characters, take your work onto mobile platforms or master the newest advanced Photoshop, InDesign, Illustrator and other Creative Suite skills.\nEach month, Computer Arts magazine also reviews the latest hardware and software releases, gives creative tips and technical advice, and interviews the leading lights in the global design world.\n', '', '', ''),
(563, 1, 'Wrights Farming Register', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Wrights Farming Register Magazine?\n\nWrights Farming Register is the best place to find the agricultural machinery, equipment and supplies you need.\n\nThere’s all the latest news on plant, technology and agriculture plus events, auctions, forestry and landscape management.\n\nWrights also offers farmers and contractors a unique machinery and equipment broker service.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Wrights Farming Register, the monthly newspaper for the farmer, agricultural dealer, plant machinery dealer and contractor. Wrights Farming Register includes monthly editorial and features on farming and countryside topics including ‘Rolling Back the Years’ which looks at pre-modern tractors, Landscape and Forestry, 4x4, Sports and Hobbies and a new Plant and Machinery section. In ''Down to Earth'', Wrights looks at environmental and climate change issues, attracting contributions from respected figures in the agriculture, biofuel and conservation fields. Plus, every month WFR features a comprehensive advertising section making it a must-have for any person or persons involved in farming.\n', '', '', ''),
(564, 1, 'Old Bike Mart', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Old Bike Mart Magazine?\n\nWhether you''re looking for bike tools at an affordable price, searching for a new engine for your pride and joy, or just keeping tabs on the classic motorcycle events calendar, an Old Bike Mart magazine subscription is the best resource you could ask for.\n\nEach issue brings you hundreds of private classifieds every month, as well as trade listings and spare parts sales, helping you to buy a ready-to-ride vehicle or to find what you need to complete a restoration project.\n\nWith detailed previews of upcoming shows and reviews of recent classic bike events, you''ll be able to keep yourself up-to-date with the vintage motorcycle scene with this monthly magazine.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nOld Bike Mart offers the UK’s largest selection of classic motorcycle classifieds. It features the latest news, reports from the racetrack, part and tool reviews and ‘how to’ guides. Newly discovered historic machines are revealed in all their unrestored glory and there’s a nostalgic look back through the annals of motorcycling history. There are also dealer and workshop profiles where the experts behind some of the UK’s finest restorations give a behind-the-scenes insight into how the magic happens. Readers’ rides are examined, buyers’ guides show you what to look for and there are hundreds of ads to browse.\n', '', '', ''),
(565, 1, 'Buses Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSubscribe to the UK’s most highly and most widely read magazine covering the bus and coach industries; Buses Magazine. Buses is written for and read by an audience that extends from senior industry professionals to passionately interested enthusiasts.Buses magazine carries the latest news written with authority on serious issues in a readable and entertaining format, and offers the most comprehensive photographic coverage of new developments. It succeeds in being fiercely independent and unafraid to criticise aspects of the industry that could be improved.Unique to Buses is Fleet News, a comprehensive section detailing the latest changes to bus and coach fleets in the UK and Ireland.Buses magazine combines enthusiast topics with expert professional writing on matters of interest to a wider range of serious bus industry readers. If you love buses subscribe to Buses magazine today.\n', '', '', ''),
(566, 1, 'The Classic Motorcycle', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The Classic MotorCycle Magazine?\n\nThis motorcycle magazine is ideal both for those that love riding or collecting vintage bikes and those that like reminiscing about motorcycling''s history.\n\nIts ''Men Who Mattered'' features take a look back at past key figures in the biking scene, while its news articles provide coverage of more recent vintage bike events.\n\nA subscription to The Classic MotorCycle magazine is also great if you''re looking for tips on how to look after your own vintage bike, with technical features and helpful product reviews in every issue, while the buyers'' guides are useful for riders and collectors alike, covering different budgets each month.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to The Classic MotorCycle magazine and celebrate motorcycling’s heritage while remaining firmly rooted in the present. The Classic MotorCycle magazine provides readers with road tests, features and in depth stories from the current classic scene. Each issue has more to offer the true vintage motorcycle enthusiast than any other publication. Despite the retro cover, inside there’s still an eclectic mix of classic machine tests, archive material and true-life stories from the halcyon days of motorcycling. The Classic MotorCycle magazine also retains the technical features and sports reports that have served readers so well over the years. A subscription to The Classic MotorCycle is a must-have for the committed classic fan.\n', '', '', ''),
(567, 1, 'Tractor', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Tractor Magazine?\n\nTractor delivers the latest news and developments in the tractor and machinery world while taking a nostalgic look back at farming heritage.\n\nThe magazine interviews owners and restorers and is packed with in-depth technical features, up-to-date sales and marketplace news, rally reports, models and rare photographs from the Tractor archive.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGet a subscription to Tractor magazine, a celebration of farming life and the tractors and machinery that worked them over the past hundred years. From seed time to harvest, dairy to stockyard, our farming heritage is as important as the tractors themselves. Featuring the rare as well as the famous names, with complete archives and beautiful colour pictures of restored machines a subscription to Tractor magazine is a must have for all tractor enthusiasts. A subscription to Tractor magazine comes with all the latest news and up to the minute information relating to tractors and to farming in general. With a subscription bringing the magazine to you every month you will be able to keep your knowledge up to date with all the latest industry developments, helping you to maximize your business potential. Tractor magazine also includes a wide variety of technical features on a multitude of topics.\n', '', '', ''),
(568, 1, 'Classic Bike Guide', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Classic Bike Guide Magazine?\n\nIf you’re passionate about vintage British motorcycles, you''ll love a subscription to Classic Bike Guide magazine.\n\nIn every issue of this monthly motorcycle magazine, you’ll get detailed road tests of much-loved vintage bikes and special feature articles taking an in-depth look at individual classics.\n\nThere’s also plenty of advice and tips on buying and looking after vintage motorcycles, regardless of your level of expertise. What makes this mag the standout title for true classic bike enthusiasts, however, is its first-hand reviews of vintage motorcycle events and rallies, and its ''Trading Post'' section for those looking to buy and sell their own vintage rides.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nClassic Bike Guide explores the world of classic motorcycle ownership and restoration. Beautiful photographs illustrate reviews of rare machines and profiles of the best British bikes of yesteryear. Legendary characters from the glory days of motorcycling and the powerful machines they rode are celebrated too and today’s finest restorers and rebuilders discuss their intricate work. Seldom seen and previously unpublished pictures from the vast Mortons Archive offer an unrivalled insight into the history of motorcycling and there’s all the latest news. CBG also offers views from our knowledgeable and occasionally cantankerous columnists, detailed workshop guides, event reports and road tests.\n', '', '', ''),
(569, 1, 'Classic Motorcycle Mechanics', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Classic Motorcycle Mechanics Magazine?\n\nIdeal for anyone with an interest in restoring and riding vintage bikes, this magazine will keep your technical knowledge up to scratch with its detailed workshop guides on everything from polishing the bodywork to changing the brakes.\n\nIts focus is primarily on classic Japanese and European models from the 70s and 80s, so Yamaha, Suzuki and Ducati bikes feature heavily in this motorcycle magazine.\n\nA monthly subscription to Classic Motorcycle Mechanics will offer you helpful advice on what to look out for when buying a specific model, as well as road test features on classic bikes, and a ''Show Us Yours'' section that showcases the best of readers'' restoration projects.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nClassic Motorcycle Mechanics examines every aspect of maintaining, restoring and rebuilding the modern classics of motorcycling. Ground-breaking 1970s, 80s and 90s machines from the likes of Honda, Yamaha, Suzuki and Kawasaki are road tested, reviewed and discussed in detail. There’s news and views too, and readers’ rides ranging from fully fared racing machines to single-cylinder road bikes are put under the microscope. The pitfalls of purchasing modern classics are outlined in handy buyers’ guides, and there’s advice on the best bargains to be had today. Particular parts are profiled and essential workshop procedures are explained in full.\n', '', '', ''),
(570, 1, 'Heritage Commercials', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHeritage Commercials delivers the best coverage of the classic commercial vehicle world on the market – from stunning restorations to memories of times past. It features in-depth restoration articles that show how a complete wreck can be turned into a show winner. It also looks at the histories of haulage companies – from large and small – from all around the UK and packs in a wealth of period photos to bring those memories flooding back. There are vintage ads and artwork from the extensive HC archive plus all the latest news, book reviews and rally reports too.\n', '', '', ''),
(571, 1, 'Scootering', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Scootering Magazine?\n\nScooter lovers will appreciate the vehicle maintenance guides and reports on local club events provided by a subscription to Scootering magazine.\n\nFocusing on both new and vintage models from the great companies like Lambretta, Triumph and Vespa, this motorcycle magazine has loads of feature articles on restored classic scooters, plus reviews and test drives of the latest models.\n\nYou''ll find photos of readers'' own restoration projects in the ''Show Us Your Scoots'' section, while the helpful ''Scooter Trader'' pull-out is one of the best places to buy or sell vehicles and spare parts.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nScootering is the world’s number one scooter magazine. The best customised and restored scoots are showcased in glorious detail with owner interviews, tech specs and beautiful photographs that pick out every carefully crafted detail. There are reports from rallies across the country, handy buyer’s guides, product and music reviews, interviews with the movers and shakers of the music scene, readers’ scoots, top technical tips and oodles nostalgia for the places, faces and two-wheeled dream machines of days gone by. This is your indispensible guide to everything that makes scootering a way of life.\n', '', '', ''),
(572, 1, 'Performance Bikes', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Performance Bikes Magazine?\n\nIf you''re seriously into motorcycle modification, then a Performance Bikes magazine subscription will be right up your street. Every issue is focused on powerful sportsbikes, bringing you detailed profiles of the best high-performance machines and advice on how to buy them. It will take you inside some of the UK''s most ambitious workshops, giving you an insight into real-life modification projects, while also offering tips on how to mod your own bike to make it perform better. In this monthly motorcycle magazine you''ll also find helpful product and bike tests, as well as all the latest race circuit news, keeping you up-to-date with recent sporting developments.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Performance Bikes magazine is perfect for the dedicated sportsbike owner. Performance Bikes, now known by the shortened title ‘PB’, is a monthly motorcycling magazine which evolved during the 1980s from the long-running Motorcycle Mechanics. The magazine features a mix of motorcycle and product tests, new and used bikes, racing, tuning, project bikes and chasis improvement with technical articles and design innovation. Performance Bikes magazine is not only rammed with the most insightful and exciting tests of the latest metal but also with the most authoritative, useful and plain inspirational stories about the bikes that matter – the bikes that they own now, the bikes that they used to own, and the bikes that they dream of owning. A subscription to Performance Bikes magazine is an all in one resource for bikers providing lots of humour and bags of reader involvement. Subscribe today and have Performance Biker delivered direct to your door every month!\n', '', '', ''),
(573, 1, 'Vintage Spirit', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nTrial subscription for new subscribers only\n\nA subscription to Vintage Spirit magazine brings you the UK''s fastest growing steam and vintage magazine, direct to your door every month. Each issue in a subscription to Vintage Spirit magazine features all the latest from the preservation world each month, along with stories of steam and vintage vehicles and exciting reports on shows and events. With a subscription to Vintage Spirit magazine you can take a nostalgic trip into yesteryear every month, it really is the magazine for the vintage transport enthusiast. Three great reasons to take out a subscription to Vintage Spirit magazine: -Free delivery straight to your door every month -Never miss an issue -Great savings So if you can’t get enough of vintage transport, invest in a subscription to Vintage Spirit magazine today!\n', '', '', '');
