(574, 1, 'Ride', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Ride Magazine?\n\nPractical and informative from cover to cover, the main topics of this motorcycle magazine are riding, bikes, products and D.I.Y., meaning it can give you all the biking information you need.\n\nA monthly subscription to Ride magazine will bring you detailed bike reviews, mainly concentrating on used motors, and loads of essential D.I.Y. advice to help you take better care of your motorbike.\n\nFamous for its trusted product tests, the magazine''s green triangle stamp of approval lets you know for sure that what you''re buying has been tried and recommended by the experts, while its bike buying guides make sure you know exactly what to look out for when purchasing a new ride.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPractical, investigative information delivered in an entertaining and friendly manner.\n\nThe most authoritative real-world product testing for all bikers - don''t buy another piece of kit until you''ve read RIDE.\n\nSubscribe to ride magazine and receive this authoritative source from the world biking to your door every month.Ride magazine has practical, investigative information delivered in an entertaining and friendly manner. The most authoritative real-world product testing for all bikers - don''t buy another piece of kit until you''ve read RIDE.A Ride magazine subscriptions brings biking mad individuals product tests and bike reviews, keeping its readers fully up to date on the latest advances in technology, new editions to the market and much much more.Ride magazine is the must ultimate must read magazine subscription for Riders and provides you with all the information you need to make informed decisions regarding your favourite hobby.Subscribe to Ride magazine today and become a fountain of knowledge on your preferred sport. The Direct Debit Guarantee\n\nThe minimum subscription term for the direct debit offer is 12 months. The amount paid by Direct Debit may change over time. If and when it does you will be notified in advance by at least 10 days. If an error is made by Bauer Media Ltd or by bank/building society, you are entitled to a full and immediate refund. You can cancel the Direct Debit at any time by writing to your bank/building society and send a copy to Bauer Media Ltd at: Magazine Subscriptions, Tower House, Sovereign Park, Market Harborough, Leicestershire LE94 7ZT. Please note that banks and building societies may not accept Direct Debit instructions from some types of account.\n', '', '', ''),
(575, 1, 'Classic Cars', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Classic Cars Magazine?\n\nWhether you''re an avid collector or someone with a keen interest in automobile history, a Classic Cars magazine subscription will provide you with hours of enjoyment each month.\n\nfind a host of fascinating motoring tales and anecdotes, insight into the buying, upkeep and restoration of vintage models and all the latest market news and trends you need to keep you up to date with the world of classic cars.\n\nAs Britain''s longest-established classic car magazine, you''ll appreciate reading the host of features by seasoned industry experts, as well as the spotlight pieces on various eras throughout classic car history.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Classic Cars, magazine, the original classic car magazine. Classic Car magazine, Britain’s longest-established classic car magazine, takes you back to the most interesting cars and people from the past. In every issue of your subscription to Classic Cars magazine, our knowledgeable writers bring you fascinating stories packed with fresh insight, and evocative photography puts you in the driving seat. Classic Cars magazine is titled Thoroughbred &amp; Classic Cars in all countries outside the UK. The Direct Debit Guarantee The minimum subscription term for the direct debit offer is 12 months. The amount paid by Direct Debit may change over time. If and when it does you will be notified in advance by at least 10 days. If an error is made by Bauer Media Ltd or by bank/building society, you are entitled to a full and immediate refund. You can cancel the Direct Debit at any time by writing to your bank/building society and send a copy to Bauer Media Ltd at: Magazine Subscriptions, Tower House, Sovereign Park, Market Harborough, Leicestershire LE94 7ZT. Please note that banks and building societies may not accept Direct Debit instructions from some types of account.\n', '', '', ''),
(576, 1, 'Old Glory', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Old Glory Magazine?\n\nOld Glory is Britain’s best-selling magazine for steam and vintage machinery enthusiasts. Its blend of news, rally reports, exclusive features and archive material has provided inspiration for new restoration projects as well as giving readers a rare look at some old favourites.\n\nAmong the many and varied subjects covered are steam traction engines, mechanical organs, mill engines, steam ships, locomotives, veteran cars and scale models.\n\nPhotographs and carefully reproduced documents from the Old Glory archive offer a nostalgic look back at steam’s golden age and there’s lively reader interaction in the letters and helpline columns.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Old Glory magazine is a must-have for vintage steam and heritage enthusiasts. Old Glory has been Britain’s best-selling transport &amp; industrial heritage magazine for over 15 years. If you love the spectacle of immaculately-restored old machinery, or are fascinated by Britain’s rich industrial and transport heritage, Old Glory is the magazine for you! In vivid detail it brings back all the sights and sounds of yesteryear. Glorious showman’s engines belt out the amperes to drive historic fairground rides, pairs of mighty steam ploughing engines turn the soil, steam rollers make up roads once more, tram wheel flanges squeal through town and city streets, colourful working narrowboats ply the canals, dray horses deliver good ale to the pubs, vintage tractors cough into life, stationary engines turn over tirelessly and the commercial vehicles we used to know take to the road again. Don’t miss out, subscribe today to ensure you never miss an issue of Old Glory!\n', '', '', ''),
(577, 1, 'Total Off Road', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTotal Off-Road - the off-roader''s choice for more than ten years! Total Off-Road is the UK''s only dedicated off-road magazine. With features on all kinds of modified 4x4s, green laning guides and information, workshop stories, product and equipment reviews and tests plus so much more.\n', '', '', ''),
(578, 1, 'Bike', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Bike Magazine?\n\nIf you want regular updates on pretty much everything in the motorcycling world, then a Bike magazine subscription is exactly what you''re looking for, bringing you detailed tests of both new and used bikes, plus invaluable riding advice from professional GP riders.This monthly motorcycle magazine''s ''Rated Section'' provides readers with an essential guide to the best models, parts and gear, while the ''Project Section'' brings you expert advice on how to go about planning your own motorcycle trip.Readers are also encouraged to share their experiences and details of their own rides in the regular ''New Reader''s Bike'' feature, creating a real sense of community for motorcyclists nationwide.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBike magazine - Epic motorcycling on the bikes that matter.\n\nBike celebrates the brilliance, the difference and detail of all the bikes that matter to you. Improved tests answer the most important questions about new and used metal, while the expert new Project Section shows you how plan a great trip, choose your next bike and achieve garage greatness. Bike''s intelligent writing and breathtaking photography will inspire you to blast past the long grey queue of normal life and do something epic on your bike.\n', '', '', ''),
(579, 1, 'Car Mechanics', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Car Mechanics Magazine?\n\nWhether you''re a professional working in the second hand car trade, or simply a DIY amateur looking to make some repairs to your motor, a Car Mechanics magazine subscription offers all the essential guidance you need. As well as providing expert tips on how to carry out repairs on everything from cylinder heads to coil springs, the magazine also offers advice on buying used cars, with in-depth analysis of popular models. Comprehensive product tests help you to buy the best tools for your money, whilst the Diagnostics Case Study feature helps to demystify common car issues.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCar Mechanics is packed with essential advice on maintaining and repairing popular makes and models, it''s an invaluable motoring resource that can appeal to the DIY car enthusiast at home and the more experienced motoring trade alike. \n', '', '', ''),
(580, 1, 'Classic Military Vehicle', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Classic Military Vehicle magazine is ideal for military-vehicle owners, enthusiasts and historians. Classic Military Vehicle magazine takes a broad approach to the subject, covering the full spectrum of armoured and soft-skin vehicles from the pioneering days of the Great War, through the inter-wars period, the technological explosion of WW2, the post-war years, and right up to date, regardless of country of origin. Every month Classic Military Vehicle brings you 96 full colour pages of the best and most detailed articles and features on both modern and historic military vehicles. Edited by leading military vehicle and aviation photographer John Blackman and Published by Pat Ware, author and life long military vehicle collector, Classic Military Vehicle is the pre-eminent monthly magazine for all military vehicle enthusiasts. From the commonplace to the unusual - every issue is packed with information and illustrated with rare and archive material, stunning modern photography and manufacturers technical material. Subscribe now, save and have the magazine delivered direct to your door every month!\n', '', '', ''),
(581, 1, 'Racecar Engineering', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Racecar Engineering Magazine?\n\nIf you’re fascinated by the mechanics of the high performance machines at the centre of the motorsport world, a Racecar Engineering magazine subscription is the perfect way to gain a greater understanding of what makes those cars work. Written by industry experts, this is one of the most prestigious motorsport magazines on the market, and has spent years building up a loyal following and trusted reputation in the industry. Focussing on everything from constantly evolving design technology to under-the-hood engineering, Racecar Engineering magazine reveals how new innovations affect the driver''s performance on the track, giving you an in-depth look at the mechanics of the sport you love.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Racecar Engineering magazine gives holders a unique insight into motorsport technology and the way the sports challenges are tackled, every month. From aerodynamics to engines and from handling theory to manufacturing practice, a Racecar Engineering magazine subscription is held by motorsport professionals and those who have an interest in how the real battles in the sport are won. Invest in a subscription to Racecar Engineering magazine, the world’s leading technology publication for motorsport. In every issue of a subscription, the magazine looks under the skin of racing and rallying to show its readers why some cars go quicker than others. Read by thousands of racers every month, a subscription to Racecar Engineering magazine helps them keep a winning edge.\n\nEach month Racecar Engineering brings the best possible insight into all forms of the rapidly changing world of motorsport engineering. From keeping pace with the latest technologies to expanding your knowledge of racecar design and operation, no other magazine gets you closer.\n', '', '', ''),
(582, 1, 'The Commercial Greenhouse Grower', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to The Commercial Greenhouse Grower covers both salad and ornamental crops reports from leading nurseries and growing businesses in the U.K. and in Europe, often featuring the latest cultural techniques. The Commercial Greenhouse Grower was first launched in 1994 filling a void as a title specific to the multi- million pound U.K. commercial glasshouse sector. Its in-depth articles coupled with its unrivalled coverage have helped to establish it as the leading magazine for this sector of Horticulture. The Commercial Greenhouse Grower is produced in full colour, and its clear easy to read format helps growers to keep ahead of the latest varieties, products and cultural practises. Regular Features include: UK and foreign news: Round-ups of what is happening in the U.K. and abroad, including information on new products and services. Varietal assessments: Expert insight into the most promising new flower and salad crop varieties from trials in the U.K. and abroad. Technical features: Written by industry experts to provide readers with the latest technical information, these features cover every aspect of growing from planting to harvesting. Machinery features: A look at the latest new machinery for protected crop growers, from both the U.K. and abroad. Nursery Visits Reports from leading nurseries and growing businesses in the U.K. and in Europe, often featuring the latest cultural techniques. Management features: Offering advice from leading experts on efficient farm management, these features cover areas such as Information Technology , Finance, Law and Marketing. Classified: The classified section includes appointments, businesses for sale, products for sale and items needed. Catalogue Guide: Special showcase section for company brochures and catalogues. Take out a subscription to The Commercial Greenhouse Grower and receive a wealth of information direct to your door every month!\n', '', '', ''),
(583, 1, 'The Fruit Grower', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSubscribe to The Fruit Grower magazine and receive all the top tips to grow your own fruit.The Fruit Grower, contains a broad range of news and features that help to keep commercial growers informed about industry developments and current best practises in the growing of top fruit, soft fruit, stone fruit, hops and cider apples.The Fruit Grower Magazine is an exclusive and best selling magazine which caters for fruit growers across UK. Fruitgrower magazine is a monthly title and has all essential news and up to date information from the world of Fruit Growing. This magazine was launched in the 1986. The magazine still continues its publication with its long credibility. It includes all latest news and up to date information, in depth and interesting technical features, machinery features, management features, farm visit, classifieds, essential and practical advice and lots more.The entire team working behind the success of this magazine has in-depth knowledge as well as a passion for fruit growing.Subscribe to The Fruit Grower magazine today and become the best fruit grower you can be.\n', '', '', ''),
(584, 1, 'The Vegetable Farmer', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Vegetable Farmer magazine is perfect for anyone looking to grow his or her own vegetables. The Vegetable Farmer magazine, offers growers informed news and reports of the latest industry developments in the UK field vegetable and outdoor salads growing industry. Published monthly The Vegetable Farmer magazine contains a whole range of topical news items and features that keeps its readers informed of the latest industry developments. Great reasons to buy a subscription to The Vegetable Farmer magazine: •Save money on the price •Never miss an issue •Get the magazine delivered free to your door each month Buy a subscription to The Vegetable Farmer magazine for you or a friend today.\n', '', '', ''),
(585, 1, 'Volkswagen Camper &amp; Commercial', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGet a subscription to Volkswagen Camper and Commercial - The original and best VW Camper magazine. VW Camper &amp; Commercial is the magazine for those who live their life with a VW van. If you drive a Type 2 then this is the mag for you. Volkswagen Camper and Commercial magazine was launched in 2000 and is the original (and best) VW Bus magazine out there. Each issue is written by approachable, passionate bus owners it has an established reputation for quality writing, drawing on a wide knowledge base, and for bringing together some of the best and most inspiring buses around in the UK (and the rest of the world). The editor, David Eccles, has owned his Split Camper since 1978 and is well respected in the Volkswagen scene and has also written several books about the VW bus and lifestyle. Whether you have a Camper or a Commercial, if it’s a VW this magazine has it covered. Subscribe today and receive a wealth of information direct to your door every month!\n', '', '', ''),
(586, 1, 'Classic Van &amp; Pick-Up', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSubscribe to Classic Van and Pick-Up magazine and receive the most comprehensive guide to vans, pick-ups, campers and ice-cream vans.Classic Van and Pick-up provides 100% coverage of all light commercials up to 1980 - vans, pick-ups, campers and ice cream vans - that are part of our motoring heritage. We also cover foreign light commercials and carry highly-nostalgic features with original black and white photos.Classic Van Pick Up magazine is published by Kelsey Publishing Group and offers unique coverage to this specialised area of classic vehicles and come with news, events, projects, buyer guides and historical motoring heritage. There is a dedicated reader section where people write in with their restoration stories.Subscribe to Classic Van and Pick-Up magazine today and learn all there is to know about this specialist area of the motoring industry/\n', '', '', ''),
(587, 1, 'Classic Bike', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Classic Bike Magazine?\n\nIf you believe that the golden age of motorcycling was in the 60s and 70s, then a subscription to Classic Bike magazine could be right up your street. Aimed at practical, hands-on enthusiasts, this monthly motorcycle magazine focuses mainly on the industry''s glorious past, with a large portion of every issue dedicated to tips on classic bike trading, maintenance and modification. Readers'' contributions about rebuild projects and their favourite memories are a big part of each edition, so there''s a great community surrounding this title, while the hotly-contested Classic Bike of the Year award is always the highlight of the magazine''s calendar.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Classic Bike magazine provides a practical guide to riding and keeping classic British bikes of the 60''s and 70''s. Classic Bike magazine is packed full of great bikes, rebuild projects, straightforward advice on how to run these bikes today from full-on restoration to simple maintenance, practical workshop tips, buying advice and fantastic tales of full-noise, high-octane, un-filtered motorcycling. Classic Bike is a UK motorcycle magazine launched in 1978 and is widely known for coverage of all makes of classic motorcycles, including US and Japanese models, and one-off specials. Under the banner real bikes for blokes with spanners it has an emphasis on practical hands-on motorcycling. A subscription to Classic Bike is a definitive guide for anyone who enjoys messing about with old bikes. Whether your first bike was a BSA Bantam or a Yamaha FS1-E, Classic Bikes is the magazine for you. The Direct Debit Guarantee The minimum subscription term for the direct debit offer is 12 months. The amount paid by Direct Debit may change over time. If and when it does you will be notified in advance by at least 10 days. If an error is made by Bauer Media Ltd or by bank/building society, you are entitled to a full and immediate refund. You can cancel the Direct Debit at any time by writing to your bank/building society and send a copy to Bauer Media Ltd at: Magazine Subscriptions, Tower House, Sovereign Park, Market Harborough, Leicestershire LE94 7ZT. Please note that banks and building societies may not accept Direct Debit instructions from some types of account.\n', '', '', ''),
(588, 1, 'Stationary Engine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPurchase a subscription to Stationary Engine and read all there is to know about the fascinating world of Stationary Engines.The engineering &amp; mechanical hobby that doesn''t cost a fortune to join. The collection, restoration and study of stationary engines is a far bigger hobby than most people imagine. The reasons for this are not hard to find. The diversity of internal combustion engine designs from the pioneer days of the 1870s to the present day outweighs the output of the automotive industry, while they are far cheaper than cars to collect! Their continual discovery, identification and restoration are brought alive each month in the pages of Stationary Engine magazine. Plus many special features and many regular features such as Restorations Identity &amp; Assistance, Discoveries, Engine Torque, Letters etc and pages of engines, and parts for sale and wanted. Buy a subscription to Stationary Engine and receive this unique magazine to your door every month.\n', '', '', ''),
(589, 1, 'Back Street Heroes', 'WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Back Street Heroes Magazine?\n\nIf you''re a serious motorcyclist keen on muscular bikes, outlaw motorcycle clubs and the dirtier side of biking, this magazine will keep you updated on all the latest news from the club scene. With a devoted following gained from 30 years in the business, every issue of this motorcycle magazine is an invaluable source of information on vehicle modification and custom bike shows and rallies, which are often organised by readers of Back Street Heroes themselves. A subscription to Back Street Heroes magazine will bring you together with other hard-core bikers from across the country, helping you to get more involved in this motorcycle subculture.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nWith a subscription to Back Street Heroes magazine you will save up to 50% on the shop price and receive the best bike magazine in the market.\n\nBack Street Heroes magazine is widely recognised as Europe''s leading custom bike magazine. For over 25 years Back Street Heroes magazine unconventional pages have reflected contemporary custom bike-building styles as well as documenting the associated subculture and lifestyle.\n\nBack Street Heroes magazine has a remarkably dedicated following, and there''s a strong relationship between the readers and editorial staff, who not only live the life on a day-to-day basis, but are also involved in the organisation of high-profile events.\n', '', '', ''),
(590, 1, 'Classic &amp; Vintage Commercials', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSubscribe to Classic and Vintage Commercial: the UK''s biggest selling magazine on historic lorries as well as working classics, along with readers'' memories and nostalgia. We cover all aspects of today''s preservation scene, with AT LEAST two restoration stories a month! We also cover rallies, news and much more. Classic Vintage Commercials magazine is published by Kelsey Publishing Group offers unique coverage on lorries from the 1930s to 1980s, some of which are still in use. This magazine details the growing hobby of vintage commercials refurbishing and collection. If you have a love for old time commercial carriers and if you have wide enough land property to park some of these strong machines, Classic Vintage Commercials magazine can be your first choice. As subscription to Classic and Commercial magazine perfect if you love the beauty of classic and vintage vehicles and if you love the heritage behind each vehicle, subscribe today.\n', '', '', ''),
(591, 1, 'Car', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Car Magazine?\n\nAs Britain''s oldest monthly car magazine, you''ll find a wealth of informative pieces every month, as well as features on thrilling driving adventures along some of the world''s most demanding roads, and coverage of the most exciting new cars on the market.\n\nYou''ll love reading the innovative ''Giant Test'' features, as well as exclusive reviews on the best new models ahead of their release.\n\nWith some of the most respected motoring journalists in the industry, a Car magazine subscription is guaranteed to deliver first rate opinions and analysis, giving you everything you need to make an informed purchase.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Car magazine puts readers in the driver’s seat of the most exotic and exciting new cars on the planet. Car magazine covers everything from definitive tests of the new cars you’ll want to drive and own, to epic driving adventures across the most demanding roads in the world. Car provides the insight and opinion that will inform your view of all things automotive. Car magazine delivers true insight on the next generation of cars, sensational scoops and the inside story on the design trends, technology and people shaping your next car. Each issue features the best, boldest writing, and photography so captivating you''ll struggle to turn the page. If you''re an unconventional thinker who is fascinated by everything from supercars to city cars, and wants to access all areas of the car industry, subscribe to Car magazine today! The Direct Debit Guarantee\n\nThe minimum subscription term for the direct debit offer is 12 months. The amount paid by Direct Debit may change over time. If and when it does you will be notified in advance by at least 10 days. If an error is made by Bauer Media Ltd or by bank/building society, you are entitled to a full and immediate refund. You can cancel the Direct Debit at any time by writing to your bank/building society and send a copy to Bauer Media Ltd at: Magazine Subscriptions, Tower House, Sovereign Park, Market Harborough, Leicestershire LE94 7ZT. Please note that banks and building societies may not accept Direct Debit instructions from some types of account.\n', '', '', ''),
(592, 1, 'Volksworld', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Volksworld Magazine?\n\nYou can find all the information you need to become a VW expert with a subscription to VolksWorld magazine.\n\nEvery issue keeps you in the loop with all the goings-on in the VW world, with reports on the latest Volkswagen car shows and other news from the VW scene.\n\nWith this monthly car magazine you''ll get advice on purchasing and maintaining your VW in the ''Practical VolksWorld'' section, which includes Q&amp;As and ''How to'' guides.\n\nYou''ll also have the chance to join in with the regular ''Readers'' Rides'' feature, where proud VW owners can show off their motors, and can write in with any questions or suggestions that they may have.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVolksWorld takes pride in going to extraordinary lengths to bring its readers the most outstanding and fascinating features which cannot be found anywhere else. A subscription to VolksWorld magazine is a MUST buy for all fans of air-cooled VolksWagons and particularly the legendary Beetle. VolksWorld takes pride in going to extraordinary lengths to bring its readers the most outstanding and fascinating features which cannot be found anywhere else. VolksWorld magazine is a major part of the VW scene, be sure to be a part of it by investing in a subscription. It covers the very best vehicles worldwide from full blown modified cars through to the original, providing inspiration entertainment and scene-defining information to its readers. VolksWorld magazine also reaches into exhibitions with the annual VolksWorld Show – the largest indoor VW event in Europe.\n', '', '', ''),
(593, 1, 'The Automobile', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The Automobile Magazine?\n\nIf you''re as interested in the history of classic cars as you are in the cars themselves, this magazine could be your perfect monthly fix. A subscription to The Automobile magazine offers readers regular, in-depth features on the origins of the cars they care about, along with buying advice and previews of vehicle auctions and reviews of sporting events like the London to Brighton Run. One of the most popular features in this classic car magazine is the ''Finds and Discoveries'' column, which every month tells a true story of salvaging a vintage motor from an unusual location, with barns and hedgerows turning out to be the hiding places for buried motoring treasures.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSubscribe to The Automobile and receive the UK’s leading magazine for the veteran, vintage and classic car scene.The Automobile is delivered to your door every month and is jam packed with the latest news and reviews from the car world.A subscription to Automobile magazine will provide you with an all there is to know guide from the vintage and classic car scene. If you are passionate about classic cars then this is the magazine subscription for you.A regular feature of The Automobile magazine is a feature on all the up and coming events for you to attend and will give you a chance to meet other fellow classic car enthusiasts.Subscribe to The Automobile magazine today and receive your indispensable guide to classic and vintage cars.\n', '', '', ''),
(594, 1, 'Truck &amp; Driver', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Truck and Driver magazine subscription presents the proffesional face of truck driving for readers who want to feel good about the vital jobs they do. It is the voice of the British trucker and is 100% for drivers.From gutsy copy on who are Britain''s worst bosses to campaigns for better pay and conditions, Truck and Driver is always on the side of the driver. It offers competitions, puzzles and crosswords in every issue and runs a highly successful family section. Never crude and never condescending, Truck and Driver presents the professional face of truck driving for readers who want to feel good about the vital jobs they do. It gives you a lively entertaining mixture of news features essential information views and comments on trucks and driving in the UK and abroad.Every month Truck and Driver magazine includes articles on all latest news and up to date information regarding the world of truck driving. The magazine brings details of all new product launches, legislative changes, trends etc. It serves the news first with accuracy exclusively for truck drivers. This magazine acts as a valuable source for all drivers.To receive Truck and driver magazine to your door monthly, order a magazine subscription today.\n', '', '', ''),
(595, 1, 'Classic Ford', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Classic Ford Magazine?\n\nIf you''re a fan of vintage Ford, you''ll love this classic car magazine, which focuses exclusively on the buying and upkeep of retro Ford models in its helpful ''How to'' section. With a Classic Ford magazine subscription, you''ll get everything from specialised advice on restoring a recently-bought car to buying guides for specific models, arriving once a month at your front door. As well as guiding you through different maintenance or restoration tasks, this magazine will also let you respond to classified ads, write in about your own Ford experiences, and find out the latest news from the classic car racing scene.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Classic Ford magazine is a must-have for all real petrolheads. Classic Ford is the UK’s top selling magazine about pre-1990 Fords. Whether standard or modified, if it’s a retro Ford it’s here. From the Ford Popular and Anglia, through the Cortina, Capri, Escort and Granada to the Fiesta and Cosworth Sierra. Each issue is packed full of practical advice on how to buy, maintain, restore and modify older Fords, along with the latest news from the classic Ford scene; shows, events, club runs, historic rallying and motorsport. It can be tough to find a regular source of information on Fords that will allow you to complete your projects. But look no further, because Classic Ford gives you all this and more in one monthly package. Every single issue provides a wealth of information that will help you in every way imaginable, from getting your new car back in shape, restoring your old car or creating a completely new car. A subscription to Classic Ford makes perfect sense! Why not treat yourself or somebody else to a year’s worth of the UK’s best selling Ford mag!\n', '', '', ''),
(596, 1, 'Smallholder', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Smallholder Magazine?\n\nWith a Smallholder magazine subscription you can look forward to receiving helpful advice about breeding and caring for livestock, tips on how to avoid and control pests and coverage of all the most important news stories from the agricultural industry.\n\nCovering a huge variety of topics, this gardening magazine offers guidance on rearing cattle, sheep, poultry, horses and even bees, as well as pointers on how to economise, make use of green technology and earn a living from your smallholding.\n\nSo, whether you''re new to the smallholding community or are an experienced smallholder considering branching into a new area, this mag is an essential read.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLet a subscription to Smallholder magazine provide you with all the inspiration you need to grow your own produce.Smallholder magazine is the definitive magazine for Smallholders and has been published since 1910.A subscription to Smallholder magazine brings you a large property and classified section, stock and stud guide plus reader’s letters and articles.Smallholder magazine reaches your door on a monthly basis and postage and packing is all included in the subscription price.The entire team at Smallholder magazine works towards providing knowledge on poultry, feeding, farming, organic farming and much much more.Subscribe to The Smallholder magazine and expand you cultivation skills.\n', '', '', ''),
(597, 1, 'Heritage Railway', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Heritage Railway Magazine?\n\nWith fantastic coverage of the heritage scene and top reporting on conservation and restoration efforts, this is the magazine for all vintage railway buffs.\n\nWhether you look back nostalgically on your memories of steam trains or are just discovering their legacy, a Heritage Railway subscription brings you monthly features on restoration projects, anniversaries and historic retrospectives.\n\nIn every issue of this railway magazine you''ll find stunning photography of trains from all around Great Britain, complete listings of museums and working heritage lines, and even scale modelling guides to let you recreate the great steam engines of the world in miniature.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHeritage Railway has all the latest news from the world of steam era preservation.The highs and lows of surviving British steam locomotives are the main attraction but there’s also room for historic rolling stock, a comprehensive guide to rail tours and updates on signals and stations.Heritage railways reproduced in miniature are detailed in the model section and there are full reports from auctions of railwayana. Interviews give a rare insight into the work that goes on behind the scene to keep preserved traction in action on the main line.\n', '', '', ''),
(598, 1, 'Practical Classics', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Practical Classics Magazine?\n\nIf you''re interested in purchasing, maintaining or restoring the automobiles of yesteryear, then a Practical Classics magazine subscription is the perfect choice.\n\nThis mag is full of engaging articles and features each month, providing you with everything you need to supplement your hobby.\n\nThere''s buying tips, historical insight and hands-on advice in every issue, all written by a team of experts who have been running their own restoration workshop for decades.\n\nYou''ll also find niche guides on everything from classic car insurance to the country''s best dealers, as well as tips on how to keep your own auto running smoothly.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Practical Classics magazine is ideal for classic car enthusiasts.Britain’s best-selling classic car magazine Practical Classics is bursting with informative features on a huge variety of classic cars and is packed with expert technical advice.The writing team runs its own workshop and restores its own project cars, which makes the magazine uniquely hands-on. Practical Classics has been providing help and inspiration for classic enthusiasts for more than 27 years.A subscription to Practical Classics will help you get the most out of your classic car. Practical Classics magazine is bursting with informative features on a huge variety of classic cars and is packed with expert technical advice.Practical Classics magazine is no.1 choice for people looking for comprehensive information on classic cars, restored classics, complete with expert knowledge on every aspect of owning classic cars.Identifying amazing finds and bringing them to life to every practical aspect of maintenance, insurance, accessories, parts, dealers and events, Practical Classics magazine comes with top class advice for classic car enthusiasts.\n', '', '', ''),
(599, 1, 'Land Rover Owner International', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Land Rover Owner International Magazine?\n\nThis car magazine is dedicated to helping 4x4 drivers get the most out of their vehicles.\n\nIf you subscribe to Land Rover Owner magazine, you''ll get access to helpful buying guides for specific models, as well as a regular workshop section which offers hands-on advice on maintenance and repairs.\n\n Experienced drivers road-test the latest models and engines, taking their 4x4s out onto the terrain they were made for, while the ''Stuff'' section gives you an overview of the best Land Rover accessories.\n\nYou''ll also find regular features on driving routes from around the globe to encourage you to plan some off-road adventures of your own.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFor 21 years Land Rover Owner International magazine has been inspiring and informing Land Rover enthusiasts. Land Rover Owner International magazine is packed with off-road adventures from around the world, events coverage, practical workshop projects and advice, off-roading techniques and thousands of Land Rovers for sale. Every issue of this best selling magazine is aimed to help readers buy, maintain, repair, restore, modify and drive their Land Rovers, as well as inspiring them with travel adventures from the UK and overseas. The writers know their Land Rovers inside out, and the adventure writers have been there and done it, showing the best routes to drive and offering top advice for maximum enjoyment. The Direct Debit Guarantee The minimum subscription term for the direct debit offer is 12 months. The amount paid by Direct Debit may change over time. If and when it does you will be notified in advance by at least 10 days. If an error is made by Bauer Media Ltd or by bank/building society, you are entitled to a full and immediate refund. You can cancel the Direct Debit at any time by writing to your bank/building society and send a copy to Bauer Media Ltd at: Magazine Subscriptions, Tower House, Sovereign Park, Market Harborough, Leicestershire LE94 7ZT. Please note that banks and building societies may not accept Direct Debit instructions from some types of account.\n', '', '', ''),
(600, 1, 'Total 911', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Total 911 Magazine?\n\nFocusing on the past, present and future of the 911 line, this mag is essential reading for fans of this iconic flagship model. If you''re interested in classic cars and the Porsche brand, subscribe to Total 911 magazine for updates on auto industry happenings and events, as well as retrospective articles exploring classic models from the sixties and features on the latest Porsche releases. The magazine also gives you a great mix of opinion pieces on the best way to maintain your 911, racing news, exclusive photoshoots and reviews of the latest modifications and updates to existing models.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Total 911 magazine, the world''s only magazine dedicated to the Porsche 911; the only Porsche with over 40 years of history and a worldwide following of keen enthusiasts. Every issue of a subscription to this high-quality magazine is written and produced by true Porsche fans, and offers in-depth, exciting features on all models of 911 – from the classics of the 1960s, through the wild Turbos of the 1970s, right up to today''s sophisticated supercars. Each month of a subscription to Total 911 magazine will feature: * Latest news and gossip from the Porsche world. * Complete Guide – looking over one car in detail – this month it is the Carrera 4 Circuit Guide – we tell you how to get the best out of your 911 on classic race tracks like Brands Hatch and Nuremburg. * Living the Legend – real life reports from Porsche 911 owners all around the world. * Columns from our regulars Kieron Fennelly, John Boggiano and Jeff Maynard - they tell it how it really is: Total 911 – nothing else matters. Invest in a subscription today!\n', '', '', ''),
(601, 1, 'Trucking', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGet a subscription to Trucking magazine - Britain’s best road-transport magazine. Trucking magazine appeals to all levels of the industry as it offers a unique mix of news, features, commentary and truck road tests. Many of Trucking’s writers and photographers are professional truck drivers. Readers can also get involved with a free legal advice service, competitions (Trucking magazine gives away everything from hot drink flasks to a 44-tonne trucks!) and a popular letters page.\n', '', '', ''),
(602, 1, 'Tractor &amp; Machinery', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Tractor &amp; Machinery magazine is ideal for the tractor enthusiast, collector &amp; restorer. Tractor &amp; Machinery is passionate about tractors and produces the most authoritative, in-depth and interesting features from around the world each month. Tractor &amp; Machinery magazine is dedicated to classic, vintage, and veteran tractors and offers practical advice, features on collections and restorations, a massive selection of tractors and implements for sale every month. Tractor &amp; Machinery’s unique approach has ensured an unprecedented demand since it’s launch in 1994 becoming the World''s best-selling tractor magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(603, 1, 'Classic Car Mart', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Classic Car Mart Magazine?\n\nIf you''re thinking of buying a vintage vehicle, this classic car magazine is a fantastic place to start looking. A subscription to Classic Car Mart will give you access to loads of car sale listings, as well as helpful buying guides for specific classic models. In every issue you''ll find features looking at some of the best restored cars, plus reports on recent classic car shows, and a ''What''s On'' section that looks ahead to upcoming vintage motoring events. This mag also offers an interesting twist on test drives in its regular ''Twin Test'' feature, which pits two similar models against each other to help potential buyers to make a decision.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Classic Car Mart, the magazine that brings you everything you need to know about buying, selling, owning and enjoying a classic – that’s probably the best way to describe Classic Car Mart magazine. Published every four weeks, this much-loved title has gone from strength to strength since its launch in 1993 and is now widely considered to be the best in the marketplace for anyone looking to buy or sell a classic car, with a subscription to Classic Car Mart being a must-have. Every issue in a subscription to Classic Car Mart will bring you detailed coverage of major events, rally news, acquisitions, restoration projects and more. Readers of Classic Car Mart can also post classic cars sale adverts on the magazine’s website for free.\n', '', '', ''),
(604, 1, 'Custom Car', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Custom Car Magazine?\n\nThis leading UK mag gives you a monthly insight into the world of modified classic cars, with dedicated coverage of everything from drag racing to hot rods. You''ll love all of the reviews and top tips that come with a Custom Car magazine subscription, as well as the regular event previews and DIY customisation guides. This mag will inspire you to pursue your own classic car projects, with technical advice and anecdotal tales from an expert team of experienced writers. There''s also a number of competitions and in-depth feature pieces in each issue, plus an active marketplace for buyers and sellers.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Custom Car magazine - the UK''s only lifestyle magazine written especially for the hot rod, custom and drag racing enthusiast. Every month in a subscription to Custom Car magazine is achieved through a combination of event reports and previews, up-to-date news, project cars, exclusive features and contributions from the UK, USA and Europe. With valuable technical advice littered through each issue of a subscription to Custom Car magazine, as well as a very active classified section, customization projects and up-to-the-minute news a subscription to Custom Car magazine will keep an enthusiast entertained for hours. All this and much, much more makes a subscription to Custom Car magazine an essential for anyone with an interest in the scene. Don’t wait, treat yourself to a subscription to Custom Car magazine today!\n', '', '', ''),
(605, 1, 'Mg Enthusiast', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO MG Enthusiast Magazine?\n\nIf your list of the world''s greatest cars consists mostly (or completely) of MG models, then MG Enthusiast is the magazine for you, covering the brand''s complete history right up to the present, with retrospectives of the earliest models alongside reviews of the latest releases.\n\nSubscribe to this classic car magazine and you''ll get monthly updates on exciting MG events around the country, as well as features on restoring and modifying classic and modern cars.\n\nReaders are regularly invited to share their MG stories, so whether you''ve spent years working on your car or just bought your very first model, you''ll be welcomed into the community.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA MG Enthusiast magazine subscription features the long-established make-specific publication dedicated to all MGs, covering all examples, from pre-war TFs, to the more familiar shapes, including the Midget and the ubiquitous MGB; and not forgetting the more contemporary mid-engined MGF. MG Enthusiast magazine features over 100 pages which are packed with popular articles aimed at MG aficionados the world over. Featuring the latest news from the scene, the very best cars, buying guides, road tests, show reports, exclusive archives, motorsport and practical advice, it’s the definitive read for fans of this popular British marque. Regular features of MG Enthusiast magazine include- The Peter Welch collection - A rare look at this stunning collection of MGs. Tribute to Phil Hill - The fastest man ever in an MG, this is our tribute to the American legend who passed away this month. The MG Magnette Story - Stunning new photography and the story of how one of MG''s greatest sporting saloons emerged. Roger Parker and the MGOC technical team have been solving your problems in our Technical Helpdesk. Also in our Technical section: MGF/TF AIR DUCT KIT - A cheap and simple way of helping a hard-worked MGF or TF engine to keep its cool and the BUYERS GUIDE for the MGA.\n', '', '', ''),
(606, 1, 'Classics Monthly', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Classics Monthly Magazine?\n\nWith a strong emphasis on practicality and hands-on car restoration, a Classics Monthly magazine subscription is ideal for both new and experienced vintage car restorers or collectors.\n\nEvery issue contains easy-to-follow guides on everything from welding to repairing brakes, all written by people working on car restoration projects of their own.\n\nRegular features such as the staff diaries, which detail repair projects and other motoring experiences, give you an insight into what the experts are doing, while the ''Buying and Selling Section'' provides a marketplace for vintage cars, parts and useful tools, making this the ideal classic car magazine for all dedicated restoration enthusiasts.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\nClassics Monthly is the UK’s most practical classics magazine – dedicated to buying, restoring and repairing any popular British and European classic and sports car from the 1930s to the 1980s.\nEach issue is packed with great technical advice, invaluable buying information and owners’ restorations. Our easy-to-follow guides for beginners and expert owners will save you time and money: we regularly tackle bodywork, electrics, welding, painting and mechanical jobs to make your classic even better.\nIf you have a love of classic cars of every genre, you will definitely love this magazine too.\n', '', '', '');
