(607, 1, 'Jaguar World Monthly', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Jaguar World Magazine?\n\nIf you''re one of Jaguar''s legion of dedicated fans then this monthly magazine makes for essential reading. Every issue discusses how to give your Jag the care it deserves, with regular maintenance advice and workshop articles. Doubling up as a classic car magazine, you''ll also find regular features like David Selby''s ''Auction Action'', giving an overview of buying at auctions, as well as road tests of both new and old Jaguar models. The events section acts as a social calendar for Jag fans and owners, making a subscription to Jaguar World Monthly magazine great for anyone looking to show off their vehicle at classic car events.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Jaguar World magazine, the world’s best selling independent magazine dedicated to this great British marque. Every issue in a subscription to Jaguar World magazine includes an exciting mix of new, classic and used model road tests, buyer’s and owner’s guides, archive photographs, historical features, motorsport and news on the latest model developments. In short, a subscription to Jaguar World magazine is the total package for any Jaguar enthusiast. Published by Kelsey Publishing, Jaguar World magazine is the best selling Jaguar car magazine in the UK market. Devoted to anyone with a passion for Jaguar cars, each installment of a subscription to Jaguar World Monthly provides the reader with essential information about this luxury automobile.\n', '', '', ''),
(608, 1, 'Mini Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMini Magazine is a monthly specialist interest car magazine for men and women of all ages who want to get the best out of their classic Minis.\n\nThe magazine is rammed with technical features, advice, inspirational feature cars and plenty of reader involvement. We create part of the classic Mini community which is a highly dedicated following that is always up for fun.\n', '', '', ''),
(609, 1, '4X4', '&lt;p&gt;WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO 4x4 Magazine? Aimed squarely at the seasoned off-road enthusiast, a 4x4 magazine subscription brings you coverage of every new four-wheel drive vehicle to hit the market, as well as essential buyer''s guides and plenty of practical advice on taking your vehicle into the rough. You''ll find dozens of inspiring features on great off-roading locations in each issue, giving you with the information you need to effectively prepare your vehicle for even the most gruelling off-road adventure. An essential purchase for any 4x4 owner, there''s also lots of handy hints and tips to help you make the most of your vehicle, with new tricks and techniques to improve your experience every month. FROM THE PUBLISHER A subscription to 4x4 magazine is the ultimate guide for owners or people looking to purchase any 4x4.With our unsurpassed coverage of the entire 4x4 market and our road tests, product news and technical features covering both the on and off road aspects of 4x4s, 4x4 Magazine has become a firm favourite with off-roaders everywhere. It is Britain''s most authoritative four-wheel drive magazine with a heritage that stretches back to 1982. 4x4 magazine is an excellent source of information and ideas for anyone who owns a 4x4 and plans to take it off road or to testing conditions. 4x4 Magazine helps you with the best advice on products, techniques, tips and tools.You will learn from this 4x4 magazine that having the best equipment doesn''t guarantee you all the adventure you seek. However, equipped with the best driving skills and techniques, you can pick the right vehicle for the right track and drive it easily through the rough tracks of forests, snow and sand. Each month, you will find tips and techniques that will help you get the most out of your 4x4 driving experience.&lt;/p&gt;\n', '', '', ''),
(610, 1, 'Total Vauxhall', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTotal Vauxhall magazine is the ultimate subscription for those who are passionate about modifying their Vauxhall.Total Vauxhall is Britain''s first and only Vauxhall-dedicated performance car magazine. It features the most exciting modified Vauxhalls around, expert tech advice and information on the latest tuning, styling, ICE systems and products. Total Vauxhall is THE magazine for owners of modified Vauxhalls and is the single most dedicated source for Vauxhall lovers.Included in every issue of Total Vauxhall are wide varieties of in depth and informative articles. It talks about all of the trends, new models, styles and new products available on the market and is a subscription is an essential guide for owners and enthusiasts of Vauxhall to maintain their performance car.\n', '', '', ''),
(611, 1, 'Fast Ford', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Fast Ford magazine, the UK’s best-selling one-make performance title Featuring performance-tuned road and track cars, product news, buying guides, technical advice, engine tuning, plus a massive section of Fords for sale, Fast Ford provides a complete guide to the modified Ford scene for the first-time Ford buyer through to the full-on Ford fanatic. Whether it''s the hiss of a dump valve, the smell of burning rubber, or the roar of a Cosworth YB that gets you going, Fast Ford is what you want to be reading. Started way back in 1985 when the Escort RS Turbo and Sierra Cosworth first hit the showrooms, the best-selling Ford tuning magazine has been covering Europe''s finest fast Fords ever since. With unrivalled tech features and buying guides, the latest news and products and 100s of cars and parts for sale, Fast Ford brings you all the latest from the world of the Blue Oval. Fast Ford magazine gives all the latest events, news and coverage which are guaranteed to appeal to all Ford owners and enthusiasts.\n', '', '', ''),
(612, 1, 'What Car?', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO What Car? Magazine?\n\nSubscribe to What Car? magazine and you''ll receive the benefits of the painstaking and fascinating research the team put into reviewing each and every new car to hit the roads of Great Britain.Their tried and tested methods have been providing car buyers with trusted and expert advice for decades, and a What Car? magazine subscription is the best way to stay up to date with the new developments in world of automobiles.You''ll also find interesting features on everything from the rise of electric cars to the value of petrol engines, plus the legendary Awards issue.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nWhat Car? has been Britain''s biggest and best car buyer''s guide for 40 years - but while the range of models and technologies has expanded enormously since the first issue back in 1973, the magazine''s core aim hasn''t changed: it helps readers to buy the right car at the right price, and to help ensure that there are no nasty surprises in store when you get it home.\n\nWhat Car? provides all the pros and cons of every car in language you can understand; what to pay, where best to buy and the most sensible way of raising the cash.\n\nEach issue of the magazine also informs readers in how to keep their running costs down, has detailed insight into the soon-to-be-launched cars, news and first drives of the latest path-breaking models due to be launched, road-tests of newly launched engine-variants of the older cars and quality photographs.\n\nWith those 40 years of experience in helping its readers make the right purchasing decisions, What Car? is now regarded as the most trusted source of new car advice and is the one-stop-shop for any car buying enthusiast.\n', '', '', ''),
(613, 1, 'Bbc Top Gear', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO BBC Top Gear Magazine?\n\nFollowing the winning formula of the hit BBC show, Top Gear magazine is essential reading for all petrol-heads. Each issue is packed with the latest supercars and gadgets, along with a generous helping of the famous threesome''s trademark banter and expert opinions. You''ll also find reviews of family cars and valuable consumer advice with road tests, price guides and world-first features. If you want a mix of entertainment, useful car reviews and fascinating motoring news from around the globe, then Top Gear is the car magazine for you.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTop Gear magazine is the perfect read for any fan of the BBC television show – and that’s why it is Britain’s top-selling car magazine subscription.\n\nMotoring enthusiasts love the show for the boys’ wit, humour and childish pranks and the magazine doesn’t disappoint either – Richard Hammond, James May and Jeremy Clarkson’s presence is definitely felt.\n\nA Top Gear magazine subscription is ideal for anyone who wants to know what’s what in the world of motoring – whether it’s reviews of the latest cars to hit the market, road tests by The Stig, price guides or even just completely pointless challenges that have no relevance to the performance of a car…\n\nIf you can’t help but daydream about that super fast car, then indulge yourself and order a Top Gear magazine subscription!\n', '', '', ''),
(614, 1, 'Fast Bikes', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nWelcome to Fast Bikes , your home of the best sportsbike tests on the planet, full of technical insight, hardcore action and all done in our own inimitable Fast Bikes style using some of the best photographers in the business. We love to test the latest and greatest bikes on the market - potentially your next bike - but we cater for every budget, thrashing everything from £1,000 hacks to £100,000 race bikes!\n\nAnd that''s not all. We get to talk to the most important and interesting people in motorcycling - be it Marc Marquez to the bloke down the road that fixes bikes, they''ve all got a tale to tell. Then we stack the magazine full of features on bikers, biking and bikers. We have our finger on the pulse in terms of what''s in the pipeline from the manufacturers. We scour the world for the best roads and tracks to ride. We dispense advice through features and regular columns. We speak to all the racers making the news. And we have regular columns, from our riding and legal advice through to top racers speaking about what''s been going on behind the scenes.\n\nWe have one hell of a time making it, meaning that what we put on each and every page is nothing short of blood, sweat, tears and beers! Whether you''re interested in buying the latest headline stealing bike or wanting a tip on how to get your kneedown, why not join the gang and subscribe so you don''t miss out on any of the action - you won''t get the insight, education or entertainment anywhere else!\n', '', '', ''),
(615, 1, 'Motorcaravan Motorhome Monthly', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nBuy a subscription to Motorcaravan Motorhome Monthly, the UK’s best selling motorhome magazine for over 47 years!\n\nMotorcaravan Motorhome Monthly magazine is the only motorhome magazine written by motorhomers for motorhomers, In every issue of MMM, you can enjoy:\n\n· Travel – pages of UK and overseas travel to inspire your next motorhome adventure\n\n· Campsites – as recommended by other MMM readers and our own in-depth site reviews\n\n· Motorhome tests – on new and second-hand motorhomes to help you choose the right motorhome\n\n· Buying – price guides and advice for new motorhomes and second-hand bargains\n\n· Practical – offering useful DIY tips and advice on simple and more complex projects\n\n· Readers’ letters – get involved in the MMM community and share your thoughts and ideas with other like-minded people\n\nSubscribe to MMM today and you will also benefit from:\n\n· SAVINGS on Warners seven outdoor leisure shows\n\n· FREE membership to the MMM Members’ Club with exclusive savings and special offers on insurance, ferry crossings, great weekends away, accessories, outdoor clothing, top gadgets and much more.\n\nDON’T MISS OUT – SUBSCRIBE NOW\n', '', '', ''),
(616, 1, 'Bbc Top Gear', 'Opinionated, entertaining and always on the mark, BBC Top Gear is the magazine that puts readers in the driver’s seat. The world’s leading motoring magazine, with editions covering 50 countries. BBC TopGear is the real deal for the true auto buff. Moreover, TopGear readers get the “real story” behind the world’s most exciting cars in its inimitable honest, irreverent and humorous style.\n\nPrice includes posting &amp; handling charges of Rs. 120 per publisher policy', '', '', ''),
(617, 1, 'Zigwheels', 'The prime objective behind the monthly edition of ZigWheels is to give our core focus groups another vehicle of expression while working within the massive ZigWheels portfolio to synergise our efforts and deliver not just the most comprehensive but also the most enjoyable, informative as well as enlightened automotive content to readers, lay persons, enthusiasts, the industry and also to opinion makers. This monthly initiative would be of a distinctive size and sport high production values to go with quality editorial content in words, visuals and layouts. Topping this off, would be a commitment to cater to the masses, get them hooked on to the automotive movement while at the same time make the content just as palatable to enthusiasts and those clued in to automotive culture. Our cover price would be ultra competitive as well, rounding off the ethos of the ZigWheels programme to penetrate into the massive Indian hinterland.', '', '', ''),
(618, 1, 'Motoring World', 'One of India’s oldest motor journal – MOTORING is the only auto magazine in India for the true auto enthusiasts. Set apart by its sophisticated flavour, bold visual representations, innovative columns, nuanced writing and varied topicality; the magazine has always been the authentic forum for satisfying the interests of a worthy auto – aficionado. Geared for the true Auto-Fanatic, it encompasses a deep range of elements that fuels the aspirations and heightens the curiosities of auto-lovers.', '', '', ''),
(619, 1, 'Evo', 'Evo India evo India is devoted to the thrill of driving. From affordable hatchbacks to 300kmph supercars and from single-cylinder sports bikes to screaming superbikes, evo India aims to put the reader firmly behind the wheel and in the saddle to celebrate the motoring experience. Launched in the UK in 1998, evo has grown to become arguably the world’s most respected automobile magazine for motoring enthusiasts. The 16 editions of evo around the globe focus on driving reviews and adventures, plus up-to-date news, opinion, technology, guides and group tests. Keeping pace with the changing needs of the motorist while remaining faithful to the mantra ‘The Thrill Of Driving’, evo punches above its weight in the hotly contested motoring magazine marketplace. evo’s core team of experienced writers, photographers and filmmakers produce award-winning content that is respected globally for its integrity and professionalism.', '', '', ''),
(620, 1, 'What Car India', 'What Car? (Indian edition) seems to have been just what the doctor ordered for the new-car buyer in India.The country’s first car magazine for everyday people has received an excellent market response.From the latest news, to group tests of vehicles, through to investigative reports and in-depth buying advice, this bi-monthly is helping buyers make an informed choice.At only Rs 30, What Car? has been priced low to ensure penetration beyond the metro cities and into smaller towns across the length and breadth of the country.Just four issues old, the magazine is being heavily promoted through ads on busbacks and hoardings and in leading newspapers.The annual What Car? Road Test Directory is also proving to be a great success', '', '', ''),
(621, 1, 'Autocar India', 'Autocar India is the country’s leading authority for car and motorbike buyers. Having pioneered road testing in India, its road test verdicts are the last word on new cars and bikes. Its monthly content of exclusive news, features and riveting stories continues to be unrivalled. Autocar India is lauded for its high level of editorial content and production standards, and the magazine is complemented by its website Autocar India.com. Autocar India pioneered the concept of advertorials in India, conceptualised and created by the in-house Special Projects team. The magazine also has the biggest and liveliest classified services section of any monthly motoring magazine.', '', '', ''),
(622, 1, 'Flying Magazine - Usa', 'Flying Magazine.', '', '', ''),
(623, 1, 'Overdrive', 'Excitement on the road 24x7…want a lowdown of the latest, best and most happening set of wheels on the road? Overdrive should be the solution and your handy guide on this road run. When this magazine was launched, it was probably the fifth auto magazine in India. But today, it is precious fuel for those who worship cars and bikes. Every month, Overdrive provides the polish and grease from the world of automobiles. What you get are in-depth and reviews of the latest vehicles. Tips on safe driving. Posters. Contests. The competition is, of course, somewhere in its rear-view mirror. Its up to you to decided which gear suits you the most • Overdrive promises to come up with the answers!', '', '', ''),
(624, 1, 'Commercial Vehicle', 'A one of its kind magazine in India, Commercial Vehicle lets CV industry participants profit from some in-depth perspectives. Trucks, buses, construction equipment, infrastructure, tractors, components, UVs and three-wheelers get their rightful coverage.', '', '', ''),
(625, 1, 'Auto Components India', 'Auto Components India, the tenth title from Next Gen Publishing which also brings out Car India, Bike India and CV magazine. As the name denotes, the new magazine will primarily focus on the end-to-end value chain of the automotive components industry and allied segments such as machine tools, service tools, testing equipment, consumables and IT. In covering these sectors, ACI does not exactly neglect OEMs. Under the ‘technology’ and ‘innovation’ sections, recently launched vehicles are analysed with respect to contribution from vendors.', '', '', ''),
(626, 1, 'Bike India', 'The first of its kind, BIKE India has been launched to satisfy the call for an exclusive two-wheeler magazine in the country. Dedicated in its entirety to the country''s burgeoning biker populace, the magazine aspires to be the bible for bikers not just in ', '', '', ''),
(627, 1, 'Car India', 'Car India overwhelmingly acknowledged as the world''s best car magazine, has driven into India under the name of CAR India. Explosive and vibrant, as well as serious and sensuous, CAR India has been launched to satiate the discerning automobile enthusiast', '', '', ''),
(628, 1, 'Airline Business', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Airline Business Magazine?\n\nIf you’re looking for a monthly round up of the most important corporate news from the airline industry, then look no further than an Airline Business magazine subscription. This leading title gives you a comprehensive breakdown of the key trends affecting the management of major airlines throughout the world, with summaries of the latest strategies, marketing techniques and cost control methods to help you develop your career. You’ll find quarterly surveys to keep you up to date with the best performing international and regional airlines, plus the celebrated Airline Industry guide, giving you all of the most important facts, figures and statistics in an easily digestible format.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nKeep up to date with all the latest Airline line news with a subscription to Airline Business magazine.\n\nAirline Business is a monthly international magazine for senior airline management.\n\nAirline Business magazine deals with management issues, including corporate strategy, alliances, marketing, cost control, yields, financial performance and labour.\n\nAirline Business magazine includes four annual surveys, including the Airline Business 100 (September), Alliances Survey (July), Regional Airlines and Aircraft (May), and Airports (December). Airline Business also publishes two special reports: Bridging the GAAP - International Airline Accounting Standards and Disclosures and The Future of Airline Alliances produced with Gemini Consulting.\n\nIn addition, Airline Business magazine also publishes its acclaimed Airline Industry Guide, full of demographic and statistical information relating to the airline industry.\n', '', '', ''),
(629, 1, 'Aviation News', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Aviation News Magazine?\n\nIf you''re interested in the world of both civil and military aircraft, subscribe to Aviation News magazine for in-depth features on all kinds of aircraft across a wide range of eras. This magazine comes with useful tips for enthusiasts, including details of upcoming events and information on hotels with spectacular views of airports, making it your perfect guide to plane spotting. With stunning photography, firsthand accounts from pilots and extensive aircraft history features, Aviation News is the ideal aviation magazine for both hobbyists and dedicated enthusiasts alike. You''ll also get a unique look at the future of the industry in every issue, with expert analysis from leading professionals and military personal.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe Past, Present and Future of Flight...\n\nAs Britain’s longest established monthly aviation journal, Aviation News is renowned for providing the best coverage of every branch of aviation. Now incorporating Classic Aircraft magazine, each issue features latest news and in-depth features, plus first-hand accounts from pilots putting you inside the cockpit. Covering both modern military and civil aircraft as well as classic types from yesteryear, Aviation News covers brings you the past, present and future of flight.\n\nSubscribers Get:\n\nPriority Delivery - subscriber copies go first.\nPrice Freeze - guaranteed no price rise during the term of your subscription.\nSpecial Discounts - subscriber-only discounts on special magazines and products.\n', '', '', ''),
(630, 1, 'Flypast', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO FlyPast Magazine?\n\nThe top title for aviation heritage and preservation, FlyPast magazine includes fascinating historical features on aircraft, manufacturers, air forces and the key events and conflicts of the past century.Spanning everything from the World Wars to the Cold War, a subscription to FlyPast magazine offers you in-depth profiles of important air squadrons and their craft, from the 617 ''Dam Busters'' RAF squadron to the iconic Spitfire.Each issue is also packed with news on warbird preservation and restoration, museum exhibitions and airshows, plus interviews with surviving pilot heroes.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nAt the Heart of Aviation Heritage FlyPast is internationally regarded as the magazine for aviation history and heritage. Having pioneered coverage of this fascinating world of ''living history'' since 1980, FlyPast still leads the field today. Each issue is packed with news and features on warbird preservation and restoration, museums, and the airshow scene. Subjects regularly profiled include British and American aircraft type histories, as well as those of squadrons and units from World War One to the Cold War.\n\nSubscribers Get:\n\nPriority Delivery - subscriber copies go first.\nPrice Freeze - guaranteed no price rise during the term of your subscription.\nSpecial Discounts - subscriber-only discounts on special magazines and products.\n', '', '', ''),
(631, 1, 'Air International', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Air International Magazine?\n\nWith sections on both the commercial and military aircraft sector, an Air International magazine subscription is the perfect source of news and features on all forms of aviation.\n\nThis specialist mag provides dozens of detailed articles, including opinion pieces on the development and evolution of unmanned aerial vehicles, air exercise reports, and individual aeroplane profiles.\n\nYou can stay up to date with recent technological developments and research, as well as flight tests and upcoming military shows.\n\nYou''ll also find plenty of stunning photography and informative articles, giving you an even greater understanding of the industry you love.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nFor the Best in Modern Military and Commercial Aviation...\n\nOver the years, AIR International has established an unrivalled reputation for authoritative reporting across the full spectrum of aviation subjects. With more pages than ever, all still dedicated to commercial and military aviation, we have correspondents and top aviation writers from around the world, offering exciting news, features and stunning photography in each monthly issue.\n\nSubscribers Get:\n\nPriority Delivery - subscriber copies go first.\nPrice Freeze - guaranteed no price rise during the term of your subscription.\nSpecial Discounts - subscriber-only discounts on special magazines and products.\n', '', '', ''),
(632, 1, 'Airforces Monthly', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO AirForces Monthly Magazine?\n\nWith a subscription to AirForces Monthly magazine, you''ll get loads of detailed profiles of modern military aircraft from across the globe every month. This aviation magazine also regularly features personnel interviews, military news continent by continent, and information on the latest technological developments in weaponry or aircraft. With fantastic colour photography of planes in every issue, often sent in by the magazine''s own readers, AirForces Monthly is ideal for any aircraft enthusiast. A regular ''Force Report'' takes an in-depth look at air forces from different countries, while frequent opinion pieces give you an expert''s take on current issues in the military world.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nOfficially The World''s Number One Military Aviation Magazine...\n\nPublished monthly, AirForces Monthly is devoted entirely to modern military aircraft and their air arms. It has built up a formidable reputation worldwide by reporting from places not generally covered by other military magazines.\n\nIts world news is the best around, covering all aspects of military aviation, region by region; offering features on the strengths of the world''s air forces, their conflicts, weaponry and exercises.\n\nAirForces Monthly presents an unrivalled combination of news and reporting, aided by the best network of freelance reporters anywhere in the world.\n', '', '', ''),
(633, 1, 'Combat Aircraft', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Combat Aircraft Magazine?\n\nThis fantastic aviation magazine covers military planes from renowned forces like the RAF, United States Air Force and many others worldwide. Linking modern coverage with intriguing historical features on World War II and the Cold War, Combat Aircraft has access to an incredible archive of vintage aviation photography you''re sure to be fascinated by. You can find out about the planes playing integral roles in recent conflicts, with detailed research going into articles on all the most topical issues surrounding aerial warfare today. If you''re into the technological side of things, you''ll love the expert insights into aerospace engineering, and you''ll be the first to hear breaking aviation headlines from around the world.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nRenowned as the world''s top military aviation magazine, Combat Aircraft Monthly is the magazine of choice for modern military aviation. The magazine covers military aviation subjects from around the world, from combat accounts from the cockpit over Afghanistan to air force overviews and emerging aerospace industry stories, the magazine covers military aviation subjects from around the world, from combat accounts from the cockpit over Afghanistan to air force overviews and emerging aerospace industry stories. Combat Aircraft Monthly delivers all the latest news, with added value from expert analysis, opinion and views from the front line of military aviation.\n\nCombat Aircraft Monthly is the military aviation magazine that sets the pace, often with world exclusives, the best and most authoritative features every month, and all supported by imagery from the world''s leading aviation photographers. With each issue packed with extensive news coverage and exciting features, Combat Aircraft Monthly delivers everything for the military aviation enthusiast in one magazine!\n\nSubscribers Get:\n\nPriority Delivery - subscriber copies go first.\nPrice Freeze - guaranteed no price rise during the term of your subscription.\nSpecial Discounts - subscriber-only discounts on special magazines and products.\n', '', '', ''),
(634, 1, 'Aeroplane Monthly', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAeroplane traces its lineage back to the weekly The Aeroplane launched in June 1911, and is still continuing to provide the best aviation coverage around. Aeroplane magazine is dedicated to offering the most in-depth and entertaining read on all historical aircraft. With a distinct emphasis on military machines from the 1930s, 1940s, 1950s and 1960s, the magazine features such icons as the Spitfire, Hurricane, Lancaster and many more.\n\nHowever, Aeroplane also regularly includes articles on historic civil light aircraft and other types that are scarcely covered elsewhere – making it the most balance historic aviation monthly on the market. Inside every issue there''s the latest news from all around the world, detailed historical accounts, exclusive archive photography from our massive collection of glass-plate negatives, a look back at how The Aeroplane reported on significant aviation milestones, events coverage, book reviews, Q&amp;As and much more. Aeroplane magazine is the essential read for any aviation enthusiast.\n', '', '', ''),
(635, 1, 'Pilot', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Pilot Magazine?\n\nIf you’re looking for detailed flight tests of both new and classic aeroplanes and reports of recent flight shows from across the country, you’ll love a subscription to Pilot magazine.\n\nRegular features include ‘Old Timers’, which takes a look back at classic aircraft from the past, ‘Airmail’, where readers write in with comments and opinions, and the popular ‘Air Brained Quiz’, which tests your knowledge of all things aviation. An Aviation events calendar is included in every issue, along with free landing vouchers that allow Pilot readers to fly into a range of airfields across the UK free of charge.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPilot magazine has been published for over 35 years and in this time it has won more awards for the quality and reliability of its journalism than any other UK flying magazine. A subscription to Pilot magazine will give you monthly access to this excellent publication and its high-quality articles and features. A subscription to the magazine keeps Pilots up to date with everything that is happening within GA. With its inspirational pictures and its regular features which include Flight Tests, Product reviews and Safety Matters a subscription to Pilot magazine is a must have for both new and experienced Pilots.\n', '', '', ''),
(636, 1, 'Sports Insight', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTrade magazine for all independent sports retailers throughout the UK. Of interest also to sporting goods/apparel/footwear/equipment wholesalers and manufacturers. The leading title to serve this extensive market. Up-to-the-minute industry news, vacancies, new products, contacts and advice - it''s an essential read for anyone associated with the retail market.\n', '', '', ''),
(637, 1, 'Director', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Director magazine is an essential purchase for any entrepreneur or senior decision-maker.Each issue of Director magazine includes talks and interviews with the people at the top to find out what has worked for them.Director provides information, advice and inspiration with a strong emphasis on the UK’s growing businesses.Director magazine is brought to you by Director publications and has a circulation base of 53,000 subscribers. All of which rely heavily on the information which is contained in this unique and specialized read.A subscription to Director magazine brings you your monthly dose of inspiration, with articles about entrepreneurs, leadership skills and technology updates.\n', '', '', ''),
(638, 1, 'B2B Marketing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nTake out a subscription to B2B Marketing magazine, your essential multi-platform B2B marketing resource. B2B Marketing magazine was established in 2004 to deliver high-value, quality content to business marketers. The magazine contains a mixture of best practice, news reviews, analysis, research, case studies, profiles, and features on a broad range of B2B subjects, all of which you can contribute to. B2B Marketing offers invaluable practical guidance on how to market your business products or services, focusing both strategically and tactically. It is the marketing bible, which informs the reader to better understand the best way to develop their marketing, to best suit their market, and to product the best revenue return. The content is packed with cutting-edge analysis, insightful comment, as well as surveys, news, case studies and industry profiles - it''s perfect for marketing practitioners in large firms to SMEs.\n', '', '', ''),
(639, 1, 'Public Finance', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Public Finance is an ideal business tool for anyone working in the public sector. Every week, Public Finance magazine is read by chief executives, directors of finance, heads of department, accountants and auditors working in local and central government, the National Health Service, social housing, education and charities. Public Finance magazines aim is to keep public servants up to date with all the latest information that affects their work. Produced on behalf of the Chartered Institute of Public Finance, each issue is packed with in-depth articles, news, comment and jobs making it an invaluable resource. If you need to be kept informed of PFI/PPP, information technology and e-government, best value and outsourcing, asset management and pension funds, risk management, recruitment, training, debate and discussion on the public’s finances, then take out a subscription to Public Finance magazine today!\n', '', '', ''),
(640, 1, 'Casino Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCasino Life is the international casino magazine for owners, operators, &amp; casino managers of European &amp; International casinos as well as gaming equipment manufacturers. Each issue we: - Interview casino owners, CEO’s and managers of gaming equipment suppliers; - Assess gaming equipment and systems in casinos - not just at exhibitions - from the latest slots to gaming tables and equipment; - Showcase operator achievements - including new &amp; refurbished casinos; - Highlight new and future gaming products, casino services and suppliers; - Cover a wide variety of industry issues - from customer service to casino security; legislation to marketing; casino employment and jobs.\n', '', '', ''),
(641, 1, 'Employer''S Law', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAn Employers’ Law magazine subscription is designed to help senior HR professionals stay informed of their legal responsibilities in the workplace. Every issue in a subscription to Employers’ Law magazine is full of news, analysis and information. Practical features in each issue of a subscription include: a ‘How-to’ section, real employment law dilemmas answered by legal experts, a ‘Policy Clinic’ giving tips on drafting policies with clear checklists on what to include, and our popular case round-up outlines the latest legal rulings and your responsibilities. An Employers’ Law magazine subscription comes with the very best news coverage, expert advice, case studies, discussions, Q&amp;As, international news, and guidance to draft or review HR policy. With expert coverage of news and informative guidance, a subscription to Employers’ Law magazine serves HR professionals and employers of all the different industries. Take out a subscription to Employers Law Magazine and make sure you are updated to the latest legal developments, and the best HR practices every month.\n', '', '', ''),
(642, 1, 'African Business', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nAfrican Business is regarded as one of the leading international business magazines. For over 40 years, it has provided decision-makers around the world with a valuable source of accurate information on business trends, risks and opportunities in Africa. African Business gives an independent and objective coverage for African business and economic affairs.\n', '', '', ''),
(643, 1, 'Database Marketing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWith a ten-year track record in covering the leading edge of direct marketing and customer management, a subscription to Database Marketing magazine provides a premier source of information on exploiting both new and traditional direct channels to the customer. Database Marketing magazine was launched in 1998 bringing together the latest news, case studies and feature articles on UK target marketing and customer management for a sophisticated audience of managers and users in the marketing, sales and service functions. Printed 11 times a year, Database Marketing magazine covers topics like campaign management, business and consumer data, customer relationship management strategy and software, profiling, segmentation and data warehousing. Reporting on both business-to business and business-to-consumer issues, each edition contains real job-useful information to keep readers up to date in this rapidly changing area of business. Take out a subscription to Database Marketing magazine today and receive the latest developments direct to your door each month!\n', '', '', ''),
(644, 1, 'What Mortgage', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nWhat Mortgage is the UK''s top selling mortgage magazine and offers a one -stop shop for consumers entering or carrying on their journey of property ownership.\n\nWe cover all aspects of the home buying process for first-time buyers, second steppers, re-mortgagers, buy to-let investors and retirees as well as the surrounding personal finance markets that would all be important when considering home ownership at any level.\n\nHaving led the market for over 30 years, we believe that What Mortgage offers a truly beneficial service to consumers in the UK, while remaining wholly impartial and keeping their best interests at heart.\n', '', '', ''),
(645, 1, 'Corporate Advisor', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLaunched in April 2006 as the first magazine for intermediaries advising companies and their employees on employee benefits including pensions, group risk and PMI.\n\nContains practical editorial content designed to guide subscribers towards new markets and develop new business models.\n\nThe essential magazine for those looking to win more corporate business.\n', '', '', ''),
(646, 1, 'Making Money', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Making Money magazine, which is the UK''s leading magazine for business opportunities and start-ups. By addressing the whole range of opportunities, from established high street franchises through to network marketing companies, a subscription to Making Money magazine gives its holders an accurate insight into what is available and what is required to make them successful. Every issue in a subscription to Making Money magazine contains all the very latest news and information from the world of business, technology, finance and the economic climate. A subscription to Making Money magazine also brings great tips and advice for new entrepreneurs and those looking to begin their journey on the road to starting up their own new business venture.\n', '', '', ''),
(647, 1, 'Boat Trader', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nTake out a subscription to Boat Trader magazine, the largest boating magazine solely dedicated to buying and selling boats and other marine related items. Boat Trader magazine is known as a one stop shop for all things marine and is proud to say they are now the biggest publication on the shelf. A subscription to Boat Trader magazine can offer an even greater choice of boats for sale from Kayaks to Super Yachts and include a comprehensive range of marine services, chandlery and boat jumble. Each issue in a subscription to Boat Trader magazine lists both broker and private boat sales throughout the UK &amp; Europe and really is the essential magazine for boat buyers and customers looking for parts and services.\n', '', '', ''),
(648, 1, 'Pet Gazette', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPet Gazette is a magazine dedicated to all those involved in the pet trade. Targeting pet shops, equestrian suppliers, garden centres and aquatics retailers throughout the UK, it caters for companies who want to sell their products and services to the pet industry.\nEvery month Pet Gazette informs retailers throughout the UK about the latest trends and developments in the industry. It is distributed to every pet retailer in the UK free of charge.\nPet Gazette contains the latest news on the market, new products and features. This magazine is a key vehicle for anyone looking to showcase their products and services in an increasingly competitive market.\nPet Gazette is the obvious advertising medium for manufacturers or distributors seeking to promote their wares to the industry throughout the UK.\nIf you are serious about selling your product or services, Pet Gazette is the place to be.\n', '', '', ''),
(649, 1, 'Money Observer', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nMoney Observer has been helping investors increase their wealth since 1979, with its unrivalled history of delivering insightful coverage on investment market trends and fund strategies. The award-winning editorial team analyses the market to give you the best tips and tactics to use when you’re trading and investing.\n\nWith a subscription to Money Observer, each month you’ll receive:\n\n•A round-up of all the latest news to help you make the most of your savings and investments.\n\n•Our expert view on which shares, funds, regions and strategies we expect to deliver top returns.\n\n•Regular free guides to the best funds, trusts and investment themes to follow.\n\n•A unique and comprehensive databank that highlights the benefits of reinvesting dividends from shares, and key investment ratios for shares, funds and trusts.\n\n•Reports on our highly successful model investment portfolios that you can also follow online.\n\nTry Money Observer and receive 3 issues for just £1, saving you 50% in the first year. Your subscription will also include free early access to the digital edition online, as well as free access to the Money Observer App for your iPad/iPhone/Android devices.\n\nCreate your own wealth with a subscription to Money Observer magazine.', '', '', ''),
(650, 1, 'Slr (Scottish Local Retailer)', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSLR (Scottish Local Retailer) is Scotland’s only monthly magazine aimed exclusively at Scotland’s independent, convenience retailing sector. The magazine is recognized as the voice of the country’s vibrant small shop sector, a sector that continues to prosper in spite of the tough economic times and consolidation of recent years. SLR’s approach has always been a practical advice and help-led one, with a single, all encompassing and very simple aim: to help our readers make more money.\n', '', '', ''),
(651, 1, 'Moneywise', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nAt Moneywise we believe everyone should cut their costs and save money in order to invest it. By investing for the long-term, families stand a greater chance of generating a decent return and being able to fulfil their financial goals. In Moneywise magazine you’ll find a wealth of tips on how to clear your debts, make household savings, economise and budget effectively to help your family prosper, whatever stage of life you’re at.\n\nEach month, Moneywise will help you get to grips with your finances:\n\n•We’ll give you practical advice to help you regularly save money and invest\n\n•We’ll show you which companies you can trust and how to avoid getting ripped off\n\n•We’ll provide you with impartial advice on pensions, Isa tips and more, without the financial jargon.\n\nPlus there are regular competitions with top prizes to be won every month!\n\nTry Moneywise today and receive 3 issues for just £1, saving you 50% in the first year. Your subscription will also include free early access to the digital edition online, as well as free access to the Moneywise App for your iPad/iPhone/Android devices. A subscription to Moneywise magazine could be the best investment you’ll ever make.\n', '', '', ''),
(652, 1, 'Employee Benefits', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLaunched in February 1997 as the first UK magazine to help companies align their benefits strategy with their corporate objectives.\n\nThe only publication to examine the full spectrum of benefits – from pensions and health insurance to company cars and crèches.\n\nEvery month keeping readers up-to-date on developments affecting benefits, case studies of the new ideas that progressive companies are introducing, and the latest research\n', '', '', ''),
(653, 1, 'Restaurant', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRestaurant magazine is the leading source for the UK restaurant trade. It is the best and only way to stay ahead of your industry. Each issue is crammed with: •Practical hints and advice for your restaurant •Inspirational ingredients and dish designs •New restaurant openings and career moves •In-depth features exploring key issues •Interviews with top chefs and owners •News and trend analysis •Top jobs from the industry Highly regarded and responsible for the famous annual ‘S Pellegrino World’s 50 Best Restaurants list’; Restaurant is a must-read for anyone working in the industry.\n', '', '', ''),
(654, 1, 'Business Moneyfacts', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Business Moneyfacts magazine features the only business finance bible.\n\nFinancial advisers, accountants, solicitors and businesses of all kinds use Business Moneyfacts to keep up to speed with the commercial finance world.\n\nEvery month Business Moneyfacts magazine will give you all the product information you need on business accounts, buy-to-let, commercial mortgages, venture capital, leasing &amp; asset finance, factoring and more.\n\nAll data is laid out in a clear, easy to read chart format making it quick and simple for you to compare products.\n', '', '', ''),
(655, 1, 'Golf Club Management', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nGolf Club Management is essential reading for anybody who is involved in shaping the future direction of their golf club. It is the only official publication of the Golf Club Manager''s Association. Each month we provide strategic insight into all aspects of the golfing industry, access to unique research and analysis from top journalists and exclusive commentary from industry leaders.\n\nA subscription to Golf Club Management includes 12 issues of the magazine, The Golf Club Manager''s Association Handbook with a directory of all GCMA members and our annual year planner.\n', '', '', ''),
(656, 1, 'Marketing Magazine', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nFounded in 1931, Marketing has become the magazine that truly gives the big picture of what''s going on in the marketing industry. Through news, insightful analysis and powerful comment, the publication continues to showcase exciting content from the media and advertising industries.\n\nSubscribe to Marketing for:\n\n•Stories from the marketing industry, delivered to your home or office\n•Access to monthly downloads of Marketing iPad edition, plus archived editions of the magazine\n•Strategy and analysis from the world’s leading marketers and brands – giving you relevant insight for future marketing campaigns\n•Opinion from the UK’s top thought leaders, including chief executives Arianna Huffington and Camila Batmanghelidgh ', '', '', ''),
(657, 1, 'Pensions Age', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSubscribe to Pensions Age magazine and receive the leading monthly publication from the pensions sector.Pensions Age magazine includes a comprehensive news section and top-quality independent editorial ensure make this an essential read for key decision makers in the industry.Pensions Age also has a higher circulation than any other UK pensions magazine on subscription.Pensions Age is published by Perspective Publishing and is aimed at UK pension professionals which are looking for a reliable source of information and direction and advice to picking the correct pension products for their clients.Subscribe to Pensions Age magazine today and stay on top of all retirement plans.\n', '', '', ''),
(658, 1, 'Moneyfacts', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Moneyfacts magazine will keep you informed with regular personal and professional financial advice. The UK''s largest selling professional financial monthly. From your first issue you''ll see why so many IFAs, accountants, solicitors and financial professionals of all kinds find it indispensable.\n\nEach issue of Moneyfacts magazine contains in depth coverage of the entire personal finance market, as well as a wealth of accurate, unbiased and comprehensive data on personal finance products from all the main UK banks and building societies.\n', '', '', ''),
(659, 1, 'Investment, Life &amp; Pensions Moneyfacts', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nInvestment Life &amp; Pensions Moneyfacts is an invaluable sales tool containing the most up to date fund performance figures of any trade monthly. Its wide-ranging coverage includes income protection, term assurance, self-invested personal pensions, annuities, ISAs and bonds. No financial professional should be without it.\n', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `oc_product_description` (`product_id`, `language_id`, `name`, `description`, `meta_description`, `meta_keyword`, `tag`) VALUES
(660, 1, 'Hr Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nHR is the single most stimulating source of strategic, people-centric, business advice, practice and dialogue. For people-focused, forward-thinking, business leaders who want insight into, and examples of, business-contextualised HR to develop high-performing organisations.\n\nSubscribe to HR today for:\n\n•Engaging content, of relevance and interest to both HR and non-HR professionals\n•In-depth interviews and comment from leaders in the field\n•Articles that provide you with what you need to know, not what you expect to hear\n\nHR will always seek to give meaningful, relevant and useful business focus to its content. HR magazine does not provide you with ''same old story'', but instead always looks to present information strategically.\n', '', '', ''),
(661, 1, 'People Management', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nKeep up to date with the latest developments in the HR world by subscribing to People Management magazine.\n\nPeople Management is the official magazine of the Chartered Institute of Personnel &amp; Development (CIPD) providing the most comprehensive source of information available to human resources and training professionals.\n\nEach issue delivers news, features, event reviews, the latest industry statistics, legal updates, letters and practical advice for anyone involved with managing people.\n\nA subscription to People Management includes:\n•Monthly issues of the HR magazine that packs a punch – delivered to your desk\n•Immediate access to the best and biggest selection of jobs of any HR title\n•Insightful interviews, in-depth features on topical issues and relevant case studies – it’s the title HR professionals are talking about\n•Access to a wider range of People Management articles online\n•The only way to get the most incisive business and HR journalism guaranteed, every month\n\nSubscribe today and have People Management magazine delivered direct to your door every month.\n', '', '', ''),
(662, 1, 'Fortune Asia', 'Business is serious stuff, but Forbes unlocks the mysteries with in depth coverage of issues, trends, events and articles about the personalities that shape the business world today and will determine the future. Forbes has something for everyone with an interest in economics, investing or growing a business. The editors also realize there is a lot going on globally that impact the &quot;man-on-the-street&quot; and his everyday life, so while the cover articles examine the &quot;big picture&quot; throughout the issue, other stories illustrate how the world economy and culture affects the average citizen. Engaging, interesting, stimulating and enlightening, Forbes covers the nexus of the worlds of commerce, lifestyle and culture as only it can.', '', '', ''),
(663, 1, 'Forbes Asia', 'Business is serious stuff, but Forbes unlocks the mysteries with in depth coverage of issues, trends, events and articles about the personalities that shape the business world today and will determine the future. Forbes has something for everyone with an interest in economics, investing or growing a business. The editors also realize there is a lot going on globally that impact the &quot;man-on-the-street&quot; and his everyday life, so while the cover articles examine the &quot;big picture&quot; throughout the issue, other stories illustrate how the world economy and culture affects the average citizen. Engaging, interesting, stimulating and enlightening, Forbes covers the nexus of the worlds of commerce, lifestyle and culture as only it can.', '', '', ''),
(664, 1, 'Cargo Talk', 'Cargotalk is South Asia’s leading monthly magazine catering to the requirements of logistics and supply chain industry. A podium for suppliers, users as well as service providers, the publication is the voice of the industry to raise issues for remedies. It’s also a right platform to display products &amp; services pertaining to complete logistics.', '', '', ''),
(665, 1, 'Mice Talk', 'MICE Talk is a B2C &amp; B2B magazine, which gives a focused insight to the latest trends, news, views and reviews of the MICE industry. It is the first and only monthly magazine dedicated to MICE business in India.', '', '', ''),
(666, 1, 'The Franchising World', 'The magazine showcases hundreds of national and international franchise opportunities across various sectors to choose from. It brings forth the latest developments taking place in the franchise sector, thereby increasing awareness in the franchise community. The magazine is an platform wherein there is information of companies looking for partners in various categories. There are articles which would guide to how to run a business and latest updates in franchise industries. Apart from an expert insight, our vast knowledge resource we also provide an ideal forum for start-ups as well as established brands, to showcase their business potential and grasp potential franchisee''s attention. As you are Aspiring to own a business -subscribe to ''The Franchising World'' magazine Asia'' largest franchise opportunity magazine. It is your gateway to the world of franchise opportunities.', '', '', ''),
(667, 1, 'Indian Management', 'The product has received wide spread appreciation because of its presentation of management issues, thoughts and ideas both from Indian and global perspectives. The Core strength of the magazine has been its ability to make global best practices and business ideas relevant to the Indian Management scenario.', '', '', ''),
(668, 1, 'Retailer', 'B2B content on retail industry, trends, technology, back-end operations, front end operations, human resources, news, marketing strategy, merchandising and licensing.Industry specific stories on Retail Trends, Retail Strategy, Marketing Strategy, Front-end Operations, Back-end Operations, Human Resources, Retail Technology and other verticals of Retail Suppliers and Mall Developments. The magazine features interviews of Retailers, MDs and CEOs of retail and related organizations. A section exploring the latest trend in Brand Licensing and Merchandising highlighting international best practices; News on Store Launch, Investment, Back-end, Shift &amp; Recognition, Merchandising and Licensing.', '', '', ''),
(669, 1, 'Human Capital', 'Human Capital, launched in June 1997, has created a niche for itself as India’s first monthly magazine on HR. It is currently in its 14th successful year of publication! Human Capital continues to be India''s most respected and widely read HR magazine with a 65000 strong readership. Every issue of Human Capital comes packed with feature articles reflecting real, live HR from India Inc. Plus interviews of HR bigwigs, insightful industry practices, HR case studies, an interactive legal Q&amp;A column and more! The magazine has spearheaded a change in the HR industry by introducing for the first time, the concept of an HR business magazine that provides local and global perspectives, as well as information on HR vendors, products and services. Human Capital continues to be India’s most respected and widely read HR magazine. Human Capital’s uniqueness lies in its content, which is largely contributed by HR business leaders and practitioners, major consulting firms and academicians from premier management schools. ', '', '', ''),
(670, 1, 'Human Capital E - Magazine', ' The Human Capital e-magazine is now accessible from your Desktop!\n    Find words &amp; content you want\n    View and use content online\n    Zoom and read pages in easy to read format\n    Navigate easily across documents\n    Replicate the reading experience,online with page flip feature', '', '', ''),
(671, 1, 'Infinithoughts', 'Infinithoughts is more than a magazine. It focuses on Destiny Designing, Spirituality, Religion &amp; Science, Management, Selling, Relationship, Marriage, Parenting, Adolescence, Psychology, Finance, Health, Clarity in thinking, Stress management, and the Science of Living. The content of the magazine is further enhanced by inspirational stories, quotes, growth-oriented posters and thoughts of great masters. Infinithoughts features regular columns on legendary people who have left their impressions in various walks of life, and silent achievers who have scaled great heights against many odds, to enable the reader to take a leaf from their lives and get inspired.', '', '', ''),
(672, 1, 'People Matters', 'People Matters is India''s leading publication on leadership, talent management, people practices and organizational development. The magazine is structured to provide accessible &amp; practical information to help companies implement people practices and initiatives successfully. It focuses on delivery of content by engaging with domain experts in India Inc. which sets the tone for future management debate and discussion, and inspires business leaders. People Matters is a platform where business leaders share their experiences, best practices and ideas which budding leaders and entrepreneurs can apply in their own careers and companies.\n\nPeople Matters is a brand owned by Tetra Media Pvt. Ltd. It is an active organizer of conclaves and events for leadership, talent management, performance &amp; productivity, and compensation &amp; rewards. Besides, it also organizes Webinars to connect with professionals in the industry and initiate knowledge sharing through the virtual platform.', '', '', ''),
(673, 1, 'Small And Medium Entrepreneur', 'With a keen focus on small businesses and entrepreneurship, Franchise India after its long prowl across franchise, retail, and licensing verticals has now come out with its first mainline small business magazine. With a strong focus on entrepreneurship, the magazine is a guiding light for small business owners and entrepreneurs. Providing the right knowledge, information, advice and opportunities to this growing breed of entrepreneurs, the magazine will serve as a reckoning guide for upcoming and growing entrepreneurs and will also carry success stories of established entrepreneurs to give a 360 degree view into the world of entrepreneurship.', '', '', ''),
(674, 1, 'Wealth Insight', 'Serious investors demand ideas and perspective. Wealth Insight brings you facts, insights and analysis you need. It will alert you on threats and opportunities others are yet to perceive. We also try to help you look for the different sides of every issue, to make informed decisions quickly.Wealth Insight is published by Value Research, India''s leading independent research firm. Besides editorial independence, Wealth Insight has attitude, so it never backs away from offering an opinion. But our readers are expected to make up their own minds.', '', '', ''),
(675, 1, 'Mutual Fund Insight', 'Mutual Fund Insight, our flagship monthly magazine, is being published since October 2002. The magazine delivers comprehensive information, analysis, opinion and advice to help you invest with confidence. Each issue contains a comprehensive scorecard of all Indian mutual funds. This magazine is not for those looking for hot investment ideas. We believe our magazine is a steady and conservative guide meant for those who want to enhance the returns on their long-term investments and savings without taking more risks than they can handle.', '', '', ''),
(676, 1, 'Money Today', 'Money Today, is the most comprehensive, yet easy-to-read personal finance magazine. It covers everything from stock markets, real estate and mutual funds to insurance, banking, investor education and even career start-ups. It doesn''t matter whether the markets are up or down, whether the budget is good or bad or whether inflation rate spells hope or despair. Money Today is a brilliant source that tells you how you can make your money work in every situation.', '', '', ''),
(677, 1, 'Outlook Money', 'Launched in the year 1998 under the name Intelligent Investor and re-christened as Outlook Money in the year 2003; it is India''s first and only personal finance magazine. Targeted at the individual investor, Outlook Money gives insight on critical issues, to the benefit of the investor. The best coverage from around the world, packed with world wide news, features, and expert opinion.', '', '', ''),
(678, 1, 'Power Watch India', 'Power Watch India is not just another business magazine in the energy domain. A trade magazine with a difference, magazine consider it imperative to focus on what the industry has to say, rather than carry a unilateral view from the editorial perspective. Power Watch India (PWI) in view of the vast potential for growth in india''s rapadily expanding energy space .Power Watch India (PWI)- aimed at all stackholders in the energy space. The magazine will offer the latest information and updates. It will present monthly industry forecasts exploring many important issues facing the power industry including stories on different segments like: captive , thermal, renewables, IT, transmission and distribution, etc.', '', '', ''),
(679, 1, 'Printweek', 'Printing is one of India’s largest industries, and PrintWeek India is the first truly nationwide title to cover its issues and news. Modelled on Haymarket’s essential UK print trade weekly, PrintWeek, the magazine is written, produced and printed in India and includes dedicated specialist sections to cater for pre-media, digital, press, post-press, paper and print buying sectors. At its launch in 2008, PrintWeek India’s target distribution was 12,000 print professionals in 200 cities. This controlled free circulation – audited from launch by media industry watchdog BPA Worldwide – will rise to a maximum of 20,000 by the end of 2010, when the magazine will become a paid-for subscription title. Editor Ramu Ramanathan has 20 years’ print industry experience and leads a team of full-time, independent journalists covering national and global print business news, trends and analysis.', '', '', ''),
(680, 1, 'Harvard Business Review - South Asia (Print + Online )', 'Established in 1922, Harvard Business Review is a wholly owned, not-for-profit subsidiary of Harvard University. Harvard Business Review''s readers are the men and women charting the future of business. They embrace HBR for its indispensable insights, breakthrough ideas, and current best practices. Harvard Business Review is the source of the best new ideas for people who are creating, leading, and transforming business. Harvard Business Review has bridged the worlds of academia and business by publishing groundbreaking ideas from experts at the forward edge of management and leadership practice, in a format that businesspeople can apply in their own careers and companies. The ideas published in HBR have wide-ranging impact, influencing strategy at leading corporations, setting the terms of management debate and discussion, and inspiring business leaders. Some of the influential landmark ideas launched in its pages include: Renee Mauborgne and Chan Kim’s ‘blue ocean strategy’, Pankaj Ghemawat’s ‘regional strategies for global companies’, Clayton C. Christensen’s ‘disruptive innovation’, Jim Collins’s ‘level-five leadership’, Michael E. Porter’s ‘five forces of competition’, C.K. Prahalad and Gary Hamel’s ‘core competence of the organization’, and Robert Kaplan and David Norton’s balanced scorecard. In 2003 and 2005, the magazine was a finalist for the National Magazine Award for General Excellence, the most prestigious award in the U.S. magazine industry.', '', '', ''),
(681, 1, 'Harvard Business Review - South Asia (Print)', 'Established in 1922, Harvard Business Review is a wholly owned, not-for-profit subsidiary of Harvard University. Harvard Business Review''s readers are the men and women charting the future of business. They embrace HBR for its indispensable insights, breakthrough ideas, and current best practices. Harvard Business Review is the source of the best new ideas for people who are creating, leading, and transforming business. Harvard Business Review has bridged the worlds of academia and business by publishing groundbreaking ideas from experts at the forward edge of management and leadership practice, in a format that businesspeople can apply in their own careers and companies. The ideas published in HBR have wide-ranging impact, influencing strategy at leading corporations, setting the terms of management debate and discussion, and inspiring business leaders. Some of the influential landmark ideas launched in its pages include: Renee Mauborgne and Chan Kim’s ‘blue ocean strategy’, Pankaj Ghemawat’s ‘regional strategies for global companies’, Clayton C. Christensen’s ‘disruptive innovation’, Jim Collins’s ‘level-five leadership’, Michael E. Porter’s ‘five forces of competition’, C.K. Prahalad and Gary Hamel’s ‘core competence of the organization’, and Robert Kaplan and David Norton’s balanced scorecard. In 2003 and 2005, the magazine was a finalist for the National Magazine Award for General Excellence, the most prestigious award in the U.S. magazine industry.', '', '', ''),
(682, 1, 'Stardust', 'Stardust is more than just a magazine. More than just the largest selling film magazine in the world. More than just simply Number one! It is an institution. Stardust the forerunner of the colossal Indian film industry ….. it is the first and the last word in the film world.', '', '', ''),
(683, 1, 'Champak - Kannada', '', '', '', ''),
(684, 1, 'Champak - Tamil', 'Champak is one of the oldest children stories magazine. Since its inception champak has adhered to inculcating moral values in the growing children. Champak is a name children swear by. Published in 8 languages, Champak is a bouquet of short stories, comic strips, puzzles, brain teasers and jokes that sets the child''s imagination free. It is the largest read children''s magazine in the country.', '', '', ''),
(685, 1, 'Champak - Telugu', '', '', '', ''),
(686, 1, 'Highlights Champs - English', 'Highlights Champs is a magazine for 6-12 year olds. In every issue, kids explore new topics, investigate cool subjects and find out more about the world we live in through stories, games, puzzles, riddles, jokes, experiments, science &amp; craft projects and interactive entertainment!', '', '', ''),
(687, 1, 'Highlights Genies - English', 'Highlights Genies is a magazine for 2-6 year olds. It is designed to keep kids engaged in fun activities while helping them develop essential skills they will need in school. It is an exciting, colorful, fun-filled magazine developed by early childhood development experts. The focus is on basic skills and knowledge, creativity and sensitivity to others.', '', '', ''),
(688, 1, 'Brainwave', 'Now science gets more exciting than ever before - Brainwave will be filled with new topics every month and the pages packed with science fun-das! Plus contests, puzzles, crosswords and AMAZING PRIZES to be won! With Brainwave, one gets easy explanations, knowledge on every science subject, things to-do-it-yourself and ideas to open the mind. All these will help children master Science concepts, with practical ways to apply them in everyday life. So, you are on your way to becoming a master in science!', '', '', ''),
(689, 1, 'Tinkle', 'TINKLE is a fun-to-read 72-page monthly comic magazine. Each issue contains several delightful stories, some revolving around lovable cartoon characters that feature regularly in the magazine. Every issue also contains a fascinating science or general knowledge feature, a do-it-yourself craft idea, puzzles, gags, a book review and first hand accounts of various experiences our young readers have had.', '', '', ''),
(690, 1, 'Tinkle Digest', 'Tinkle Digest Magazine is a monthly magazine for kids, it includes new stories, contests (that includes Tinkle Fun Time, Tinkle Picture Quiz, Say It Your Self), news article (labeled as Tinkle Times),''It Happened To Me'' which is a section where readers send in their true life incidents and ''Rhythm and Hues'' where readers send in their original poetry and artworks and ''You Be The Detective'' where you have to solve cases.', '', '', ''),
(691, 1, 'Stuff', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Stuff Magazine?\n\nWhy should you buy a subscription?\n\nWith a monthly Stuff magazine subscription you''ll get plenty of clear and knowledgeable advice, helping you to pick out the best new devices and stay ahead of the technology trend. It''s packed full of insightful information, product reviews and up-to-date buyer''s guides, as well as a witty and down-to-earth breakdown of the latest consumer electronic news and rumours. There''s more than just tech advice, though, with top 10 lists and regular features on everything from the coolest watches to the best jet-skis, making this one of the most unique technology magazines on the market.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nFor 15 years Stuff magazine has been keeping our 3 million readers in 27 countries up to date with a mix of gadgets, gear and tech. Rammed to the virtual rafters with the coolest kit – smartphones, tablets, sat-navs, laptops, cameras and more, with every technology change in the last decade predicted, documented and explained you won’t want to miss an issue and get behind on the latest trends.\n\nFlick through the 150+ pages in each issue and find great sections like ‘Hot Stuff’ – 20+ pages of the biggest stories from planet tech and our ‘Top 10 of everything’ countdown from TV’s to tablets.\n\nWhen you take out a Stuff magazine subscription, not only do you save money on the shop price, you’ll also never miss a copy as every issue is delivered direct to your door. Split the cost of your subscription with bite-sized direct debit payments and ensure that you receive every gear-packed issue.\n\nShould you wish to cancel your subscription it will be cancelled on expiry of the current term which will not be refundable, other than in exceptional circumstances.\n', '', '', ''),
(692, 1, 'Linux User &amp; Developer', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Linux User &amp; Developer magazine, which is the UK’s only magazine aimed solely at Linux professionals and IT decision makers. Every month in a subscription to Linux User &amp; Developer, this magazine provides the best in tutorials, features, hardware reviews, information and inspiration to help GNU/Linux professionals expand their knowledge base and perform more effectively in the workplace. Written by experts in the field, each issue in a subscription to Linux User &amp; Developer magazine also features informative interviews with leading figures from the GNU/Linux scene and high-profile companies that have built their businesses using Open Source software. The GNU/Linux user base is growing at a phenomenal rate and with new developments occurring every day, a subscription to Linux User &amp; Developer magazine is the best way to keep on the cutting-edge of the Open Source scene. Don’t hesitate, invest in a subscription to Linux User &amp; Developer magazine today.\n', '', '', ''),
(693, 1, 'Edge', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Edge Magazine?\n\nFor hardcore gamers, a subscription to Edge magazine is a must, covering all the major gaming platforms, including Microsoft''s Xbox 360 and Sony''s PlayStation 3, as well as online browser and PC games.\n\nThis varied gaming magazine offers you reports on the biggest companies in the industry, giving you updates on significant events like mergers, redundancies and team-ups, as well as news coverage of exciting tech developments.\n\nIn each issue you''ll also find in-depth reviews and previews of the latest consoles and the most anticipated new games releases, from first-person shooters to platform puzzlers.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPurchase a subscription to Edge magazine and keep on top of everything which is happening in the world of videogaming. Edge is the world’s most respected multi-format videogame magazine, delivering incisive, intelligent writing and stunning designs with extensive news, interviews and preview sections. Edge is independent, intelligent, informative, and delivered with unrivalled design values. Among Edge''s many new features, we''d like to highlight: Extended previews and reviews - We''re devoting more pages to the games you care about, providing new levels of insight with expanded content, from extended analysis of game features to in-depth interviews with game creators. Create - We will be looking in detail at the world of game development, identifying emerging talent, landmark design and leading technology to tell the fascinating stories of how game production is shaping game forms. Enhanced online content - Extra insight, related content, screenshot galleries - whenever our website has something to add to your enjoyment and understanding, we''ll let you know. Covering hardware and software from all over the world, whether it’s online, portable, coin-op, PC or console, Edge covers them all, giving detailed, clear and impartial reviews to tell you what you need to know, not what the developers want you to think. To receive all the information you’ll ever need to know from the video gaming industry, place a subscription to Edge magazine today.\n', '', '', ''),
(694, 1, 'Playstation Official', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Playstation Official Magazine?\n\nA PlayStation Official magazine subscription gives you instant access to a world of Sony-related news, making it the ideal gaming magazine for lovers of this legendary brand.\n\nFocussing mainly on PlayStation 3, you’ll also have access to PSP news, Blu-ray reviews, and information on the upcoming PlayStation 4.\n\nPlayStation Official magazine also previews the future of the company and its latest technology, while frequently offering free Blu-ray discs, which give you the latest demos and trailers so that you can try the games before you buy them. There''s also a comprehensive reviews section and lively online forum, helping you to pick out your next purchase.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPlaystation Official magazine is packed full of trustworthy reviews, the biggest previews, plus with official links to Sony it gets the biggest exclusives! Playstation Official magazine, originally known as PlayStation Magazine, has consistently outsold every other Playstation-dedicated magazine in the U.K. as well as abroad. Published by Future Publishing in the UK, Playstation Official magazine is well- know for its integrity and trust-worthy reviews.\n', '', '', ''),
(695, 1, '.Net', '&lt;p&gt;FROM THE PUBLISHER A subscription to net magazine (formerly .net) provides the computer lover with all the information they need to know on the net. net is the world''s best-selling magazine for any web designer and developer. Regular features in the magazine include, cutting-edge features which delve into net culture and the hottest issues for web site builders, hopping and home banking to booking theatre tickets and watching exclusive movie trailers, net is here to show its readers how! Every issue of net also boasts pages of tutorials covering topics such as CSS, PHP, Flash, JavaScript, HTML5 and web graphics written by many of the world’s most respected web designers and creative design agencies. Interviews, features and pro tips also offer advice on SEO, social media marketing, web hosting, the cloud, mobile development and apps, making it the essential guide for practical web design. net magazine caters for all those are serious about commercial internet applications. It is a single most comprehensive guide for all professional and amateur web designers, web developers and graphic designers. Subscribe today to net magazine and keep on top of the internet trends as and when they occur.&lt;/p&gt;\n', '', '', ''),
(696, 1, 'Linux Format', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\nTake out a subscription to Linux Format magazine, Future Publishing’s market-leading UK magazine dedicated to the Linux operating system. Linux Format magazine is the voice of the Linux and Open Source community. Its unique style brings you entertaining and essential news and reviews of the latest from Ubuntu, OpenSUSE, Red Hat and the leading distros. You’ll learn great programming tips in Coding Academy, including Python and Android. Plus get the best from apps like GIMP, VLC and Open Office. All brought to you with our inimitable humour. Whether you’re an IT professional, system admin or you just hate Microsoft and are a Linux user, Linux Format is for you. This scope and depth of coverage has won the magazine a loyal readership among both professionals and enthusiasts.\n', '', '', ''),
(697, 1, 'Retro Gamer', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Retro Gamer Magazine?\n\nThe first publication to be totally dedicated to retro, Retro Gamer magazine is the ideal choice for anyone looking for more information on the console classics. Unlike other gaming magazines, Retro Gamer focuses solely on old-school titles, with developer interviews, plenty of reviews of latest retro-themed releases, and important guides for collectors. When you subscribe to Retro Gamer magazine, you''ll discover things you never knew about your favourite games, with comprehensive walk-through guides, a retrospective look at classic consoles, debates on the best classics from genre to genre, and the chance to be part of one of the most active online gaming communities.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nDo you remember Pac-Man? Do you love classic videogames? Then you’ll love a subscription to Retro Gamer. Retro Gamer is the only gaming magazine in the UK that is totally dedicated to all aspects of retro gaming. If you’re a fan of Jet Set Willy, or still feel that the Spectrum is the best games machine of all time then Retro Gamer is a must-have for you. Each issue contains exclusive interviews with classic developers of old, goes behind the scenes of some of the biggest games of all time, reveals fascinating new facts about all of your favourite games and features the best games released for every console in the last 20 years! Retro Gamer also offers reviews on the latest retro-themed games and boasts an in-depth buyer’s guide for those wanting to add to their existing collections. If you''ve ever fondly blasted away at the Bydo Empire in R-Type, swung Bowser by the tail in Super Mario 64, or navigated all 20 levels of Matthew Smith''s Manic Miner, subscribe to Retro Gamer today!\n', '', '', ''),
(698, 1, 'Digit', 'Digit is a complete family magazine, serving students, parents and working professionals. Digit is published monthly and includes a magazine, a Fast Track and two dual-layer DVDs. Special issues include additional content such as thicker magazine, bonus DVDs, special booklets, and other goodies.', '', '', ''),
(699, 1, 'It Next', 'Presenting India’s only information platform for senior information technology professionals and managers. IT Next aims to aid, inspire and show the way to the top job-CIO Brought to you by India’s premium business–to–business media group, 9.9 Media. If you would like to know more about this exciting platform, give us your contact details.', '', '', ''),
(700, 1, 'Apps Unveiled', 'In today’s time, everyone’s closest companion is a mobile phone. But at the same time, are you utilising your mobile phone to the fullest? Well, check out this issue of Apps Unveiled and find it out yourself whether you are an ‘Appintelligent’ or not.', '', '', ''),
(701, 1, 'Pc Quest', 'PC Quest is the second oldest IT publication in the country. It''s positioned in the enterprise IT implementation space and helps key IT decision makers to understand technologies, choose the right products and solutions, and implement the right IT solutions. PC Quest is ranked as the number one magazine by IT purchase decision makers across the country in helping them with their IT purchases. Established in 1987, PC Quest (earlier PC World India), is the fastest growing infotech monthly in India. ', '', '', ''),
(702, 1, 'Voice And Data', 'Voice&amp;Data is India''s only magazine on the business of communications providing vital information, statistics and analyses on the business, technology and regulatory aspects of Indian telecom and networking. Voice&amp;Data reaches out to the Senior technical, business and marketing managers and other purchase decision-makers across telecom service providers, equipment vendors, corporate users, regulatory authorities and R&amp;D institutes.', '', '', ''),
(703, 1, 'Open Source For You', 'Open Source For You ( Linux For You ) is the latest publication from the EFY Group. With it''s first issue in January 2003, this magazine caters to newbies, power-users, administrators, developers and those belonging to the IT industry. It''s main goal is to enhance the return on investment (RoI) for organizations by deploying Linux (or open-source) solutions. Accompanied by a FREE CD, which carries source code, white-papers, software tools, Linux distributions, and even games -- the magazine aims to provide complete solution for deployment of Linux.', '', '', ''),
(704, 1, 'Electronics For You Plus', 'Introducing EFY'' Premium Edition.\nWith Software Packed DVD.', '', '', ''),
(705, 1, 'Food And Nightlife', 'Capturing the buzz of Mumbai and New Delhi, Food and Nightlife is a fresh and innovative city magazine that guides the young and spunky about their food and party quotients in Delhi and Mumbai. The magazine aims to give its readers a heady dose of food, fashion, party, art, music and lifestyle in a manner they always wanted to know. ', '', '', ''),
(706, 1, 'Hotelier India', 'Hotelier India combines the latest news analysis, products news, industry features, business trends and best practices to create a must read title for professionals in the country''s hospitality industry.', '', '', ''),
(707, 1, 'Food And Travel', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Food and Travel Magazine?\n\nWritten exclusively for people who love gourmet travel and exciting flavours, this magazine covers everything from tips for your next foodie getaway, to unusual and exotic ingredient suggestions to impress your friends and dinner guests. There are plenty of internationally inspired recipes from chefs including Tom Kerridge and Yotam Ottolenghi, as well as advice on the perfect wines to match your creations. A Food and Travel magazine subscription will also help you to discover the most desirable culinary destinations in the UK and abroad, with feature pieces on the best international cuisine, as well as tried and tested restaurants and delis to suit every budget.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nWe in the UK are now among the world''s most adventurous travellers and gastronomes. Horizons are broad, tastes eclectic. Every month, Food and Travel brings these two naturally complementary interests together in a single magazine.\n\nFood and Travel is about adventure; the quest for new foods and new flavours; the discovery of new places and new friends.\n\nThe best travel, wine and food writers have been briefed to search the world for exciting destinations, the latest restaurants and the finest cooking.\n\nTogether we''ll be lifting the lids off saucepans, sticking our noses into glasses, moving and shaking in bars and checking in to some of the most interesting and undiscovered destinations at home and around the globe.\n', '', '', ''),
(708, 1, 'Jamie', 'WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Jamie Magazine?\n\nWhy should you buy a subscription?\n\nThis fantastic food mag is brought to you by Jamie Oliver, one of Britain''s best loved chefs.Packed with great advice on growing your own veg, searching for seasonal produce and working with fresh and exciting British ingredients, a Jamie magazine subscription will give you hundreds of tips on how to create delicious dishes on a budget. In addition to Jamie''s own beautifully photographed recipes, you''ll also find fascinating articles on the history of food, as well as spotlights on a number of top foodie destinations.This is a great mag to help you hone your kitchen skills, with how-to guides on everything from making your own pastry to rustling up a quick mid-day snack.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Jamie magazine subscription is the ultimate read for foodies! Each issue of Jamie magazine has over 101 recipes inside, which are not only delicious but quick, easy to make and come from both Jamie Oliver AND a number of other top chefs - so you know it''s the very best!\n\nThe featured recipes are always seasonal and a fantastic mix of traditional British dishes and food from different cultures all over the world.\n\nIt''s not just a glorified cook book though - the magazine also features advice and profiles on talented chefs and home cooks, as well as Jamie Oliver himself. If you''ve ever wondered what he grows in the vegetable patch in his garden or cooks for his family on a Sunday morning, Jamie magazine is where you''ll find it all!\n\nJamie Oliver says of the magazine, &quot;I might be biased, but I really think Jamie Magazine is up there with the best food mags out there. Every issue is packed with all sorts of delicious recipes from all over the world, plus some British favourites of course, and we''ve also always got loads of exciting stories, tips, tricks and techniques to help you in the kitchen, as well as super quick ideas for midweek meals. Check us out and get inspired in the kitchen!&quot; ', '', '', ''),
(709, 1, 'Great British Food', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Great British Food Magazine?\n\nIf you love celebrating the wealth and variety of British cuisine, then this is the best food and drink magazine for you.\n\nThis magazine is filled with new and delicious British dishes to get your taste buds tingling, helping to inspire you in the kitchen.\n\nYou''ll discover new ways to prepare old favourites, as well as plenty of innovative seasonal recipes, all using 100% British ingredients.\n\nNot only will you learn how to make great, ethically-sourced food with a Great British Food magazine subscription, but you’ll also get helpful pointers on how to kick the supermarket habit, with guides on the best farmers markets and delicatessens in the country.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Great British Food magazine, the publication that scans the length and breadth of the British Isles to unearth forgotten flavours and discover hidden gems. From rapeseed oil producers, to pork pie makers, and oyster dredgers to pig farmers – a subscription to Great British Food magazine brings our best food and drink to life each month. Alongside interesting and informative features, interviews with top chefs, and showcases of the latest grub to hit the shops, every installment of a subscription to Great British Food magazine also includes a wealth of fantastic recipes designed to make the mouth water. If you love eating, cooking and shopping for British food, then a subscription to Great British Food magazine is the ideal magazine for you!\n', '', '', ''),
(710, 1, 'Food &amp; Wine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFood and Wine Magazine is Irelands ''Food and Drink Bible''. Food and Wine is packed with lively and authoritative editorial that includes recipes, restaurant and wine reviews plus features on food and drink trends, Irish artisan producers travel and kitchen accessories.\n', '', '', ''),
(711, 1, 'Cook Vegetarian!', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Cook Vegetarian! Magazine?\n\nYou''ll love learning about vegetarian cuisine with a Cook Vegetarian! magazine subscription. This is the ideal cooking companion for vegans and vegetarians alike, and you''ll find plenty of fantastic meat-free ideas in every issue, as well as recipes catering for a whole range of other dietary needs. Each issue of Cook Vegetarian! magazine has over a hundred original recipes for you to rustle up at home, with everything from quick and delicious weekday meals to top dishes for your next dinner party. You''ll also find a plenty of advice, tips and tricks from top celebrity chefs, with each issue giving you a master class in vegetarian cookery.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Cook Vegetarian! will provide readers with exciting new ways of preparing delicious, easy meat-free food! Cook Vegetarian! is packed with tips, ideas and advice for anyone who wants to create delicious meals without meat or fish. From innovative recipes created by top celebrity chefs that will really impress the guests, through to simple, no-fuss family meals that won’t break the bank, every issue is a one-stop guide for all your cookery needs. Each issue of Cook Vegetarian includes stunning mouth-watering recipes, you can also pick up expert tips to sharpen your culinary skills, nutritional advice to keep you feeling at your best, and all the latest news, ideas and products to emerge from the growing UK vegetarian scene. Whether you’re a committed vegetarian or cutting down on meat for ethical, health or financial reasons Cook Vegetarian! will show you just how creative, adventurous and above all, easy vegetarian cooking can be.\n', '', '', ''),
(712, 1, 'Sainsbury''S Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Sainsbury''s Magazine?\n\nMake your weekly food shop more interesting with this innovative food and drink magazine, with plenty of ideas for healthy and delicious meals that you and your family will love. This well-established monthly mag will guide you through the process of making tasty low-fat food, with buying guides to help you find affordable seasonal ingredients. You''ll find dozens of recipes from some of the world''s best chefs and food writers with a Sainsbury''s Magazine subscription, with the likes of Raymond Blanc, Nigel Slater and Mary Berry helping you to impress your guests and delight your family. It''s not all about food, though, with practical tips on everything from saving money to dealing with everyday family problems.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSainsbury’s Magazine is a must-have for people who don’t just have to cook....they love to cook! Packed with delicious recipes from the UK’s best chefs and recipe writers it will inspire you for months to come. From Nigel Slater to Raymond Blanc, Mary Berry to Nigella Lawson there is always something something special for when you’re entertaining friends and family, and the magazine’s SmartCook section will help you out every day of the week as it focuses on quick, healthy suppers and step-by-step dishes. But Sainsbury’s Magazine is not just another food magazine! In addition there are many beautiful glossy pages filled with brilliant ideas for all the other important areas of your life; from health to home decorating, travel to style and beauty. Top writers cover subjects such as money, work, relationships and all the issues affecting families today. Sainsbury’s Magazine has more readers than any other glossy monthly magazine in the UK. Here is your opportunity to find out why!\n', '', '', ''),
(713, 1, 'Food Heaven', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Food Heaven Magazine?\n\nThis is a truly unique food and drink magazine series, focusing on an entirely new area of baking in every issue, from cupcakes to cake decoration. You''ll find inspiring recipes, challenging projects and new techniques every month with a Food Heaven magazine subscription, all designed to help you create delicious treats for your friends and family. There''s also a whole range of fantastic features and interviews with a number of celebrated international chefs, including French patisserie Eric Lanlard and royal wedding baker Fiona Cairns, giving you an insight into the creative process and inspiration behind some of their best creations.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nDo you know someone who has been bitten by the baking bug? Food Heaven is just for them. With three magazines in one, they will receive Cupcake Heaven, Cake Decoration Heaven and Baking Heaven on a seasonal rotation basis, providing new recipes and techniques for taking their hobby to the next level.\n', '', '', ''),
(714, 1, 'Decanter', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Decanter Magazine?\n\nAs the world’s best-selling monthly wine publication, a Decanter magazine subscription is a great way to improve your knowledge of your favourite tipple.\n\nEach issue offers in-depth taste guides and shopping advice to help you seek out the best quality vintage and modern wines from around the world.\n\nWhether you''re looking for the next bottle to add to your growing collection or simply want to find the perfect flavour to compliment your culinary exploits, this magazine will guide you through the process, step-by-step.\n\nYou''ll also find insightful interviews with international producers and tasters, plus a comprehensive list of luxury and budget bottles every month.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Decanter magazine gives you everything you need and want to know about wine from all over the world.Decanter Magazine was founded in 1975, Decanter is the ‘wine bible’, read by experts and enthusiasts in over 90 countries. Its authoritative mix of news, interviews with leading wine personalities, regional profiles and wine recommendations, mean you will always be well informed. Decanter, the world''s number one wine and spirit magazine, is read by serious experts and enthusiasts alike all of whom appreciate the varied editorial based on news updates regional profiles buying guides and informed features. If you are passionate about wine it''s the magazine for you. Decanter Fine Wine Encounters, Decanter City Events, Decanter Trade Events and Decanter Dinners are some of the features that bring the news of finest wine events of the world. Hundreds of wine producers present their productions and wine tasters share their verdict on the wines presented. Decanter magazine gives a chance to learn about the fine wines of Bordeaux to the less expensive wines from different parts of Europe and around the world. Whether you want to learn more or enhance your existing knowledge of wine, subscribe to Decanter today.\n', '', '', ''),
(715, 1, 'Cake Craft And Decoration', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nCake Craft &amp; Decoration is the world’s leading monthly magazine for all those interested in cake decoration and sugarcraft. Every issue carries eight to twelve complete projects for readers to make, plus news on products, shows and suppliers.\n\nProjects include birthday cakes, wedding cakes, novelty cakes, floral decorations, and anniversary cakes. Each one has clear instructions and step-by-step colour photographs plus details of equipment and ingredients, and tips and techniques for the perfect results.\n\nProjects are designed for all levels of cake decorating skills and include modelling, sugar flowers, pastillage work, sugarpaste, marzipan and royal icing.\n', '', '', ''),
(716, 1, 'Bbc Good Food', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO BBC Good Food Magazine?\n\nIf you want to add a few new skills to your cookery repertoire but don’t know where to start, then this is the perfect magazine subscription for you.\n\nThere’s no need to struggle to find exotic ingredients, with BBC Good Food magazine providing you with a comprehensive buying guide to accompany all of their mouth-watering dishes.\n\nSome of the UK’s top TV chefs come together to give you a head start on even the most complex of recipes, with candid interviews giving you an insight into professional techniques and time-saving tricks.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to BBC Good Food Magazine is a must for everyone who loves food and cooking. Every issue of a BBC Good Food Magazine subscription is packed with great seasonal recipes, tried and tested by our experts so you can be sure they’ll work first time. With buyers’ guides and recipes from all the top TV chefs, it’s a feast in itself. BBC Good Food Magazine is the UK''s no.1 food magazine, and every issue in a subscription is filled with over 80 recipes for everyday meals, easy entertaining and dishes from celebrity chefs. At BBC Good Food magazine our expert team provides you with lots of tips that will help you every step of the way. Plus, each month of the subscription there is a TV section, which includes recipes from popular cookery programmes. Whether you are a beginner or want to create something new and exciting for every meal of the month - this is the magazine for you. Take out a subscription online today!\n', '', '', ''),
(717, 1, 'The Spirits Business', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe Spirits Business, the world''s only dedicated spirits trade publication, is at the forefront of everything that is happening in the spirits industry, from new product launches and marketing campaigns to cocktail competitions and on-trade news.\n\nOur varied and insightful features and analysis cover a broad range of topics, while our team of award-winning journalists strive to cover the issues most important to our readers through probing interviews, business news, brand updates and exclusive investigative articles.\n\nThe Spirits Business is also proud to say that it is the official and exclusive media partner to the International Bartender''s Association (IBA) which, with thousands of members from 60 countries around the globe, is the largest cocktail community in the world.\n', '', '', ''),
(718, 1, 'The Drinks Business', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe Drinks Business is the world''s leading drinks trade publication. We are at the forefront of what is happening in the drinks industry; focusing on wine, spirits and beer.\n\nEvery month we deliver a magazine containing a unique mix of the latest news, opinion and features. No other magazines covers beer, wine and spirits with such enthusiasm, insight and quality every month of the year.\n', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `oc_product_description` (`product_id`, `language_id`, `name`, `description`, `meta_description`, `meta_keyword`, `tag`) VALUES
(719, 1, 'Olive', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Olive Magazine?\n\nIf you''re a food lover who wants ideas on how to cook up a storm without breaking the bank, then this is the food and drink magazine for you. Every issue contains over 75 easy and on-trend recipes, all of which have been tested by a team of culinary experts to ensure that you get delicious results every time. An Olive magazine subscription also gives you dozens of great tips on how to save money on eating out, as well as guides to help you create a number of mouth-watering dishes from around the world.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\neat in, eat out, eat away.\n\nOlive is the stylish monthly food magazine packed with great-value recipes, restaurants and food-inspired travel Every issue features easy recipes that have been triple-tested so they work for you first time. Find out how to cook a whole week''s suppers for just £35, create quick after work meals and great value weekend cooking ideas. Plus nationwide restaurant recommendations including pro vs punter, in which we invite readers to review the latest opening. Our travel pages feature affordable trips to foodies destinations and recipes from around the world to try at home.\n', '', '', ''),
(720, 1, 'Your Home', 'WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Your Home Magazine?\n\nWhy should you buy a subscription?\n\nWhether you’re on the hunt for some stylish home accessories or planning a complete makeover of your humble abode, a Your Home magazine subscription will help you to turn your home around within a realistic budget.\n\nThis monthly home interest magazine offers step-by-step guides for making home improvements, together with decorating inspiration and lessons from celebrity designers and property experts on how to make the most of your space.\n\nYou''ll also find inspirational tips from regular readers, plus money-saving ideas to help you with everything from quick home repairs to clever furniture updates.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Your Home magazine, featuring real life reader homes, budget-conscious room by room makeovers and plenty of ideas to steal, is not to be missed. And if this wasn’t enough, celebrity experts – such as interior designer Richard Randall and property expert George Clarke – are on hand every month to offer decorating and DIY advice.\n\nWhether you''re currently renting, buying your first home or simply want to revamp your current house, Your Home is the ultimate magazine for affordable ideas and inspiration.\n\nA Your Home magazine subscription delivers direct to your door excellent value, easy to understand decorating inspiration and practical home improvement advice for every room, all in a contemporary and upbeat magazine. Plus, refreshing editorial features to bring out the hidden decorator in everyone, inspiring confidence and trust by showing you how to make the most of your space.\n\nEvery issue is packed with inspiring ideas to give your home a personal touch from simple sewing projects to creative crafts to make, as well as money-saving furniture revamps and clever quick fixes.\n\nFrom only £16 for one year, get a subscription to Your Home magazine and every month you will be guided step-by-step through a selection of quick and simple projects that not only look great but really work; from what it will cost to how long it will take and how you can do it. Your Home magazine also provides an invaluable source of information on what to look for when you buy and how to achieve designer looks within a realistic budget. ', '', '', ''),
(721, 1, 'Modern Painters', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Modern Painters magazine subscription is the definitive international source for analysis of contemporary art and culture, from painting and sculpture to photography, film, architecture, design, and performance. The oversized pages are visually dynamic, full of artwork by some of the most exciting talents working today, much of it previously unseen. The writing - by some of the best known voices inside and outside of the art world - is fresh, incisive, and above all accessible. Modern Painters magazine, which was founded in 2001 by the publisher Louise Blouin, is an international source of commentary and analysis of culture and contemporary art. The magazine offers an uncompromising and direct approach to exploring art in every aspect along with film, photography, culture, books, dance and design. Magazine readers and subscribers will benefit from information provided on trends and events in the world of art and culture. Modern painters magazine provides a dynamic and empathetic voice to both readers who are involved in the art world and those who may be just entering.Modern Painters is a monthly art magazine, which is published by Louise Blouin Media in New York City. If you subscribe to Modern Painters you will receive 9 issues per year and each issue includes two profiles from International artists.\nSubscribe to Modern Painters today: It is the complete read for the true creative in you.', '', '', ''),
(722, 1, 'House Beautiful', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO House Beautiful Magazine?\n\nAs one of the leading home interest magazines, House Beautiful has been helping generations of home owners to get creative with their interiors for over a century. Every issue includes tips from leading international designers, features on stunning properties from Italy to India, and exclusive budget-conscious advice on how to add those special details that''ll update any interior.\n\nIf you subscribe to House Beautiful magazine you’ll also have access to its regular colour-scheming pages, as well as competitions and original gift ideas. All of this is complemented by breathtaking photography that''s sure to inspire you to freshen up the look of your home.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA House Beautiful subscription will inspire you to create the home of your dreams!\n\nHouse Beautiful is an interior design magazine that focuses on decorating and the domestic arts, discovering expert design tips and creative ideas to help you transform your home.\n\nHouse Beautiful is your one-stop shop for classic decorating looks, with regular and comprehensive colour-scheming pages and a wide range of shopping suggestions for those special details that make a difference.\n\nEach issue of House Beautiful magazine provides top designs by international designers and architects, gardening and landscaping articles, ideas and suggestions on how to beautify any ordinary home, complete with breathtaking photographs!\n\nWith over 100 years experience in assisting readers in every aspect of creating the perfect home from planning their budgets and making the best decisions on building materials, colours and concepts, a House Beautiful magazine subscription is a must-have for all who take pride in where they live.\n\nTHESE SUBSCRIPTIONS MAY NOT INCLUDE ALL PROMOTIONAL ITEMS PACKAGED WITH THE MAGAZINE.\n', '', '', ''),
(723, 1, 'Aesthetica Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Aesthetica Magazine?\n\nIf you''re keen to discover new talent or want to gain a fresh perspective on contemporary culture, then this is the perfect arts magazine for you.\n\nIt''s packed full of engaging content, including regular insights into the work of up and coming contemporary artists, complete with compelling debate surrounding the future of the art scene. This magazine explores the worlds of music, film, theatre and literature, providing you with an insight into all of the most on-trend developments.\n\nYou''ll also uncover new artists and musicians, with an Aesthetica magazine subscription giving you a round up of all of the latest YouTube sensations.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nEach artist featured in this issue draws upon a variety of influences to create something entirely original and interdisciplinary. Many of the practitioners are people that have backgrounds in other areas. For example, Barbara Kasten trained as a painter and textile artist before moving into sculpture, installation and photography. A major survey of her work opens at the ICA, Philadelphia. Douglas Coupland’s creative output is prolific; from writing to working as a designer, his latest show everywhere is anywhere is anything is everything opens in two venues in Canada. Fashion designer Dries Van Noten creates collections that are inspired by art and music; the current exhibition Inspirations articulates his creative universe.\n\nWe present work from Viviane Sassen, who creates interplay between the body and its environment. Robert Harding Pittman takes pictures of abandoned construction sites, scrutinising global systems. Matthias Heiderich captures geometric shapes and transforms architectural spaces. And, in film, we speak to Robert Connolly about The Turning, which is based on Tim Winton’s novel. This issue urges you to fuse together concepts from other disciplines and explore the possibilities of stepping outside of your routine.\n', '', '', ''),
(724, 1, 'Period Ideas', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Period Ideas magazine is an essential monthly read for the traditional home lover who is looking to be inspired with beautiful and traditional interior designs for their home. With 180 pages of advice and inspiration, Period Ideas magazine is the biggest traditional homes magazine on the market with the stunning interior designs and home photography from the experts. Every issue of Period Ideas magazine covers everything from the bricks-and-mortar of renovation to the most beautiful interiors; you’ll find every issue full of practical wisdom and design suggestions from some of the UK’s leading experts.\n', '', '', ''),
(725, 1, 'Selfbuild And Design', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nInvest in a subscription to SelfBuild &amp; Design magazine, the essential magazine for anyone considering building, renovating or converting their home. Each issue of a subscription to SelfBuild &amp; Design magazine is packed with expert advice, product updates, inspiration and case studies. Whether you are building your own home, changing one room or just thinking about taking the plunge, a subscription to SelfBuild &amp; Design magazine has all the information you need whatever your style, budget or experience. Whether you are building your own home, converting a current property or modernising an older dwelling a subscription to SelfBuild &amp; Design magazine is the perfect way to achieve the home of your dreams. SelfBuild &amp; Design magazine brings you expert advice, information about all the latest products and inspirational case studies to help you make that dream home a reality.A subscription to SelfBuild &amp; Design magazine really is everything you need to get your project started.\n', '', '', ''),
(726, 1, 'Real Homes', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Real Homes Magazine?\n\nThis magazine can serve as a design handbook for transforming every part of your home, including your garden. In each issue you''ll find contemporary decorating ideas for specific rooms in your house, from kitchens and bathrooms to home offices and kids'' bedrooms.\n\nWith a subscription to Real Homes magazine, you''ll receive great-value shopping guides every month, with advice for stylish additions to certain rooms, plus photos of inspirational real-life renovations. You''ll also get expert advice on practical home improvements, like maximising space or adding an extension.\n\nIf you subscribe to this home interest magazine you''ll even benefit from free tickets to property shows and events across the UK, including the National Home Improvement Show.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Real Homes magazine will help you make the most of your home. Full of practical, accessible solution-focused ideas. Plus expert advice, offering the best tips and researched resources for everyday home improvement.Real Homes is an exclusive monthly home magazine dedicated to helping people create their perfect home. Real Homes gives you the confidence to make the right home shopping decisions as well as giving you a peek into the world of truly stylish real homes. Real Homes is all about helping you make the most of what you''ve got. Full of practical accessible solution focused ideas. Plus expert advice offering the best tips and researched resources for everyday home improvement.\n', '', '', ''),
(727, 1, 'Good Homes', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Good Homes Magazine?\n\nYou''ll love this magazine if you''re an amateur interior designer or a fan of DIY. Packed with photoshoots taking you inside real British homes, it also gives you a monthly overview of new design trends, and brings you the latest in home products from the high street. Subscribe to Good Homes magazine for a monthly dose of advice on where to shop and what to buy when decorating your own home, whether your tastes are traditional, modern or somewhere in between. This home interest magazine is great for giving you the inspiration and confidence you need to start your own home interior project.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGood Homes magazine is now bigger and better than ever!\n\nEvery issue is packed with seasonal shopping ideas, new –season decorating colours and trends and expert interior –design advice, as well real homes, kitchen and bathroom makeovers, and extension projects, plus crafts, recipes and exclusive reader offers and competitions. Plus so much more!\n', '', '', ''),
(728, 1, 'The World Of Interiors', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The World Of Interiors Magazine?\n\nThis beautifully presented home interest magazine is full of interesting features and design ideas to help inspire your next foray into the world of home design. With its stunning photography and fascinating articles, a World of Interiors magazine subscription brings you a number of seasonal design tips from some of the most well-presented homes in the world. From stately homes to rural cottages, modern apartments to exotic villas, this top mag gives you new and original ways to update your property with the latest trends in furniture, colour-schemes and accessories. You''ll also find everything from book reviews to international art exhibitions, keeping you entertained each month.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nINSPIRING, UPLIFTING AND UNIQUE. The World of Interiors magazine subscription brings together the best and the most original features from every corner of the decorating and art world for over 25 years. A World of Interiors magazine subscription is great for Non-professionals who want to collect every issue to see what the stars of the trade are doing. The World of Interiors magazine contains the best design photography and writing, plus expert book reviews, round-ups of the finest new merchandise, and comprehensive previews and listings of international exhibitions.\n\nEvery month a World of Interiors magazine subscription brings together an amazingly varied range of locations and unlocks the door to places you will see nowhere else, from stately homes to seaside shacks, sleek Modernist apartments to crumbling castles. Designed to delight, surprise and inspire, every issue is a source of ideas that will never go out of fashion!\n', '', '', ''),
(729, 1, 'Riba Journal', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSubscribe to RIBA Journal and receive the official magazine of the Royal Institute of British Architects. RIBA Journal magazine is packed with regular essential reading, in-depth building studies, inspirational development profiles and exclusive interviews. RIBA Journal is unmatched in its coverage of topics like commercial and legal aspects of running a practice PLUS there''s our ongoing CPD (Continuing Professsional Development). Edited by Hugh Pearman, the Architecture Critic of the Sunday Times, RIBA Journal is the most reliable source of information for the world of British Architecture.An extremely popular section of RIBA Journal is their classified advertising section, giving details of available jobs in the architecture market.Subscribe to RIBA Journal today and receive this magazine direct to your door every month.\n', '', '', ''),
(730, 1, 'Essential Kitchen Bathroom Bedroom Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Essential Kitchen Bathroom Bedroom Magazine Magazine?\n\nEvery issue of this home interest magazine gives you stunning photography of real-life kitchens, bathrooms and bedrooms that will inspire you to really splash out on updating the rooms in your own home.\n\nAn Essential Kitchen Bathroom Bedroom magazine subscription will bring you feature articles on top-of-the-range kitchen gadgets and bathroom accessories, as well trend forecasts in home decoration and exclusive style secrets from top interior designers.\n\nYou can also find out where to buy the latest furniture and bedroom accessories, helping you to recreate the luxury rooms featured in the mag, so that you can add a stylish, modern touch to your home.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to the Essential Kitchen Bathroom Bedroom magazine caters for the needs of AB homeowners looking to spend money on these key rooms. Subscription readers are at the point of purchase and searching for the very best information, advice, guidance and inspiration from Essential Kitchen Bathroom Bedroom magazine. In every month of your subscription to Essential Kitchen Bathroom Bedroom magazine you can expect to find professional photography of beautiful homes, the latest products, appliance buying guides, interviews with key designers and those in the know, trend forecasts, plus contact details for everyone featured in this prestigious title. Essential Kitchen Bathroom Bedroom magazine has only the top quality, elite products listed, complete with photographs and features of real bathrooms, bedrooms and kitchens. With the extensive listing of the top end products for your kitchen, you can make sure you have luxurious bedrooms, kitchen and bathroom. Don’t hesitate, invest in a subscription to Essential Kitchen Bathroom Bedroom magazine today!\n', '', '', ''),
(731, 1, 'Artists And Illustrators', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Artists &amp; Illustrators Magazine?\n\nSeeking inspiration for your art work is easy when you know where to look, and with a monthly Artists &amp; Illustrators magazine subscription you''ll discover an abundance of creative ideas.\n\nFeaturing step-by-step how-to guides and a wealth of exciting features on some of the best artistic pieces in the world, it''s no wonder that Artists &amp; Illustrators is one of Britain''s most popular art magazines.\n\nYou''ll get an exclusive insight into the creative processes behind a number of the world''s most famous paintings, and top tips on where to find the best materials for use in your own work.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAn Artists &amp; Illustrators magazine subscription is essential for any artist and is the number one best selling art magazine. Artists &amp; Illustrators magazine has for more than 20 years provided inspiration and practical advice to professional and aspiring artists as well as gifted amateurs – and is a compulsive read for everyone inspired by art. Issue by issue, an Artists &amp; Illustrators subscription brings you candid interviews with both famous and up-coming artists, giving you an exclusive behind-the-canvas insight into their paintings and techniques. A constant flow of practical advice from well-known experts helps improve and expand your creative horizons, whilst news of exhibitions and the latest supplies for your studio ensures you stay in touch with this inspirational, energetic world. Whether you favour oils or watercolours, portraits or landscapes, abstract art or botanical illustration, a vibrant palette of features awaits...\n', '', '', ''),
(732, 1, 'Web Designer', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Web Designer is all you need to design and develop stunning websites. Every month Web Designer delivers the finest tutorials, features, news and reviews so you can unleash your creative side. As the premier magazine for aspiring online creatives and industry professionals we offer cutting-edge practical projects spanning XHTML, CSS, Flash and WordPress as well as hosting features and interviews with the web community’s most influential people. Web Designer also has a dedicated Industry section covering news and views from the trade and website showcases featuring the finest design talent. The official blog site at webdesignermag.co.uk uk offers additional editorial, exclusive interviews, reader support plus a series of entertaining podcasts from the magazine team. Every month you’ll read: * Exclusive interviews * Professional advice in our business section on what works and what to avoid. * See behind the scenes with top developers and agencies. * Site Showcases to inspire and encourage you. * How to’s, tips and techniques on: Dreamweaver, XHTML &amp; CSS, Flash &amp; ActionScript, Photoshop &amp; Illustrator, Wordpress &amp; Micro-blogging.\n', '', '', ''),
(733, 1, 'Photoshop Creative', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Photoshop Creative magazine subscription provides Photoshop users with lashings of practical advice and inspiration.\nWhether you''re brand new to the program or simply looking to improve your existing skills, this is the magazine for you. We don''t like to leave anyone out, so we want to make sure there''s something for everyone - from the Adobe Photoshop Elements user right through to those lucky enough to own Photoshop CS3.The aim of Photoshop Creative magazine is to provide you with the best possible resources to help you develop your skills. We know just as well as you do that Photoshop''s capabilities can seem never-ending at times, which is why we''re here to demystify the program and teach you how to use it in a way that suits you. Acting as the backbone of the magazine are the tutorials, which are designed to help you explore new tools and develop new skills. Each tutorial is given a grade - Beginner, Intermediate or Expert - enabling you to learn at your own pace.Whether you''re after information on specific tools and functionality, or you want to learn specialised techniques, we''ve got it covered. We pride ourselves in striking a balance between technical and creative tutorials, ensuring you develop a really good understanding of Photoshop from all angles. Our Big Technique section is specially designed to teach you the ins and outs of specific tools or methods such as Adjustment Layers and Actions. As well as stocking up on practical advice and getting stuck into fun projects, you can also enjoy our in-depth features. These cover all sorts of interesting topics, such as how to compile the perfect portfolio or fake the weather using nothing but Photoshop.Who says learning has to be boring? The main emphasis of this Photoshop Creative magazine is on fun, and we''re here to make your Photoshop experience as rewarding and enjoyable as possible.\n', '', '', ''),
(734, 1, '3D Artist', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to 3D Artist magazine: a luxury title for fans of 3D software and the phenomenal images that can be created. Each issue is packed with advice and inspiration for 3D devotees, all written by first-class artists. In each 3D Artist magazine there are tutorials that give readers valuable insight into the techniques used by 3D professionals, while interviews and features focus on the latest projects being created by commercial studios and freelancers. 3D Artist magazine looks at all 3D disciplines, from TV and architecture design, through to film work, concept art and character development. The unique ''Workspace'' mini-mag is for people training for a 3D career and shines the spotlight on 3D university and college courses, in addition to specific career advice from experts in the field, interviews with 3D studios and recruitment agencies, plus tips for anyone starting out as a freelancer.In addition to the printed magazine, a 3D Artist subscription also has a companion gallery-based website which allows people to showcase their best 3D work and help build up a strong magazine community.\n', '', '', ''),
(735, 1, 'Advanced Photoshop', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Advanced Photoshop magazine is the perfect magazine for polishing up already great Photoshop skills. Aimed towards Adobe Photoshop professionals and enthusiasts, every issue prides itself on its unbeatable quality and sophisticated content. Every month Advanced Photoshop magazine gives you the chance to develop your techniques through several creative and challenging Masterclass and Workshop tutorials. Our intention is to give you the chance to learn new tricks and fine-tune your skills. Whether you''re a design student, an enthusiast who is considering going into the design industry full-time, or an established pro, we guarantee that there will always be something new to get your teeth into. As Advanced Photoshop magazine is written for those who already have a lot of experience in Photoshop, we never dumb down the tutorials, always getting straight into the business of creating superb imagery without wasting time on the simple techniques you already know. Every month includes many different techniques and styles so you can be sure to find something that grabs your interest. If you enjoy learning more about the culture of art and design and appreciate the inspiration that can come from other artists'' designs, then you''ll be pleased to hear that there are regular features on contemporary design subjects and in-depth interviews with a real mixture of pros. One thing that pleases us every issue is how responsive and enthusiastic even the most established Photoshop artist is when we approach them to be included in the magazine. With this in mind, the team hunts high and low every issue to showcase work from only the best.\n', '', '', ''),
(736, 1, 'Grand Designs', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Grand Designs Magazine?\n\nWhat truly sets Grand Designs magazine apart from other home and decor publications is its focus on new technologies and trends in the world of architecture and eco-building.\n\nIf you’re looking for expert advice on how to plan a sustainable project, improve the energy efficiency of your property, or simply want some architectural design inspiration, then this is your go-to mag.\n\nPlus, if you subscribe to Grand Designs magazine you’ll also have access to regular tips on how to make the most of your living space, as well as exclusive interviews with TV presenter Kevin McCloud and some of the property owners that feature on the show.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe official magazine of the hit TV series, Grand Designs Magazine is one of the best modern homes and interiors titles, packed with inspiring projects, expert advice and must-see shopping. With more than 50 pages of real homes every issue, dozens of pages dedicated to the latest launches and innovations, and fact-filled features dedicated to kitchens, bathrooms and decorating, it''s an essential read whether you''re embarking on a total redesign or simply smartening up your existing rooms.\n', '', '', ''),
(737, 1, 'Stuff India', 'The Indian edition of Haymarket gadget title Stuff offers the lowdown on lifestyle gadgets, luxury gadgets, private jets, yachts and adventure sports.Like the original UK edition, Stuff India aims to become one of the most recognisable magazines on the rack.Although its target audience is men in their 20s and 30s, readers of all ages and genders are bound by one common trait: an addiction to the shiny things in life.Editor Nishant Padhiar, former the editor of T3 and consultant editor on AV Max, also edits the Indian edition of fellow Haymarket title What Hi-Fi?Stuff India is among 25 international editions of the title, which together reach more than one million readers worldwide.', '', '', ''),
(738, 1, 'What Hi Fi? Sound And Vision', 'What Hi-Fi? Sound and Vision India was launched in 2005 as Haymarket’s first non-automotive title in India.Initially a quarterly magazine, Drawing heavily on content generated in the UK and benefiting from the title’s worldwide reputation, the Indian edition of What Hi-Fi? Sound and Vision has become the country’s magazine of choice among audiophiles and home-cinema buyers.With the consumer electronics market booming in India, more retailers opening and more country-specific products being developed, the significance and importance of What Hi-Fi? Sound and Vision grows, and it is expected that the title will soon become monthly.', '', '', ''),
(739, 1, 'Exhibit', 'Gadgetise Ur Lifestyle! 130 + Glossy pages hitting the stands every month and giving the readers their monthly dose on the latest in Gizmos,technology &amp; lifestyle .', '', '', ''),
(740, 1, 'Electronics For You', 'EFY was coined after its first product - Electronics For You magazine, which came out with its first issue when the Indian electronics industry was at a nascent stage. Even television manufacture started later. Within a few years the magazine became very popular as the industry grew. Now, with a readership exceeding half-a-million readers, EFY is India''s largest selling technical magazine.', '', '', ''),
(741, 1, 'Electronics Bazaar', ' Launched in February 2007, Electronics Bazaar is India''s first sourcing magazine in the electronics space. This monthly magazine will cater to the sourcing needs of the Indian electronics industry. It will have information on latest components, products and machinery, movements within the industry, along with future trends that will help the trade.  ', '', '', ''),
(742, 1, 'What Digital Camera', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWhat Digital Camera is the world''s oldest digital photography magazine and the UK''s biggest-selling guide to digital cameras and accessories. Packed with authoritative, independent reviews of the latest gear, from DSLRs and compacts, to lenses, flashguns and software, it also offers impartial buying advice, easy to follow tutorials on getting the best from your camera and inspirational features on photographers'' own gear. Learn all you need to know about your digital camera and take the perfect picture with a subscription to What Digital Camera magazine. What Digital Camera magazine is better than ever and now Britain''s best digital photography magazine. Every issue of What Digital Camera magazine features over 200 pages of the latest camera and accessory tests. What Digital Camera magazine also features the most comprehensive Buyer''s Guide, with over 20 pages of inspirational photography and a FREE pull-out camera technique magazine for you to collect and keep. Be sure to guarantee your copy each month by subscribing today! Buy a subscription today to What Digital Camera magazine for you or a friend today!\n', '', '', ''),
(743, 1, 'Electronics World', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIf you are a professional design engineer or enjoy working with electronics, then you should be reading Electronics World every month.\n\nEW provides in-depth analytical features, packed with information and advice to enable you to keep abreast of developments in the electronics industry and help suggest design problem solutions. A subscription to Electronics World supplies handy information in all areas of the engineering industry including test and measurement, RF and microwave, nano measurement, digital signal processing, embedded, automotive, lighting, USB design, and much more.\n\nFirst published in 1913, Electronics World is the most established electronics magazine in the UK.\n\nSubscribe today and save 20% off the cover price Your subscription offers:\n•12 monthly issues in digital and print format\n•Regular supplements\n•Weekly email e-newsletters\n•Annual Test and Measurement Supplement\n\nTestimonial - News, editorial, engineering level articles, but also for projects. I enjoyed the articles/debate/discussion by Self, Williamson and others about audio amps and systems. The magazine addresses an educated audience - an important feature for me. I guess also, that one becomes accustomed to the same authors and come to value their contribution. EW has a regular group of contributors in various fields and I always enjoy reading the contributions they write. E McAndrew Subscriber from Electronic World magazine 2012\n', '', '', ''),
(744, 1, 'Hi-Fi Plus', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHi-Fi+ is Europe''s premier English-language high-end audio magazine. Whether it''s the latest in digital technology or the best turntable you''ve ever heard, Hi-Fi magazine is the ultimate audiophile authority. Our goal is clear; to seek out the finest audio components money can buy. Music is the soundtrack to all our lives and we think that the better that soundtrack sounds the more enriched our lives can be. A good audio system can open up new avenues of music that might surprise you. We don''t differentiate; it could be a classic valve amplifier or a state-of-the-art music server - if it sounds good, we want to know and we want to tell you about it. The difference between good sound and great sound lies in the details... and we are obsessive about detail. We aren''t constrained by measurement of bogged down in the stuffy old paradigms. We are relevant and a little bit irreverent. Hi-Fi+ features some of the best writers in the business, all passionate about making music sound as good as it possibly can. We seek out the finest audio components - and the latest and greatest music - and aren''t afraid of finding the best, whatever the cost.\n', '', '', ''),
(745, 1, 'Pc Advisor With Disc+', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to PC Advisor magazine gives you comprehensive and impartial buying advice, informed easy-to-understand tutorials and trusted reviews. Whether you are looking to purchase new products or make the best of the products you already own, you can trust PC Advisor magazine to deliver expert and trustworthy advice. Every issue of PC Advisor comes with over 30 pages of reviews, covering both hardware and software, from smartphones, laptops and tablet PC’s to graphic cards, netbooks and printers. Plus in depth PC group tests where the latest kit is put through benchmark tests and rated. PC Advisor magazine also features pages of How To’s giving expert help and advice showing you how to improve your PC and its performance. Plus every issue comes with a DISC+ packed with full-version PC security and utility software.\n', '', '', ''),
(746, 1, 'Hi-Fi Choice', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Hi-Fi Choice Magazine?\n\nIf you''re looking to get the best possible sound quality from your home entertainment set-up, then you''ll appreciate the detailed product reviews in this technology magazine. In every issue you''ll find a unique ''Group Test'' feature which pits similar products against each other so that you know which speakers, turn-tables or hi-fis are the best in their class. With a subscription to Hi-Fi Choice magazine, you''ll have access to rumours about future product releases in the audio industry, while you''ll also get the chance to have your questions answered by the mag''s own sound experts every month.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Hi-Fi Choice is the perfect magazine for anyone who has a passion for music and audio excellence.The technology of recorded sound has seen a seismic shift since Hi-Fi Choice’s launch in 1975, yet despite this its core ethos remains. From vinyl and valves, to multi-channel digital audio and high-fidelity video, we sort the best from the rest with rigorous test processes and a highly experienced team of reviewers – a thorough, no-nonsense guide for those who demand supreme fidelity. Hi-Fi Choice magazine conveys our love for music and hi-fi with both depth and accessibility, widening the window on real hi-fi for audio buffs and music fans wishing to make the most of their sonic passions. We have a Passion for Sound.” EDITORIAL FEATURES: A Hi-Fi Choice subscription is the essential guide to audio excellence in the home. It is a no-nonsense guide to the finest products available, packed front to back with tests of unique depth and clarity. Product group tests sit alongside solo reviews, news, industry comment and analysis, added to by authoritative advice sections and a comprehensive buying guide listing all our favourite products.Subscribe to Hi-Fi Choice magazine today and feed your audio passion on a monthly basis direct to your door.\n', '', '', ''),
(747, 1, 'Hi-Fi News', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Hi-Fi News magazine, the world''s longest-established audio magazine. Hi-Fi News magazine was first published in June 1956 and is also the UK''s best-selling enthusiast title with a global reputation for authoritative, decisive product reviews - covering high-quality home cinema equipment as well as the best in two-channel pure audio. A subscription to Hi-Fi News magazine is for people who are passionate about great sound. A Hi-Fi News magazine subscription is the best choice publication for audiophiles looking for a serious guide to equipment, news and developments from the world of sound and audio. Every issue of a Hi-Fi News magazine goes deep into the technology of high fidelity sound systems and brings to a detailed coverage of what it is like to having the best of Hi Fi systems for your entertainment. Each month, the writers of the magazine, passionate about the technology and quality of sound, test several different products and give you their verdict on each product. You will also get tips and techniques of finding energy efficient parts and enhancing your Hi-Fi video experience. The magazine also runs the Hi-Fi News Awards to recognise the finest of analogue and digital components, amplifiers, loudspeakers and home cinema products of all kinds. The coverage of these awards is good option for you to keep updated about the best products available for purchase. The award winning products are usually the items you need to buy.\n', '', '', ''),
(748, 1, 'Android', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Android Magazine?\n\nIf you''re looking for a detailed but easy-to-understand technology magazine that focuses exclusively on apps and devices related to the Android operating system, then this title is for you.\n\nStuffed full of helpful, well-researched features, tutorials and reviews all relating to smartphone and tablet devices and software, Android magazine will provide you with the technical expertise to help you get the most out of your mobile devices.\n\nFrom buying your first phone to everyday use, this magazine provides handy step-by-step guidance and advice each month, regardless of your level of expertise.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nForget iPhones! Android is the world''s biggest selling smartphone platform and a third of all smartphones sold are powered by Android.\n\nAndroid magazine is the go-to resource for tech-savvy Android enthusiasts who want to maximise the use of these powerful and versatile devices.\n\nWith reviews on the latest handsets, advice on the best apps and tutorials on setting up, customising and even hacking Android, this magazine is everything the Android user needs.\n', '', '', ''),
(749, 1, 'Icreate', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO iCreate Magazine?\n\nThis publication is full of up-to-date information on all Apple products, including reviews, special features and step-by-step guides to help you get the most out of your favourite devices.\n\nAn iCreate magazine subscription will ensure that whether you''re searching for a useful application, editing digital video or creating a song using Garageband, you''ve got the latest hints and tips on hand to keep everything you produce on your iPhone, iPad or Mac completely fresh and original.\n\nThere''s more than 50 pages of bespoke tutorials and editorial features in each issue, giving you a comprehensive look into the well-designed world of Apple and its products.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nGet a subscription to iCreate magazine. If Apple made a magazine it would be iCreate. Offering readers a monthly fix of creative guides, exciting features and in-depth reviews, a subscription to iCreate magazine is the essential resource for Mac and iPod users. Designed with the same passion and attention to detail found in Apple products, iCreate magazine offers creative guides to iMovie, iPhoto, iDVD, iWeb, GarageBand and iTunes as well as the Apple Pro Apps and Mac OS X. Offering over 50 pages of tutorials each month, dedicated iPod and iPhone content as well as help and advice for common system problems a subscription to iCreate magazine is the publication no Apple owner can be without.\n', '', '', ''),
(750, 1, 'T3', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO T3 Magazine?\n\nIt''s easy to keep up with the rapid pace of technology and pick out the must-have gadgets with a T3 magazine subscription.\n\nYou''ll find pages filled with all of the most up-to-date gadget news and reviews, as well as a selection of the hottest developments and devices that the industry has to offer, all written in an easy to read and engaging style.\n\nEach piece is accompanied by a stunning selection of photographs to keep you fully engaged, whilst the handy editorial features give you a detailed insight into a brand new sector each and every month.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA T3 magazine subscription is essential for anyone who needs to keep updated on the world’s best gadget. Launched in 1996, T3 magazine is Britain’s best-selling monthly technology magazine. T3 magazine features stunning photography and a powerful blend of news, reviews and features to keep our readers bang up to date with the latest gadgets. Each monthly issue includes a full list of the latest boys'' toys to come out, along with honest reviews of technological gadgets both new and old. Every reviewed gadget is given a rating, which allows readers to an honest and objective opinion before purchasing. EDITORIAL FEATURES: Showcase, Tfile, T3 Essentials (including Deluxe, Active, Style, Auto), Competitions, Reviews, Monster tests, Mini tests, How To, Buyer’s Guide, Installations and Entertainment features. T3 magazine also covers lifestyle consumer products including cars, hi-fi, mobile phones, home entertainment, computing and gaming products and gadgets. A T3 magazine subscription is the perfect gift for the gadget – lover!\n', '', '', ''),
(751, 1, 'Imagine Fx', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nAn Imagine FX magazine subscription is perfect for anyone with an interest in the world of fantasy and science fiction digital art. Imagine FX is the only magazine for Fantasy and Sci-Fi artists. Each issue of Imagine FX magazine contains an eclectic mixture of in-depth workshops from the world''s best artists. Imagine FX magazine also features the latest community news, software and hardware reviews, and the latest sci-fi and fantasy films and comics.\n\nProviding bespoke, in-depth digital and traditional art workshops, tips and techniques, Imagine FX magazine really is the only monthly read for Fantasy &amp; Sc-Fi Digital Art!\n', '', '', ''),
(752, 1, 'Windows 7 Help &amp; Advice', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Windows 7 Help &amp; Advice Magazine provides readers with a complete guide to Microsoft’s new operating system. Windows 7 Help &amp; Advice is the only magazine you’ll ever need to get more from your Windows PC, whether it’s a desktop, laptop or tablet. If you’re new to computers we show you how to get to grips with Windows XP, Vista and 7, but we also go in-depth with a wealth of features and tutorials which show you how to speed up your PC, reinstall your operating system, and make it secure against internet viruses and scams. You’ll even save money as we recommend the latest hardware and gadgets, like Smartphones, that are worth your money.\n', '', '', ''),
(753, 1, 'Mac Format', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to MacFormat magazine will help you get the most out of your Mac. Whether you''re interested in professional 3D work, photo editing or home accounting we''ve got product tests and in-depth tutorials to suit.\nMacFormat is the UK’s best selling magazine for the home Mac user. Each issue brings you all the exciting developments from the world of Apple, including reviews of new Macs, iPads and Apple’s own apps like iPhoto, iMovie and GarageBand.\nWe’ll show you how to make the most of your Mac, OS X and all the creative things you can do with it. We also review all the latest 3rd party software and kit – so if you’re looking for a new hard drive, monitor or printer that works with a Mac, you’ll be well served. iOS users are also welcome and we review the latest iPad and iPhone apps.\n', '', '', ''),
(754, 1, 'Net', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to net magazine (formerly .net) provides the computer lover with all the information they need to know on the net. net is the world''s best-selling magazine for any web designer and developer. Regular features in the magazine include, cutting-edge features which delve into net culture and the hottest issues for web site builders, hopping and home banking to booking theatre tickets and watching exclusive movie trailers, net is here to show its readers how! Every issue of net also boasts pages of tutorials covering topics such as CSS, PHP, Flash, JavaScript, HTML5 and web graphics written by many of the world’s most respected web designers and creative design agencies. Interviews, features and pro tips also offer advice on SEO, social media marketing, web hosting, the cloud, mobile development and apps, making it the essential guide for practical web design. net magazine caters for all those are serious about commercial internet applications. It is a single most comprehensive guide for all professional and amateur web designers, web developers and graphic designers. Subscribe today to net magazine and keep on top of the internet trends as and when they occur.\n', '', '', ''),
(755, 1, 'Pc Gamer', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO PC Gamer Magazine?\n\nWith a reputation for in-depth reviews scored out of 100, a subscription to PC Gamer magazine is the ideal choice if you love straight forward computer gaming.\n\nEach monthly issue is full of exclusive game previews and interviews with designers and developers, as well as news on all your favourite game franchises from MMORPG to FPS.\n\nThis top gaming magazine also covers the wider world of PCs, with features on their development and their environmental effect, plus in depth hardware and software reviews and an ever-growing online community, giving you even more hints and tips.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to PC Gamer magazine features the UK''s best, and best-selling, PC games magazine. Reviews and features-led, it also contains in-depth previews of all the biggest new games, interviews and is packed with world-exclusive news.\n\nPC Gamer magazine is the trusted by both the games-buying public and the industry to deliver the most authoritative, honest, informative and entertaining reviews, PC Gamer is the ultimate buyer’s guide.\n\nPc gamer magazine also has a monthly DVD which offers the capacity to supply all the very biggest and best exclusive playable demos, add-ons, patches, videos and interviews every month.\n\nBecause PC Gamer magazine offers the toughest games reviews in the business, readers know exactly what they''re getting before they buy.\n', '', '', ''),
(756, 1, 'Xbox: The Official Magaziner', 'WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Xbox: The Official Magazine Magazine?\n\nIf only an official view will do, then a subscription to Xbox: The Official Magazine is for you, giving you unrivalled coverage of all the latest news on Microsoft''s market-leading console.\n\nA must-read for dedicated Xbox gamers, this magazine brings you updates on hardware and software changes to the console itself, as well as exclusive scoops from game developers on new features, whether that''s improved multi-player connectivity and gameplay or innovative in-game storytelling and graphic elements.\n\nEach issue also contains readers'' opinions and letters, plus the all-important reviews and previews of new and upcoming releases.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nXbox: The Official Magazine subscription will provide you with all the information you need to experience a multi-channel gaming experience.\n\nThe UK’s biggest games magazine, Xbox: The Official Magazine brings you unbeatable coverage of everything Xbox.\n\nEvery issue offers unrivalled access to the world’s biggest games, including innovative feature coverage and expert reviews from our stable of award-winning writers. Find out more on oxm.co.uk, and catch the OXM Report every week on Inside Xbox on Xbox Live in the UK.\n\nIt comes with the hottest news from the world of Xbox. Like other game magazines this one also has independent and impartial reviews and previews which are hugely reliable as they are written by the guru’s of gaming.\n', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `oc_product_description` (`product_id`, `language_id`, `name`, `description`, `meta_description`, `meta_keyword`, `tag`) VALUES
(757, 1, 'Computer Music', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Computer Music Magazine?\n\nMost of the songs in the charts today have been helped along at some point by a computer, so if you''re interested in music production, this is absolutely the magazine for you. With your subscription to Computer Music, you can learn all the tricks of the trade to turn you from novice to professional in no time at all. You will be guided along the way with simple tutorials covering a wide range of software for both PC and Mac users, teaching you about everything from standard tuning edits to experimental compositions. You will also get reviews on new products and DVDs with samples, demos and plug-ins, all included in every issue.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA Computer Music magazine subscription is the complete guide to making music with a computer. Computer Music is the world’s best-selling magazine dedicated solely to making music with your Mac or PC.\n\nEach month find easy-to-follow tutorials for all sorts of music software, unbiased reviews of the latest products, answers to technical questions. There are millions of potential musicians out there and this magazine will help them get the right software and hardware and show them how to use it. CM brings you the best in tutorials, reviews, news and features, and no matter whether you’re a complete newcomer to computer-based music production or a seasoned pro, there’s plenty for you in every issue.\n', '', '', ''),
(758, 1, 'Pc Format', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to PC Format magazine, the UK''s oldest and best known PC entertainment magazine. A subscription to PC Format magazine brings you the leading independent editorial voice on all matters relating to home computing, designed to inform and enthuse its readers with passion for the PC. As the PC becomes ever more central to the home entertainment experience, a subscription to PC Format magazine is there to provide commentary and advice on new technologies, trends and games. Every month, a subscription to PC Format magazine delivers straight to your door the latest news, most relevant features and up to date reviews of games and PC technology, as well as a DVD packed with software toolkits, applications, games demos and movie footage. PC Format Magazine comes with informative and accurate previews of latest games and other products to be launched in the computing world. There are wide varieties of features in PC Format Magazine. It carries a number of feature stories that are well written and informative. Each issue in a subscription to PC Format magazine covers a particular area of computing or any latest issues in the world of computing. This magazine is a single comprehensive guide for all levels of PC Users from beginners to experts.\n', '', '', ''),
(759, 1, 'Jazzwise', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nJazzwise, the UK''s biggest-selling jazz monthly and the leading English language jazz magazine in Europe, has changed the way jazz magazines look and think with a stunning editorial and design package that reaches out to both the new jazz audience and established fans – qualities that have led to it winning Best Jazz Media 2013 at the Jazz FM Awards, and Jazz Publication of the Year at both the prestigious Parliamentary Jazz Awards and the Ronnie Scott’s Jazz Awards.\n\nEvery month Jazzwise''s acclaimed team of writers takes you on the journey of your life: from the cutting edge of contemporary jazz, mainstream, fusion and free-jazz to jazz electronica and world music with hot news, gossip, a nationwide gig guide, major features and the UK''s most authoritative reviews section. From the outer edges to the inner circles Jazzwise is committed to discovering new talent as well as extensive coverage of today’s scene and expansive retrospectives of jazz’s vibrant past. You simply can’t afford to be without it.\n\nTHIS SUBSCRIPTION OPTION IS FOR THE PAPER MAGAZINE ONLY\n', '', '', ''),
(760, 1, 'Logic Problems', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLogic Problems is the premier magazine for the very best in classic logic puzzles. The collection of puzzles is designed to challenge and develop your powers of logical thinking in a fascinating and entertaining way, with regular characters and story settings. Inter-related clues allow you to put two and two together and deduce who’s who, what’s what, where, why, when and how! Published monthly, each 68-page issue also includes a step-by-step guide to each solution. Logic Problems is the perfect choice for everyone who enjoys logic puzzles.\n', '', '', ''),
(761, 1, 'Miniature Wargames', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMiniature Wargames is Britain’s oldest and best-selling independent wargames magazine and has showcased the hobby at its grassroots for over 25 years.Each issue features articles by expert wargamers on how to improve your performance on the tabletop battlefield across the full range of popular periods as well as a dedicated section on sci-fi and fantasy wargaming and regular features on painting and modelling plus reviews of the latest rules, figures, books and products for wargamers.\n', '', '', ''),
(762, 1, 'Sight And Sound', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Sight and Sound Magazine?\n\nIf you''re looking for a film magazine that covers everything from major releases to low-budget independent productions, then Sight and Sound is just what you need.\n\nYou will love the informative features covering every aspect of cinematography, keeping you in the know about all the creative geniuses behind the scenes. Their polls of critics'' Top Ten Greatest Films of All Time have run every ten years since 1952, giving you the definitive expert opinion on which films are the enduring classics all cinema lovers should see.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Sight and Sound magazine subscription is essential for anyone serious about film. Published by the British Film Institute since 1932, Sight &amp; Sound is the magazine that offers a unique insight into the very best of film culture. Sight &amp; Sound brings cinema history to life with extensive coverage of cinema past, present and future, from all corners of the globe. Each issue provides detailed reviews of all films released theatrically in the UK, exclusive news and interviews with the biggest directors, in-depth features, festival news, the latest DVD releases and comprehensive film reviews. Sight and Sound magazine casts off the gossip and hype of the many film magazines in the market with writing from Mark Kermode, Kim Newman and Tony Rayns among a host of film experts.\n', '', '', ''),
(763, 1, 'Mixmag', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMIXMAG is the worlds biggest dance music and clubbing magazine. Each month you''ll find the planet''s most exciting dance acts and DJ''s, reviews of the hottest tracks and albums (from techno to dubstep) news and views from international club culture and features on the worlds best festivals and parties.\n\nPlus, each issue comes with an exclusive mix from the world''s best DJ''s.\n', '', '', ''),
(764, 1, 'Q', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Q Magazine?\n\nWith a subscription to Q you can guarantee you’ll never be out of the loop when it comes to the very best rock and pop around. Q regularly photographs and interviews all the greatest groups and musicians, from Paul McCartney and U2 to Kasabian and Muse.\n\nRegular features include Rewind, a look back at Q''s archives, The Q50 essential tracks of the month, as well as frequent CD giveaways and lists of the ''100 Greatest...'' The extensive reviews section lets you hear about all the biggest new albums, reissues and concert DVDs, and even gives you expert opinions on upcoming films, books and gadgets.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Subscription to Q magazine provides an essential music guide with exclusive interviews from the biggest names in music. Q magazine is inventive, insightful and irreverent, it is the UK’s biggest selling music magazine and the world’s best music guide. Q magazine gets the interviews and exclusives that no other magazine can. Couple this with the famous Q magazine Review section and new Entertainment section, featuring everything you need to know about films, DVDs, radio, books, games and gadgets, and you’ve got what amounts to the most essential music/entertainment guide there is. If you’re looking for a different take on music, subscribe to Q magazine today!\n', '', '', ''),
(765, 1, 'Empire', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Empire Magazine?\n\nWhy should you buy a subscription?\n\nThis film magazine has loads of news, reviews and interviews from the world of movie-making to keep you informed on all the gossip every month. In every issue of Empire magazine you''ll find great features like ''Classic Screen'' transcripts of memorable movie dialogue and ''Pint of Milk'', where celebrities are quizzed on unusual topics to reveal how far their feet are from the ground. The ''At Home'' section guides you through all the best DVD and Blu-ray releases, so whether you''re looking for a horror or a comedy, you''ll find plenty of recommendations from expert critics to help you plan your movie night wisely.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Empire magazine is perfect for all those movie buffs who want the latest on production news and reviews on new releases!\n\nCounting celebrity fans like Steven Spielberg, George Lucas and Quentin Tarantino, EMPIRE is currently the biggest selling, most respected film magazine on the planet.\n\nEmpire magazine covers everything you want to know about films from the biggest blockbusters, to the coolest indies, to the most revered arthouse flicks.\n\nIt brings you the best in cinema and DVD every month, razzing your retinas with stunning photo shoots and exclusive pictures, bringing its readers interviews with the biggest star names from the hottest locations and helping them plan their viewings with the most comprehensive reviews section around, all with a unique, informed irreverent sense of humour.\n\nSubscribe to Empire and have the latest industry news delivered to your door each month!\n', '', '', ''),
(766, 1, 'Uncut', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Uncut Magazine?\n\n\n\nIf you’re obsessive about rock from every era, Uncut is the ideal music magazine for you, offering a passionate take on everything from the Beatles and the Stones to the latest upcoming acts. As well as classic rock coverage, there''s plenty of column inches devoted to Americana and alternative country, with dedicated sections for these genres in every issue. You''ll find critical opinions on all the latest albums, as well as a cinema section with reviews of films and music DVDs. With your subscription to Uncut you''ll even get a free fifteen-track CD* with every issue, keeping you up to date with the month''s musical highlights. *Included with UK delivery only.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nUncut is the home of great, timeless rock music, from Bob Dylan to Arcade Fire. It aspires to be the monthly magazine of choice for discerning, knowledgeable music fans that typically grew up with the classic rock of the sixties and seventies who continue to be excited by new music that connects them to the records they have always loved. Uncut has a specific emphasis on delivering the most comprehensive and definitive reviews section in the monthly music sector. A subscription to UNCUT magazine brings you the UK''s most authoritative music and film magazine, straight to your door. Every month of the subscription celebrates the great legends, icons and maverick talents of rock and movies in one brilliant package that embraces both old and new, cult and classic. UNCUT magazine is essential reading for anyone with a passion for music and film - and every issue in a subscription comes with a free CD*. *Included with UK delivery only. Launched in 1997, UNCUT magazine focuses on music and movies and is aimed at men aged 25 to 45 years. Contents include features about old albums, interviews with movie directors, reviews of all major new album launches, film and DVD releases as well as all the latest music and film news. With every issue of a subscription bringing you such a wide variety of features, reviews and articles, UNCUT magazine is the perfect companion for anyone with a passion for music and films.\n', '', '', ''),
(767, 1, 'Clash', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Clash Magazine?\n\nThis is the music magazine for people who are passionate about a wide range of artists, with no authentic genre off-limits.\n\nYou''ll get in-depth listings of ''Ones to Watch'' as well as regular interviews with the biggest names in music, from Red Hot Chili Peppers to Jay-Z.\n\nIf you''re into fashion, the magazine publishes two special fashion issues every year alongside regular creative photoshoots with bands.\n\nYou''ll also find a six-page cinema section each month and an annual Film Issue, which goes beyond Hollywood to bring you the best releases worldwide.\n\nThis is a great monthly read for dedicated music fans who want to stay on top of every aspect of today''s pop culture.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nAny music buff would love a magazine subscription to Clash magazine.Clash is an award-winning (Magazine of the Year – PPA 2008) monthly music magazine bringing originality and independent opinion in a truly unique style.While music continues to diversify and evolve, Clash endeavours to represent the crossover appeal of all genres of music for the more discerning fan. Every month Clash features the best new emerging bands alongside established acts and legends of the industry.Clash magazine a strong design focus as well as industry related articles - Clash is dedicated to Music and Fashion, which makes it is a monthly favourite among artists and labels. Subscribe now to explore the best gigs, festivals, news, reviews and features every month.Regular Features within the Magazine include:• Clash Essential 15 – Find out what''s been tickling the eardrums of the Clash Staff in the office every month....• Bowman''s Blog – A month in the life of DJ &amp; TV Presenter Edith Bowman.• Spotlight Album – Every Issue we take a moment to celebrate legends within the industry. Each month Clash revisits a Classic Album that will always have a place in our hearts......• Royal Academy Reviews – Each month, our resident boffin from London''s Royal Academy of Music is given five indelibly-linked tunes and unaware of the song''s authors, he blindly merits the compositional qualities, judging the best of the bunch.\n', '', '', ''),
(768, 1, 'Vanity Fair', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Vanity Fair Magazine?\n\nThis celebrity and gossip magazine is your monthly guide to the most talked about news and pop culture developments, whilst also bringing you fashion tips and style guides from leading journalists. Each issue includes striking and occasionally controversial photography from the likes of Mario Testino and Annie Leibovitz, which sits alongside features on some of the most influential famous faces. With a subscription to Vanity Fair magazine, you''ll also get gorgeous style inspiration and coverage of some of the most important international events. Striking a great balance between the popular and the serious, the intelligent and the beautiful, this is a sought-after read for the thinking woman with a soft spot for celebrities.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVanity Fair is unique. No other magazine combines the grit of serious newspaper with the glamour of a glossy in quite the same way. A subscription to Vanity Fair brings you the magazine that is home to a matchless stable of award-winning writers and photographers, many of them household names. These are men and women who break and make the news. In terms of access and depth – the extraordinary lengths our contributors go to get under the skin of a story, to investigate the big issues thoroughly and intelligently – Vanity Fair is in a league of its own. Simply put, readers who care about what is going on in the world care what is in Vanity Fair, and a subscription to this magazine is a must-have. The magazine reaches opinion-formers all over the world, who value its breadth and seriousness as well as its wit, its style and its sense of humour. First published in 1991 by Condé Nast Publicatioins, Vanity Fair magazine is no stranger to controversy. Not afraid to push the boundaries and go the extra distance to expose the truth or cover the sensitive subject, Vanity Fair magazine is renowned world wide for its groundbreaking content.\n', '', '', ''),
(769, 1, 'Puzzler', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe UK''s first ever puzzle magazine, Puzzler is now forty years old and is renowned for excellence. There is a variety of straightforward and more complex puzzles making it suitable for all. Easier puzzles include Wordsearch, Straight Crossword, Number Jig, Arroword, Dot-to-Dot and Spot the Difference. More challenging puzzles include Cryptic Crossword, Alphabetical Jigsaw, Numerical Crossword, Logic Problem, Sudoku and Kakuro. There is also a £6000 cash competition in every issue.\n\nDon’t delay, subscribe today!\n', '', '', ''),
(770, 1, 'Lucky Seven Crossword Collection', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nLucky Seven Crossword Collection is Britain’s best-selling giant crosswords magazine – and no wonder. Its 132 pages are packed with mega crosswords featuring straightforward clues and a smattering of general knowledge ones and anagrams. For easy-to-read giant crosswords and a £1,500 cash competition, you can’t do better than Lucky Seven Crossword Collection.\n', '', '', ''),
(771, 1, 'Popular Wordsearch', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nYou’ll find dozens of easy-to-solve wordsearches large and small in Popular Wordsearch – not forgetting a cash competition in every issue which could make you a winner. What’s more, there’s a unique start biography puzzle to tie in with our celebrity-themed cover.\n', '', '', ''),
(772, 1, 'Select Codewords', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nIf code-cracking is your thing, look no further than Select Codewords. It’s packed with 101 puzzles – regular codewords as well as a number of brain-teasing variations and some unique ‘minicodes’ too. The cash competition has prizes totalling £1,500, so get code-breaking today.\n', '', '', ''),
(773, 1, 'Puzzler Collection', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPuzzler Collection is the UK’s best-selling puzzle magazine with a stimulating selection of over 120 puzzles in each 100-page issue, plus there is £2,025 in cash prizes to be won! The wide range of quality puzzles makes it suitable for all, with favourites such as crosswords, arrowords, codewords, piecewords and fitwords. And for those that enjoy more of a challenge there are cryptics, two-timers, and logic puzzles. There are still many exceptional puzzles that first made an appearance in Puzzler Collection and the search for originality continues. This is the magazine that continues to inspire generations of puzzlers.\n', '', '', ''),
(774, 1, 'Home Cinema Choice', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Home Cinema Choice Magazine?\n\nThe world of home cinema is continuing to find its way into more and more households across the UK, but deciding on what to invest in can be difficult. If you''re overwhelmed by the options, then a Home Cinema Choice magazine subscription will help you to identify the right products for your home. This technology magazine is full of reviews, features and news written by experts, giving you an insightful look into the home cinema industry. There''s also hundreds of handy buying guides in each issue, as well as in-depth software guides and an exclusive online environment for subscribers.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Home Cinema Choice will bring you the UK''s best-selling home cinema enthusiasts magazine.Every issue of Home Cinema Choice magazine features news and reviews of the latest home cinema equipment, from amplifiers, receivers, processors and power amps, to DVD recorders, speakers, projectors and flat panel TVs. A subscription to Home Cinema Choice magazine also offers advice on setting up this hardware alongside features focussing on drop dead gorgeous home cinema installations, and reviews of the latest DVD releases.In every issue you will read about product launches, new technology as it emerges. Read about the on-going war between LCD and plasma technologies, the settled war between HD DVD and Blu-ray, growing trends of downloadable content. Home Cinema Choice magazine has it all.\n', '', '', ''),
(775, 1, 'Terrorizer', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nIf you love Heavy Metal and Extreme Music then a Terrorizer magazine subscription is for you.\n\nTerrorizer magazine prides itself on its reputation across the globe as the world’s authority on all forms of Heavy Metal and Extreme Music: Terrorizer magazine has pioneered forms of music and covered artists that no-one else would touch, if you name it, Terrorizer was there first.\n\nEach issue of Terrorizer magazine comes with our Fear Candy cover-mount CD giving you the sickest sounds to listen to while you enjoy reading about your favorite music, you will be able toread ground-breaking features, our definitive album and live reviews and be informed by our regular Scene Reports and Specials.\n\nWith a subscription to Terrorizer magazine you will be able to revisit Classic Albums, and read today’s artists rant in the Bar-Barian Wrath and Hard of Hearing sections, and enjoy throughout the year 13 Fear Candy CDs covering the best of the music that you like, and our Fear Candy Unsigned discs, which bring you the newest, most depraved sounds from around the world''s up and coming metal artists.\n', '', '', ''),
(776, 1, 'Classic Rock', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Classic Rock Magazine?\n\nThis dedicated rock magazine brings you exclusive content from some of the world''s biggest rock legends, with interviews and retrospective features in every issue. Re-live the glory years of the ''60s, ''70s and ''80s, before delving into reviews of the best up and coming rock talents from around the globe. This music magazine brings you the true stories behind legendary bands including Pink Floyd, Led Zeppelin and The Who, as well as stunning photography, extensive interviews and exclusive tour coverage bringing you closer to the acts you love. A Classic Rock magazine subscription also comes complete with free CD''s and downloadable tracks, plus access to an exciting mobile app.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nClassic Rock, the voice of Rock journalism, goes behind the scenes to bring the real stories behind rock legends from Led Zeppelin to Metallica, to Marilyn Manson and beyond. You''ll find interviews, news, tour dates, retrospective articles and a hefty reviews section in every issue. If you’re a serious rock fan, take out a subscription to the world’s only high-voltage rock’n’roll magazine!\n', '', '', ''),
(777, 1, 'Bbc Music', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to BBC Music magazine is a must-have for anyone with a passion for classical music. BBC Music is the world''s best-selling classical music magazine covering the latest news, reviews and the most thought provoking features. BBC Music’s links with BBC Radio 3''s Composer of the Week and Building a Library offer you the best new thinking and CD buying advice. Classical music experts and new enthusiasts will enjoy the fascinating articles and recordings featured each month. Plus receive our own unique cover CD, free with every issue, presenting you with a superb quality recording of complete works performed by internationally renowned musicians.- No other classical music magazine offers you so much every month. A subscription to BBC Music Magazine is your essential guide to the world of classical music.\n', '', '', ''),
(778, 1, 'Scifinow', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to SciFiNow magazine is perfect for the fan of science fiction, horror films, cult TV and fantasy. The first choice for dedicated followers of sci-fi, cult TV and horror, SciFiNow magazine is the most dynamic, sophisticated genre magazine around.\n\nDelivering the best reviews, the most in-depth features, unprecedented industry insight, episode guides, memorabilia, convention news, and access to the stars. SciFiNow magazine is the ultimate sci-fi magazine. Written by fans for fans SciFiNow magazine is the first new science fiction, horror, cult TV and fantasy magazine in the last 12 years – a high quality title that celebrates the explosion of new scifi TV shows, films and culture, past present and future. From Doctor Who to Buck Rogers. Star Wars to Heroes, Buffy to Battlestar Galactica. SciFi Now loves them all, and there’s no better magazine if you want in-depth interviews, lavish features, trustworthy reviews and detailed scifi TV listings. Great reasons to subscribe to SciFiNow magazine: •Never miss an issue\n•Free delivery to your door every month\n•Fantastic savings off the cover price\n\nJoin the future; buy a SciFiNow magazine subscription for you or a friend today and save up 30%. .\n', '', '', ''),
(779, 1, 'Sfx', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO SFX Magazine?\n\nIf you''ve got your television set to record every single episode of any sc-fi and fantasy programme showing, you''ll definitely love SFX magazine.\n\nWith a subscription to this magazine you can get regular updates from the sets of all your favourite shows as well as upcoming big-budget movie releases.\n\nYou''ll get to read interviews with actors, directors and writers and see behind-the-scenes shots from incredible filming locations. All the newest releases on the big and small screens are reviewed by serious sci-fi and fantasy fans, as well as the latest books, video games, cartoons and graphic novels, making sure you hear about great stories told in any format.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGet a subscription to SFX magazine, the Earth''s greatest sci-fi and fantasy magazine. We cover all areas of sci-fi and fantasy across TV, movies, books, games, collectables and comics. A subscription to SFX magazine brings you news, features, exclusive interviews, behind-the-scenes stories, star profiles and TV episode guides with every issue. All this stuff makes us the market-leading genre magazine. SFX Magazine is one of the best selling science fiction and fantasy magazines. Published by Future Publishing, every issue of this monthly magazine subscription provides the reader with essential and informative news on topics related to sci-fi and fantasy. It covers all areas of sci-fi and fantasy from TV, movies, books, collectables, games and comics. You can find all the latest news, up to date information, in depth and extensive features, exclusive and inspiring interviews, authoritative and independent reviews, TV episode guides, exciting competitions and lots more. The entire team working behind the success of SFX magazine has specialist knowledge and keen interest in sci-fi and fantasy. With all these ingredients SFX magazine has become one of the most popular and well-recognized titles of its kind in Britain.\n', '', '', ''),
(780, 1, 'Gramophone', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Gramophone Magazine?\n\nA subscription to Gramophone magazine is ideal for anyone interested in Classical music. Gramophone magazine is packed with features from globally acclaimed writers covering all classical music genres, informing and entertaining you with independent and intelligent editorial and over 160 reviews in every issue. Gramophone magazine reputation is founded on acclaimed critical analyses of the latest CD releases, in-depth features and interviews with classical stars, and our comprehensive coverage of live, recorded and broadcast music.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Gramophone magazine is ideal for any interested in Classical music. Gramophone magazine is hugely packed with features across all classical music genres, globally acclaimed writers will inform and entertain you with independent and intelligent editorial and over 160 reviews in every issue. Gramophone magazine reputation is founded on acclaimed critical analyses of the latest CD releases, in-depth features and interviews with classical stars, and our comprehensive coverage of live, recorded and broadcast music. PLUS every issue comes with our collectable Editor''s Choice CD with excerpts from James Inverne''s pick of this month''s recordings.\n', '', '', ''),
(781, 1, 'Total Film', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Total Film Magazine?\n\nThis magazine lets you know about everything going on the movie business today, with reviews of all the latest releases both on disc and in theatres.\n\nEvery issue of Total Film magazine features an in-depth chat with an actor or director including an overview of their career, spanning six whole pages to really give you an insight into your screen heroes'' lives.\n\nIn the magazine''s regular ''Dialogue'' section you can read fans'' letters, emails and feedback, in ''Buzz'' you''ll see exclusive photos and on-set previews, and with ''Agenda'' you''ll hear all about film releases outside the Hollywood bubble, keeping you up to date with the best independent, foreign language and underground cinema.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Total Film magazine subscription provides it’s readers with definitive movie info they need to guide them through the latest theatrical and DVD releases and is perfect for anyone who has a passion for the movies. Total Film is the UK''s sharpest, funniest and most informative movie magazine.\n\nCovering everything from Hollywood blockbusters to independent, homegrown and world cinema, Total Film boasts trustworthy reviews, revealing features, exclusive photos and previews and unrivalled access to the hottest stars and filmmakers in the industry. Lounge, Total Film''s massive new home entertainment section, offers a comprehensive guide to current DVD releases and re-issues, as well as exclusive competitions and the latest movie-related books, CDs, games and hardware.Every issue of aTotal Film Magazine subscription includes snippets on all latest news and up to date information from the world of films. It helps the readers to follow what’s happening in the world of cinema. The magazine comes with latest film news and latest films. It brings the blockbuster reports. This magazine is a valuable resource for all people who have passion for films.Like other film magazines Total Film Magazine carries independent and authorative reviews. The reviews are and help to know more about the latest releases. You will find larger reviews for successful films and shorter reviews for less success films.To know everything about the world of films, place a magazine subscription today to Total Film.\n', '', '', ''),
(782, 1, 'Harper''S Bazaar', 'Harper’s Bazaar is an American fashion magazine, first published in 1867, considers itself to be the style resource for “women who are the first to buy the best, from casual to couture.”Aimed at members of the upper-middle and upper classes, Bazaar assembles photographers, artists, designers and writers to deliver a “sophisticated” perspective into the world of fashion, beauty and popular culture on a monthly basis.', '', '', ''),
(783, 1, 'L’Officiel', 'Launched in April 2002, L’Officiel India is the Indian version of leading French fashion bible, L''Officiel is an unparalleled leader in luxury lifestyle, fashion and beauty. A visual treat, L''Officiel has always featured the best in Luxury Lifestyle catering to the niche market that has been entirely neglected by a plethora of lifestyle magazines. With 10 issues produced annually (along with supplements), each issue of L''Officiel is exceptional enough to be a collectors item. It is the country''s premier fashion and luxury magazine, having won several awards for timely and perceptive coverage of local and international fashion trends.', '', '', ''),
(784, 1, 'Images Business Of Fashion', 'Focuses primarily on the design, manufacturing, merchandising, branding, marketing &amp; retailing across all aspects of the business of fashion. BOF plays a directional and supporting role in the evolution of branded fashion in India. Besides chronicling the activities of the country''s largest branded fashion companies, its rich researched content also brings to the forefront regional and single store retailers from diverse markets, marketing and retail of branded fashion in India, effectively linking retailers and fashion brands across the country', '', '', ''),
(785, 1, 'Images Retail - English', 'Launched in 2003, IMAGES Retail took on the task of analysing the emerging industry of organized retail, at a time when industry itself had little data to work on.Since then, the magazine has grown in tandem with the business of retail in India, and its broad-based research now covers the gamut of Indian and international movements in technology, logistics, formats, store design, retail real estate , franchising and human resource, besides reporting on significant directions within India''s sunrise industry', '', '', ''),
(786, 1, 'Femina - Tamil', 'After becoming the life and lifestyle guide for the modern Indian woman, in both English and Hindi, Femina launched its Tamil edition in April. The Tamil reader’s lifestyle has evolved over the years and so have her tastes. All the content of Femina Tamil has been written with this in mind. It is designed to keep the readers in step with the times, and with all that interests her – fashion, trends, celebrity gossip, beauty tips, relationships and intimacy. The magazine offers the best of both worlds – rich, robust and relevant content put together with stylish, elegant and contemporary production values that Femina is known for.', '', '', ''),
(787, 1, 'Grazia', 'Grazia stays tuned into women''s tastes, season after season. The Grazia credo is that fashion should be uncomplicated and fun. From catwalk fantasy to high-street steals, from budget-busting bags to the shoe to have, Grazia is ahead of the pack in delivering fashion''s best, loveliest and most wanted. Featured trends are made easily accessible with tips on where to buy and how to wear. Grazia doesn''t dictate. Instead, it demystifies style.\n\nPrice includes posting &amp; handling charges of Rs. 120 per publisher policy', '', '', ''),
(788, 1, 'Vogue India', 'Everything you need to know about fashion, trends, beauty, people and lifestyle, Vogue India is your ultimate style guide. In these pages you’ll find the hottest, newest and latest from the world of fashion and beyond, both in India and from across the world, making it the must-have accessory for the modern, fashionable Indian woman. Vogue India is India''s best women''s fashion magazine offering access to the latest fashion news, trends, accessories, celebrity photos, beauty tips.Vogue’s wide-reaching influence stems from various sources, including the persona and achievements of its most famous editor, its various charitable and community projects, its ability to reflect political discourse through fashion and editorial articles, and its move to emerging economies.', '', '', ''),
(789, 1, 'Shoes And Accessories', 'Images Shoes &amp; Accessories magazine aims to play an important role in shaping this dynamic market through its in-depth trend forecasting, news, reportage, research, industry thoughts and be an indispensable publication on the evolving footwear and accessory industry.As a market authority for finding your way around the Footwear &amp; Accessory Market of India, Images S &amp; A aims at shaping the design, manufacturing, marketing &amp; retailing areas of this growing market. For designers and manufacturers, the publication will continuously present new concepts, designs, materials and innovation for constant betterment.For the brands, retailers and marketing experts of this industry, Images S &amp; A will update these key professionals on business information, consumer behaviour, market studies, industry reports, trade events that ultimately helps create a better retailing environment at large.For the fashion conscious consumers, the publication aims to provide information on trends and trend-setting products covering all categories in shoes, bags and fashion accessories including leather products, costume jewellery and other add-ons.', '', '', ''),
(790, 1, 'Cosmopolitan', 'New ideas to stimulate your senses, tips and tricks to keep you ahead in the style sweepstakes, what''s hot, what''s not, cues to make relationships and careers bloom... No wonder, Cosmo is the soul-mate of choice for hip and happening women across India and the world. And now you have the chance to get the Fun, Fearless Female magazine, delivered at your doorstep, month after month at a special price!', '', '', ''),
(791, 1, 'Estetica', 'Estetica India is the 25th International edition of Estetica worldwide network. It’s the undisputed worldwide leader in hair fashion publications, targeting the hair and beauty industries, stylists, salons and anyone passionate about hair fashion. The magazine gives its readers an insight in the world of creative hairstyling at its best. Hear the industry leaders talk about the what’s making news – only in Estetica. Admire the world of interiors and design of leading salons from around the globe and be on the beam about major international business events of the hair and beauty industry.', '', '', ''),
(792, 1, 'Elle', 'Elle is a leading fashion and beauty magazine, covering the latest style trends and lifestyle for women. .', '', '', ''),
(793, 1, 'Apparel', 'Apparel magazine is widely distributed in India and abroad amongst manufactures, exporters, importers, retailers, fabric and accessory suppliers, government agencies, machinery manufactures, trade fair organisers, fashion institutes and all those connected with the garment industry.\n\nReaders from the Fashion industry value global inputs which are mainly on contemporary issues on fashion manufacturing and design trends.\n\nLet ''Apparel'' magazine be your most trusted source of information.', '', '', ''),
(794, 1, 'Hair', 'HAIR is your complete guide to great hair and beauty. Get your monthly dose of the hottest trends, latest products, inspiring styles, expert advice, tips and more. UK''s biggest-selling hair magazine is published in India by Spenta Multimedia under an exclusive licensing arrangement with IPC Media, UK. HAIR in India is the only specialist magazine on hair and beauty ', '', '', ''),
(795, 1, 'Verve', 'Ever since it was launched in 1995, Verve, India premier women’s trend-setting international magazine, published and edited by Anuradha Mahindra, has changed with the times – defined and moved with the trends, styles and fashion. Featuring the best talent, the lifestyle and leisure monthly presents achievers from every spectrum of society – from fashion, business and style to Bollywood, books and travel. Editorially stimulating and visually exciting, Verve has over the years pioneered a revolution in the depiction of contemporary Indian fashion, through stylised shoots that are international in approach and individual in execution. Its covers, like its inside pages, are a talking point for quality and aesthetics remain its cornerstones. It is and continues to be an icon of fashion, style and lifestyle!', '', '', ''),
(796, 1, 'More', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLifestyle magazine for the 40+ woman in the stride of her life. Fashion, beauty, health and fitnesss issues as well as real life features and lifestyle ideas\n', '', '', ''),
(797, 1, 'Port Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRead by key decision-makers in the industry. Port Strategy is renowned for excellence and informed opinion within the commercial ports sector. With unique best-practice articles, case studies, and industry led views and features, Port Strategy provides an exceptional reference point for the operation and profitability of international ports and terminals.\n\nPort Strategy''s coverage of port development and investment from both the developed and emerging world offers readers unrivalled coverage of the international marine ports industry - something no port executive should be without.\n', '', '', ''),
(798, 1, 'Hatalk E-Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nHATalk is a downloadable e-magazine written for everyone who loves to wear and make hats. Every month HATalk showcases the work of milliners from around the world and publishes helpful hints, tip and step-by-step instructions for projects to try at home. So whether you are an experienced hat maker or someone who loves to create and craft, HATalk e-magazine is the choice for you. Subscribe now and get over 85 back issues of HATalk to download whenever you like!\n', '', '', ''),
(799, 1, 'Prima', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Prima Magazine?\n\nWhy should you buy a subscription?\n\nSubscribe to Prima magazine for a monthly dose of creative inspiration, with loads of ideas on how to improve and simplify your daily routine. This mag is full of expert advice on a whole range of topics, with features on everything from the latest diets to great new hobbies.\n\nYou''ll find dozens of easy to follow recipes and stylish interior and garden tips to help you make the most of your time at home, as well as money-saving hints and buying guides in every issue. There''s also regular free gifts and exciting competitions to keep you entertained, and a fun real-life stories section dealing with the issues that matter to you.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Prima magazine subscription provides real-life guidance, inspiration &amp; ideas to simplify the lives of modern women today. A subscription to Prima magazine offers a little something for all women - advice on how to look and feel your best, time and money-saving solutions, quick and easy food recipes, beautiful homes and gardens, and above all, everything you need to get the most out of life. Prima caters for every stage of life - using reader experiences and real-life stories, as well as expert advice from those in the know. The magazine covers a broad range of subjects in a warm, helpful and fun way. Prima magazine is a trusted source for consumer information, with professional advice on health and wellbeing, best buys, your family, career and much, much more. Prima understands their readers'' busy schedule and aims to be the antidote to your everyday stresses. With a Prima magazine subscription almost anything is possible - beauty is attainable, fashion is wearable and cookery is easy but the best part about Prima is that everything is affordable. Subscribe to Prima today and treat yourself to a great read every month!\n', '', '', ''),
(800, 1, 'Esquire', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Esquire Magazine?\n\nWith a history dating back to the 1930''s, this men''s magazine has established itself as the top authority on the latest in design, fashion, business and technology. An Esquire magazine subscription will keep you informed about the latest trends from around the world, with features and reviews of the hottest new restaurants and travel destinations, as well as interviews with the most stylish celebrities. In addition to receiving a wealth of informative and intelligent articles, you''ll also get a free membership to the Esquire Premium Club, giving you exclusive access to reader events, competitions and discounts in the form of a handy quarterly newsletter.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nAn Esquire Magazine subscription is perfect for the modern man. Esquire magazine is a sharper read for men – for the very best celebrity features and interviews, fashion, sport, thought-provoking writing and top quality photography in a stylish accessible package. An Esquire Magazine subscription features articles on luxe design and culture, food, business and technology, style, music and books. Esquire Magazine brings you the hottest and most stylish celebrities, great tips on fashion, the latest trends and hot spots, travel advice and current affairs. As a subscriber you also get free membership to the Esquire Premium Club where you’ll receive a quarterly newsletter packed full of reader events, competitions and discounts. An Esquire magazine subscription is essential for men who mean business!\n', '', '', ''),
(801, 1, 'Jewellery Focus', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Jewellery Focus magazine brings you a publication dedicated to all retailers in the jewellery trade as well as gift shops and department stores. Every month a subscription to Jewellery Focus magazine informs retailers throughout the UK of the latest trends and developments in the jewellery industry. Every issue in a subscription to Jewellery Focus magazine contains the latest news on the market, new products and features and practical advice on subjects ranging from store design to sales training. Jewellery Focus magazine is an exclusive and leading title which covers various aspects of jewellery trade. Published once in a month, the magazine reaches your doormat tightly packed with essential news and information regarding the trade. A subscription to Jewellery Focus magazine is considered as best selling jewelry trade publication in UK and all retailers in the trade, as well as gift shops and department stores, find a subscription to this magazine a must-have.\n', '', '', ''),
(802, 1, 'Hair', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHAIR magazine, the magazine for women who love their hair.Every issue has 130 pages packed with ideas, tips and factual information for keeping you and your mane looking and feeling fantastic.Reader makeovers, catwalk trends, hair how-to features and hair products on trial.A HAIR magazine subscription brings you the latest looks and how to achieve them.\n', '', '', ''),
(803, 1, 'Make &amp; Sell Jewellery', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nStart designing your own jewellery with a subscription to Make &amp; Sell Jewellery magazine. Get original catwalk style with the UK''s most exciting jewellery making magazine, Make &amp; Sell Jewellery. Make &amp; Sell Jewellery magazine is packed each month with on-trend projects influenced by the latest fashions and high street looks. Each monthly issue of Make &amp; Sell Jewellery magazine features beautiful photography, essential shopping guides and projects from the best contemporary designers- it’s a must-have magazine whatever your skill level or area of interest. If you love to create your own accessories and stand out from the crowd, a subscription to Make &amp; Sell Jewellery magazine is for you!\n', '', '', ''),
(804, 1, 'Glamour', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Glamour Magazine?\n\nWhy should you buy a subscription?\n\nThis women’s lifestyle magazine is a great resource for all things fashion.\n\nEvery issue includes photo shoots that show you how to create stylish everyday outfits inspired by the latest catwalk trends, plus a number of top style tips specific to the season.\n\nYou''ll read about all your favourite fashion-forward celebs in exclusive interviews every month, and you''ll find thought-provoking articles on the issues that matter to you, from the pay gap between men and women to relationship concerns.\n\nAdd health, food and travel into the mix, and a subscription to Glamour magazine will provide you with a monthly handbag essential, in a practical, portable size.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA Glamour magazine subscription is the perfect fit for both your life and your handbag! Plus your subscription also includes a FREE Digital Edition. Your Glamour magazine subscription features all the hottest celebrities, the best fashion and beauty, gripping real-life stories and in-depth features.With entertainment, health, fitness, travel and more, a Glamour magazine subscription is an ideal gift or a luxurious (yet affordable) treat for you! Glamour magazine, which was founded in 1939 in the USA before being launched in the UK in 2000, is one of the best-selling fashion magazines for women. Within the pioneering ‘handbag size’ format of Glamour magazine’s pages you will find the best of celebrity style tips, advice and fashion guidance. Other topics featured in the magazine include health, romance and relationships, as well as horoscopes. Glamour magazine also conducts regular polls and contests for the reader to get involved in. As well as producing 12 issues of the magazine each year, every June Glamour organize and host the “Glamour Woman of the Year Awards”. These annual awards recognize influential women in the public eye. Previous winners of this prestigious award include Cheryl Cole and Kylie Minogue.\n', '', '', ''),
(805, 1, 'Diva', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSubscribe to DIVA and receive free delivery, exclusive subscriber only covers and discreet packaging!\n\nThe edgy, sophisticated lesbian and bisexual lifestyle magazine\n\nFirst published in March 1994, DIVA has been delivering informative, innovative and inspiring news, views and interviews to lesbians everywhere, ever since! Providing the essential monthly guide to lesbian and bisexual life, the DIVA team are dedicated to creating an ever-evolving magazine to be proud of.\n', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `oc_product_description` (`product_id`, `language_id`, `name`, `description`, `meta_description`, `meta_keyword`, `tag`) VALUES
(806, 1, 'Red', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Red Magazine?\n\nWhy should you buy a subscription?\n\nBecome a Club Red member for free and receive great offers handpicked for Red subscribers each month.\n\nFilled with fashion, beauty and travel, this is the ideal magazine for busy thirty-somethings who like to add a touch of glamour to their lives.\n\nEvery glossy issue of this women''s magazine is packed with fashion features focusing on women of all shapes and sizes, as well as coverage of the latest looks in hair and beauty, giving you stylish ways of adapting catwalk trends to suit you.\n\nRed makes a particularly great read for lovers of fashion, but it also has interesting sections on current affairs and gender equality, as well as travel and food, covering a broad range of lifestyle interests.\n\nWith a subscription to Red magazine, you can read about exotic holiday hotspots, discover newly published authors and upcoming musicians, and spice up your cooking with simple but tasty recipes.\n\nPlease note, in order to offer this saving for subscribers, the free gifts included on retail copies will not be included in your subscriber copies.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Red magazine brings you this best selling magazine featuring gorgeous fashion that you can actually wear, expert health &amp; beauty advice, inspirational &amp; entertaining ideas and intelligent writing on the issues that really matter to our readers. Get a subscription to Red magazine for a gorgeous, luxurious and, above all, relevant read for today''s thirty-something women, who spend their days living real lives in fabulous shoes! Red magazine offers an unrivalled quality of photography and journalism, in a sun-drenched, glossy package that mirrors their readers'' passion about style in all areas of their lives. Red magazine''s unique formula of stunning fashion and beauty, practical lifestyle pages and features make an emotional connection with their readers.\n', '', '', ''),
(807, 1, 'Hairdresser''S Journal International', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Hairdressers Journal International is essential for any serious hairdressing professional.\nHairdressers Journal International was first published over 120 years ago and is packed full of important information and bold colorful images, it really is the monthly read you can''t afford to miss.\nContents include the latest techniques and styling, trends, fashions and product news as well as profiles on the top stylists. There is also an extensive section covering career prospects and training as well as a monthly business section with advice and information.\nThe Hairdressers Journal International team also organizes the British Hairdressing Awards and supports Salon International exhibition which covers every aspect of the business and attracts tens of thousands of visitors each year.\nSubscribe now to have the latest hairdressing industry news, trends and essential salon business information delivered straight to your door each month.\n', '', '', ''),
(808, 1, 'Tatler', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Tatler Magazine?\n\nIf you want witty editorials and high fashion photography along with all the latest news from the British elite, Tatler is the magazine for you.\n\nAmusing cultural and political articles sit alongside features on the latest designers, and if there''s been a spectacular party anywhere in the country, this fashion magazine is sure to have been there.\n\nTheir famous Little Black Book provides the definitive list of the nation''s most eligible ladies and gentlemen, so whether it''s to check your own rating or pick out your fantasy partner, you''ll love flicking through Tatler''s high society pages every month.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Tatler magazine today! Tatler is proudly Britain''s most sophisticated magazine. A vibrant mix of fashion, beauty and sensational features giving insights into the lives of the world''s leading and most glamorous celebrities, a subscription to Tatler magazine is a must-have. Featuring unrivalled coverage of people, parties, fashion, beauty and the arts, Tatler magazine is modern and witty. Get a subscription to the magazine that catches the eye and sets the agenda for others to follow. Tatler magazine is a monthly glossy publication produced by Condé Nast Publications and focuses on the glamorous lives and lifestyles of the elite upper classes. Tatler magazine as we know it today is the latest incarnation, of which there have been several, of the original literary and society journal founded by Richard Steele back in 1709. The idea behind Steele’s original Tatler magazine was to create a publication in which to publish the news and gossip heard in London coffeehouses, hence the name Tatler magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(809, 1, 'Vogue', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Vogue Magazine?\n\nWhy should you buy a subscription?\n\nA Vogue magazine subscription is every season’s must-have accessory. It’s the ultimate fashion bible and that''s exactly why it is adored by fashion-lovers all over the world.\n\nEach issue of the magazine to bring you a lowdown of each season’s trends, the latest looks straight from the catwalk, coverage of all the biggest shows and interviews with your favourite designers and some of the most stylish celebrities.\n\nOf course, there are also the infamous deliciously sumptuous photo shoots for you to feast your eyes on, featuring renowned models and celebrated fashion photographers.\n\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGET A SUBSCRIPTION TO BRITAIN’S No1 FASHION MAGAZINE, VOGUE. VOGUE sets trends. A VOGUE magazine subscription is the perfect point of reference for the fashion industry, it is filled with insightful interviews with leading designers, runway reviews, practical style tips and must-have buys. VOGUE magazine''s fashion teams travel the world to captivate, inspire and enchant you with the latest international collections. Using famed photographers and beautiful supermodels, VOGUE magazine’s photo shoots are world-renowned. VOGUE magazine also acts as a launch pad for new faces and young designers ensuring it is always the first word in fashion. Given VOGUE’s iconic status, it is able to attract the most talented and gifted actresses, musicians, designers, as well as high-profile figures, to its pages. No other magazine combines beauty, style, glamour, design and contemporary culture in such an inspiring mix. The British edition of VOGUE magazine was launched in 1916 and was the first ever overseas edition of an existing fashion magazine. British VOGUE is the most profitable magazine in the UK industry and is the second most profitable incarnation of VOGUE behind the US edition.\n', '', '', ''),
(810, 1, 'Gq', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO GQ Magazine?\n\nWhy buy a subscription to GQ?\n\nThis leading magazine is regularly voted as the best men''s magazine in the UK, and a subscription to GQ will provide you with a monthly guide to the most exciting topics and trends from around the globe.\n\nThere are regular interviews with the most authoritative figures from the world of business, together with updates on the most sought after up-and-coming designers. You''ll stay up to date with the latest fashion trends, and get a sophisticated insight into everything from current affairs to politics, the latest movies to top consumer gadgets from the people in the know.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA Subscription to GQ provides its readers with the brightest, most authentic and quite simply the best men’s magazine in the world. Whether it’s fashion, sport, health, humour, politics or music you are after, GQ covers it all with intelligence and imagination.\n\nGQ is wittier, more sophisticated and stylish than any other men’s magazine on the market, featuring the most beautiful women in the world, the most authoritative figures and the most stylish men.\n\nWhether it''s getting Dennis Hopper to shoot Quentin Tarantino, interrogating David Miliband on life, love and leadership or asking U2''s Bono for advice on headlines, GQ is your access-all-areas pass to corridors of power in Hollywood, Westminster and more.\n\nGQ is the ultimate monthly men’s lifestyle guide and is well ahead of the game when it comes fashion trends and grooming. While most men currently live in an age of casual jeans and t-shirts, GQ definitely proves that there is still room for elegance.\n\nA subscription to GQ is a must-have for anyone who considers themselves a proper gentleman!\n', '', '', ''),
(811, 1, 'Irish Tatler', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIreland''s Original style bible since 1890, Irish Tatler prides itself on it''s regular mix of fashion and beauty, a glimpse at all things gorgeous and new in Pandora''s Box, regular columns on food, drink, interiors, books and travel. Irish Tatler definitely has something for everyone.\n', '', '', ''),
(812, 1, 'Shout', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Shout magazine subscription is perfect for the young teenager who wants to keep up to date with all the latest gossip, fashion and beauty trends. A Shout magazine subscription features the award winning teenage monthly magazine that is aimed at girls aged 11-14 who need to know everything! If they want the latest celebrity news, hottest fashion buys and beauty products, real-life stories, hilarious cringes and problem pages, Shout has it all! Shout magazine is also packed with pop music, celebrities, flowcharts and make-up! Plus it also has unmissable true stories, life and health advice from the experts and embarrassing moments by Shout readers! Shout is also the only magazine, which offers a completely confidential and individual reply from its agony aunt. There’s even a brilliant free gift with every issue If it’s in her life- it’s in Shout!\n', '', '', ''),
(813, 1, 'Manohar Kahaniyan', 'The Crime Hindi Monthly Magazine- The magazine is comprehensive and complete in coverage, full of thrill and suspense, ranging from international and national crimes, social problems, true murder stories and general stories for entertainment. Written by masters of crime,the stories reveal true facts, conspiracies and evil designs behind heinous crimes like murder, rape, abduction etc.', '', '', ''),
(814, 1, 'Satyakatha', 'It was launched in 1972. It comes in a digest size; Satyakatha is about crime, love and courage, based in true stories.', '', '', ''),
(815, 1, 'Bio Spectrum', 'India''s Leading Biotech magazine..it researches the growth of the domain and shares the emerging possibilities for commercial and research sectors alike. Committed to the cause of biotechnology, professionals will find the magazine informative and useful in the current context as well.', '', '', ''),
(816, 1, 'Geospatial World', 'Geospatial World monthly magazine (formerly known as GIS Development magazine) addresses current and relevant issues of the Global Geospatial domain. Each edition of the magazine brings for the latest news and happenings from the various part of the world, presents viewpoints of the experts, through interview and perspective articles, assimilate case studies and reviews on the recent and upcoming technologies, products and also advocate on various policy issues. Considered by the experts’ as one of the best publications in its field, the magazine enjoys a circulation of 16,000 copies to over 140 countries across the globe. The special focus of the magazine is in South Asia, Asia Pacific, Middle East, South America and African countries.The readership of Geospatial World magazine comprises of a complete cross section of the community. It is widely read by geographers, surveyors and cartographers, academician, researchers and students and also by engineers, managers and developers.', '', '', ''),
(817, 1, 'Popular Science India', 'Popular Science Magazine is licensed from Bonnier Corporation, Popular Science is a leading source of Science and Technology news all over the world since its inception way back in 1872 in the U.S.A. The currently largest selling magazine has just been launched in India with partly customized content for India specific tastes.Popular Science India covers the latest innovations and discoveries across fields and also carries the latest news on gadgets and technology in Indian context.', '', '', ''),
(818, 1, 'Medal News', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAre you a medal collector? Are you interested in Military History? If so, then a subscription to Medal News magazine is for you. MEDAL NEWS magazine is the world''s only independent magazine devoted to battles, medals and military history. Every issue of Medal News magazine is packed with informative articles, the latest news and sale room reports, medal finder service and much more. Subscribers to Medal News magazine also benefit from a free Digital version of the magazine with direct links to advertisers''s websites and free classified advertising. Our world-renowned Medal Tracker service is also available free to subscribers. Medal News magazine is packed with the latest industry and historic news, comment, auction reports and fascinating articles.\n', '', '', ''),
(819, 1, 'Reform', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nReform is a fresh and challenging monthly magazine exploring theology, ethics, personal spirituality and Christian perspectives on social and current affairs.\n\nThe magazine is for thinking people who enjoy reading about Christian ideas from a range of viewpoints. It features writing from journalists, academics, politicians, campaigners, scientists and religious leaders.\n\nAs well as high-profile interviews, in-depth features and book, music and film reviews, Reform carries letters and a regular light-hearted column.\n\nThe magazine is published by the United Reformed Church but has readers from all Christian denominations, as well as readers from other faiths and from no faith tradition.\n', '', '', ''),
(820, 1, 'Literary Review', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Literary Review Magazine?\n\nThose who love to keep up to date with the latest book reviews, but baulk at wordy criticism and academic jargon are bound to enjoy a subscription to Literary Review magazine. Originally set up by renowned journo and editor Auberon Waugh, this books and literature magazine is lively and to the point, attracting top authors and award-winning journalists as its regular columnists. With passionate and no-nonsense reviews from highly respected literary voices on the newest biography, history, fiction and non-fiction available, this is the ideal subscription for the serious reader.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLiterary Review was founded in Edinburgh in 1979 by Dr Anne Smith, head of the English Department at Edinburgh University. She created a lively, intelligent literary magazine for people who love reading, but hate academic and intellectual jargon.\nFrom the start, Literary Review plugged in to the best and most exciting current writing. The reviewers are usually authors themselves, not just critics. In the 1980s, the new owner, Naim Attallah, secured award-winning journalist Auberon Waugh as editor. For fourteen years Auberon Waugh led the magazine and gave it the high profile it has today. Nancy Sladek, who has been at Literary Review for ten years, is the current Editor. The magazine is recognised as being intelligent, informative, and witty. It attracts the best writers in the country, many of them experts in their fields. &quot;This magazine is flush with tight smart writing.&quot; Washington Post &quot;Literary Review is extremely informative, well-written and altogether enjoyable. It is my favourite monthly magazine.&quot; Muriel Spark “In Literary Review you find something that has almost vanished from the book pages: its contributors are actually interested in Literature.&quot; Martin Amis &quot;I’m always impressed at how successful Literary Review is at recruiting top writers and then getting them to write their best.&quot; John Sutherland &quot;The best books in history and politics reviewed by people whose independence of mind one respects.&quot; Michael Burleigh\n', '', '', ''),
(821, 1, 'Saga Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nLife begins at 50... or so your Saga magazine subscription would have you believe! Reaching that milestone doesn''t mean that you stop wanting to reading great quality magazines, if anything you want them to get better. A subscription to Saga magazine is perfect for people aged over 50 as it knows you''re reaching a different stage in your life and gives readers expert advice and guidance on managing their money and making the most out of their pension, offers suggestions on insurance of all kinds as well as featuring celebrity interviews, juicy literary extracts, fascinating analysis on the way we live our lives and useful articles on health, travel, gardening, money, technology and just about everything else you want to know. Saga magazine is now the UK''s bestselling subscriber magazine, holding a unique position in providing high quality journalism, success stories by recently retired entrepreneurs, social issues and general interest topics, business and financial news and information from the healthcare sector. Saga magazine also offers subscribers fantastic discounts on holidays, cinema tickets, books and more money-saving deals. So, subscribe today and ensure you benefit from all that Saga magazine has to offer!\n', '', '', ''),
(822, 1, 'Berkshire Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEvery month Berkshire Life is packed with features about this picturesque part of England - from characters and personalities to heritage and traditions. We turn the focus on our towns and villages, and give comprehensive guides to enjoying life in Berkshire - including what''s on, restaurant reviews and topical features on major events. There are also pages of the best property, fashions and the interior design of some of the area''s most interesting home\n', '', '', ''),
(823, 1, 'Buckinghamshire Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBuckinghamshire Life is the county magazine offering hundreds of pages of articles and superb photography every month. Everyone who loves Buckinghamshire will find something to interest them on a whole host of local subjects, with features on the finest property, antiques, history and heritage, countryside and wildlife, town and village features, country shows, regattas, sports and leisure, interiors, fashion and motoring. Buckinghamshire gardens and gardening are beautifully featured in each issue. Buckinghamshire Life is published 12 times a year.\n', '', '', ''),
(824, 1, 'Cornwall Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCornwall Life is THE county magazine, offering page after page of compelling features and superb photography every month from our talented and popular writing team. Each issue features the ‘must see’ events, the people, the places and the properties which you cannot miss for a true celebration of this wonderful county. We also feature the latest in gardening tips, a peek inside very special homes, the latest arts exhibition news and all you need to know about the fabulous food and drink on offer in our county. Our experts also guide you through the latest entertainment choices in our what’s on news.\n', '', '', ''),
(825, 1, 'Hampshire Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHampshire Life is your one-stop guide to this beautiful county encompassing food and drink venues, local events and brilliant ideas for days out with the family. Whether you want to learn more about our stunning towns and villages or are simply looking to spend an hour or so with the county’s celebrities, Hampshire Life is the perfect publication to keep you entertained all month.\n', '', '', ''),
(826, 1, 'Derbyshire Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDerbyshire Life is the magazine that puts the gloss on life in Derbyshire. Every month it''s packed with features about this picturesque part of England - from characters and personalities to heritage and traditions. We turn the focus on the towns, and give comprehensive guides to enjoying life in Derbyshire - including what''s on, restaurant reviews and topical features on major events\n', '', '', ''),
(827, 1, 'Somerset Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSomerset Life is the magazine that puts the gloss on life in Somerset. Every month it''s packed with features about this picturesque part of England - from characters and personalities to heritage and traditions.\n\nWe turn the focus on our towns and villages, and give comprehensive guides to enjoying life in Somerset - including what''s on, restaurant reviews and topical features on major events. Somerset Life is published 12 times a year.\n', '', '', ''),
(828, 1, 'Cumbria', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Cumbria magazine, covers the most scenic area in Britain. Each issue of a subscription to Cumbria magazine includes a mixture of stunning photos and informative articles about Cumbrias people, the landscape, where to go and what to do. Every installment of your subscription contains regular walking route guides and will reveal some of the Lake District''s hidden gems. For over 50 years Cumbria magazine has been bringing a breath of the fells and valleys to enthusiasts all over the world. Each month Cumbria magazine introduces its readers to the characters who shape this beautiful corner of England. Every issue in a subscription boasts a combination of photography, articles and information about the traditions that give the Lake District its unique flavour.\n', '', '', ''),
(829, 1, 'Dalesman', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDalesman magazine is the perfect subscription for those who have a passion for Yorkshire and the beautiful Yorkshire Dales.The Dalesman is Yorkshire’s best selling magazine. Each issue of a subscription is packed with fascinating and thought provoking stories about the people and the places which make Yorkshire such a special place to live or visit.Dalesman magazine is a monthly celebration of Yorkshire and all that it has to offer its visitors. With stunning photography, you will also find out what is going on in terms of events, festivals, fates, places to walk and local business information.There is a very good reason why Yorkshire and specifically the Yorkshire Dales are visited by millions of people annually as there are activities in abundance and natural beauty to be experienced by all who can appreciate it.Place a subscription to the Dalesman today and be guaranteed to hear about everything which this beautiful county has to offer.Get inside the ‘real’ Yorkshire with the county’s best selling magazine. Each issue contains fascinating and thought-provoking stories about the people and the places that make Yorkshire so special.NO-RISK GUARANTEE - Should you wish to cancel the subscription you will receive a refund for the cost of all un-mailed issues (UK readers only)\n', '', '', ''),
(830, 1, 'France Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO France Magazine Magazine?\n\nEvery edition of this monthly mag will help you to discover something new about this amazing country, from the best places to visit for the wine harvest to booking your trip in time for a local festival.A France Magazine subscription is full of ideas to inspire your next holiday to the continent, whilst also helping you to find different language courses and unique cultural highlights.This specialist travel magazine isn''t just for planning a holiday, though; it also gives you plenty of info on the best French food and wine, important historical sights and cultural highlights, helping you to make the most of your next trip.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to France magazine brings you the very best of France - from the spectacular scenery to the vibrant cities and charming villages. The food and wine section of each issue in a subscription acts as the complete guide for French foodies and, together with its features about culture, history, language and people, a subscription to France magazine truly is the next best thing to being there. France magazine introduces to you the different language courses conducted by recognized institutes. Every issue in a subscription to France magazine also gives you an introduction to enjoying French music and better appreciating French language and developing vocabulary. A subscription to France Magazine is the best investment for travel planners looking to visit this country. Whether you are planning a short break or a long stay in this country, this magazine has the essential guidance and suggestions to make your stay comfortable and enjoyable. Get the suggestions for hotels and holidays, information about French tourism events, not-to-be-missed points of interest and much, much more.\n', '', '', ''),
(831, 1, 'Scottish Memories', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDiscover the real history of Scotland and enjoy all the evocative historic stories from the last century with a subscription to Scottish Memories magazine.\n\nScottish Memories is a monthly magazine packed full of fascinating, exciting stories covering what the Scots got up to at home and abroad from prehistory up to the end of last century.\n\nEvery subject under the sun is covered in the magazine, including warfare, sports, the arts, the supernatural world, crime, humour, religion, inventions, exploration and all in a lively entertaining style from a team of top writers, as well as personal, nostalgic features.\n\nScottish Memories magazine is packed with photographs, both from the archives and timeless, sweeping, panoramic views.\n\nEach issue of Scottish Memories magazine features an in-depth travel guide to a beautiful location in Scotland, detailing things to do, places to stay, and how to get the best out of a visit to the area.\n\nWith a Scottish Memories magazine subscription you’ll never miss an issue and you’ll also get the magazine delivered free to your door each month before it hits the shops. Plus the magazine features regular competitions and prizes to be won.\n\nBuy a subscription today to Scottish Memories magazine for you or a friend.\n', '', '', ''),
(832, 1, 'Sunday Times Travel Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Sunday Times Travel Magazine Magazine?\n\nWhy buy a subscription to Sunday Times Travel magazine?\n\nThe Sunday Times is renowned for its top quality writers, and this companion publication brings the same high-quality journalism to the world of travel every month.\n\nSubscribe to the Sunday Times Travel magazine for ideas and recommendations on where to spend your next holiday, with reviews of everything from &quot;staycations&quot; to long-haul destinations and exotic adventures.\n\nBeautiful photography will give you a flavour of some of the best destinations in the world, whilst regular tips from well-travelled journalists will help you to research travel plans and find the best holiday deals.\n\nYou''ll also find a range of in-depth guides, making it easy to make an informed decision about your next holiday.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Sunday Times Travel Magazine subscription brings you the best writers, the best photography and the best, practical, in-depth travel information every month!The Sunday Times Travel is the perfect magazine if you are looking for inspiration for your next trip, or you just enjoy reading about exciting destinations – there is something for everyone! Here are just a few of our popular, regular features: Total Guides: Who needs a guidebook? Our in-depth 25-page guides to classic destinations uncover the real country. Six of the Best: The world’s best hotels with Sea Views. Smart Traveller: Top tips for the savvy traveller: how to take perfect holiday photos, when to complain, and how to save money on last-minute flights. Classic and Contemporary City Breaks: No not just the same old places. Get the lowdown on the real city – the best bars, hotels and restaurants plus the smart way to see the sights. A Sunday Times Travel Magazine subscription is filled with both inspirational and practical travel advice and holiday solutions, covering everything from active city breaks to barefoot beach luxury. The Sunday Times Travel magazine brings you all the best holiday information for you every month, every season. Be informed. Be inspired. Be there, with a subscription to The Sunday Times Travel magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(833, 1, 'The Scots Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The Scots Magazine Magazine?\n\nThis popular magazine has the impressive distinction of being the oldest in the world still being published today.\n\nFounded in 1739, The Scots Magazine has been there to discuss important Scottish events from the Battle of Culloden to the two World Wars, and is still going strong today with features covering all the significant developments in our country''s modern life.\n\nYou''ll read interviews with leading musicians, actors, chefs and artists, and enjoy stunning photography of Scotland''s beautiful landscapes and wildlife in every issue. In-depth articles explore everything about our national history, culture and psychology, in a compact high-definition format that''s easy to carry around wherever you go.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Scots Magazine is the perfect magazine for you if you enjoy reading about current and relevant Scottish-themed articles. Believed to be the oldest magazine still in publication, it was first published on 9th February 1739, as a 48-page pamphlet, priced sixpence monthly. It was edited and printed in Edinburgh. In the present day, through use of powerful and evoking photography, relevant and thought provoking features, the magazine will keep engrossed within Scotland’s heritage. The Scots Magazine is proud that whist embracing the new, it stays true to its values as the world’s most widely-read Scottish interest publication. A Scots Magazine subscription is your invitation to get involved and become part of the most widely-read Scottish interest magazine. Each issue embodies Scotland''s heritage, its history, its people and its past. Plus enjoy fascinating insights into Scotland''s events and activities; all complimented by stunning photography. Never miss an issue again...order your Scots Magazine subscription now!\n', '', '', ''),
(834, 1, 'Britain At War', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Britain At War Magazine?\n\nBritain At War is the UK’s best-selling military history title, and one of the nation''s most respected history magazines. Each issue is over 100 pages long and contains all the latest news on historic military discoveries, as well as detailed personal accounts of military engagements ranging from the Great War to the Falklands conflict. You''ll get a visual perspective with incredible photography from regular features such as the ‘Camera at War’ section, and read monthly stories of real life war heroes. A Britain At War magazine subscription also comes complete with dozens of reviews of new book and DVD releases.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nBritain at War is dedicated to exploring every aspect of Britain’s involvement in conflicts from the turn of the 20th century through to modern day. From World War I to the Falklands, World War II to Iraq, readers are able to re-live decisive moments in Britain’s history through fascinating insight combined with rare and previously unseen photography.\n', '', '', ''),
(835, 1, 'Military History Monthly', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Military History Monthly Magazine?\n\nIf you’re looking for a history magazine and have a particular interest in warfare, then a Military History Monthly magazine subscription is for you. This new title focuses on British military history throughout the ages, with expertly written features on everything from the Second World War to the Crusades. You''ll find vivid storytelling and incisive analysis of key military campaigns, with propaganda cast aside to give you the real story. There''s also detailed battle maps to go with descriptions of historic regiments and warriors from around the world, as well as information on the latest museum exhibitions and reviews of new military books.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nMilitary History Monthly is a monthly magazine dedicated to the history of conflict on Land, at Sea and in the Air. Military History Monthly is dedicated to answering the big questions of military history. The aim is not only to bring you action-packed narrative, but to provide all the technical detail, in-depth analysis, and cutting-edge controversy you need to understand not just what happened, but also why. Packed with battlefield maps, eyewitness accounts and book reviews, this is the magazine for everyone who wants to understand war, past and present, in all its dimensions.\n', '', '', ''),
(836, 1, 'The Oldie', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to The Oldie magazine provides an eclectic mix of humour, cartoons, reviews, interviews and eccentricity. The Oldie dares to give readers something different and unpredictable. Each issue brings you great writers such as Mavis Nicholson, Raymond Briggs, Ruth Rendell and Tom Stuttaford. As well as these and other equally famous and talented guest writers, there are contributions from people of whom you will not have heard. It is this unsolicited material that makes it unique. The Oldie magazine was founded in 1992 by Richard Ingrams, who for 23 years was the editor of Private Eye. The Oldie recognises that what readers want more than anything else is good writing and amusing articles on a wide variety of topics. The Oldie magazine is for any independent-minded reader. The Independent Newspaper recently described The Oldie as ''the most original magazine in the country...their eclectic embrace of human variety is a monthly rebuke to the formulaic, celebrity-led concept of features in our newspapers and magazines’, the novelist PD James has said ''an indispensible antidote to the triviality of the 21st-century'' and as stated by Terry Wogan ''age only matters if you are a cheese.'' Please note that The Oldie is published 13 times a year meaning a 12 issue subscription runs for 48 weeks. Treat yourself and subscribe today! A subscription to The Oldie magazine also makes a great gift for that someone special on any occasion!\n', '', '', ''),
(837, 1, 'Scottish Field', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Scottish Field Magazine?\n\nIf you want lifestyle news and features that are specifically designed for residents of bonny Scotland, you need a subscription to Scottish Field magazine. Inside each edition you’ll find profiles of gorgeous properties across the country and stunning landscaped gardens, all beautifully captured through spectacular photography. You can find out about hidden gem locations for holiday destinations around the country, and discover the history of Scotland’s oldest stately homes and castles. Regular updates on sports, travel, music, food and drink are also included, along with insightful profiles of some of the greatest Scots of the past and present.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSubscribe to Scottish Field magazine and receive Scotland’s best-selling quality lifestyle magazine.Each month we feature property, homes and gardens, art and antiques, lifestyles, Scottish food, wildlife, whisky, fashion and fantastic competitions, great for the ex-pat.Scottish Field magazine is published by Oban Times and is delivered every month to subscribers doors, inclusive of postage and packing. Scottish Field magazine celebrates everything Scottish and covers all the topics which make Scotland such a fabulous and unique place to live and visit. With stunning photography and feature articles this is an essential read for anyone who has a passion for Scotland and Scottish life.\n', '', '', ''),
(838, 1, 'Current Archaeology', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Current Archaeology Magazine?\n\nGet to know the history that lies beneath the British soil with this brilliant archaeological history magazine.\n\nYou can virtually visit your favourite sites like Roman Colchester, Sutton Hoo and the Clava Cairns, and hear the latest news and analysis from the likes of Phil Harding.\n\nThis magazine is also great for putting archaeological finds into their historical and anthropological context.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCurrent Archaeology is the top monthly magazine devoted to British archaeology. For 40 years Current Archaeology has been visiting the digs, talking to the excavators and reviewing the literature to keep our readers up-to-date.\n', '', '', ''),
(839, 1, 'Suffolk Norfolk Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Suffolk Norfolk Life magazine is a monthly read packed full of features about everything that makes Suffolk and Norfolk so special. Suffolk Norfolk Life magazine is also East Anglia''s oldest county magazine and has been running for over 20 years. Every issue of Suffolk Norfolk Life magazine is full of tradition, local history, local information, car reviews, great food and drink guides to keep readers updated on all the best places to dine, delicious recipes and book reviews. Suffolk Norfolk Life magazine also features music notes, bygone memories, local and national events, interior design advice to keep you home looking modern and smart and a wide range of regular features you''re sure to find plenty of interesting articles.\n', '', '', ''),
(840, 1, 'Soul &amp; Spirit', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nExplore your mind with a subscription to Soul and Spirit magazine.Want to explore your spirituality? Improve your emotional wellbeing? Hone your intuitive powers? Then Soul &amp; Spirit is the magazine for you. Written by the very best life coaches, psychics, healers and astrologers, each issue includes meditations and mantras, inspiring celebrity interviews, interactive self analysis, book and product reviews and locates the best soul-boosting retreats and holidays in the world.Soul &amp; Spirit guides you every step of the way to help you gain a deeper understanding of yourself, your relationships and your spiritual path in life. Soul &amp; Spirit Magazine comes with fascinatingly inspiring celebrity interviews, where the magazine talks to the celebrities and they share their experiences with readers. Subscribe to Soul and Spirit magazine today and get in touch with your spirituality.\n', '', '', ''),
(841, 1, 'The Railway Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The Railway Magazine Magazine?\n\nSubscribe to The Railway Magazine and you''ll receive the latest news about the UK''s rail industry, along with articles about the history of rail, modern traction, heritage railways and international railway topics.\n\nYou''ll find detailed reports on locomotive and rolling stock movements, as well as features on the most controversial issues facing the industry.\n\nIn addition to plenty of fascinating articles, you''ll also see stunning photography to help you relive the glory years of British rail, plus an interesting look at the future of the industry.\n\nWith innovative features and respected news coverage, a subscription to The Railway Magazine is a must for any fan of rail.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Railway Magazine is Britain’s best-selling rail title. Published continuously since 1897, it prides itself on its incisive news content and its unique blend of award-winning photos, in-depth features, interviews and exclusives. Drawing on a team of expert correspondents and extensive archives, The Railway Magazine offers wide-ranging and innovative coverage of the rail industry, encompassing everything from historical engines and nostalgia from the golden age of steam to locomotives, lines and railways around the world as well as contemporary and controversial issues. Unrivalled in scope and authority, it commands the respect of professionals and enthusiasts alike.\n', '', '', ''),
(842, 1, 'Countryside', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Countryside Magazine?\n\nThis nature magazine takes you deep into the British countryside, with fascinating features and interviews with a number of famous faces, plus handy guides on everything from how to take care of your ducks to maintaining listed buildings.\n\nYou''ll also find plenty of essential gardening tips and an interesting look at making local British food, as well as great ideas for your next trip. There are also regular celebrity contributions, with previous guests including the likes of Raymond Blanc and Rosemary Shrager.\n\nA Countryside magazine subscription is the ideal monthly read for any rural dweller, and a great way to experience country life from the city. \nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAre you passionate about the great British Countryside or do you know someone else who is? Indulge that passion with a subscription for membership of NFU Countryside, the organisation that celebrates all that’s great about the British countryside, from farming and great local food, stunning wildlife, places to visit, gardening and getting the most from your horses and dogs. Each month you will receive Countryside magazine and will be able to enjoy many discounts and savings with our affinity partners such as cottages4you, Countrywide stores, Thompson and Morgan, Mountain Warehouse and Rayburn to mention but a few. ABOUT COUNTRYSIDE MEMBERSHIP The award-winning Countryside magazine will be delivered directly to your door each month for a year and is full of practical advice, inspiring features and dazzling competitions. You can access free initial personal legal advice on a wide range of issues and there are free practical Countryside Guides covering subjects relating to life in the countryside. Other member benefits include saving money on rural shows and events, country breaks, plants, gardening equipment, outdoor clothing and building materials. We focus on the issues that matter bringing practical advice and benefits to those who have a passion for rural Britain.\n', '', '', ''),
(843, 1, 'Best Of British', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Best Of British Magazine?\n\nThis magazine is filled with fascinating stories of day to day life in Britain throughout the twentieth century, as well as celebrating the finest parts of our heritage that still survive today.\n\nBest of British looks at everything to do with the tastes and trends of each decade, so you can read all about the fashion, music, transport and food that the country has experienced throughout the ages.\n\nReaders'' letters and photographs play an integral part in every issue, so you can write in with your own memories, or even attend one of the revival events listed each month that take place all around the UK.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPlace a subscription to Best of British magazine and sample the delights of Britain past and present.Best of British is Britain’s leading nostalgia and heritage magazine. In every issue of your subscription you will experience and celebrate all aspects of British life – from the 1930’s through to today. Packed full of golden memories, Best of British delights everyone passionate about Britain past and present. Places, people, pastimes, jobs and events are all remembered from years gone by - alongside the unique and captivating face of modern Britain. Every page of the magazine is a collectors item, with stories to enable you, a revisit history evoke memories for yesteryear. For those people who want to savour the sweet memories of mighty Britain, this magazine is the best choice. Enjoy every issue and contemplate on the facts that gave British its might.Best of British is a monthly celebration of everything British – from the past through to present day. It is packed with nostalgic stories and pictures every month, with many from our own readers. Remembering all our yesterdays – the music, the schooldays, the holidays, the transport and the shops of the Forties, Fifties and Sixties. Readers’ tales guaranteed to stir so many memories – what we wore, where we worked, how we were entertained.Subscribe to Best of British magazine today and enjoy the traditions of Britain that have stood the test of time.\n', '', '', ''),
(844, 1, 'Ibelieve', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\niBelieve is a great new Christian lifestyle magazine for all believers everywhere. We believe faith is too good just for Sundays. Faith is a seven-day event – and our aim is to capture it all in one great new Christian lifestyle magazine. In short, we believe iBelieve is what you believe.\n\nOur three aims are simple. Fun. Family. Faith.\n\niBelieve is unashamedly Christian but never churchy. Like you, we love Sundays. But like you, we also love holidays, work days, birthdays, shopping days and lazing-about-at-home days. We also know there are sad days, lonely days and downright dark days.\n\niBelieve is perfect for people who believe – and for people who want to believe.\n\nThat’s why we’ll report on the stories that separate the spiritual from the secular. It could be the testimony of a Hollywood superstar, a Premiership footballer, or someone who lives on your street. What makes their story stand out from those in other magazines is one name – Jesus. We believe he is present in every day of our lives – seven days a week.\n\nSo we’ll write about the commonplace as much as chapter and verse. We’ll focus on holidays and healing. We’ll feature faith and fashion. We’ll be positive in everything we do and all we write about. Even the difficult issues. Because we know our readers are people who understand that the Bible is for believing, not for bashing.\n\nAbove all, we have created this magazine for the same reason you’ll enjoy reading it. iBelieve.\n', '', '', ''),
(845, 1, 'Cornwall Today', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nCornwall Today is an award winning sophisticated magazine based in the heart of Cornwall that prides itself on its combination of superb photography and inspiring editorial. Cornwall Today is the biggest and best-selling monthly magazine for Cornwall, bringing you fascinating features and stunning photographs covering walks, wildlife, art, food, leisure, wellbeing, homes, gardens and more.\n\nIf you love Cornwall, whether you live there, or enjoy visiting and want to stay in touch with what is happening in the county, then Cornwall Today is your monthly pass to all things Cornish.\n', '', '', ''),
(846, 1, 'Lincolnshire Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Lincolnshire Life magazine is perfect for anyone with a love for this county. Published monthly, Lincolnshire Life the county’s biggest selling magazine and is devoted to the history, culture and contemporary life of Lincolnshire, England. Every month, Lincolnshire Life magazine features fabulous fashion, glorious homes and gardens, inspiration for places to eat out from traditional local restaurants to 5 star hotels, exciting events in your area plus the charming characters, captivating culture and outstanding heritage of Lincolnshire. If you love life in Lincolnshire, you’ll love Lincolnshire Life.\n', '', '', ''),
(847, 1, 'Bbc Sky At Night Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO BBC Sky at Night Magazine Magazine?\n\nWhy should you buy a magazine subscription?\n\nThe TV series has been providing astronomy lovers with an insightful look into space for the last 50 years, and this companion mag is a great way for you to get closer to the action. Each issue includes features from the world''s best astronomers and academic writers, as well as star charts, equipment reviews and easy-to-follow beginners'' guides to catching a peek of what''s out there from your very own telescope. PLUS reviews on the latest books and equipment to help you get the best results on your next stargazing adventure.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\nYour practical guide to astronomy, helping you discover the night skies, understand the universe around us and learn exciting techniques for using your telescope. Whatever your level of knowledge, you’ll find something to enjoy in the night sky. Each issue features columns by renowned experts such as Chris Lintott as well as in-depth cosmological features, practical observing tutorials, comprehensive equipment reviews, astrophotography masterclasses and much, much more. And with easy-to follow star charts and expert advice on how to get the most out of the observing month, Sky at Night Magazine is essential reading for both the novice and experienced astronomer. Inside every issue: -Eye on the Sky: the month in amazing astronomy images including the latest from NASA and Hubble. -Beginners Guide: easy-to-follow, step-by-step walkthrough of a particular topic -Reviews: new telescope, accessories, book and software reviews - Plus much more from the UK’s biggest and best astronomy magazine.\n', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `oc_product_description` (`product_id`, `language_id`, `name`, `description`, `meta_description`, `meta_keyword`, `tag`) VALUES
(848, 1, 'The Field', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The Field Magazine?\n\nWith an impressive publishing track record dating back to 1853, The Field is the ideal magazine for anyone who loves shooting, hunting and fishing. Written by active experts from all three disciplines, a subscription to this magazine lets you read Olympians'' shooting tips as well as advice from professional anglers on how to land sizeable catches every time.\n\nYou''ll hear about the best locations around the country to enjoy your hobbies year round, learn how to train the perfect gun dog, and benefit from reviews of guns made by a huge range of suppliers.\n\nEvery feature is beautifully illustrated with stunning photography, making this magazine a great monthly update on everything from the world of field sports.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Field is the world’s oldest field sports and country magazine. Founded in 1853, it’s for everyone who loves shooting, fishing, gundogs and the best of British rural life. It’s delivered with style, wit and a reckless disregard for modern thinking on claret consumption. If you love everything from gameshooting, flyfishing, hunting, dogs and the land, to the unusual such as salmon-skin bikinis, then a subscription to The Field magazine is just the thing for you. Founded back in 1853 for those who loved shooting, fishing and hunting, the first editor of The Field magazine, Mark Lemon, was a friend of Dickens. The Field magazine was pioneered by sportsman Robert Smith Surtees and was an instant success.\n', '', '', ''),
(849, 1, 'Cheshire Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCheshire Life is a perfect read for those who have both a love of Cheshire and the finer things in life. Packed full of features on the county''s interesting people and places as well as what''s on it really is Cheshire''s essential read. With its famed society pages - we photograph all the county''s finest charity balls and events - Cheshire Life is also about glamour. You''ll find the finest fashions, best places to eat out and much, much more\n', '', '', ''),
(850, 1, 'Lancashire Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIf you love Lancashire you''ll love Lancashire Life.\n\nPacked full of features on the county''s interesting people and places as well as what''s on it really is Lancashire''s essential read.\n\nAnd with its famed society pages - we photograph all the county''s finest charity balls and events - Lancashire Life is also about glamour. You''ll find the finest fashions, best places to eat out and much, much more.\n', '', '', ''),
(851, 1, 'Kent Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nKent Life is the magazine that puts the gloss on life in Kent. Every month it''s packed with features about this picturesque part of England - from characters and personalities to heritage and traditions. We turn the focus on our towns and villages, and give comprehensive guides to enjoying life in Kent - including what''s on, restaurant reviews and topical features on major events.\n', '', '', ''),
(852, 1, 'Stack', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nEvery month Stack sends out a different independent magazine. You never know what you’ll get next, but you do know it will be a beautiful, intelligent magazine you probably wouldn’t otherwise have come across.\n\nThe titles on Stack represent the very best independent publishing, and because we only ever send out the current issue of any magazine you know you’ll be right up to date with the latest from beyond the mainstream. Covering subjects from film and music through to cycling and cooking, every magazine Stack sends out will be different, but they’re all made with passion by people who believe in the power of quality print.\n', '', '', ''),
(853, 1, 'History Revealed', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nHistory Revealed brings the past to life for everyone. It’s an action-packed, image-rich magazine with zero stuffiness. Each issue has a central section that takes a closer look at one of history’s big stories, such as the Wild West or Ancient Rome, telling everything you need to know. We also explore the lives of the truly famous, follow the great adventures of the past, taste the blood and thunder of battles, and look at how closely Hollywood blockbusters have told history. Plus, we answer questions about some of the more surprising and strange aspects of the past.', '', '', ''),
(854, 1, 'Bbc Countryfile', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO BBC Countryfile Magazine?\n\nWhy should you buy a subscription?\n\nIf you''re passionate about getting out and about in the great British countryside, taking care of your garden or cooking and growing authentic produce, then this is the ideal magazine for you. Featuring the best outdoor walks, exceptional photos and all of the latest news and recipes using homegrown food, a Countryfile magazine subscription is a fantastic resource to help you explore rural life from wherever you are in the country. You''ll find in-depth articles from the stars of the show including Julia Bradbury, Matt Baker and John Craven, as well as coverage of the most important issues facing the British countryside.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA Countryfile Magazine subscription is perfect for the country lover! If you love the Great British countryside, you’ll love Countryfile Magazine. Countryfile Magazine is based on the smash hit prime-time BBC show, every issue features stunning photography and celebrates the very best in rural Britain. From awe-inspiring landscapes to secret countryside locations Countryfile Magazine provide you with the ultimate guide to exploring Britain.\n\nDiscover new tastes as we serve up the best in local food and marvel at the wildlife spectaculars you’d never expect to find in the British Isles. Countryfile Magazine also explains the biggest issues rocking the countryside, explaining how they affect us all, whether we live in town or country. N.B. Direct Debit prices are based on receiving 12 issues; non Direct Debit prices are based on receiving 13 issues.\n', '', '', ''),
(855, 1, 'Skin Deep', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\nSkin Deep Tattoo magazine, the UK’s leading Tattoo magazine has been in the newsagents for over eleven years now and has established itself as the UK’s best selling tattoo magazine. Featuring in-depth interviews with readers and tattooists around the globe. Find inspiration for new body art, read reviews through out the show season and discover the colorful world of tattoos.The art of tattoo has become a global phenomenon and Skin Deep magazine brings you all of the latest designs and news from around the tattooing world.A regular feature of Skin Deep magazine are the exclusive and inspirational interviews with people related to the art of tattooing. Skin Deep magazine speaks to the famous as well as new comers to the world of tattooing share their experiences and opinions with its readers.\n', '', '', ''),
(856, 1, 'All About History', '&lt;p&gt;FROM THE PUBLISHER All About History is the new, action-packed history magazine that’s bursting with information on times past. Be inspired by the amazing stories offered by world history, from the complex society of ancient Maya to the dark motivations of the great dictators. Every issue, All About History features a huge range of topics as rich and diverse as history itself and strives to show how events from the past shape the world we live in today. This is a magazine that aims to entertain and enthral readers of all ages while they learn about past events. There’s no stuffy academic essays or squabbling professors, instead it’s bright and engaging with stunning photos, illustrations and infographics that bring the past to life. Written in a style that makes even complex subjects easy-to-understand, All About History is guaranteed to create a desire to discover more. With every issue of All About History comes a wealth of accessible and entertaining information on history from all countries, cultures and eras. With fantastic, world-leading features covering the most amazing real-life events, this magazine will grip anyone who has fallen in love with history through school, film, TV or books.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '', '', ''),
(857, 1, 'Bbc Focus', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO BBC Focus Magazine?\n\nWhat’s in the latest issue of our BBC Focus magazine subscription?\n\nThe Summer 2014 issue of BBC Focus is another great one. The team are on the search for the greatest genius of all time – and there are some pretty great nominations in there, it might be hard for you votes to choose!\n\nAlso in the issue you can discover if there is a cure for headaches, discover how black holes can be consciously created and learn the real science behind those summer blockbuster stunts.\n\nWhy should you buy a subscription?\n\nYou''ll find stunning images, fascinating facts, and articles covering some of the most pressing science and technology issues of our generation with this unique magazine from the BBC. Look out for regular features and interviews with leading brains from the world of science, as well as news updates and engaging discussions that help explain the science behind the world around us. A Focus magazine subscription also comes with The Guide – a collection of reviews on factual books, TV programmes and events, as well as ‘tried and tested’ experiments to help you to test some of the most interesting theories yourself at home.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\nThe science magazine for the inquisitive mind. Every month Focus brings you all that''s new and exciting in science, technology and the natural world.\n\nOur expert team brings you fascinating, authoritative articles, illustrated with stunning images, to explain the science behind the world around you.\n\nWith topics such as the death of the sun, gay genetics, tech fixes for climate change, and future space travel, you just won''t be able to put it down.\n', '', '', ''),
(858, 1, 'Bbc History', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO BBC History Magazine?\n\nWhy should you buy a subscription?\n\nWhether your interest is academic or hobby-based, BBC History magazine makes an informative read for anyone with a passion for the past.\n\nAs well as the latest news on historical discoveries and archaeological finds, there are also features analysing the social habits of the past and how historic events impact on our modern lives, so it''s as much a magazine for those interested in the present as those curious about bygone eras.\n\nWith a BBC History magazine subscription you can expect great writing from the best historians around, such as Lucy Worsley and Chris Bowlby, covering areas as diverse as the Tudor period, ancient Rome and the World Wars.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA BBC History Magazine subscription is essential for anyone with a keen interest in all things historical. Helping bring Britain and the world''s rich past to life, BBC History magazine provides you with accessible and informative features from leading academic historians. BBC History Magazine was established in May 2000 devoted to history enthusiasts of all levels of knowledge and interest. It publishes authoritative history in an accessible and attractive format but readers are provided with much more than that: the contributors are the leading experts in their fields, and so whether the issue is exploring Ancient Egypt, Tudor England or the Second World War, readers are guaranteed the latest, most thought-provoking historical research. BBC History Magazine is first and foremost simply an enjoyable read for anyone who''s interested in the past and each edition seeks to maintain the high journalistic standards traditionally associated with the BBC.\n', '', '', ''),
(859, 1, 'Family Tree', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Family Tree Magazine?\n\nThis magazine has been helping family historians to uncover their past since 1984, giving experts and amateurs a chance to discover more about their heritage and trace their family line. You''ll find informative reviews of the best new genealogy websites and tips on how to search a variety of records, as well as engaging features on wider issues in social history, all brought to you by global experts in the field. There''s also a number of guides to help you jump start the creation of your very own family tree, plus completely free access to thousands of online records.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nFamily Tree February 2015 is on sale now and brimming with ways to help you solve your family history mysteries!\n\nInside this issue... Expert genealogist research tips; How to trace merchant sailors; Scottish wills and testaments; weights and measures; find graves online; death duty records; blogging tips; church registers; WW1 fashion; your stories; &amp; much, much more… Plus, free access to selected records at The Genealogist!\n', '', '', ''),
(860, 1, 'Who Do You Think You Are?', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Who do you think you are? Magazine?\n\n\n\nIf you enjoyed watching a host of celebrities work their way though their own family trees, then this is the history magazine for you.\n\nFollow in the footsteps of John Bishop, Alan Cumming, Annie Lennox and Sarah Jessica Parker, and inspire yourself to uncover your own fascinating genealogy.\n\nSubscribe to Who do you think you are? magazine for expert advice on where to start your search, how to negotiate archives, and how to keep track of your research documents online, as well as unique features giving you an insight into the lives of some of the most interesting people in the country.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTrace your family''s past and discover your roots with Who Do You Think You Are? Magazine. The official companion to the successful BBC TV series, Who Do You Think You Are? Magazine delves in to the celebrities’ pasts, plus features military and social history, telling the stories of ordinary and extraordinary people and how they used to live. Packed with practical advice, from getting started to expert tips, we show you how to get the most out of online resources and build your own family tree.\n', '', '', ''),
(861, 1, 'Fast Car', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Fast Car magazine subscription covers everything you need to know on the modified car market and car culture. Fast Car is officially the best car magazine ever made, and the only one that delivers on its promise of defining today’s car culture. Stuffed with the finest feature cars from the United Kingdom, all the hottest new gear and kit, inspiring guides and even the odd top model for good measure, it’s so jam-packed, you can see it from space. Subscribe to Fast Car magazine today and have all the latest news delivered direct to your door every month.\n', '', '', ''),
(862, 1, 'History Of War', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nHistory of War explores in lavish detail and with evocative imagery the campaigns, characters, weapons and machines of war – not just from the 20th Century, but back through the Napoleonic era to the Middle Ages and beyond. Renowned for its in-depth authoritative approach, expert authors and factual accuracy, the History of War brand provides trusted coverage of conflicts worldwide through its high quality print magazine, digital editions, website and bookazines\n', '', '', ''),
(863, 1, 'Gay Times', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Original Gay Magazine. Subscribe to GT and receive free delivery, exclusive subscriber only covers and discreet packaging! GT (Gay Times) was established in magazine format in 1974 as HIM Magazine and was the UK’s first paid-for monthly magazine aimed at gay men. Team GT have been working hard to bring you the best monthly glossy for the discerning gay man. We''ve chinwagged with divas, drooled over Olympians and rubbed shoulders with some of the biggest names in entertainment. All while simultaneously bringing you top columnists, television, fitness, favourites and fresh talent in music, travel, fashion pointers, community news, geekery, and supplying the hottest hunks to grace your coffee table. We won’t stop trying to better each issue, so we hope you will continue to join us for the ride.\n', '', '', ''),
(864, 1, 'Cotswold Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEvery month Cotswold Life is packed with features about this picturesque part of England - from characters and personalities to heritage and traditions. We turn the focus on our towns and villages, and give comprehensive guides to enjoying life in the Cotswolds - including what''s on, restaurant reviews and topical features on major events. There are also pages of the best property, fashions and the interior design of some of the area''s most interesting homes.\n', '', '', ''),
(865, 1, 'Attitude', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAttitude magazine is the best-selling gay magazine in Britain. Launched in 1994, Attitude magazine is the undisputed heavyweight of gay media. Teaming with style, irreverent wit and exclusive celebrity interviews, Attitude is the essential one stop read for anyone who wants an intelligent gay take on the world – but knows there is life outside of the Ghetto. In addition to celebrity interviews, Attitude magazine also includes serious features on a range of subjects from current and racial affairs and exclusive interviews with influential figures within the gay market. An Attitude magazine subscription contains writing from the most respected gay voices from home and abroad, the coolest, cutting edge style coverage and the biggest blockbusting celebrity exclusives, which leave other magazines – gay or straight – trailing or far behind.\n\nSubscribe to Attitude today and receive each new copy straight to your door every month in discreet packaging.\n', '', '', ''),
(866, 1, 'Sussex Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSussex Life is the magazine for enjoying life in Sussex. If you love the county and want somewhere to go, something to do, or just a good read, then this is the title for you. We have regular food and drink pages, items for your diary, interviews with local characters, articles about our towns and villages and much, much more. Every month there is something different to enjoy, all with a special Sussex flavour. Love Sussex? You’ll love Sussex Life.\n', '', '', ''),
(867, 1, 'Natural Health', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Natural Health Magazine will provide you with a unique guide to complementary therapies for your mind, body and soul.With our panel of experts on-hand to answer your questions on holistic medicine and healthy living. Discover the secrets of looking and feeling fantastic – naturally.Natural Health Magazine is an exclusive magazine for health conscious people. This magazine comes with all the essential information to keep you body and mind healthy for life. Natural health magazine is the one stop shop for all who wants to keep their body and mind healthy. Natural Health magazine includes a healing food section that provides you with recipes of healthy food, a recipe finder and a remedy finder. You will find these useful for all the family.A subscription to Natural Health will provide you with the single most comprehensive guide for health conscious individuals.\n', '', '', ''),
(868, 1, 'Boxing Monthly', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Boxing Monthly is ideal for serious followers of the boxing arena. Boxing can be the most thrilling and demanding of sports and Boxing Monthly magazine gives it to you in full colour, no punches pulled. Regular features include a monthly round-up and reviews of any boxing related DVDs, films or books released that month along with sections dedicated to the domestic scene with reports and previews from the boxing beat in Britain. Boxing Monthly also includes interesting interviews with current and past boxers as well as catching up with retired champions who talk about life after boxing. The magazine was founded in 1989 and is the best British boxing magazine available. Boxing Monthly was the first British boxing magazine to go for the colourful, glossy look and feel of an American boxing magazine. Boxing Monthly magazine is full of blood, guts, intrigue and humour but above all it’s a bloody good read!\n', '', '', ''),
(869, 1, 'What Doctors Don''T Tell You', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\n''What Doctor''s Don''t Tell You'' is a unique health magazine. It provides an easy to understand review of the shortcomings and limitations of conventional medicine and safer alternatives proven to work. It is a must read for anyone interested in medicine and health.\n\nEvery month What Doctors Don''t Tell You reveals the therapies your doctor should be offering you. By researching the very latest discoveries from some of the world''s most prestigious academies, including Oxford, Harvard and Yale, WDDTY brings you the very latest, and proven, therapies that could make all the difference to your condition. Its pages focus on prevention, too. The best diets, exercises and supplements are highlighted every month, making the magazine the complete health package for everyone of all ages.\n', '', '', ''),
(870, 1, 'Women''S Running', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Women''s Running Magazine?\n\nIf you want to improve your running skills, find the perfect pair of trainers or develop your own personalised race plan, this health and fitness magazine is a great place to start. Every issue features helpful nutrition advice, with recipes to speed up recovery or boost energy, and uplifting real-life stories that''ll get you off that sofa and reaching for your trainers. With a subscription to Women''s Running magazine, you''ll get expert fitness tips tailored to specific goals, whether you''re working towards a certain event or simply want to improve stamina, plus reviews of new exercise gear and current running fashion trends.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWomen’s Running magazine is the UK’s first running title just for women. Written by women for women, the magazine caters for both beginners and regular runners who want to lose weight, feel fitter and improve their stamina.\n\nIt features inspirational stories and case studies, motivational tips, nutritional advice and the latest running products and fashions. It also includes regular sections on weight-loss and healthy eating. Women’s Running is published monthly.\n', '', '', ''),
(871, 1, 'Men''S Running', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Men''s Running Magazine?\n\nThis specialist running magazine brings you exceptional articles to help you tackle your next big challenge.\n\nMen''s Running magazine features everything from information on running styles, to motivational training guides to improve your performance. Not only will you love the exercise tips and nutritional advice that will get you running at your best, but you''ll also enjoy reading about tried and tested gadgets that help to enhance your workout and monitor your progress.\n\nA Men''s Running magazine subscription will bring you innovative techniques to help you make the most of your run, with top tips for runners of all levels.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMen''s Running is the UK''s first running magazine just for men. Each issue of Men''s Running magazine features fitness, sports, lifestyle, health, nutrition, plus gear and gadget reviews and jaw-dropping stories that will inspire men to run. Men''s Running magazine offers straightforward advice, inspiration and guidance to all levels of runner, including beginners. Get fit today with a subscription to Men''s Running magazine!\n', '', '', ''),
(872, 1, 'Flex', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Flex Magazine?\n\nIf you''re looking for advice on how to pack on muscle and develop more definition, then this magazine dedicated to bodybuilding is crammed with helpful insider knowledge.\n\nA monthly subscription to Flex magazine will take you behind the scenes at bodybuilding events across the globe, with contest photography and profiles of the competitors, as well as revealing the goals that the world''s champions set themselves and how they achieve them.\n\nThis fitness magazine is loaded with useful information on the best nutritional supplements for muscle growth, and authoritative workout tips covering all parts of the body, helping you to achieve your bodybuilding goals.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to FLEX magazine will provide you with your monthly guide to the world of bodybuilding. FLEX magazine talks to the biggest pros to get the inside scoop to how the best in the world get there and stay there. With a subscription to FLEX you will learn the latest strategies that they will use to further develop their title-winning physiques, and the competitive goals they will apply them to. Each issue brings this state-of-the-art information from the champions to you in order for you to reach your ultimate muscular goals by the fastest route possible. In FLEX magazine, you see no rehashes of old information, no miracle cures, no make-believe theories from armchair experts. You will be hearing directly and accurately from the champions themselves – how they train, what they eat, how they live. The champions talk to FLEX because they trust us to present their expertise faithfully to the bodybuilding community. FLEX is also the only bodybuilding magazine the champions themselves read, because they know that they can learn from their fellow competitors. The champions consider FLEX magazine the bible of hardcore bodybuilding. FLEX is not just another bodybuilding magazine: ''It is the voice of the champions!'' Subscribe to FLEX magazine today and guarantee yourself a direct pipeline to the stars every month.\n', '', '', ''),
(873, 1, 'Muscle &amp; Fitness', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Muscle &amp; Fitness Magazine?\n\nThis health-conscious magazine is full of training techniques and new ideas to help you start pumping iron more effectively. You''ll be inspired to reach and exceed your goals, with some of the world''s leading athletes giving you the inside track into their daily training plans. There''s a number of easy to follow how-to guides in each issue, complete with incredible photography to show you what the end result should look like. With in-depth features from dieticians and industry insiders, a Muscle &amp; Fitness magazine subscription will help you to build muscle, strip fat and hone your body.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Muscle &amp; Fitness magazine brings you the essentials of serious fitness training aiming to help you maximize your potential.With: strength and fitness training for every body type; diet plans and strategies for men and women; expert tips and advice for every fitness level. When the time comes to take training even more seriously Muscle &amp; Fitness will show you how.Muscle and Fitness Magazine comes up with regular features on fitness training. The magazine gives the essentials of serious fitness training. This information is aimed for beginners and expert fitness trainers. It carries articles on strength and fitness for all body types. Muscle and Fitness Magazine includes section on nutrition, which is of paramount importance when bodybuilding. Many people want to have a fitter and stronger body but they are not aware of the type of nutrition they need. The magazine contains all the relevant nutrition knowledge for readers. Along with nutrition topics, the magazine also deals with diet plans. In short, the magazine takes you to the world of bodybuilding within no time.For monthly expert advice on your Body Building regime, place a magazine subscription to Muscle and Fitness. An essential read for any Bodybuilder.\n', '', '', ''),
(874, 1, 'Runner''S World', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Runner''s World Magazine?\n\nEach issue of Runner''s World magazine is packed with helpful tips for runners of all standards, and inspirational content to to help you reach your goals.  Whether you''re training for a charity 5km or attempting to get in shape for your next marathon, you''ll find bespoke training advice from industry professionals, as well as comprehensive buying tips for all of the essential gear. There''s tons of motivational interviews with runners from around the UK, and in-depth guides on how to prevent injuries, enhance your technique and improve your pace. Subscribe to Runner''s Magazine today, and join one of the largest and most established running communities in the UK.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWhether you''re a beginner or an old hand, take out a subscription to Runner’s World magazine and we''ll show you- how to train and race better, how to eat healthier and stay injury-free, and how to choose the best shoes and equipment.. in every issue of your subscription. Runner’s World magazine is the UK’s largest running magazine packed full of articles aimed to give friendly, authoritative ‘how to’ advice and inspiration to all levels of runner. Don’t miss out on this excellent magazine, take out a subscription today.\n', '', '', ''),
(875, 1, 'British Journal Of Community Nursing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nBritish Journal of Community Nursing is the UK’s leading peer-reviewed journal for community nurses, with a unique focus on the district nursing team. It covers all professional issues facing community nurses today and provides essential career development advice.\n\nSubscribe to British Journal of Community Nursing today and benefit from:\n\n•Articles on all aspects of end-of-life and palliative care in the community\n•A focus on the complex needs of frail older people at home\n•Up-to-date information on developments in clinical practice\n•Latest primary care research and guidance on the complex dilemmas\n•Essential information on the issues facing community nurses, together with advice about career development\n\nBritish Journal of Community Nursing ensures that you stay up-to-date with the latest developments in clinical practice, primary care research and policy.\n\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nBritish Journal of Community Nursing is the UK’s leading peer-reviewed journal for community nurses, with a unique focus on the district nursing team. It covers all professional issues facing community nurses today and provides essential career development advice.\n\nSubscribe to British Journal of Community Nursing today and benefit from:\n\n•Articles on all aspects of end-of-life and palliative care in the community\n•A focus on the complex needs of frail older people at home\n•Up-to-date information on developments in clinical practice\n•Latest primary care research and guidance on the complex dilemmas\n•Essential information on the issues facing community nurses, together with advice about career development\n\nBritish Journal of Community Nursing ensures that you stay up-to-date with the latest developments in clinical practice, primary care research and policy.\n', '', '', ''),
(876, 1, 'Running Fitness', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Running Fitness Magazine?\n\nBringing you training exercise tips and reviews of the latest gear on the market for runners, Running Fitness will give you all the information you need to get the most from your running.\n\nYou''ll find out about how to prevent injuries, eat right before and after your runs, and how to keep motivated while you exercise.\n\nWith a subscription to Running Fitness magazine, you''ll be able to read insider profiles of successful athletes from across the country, in addition to recommendations for new clothing and equipment in the ''On Test'' section.\n\nWith regular race diaries in every issue, this fitness magazine is also a great way to keep yourself up-to-date with the competitive running circuit.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Running Fitness magazine is perfect for anyone who''s ever been inspired to lace up their sports shoes and head out for a run. Running Fitness magazine is aimed at anyone from a beginner level through to an experienced athlete. Every month, Running Fitness covers the latest developments, products and essential training tips to help you improve your running performance through an informative mix of articles on topics as varied as, nutrition, injury prevention, gear testing, profiles of runners products and motivation, while providing a comprehensive race diary and events coverage. Running Fitness magazine also has an official website which provides essential news and up to minute information on all aspects of running, allowing readers to have access to everything they need to know 24/7. A subscription to Running Fitness is a must-have for anyone for whom running is part of their life.\n', '', '', ''),
(877, 1, '220 Triathlon', '&lt;p&gt;WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO 220 Triathlon Magazine? A monthly subscription to 220 Triathlon magazine is a great way to keep up-to-date with what''s going on in the world of triathlon. Every issue features reports and photography of the most recent races, as well as previews of upcoming competitions. Whether you''re a novice or a pro triathlete, you''ll love the magazine''s ''Test Centre'', which reviews the latest triathlon equipment, like bikes and tri-suits, and you''ll find expert answers to common fitness questions in the ''Tri Clinic''. You can also read professional coaching advice relevant to all parts of the race to help improve your times, while features on top triathletes will show you how the world''s best train. FROM THE PUBLISHER 220 Triathlon Magazine Subscription.220 Triathlon brings together all the finest elements of the world''s fastest-growing sport in a visually stunning and practical format. In-depth gear tests, world-class coaching advice, evocative race reports - just three reasons why multi-sporters have gravitated to 220 Triathlon for the last 20 years.&lt;/p&gt;\n', '', '', ''),
(878, 1, 'Triathlon Plus', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Triathlon Plus subscription is essential magazine for all triathletes. It is the magazine for people who love the energy and excitement of a multi-disciplinary sport. Whatever level you’re at, Triathlon Plus will help you reach your goals by bringing you in-depth training advice from the world’s leading athletes, unrivalled kit coverage and inspirational imagery that reflects the true spirit of the sport.Triathlon Plus brings you all the latest information regarding, the shoes, the bikes and tips and suggestions to improve your stamina for the big race.An expert panel of athletes give you suggestions for exercise and training schedules. A subscription to Triathlon Plus will provide you with the monthly motivation you need to train harder making you a bigger, better and stronger athlete. The training for this multi-disciplined sport is of paramount importance. With Triathlon Plus you will know that the training tips you receive are given by the best of the best.\n', '', '', ''),
(879, 1, 'Outdoor Fitness', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nWelcome to Outdoor Fitness, Britain''s only magazine dedicated to helping you get fit and train for amazing challenges and events, all in the great outdoors. Each issue is packed with expert advice on how to get in shape and stay fit, alongside inspirational adventures. So whether you want to run a first 10K or take on a desert marathon, try a triathlon or ride 100 miles, climb a Munro or row the Atlantic, we''ll be with you every step and pedal stroke of the way.\n\nOur philosophy? &quot;Life shouldn''t be a journey to the grave in which you arrive in a well-preserved body. Rather, you should skid there sideways, body thoroughly used up, totally worn out and screaming ''woo-hoo, what a ride''.\n\nSo if you want to get out, get fitter and live life to the full, welcome aboard.\n', '', '', ''),
(880, 1, 'Funeral Service Times', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFuneral Service Times is a magazine dedicated to all those involved in the funeral service profession. Targeting funeral directors throughout the UK, this magazine caters for companies who want to sell their products and service to benefit the funeral sector.\n', '', '', ''),
(881, 1, 'Occupational Health', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Occupational Health keeps all those involved in workplace health up to date each month on changes in the practice and sets the agenda on workplace health policy. Occupational Health magazine’s practical features, authoritative advice, evidence-based practice and occupational health policy make sure you stay ahead of the game, and give you the tools to take a lead on issues affecting health at work. Occupational Health is written specifically for those managing health at work. Read by occupational health managers, advisers, nurses and physicians, it is designed as a practical business tool to aid health and safety. Each issue of Occupational Health magazine carries a wealth of jobs, news, features and research as well as a section encouraging continuing professional development. Sustain your professional development with our career section and dedicated appointments pages.\n', '', '', ''),
(882, 1, 'Men''S Health', 'Men''s Health is India''s largest selling men''s Health and Lifestyle magazine. The editorial content focuses primarily on Indian men and helps them take control of their physical, mental and emotional lives. Each issue discusses various aspects of a man''s life, providing valuable information on health, fitness, fashion, nutrition, relationships, sex, travel etc.. Published by the India Today Group, the Indian edition of the magazine blends the best of the international editions with content in the local context. The magazine is distributed nationwide with an approximate circulation of 70,000 copies every month. There are 16 million readers worldwide, and editions in over 44 countries. The readers get practical and entertaining information that they can use each day, in every part of their lives.', '', '', ''),
(883, 1, 'Prevention', 'The health magazine for 30-plus Indian women -- was launched by the India Today Group in April 2007. The largest health magazine in the US (published by Rodale Inc.), Prevention has shown American women how to lead an active, healthy life for the past 57 years. In less than a year, Prevention is amongst the most trusted sources of health information in this country! A strong-panel of health experts and a crack team of columnists and journalists have made this possible.', '', '', ''),
(884, 1, 'Reader''S Digest', 'Reader''s Digest is the world''s largest circulated English magazine reaching almost 100 Million people, in 21 Languages, 52 Editions.\n \nIts articles are simple to read, famed for its impeccable English and the wealth of knowledge they provide. Moreover, Reader''s Digest has something for every one in the family. Reader''s Digest is a magazine that offers the best in English reading with its many well-written stories from all over the world- stories that deliver knowledge on many subjects, real-life dramas and highlight human achievement. Each issue brings you stories about life and advice about living. Plus features like ''word power'' and ''RD Challenge'' to improve your language; ''Quotable Quotes'' and humor sections like ''Life is like that'', ''Laughter'' and ''All in a Day''s Work''.\n\nEach issue of the Digest is packed with practical advice - guidance from experts on techniques for getting better job.....keeping your money safe....tips on raising brighter children.\n\nYou''ll discover surprising medical discoveries to help you live a longer and healthier life....easy-to-follow diet plans to get you looking slimmer and younger.....and little known facts about yourself you didn''t know before.  ', '', '', ''),
(885, 1, 'B Positive', 'B Positive- Health and Lifestyle magazine, empowers, liberates and educates you with its exclusive, researched content on health, well being, disease management, fitness, beauty, diet &amp; nutrition, safety &amp; hygiene, stress &amp; dependency management &amp; psychology.', '', '', ''),
(886, 1, 'Health And Nutrition', 'A magazine targeted primarily at the lay Indian, its aim to provide the reader with the motivation as well as information. With an objective to enable the reader to cultivate a health-conscious lifestyle and take the reins of his health and well being in his own hands.', '', '', ''),
(887, 1, 'Adventurebox', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO AdventureBox Magazine?\n\nEncourage your kids'' natural curiosity with a subscription to AdventureBox magazine, giving them access to lots of fun features every single month. Every issue has loads of educational and exciting science, history and nature trivia, along with illustrations to help your kids through the trickier school topics. As well as fun facts and fascinating features, your kids can enjoy comic strips, games and a full-length story to be read together or tackled alone. An AdventureBox magazine subscription will also answer all the questions your kids can come up with about how the world works, and help them to learn about important new subjects in a fun and entertaining way.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAn AdventureBox magazine subscription provides great entertainment for you and your child. AdventureBox is a 2010 winner of a Parent''s Choice Silver Award.\n\nGet a subscription to AdventureBox magazine, an exciting magazine to get kids hooked on reading! AdventureBox is a high-quality, educational and fun magazine especially designed for the children aged 6 to 9 years old, with an eye on the National Literacy Strategy. In every issue of an AdventureBox magazine subscription you will find an exciting 44-page illustrated story, divided into manageable chapters, followed by a great section about nature, with stunning pictures and fascinating information, puzzles and games to stimulate children''s literacy and reasoning skills in a fun way, as well as two hilarious comic-strips that children will love! All this in a single issue! Don’t hesitate, invest in a subscription to AdventureBox magazine today!\n', '', '', ''),
(888, 1, 'Let''S Get Crafting', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Let''s Get Crafting Magazine?\n\nLet''s Get Crafting is the UK''s only knitting and crochet bumper magazine, arriving every month complete with needles, yarn and patterns to get you started right away.\n\nIt doesn''t matter whether you’ve been knitting for years or are just eager to learn, as there are projects to suit beginners as well as advanced knitters. Projects range from practical to whimsical, so whether it''s a baby''s jumper, stripy scarf or knitted cupcake you''re after, you''re sure to find the right pattern.\n\nA generous selection of free gifts accompanies every issue, providing all of the basic equipment you need. Add that to the magazine''s monthly giveaways and this is a great value companion for any crafting enthusiast.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLet''s Get Crafting magazine is perfect for anyone who loves to knit and crochet. Each issue of your subscription includes a completely exclusive knitting and crochet kit to get you started on the stunning projects inside. Whether an expert or novice, Let''s Get Crafting project ideas, top designer tips and latest news will give you the inspiration to create beautiful clothing, accessories and gifts from scratch. A subscription to Let’s Get Crafting magazine is a must-have for knitters of all skill levels.\n', '', '', ''),
(889, 1, 'Your Chickens', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nYour Chickens is the first magazine in the UK, dedicated to the rapidly growing number of people who keep, or would like to keep chickens in their back garden or yard.\n\nWriters are respected experts in the field, and it is a comprehensive guide to all things chicken for those who have embraced this enjoyable lifestyle. Your Chickens celebrates all that is good about chicken keeping. It’s full of tips, advice and real life stories of people who have joined the chicken keeping boom. The style of the magazine is informative but fun. It is visually stunning and carries content for all the family including Hattie Hen’s kids club!\n', '', '', ''),
(890, 1, 'Stamp &amp; Coin Mart', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nInvest in a subscription to Stamp &amp; Coin Mart magazine, which is the UK''s fastest growing stamp and coin magazine. With every issue in the subscription to Stamp &amp; Coin Mart containing news, views and articles on every aspect of these fascinating hobbies. Readers questions are answered in the regular ''Ask the Expert'' feature, while a country''s postal output is assessed in the informative Philatelic Bureau column. Collectors can buy, sell and exchange with other like minded enthusiasts with the FREE classified ad pages found in every monthly issue of a subscription to Stamp &amp; Coin Mart, while competitions give readers the chance to win. With auction results, regular technical guides, thematic features and monthly interviews and comprehensive new issues pages, a subscription to Stamp &amp; Coin Mart magazine is a must read for every stamp and coin collector.\n', '', '', ''),
(891, 1, 'Guitar &amp; Bass Magazine', 'WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Guitar &amp; Bass Magazine?\n\nIf you’re already an accomplished player of guitar, bass, or both, then this music magazine can offer you some seriously in-depth reading you''re sure to love.  With your subscription to Guitar &amp; Bass magazine, you''ll enjoy  guitar tests, tips on new techniques and expert reviews of the latest instruments and gear. They have detailed features on the best guitarists from days gone by, as well as info on upcoming artists with real potential. You''ll find practical suggestions on buying second hand accessories and equipment, advice on home recording, and step-by-step guides on how to fix anything that might be wrong with your instrument.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFor over 20 years Guitar &amp; Bass has provided in-depth and essential reading for the serious guitarist, with dozens of guitar tests, playing techniques, an exclusive bass section and in-depth features on guitar heroes past, present and future. Each issue is packed full of reviews of the latest guitars, amps, effects and basses. Guitar &amp; Bass also delivers the informed verdict on home recording equipment and regularly offers tips on buying second hand and vintage gear. When you occasionally put down that guitar, it is also packed full of interviews with the great and good of guitardom!\n\nAs well as all this there is news, reviews, features and interviews. So why wait? Take advantage of the fantastic savings on offer and invest in a subscription to Guitar &amp; Bass magazine today.\n\nFor any guitar enthusiasts out there, Guitar &amp; Bass magazine is the ideal Christmas gift, packed with guitars they''ll love and all their favourite guitarists.\n', '', '', ''),
(892, 1, 'Hornby Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Hornby Magazine Magazine?\n\nA fun and easy-to-read monthly, Hornby Magazine is an independent title with a wide range of articles for the experienced modeller, as well as introductory guides for new hobbyists.\n\nIncorporating expert advice into their step-by-step guides, a subscription to Hornby magazine offers access to modelling tips from the best in the business, allowing you to develop and hone your technique.\n\nBesides this, you can keep up to date with the latest news in the railway world, and find out how you can meet fellow modellers with notifications of upcoming clubs, societies and events across the UK.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHornby Magazine is an informed and entertaining magazine subscription for the model railway enthusiast.Each issue contains expertly researched, informed and totally independent coverage of all new product releases in the most popular scales. These are exciting times for railway modellers with the hobby finally arriving in the 21st Century!. Hornby Magazine fills a much needed niche for beginners of all ages. Each issue is packed with inspirational features showing how to get started in the hobby and what can be achieved.As well as appealing to youngsters who can now combine computer technology with a worthwhile 3D hobby, the magazine will also be welcomed by those 40 to 50 year olds, who’s activities with model trains were interrupted by family matters 20 to 30 years ago.Subscribe to Hornby magazine today and receive your monthly copy of this utterly unique magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(893, 1, 'Localrider', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLocalrider Magazine is the only monthly paid for Equestrian Magazine dedicated to covering the South East of England. Now in its eighth year, the glossy, full-colour publication contains a unique mix of up-to-the-minute show reports, results, features and news. Localrider Magazine is packed full of photographic show reports, interviews with local riders and news and views from across the region, together with informative and educational features. Also popular with our readers are the giveaways, and product reviews sections of the magazine. A subscription to Localrider Magazine covers Kent, Sussex, Surrey, Berkshire, Hampshire, and the Isle of Wight.\n', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `oc_product_description` (`product_id`, `language_id`, `name`, `description`, `meta_description`, `meta_keyword`, `tag`) VALUES
(894, 1, 'Railways Illustrated', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Railways Illustrated Magazine?\n\nThis leading specialist railways magazine is a great choice for anyone looking to stay up to date with the modern day British railway scene, with a comprehensive round up of the latest news and topical issues facing the industry.\n\nYou''ll find considered articles from industry professionals, as well as a nostalgic look at the history and heritage of UK rail, complete with stunning photographs and clever illustrations.\n\nEvery issue of a Railways Illustrated magazine subscription will also bring you detailed articles on the more technical aspects of train life, plus tips on how to get started with trainspotting and model rail construction.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEach issue of a Railways Illustrated magazine subscription offers you a comprehensive round-up of the latest news and topical events from the UK across the present day railway, including heritage traction in operation on the main lines.Supported by high quality photography and editorial from experienced railway enthusiasts, Railways Illustrated magazine reflects the energy and vitality of the present day railway scene.Devoted to coverage of railway companies, train operators, infrastructure functions, main line steam operations and principal modern traction heritage sites, Railways Illustrated magazine also presents a regular photographic overseas feature, some semi-technical articles, and a popular practical series on digital photography.\n', '', '', ''),
(895, 1, 'Real Classic', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Real Classic Magazine?\n\nThis magazine offers classic bike lovers a great mix of historical features, road test reports and repair and maintenance tips, giving you an in-depth guide to which models to invest in and how to keep them in top condition.\n\nFocusing on British models dating from the 1950s onwards, but also dabbling in American and European classics, this mag boasts a team of entertaining and refreshingly honest writers who give their verdicts on everything from retro replicas to spare part pricing.\n\nYou''ll also find real life stories of epic biking adventures, buying guides, and reports from all the major motorcycle festivals and championships.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRealClassic revels in the nuts and bolts of running, riding and rebuilding real classic motorcycles. Expert and enthusiastic riders from across the world share their passion for old bikes via test rides, rebuild reports, retro recreations and reviews. RC features the best of British bikes alongside international classics from all eras, and tells it like it is, with in-depth articles written by authoritative historians of the automotive industry, and life-long, real-world riders. Subscribers can join the RealClassic Club with exclusive benefits including discounts, a monthly newsletter, interactive online access to editorial staff, and more.\n', '', '', ''),
(896, 1, 'Reloved', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nFor someone who loves crafting with an upcycling twist, Reloved is the perfect magazine. With an emphasis on breathing new life into old, forgotten objects, Reloved brings a hands-on approach to this thriving pastime. Reloved magazine is a brand new publication, so why not introduce someone you know to this fantastic magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(897, 1, 'Collectors Gazette', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCollectors Gazette is the UK’s only monthly newspaper dedicated to toy and model collectors. Covering all aspects of toy memorabilia and childhood collectables, Collectors Gazette is a must to keep up to date with the latest news, comprehensive event listings, swapmeet reports, price guides and more. Also each month is our sales and exchange and dealer directories.\n\nSubscribe to Collectors Gazette today to make sure you never miss and issue.\n', '', '', ''),
(898, 1, 'Coin News', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCOIN NEWS - The UK''s biggest selling numismatic magazine packed with informative articles, news, views, latest coin values paper money and market movement reports. Subscribers also benefit from a free Digital version of the magazine with direct links to advertisers''s websites and free classified advertising. There is also a special banknote section every month.\n', '', '', ''),
(899, 1, 'Dogs Today', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Dogs Today magazine, the glossy, award-winning magazine aimed at people who really do care about dogs. Dogs Today magazine campaign hard for improvements to dog health and welfare and provide the most comprehensive help and advice for acquiring and training a new dog. Innovative, entertaining and ethical! With 132 pages each month, typical content includes: TV dog trainer Victoria Stilwell, assistance dog crusader Allen Parton, alternative vet Richard Allport, investigative TV journalist Jemima Harrison, in-depth celeb dog owner interviews, ground-breaking investigative journalism, true stories of remarkable dogs, Problem-solving, unbeatable advice and support, competitions and giveaways and much, much more.\n', '', '', ''),
(900, 1, 'British Patchwork And Quilting', 'WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO British Patchwork and Quilting Magazine?\n\n\n\nThis craft magazine offers a variety of helpful features on patchwork, quilting, appliqué and textile work.\n\nSuitable for novices and seasoned crafters alike, a subscription to British Patchwork &amp; Quilting magazine gives you a monthly collection of articles from renowned expert contributors and part-time enthusiasts.\n\nYou’ll receive new patterns and project ideas as well as tips on pop-up exhibitions around the country to inspire your work.\n\nPlus, with the Block of the Month feature, you''ll be able to make a full patchwork quilt from start to finish, complete with in-depth instructions to guide you through every step of the way.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBritish Patchwork and Quilting Magazine is a monthly publication written by quilters, for quilters, with projects and features specifically to do with patchwork, quilting, applique and textiles. The team behind the magazine includes a combination of renowned contributors and ''ordinary'' quilters. Their talent and expertise brings a mixture of easy and complex pieces together to inspire the novice and expert reader alike.', '', '', ''),
(901, 1, 'Craft Stamper', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nCraft Stamper Magazine is the UK''s only dedicated stamping magazine, featuring an eclectic mix of rubber-stamped art every month.\nWith a hugely talented international design team and a free stamp every month, Craft Stamper is THE magazine for the stamping enthusiast.\n', '', '', ''),
(902, 1, 'Radio Race Car International', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Radio Race Car International Magazine?\n\nEvery issue of this monthly modelling magazine will bring you coverage of some of the most recent RC races and events from across the world. On top of that, you''ll not only read in-depth reviews of new radio-controlled cars and car parts, but you''ll also find a wide range of classifieds and a ''Shoppers'' Directory'', so that you know what gear to buy to improve your vehicle and where to find it. Great for beginners and more experienced racers alike, a subscription to Radio Race Car International magazine will give you all the info you need to keep your car up-to-date and ready to race.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRadio Race Car International magazine has been setting the pace in the ever-changing world of RC cars and racing since it was founded in 1981. The magazine offers a global insight into the latest industry news, results, cars, components and technology\n', '', '', ''),
(903, 1, 'Rc Model World', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO RC Model World Magazine?\n\nTake your hobby to the next level and build something that does more than just look good on a shelf with the helpful flying and building hints in this informative modelling magazine.\n\nThe experts at RC Model World have more than 20 years of experience behind them, giving you fantastic first-hand advice on everything from the world of radio-controlled models.\n\nIn each issue you''ll find features on indoor flying, scale building projects, remote control upgrades and engine tests.\n\nThere''s also a quarterly column written specifically for younger fans, making this a magazine that enthusiastic modellers of all ages can enjoy.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRC Model World Magazine is a monthly publication that has built up a reputation over 25 years for quality of content covering most aspects of the RC hobby. Each issue contains over 120 pages and includes a free plan.\n', '', '', ''),
(904, 1, 'British Railway Modelling', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO British Railway Modelling Magazine?\n\nThis classic modelling magazine is written by committed experts with years of experience behind them to make sure you get the best help and advice around.\n\nBritish Railway Modelling covers all working scales, so whether you prefer to work in N, O, or OO gauge,  you''ll get plenty of easy to understand tutorials to guide you on your way. They give equal attention to steam and diesel miniatures, so over time you can build up a complete collection of historic and modern trains.\n\nYou''ll even by invited to their three national model railway shows every year, each with over 80 exhibitors and plenty of modelling demonstrations to inspire you and your next creation.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEach month with a subscription to British Railway Modelling readers can enjoy a varied content covering steam and diesel era modelling in all the popular scales and gauges. From diminutive N gauge and 2mm finescale models to the robust engineering of 5&quot; gauge live steam, and almost everything in between, you will find it has been covered by BRM. A typical issue of British Railway Modelling magazine covers topics such as: * Inspirational layout features and superb photography * How to'' articles on locomotive and rolling stock construction * Kit building and conversion projects * Scenery and structure modeling * Historical information – from train formations to livery details * Articles to help and guide juniors or first time modelers * Readers layouts – British Railway Modelling finds some ''hidden gems'' * Unbiased and in depth product news and reviews British Railway Modelling magazine features top quality layouts, regular construction articles, the latest news, independent and unbiased reviews and informed comment on all aspects of the hobby.\n', '', '', ''),
(905, 1, 'Stamp Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nBeing Britain''s longest-running independent philatelic magazine, Stamp is better value than everm, with a wide range of news and features to interest, entertain and inform you, whatever you collect. Our news pages are the most lively and well-informed in the UK, our GB Collector section gives you the inside line on all the upcoming British issues, and our features on everything from classics to thematics are the best-written and best illustrated in the world of philately. There is no better showcase for the most exciting material appearing on the market than our colourful Auction Highlights round-up, and you won''t find a more detailed new issue guide anywhere. All this comes with provocative opinion columns, and our comprehensive listing of the month''s events. Subscribing is the best way to keep right up to date.\n', '', '', ''),
(906, 1, 'Stamp', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nBeing Britain''s longest-running independent philatelic magazine, Stamp is better value than everm, with a wide range of news and features to interest, entertain and inform you, whatever you collect. Our news pages are the most lively and well-informed in the UK, our GB Collector section gives you the inside line on all the upcoming British issues, and our features on everything from classics to thematics are the best-written and best illustrated in the world of philately. There is no better showcase for the most exciting material appearing on the market than our colourful Auction Highlights round-up, and you won''t find a more detailed new issue guide anywhere. All this comes with provocative opinion columns, and our comprehensive listing of the month''s events. Subscribing is the best way to keep right up to date.\n', '', '', ''),
(907, 1, 'The British Chess Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe British Chess Magazine is Britain’s leading chess magazine, and the world’s oldest, having been published continuously since 1881. It appears every month, and each issue is packed with in depth and informative content about the chess world. You will find high quality games and analysis, reports on recent tournaments, articles and analysis about chess openings, interviews, authoritative and independent book reviews, instructional articles and regular features on chess problems and endgame studies. Articles about famous players of today and from the past reveal the game’s greatest talents and rich history.\n\nThe British Chess Magazine has a unique focus on the British chess scene, and collaborates with the English Chess Federation, while also covering major chess news and events on the international scene.\n\nThe British Chess Magazine caters for players of all ages and strengths, from beginners to master players, and features both men’s and women’s chess. Subscription to the British Chess Magazine will help every reader improve their play and results, and you can check your progress by playing through our monthly “Test Your Chess” feature written by our own International Master Shaun Taulbut, a member of our editorial team. You can also sharpen and test your attacking skills by enjoying our monthly “Spot the Continuation” feature.\n\nYou can find out where to go to buy chess books and equipment. And great pictures bring The British Chess Magazine to colourful life!\n\nAll in all, the British Chess Magazine is a must read and the best choice for chess players and enthusiasts of all ages and abilities - and makes a great present for any player whatever his or her age or standard of play.\n', '', '', ''),
(908, 1, 'Parrots', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription for Parrots Magazine will open up a whole new world for parrot and parakeet lovers. Every month, Parrots magazine is packed full of fabulous information, and stunning photography, covering all aspects of keeping parrots as pet and aviary birds. The world''s best parrot experts write about pet behaviour, healthcare, breeding, conservation and much more informing all parrot and parakeet owners about the important issues that can affect their birds. Many advertisers are featured in Parrots Magazine offering the widest range of products and services, satisfying all the requirements that parrot owners need, which makes buying all those favourite things so easy. Subscribe to Parrots magazine and experience a whole new world about your favourite subject! Why not buy a gift subscription for a relative or friend?\n', '', '', ''),
(909, 1, 'Steam World', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Steam World Magazine?\n\nSubscribe to Steam World magazine, Britain’s best-selling historical railway title, if you''re fascinated by fine engineering and the UK’s exciting social and industrial history.\n\nFeaturing lively photography and all of the latest news on restoration projects and upcoming events, this is a truly unique history magazine.\n\nYou’ll also find interviews and articles by specialist railway personnel, including British Rail managers, train drivers, firemen and other enthusiasts who share your passion.\n\nPublished monthly, this is an intriguing read for those who remember riding steam trains, and a great way to introduce your offspring to the golden age of rail travel.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSteam World relives the glorious days when Britain’s steam railways were the lifeblood of the country. Combining the very best pictures with accounts from drivers, fireman, BR managers and enthusiasts the heydays of british steam are brought back to life. Steam World magazine is packed with stunning pictures from the fifties and sixties which are guaranteed to bring back magical memories for those were there, but will also thrill those who are too young to remember mainline steam. Steam World is as real as it gets. A unique section of Steam World magazine is letter pages where readers can share memories and keep in touch with old friends.\n', '', '', ''),
(910, 1, 'Dolls House &amp; Miniature Scene', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Dolls House &amp; Miniature Scene Magazine?\n\nThe beautiful spreads in Dolls House and Miniature Scene give you exclusive access to photos of unique creations from around the world, making this magazine perfect inspiration for either starting or perfecting your dolls house decorations. Focusing on historical houses, you''ll love learning about the architecture of periods from Tudor to gothic to modern, with explanations on how to transfer the styles to your own miniature displays. Whether you''ve just been given your first dolls house or have cherished yours for years, a subscription to Dolls House and Miniature Scene magazine lets you in on gatherings, displays and festivals where you can chat to fellow enthusiasts and marvel at the exquisite creations on show.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDollsHouse and Miniature Scene is the UK’s best selling miniatures magazine. Each issue covers a variety projects and features on dolls house dolls, doll house furniture, dollhouse miniatures, dollshouse kits, dolls house fairs and shows. This magazine includes something for everyone from beginner’s right through to experienced miniaturists.\n\nA subscription can cost from as little as £10.50*plus all subscribers receive membership to the DHMS Subscriber Club entitling you to discounted fair tickets to Arnhem Dollshouse Show, Kensington Dollshouse Festival and Creative Craft Shows, discounts from retailers such as Dateman Books, Curtains Petite, The House that Jacq Built, Petite Properties, The Model Tree Shop, Jane Harrop Miniatures, Homes in Miniature and other special offers on Dolls House Projects and Naked Wines plus exclusive subscriber only competitions. *This rate is for a UK quarterly Direct Debit only.\n', '', '', ''),
(911, 1, 'Everyday Practical Electronics', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nEveryday Practical Electronics (EPE) is the UK’s premier magazine for electronics and computer enthusiasts. Every issue is packed with ideas, theory and projects for beginners and experts, with full circuit diagrams, printed circuit board layouts, artwork and photos.\n\nIf you''re interesting in learning more about electronics and computing, then EPE is bound to have something of interest to you!\n\nIndustry experts keep you informed of all the relevant news and events, plus in-depth articles on electronics theory, microprocessors, the Internet and constructional techniques etc. There is also a selection of readers’ letters and a wide range of relevant advertisements from component, equipment and software suppliers.\n', '', '', ''),
(912, 1, 'Sew', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Sew Magazine?\n\nWhether you''re just starting out on your sewing journey or have been working on your skills for a while, this sewing magazine covers all your queries with simple workbooks and templates, giving you project ideas on everything from trendy tunic tops to stitched pyjama cases and other decorative pieces for your home.\n\nWith a subscription to Sew magazine, you can look forward to receiving a free, full length dressmaker’s pattern with every issue, as well as a helpful stitch glossary and reviews of the best new sewing-related books, websites and products.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Sew magazine is the perfect read for anyone who is crazy about sewing. Sew magazine comes with regular FREE sewing pattern on dressmakers tissue worth £7! Sew magazine will provide you with fashionable projects for your wardrobe and your home exclusively created by some of the UKs leading stitching designers.Sew magazine will provide you with fashionable projects for your wardrobe and your home exclusively created by some of the UK’s leading stitching designers. Each project is presented in an informative, friendly and easy-to-follow style. Every issue of a Sew magazine subscription also comes with a 24-page essential pull-out Sew workbook including sewing information, stitch glossary and templates. Sew magazine comes with stunning and lavish pictures of new trends and designs, enabling you to gain more knowledge on your favorite hobby. Advice from an expert team of writers makes Sew magazine an indispensable guide.\n', '', '', ''),
(913, 1, 'Rail Express', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRail Express is essential reading for today’s rail enthusiast. It has all the latest news from across Britain’s railway network, illustrated with superb photographs of traction in action. There’s full coverage of main line movements, London Underground, railtours, the preservation scene, shunters, coaches and developments over on the Irish network. Every movement and acquisition is examined and the Time Traveller column offers a nostalgic look back at the rail news of yesteryear. Rail Express Modeller is your comprehensive guide to the world of model railways, featuring reviews of new releases and how-to guides for getting the best from your layout.\n', '', '', ''),
(914, 1, 'Garden Rail', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Garden Rail Magazine?\n\nIf you fancy a new challenge, Garden Rail magazine is your first port of call for how to take your model railway building skills outside, and join the many other member of the modelling community who are moving their favourite hobby into their gardens. The only monthly title dedicated to outdoor modelling, each issue is full of articles on the most recent modelling developments and products, as well as information and advice from seasoned professionals. On top of this, a subscription offers plenty of coverage on taking care of your garden, so that you can be sure it always looks its best.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGarden Rail is the only British magazine covering all aspects of outdoor model railways, and the only related magazine worldwide, that publishers monthly. The magazine provides a comprehensive and up-to-date overview, not only of the developments within this fast-growing hobby, but also the seasonal joys of the garden.\n\nMore and more people are recognizing that building an outdoor model railway is one of the most satisfying and diverse hobbies possible to find. A small-scale railway in a pleasing garden setting can be an activity involving all the family, as well as a joy to contemplate.\n\nThe sight provides sheer delight; sound and smell of a real steam locomotive hauling a train through the rockery, perhaps under radio control, or a train running at night with lights in the coaches, gliding to a halt at a bucolic station platform. How about an American diesel locomotive, (complete with sound unit) working hard against grade at the head of a long freight – or maybe a coal fired garden scale locomotive provided the evocative smells as well as the sight and sound of steam motive power (yes, this is possible and perfectly functional on the 32mm or 45mm gauge tracks).\n\nGarden Rail magazine is aimed at established ‘converts’ to the hobby, as well as those yet to desert their indoor layouts and discover the real potential of large-scale modeling in an outdoor setting.\n', '', '', ''),
(915, 1, 'Bbc Homes &amp; Antiques', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Homes &amp; Antiques Magazine?\n\nIf you can''t get enough of antique shops, car boot sales and vintage finds, then a Homes &amp; Antiques magazine subscription is the perfect way to inspire your next purchase or project. Each issue is packed with practical how-to guides on vintage arts and crafts, as well as information on how to upcycle your new antiques and old furniture. You''ll be inspired by photographs of beautiful antiques and stylish interiors, helping you to make the most of your collections at home. There''s also dozens of handy shopping guides every month, plus the latest exclusive news from the BBC''s Antiques Roadshow.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHomes &amp; Antiques is a must-read for those who love great design and beautiful objects from every era. Alongside our unrivalled guides to antiques and collectables, you’ll find inspiring real interiors, sizzling style and decorating ideas and a huge range of features on everything from heritage and architecture to vintage fashion.\n\nInside every issue, you will find achievable and stylish decorating ideas, up-to-the minute shopping guides and four real homes, as well as news from the Antiques Roadshow, and must-read guides on collecting everything from compact cases to silver candlesticks.\n\nIf you love antiques and interiors, Homes &amp; Antiques is the only magazine that can offer you the inspiration you''re looking for.\n', '', '', ''),
(916, 1, 'Homes &amp; Antiques', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Homes &amp; Antiques Magazine?\n\nIf you can''t get enough of antique shops, car boot sales and vintage finds, then a Homes &amp; Antiques magazine subscription is the perfect way to inspire your next purchase or project. Each issue is packed with practical how-to guides on vintage arts and crafts, as well as information on how to upcycle your new antiques and old furniture. You''ll be inspired by photographs of beautiful antiques and stylish interiors, helping you to make the most of your collections at home. There''s also dozens of handy shopping guides every month, plus the latest exclusive news from the BBC''s Antiques Roadshow.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHomes &amp; Antiques is a must-read for those who love great design and beautiful objects from every era. Alongside our unrivalled guides to antiques and collectables, you’ll find inspiring real interiors, sizzling style and decorating ideas and a huge range of features on everything from heritage and architecture to vintage fashion.\n\nInside every issue, you will find achievable and stylish decorating ideas, up-to-the minute shopping guides and four real homes, as well as news from the Antiques Roadshow, and must-read guides on collecting everything from compact cases to silver candlesticks.\n\nIf you love antiques and interiors, Homes &amp; Antiques is the only magazine that can offer you the inspiration you''re looking for.\n', '', '', ''),
(917, 1, 'Continental Modeller', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nYour passport to the best in International Railway Modelling.\n\nRegarded as essential reading for every enthusiast who models the different railways of the world. Each month a subscription to Continental Modeller magazine shows you how to reproduce foreign railway scenes perfectly and is filled with regular tips and articles intended to inspire beginners and experts alike.\n\nFilled with many exciting layouts including photographs, illustrations and plans and also boasts a huge range of display advertisements for those seeking to purchase further model equipment.\n', '', '', ''),
(918, 1, 'Birdwatch', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nBirdwatch is the number one magazine in the UK for expert birders. Including everything you need to improve your birding skills such as in-depth ID features, better birding, the latest rarity reports and highlights, gear reviews, and informative features from the birding world.\n', '', '', ''),
(919, 1, 'Diecast Collector', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDiecast Collector is the UK’s number one model magazine, packed full each month of latest releases, news, up-to-date auction price guides and events, plus we give you the full insight into some iconic models in our in-depth features. Covering everything diecast, including cars, trucks, buses, planes and more, Diecast Collector is a must buy for any model enthusiast.\n\nSubscribe to Diecast Collector today and make sure you never miss and issue of your favourite collecting magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(920, 1, 'Birdwatch', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nBirdwatch is the number one magazine in the UK for expert birders. Including everything you need to improve your birding skills such as in-depth ID features, better birding, the latest rarity reports and highlights, gear reviews, and informative features from the birding world.\n', '', '', ''),
(921, 1, 'Knitting', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Knitting Magazine?\n\nKnitting has firmly shed its old-fashioned image and established itself as a fun and vibrant hobby, and knitters from all walks of life will find something to enjoy in this lively knitting and sewing magazine.\n\nWhether you''re young or old, expert or amateur, you''ll be able to develop your skills by reading through the tips, news and patterns offered in every issue of a Knitting magazine subscription.\n\nYou''ll also find easy-to-follow knitting and crochet patterns to make the latest fashion items and gorgeous home accessories, plus beautiful baby clothes and children''s wear to\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Knitting magazine subscription is the perfect magazine for anyone who has a keen interest in Knitting. Knitting is the UK''s original and best magazine devoted to this popular craft. Bridging the divide between fashion and hand-Knitting, each issue offers at least 25 new and contemporary patterns including knits for women, men, children and the home. Bursting with patterns from the world’s leading hand-knit designers, it is both style conscious and practical with techniques, clear how-to''s, designer profiles and interesting features, making it an essential reading for the discerning knitter.\n', '', '', ''),
(922, 1, 'Shooting Gazette', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nShooting Gazette is the world''s leading monthly driven game shooting magazine. First launched in 1989. Shooting Gazette has become entrenched in UK shooting circles as well as being a popular read all around the world. It''s an entertaining and informative read with the emphasis on quality of writing and topical feature material. A true finger on the pulse of the game shooting world.\n', '', '', ''),
(923, 1, 'Carriage Driving', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nCarriage Driving is the only monthly magazine dedicated entirely to sport and recreation with the harness horse. It is a must-read publication for all carriage driving enthusiasts, covering all aspects of recreational and competitive driving, including private driving, light trade, coaching, show Hackneys, scurry driving and horse driving trials.\n\nSubscribe to Carriage Driving today for:\n\n•The latest driving news, views, show and competition coverage, together with regular features, such as: Over the Tandem Bar – its very own gossip column; In the Ribbons – keeping you up-to-date with all the results and driver profiles\n•Expert view – answers to reader’s questions\n• Training – with tips to help you enhance your driving skills Junior Spotlight - for those up and coming youngsters\n•The best place to buy and sell your driving horses, harnesses and carriages, as well as advertise all your other carriage driving services\nAll UK subscribers receive a free Carriage Driving calendar with their December issue, which includes all those important driving dates, providing an invaluable source of information together with some stunning photography.\n', '', '', ''),
(924, 1, 'Family Wordsearch', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nIf it’s fun family wordsearches you’re after, then Family Wordsearch is just for you. You’ll find recipe puzzles, readers’ puzzles and a whole host of super themed wordsearches. With more than 100 puzzles and a super £1,500 cash competition in every issue, Family Wordsearch is fantastic value too.\n', '', '', ''),
(925, 1, 'Family Criss Cross', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nOur great value Family Criss Cross magazine contains a host of terrific criss cross puzzles and a £1,500 cash competition. Words are listed according to length and your task is to fit them into the empty grid jigsaw-style, reading across and down. This unrivalled selection of fun themed puzzles is guaranteed to keep you\n', '', '', ''),
(926, 1, 'Family Criss Cross Jumbo', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nFamily Criss Cross Jumbo is put together with the criss cross fanatic in mind – regular themed criss crosses and a sprinkling of variety criss crosses to keep you on your toes. Add a £1,500 cash competition and you’ve got a great value package, coming in at a whopping 164 pages.\n', '', '', ''),
(927, 1, 'Family Wordsearch Jumbo', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nFamily Wordsearch Jumbo lives up to its supersized name – it’s a jumbo wordsearch magazine with an unbeatable selection of fun-to-solve puzzles and a £1,500 cash competition. There are seasonal wordsearches and more than 130 other puzzles grouped into categories such as travel, food and drink, TV and so on.\n', '', '', ''),
(928, 1, 'Family Wordsearch Special', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nClocking in at a bumper 136 puzzles, including a cash competition, Family Wordsearch Special is a guaranteed winner for even the most demanding wordsearch fan. There are regular wordsearches, variety ones and a few fun challenging searches to make it an all-round puzzles treat.\n', '', '', ''),
(929, 1, 'Model Engineers Workshop', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Model Engineers Workshop Magazine?\n\nThis modelling magazine is the ideal title for anyone really committed to engineering in miniature. Specialising in metalwork techniques for the experienced enthusiast, Model Engineers Workshop shines a spotlight on the intricate processes and techniques required to develop the precise skills needed to make miniature machinery. You''ll receive monthly advice on building and maintaining useful workshop kit, and find out how to recycle old power tools for use in your creations. There''s a section on engineering for beginners to help out any newcomers, as well as detailed features on problem solving and safety precautions, and readers'' letters from around the country.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Model Engineers Workshop is a must read for the serious model engineering hobbyists!\n\nModel Engineers'' Workshop magazine deals with machines, materials, processes and techniques for precision metalwork.\n', '', '', ''),
(930, 1, 'Steam Railway', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Steam Railway Magazine?\n\nA Steam Railway magazine subscription keeps you up to date with everything from the world of steam, including development and extensions of preserved tracks and main lines. Each issue contains spectacular photography and archive material, giving you a glimpse of all the great steam locomotives that have graced Britain''s railways in years past and present. You''ll also find book reviews of the latest steam and railway related releases, as well as a guide to important upcoming events, galas and rail tours in the steam calendar.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSubscribe to Steam Railway; The World’s biggest-selling steam magazine.Railway preservation’s biggest selling title is the ultimate celebration of the world of steam. The original and the best, Steam Railway is number one for exclusive news and stunning photography. Steam Railway magazine is top class heritage rail magazine published in the UK, coming with top class photographs and lucid coverage of locomotives. Steam Railway magazine covers steam engines, preservations and history. Steam Railway magazine comes with the news and coverage of the classic locomotives..Steam Railway magazine provides its readers with a unique celebration of the world of Steam Railway, complete with all the news of current goings on from around the globe. The Direct Debit GuaranteeThe minimum subscription term for the direct debit offer is 12 months.\n', '', '', ''),
(931, 1, 'Model Rail', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Model Rail Magazine?\n\nCatering for long-time modelling enthusiasts and new-comers alike, a subscription to Model Rail magazine offers enthusiastic and dedicated features articles for all to enjoy. Its pages feature practical guidance for modellers of all experience levels, as well as inspiring photography that showcases the most impressive models and landscapes around.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA Model Rail magazine subscription is an essential monthly read for anyone interested in railway modelling. First published in 1997, Model Rail is a British railway magazine focusing on Model Railways. Model Rail has a fresh new approach to model railway magazines; it shows you how to get the best from your hobby. Model Rail magazine is published 13 times a year and features articles about railways in Britain, layouts, weathering, building kits, kit bashing, scratch building, and other model making techniques. The Direct Debit Guarantee The minimum subscription term for the direct debit offer is 12 months. The amount paid by Direct Debit may change over time. If and when it does you will be notified in advance by at least 10 days. If an error is made by Bauer Media Ltd or by bank/building society, you are entitled to a full and immediate refund. You can cancel the Direct Debit at any time by writing to your bank/building society and send a copy to Bauer Media Ltd at: Magazine Subscriptions, Tower House, Sovereign Park, Market Harborough, Leicestershire LE94 7ZT. Please note that banks and building societies may not accept Direct Debit instructions from some types of account.\n', '', '', ''),
(932, 1, 'The Artist', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The Artist Magazine?\n\nWith a monthly subscription to The Artist magazine you''ll learn how to paint, sketch and print to a high standard in no time.\n\nThis art magazine is packed with advice from both amateur and professional artists, with everything from brush techniques to project ideas, as well as advice on how to start selling your work. If that''s not enough, you''ll also find news, reviews, profiles and interviews with leading figures in the art world, as well as top tips on where to find the best materials to use at home.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Artist magazine is the UK’s leading practical art magazine and the essential source of inspiration, advice and information for all artists, since its launch in 1931. With the demise of the teaching of traditional drawing and painting skills in our art schools, The Artist stands out for its commitment to teach traditional artistic skills and techniques in all media, covering all traditional subject matter. Written by artists, for artists, every issue is packed with practical articles to inspire artists of all levels, and includes interviews with top professional artists who provide insights into their approach and working methods.With regular up-to-date information on the latest art materials available, exhibitions to see and enter, events, opportunities, books, courses, and the business side of being a fulltime artist, The Artist is an essential and inspirational resource for all artists, whether a passionate amateur or hard-working professional.\n', '', '', ''),
(933, 1, 'Model Boats', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Model Boats Magazine?\n\nFirst published nearly 50 years ago, this is ideal monthly reading if you love building model boats. This modelling magazine covers every type of model boat including warships, tugs, lifeboats and historical ships, with a special emphasis placed on scale modelling and radio controlled boats. Each issue features kit and model reviews, show reports, news from the boat modelling world and regular expert columns. If you''re just getting started, this is the perfect way to improve: in every other issue of your Model Boats magazine subscription you’ll receive a free, high-quality plan and a matching build article.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSubscribe to Model Boats: the world’s best selling model boating magazine.Model Boats has brought benchmark levels of in depth writing and quality photography to the hobby and is the best selling model boating magazine.\n\nEach issue has extensive kit and model reviews, informative features, show reports, club news, new items for the modeller and regular expert columns from a number of highly regarded contributors. Model Boats covers all areas of this absorbing hobby. Whether your interest is in Tugs, Lifeboats, Warships, Sailing Craft, Model Yachting or Offshore Racing, (just to name a few!), you will find something of interest within its pages.\n', '', '', ''),
(934, 1, 'Popular Patchwork', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Popular Patchwork Magazine?\n\nWhether you''ve been quilting for years or have just picked up your first pattern, Popular Patchwork magazine is the perfect accompaniment to the hobby.\n\nThey have thoughtful advice to ease newcomers in, as well as elaborate challenges for more experienced readers to tackle.\n\nWith your subscription, you''ll be introduced into an active and sociable community of quilters, with the ''show and tell'' page dedicated to letting you present your prized projects and admire everyone else''s. In each issue you''ll find advice from at least six top designers, with suggestions for bags, aprons and samplers as well as a range of impressive quilts. There''s even a kids corner section, letting you include your children in your favourite hobby.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPopular Patchwork magazine embraces both traditional and contemporary quilting This magazine covers a variety of projects for all skills levels from well known designers (at least six in every issue!), kids’ corner, reviews of quilts shows (both large and small!) ; interviews with celebrity and grass roots quilters, articles on design as well as historical and international features. Popular Patchwork magazine is a great source of news of the latest fabrics and products out in the market place as well as all book reviews and regular reader offers. 3 great reasons to buy a Popular Patchwork magazine subscription: • Every issue, Delivered conveniently to your door for FREE • View the full range of content on www.popularpatchwork.com • Gain access to the complete back catalogue of Popular Patchwork Magazine Digital Editions\n', '', '', ''),
(935, 1, 'The Woodworker', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to The Woodworker magazine will provide you with the mose authoritative voice of wood working.The Woodworker is a hands-on magazine aimed at the home woodworker. Its 108 year heritage makes it the authoritative voice on the subject. Edited and written by enthusiasts there is a real feel for, and understanding of, the subject. The Woodworker magazine presents projects and technical advice on all aspects of woodworking, plus news, reviews and tests of the new and most popular woodworking tools and equipment available today.\n', '', '', ''),
(936, 1, 'All About Space', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO All About Space Magazine?\n\nTake a trip through the wonders of the universe with this fantastic science and nature magazine.Each issue features awe-inspiring space topics that are brought to life by field experts in a simple and easy to follow way, making sure everyone can understand the wonderful facts of our solar system, regardless of their age.An All About Space magazine subscription will bring you the latest research and technology developments, with brilliant satellite photography to bring you closer to the action.You''ll also find how-to guides for your next stargazing adventure, plus product reviews on the latest telescopes and star maps.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\nExplore the wonders of the universe with the new space magazine, All About Space. Every month, All About Space provides expert authors, mind-blowing photography and full-colour illustrations that bring the amazing universe around us to life. Our expert authors will amaze and educate you with fascinating articles and features on all aspects of space and space travel in a style that''s engrossing and easy to read.\n\nEvery issue of All About Space takes readers on an awe-inspiring journey through our Solar System and beyond, from the amazing technology and spacecraft that enables humanity to venture into orbit to the unfathomable phenomena of deep space science. This amazing magazine provides fascinating, inspiring and thought-provoking articles from experts in every field of space discovery to satisfy readers’ natural curiosity on this unimaginably vast subject.\n\nAll About Space is dedicated to delivering expert features and articles on the latest cutting-edge research, technology and theories in an entertaining and visually stunning way, all in a language that everyone can understand.The magazine also features a regular Stargazing section dedicated to helping readers get starting in the absorbing world of amateur astronomy with how-to guides, kit reviews and advice.\n', '', '', ''),
(937, 1, 'Model Collector', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Model Collector Magazine?\n\nIf you’re looking for a way to stay up-to-date with all the latest model collecting news and events, then a subscription to Model Collector magazine is just what you need. Whether you''re into classic vehicle toys or collect detailed scale replicas, you''ll love the features on special editions and manufacturer announcements in this monthly modelling magazine. There are previews of upcoming releases in every issue, plus unbiased reviews of recently-launched models. If you subscribe to Model Collector magazine, you''ll also learn about the current values of classic replicas and will get reports on recent auctions as well as previews of future events, making sure that you know where you stand whether you''re looking to buy or sell.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nModel Collector is not only Britain''s longest running magazine for model collectors, it''s also the best loved title in hobby and essential monthly reading for miniature transport enthusiasts everywhere. As well as keeping you bang up to date with all the latest news and events, we boast the UK''s No. 1 Guide to New Releases, where you''ll find our reviewers uncensored comments refreshingly honest, unbiased and outspoken. In response to these reviews and other issues, the letters pages are equally candid and brimming with your reactions, personal reminiscences and additional input. Elsewhere in the magazine, fascinating features penned by experts in their individual fields will help you increase your knowledge of the classics and their current values. In fact, whether you collect the nostalgic toys of yesteryear or today''s high tech scale replicas, we can guarantee you a riveting read.\n', '', '', ''),
(938, 1, 'Quick Cards Made Easy', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Quick Cards Made Easy Magazine?\n\nSubscribe to Quick Cards Made Easy magazine for the inspiration and techniques to create your own stunning cards in under an hour. Each issue is packed with 70 card designs, plus hints and tips from card-making experts to guide you along the way. Whether you''re a complete beginner, or an experienced card-maker, the magazine is designed to cater for all experience levels with plenty of useful hints for all. With a fabulous free gift in every issue and inspiration for how to use it, you''ll soon be on your way to making personalised masterpieces for all your friends.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nWith a Quick Cards made easy subscription you''ll always have a quick and easy project at your fingertips. Every issue is packed with 70 new card designs from the UK''s favourite card designers, all the latest product news plus expert advice on card making and money saving ideas.\n', '', '', ''),
(939, 1, 'The World Of Cross Stitching', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The World of Cross Stitching Magazine?\n\nThis brilliant crafts magazine comes with great advice from cross-stitch champions, sure to get everyone from seasoned professionals to complete novices producing beautiful pieces in no time at all. In each issue of The World of Cross Stitching magazine, you''ll get product reviews, reader letters, competitions and giveaways, giving you loads of opportunities to really get involved in this exciting creative community. Newcomers are well looked after with handy step-by-step guides and designs, and with a free crafty gift in each issue, they''ll soon build up an impressive sewing kit and cross-stitch portfolio of their own.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe World of Cross Stitching is THE cross stitch magazine to inspire every stitcher, whatever your level of expertise.\n\nEvery issue is packed with the very best cross stitch designs, expert advice and in-depth technical features, as well as product news, reader letters and stories, competitions and giveaways.\n', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `oc_product_description` (`product_id`, `language_id`, `name`, `description`, `meta_description`, `meta_keyword`, `tag`) VALUES
(940, 1, 'Cross Stitch Crazy', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Cross Stitch Crazy Magazine?\n\nLearning to cross-stitch is easy with a subscription to Cross Stitch Crazy magazine.Each issue is full of patterns for every skill level that will get you practising, technical how-to guides to help you improve, and all of the latest designs from the cross stitching community for inspiration.Designs range from novelty ''celeb'' stitches to beautiful cross stitch greeting cards and simple stitch charts for kids.You can also look forward to thrifty money saving tips, entertaining reader stories, competitions and free gifts, plus access to subscriber-only CRAFT XTRA pages with exclusive charts and offers.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nBursting with fun, this is the magazine for stitchers who just can''t get enough! In each issue, we promise to deliver easy-to-follow and quick-to-stitch designs from your favourite designers, direct to your door.\n\nWith fun stories, great competitions and a fab free gift for you with every single issue you''d have to be mad to miss it!\n\nGreat reasons to subscribe:\n• Receive the FREE cover gift with every issue\n• EXCLUSIVE subscriber projects in each issue\n• BONUS CraftXtra Newsletter three times a year - with special offers, puzzles &amp; giveaways\n', '', '', ''),
(941, 1, 'Knit Today', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Knit Today Magazine?\n\nKnitting a garment from scratch is hugely rewarding and with a subscription to Knit Today magazine, you won''t have to sacrifice fashion or style when you do. Each issue of Knit Today is full of eye-catching designs inspired by the trends of the season, with simple patterns that are suitable for beginners as well as advanced knitters. In addition to clothing patterns, you''ll also find how-to guides for knitting accessories such as socks and bags, as well as attractive knit decorations for the home. Expert columns provide in-depth guidance on specific techniques such as buttonholing and translating US patterns, whilst write-ups on knitting events and classes around the UK ensure you''re kept in the loop.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nKnit Today is the fun, inspirational magazine written for knitters of all abilities, budgets and sizes. Every issue is packed with gorgeous knits for all the family from stylish women’s garments and baby designs, to fun quick knits and home projects. Knit Today brings you exciting news from the world of knitting, interviews with our favourite designers and reviews of all the latest must-have products including yarns, books and patterns. PLUS every issue has a quality free gift!\n', '', '', ''),
(942, 1, 'Cardmaking &amp; Papercraft', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Cardmaking &amp; Papercraft Magazine?\n\nThis crafts magazine has every possible paper-based project covered, with cards for any occasion as well as plenty of ideas for giftboxes, rosettes and much more. With easy to follow guides from experienced artists, your subscription to Cardmaking &amp; Papercraft magazine will make sure you never buy a pre-made card again. You''ll love the letters page, where you can send in your own creations to share with fellow readers and comment on their contributions each month. You''ll even receive a free gift in every issue, and with projects themed to suit each season and holiday, you''ll always have a reason to try out new cards.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWith a Cardmaking &amp; Papercraft subscription, you''ll never be short of cardmaking ideas. Each issue is packed with the very best techniques with detailed step-by-steps, essential advice and know how from top experts, gorgeous card ideas from all your favourite designers plus a fab free cover gift in every issue.\n\nGreat reasons to subscribe:\n• Save over 30% on a year’s subscription with free delivery in the UK\n• Never miss an issue of inspirational cardmaking ideas and top designer tips\n• FREE cover gift with every issue\n• FREE UK home delivery\n•EXCLUSIVE craftXtra subscriber only competitions, reader offers and giveaways\n', '', '', ''),
(943, 1, 'Crafts Beautiful', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Crafts Beautiful Magazine?\n\nFrom origami to glass painting, you''ll find yourself trying out a new hobby every month with a subscription to Crafts Beautiful magazine. Each issue comes with a free pull-out pattern book accompanied by detailed but simple instructions, so even completely unfamiliar crafts will be easy to figure out. If you''re interested in selling your work, this magazine offers insider tips from successful creative businesses to give you the support and advice you need. You''ll get ideas on planning great events like crafting hen parties, plenty of freebies, and the chance to enter exclusive competitions and win some amazing prizes.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nIf you are crazy about crafts, a magazine subscription to Crafts Beautiful is the perfect magazine for you. You''ll find something to tempt you from the choice of inspirational projects from the UK''s top craft designers. Each issue contains a free pull-out pattern pack and regular free books throughout the year.Crafts Beautiful magazine is the perfect choice magazine for people looking for creative ideas for crafts, craft products, craft sales ideas, and special occasion craft ideas. Crafts Beautiful magazine comes with ideas on different topics like beading, painting, paper craft, stitching, computer &amp; digital arts, etc in every issue of a subscription.The magazine takes you through the different craft projects and tells you about all the cool and nice products available for purchase.\n', '', '', ''),
(944, 1, 'Let''S Knit', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Let''s Knit Magazine?\n\nEach copy of Let''s Knit magazine is stuffed full of fantastic and fun new patterns, whether you''re just starting out as a knitter or are simply looking for a challenge.\n\nEach issue has exciting competitions and also offers crafting tips for crochet and needle felting, giving you plenty of variety each month. As one of the UK''s leading knitting and sewing magazines, this is the perfect read if you''re looking for easy-to-follow instructions, as well as informative tips and tricks from seasoned knitters.\n\nA Let''s Knit magazine magazine subscription is also a great way to learn how to create beautiful, fun pieces that make wonderful gifts for friends and family.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSubscribe to Lets Knit magazine and receive all of the latest patterns, designs and creations from the Knitting world. Lets Knit is the perfect gift for any Knitting enthusiasts.Let''s Knit magazine takes a fresh perspective on knitting! If you are a modern knitter wanting patterns and creations that are not just fun to make but fashionable too then this magazine is for you.A Let’s Knit subscription brings its readers exclusive patterns from some of the best contemporary designers, with clear instructions presented in a fresh, accessible format – plus we give you colour variations and freestyling tips to help you make them your own.Lets knit comes with projects for beginners and experienced knitters alike, each issue offers more of what knitters want – more patterns, more style, more shopping, more options and more excitement.\n', '', '', ''),
(945, 1, 'Papercraft Inspirations', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Papercraft Inspirations Magazine?\n\nHelping you to get creative and make your own beautiful, homemade cards, Papercraft Inspirations provides monthly motivation with step by step guides for every occasion.\n\nEach issue contains plenty of pictures and articles from card making experts, as well as tutorials on how to personalise your creations and make them look truly professional.\n\nYou''ll also receive a free gift with every edition, complete with suggestions on how to use it in your card designs.\n\nDelve into the world of papercraft to show off your creative side - and never have to buy a birthday card again!\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPapercraft Inspirations is the best magazine for all papercrafters – from beginners to experts. Our friendly, helpful approach leads readers through from their very first card to great scrapbooking pages, involving the whole family in the fun. Each issue of PaperCraft inspirations magazine is crammed with inspirational ideas and loads of techniques for you to try. Great reasons to subscribe to Papercraft Inspirations magazine:\n', '', '', ''),
(946, 1, 'Simply Knitting', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Simply Knitting Magazine?\n\nWith top technical advice, step-by-step instructions and gorgeous patterns included in every issue, a subscription to Simply Knitting magazine will help you to create beautiful handmade garments and accessories for every season.\n\nEach issue comes with a variety of design ideas, ranging from classic cardigans and on-trend cover-ups to adorable baby clothes and stylish knit interior decorations.\n\nYou''ll also find coverage of craft events and festivals from around the UK, plus guides on the best type of wool to buy for your project and the best equipment and tools to add to your collection.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Simply Knitting magazine subscription is ideal for anyone who is either new to the wonderful hobby of knitting or already a fully fledged knittaholic. Simply Knitting is the UK’s best-selling knitting magazine providing readers with loads of gorgeous patterns, easy-to-follow instructions, interviews with designers, top technical advice, knitting news and great buys. So why not subscribe today and be a part of the wonderful community of knitting! And don’t forget, every issue comes with a gift!\n', '', '', ''),
(947, 1, 'Craftseller', 'WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Craftseller Magazine?\n\nFor helpful advice on how to create and sell your homemade crafts, subscribe to Craftseller magazine.\n\nFeaturing a wide range of how-to guides on everything from knitting and sewing to baking, this craft magazine will inspire you to start new projects, whilst also guiding you through the world of online selling.\n\nEach issue keeps you informed on current fabric trends and the latest techniques, and also provides expert advice from accomplished crafters on the best equipment, useful sales apps and top websites to help you bag a bargain and trade your arty pieces.\n\nPlus, look out for the real-life success stories and free gift in every issue.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCraftseller is a magazine which will inspire and advise crafters looking to make and sell their homemade crafts. Make money from your crafting today with Craftseller featuring quick projects and how to sell them. Now''s your chance to: try new crafts- knitting, cross stitch, paper craft, projects and more, discover how to sell online and discover the latest buys, useful apps and top websites!\n', '', '', ''),
(948, 1, 'Love Patchwork &amp; Quilting', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBringing you the best modern quilting projects each month, with projects included to keep you busy and every issue comes with a FREE gift!\n\nLove Patchwork &amp; Quilting is the brand new magazine from the makers of Mollie Makes and Simply Crochet. With monthly features on the most modern designs and best projects for quilts, cushions, home style and gifts, there is something for any skill level.\n\nThis is an essential read for the modern day quilter.\n\nYou''ll receive 13 issues during a 1 year Love Patchwork &amp; Quilting magazine subscription.\n', '', '', ''),
(949, 1, 'Xone', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nX-ONE is the UK''s best Xbox One and Xbox 360 magazine thanks to its unrivalled exclusives, editorial integrity, an entire section dedicated to the Xbox community and a team that lives, sleeps and breathes everything associated with the console. There simply isn''t a better Xbox magazine on the market!\n', '', '', ''),
(950, 1, 'Cross Stitcher', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nGet a subscription to Cross Stitcher magazine, Britain''s best-selling cross stitch magazine. And what is the secret of Cross Stitcher magazine’s success? There''s something for every stitcher in every issue of a subscription to the magazine. Cross Stitcher Magazine is packed with beautiful designs for you to stitch and stylish ideas to inspire you. In each issue you’ll find plenty of original, creative projects and new ways to finish them. If you’ve never cross stitched before or feel a bit rusty, our new easy-to-follow diagrams and guides will help you pick up the technique quickly and have you hooked right from the word go. Get ready to be inspired!\n', '', '', ''),
(951, 1, 'What Hi-Fi Sound And Vision?', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO What Hi-Fi Sound and Vision? Magazine?\n\nSubscribe to What Hi-Fi Sound and Vision, the world’s best selling home entertainment magazine. Every month What Hi-Fi brings you the latest news and hottest reviews of all the best TVs, HiFi’s, Headphones and more providing you with expert and independent advice to ensure you get the best kit for your cash and make the most of your favorite music, movies and games.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNews and reviews on separates, systems and home cinema keep the hi-fi follower up-to-date with the latest products to hit the shops. What Hi Fi Sound Vision is the UK''s biggest hi fi and home entertainment magazine. Every issue gives you expert advice on how to save money and get the best equipment for your cash to ensure that you get the best out of your movies and music.What Hi-Fi Sound &amp; Vision Magazine includes authoritative and independent reviews on all latest home entertainment products. It comes with excellent reviews about latest Televisions, home cinema, accessories, Hi-Fi, portable, digital TV boxes and lots more. What Hi-Fi Sound and Vision magazine is a perfect guide as well as true companion of all who have passion for home entertainment products.What Hi-Fi Sound and Vision magazine is the perfect companion for technology enthusiasts. Subscribe today!\n', '', '', ''),
(952, 1, 'Cross Stitch Collection', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Cross Stitch Collection magazine is ideal for anyone who wants to work with the world’s most beautiful, classic designs. Cross Stitch Collection aims to present its readers with inspiring cross stitch projects from Britain’s best designers, with high value, top quality charts. Cross Stitch Collections designs will whisk you away to another world where large designs, in traditional, artistic styles, always have a special home. We also bring you all the latest news, reviews and advice from the wonderful world of cross stitch, plus unmissable giveaways. Cross Stitch Collections standards are based on strict accuracy and attention to detail. Every project includes clear step by step instructions for stitchers of all abilities. Editorial features include: News, letters, giveaways, kit and product reviews, advice, competitions, technical features. Also designer interviews, columns, features and club reviews. A subscription to Cross Stitch Collection Magazine has designs guaranteed to please stitchers from beginner to advanced.\n', '', '', ''),
(953, 1, 'Simply Crochet', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSimply Crochet is a brand new magazine from the maker of Simply Knitting and Mollie Makes. This new monthly instalment celebrates the best of the best when it comes to crochet, it is packed with new designs, photos and advice on you crochet projects. Plus a free gift with every issue!', '', '', ''),
(954, 1, 'Papercraft Essentials', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Papercraft Essentials Magazine?\n\nEvery issue of this magazine arrives with 100 pages of creative card-making ideas to keep you occupied throughout the month. With regular Masterclass features from their talented Design Team, as well as a handy Cut Out &amp; Keep pullout, a subscription to Papercraft Essentials prepares you with all the tools you need to make the perfect card for any anniversary, birthday or wedding. Two free gifts are included in every copy to help you on your way to making professional looking cards at home, and you can pick up lots of new crafting skills along the way with their easy-to-follow step-by-step guides.  From simple cards you can make in an evening to elaborate crafting projects, this magazine has card suggestions to suit all levels of experience.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Papercraft Essentials magazine subscription shows you how to create fun cards in a flash!Every month it gives you:• 100 pages of bright ideas• Dozens of fun card designs you can make in an evening!• Step-by-step, illustrated guides — master all the techniques!• Two fantastic FREE gifts — boost your stash.Published thirteen times annually Papercraft Essential magazine gives you great inspirational ideas, latest news, product launches, step by step instructions and top tips and guidance from those who know how.Papercraft Essential is a must have subscription for anyone who likes to demonstrate their creativity through making their own beautiful cards. Papercraft Essentials is a great gift for anyone who likes to fill their sparee time making cards.Subscribe to Papercraft Essentials magazine and get the creative injection you need.\n', '', '', ''),
(955, 1, 'Simply Cards &amp; Papercraft', 'WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Simply Cards &amp; Papercraft Magazine?\n\nWith plenty of helpful how-tos in each issue, this crafts magazine has loads of ideas for fabulous cards that you can start making right away, regardless of previous experience. Simply Cards &amp; Paperwork is divided into different easy-to-follow sections, with suggestions for a huge variety of cards covering everything from your parents'' anniversary to Valentine''s Day or your vintage-obsessed friend''s birthday. You''ll love the suggestions for simple but charming handmade gifts to accompany your cards, and you''ll receive a freebie in each issue to help replenish your collection of paper, stickers, glitter and everything else you need.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSimply Cards &amp; Papercraft magazine shows you how to create stylish and beautiful cards for every occasion — cards that will light up the faces of your loved ones!\n', '', '', ''),
(956, 1, 'Simply Homemade', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Simply Homemade Magazine?\n\nThis magazine comes with loads of arty ideas to help you bring back old skills as well as learn some new ones.\n\nWith a subscription to Simply Homemade magazine, you''ll get expert tips on a variety of creative hobbies, all explained in easy, bite-sized guides.\n\nThis craft magazine uses helpful photographs to guide you through the most intricate projects, and has contributions from stylish brands including Cath Kidston, Amy Butler Fabrics and Emma Bridgewater Designs.\n\nYou''ll get great suggestions for projects from cushions to jewellery to baking, so you''ll have plenty to keep you busy making your home beautiful every month.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSimply Homemade is the essential magazine for creative minds, with beautiful and stylish projects for papercrafters, seamstresses, knitters and beaders. It also features craft hobbies which are often neglected, such as soapmaking, candlemaking and feltmaking. Covering stylish brands such as Cath Kidston, Amy Butler Fabrics and Emma Bridgewater Designs, and adding a pinch of recipes, baking ideas and homestyle tips and advice, Simply Homemade is a treasure trove of beautiful projects for gifts and your home.\n', '', '', ''),
(957, 1, 'The Knitter', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The Knitter Magazine?\n\nYou''ll love the fantastic new patterns and designer inspirations in The Knitter magazine.\n\nEvery issue includes original, exciting patterns that are as enjoyable to create as they are to admire once complete.\n\nThis knitting and sewing magazine is perfect for you if you know the knitting basics already and are keen to stretch yourself with some more ambitious projects.\n\nTaking its cues from current fashion trends, The Knitter includes features on everything from vintage 50s style to making statement lace and sequin embellished pieces, as well as tips on how to make best use of online resources like Pinterest for inspiration.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to The Knitter magazine caters for skilled knitters with more than 10 challenging patterns in each issue. The Knitter magazine is the UK’s first quality, collectable knitting magazine. It has beautiful, original patterns, inspiring ideas from top knitwear designers and new techniques even an experienced knitter would like to try. Every issue also caters for skilled knitters with challenging patterns. The patterns aren’t just fabulous to look at, they’re enjoyable to make, with a few unusual techniques and intriguing ways with yarns for you to try. The Knitter magazine regularly features beautiful, original patterns and inspiration from world-class designers. Here''s what you''ll find in The Knitter: - Gorgeous, original designs? - Inspiring ideas from top knitwear designers - NEW techniques and ways with yarn\n', '', '', ''),
(958, 1, 'Rcm&amp;E', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO RCM&amp;E Magazine?\n\nWith information on everything from engine choice to in-air acrobatics, anyone who enjoys radio controlled modelling and engineering should sign up for this great magazine.\n\nRCM&amp;E is full of practical tips and tricks, easy-to-read guides and entertaining and opinionated comments from seasoned experts.\n\nWith your subscription to RCM&amp;E magazine you''ll get a free high-quality plan every month, with an accompanying build article, making it easy to get started on an impressive collection of remote controlled planes.\n\nYou''ll also be introduced to a welcoming group of fellow modellers, with regular events for readers up and down the country.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to RCM&amp;E magazine is an essential purchase for any model aeroplane enthusiast.Radio Control Models and Electronics first appeared in May 1960 and has grown to become the UK''s biggest and best selling monthly model flying magazine.RCM&amp;E has brought benchmark levels of writing and photography to the hobby and each issue has extensive reviews, informative features and opinionated columns from a number of well known contributors.With every issue you''ll find a high-quality free plan along with an accompanying build article. RCM&amp;E covers all the important issues within the absorbing hobby of radio control model aircraft and is published monthly by MyHobbyStore Media.\nPurchase a subscription today and receive your monthly fix of everything model plane related.\n', '', '', ''),
(959, 1, 'Papercrafter', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Papercrafter Magazine?\n\nIf you''ve ever wanted to learn how to master decorative techniques like decoupage and quilling, a subscription to Papercrafter magazine will teach you a host of new skills.Each issue comes with a variety of neat ideas for projects to get your creative juices flowing, ranging from card making and embossing to papercutting and designing elegant invitations for events.Step-by-step how-to guides help to make the learning process easier, and when you subscribe to Papercrafter you''ll receive a complete papercraft kit worth £14.99 and a 32-page Studio Selection Paper Book, making this magazine great value for money.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPapercrafter is a must-buy mag for makers who adore all things paper, offering everything you need to create cards and paper craft projects in one package.\n\nPapercrafter comes with beautiful kits and paper books that are designed by a different illustrator every issue, giving projects a fresh new look and providing inspiration with every purchase.\n', '', '', ''),
(960, 1, 'Make &amp; Craft', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Make &amp; Craft Magazine?\n\nMake &amp; Craft is packed full of exciting and inventive project ideas to keep you busy on rainy days, accompanied by easy-to-follow tutorials. Up-and-coming crafts are included as well as traditional techniques, so you''re sure to find something new to try. Alongside advice from Anthea Turner, the Face of Create and Craft TV’s ‘Get Britain Crafting’ campaign, you''ll also find reviews of the latest tools, books and supplies. This craft magazine also provides a great way to get involved with the Crafting Community, with a guide to crafting events around the UK included in each edition.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPLEASE NOTE- The £15 and £25 options are a DIGITAL magazine, delivered via email.\n\nWelcome to Make &amp; Craft magazine, a creative hub for the craft community packed with inspiration, crafty tips, creative tricks and exciting ideas.\n\nMake &amp; Craft magazine is an inspiring environment featuring contemporary tutorials and projects using a wide variety of crafts, supplies and techniques, as well as, reviving traditional crafts worth cherishing.\n\nMake &amp; Craft magazine also brings you the latest trends, up to date products, craft books and supplies, new techniques, sneak peeks behind the scenes of artists and crafters, the best online sites, headline news, a diary of craft events and a whole host of competition and giveaways.\n\nThe digital version of Make and Craft magazine is readable on any computer or mobile device. The support of Flash and HTML5 technologies allows Make and Craft to be readable on mobile phones (iPhone and Android) and tablets (iPad and Android). And the support of HTML provides access to information for those who use mobile phones of previous generations.\n', '', '', ''),
(961, 1, 'Airfix Model World', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Airfix Model World Magazine?\n\nWhether you''re new to scale modelling or are an experienced hobbyist, this monthly mag has all the info you need to improve your craft.\n\nThis modelling magazine is particularly focused on model aircraft, but it also covers ships, cars, military models and more.\n\nWith a subscription to Airfix Model World magazine, you’ll regularly receive step-by-step tutorials and handy tips to help with your building and painting. You''ll also get impartial reviews of the latest re-issues and releases, as well as updates on upcoming modelling events across the country.\n\nPlus, thanks to the mag''s regular ‘Ask the Experts’ section, you can write in to make sure you’re staying on the right track to modelling success.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPublished monthly, Airfix Model World magazine is your complete guide to the world of scale modelling, making it essential reading for modellers with all levels of experience. Focusing on model aircraft; Airfix Model World also features cars, ships, sci-fi and space, armour and figures. Airfix Model World brings you the latest news, reviews and handy step-by-step tips, plus the chance to ''Ask the Experts'' to improve your modelling skills.\n', '', '', ''),
(962, 1, 'Quiet And Electric Flight International', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA combination of electric flight and gliding, bringing you advice and assistance in all areas for both beginners and experts alike.\n', '', '', ''),
(963, 1, 'Beads &amp; Beyond', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Beads &amp; Beyond Magazine?\n\nSubscribe to Beads &amp; Beyond magazine for a wealth of inspiration to get you creating beautiful jewellery in no time. Crammed with photos, guides and articles, each issue will show you how to make your own beaded jewellery and crafts, guiding you step-by-step with easy to follow instructions. The magazine covers a range of different techniques for beginners as well as experts, so there''s always something new to work on. Whether you want to perfect your skills as a hobby or plan to sell your creations, you’ll find the inspiration and know-how to make countless different pieces inside.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBeads &amp; Beyond Magazine is a monthly publication filled with gorgeous jewellery and beaded makes. It is for designers and crafters who want to learn how to create their own jewellery. Whether you are a hobbyist or a designer, you''re sure to find lots of projects to inspire you.\n', '', '', ''),
(964, 1, 'Marine Modelling International', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Marine Modelling International Magazine?\n\nEach issue of this modelling magazine has loads of fantastic features on everything from equipment reviews and building specialist models from scratch to the most popular maritime themed shows from around the world.\n\nA subscription to Marine Modelling International magazine also gives you access to regular articles on topics such as electronics, scale model building, racing yachts, plastic kits and internal combustion-powered models.\n\nYou''ll get inspiration on making different boats as diverse as historic warships and submarines, and with free plans frequently included in the magazine you''re sure to find a new project to tackle, whether you''ve been modelling for years or are just getting into the hobby.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMarine Modelling International is a monthly magazine with 76 pages covering all aspects of maritime modelling, with a free plan inserted every quarter.\n', '', '', ''),
(965, 1, 'Model Helicopter World', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Model Helicopter World Magazine?\n\nFocusing entirely on the world of radio-controlled model helicopters, this magazine makes an ideal read for anyone who wants regular information on events, repairs and new models and equipment. In each issue of this modelling magazine, you''ll find articles on topics like scale building, competition flying and the club scene, as well as readers'' letters sharing questions, issues and advice. On top of this, with a subscription to Model Helicopter World magazine you''ll get a regular column all the way from the USA, tips on repairing and maintaining your helicopter, and a shoppers'' directory and loads of classifieds to help you source and sell models and parts.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nModel Helicopter World is the world''s biggest magazine devoted to Radio Controlled Model Helicopters. It is highly respected throughout the world for its technical and broad-based content. Every issue is packed with regular columns on all aspects of the sport including scale building and flying, competition flying, electric models, 3D flying, and of course the club scene. Reviews of the latest models and equipment are included in every issue along with a regular column from the USA, and event reports from across the World.\n', '', '', ''),
(966, 1, 'Sewing World', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Sewing World Magazine?\n\nIf you''re looking for a fresh sewing project to sink your teeth into, a subscription to Sewing World magazine can provide you with plenty of fantastic ideas.\n\nEach issue comes with a variety of monthly ''makes'', ranging from simple shift dresses to kimono-style robes and clutch bags, accompanied by how-to guides on handling different types of fabric and mastering complex techniques.\n\nYou''ll also find interviews with textile and fashion designers in each issue for a professional perspective, plus a ''Bookshelf'' feature that recommends the best pattern books and textile-related reads to add to your collection.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSewing World is devoted to inspirational makes, including projects showing how to make bags, garments and accessories, home furnishings, children’s clothes and stitched gifts.\n\nSewing World Magazine is a colourful, jam-packed, monthly magazine for people who love to sew with their machine, or want to learn. Every issue is filled with exciting projects, sewing tips and techniques , ''how-to'' hints, book reviews, show news, new product information and of course feature articles on people and places involved in sewing.\n', '', '', ''),
(967, 1, 'Parchment Craft', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nParchment Craft magazine remains the only publication of its kind anywhere in the world making it the premier choice for enthusiasts who demand the full diversity of their chosen subject.\n\nA global team of widely respected editorial contributors bring a broad range of parchment ideas, patterns and techniques every month presenting possibilities with new products as well as traditional methods including white work embossing and working with different colouring mediums.\n', '', '', ''),
(968, 1, 'Railway Modeller', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Railway Modeller Magazine?\n\nThis brilliant magazine was established in 1949, so with a subscription to Railway Modeller you''ll know for certain you''re getting the benefit of several years of experience and accurate first-hand descriptions. You will get detailed scale drawings and layout plans, along with easy-to-follow ''how-to'' guides for creating your own models. If you are new to the game, you''ll be well looked after with this magazine - every issue has a special section for novice modellers, as well as reviews of the newest products and up-to-date news. If you''re looking to meet some fellow fans, you''ll also find an extensive diary of railway modellers events around the UK.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nRailway Modeller is the UK''s No1 model railway magazine.\n\nEvery month it features the best from the hobby for those modelling Britain''s railways in all the popular scales and offers a unique blend of articles by experts and beginners alike, including a special section for newcomers wanting to learn all about the hobby and model making in general.\n\nEach issue includes featured layouts, scale drawings, layout plans, shows-you-how constructional articles and prototype surveys. Plus all the regular sections; product reviews, up-to-the-minute news, book reviews, reader''s letters and the UK''s most comprehensive model railway events diary.\n', '', '', ''),
(969, 1, 'Burda Style', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWritten in English but published in Germany, BURDA STYLE is a beautifully laid out magazine with over 40 patterns in each issue that offers a whole world of fashion for the hobbyist.\n\nAll patterns are rated by sewing expertise and there is something for everyone, from the beginner to expert.\n\nBURDA STYLE brings the craft of sewing to a new generation of fashion designers, hobbyists and DIYers as well as inspiring fashion enthusiasts.\n', '', '', ''),
(970, 1, 'Rcm&amp;E', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO RCM&amp;E Magazine?\n\nWith information on everything from engine choice to in-air acrobatics, anyone who enjoys radio controlled modelling and engineering should sign up for this great magazine.\n\nRCM&amp;E is full of practical tips and tricks, easy-to-read guides and entertaining and opinionated comments from seasoned experts.\n\nWith your subscription to RCM&amp;E magazine you''ll get a free high-quality plan every month, with an accompanying build article, making it easy to get started on an impressive collection of remote controlled planes.\n\nYou''ll also be introduced to a welcoming group of fellow modellers, with regular events for readers up and down the country.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to RCM&amp;E magazine is an essential purchase for any model aeroplane enthusiast.Radio Control Models and Electronics first appeared in May 1960 and has grown to become the UK''s biggest and best selling monthly model flying magazine.RCM&amp;E has brought benchmark levels of writing and photography to the hobby and each issue has extensive reviews, informative features and opinionated columns from a number of well known contributors.With every issue you''ll find a high-quality free plan along with an accompanying build article. RCM&amp;E covers all the important issues within the absorbing hobby of radio control model aircraft and is published monthly by MyHobbyStore Media.\nPurchase a subscription today and receive your monthly fix of everything model plane related.\n', '', '', ''),
(971, 1, 'Military Modelling', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Military Modelling Magazine?\n\nThis modelling magazine has loads of information on everything in the military model world.\n\nYou''ll not only find regular product and kit reviews in the popular ''Atten-Shun!'' section, but you''ll also read reports of recent events in the modelling calendar.\n\nFrom vehicles like tanks and helicopters to distinguished officers from the army, navy and airforce, a subscription to Military Modelling magazine offers you guides to applying paints, decals and transfers to your favourite models.\n\nIn every issue, there are also tips on preparing model scenic accessories, plus roundups of new military kit releases, covering vehicles from 1:35 scale to 1:76 and figurines from 54mm to 120mm.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Military Modelling is the ideal read for anyone with a passion for historic military model figures.Military Modelling magazine is the longest established, quality hobby title for what is the niche pastime that we now term ‘military modelling’, which from its early beginnings in the early 1930s in the UK, when modellers began to alter and repaint children’s and collectors’ lead toy soldiers into miniature works of art. The hobby of modelling military figures from these early days established itself into a popular pastime developing slowly after the Second World War into what was virtually an ‘explosion’ in the late 1960s and on into the 1970s into the hobby we know today.The Military Modelling magazine’s content falls into two major interests, making models of military vehicles, tanks, armoured cars, and trucks from throughout history and modelling miniature figures. We push the envelope to include occasional features on battlefield helicopters and maritime coastal craft, the odd warship and submarine. There are articles in each issue on model making and studies of the real soldiers and military equipment from all periods of history.Subscribe to Military Modelling magazine today and receive your monthly fix from your favorite hobby.Military Modelling magazine’s ‘supporting items’ are news, views, model show reports, readers’ letters, product, book and visual media reviews … • The Latest News and Reviews in Military Modelling • Every issue, Delivered conveniently to your door for FREE • View the full range of content on www.militarymodelling.com • Gain access to the complete back catalogue of Military Modelling Magazine Digital Editions\n', '', '', ''),
(972, 1, 'Quilt Now', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nDiscover the brand-new magazine for quilting enthusiasts.\n\nIf you adore quilting and patchwork and love contemporary fabric then Quilt Now is your perfect companion. Each issue of Quilt Now is filled with beautiful quilting projects and patchwork techniques from some of the leading experts worldwide.\n\nProduced by quilters for quilters, every issue showcases stunning quilting projects, from full-size bed quilts to lap quilts, cushions, bags and accessories, all using the latest, widely available fabrics and stash-friendly scraps. You''ll find inspiring ideas for refreshing your home decor plus great gifts and fun quick-make creations.\n\nEvery issue comes with free gifts too, including essential quilting tools, sewing project kits and much more!\n\nWhether you''re a complete beginner or a skilled quilter, every issue will inspire and introduce new techniques and fabrics to kick-start your next project. Why wait? Get Quilt Now.\n\nWhy subscribe?\n• Never miss an issue\n• Free delivery direct to your door\n• Be the first to read Quilt Now\n• Save money on every issue\n• Every issue includes a FREE gift worth over £5\n• FREE access to the VIP lounge – exclusive craft offers, projects, downloads and more!\n\nNever miss an issue of Quilt Now!\n\nBuy a subscription to Quilt Now magazine for you or a friend today.\n', '', '', ''),
(973, 1, 'Mollie Makes', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Mollie Makes Magazine?\n\nIf you''re forever searching the internet for the coolest new craft ideas, you''ll love having them all delivered directly to your front door with a subscription to Mollie Makes magazine.\n\nIn each issue, you''ll find dozens of offers, hints, and tricks to help you customise, embellish, and personalise your handmade projects, with guidance from the pros in each field.\n\nYou can enjoy travel features on the most creative cities around, and step-by-step guides on how to kick start a new project or a business venture.\n\nWith this craft magazine, you''ll learn how to make clothes, toys and cakes so perfectly people won''t believe you did it all yourself.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Mollie Makes , the lifestyle and craft magazine that focuses on contemporary fabric crafts. Mollie Makes is not just a traditional craft project-book, but a magazine which celebrates craft as a part of life; curating the best contemporary craft content from around the world into a beautiful, collectible, unique and totally irresistible magazine. Mollie Makes Magazine is aimed at the new generation of crafters providing a mix of unique editorial, first-class design, beautiful production values and with innovative cover gifts this magazine is an irresistible, must-have for anyone with a passion for handmade.\n', '', '', ''),
(974, 1, 'Knit Now', 'WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Knit Now Magazine?\n\nFor crafters looking for a quick project, Knit Now is the ideal choice, offering a variety of simple, stylish designs that can be completed within a few days with a relatively small amount of yarn. A subscription to Knit Now magazine gives you access to interviews with established knitting pros and step-by-step technique tutorials from resident knitting guru Debbie Tomkies. In each issue you''ll also find yarn reviews from fellow knitters, trend guides and catwalk-inspired patterns, as well as chic accessory ''one ball knits'' and great reader giveaways and offers.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nKnit Now magazine is packed with stylish designs for the modern knitter. It covers a wide variety of techniques with clear step-by-step instructions and expert hints and tips.\n\nWhat’s more, each issue features interviews with hot, new and established designers, tried and tested yarns, online and high street inspirations as well as all the very latest news, views and things to buy.\n\nEach issue features exclusive free gifts worth over £5 plus exclusive discounts on top yarn brands\n\nEvery month it brings you:\n• 100 pages of inspirational ideas\n• Step-by-step, illustrated guides — master all the techniques!\n• Hot product news — keep up with the latest knitting trends!\n• A fabulous FREE gift worth £5 — boost your stash!', '', '', ''),
(975, 1, 'The English Home', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The English Home Magazine?\n\nCelebrating quintessential English style in all its glory, The English Home magazine showcases beautifully classic, elegant and country interiors alongside design and buying advice from world acclaimed designers. Add to this quintessential traditions, seasonal recipes and explorations of our most breath taking regions and the result is a gloriously evocative, engaging and insightful read to savour and refer to again and again. The English Home is published 12 times a year.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to The English Home magazine subscription is perfect for anyone looking for a little luxury within their home.\n\nThe English Home is the leading international magazine of English style! The magazine features luxurious furnishings, exquisite antiques, stylish interiors … wonderful photography and expert advice from top British designers.\n\nAn English Home magazine subscription celebrates the quintessential English style with all its glory.\n\nThe English Home magazine features beautifully classic, elegant and country interiors alongside design and buying advice from world acclaimed designers.\n\nThe magazine is also full of seasonal recipes and explorations of England’s most breath taking regions and as a result the magazine is gloriously evocative, engaging and an insightful read to savour and refer to again and again…\n', '', '', ''),
(976, 1, 'Kitchen Garden', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Kitchen Garden Magazine?\n\nWhy should you buy a subscription?\n\nThis magazine takes the hard work out of growing your own fruit and veg at home, with hundreds of useful tips on everything from how to handle garden pests, to picking the best seasonal seeds.\n\nYou''ll also find dozens of practical and inspiring features in each issue of a Kitchen Garden magazine subscription, as well as loads of fun competitions with a number of exciting green-fingered prizes.\n\nThere''s also a number of tasty recipes to help you take your produce from the garden to the plate, plus interviews with local food producers from around the UK to help you get creative with your planting.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nKitchen Garden is Britain’s best guide to growing your own. It offers down-to-earth advice from the finest minds in gardening to make sure you get the tastiest produce from your plot.There are tips on how to grow a wide range of fruit and vegetable crops and how to control troublesome pests plus what to do on your plot each month.Also buying guides, recipes and inspirational garden visits. Gardeners up and down the country share their experiences of sowing, growing and harvesting and every month KG has prizes and offers that could save you a fortune on a range of gardening essentials.\n', '', '', ''),
(977, 1, 'Grow Your Own', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Grow Your Own Magazine?\n\nIf you’re a keen gardener then you''ll love this easy to read magazine, which is packed with great tips on how to grow your own fruit and veg.\n\nThere''s plenty to keep you inspired and engaged, with hints and tips from industry experts to help you make the most of your space, regardless of its size.\n\nGrow Your Own magazine offers hands-on and practical advice from experienced gardeners, as well as a number of competitions and discount vouchers to get you saving money on everything from the latest equipment to your next set of seeds.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Grow Your Own magazine is ideal for anyone and everyone who produces their own fruit and vegetables in their own garden or allotment. Grow Your Own magazine leads you into the exciting world of self-sufficiency whether you are a novice or experienced grower. Each magazine provides helpful advice and pointers from the industry experts. Grow Your Own magazine is packed with growing tips and ideas for gardeners of all abilities, from window box-growers to allotment plot-holders. Grow Your Own is a real treat as well as essential reading. By subscribing to Grow Your Own, you will receive a monthly indispensable guide to all you need to know to start living the good life today. Plus! With regular free seeds and plenty of discounts from top brands, you''ll keep on saving those pounds.\n', '', '', ''),
(978, 1, 'Coast', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Coast Magazine?\n\nIf the thought of a calming sea breeze, a long cliff-top stroll, or a picnic by the waves brings a smile to your face, then a Coast magazine subscription is the perfect addition to your reading list. With thoughtful features on different coastal locations from around the UK, each issue is packed with ideas and inspiration for coastal breaks, as well as sneak peeks into some of the best coastal properties in the country. This magazine has everything you need to plan your perfect &quot;staycation&quot; beach break, plus tips on how to bring some seaside style into your own home.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nBring that blue-sky, sea-breeze feeling into your home every month with a subscription to Coast magazine. Published by Country Living Magazine, Coast is the perfect read for anyone who lives by the sea or dreams of a beach house of their own. A subscription to Coast magazine celebrates all that is unique about Britain’s coastline, every month. Coast Magazine is one of the UK''s best-selling magazines. Within every issue of a subscription to Coast, the magazine offers you lots of fantastic tips on homes, travel, food, property, gardens and much, much more. A subscription to Coast magazine is the natural choice for those of us who feel the draw of the beautiful, peaceful and cathartic properties of Britain’s coastline. Don’t resist temptation, take out a subscription to Coast magazine today.\n', '', '', ''),
(979, 1, 'Icon', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTo celebrate Icon''s 10th Anniversary we are offering you a 50% saving on your subscription. Plus all subscribers can opt in to free access to the digital version by visiting the Icon website. Icon is the essential international architecture and design magazine. Every month a subscription to Icon magazine brings you interviews with the most exciting architects and designers and brings you the best in new buildings and design. Each issue of a subscription to Icon magazine analyses the most interesting cultural movements and technologies and reviews a range of exhibitions, books, films and events. Beautifully presented, rigorous and insightful, Icon magazine goes in depth to get under the skin of design culture. It explores exactly what''s happening today, and what it means for the future. For the global picture, read Icon. A subscription to Icon magazine is an indispensable tool for the architecture and design community and the design literate individual. Plus, every subscriber can apply for free access to the digital version at Icon online.\n', '', '', '');
