(980, 1, 'Bbc Gardeners'' World', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO BBC Gardeners'' World Magazine?\n\nWhy buy a subscription?\n\nThis magazine is one of Britain''s best-selling gardening magazines, providing you with a bunch of handy tips and tricks to use in your own space. If you struggle to find the inspiration to create your very own garden paradise, then you''ll love the range of detailed feature pieces and behind-the-scenes trips into some of the most well-designed gardens in the world.\n\nYou''ll also find dozens of interviews with leading green-fingered professionals, including the BBC''s own Monty Don,and television favourite Alan Titchmarsh, as well as a range of easy-to-follow how-to guides to help you bring your garden to life.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to BBC Gardeners’ World magazine is just what any gardening enthusiast needs in their life. It contains everything that you love about the television show, but in a glossy magazine that arrives directly to your door, every month! It’s the only magazine that features advice from the world’s biggest gardening experts, such as Monty Don, Alan Titchmarsh and Carol Klein and that’s why BBC Gardeners’ World is Britain’s best-selling gardening magazine. As a subscriber not only will you get the fantastic content inside every issue – practical gardening tips, inspiration from the most beautiful gardens around the world, design ideas and insightful features – but you’ll also get added extras, such as membership to the Gardeners’ World Subscriber Club, special subscriber editions, a quarterly newsletter and subscriber-only offers. There’s no better time to buy a BBC Gardeners’ World magazine subscription!\n', '', '', ''),
(981, 1, 'Garden Design Journal', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Garden Design Journal Magazine?\n\nThis unique gardening magazine will keep you up to date with all the latest garden showcases, industry news and up and coming designers, as well as guides on how to turn your garden into a true work of art. Published by the Society of Garden Designers, a Garden Design Journal magazine subscription will give you expert advice on everything from artistic planting to the latest must have tools, plus a whole range of ethical and sustainable design ideas to use in your own space. You''ll also got an unrivalled insight into some of the most beautiful public and private gardens in the world, helping to inspire your horticulture exploits.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Garden Design Journal is essential for anyone involved or interested in the subject. Garden Design Journal is the only publication in the UK dedicated solely to garden design. The magazine is both inspirational and educative and showcases the very best of garden design, in public and private gardens at home and abroad.\nEvery monthly issue features beautiful photography and concise, clear presentation of information and is packed with: •technical advice, techniques and best practices •plants in design •a round up of the latest ''must haves'' •garden showcases •sustainable, environmental &amp; ethical design options •events reports •industry news &amp; comments •designer profiles •book reviews and... much, much more! Subscribe to Garden Design Journal today and save up to 25% on the normal cover price with free postage and packing for all UK orders. If you decide that GDJ is not for you, simply cancel and receive a full refund on all unmailed issues.\n', '', '', ''),
(982, 1, 'Homebuilding &amp; Renovating', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIf you are considering or in the middle of renovating, extending, converting or building you own home then a subscription to Homebuilding &amp; Renovating magazine is an essential purchase for you. A subscription to Homebuilding &amp; Renovating magazine provides you with a regular dose of inspiration and practical advice for your project. A Homebuilding &amp; Renovating magazine subscription brings you a Beginner’s Guide section in every magazine, with advice on finding the finance, build costs, insurance and planning to help you get started. A Homebuilding &amp; Renovating magazine subscription also includes every month around 50 pages of reader case studies with their story and tips, houseplans, costs and contacts, special features from DIY and step-by-step guides to how managing your contractors and advice on how to complete your project on time and within budget. Homebuilding &amp; Renovating also runs six shows every year. The Homebuilding &amp; Renovating show is Britain’s number one self build show, where you can literally find every product and service needed for self build and home improvement all under one roof.\n', '', '', ''),
(983, 1, 'House &amp; Garden', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO House &amp; Garden Magazine?\n\nA subscription to House and Garden magazine is a great way to find leading home design ideas and lifestyle suggestions.Each issue is filled with photos of beautiful homes and gardens, from fabulous high rise apartments and renovated country barns to breathtaking water gardens and pretty urban courtyards.This monthly home improvement magazine gives you plenty of advice on how to update your own home, regardless of its size, condition or location.But the tips don’t stop with just the décor; House and Garden magazine also brings you delicious recipes, recommendations on fine wines, and reviews of stunning travel destinations.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA SUBSCRIPTION TO HOUSE &amp; GARDEN MAGAZINE BRINGS YOU THE DEFINITIVE GUIDE TO STYLISH LIVING STRAIGHT TO YOU DOOR EVERY MONTH. House &amp; Garden magazine unlocks the door to an international array of unique homes and outdoor features, ranging from town houses, to converted barns and fabulous apartments to island retreats. Outdoor features are equally varied, including cottage gardens, water gardens and chic, city courtyards. House &amp; Garden provides an invaluable sourcebook of ideas, from design and decoration to the best of travel, delicious recipes and fine wine. First launched in the US in 1901 as an architectural journal, the magazine was bought out in 1915, becoming one of Condé Nast’s publishing empire. House &amp; Garden magazine was transformed into the magazine about interior design that we recognize today, as part of Condé Nast’s drive to create specialized publications aimed a niche markets.\n', '', '', ''),
(984, 1, '25 Beautiful Homes', '&lt;p&gt;WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO 25 Beautiful Homes Magazine? Take a tour of Britain’s most beautiful and stylish properties from the comfort of your own home, with a 25 Beautiful Homes magazine subscription. Each issue is brimming with gorgeous images of simple, stylish and successful home décor ideas from real-life families, showcasing some of the most effective interior design projects from across the UK. This magazine will give you the inspiration you need to kick-start your own interior renovation, with stunning photographs showing you how to do it right. You''ll discover the best cottages, mansions and farmhouses in Britain and hear from the designers behind their distinctive style. FROM THE PUBLISHER Celebrating the UK''s love of home interiors is the passion of 25 Beautiful Homes. Full of decorating ideas and home interior advice, 25 Beautiful Homes will help you create the home of your dreams. Every month be inspired by a fantastic mix of 25 real-life homes, from apartments to farmhouses.&lt;/p&gt;\n', '', '', ''),
(985, 1, 'Garden Answers', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Garden Answers Magazine?\n\nThis magazine is a great choice if you love to spend time in the garden but need a bit more advice about creating and maintaining the perfect space.\n\nYou’ll find top tips on when to plant your seeds, how to cultivate unusual plant species, dealing with problems like pests and disease, and loads of advice on choosing the right tools and equipment.\n\nA Garden Answers magazine subscription will inspire you in the great outdoors, with in-depth features on celebrity gardeners and regular Q&amp;A''s with leading green-fingered experts, including Pippa Greenwood and Naomi Schillinger.\n\nThere''s also free seeds and competitions, plus guides on planting seasonal bulbs.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Garden Answers magazine will solve all your gardening problems! Garden answers is the most practical gardening monthly, however practicality is not the only aspect in which it differs to other magazines. It inspires, encourages and helps you to garden with a no-nonsense approach. You can trust our experts and our advice to help you get the most from your hobby. Garden Answers magazine is a respected and reliable source of information for individuals who love gardening as their hobby. Coming with detailed instructions and ideas on flower and bulb selection, Garden Answers magazine gives you great amount of information on caring of your garden, and bringing the right kind of plants to suit your garden. Gardens Answers magazine comes with garden maintenance tips which enthusiastic gardeners find incredibly interesting and highly motivating. This magazine is a one of a kind that gardeners across the UK will enjoy reading and trying out the suggestions of plants, flowers and seasonal maintenance routines.Subscribe to Garden Answers magazine today and have all of your questions answered.The Direct Debit Guarantee The minimum subscription term for the direct debit offer is 12 months. The amount paid by Direct Debit may change over time. If and when it does you will be notified in advance by at least 10 days. If an error is made by Bauer Media Ltd or by bank/building society, you are entitled to a full and immediate refund. You can cancel the Direct Debit at any time by writing to your bank/building society and send a copy to Bauer Media Ltd at: Magazine Subscriptions, Tower House, Sovereign Park, Market Harborough, Leicestershire LE94 7ZT. Please note that banks and building societies may not accept Direct Debit instructions from some types of account.\n', '', '', ''),
(986, 1, 'The English Garden', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The English Garden Magazine?\n\nThe English Garden takes its readers to incredible and yet achievable gardens with the use of brilliant photography and professional garden writers. This inspiration is backed up with practical notebooks with advice offered from the garden owner or head gardener. Readers hear from those with real gardening miles under their belts. It’s a real treat for anyone with greenfingers. The English Garden is published 13 times a year.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSubscribe to The English Garden magazine and be guaranteed to receive the UK’s leading Gardening magazine. With expert tips, advise and photography from the experts, this magazine will fill you with inspiration for your own garden. Each issue of The English Garden is overflowing with beautiful gardens from the length and breadth of the land - from traditional to modern and from tiny plots to rolling acres. The English Garden is the glossy magazine for everyone with an overflowing imagination for creating their own beautiful garden, providing you with inspiring ideas to transform your garden. Each issue brings you the very best in English gardening…seasonal planting tips…design ideas…expert practical guides...and month after month of glorious gardens.Whether your first love is spring flowers, the heady perfume of roses on a summer''s afternoon, the myriad colours of an autumn border, or even the structural beauty of winter, you will find it all in a English Garden magazine subscription.\n', '', '', ''),
(987, 1, 'Homemaker', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nHomemaker is a brand new print magazine full of creative ideas for your home. With projects, interiors, baking and more, there''s something for everyone seeking a beautiful living space. Expert tips, top buys and up-and-coming designers will keep readers up to date with the latest trends, and there''s plenty of gorgeous photography for creative inspiration too.\n', '', '', ''),
(988, 1, 'Home Review', 'Home Review helps you decide a theme in your bedroom, living room, dining and bath areas, using soft furnishings and fabrics that inspire.', '', '', ''),
(989, 1, 'Good Housekeeping', 'Chosen by over 58 million women across the globe since 1885, Good Housekeeping has all that you want, and more... Savour International and Indian recipes from the Good House keeping kitchens. Keep fit with up-to-date health articles for the entire family. Get practical advice from experts on Home Decor &amp; Modern Manners. Read up the latest in Fashion &amp; Fiction... This is the one magazine that''s Good till the last page. Send in your subscription request today... Don''t keep a good thing waiting!', '', '', ''),
(990, 1, 'Society Interiors', 'Society Interiors focusses on both functional and aesthetic aspects with a special focus on home interiors. Professionally written articles and reviews on relevant products offer useful insights for those who are trendy or are simply mulling over home renovation plans.', '', '', ''),
(991, 1, 'The Ideal Home And Garden', 'We are house proud. And home loving.And that''s what we are hoping The Ideal Home and Garden will reflect. The happiness, the contentment and the peace we talk about in the magazine are all part of the emotion we feel for our home. With work occupying cent ', '', '', ''),
(992, 1, 'Better Homes And Garden', 'Founded in 1922, Better Homes and Gardens magazine is dedicated to improving the lives of its readers through inspiring, informative and educational articles. Beyond the magazine, the Better Homes and Gardens brand extends to multiple platforms including books, special interest magazines, video and consumer products. Its Web site – www.bhg.com – reaches more than 4.5 million unique visitors each month.Better Homes and Gardens is America''s style leader for fresh, value-based, inspiring and refreshing ideas. It''s where decorating is made easy and fun. Better Homes and Gardens surpasses your expectations, surprises you with inspired decorating ideas, saves you money on projects large and small, showers you with the best and brightest ideas for your garden, your kitchen, your home and your life. Better Homes and Gardens is one of the largest selling titles in the United States, where it has a circulation base of 7.6 million and reaches 40 million readers each month. In terms of audience reach, BH&amp;G outsells both Time and Newsweek combined by more than a million numbers in the US. It also outsells the combined numbers sold by Cosmopolitan, Good Housekeeping, Vogue, Elle and Marie Claire in the US.On the occasion of International Women’s Day in March 2007, Media Transasia India launched one of America’s best-known women’s magazines, Better Homes and Gardens (BH&amp;G), India Edition, as a part of a licensing agreement with its US publishers Meredith Corporation. The English Edition BH&amp;G Launch issue is available on stands priced in line with its international premium positioning at Rs. 100. Better Homes and Gardens, is distinct, captivating, refreshing and very international. Its vibrant layouts, contemporary look and easy-to-navigate format are a sure-fire favourite with its readers. BH&amp;G is positioned at the stylish, urban young woman of today, who makes her own decisions, is savvy about what''s best for her home and family and seeks inspirational ideas for a more evolved lifestyle. BH&amp;G is her one-stop shop for all her needs concerning her home and environment. With a unique editorial mix that combines the best international and local inputs, the magazine covers a variety of appealing themes and issues that range from smart everyday solutions, decorating tips, outdoor living, health, family, food, fashion and in-depth features, all focusing on the woman and her environment. This unique blend gives us the rare distinction of being a complete women’s magazine all focusing on the woman and her environment. ', '', '', ''),
(993, 1, 'Hotel Business', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Hotel Business magazine is your complete guide to the hotel industry. Reporting on latest developments from the world of hotels, including in-room facilities, food and drink, new technology, and advice on increasing revenues and sales.Hotel Business includes interviews with top industry figures, shop previews &amp; reviews of new products plus service profiles.Hotel Business details about travel preferences, local laws, customer requirements, opening of new businesses, luxury travel and notifies its readers of hospitality events. Included in each of your 10 issues per subscription arethe views and opinions of top professionals from the hotel world, giving you the latest pulses from the industry.Subsribe to hotel business today and make your ‘Hotel Business’ a success!\n', '', '', ''),
(994, 1, 'Cw Interiors', 'CW INTERIORS India and Gulf’s first B2B Interiors Magazine, the focus of the magazine is to generate business leads, ideas and opportunities. The monthly publication presents timely, well packaged and extensive information on interior design and trends. It is an invaluable business tool for its readers which include Architects, Interior Designers, Builders, and Contractor.', '', '', ''),
(995, 1, 'Indian Cement Review', 'Indian Cement Review, the premier magazine catering exclusively to the cement industry, covers the latest updates and happenings of the industry from around the world. The magazine gives wide ranging technical articles, informative views of industry professionals, analysis and on-site case studies. It acts as a useful interface between the producers, manufacturers and the user fraternity of the cement industry, and is a must read magazine for the User industry, Manufacturers &amp; suppliers and Auxiliary services providers.', '', '', ''),
(996, 1, 'Cargo Talk', 'Cargotalk is South Asia’s leading monthly magazine catering to the requirements of logistics and supply chain industry. A podium for suppliers, users as well as service providers, the publication is the voice of the industry to raise issues for remedies. It’s also a right platform to display products &amp; services pertaining to complete logistics.', '', '', ''),
(997, 1, 'Digital Studio', 'Professionals based in the booming digital media production hubs across the country will enjoy this magazine both from a learning and application perspectives. Whether you are a broadcast, audio video or photography professional, you will find the magazine a prolific', '', '', ''),
(998, 1, 'Equipment India', 'EQUIPMENT INDIA is India’s first only magazine for the infrastructure equipment industry. It successfully addresses the needs of information of the infrastructure. Equipment India magazine it the most focused on marketing.', '', '', ''),
(999, 1, 'Indian Cement Review', 'Indian Cement Review, the premier magazine catering exclusively to the cement industry, covers the latest updates and happenings of the industry from around the world. The magazine gives wide ranging technical articles, informative views of industry professionals, analysis and on-site case studies. It acts as a useful interface between the producers, manufacturers and the user fraternity of the cement industry, and is a must read magazine for the User industry, Manufacturers &amp; suppliers and Auxiliary services providers.', '', '', ''),
(1000, 1, 'Power Today', 'POWER TODAY is an influential, well-read and respected magazine that provides all the news and information from the Indian and global power generation, transmission &amp; distribution sectors. Along with a comprehensive, in-depth and insightful analysis, Power Today brings to readers interviews with the who’s-who of the industry, policy analyses, project updates, statistics, technologies, features, key commercial developments and lots more.', '', '', ''),
(1001, 1, 'Manufacturing Today', 'Launched in October 2010 by ITP India, ‘Manufacturing Today’ continues with the Group’s tradition of providing a competitive ‘4i’ advantage to our readers (the industry) – the latest Information, cutting edge Intelligence, business enabling Insights as well as by helping them attract meaningful Investments. The key objective of this monthly B2B publication is to help the manufacturer in India excel and grow. Manufacturing Today clearly distinguishes itself with industry focussed editorial content that facilitates decision makers to take the right call. It stands out as a credible platform where industry issues are discussed and possible solutions are churned out. It not only informs but also analyses.The magazine highlights the latest and the relevant from the world of technology. Manufacturing Today focuses on use of technology for achieving the highest level of operational efficiencies and manufacturing excellence. While manufacturing industry hasn’t been as agile as some of other industries in India with regards to adoption of latest technology, the industry certainly has acquired momentum on this front – especially in the light of the economic downturn – as it gives a better real time lever for management to take informed business decisions. Manufacturing Today highlights such trends and best practices for the benefit of the industry by talking to the experts, the vendors and the adopters.Spectrum of industries covered: Automation, automotive, automotive components, aviation, chemicals, coatings, dies &amp; moulds, electronics &amp; electricals, EPC, equipment &amp; components manufacturing, heavy engineering, hydraulics &amp; pneumatics, logistics &amp; supply chain management, machine tools, maintenance &amp; safety, material handling, mechanical engineering, oil &amp; gas, plastics &amp; polymers, power, pumps &amp; valves, rubber, steel, ship building and so on.', '', '', ''),
(1002, 1, 'Coal Insights Magazine', 'Coal Insights is India''s premier and widely read monthly magazine on coal &amp; mining industry published by mjunction services ltd (A JV of Tata Steel and SAIL).It caters to the entire coal supply chain from mining to consumption. It tracks the coal market with special focus on India, &amp; covers production &amp; consumption reports, as well as dispatch and stocks at power plants.It covers a variety of topics including demand, supply, e-marketing, mining technology, imports, pricing and policy matters, logistics, infrastructure and clean coal initiative. It also covers the interviews of the decision makers of coal industry on a regular basis. ', '', '', ''),
(1003, 1, 'Steel Insights Magazine', 'Steel Insights is India''s premier and widely read monthly magazine on steel and metallurgical industry published by mjunction services ltd (A JV of Tata Steel and SAIL).It delves into the various facets of the domestic and global steel industry, such as market fundamentals, raw material price trends, price forecasts, upcoming projects, corporate updates and international trade and logistics issues.It also includes an incisive analysis of news on steel and allied industries, as well as expert opinions on relevant topics and interviews of industry stalwarts on a regular basis.', '', '', ''),
(1004, 1, 'Power Watch India', 'Power Watch India is not just another business magazine in the energy domain. A trade magazine with a difference, magazine consider it imperative to focus on what the industry has to say, rather than carry a unilateral view from the editorial perspective. Power Watch India (PWI) in view of the vast potential for growth in india''s rapadily expanding energy space .Power Watch India (PWI)- aimed at all stackholders in the energy space. The magazine will offer the latest information and updates. It will present monthly industry forecasts exploring many important issues facing the power industry including stories on different segments like: captive , thermal, renewables, IT, transmission and distribution, etc.', '', '', ''),
(1005, 1, 'Progressive Grocer', 'PROGRESSIVE GROCER has been the voice of the food retail industry for over 80 years in the USA. Serving a wide audience in the Indian market, Progressive Grocer India''s readers are top management at headquarters and top decision makers at store level. By anticipating, reporting and interpreting important data and trends, PROGRESSIVE GROCER fulfills its mission of identifying and highlighting insights and opportunity for leading grocery retailers, thereby accelerating brands and sales success for leading manufacturers\n', '', '', ''),
(1006, 1, 'Salon International', 'Salon International is a comprehensive and dynamic magazine about hair and beauty. This Italian magazine has been launched in India for the first time in December 2008. The magazine comes in a high prestige format with contributions by national and international hair stylists, aestheticians, architects and designers', '', '', ''),
(1007, 1, 'The Africa Report', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSubscribe to The Africa Report today and receive this exclusive African magazine direct to your door every other month.Included in a subscription to The Africa Report is articles on African politics, business, society and culture and is published by Groupe Jeune Afrique, leading pan African publisher for over 50 years.The Africa report calls upon the finest African and international journalists, renowned specialists on the continent’s politics, economy, industry and governance and in-the-field writers from every region, The Africa Report guarantees in-depth, on-the-ground reportage.If you are interested in Africa from a business and economic perspective, then this is the magazine subscription for you.Subscribe to The Africa Report today and be guaranteed to receive this unique publication 6 times per year.\n', '', '', ''),
(1008, 1, 'Waypoint Airmed &amp; Rescue', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Waypoint AirMed &amp; Rescue magazine is the definitive resource for the aeromedical and rescue industry. Combining a mix of news, lectures, industry debates, and technical papers, Waypoint is a one-stop shop for up-to-the minute knowledge on all things air rescue. Each issue of Waypoint AirMed &amp; Rescue magazine has the latest news on air ambulance providers, both fixed-wing and rotary, search and rescue operators, including coastguard services and the armed forces, and developments in avionics and ancillary equipment. Every issue also features dedicated coverage for medical crew, pilots, maintenance staff, police aviation, and fire and rescue aircraft. Subscribe to Waypoint AirMed &amp; Rescue magazine today.\n', '', '', ''),
(1009, 1, 'Gastrointestinal Nursing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nGastrointestinal Nursing is the UK’s leading journal exclusively dedicated to all gastrointestinal and stoma care nurses. It is a vital resource for anyone working in this fast-developing area of nursing who wants to further their career, develop their training and enhance their knowledge and skills in all areas of practice.\n\nSubscribe to Gastrointestinal Nursing today and benefit from:\n\n•Clinical reviews and articles written by experts, including the management of upper GI bleeds and emergency admissions, endoscopic mucosal resection of colonic polyps and early assessment of endoscopy patients\n•Features on key topics such as endoscopy, constipation, irritable bowel syndrome, gastro-oesophageal reflux disease, gastric cancer, faecal incontinence, Crohn’s disease and ulcerative colitis\n•The latest developments in practice and major research findings on areas such as patient involvement, new and alternative medicines and recent nursing innovations\n•Step-by-step guides to key clinical competencies in GI practiceNews from policy to practice, including updates on the E-endoscopy programme\n\nEach issue of Gastrointestinal Nursing is packed with peer-reviewed clinical, professional and educational articles covering all aspects of upper and lower gastrointestinal nursing practice. The journal features all the specialties in the field, including stoma care, endoscopy, IBD, nutrition, coloproctology and hepatobiliary nursing.\n', '', '', ''),
(1010, 1, 'The Veterinary Nurse', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe Veterinary Nurse is a clinical, professional and educational journal created especially for enthusiastic veterinary nurses looking to extend their knowledge in the field. This international peer-reviewed journal written by fellow veterinary nurses covers the full range of therapeutic areas and topics, including education, clinical, practical and management issues.\n\nSubscribe to The Veterinary Nurse today and benefit from:\n\n•High-quality peer-reviewed clinical articles on all aspects of veterinary nursing and best practice\n•Articles written by veterinary nurses for veterinary nurses, creating a platform for learning and sharing best practice worldwide\n•All the latest jobs and course information to help you develop within your career and different levels of support to match your particular needs\nThe Veterinary Nurse is passionate about supporting and championing veterinary nursing, which is reflected in the high-quality content and topical articles inside every issue. Articles within The Veterinary Nurse encourage veterinary practitioners to discuss, debate and improve their clinical practice.\n', '', '', ''),
(1011, 1, 'Journal Of Aesthetic Nursing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nJournal of Aesthetic Nursing is a peer-reviewed clinical and professional journal for aesthetic nurses. The journal pledges to support aesthetic nurses in advancing their practice and to encourage other nurses wishing to make a career in this specialty. Its aim is to publish articles of the highest quality that have clinical and practical relevance for aesthetic nurses.\n\nSubscribe to Journal of Aesthetic Nursing today and benefit from:\n\n•An invaluable resource for you as a nurse working in this challenging and demanding specialty\n•An evidence-based journal that draws on research and provides case studies to reinforce good practice\n•A focus on practice management issues\n•A forum for discussion and debate on important clinical and professional issues\n\nJournal of Aesthetic Nursing champions the cause of aesthetic nurses and endeavours to ensure your contribution is properly understood. The journal encourages involvement and participation, to help put aesthetic nursing even more firmly on the map. NB: This subscription also includes access to content on the Journal of Aesthetic Nursing website, www.aestheticnursing.co.uk. Subscribers will be emailed login details for their account within three working days of the subscription being taken out.\n', '', '', ''),
(1012, 1, 'Port Strategy', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRead by key decision-makers in the industry. Port Strategy is renowned for excellence and informed opinion within the commercial ports sector. With unique best-practice articles, case studies, and industry led views and features, Port Strategy provides an exceptional reference point for the operation and profitability of international ports and terminals.\n\nPort Strategy''s coverage of port development and investment from both the developed and emerging world offers readers unrivalled coverage of the international marine ports industry - something no port executive should be without.\n', '', '', ''),
(1013, 1, 'British Journal Of School Nursing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nBritish Journal of School Nursing will support your professional development and training, through high-quality information and advice on clinical topics, mental health and wellbeing, child and adolescent health research and professional issues.\n\nSubscribe to British Journal of School Nursing for:\n\n•Essential advice on important issues affecting children and young people''s health, and keep up-to-date with the latest developments in policy and public health\n•The latest research findings on key areas of importance to you, as well as up-to-date information on the issues and concerns facing all school nurses\n•Access the best clinical articles available to school and public health nurses, written by experts and peer-reviewed by leading authorities in the profession\n•Key articles and case studies to help you develop your practice and provide first class care\n•Review the legal aspects of providing care to children within the school setting, including reports and analysis of the issues affecting you from policy to practice\n\nMeet the complex needs of the children and young people in your care and help them reach their full potential with British Journal of School Nursing.\n', '', '', ''),
(1014, 1, 'Essentially Midirs', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA monthly magazine (11 issues per year), read by over 3,400 practising midwives and students.\n\nEasily accessible articles and case studies combined with abstracts of articles and documents sourced from the unique MIDIRS Reference Database, make this a priority resource for students and other allied health professionals working with pregnant women, new mothers, babies and families.\n', '', '', ''),
(1015, 1, 'African Review Of Business And Technology', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAfrican Review of Business and Technology contains news articles on new developments, materials and contracts relevant to the continent. Within every issue, the editorial content covers banking and financial forecasts, management and business, executive travel and international reports. Regular features include IT and telecommunications, water supply and electricity, vehicles and transport, oil and petrochemicals, mining and quarrying. There are also annual suppliers and buyer’s guides, as well as coverage of regional exhibitions and conferences.\n', '', '', ''),
(1016, 1, 'World Fishing And Aquaculture', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nReaching international commercial fishing professionals worldwide, World Fishing &amp; Aquaculture provides valuable information for decision makers engaged in this fast-moving and competitive market. Established for over 50 years and distributed to a global audience, World Fishing is the leading monthly magazine dedicated to coverage of industry news, political issues, technical developments and new products.\n\nWorld Fishing is essential reading for vessel owners, fleet managers, processors and those readers who either influence or make buying decisions within every sector of the industry.\n', '', '', ''),
(1017, 1, 'The Motorship', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Motorship is the oldest-established, monthly technical maritime journal, since 1920 it has been the journal of choice for marine professionals involved with ships and their machinery.\n\nFocusing on the technical aspects of shipping and shipbuilding, the Motorship provides in-depth technical coverage in a concise, easy to read style, dealing primarily with vessel propulsion and ship machinery. The Motorship strives to deliver informed, unbiased opinion, commenting on issues affecting the industry today and providing a valuable resource to aid decision making.\n', '', '', ''),
(1018, 1, 'Electrical Review', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nElectrical Review magazine provides you with in-depth analytical features and news you need to keep you abreast of the latest developments in the electrical industry. The website and events are also a great way to stay on top of the key trends and products with the sector.\n\nAlong with the magazine, Electrical Review produces an annual Specification Guide. This print and online resource provides a best practice guide to specifying electrical systems in buildings and industry, from plugs and sockets through to HV substations, installation and smart grids. The guide is divided into six categories Power, Automation, Compliance, Panel building, Building services and Test and measurement.\n\nOur subscribers range from engineers to technical managers, project managers and people with an interest in this rapidly changing industry.\n\nSee the benefits in your pockets, saving 20% off and receive Your Electrical Review subscription also includes:\n•11 issues in print and digital formats\n•Our quarterly Data Centre Power supplement\n•Topical supplements\n•Free invitations to ours webinars and seminars\n•Weekly emails e-newsletters\n\n\n“Electrical Review is an excellent trade magazine, and one that I read because I can respect its content. As editor, Elinore Mackay, stamps a mark of professionalism on it, making it relevant, factual and interesting. The articles within it are varied to appeal to many aspects of the electrical business, and allow those in one area to stay current with technology in all others, and with an open mind one can see how they can be adapted to other market areas. As for advice, I would tell anyone with a genuine interest in our business arena, a subscription to Electrical Review is a must.” John Kirby, British Gas\n', '', '', ''),
(1019, 1, 'Parking Review', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nParking Review magazine was launched in 1989 and is published 11 times a year. It is the UK''s leading publication for parking professionals and it is the only independent magazine dedicated to the UK parking sector. Subscribe now for essential reading for both public and private sector professionals in the UK and beyond.\n\nParking Review provides unrivalled coverage of the UK off-street and on-street parking scene. Readers trust its content and rely on its independence. Through a true commitment to excellent editorial content, Parking Review brings thought-provoking, comprehensive coverage of the latest trends and developments in this dynamic and vital sector.\n\nBy subscribing you will ensure access to:\nLatest news and policy updates\n\nDevelopments in technology\n\nPractical case studies and company profiles\n\nQuarterly publication The Enforcers\n\nAward winning schemes\n\nSpecial supplements\n\nJobs and tenders\n\nSpecialist service directories\n\nAn annual industry survey', '', '', ''),
(1020, 1, 'Fundraising For Schools', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nFundraising for Schools is an essential independent monthly magazine for anyone with responsibility for raising school funds and finance. It contains up-to-date and accurate information on the sources of extra funding your school could benefit from.\n\nSubscribe to Fundraising for Schools today for:\n\n•Details of which grants and awards are available, the criteria for application and how and when to apply\n•Advice and guidance on how to apply for, and successfully receive, funding\n•Inspirational and practical ideas to help brighten up your traditional fundraising events\n•Up-to-date fundraising stories – learn from the successes and failures, through case studies, from schools that have previously applied for funding.\n\nIf your school is seeking funds for a specific project – or raising funds to aid its improvement and development – then Fundraising for Schools is a must-read publication. Subscribe today to ensure your school has the best chance of funding success! NB: Fundraising for Schools is not published in August\n', '', '', ''),
(1021, 1, 'Modern Railways', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Modern Railways Magazine?\n\nIf you want to stay informed on everything to do with the British Railway network, then this is the perfect magazine for you. Every major development in UK rail, both freight and commercial, is covered extensively, so you''ll get expert analysis on everything from infrastructure to traction, signalling to management. With a Modern Railways magazine subscription, you''ll also find all the latest news from Europe and the USA, keeping you totally up to date on international advances in rail technology. There''s also features on topics as diverse as restaurant cars, HS2 and disabled accessibility, as well as regular articles covering new appointments, classifieds and readers'' letters.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWith a subscription to Modern Railways magazine, reader’s can keep up to date with the latest railway industry news from the British Railway network.\n\nPublished for over 45 years, Modern Railways magazine has earned its reputation in the industry as an established and highly respected railway journal.\n\nModern Railways magazine is essential reading for professionals in the railway industry as well as individuals with a general interest in the state and developments of the British railway network.\n\nA subscription to Modern Railways magazine carries not only the latest news but also analysis of why those events are happening.\n\nPublished monthly, Modern Railways magazine keeps its readers fully informed with detailed articles, informative features, and special issues throughout the year.\n\nWith a Modern Railways magazine subscription you’ll never miss an issue and you’ll also get the magazine delivered free to your door each month before it hits the shops.\n\nBuy a subscription today to Modern Railways magazine for you or a friend today and keep up to date with all the latest railway industry news.\n', '', '', ''),
(1022, 1, 'Airliner World', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Airliner World Magazine?\n\nIf you''re looking for a title that offers up-to-date coverage of the latest developments on the global airline scene, invest in a subscription to Airliner World magazine.A fantastic read for aviation enthusiasts, this magazine is ideal for anyone interested in the latest flight technology, key industry personnel and airport developments from around the globe, including new leases and deliveries.As well as giving you a complete review of the latest aviation simulators, DVDs, books and other aviation-related memorabilia, Airliner World also includes retrospective articles on classic retired aircraft and updates from the preservation scene.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPublished monthly, Airliner World is dedicated to bringing its readers the latest developments from across the global airline scene. It has a worldwide following comprising both industry readers and commercial aviation enthusiasts. For up-to-the-minute news and features on new leases, deliveries, technology, key industry personnel and airport developments from the airline scene; make Airliner World your magazine of choice!\n\nSubscribers Get:\n\nPriority Delivery - subscriber copies go first.\nPrice Freeze - guaranteed no price rise during the term of your subscription.\nSpecial Discounts - subscriber-only discounts on special magazines and products.\n', '', '', ''),
(1023, 1, 'Writing Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Writing magazine Magazine?\n\nWhether you’re searching for your first publishing opportunity or your third book deal, this magazine’s combination of technical advice and inspiring stories is the perfect way to push through that writer''s block.\n\nWith a subscription to Writing magazine, you''ll also get a copy of Writers News, full of helpful advice for both fiction and non-fiction authors on navigating the murky worlds of agents and publishers to get your book onto shelves.\n\nIn Writing magazine you can read interviews with internationally acclaimed authors like Jodi Picoult and Jeffrey Archer, and send in your own work to be evaluated by authors, editors and critics to get a real taste of life as a published author.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWriting Magazine is essential reading for any aspiring or published writer, subscribe and discover how we can help you develop your unique writing style. Every month, our knowledgeable, expert writers provide pages of practical how-to advice, hints and tips, author features, information on what editors and publishers are looking for, writing competitions, and inspirational ideas - everything you could need to make the most of your writing potential. Writing Magazine now also features our sister publication Writers’ News, the perfect resource for writers looking to sell their work. Every month Writers'' News features articles on magazine and book publishers looking for manuscripts, competition announcements and news from the publishing world. That is 112 pages of essential writing information and inspiration in one monthly magazine! Every month you’ll receive expert advice on how to improve your writing, invaluable tips, entry to cash prize competitions, interviews with leading authors on how they achieved success, up-to date news, upcoming events, and 100s of leads to sell your work...everything you need to know to be a successful writer\n', '', '', ''),
(1024, 1, 'E-Learning Update', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nUK price is inclusive of VAT. Single User entitles the named person to 12 months of 24/7 online access (via teaching times website) to the content, online issues, library archive, education zones and knowledge banks.\n\nThe list of requirements for schools regarding the use of technology gets longer each year - VLEs, white boards, video-conferencing, mobile learning and so on!e-Learning Update aims to help school leaders and teachers understand the issues, products, problems and the possibilities associated with new technology.Technology has the capacity to transform teaching and learningin every subject, so let e-Learning Update unlock its potential for you.', '', '', ''),
(1025, 1, 'Poultry World', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSubscribe to Poultry World today, the only journal that covers the whole of the poultry industry.\n\nFocusing on large scale production and processing of poultry and eggs, but still ensuring the interests of niche markets and hobbyists are covered, Poultry World is a valuable and reliable source for poultry keepers that continues to reflect the needs of the changing poultry industry.\n\nIn every issue, practical business and technical information on the whole range of egg, broiler, turkey, duck and goose production, breeding and marketing will keep you up-to-date with all the news affecting your industry.\n\nSubscribe now to make a great saving.\n', '', '', ''),
(1026, 1, 'Oilfield Technology', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nOilfield Technology Magazine is the latest magazine from Palladian Publications Limited which covers all facets of the global exploration, drilling and production sector. It provides the link between technology, innovation and the global oil and gas sector.\n', '', '', ''),
(1027, 1, 'Practical Pre School', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPractical Pre-School is the essential monthly resource for anyone working with children in early years settings, containing expert information and inspirational activity ideas.\n\nSubscribe to Practical Pre-School for:\n\n•Early years news, features, management guidance and professional development articles\n•Practical activities section – a 16-page pull-out packed with inspirational ideas, linked to all areas of development in the revised EYFS\n•A full colour A3-sized poster\n•Child Care magazine, a distinct and separate magazine within Practical Pre-School, providing essential information for home-based childminders and childcarers, and EYFS-related activities for mixed aged groups As a publisher, we are dedicated to increasing the value we offer to our readers. That is why we have incorporated Child Care into Practical Pre-School, to provide you with the most comprehensive source of early years information, creative ideas and resources available to anyone working with young children. Moreover, this bumper magazine is designed to cater entirely for the requirements of the revised EYFS.\n', '', '', ''),
(1028, 1, 'British Journal Of Healthcare Assistants', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nBritish Journal of Healthcare Assistants (BJHCA) supports the career development of healthcare assistants (HCAs) and assistant practitioners (APs). BJHCA helps to meet the learning outcomes of the Quality and Credit Framework diploma qualifications.\n\nSubscribe to British Journal of Healthcare Assistants for:\n\n•Peer-reviewed clinical articles designed to aid your development\n•Key articles to assist your education and training. BJHCA highlights appropriate training courses and provides in-depth information about future learning and understanding in important areas of practice\n•Essential up-to-date information on concerns facing HCAs and APs in the workplace\n•Expert discussion on clinical and professional issues, including articles on the different roles available to HCAs and APs, as well as patient case studies\n\nImprove your knowledge and skills in all areas of practice for all HCAs and APs. Raise your awareness of best practice with highly practical examples, and articles that are packed full of information specifically designed to keep you up-to-date in all the essential topics relevant to healthcare.\n', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `oc_product_description` (`product_id`, `language_id`, `name`, `description`, `meta_description`, `meta_keyword`, `tag`) VALUES
(1029, 1, 'Primary Teacher Update', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPrimary Teacher Update – the monthly magazine that supports primary teachers and the wider primary workforce in their day-to-day work and careers. It provides the latest pedagogy and thinking from the classroom, with practical suggestions to help teachers apply this in the primary school environment.\n\nSubscribe to Primary Teacher Update for:\n\n•A magazine containing essential information delivered direct to your door each month to support you in delivering best primary teaching practice\n•Ideas and lesson materials every term to help take some of the stress away from your lesson planning and preparation\n•Access to over 2,000 expert articles, lesson plans, exclusive reports and special features from Primary Teacher Update''s sister publication 5to7 Educator*\n\nPrimary Teacher Update also publishes professional guidance to aid continued professional development in all areas of teaching practice, as well as providing the latest primary education news and debate. NB: This subscription also includes access to content on the Primary Teacher Update website, www.primaryteacherupdate.co.uk. Subscribers will be emailed login details for their account within three working days of the subscription being taken out. *5to7 Educator is no longer published\n', '', '', ''),
(1030, 1, 'Hydrocarbon Engineering', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Hydrocarbon Engineering magazine is a leading source of business, technical and analytical information for the hydrocarbon processing industry worldwide. Published monthly, a subscription to Hydrocarbon Engineering magazine is essential reading for the downstream processing sector from the head office to plant operators, from oil refineries to gas processing, petrochemical and LNG facilities. A subscription to Hydrocarbon Engineering magazine is the industry''s ''must have'' publication. A wide variety of in depth and informative features wait for you in every issue of a subscription to Hydrocarbon Engineering magazine. The main vision of this magazine is to provide readers with excellent information related to the oil and gas processing sector. It includes features on technical areas, new products, developments, changes and lots more. All these features are of high quality and well-written. A subscription to Hydrocarbon Engineering magazine is the best companion for all professionals involved in the industry.\n', '', '', ''),
(1031, 1, 'Maritime Journal', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMaritime Journal is the only magazine dedicated to commercial marine activity in the European port, harbour, coastal and nearshore environments. Everything from workboats to marine renewable energy, navaids to safety equipment falls within its broad remit. It thus provides a unique and vital link placing marine equipment vendors and service providers from across a very broad spectrum in contact with purchasing decision makers. Maritime Journal''s editorial policy is to provide a concise overview of industry news in the context of current operational applications. A user friendly style and signposted sections keep its busy readers efficiently up to date with the most useful and relevant information available.\n', '', '', ''),
(1032, 1, 'Early Years Educator', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nEarly Years Educator (EYE) is essential reading for anyone working with children aged from birth to five-years-old. As the most trusted and respected early years magazine, EYE will provide you with expert articles, case studies, best practice, special features, international comparisons, in-depth analysis, regular series and a 16-page practical activities supplement containing creative and developmentally appropriate ideas to take straight into your setting.\n\nEYE features everything from the power of storytelling to insights into qualifications and training, from analysis of the latest government policy announcements to promoting sustained shared thinking and co-construction of learning, from attachment and mud kitchens, to schemas and children as researchers, and so much more, but most of all, EYE will help you understand why these matter and how you can use them to improve your provision.\n\nThe magazine is dedicated to helping all members of the early years team improve their practice, from student to room leader, from manager to consultant, and provides the best possible support for the children in their care. EYE is a vital resource that you and your team can rely on for all of your practical and educational needs in the early years, and that caters for requirements of the revised Early Years Foundation Stage.\n\nRead EYE today and benefit from:\n•Up-to-date guidance on the requirements of the revised Early Years Foundation Stage\n•Expert articles on professional development, training and best practice procedures\n•Regular contributions from the leading names in early years education\n•A special 16-page supplement of inspirational practical activity ideas\n•Essential information and resources to help you develop your career and provide the best possible outcomes for the children in your care\n', '', '', ''),
(1033, 1, 'Journal Of Wound Care', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nJournal of Wound Care (JWC) provides the latest evidence-based information and best practice procedures. Keep up-to-date on all aspects of wound care, including the prevention and treatment of wounds and associated skin conditions. All articles are peer-reviewed by an expert panel of advisors and reviewers, and include the latest state-of the-art research and clinical practice articles.\n\nSubscribe to JWC today for:\n\n•High-quality evidence on all aspects of wound care, including: leg ulcers, pressure ulcers, the diabetic foot, burns, biofilms and more\n•The latest developments and innovations in wound care through both preclinical and preliminary clinical trials of potential new treatments worldwide\n•In-depth prospective studies of new treatment applications, as well as high-level research evidence on existing treatments\n•Clinical case studies providing information on how to deal with complex wounds\n•Comprehensive literature reviews on current concepts and practice, including cost effectiveness\n•Updates on the activities of wound care societies around the world\n\nJWC is indexed on Medline, Scopus, CINAHL and the Thomson Reuters'' Science Citation Index-Expanded and Current Contents/Clinical Medicine. Let JWC help you make the right decisions for the patients in your care.\n', '', '', ''),
(1034, 1, 'The Energy Industry Times', '', '', '', ''),
(1035, 1, 'Kennedy''S Confection Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Kennedy''s Confection magazine is essential for anyone working in the confectionary manufacturing industry.\n\nFounded in 1971 Kennedy''s Publications Ltd is a privately owned international business-to-business publishing company based in the UK.\n\nKennedy''s Confection magazine is the most well-read magazine for confectionery manufacturers across the globe. The magazine (now over 118 years old!) aims to both educate and entertain its readers. The editorial team receives a huge amount of information every month and, in addition to our exclusive features and regular commissioned articles, we receive a vast amount of potential information every month.\n\nIt is our job to sift through this to find what we believe to be the most interesting and relevant information for our global audience and to present this in an easy-to-read and entertaining format.\n', '', '', ''),
(1036, 1, 'Companion Animal', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nCompanion Animal aims to meet the clinical needs of veterinary surgeons in practice who care for small animals and exotics. The journal is authoritative and accessible, and has become one of the best-read publications for veterinary surgeons wanting to keep up-to-date with clinical developments that enhance their practice.\n\nSubscribe to Companion Animal for:\n\n•The latest in clinical developments\n•Authoritative and accessible peer-reviewed articles\n•A professional voice for veterinary surgeons, both supporting and sometimes challenging\n\nCompanion Animal provides regular clinical updates, visual surgery and case studies for CPD assessments.\n\nA highly respected veterinary surgeon, consultant editor Carl Gorman understands the needs of veterinary professionals in practice.\n', '', '', ''),
(1037, 1, 'Prweek', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPRWeek magazine is the market leading title in communications and PR and the key source of information for people working in this industry. The monthly magazine offers a dynamic mix of authority, insight, intelligence, entertainment and expert opinion on one of our most fascinating professions.\n\nSubscribe to PRWeek for:\n\n•Stories from the PR industry, delivered to your home or office\n•An essential mix of news, views and in-depth knowledge, backed by the expertise to put them into context\n•Expert opinion and authoritative analysis covering everything from big business issues to everyday life in the communications industry\n•Creative inspiration from artists, storytellers, songwriters, filmmakers and photographers', '', '', ''),
(1038, 1, 'Practice Nursing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPractice Nursing is the only monthly journal dedicated to promoting a culture of professional and clinical excellence in general practice nursing. The journal is dedicated to all nurses working in general practice looking to stay ahead in their profession.\n\nSubscribe to Practice Nursing today and benefit from:\n\n•Reliable, evidence-based information for practice nurses, written by experienced practitioners and peer reviewed by leading figures in clinical practice, education and research\n•Best practice techniques for immunisation, travel health, women’s health, diabetes, dermatology and much more\n•Career planning, legal and ethical issues news, as well as prescribing updates\n•Insight into reports of studies, audits and service development pilots extending the boundaries of general practice nursing\n\nAs a practice nurse who wishes to invest in your professional development, you need access to the right information. Practice Nursing is here to help practice nurses like you.\n\nNB: This subscription also includes access to content on the Practice Nursing website, www.practicenursing.com. Subscribers will be emailed login details for their account within three working days of the subscription being taken out.\n', '', '', ''),
(1039, 1, 'International Journal Of Therapy And Rehabilitation', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nInternational Journal of Therapy and Rehabilitation is the only interdisciplinary review journal for occupational therapists, physiotherapists, speech and language therapists, nurses and other allied health professionals working in therapy and rehabilitation. It publishes original research and clinical reviews, written by experts and peer reviewed by leading international authorities to ensure that the journal is accessible, relevant and useful in daily practice.\n\nSubscribe to International Journal of Therapy and Rehabilitation today and benefit from:\n\n•Peer-reviewed clinical practice, education and original research articles covering a wide range of topics to ensure that the journal is relevant to all allied health professionals\n•Commentaries published alongside articles to encourage further thought and analysis\n•In-depth reviews of the evidence on a particular area of therapy and rehabilitation\n•Narrative, evidenced-based articles discussing important developments and issues in therapy and rehabilitation practice\n•Articles with a more personal and sometimes controversial opinion on current issues affecting allied health professionals\n•Case reports focusing on interesting cases, and often highlighting novel approaches to interdisciplinary working\n\nInternational Journal of Therapy and Rehabilitation will help ensure that you have all the information you need to develop your career and provide the best possible care to your clients. The journal contains interdisciplinary content and strong international focus encouraging collaboration and the sharing of new ideas, to help practitioners enhance their knowledge and skills in a variety of fields and settings.\n', '', '', ''),
(1040, 1, 'British Journal Of Midwifery', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nBJM is the premier journal for midwives, containing a wealth of clinical, professional and educational peer-reviewed content focused on midwifery and women''s health. The journal publishes the most relevant and up-to-date original research, evidence-based papers and clinical reviews which establish best practice and current thinking in the field.\n\nSubscribe to BJM today and benefit from:\n\n•Clinical practice updates to keep your knowledge of clinical practice current\n•Research that will inform clinical practice, now and in the future\n•Essential information on issues and concerns, including advice about professional development\n•Articles aimed specifically at students to help them pass exams, improve clinical practice and secure their first position\n•A review of the important legal issues and responsibilities relevant to midwifery\n•An informal look at the latest developments in midwifery\n•Teaching methods and innovative ways to educate student midwives\n•A roundup of the latest events, including presentations, talks and debates\n\nBJM aims to challenge readers to reflect on and evaluate their own practice. The journal covers the full spectrum of midwifery from antenatal through to postpartum care and support, including issues of neonatal care. Improve your knowledge and skills in all areas of practice and enjoy articles written and peer-reviewed by prominent authorities in the profession.\n', '', '', ''),
(1041, 1, 'Nursing And Residential Care', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nNursing &amp; Residential Care is the only monthly journal providing essential reading for nurses, managers and training coordinators and care assistants working in care homes.\n\nNursing &amp; Residential Care covers a variety of issues from across the profession and is the only journal that contains a monthly section for those studying for Diplomas in Health and Social Care for levels 2 and 3.\n\nSubscribe today for:\n\n•Peer-reviewed clinical articles to keep you up to date with current best practice\n•Level 2 and 3 diploma series including case studies and reflective practice questionnaires\n•Care Quality Commission series on how to comply with the Essential Standards\n•Legal issues to ensure all employees adhere to the latest legislation\n•Management and practical issues, including staffing, laundry, nutrition and managing the care home environment, both indoor and outdoor\n•Dementia series exploring different practical care approaches that follow on from the National Dementia Strategy and focus on non-pharmacological care\n•News and clinical updates from the past month\n\nNursing &amp; Residential Care provides practical information, guidance and support on everything you need to know to achieve your qualifications and keep you updated on best practice. Ensure you keep informed and remain ahead of developments with NRC.\n', '', '', ''),
(1042, 1, 'Harpers Wine And Spirit', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSubscription price includes VAT for the digital element\n\nTrusted for over 100 years by producers, suppliers and retailers from across the on and off trades, Harpers provides unrivalled knowledge of the wine and spirit industry. Keep up-to-date with unique news coverage, analysis of key business trends and the latest market developments. Boost your drinks knowledge and be confident that Harpers provides all the information you need to stay on top.\n\nYou will get:\nThe monthly magazine delivered in print direct to your desk and accessed online through Harpers.co.uk\n\nUnlimited access to our revamped website, harpers.co.uk. Highlights include:\n-Channel specific breaking news and analysis\n-Highly targeted content for retailers, merchants, on-trade, suppliers and producers\n-Search for wine and spirits news by country, spirits type, or individual brand owner and producer\n-Dedicated sections for independent merchants and sommeliers\n\nHarpers business reports\n\nHarpers Directory on-line including:\n-UK Buyers Guide: comprehensive search of UK wine and spirits trade\n-Wineries Guide: covering over 7,000 leading wineries worldwide\n\nA selection of Email newsletters including the popular Top Merchant and At Your Service', '', '', ''),
(1043, 1, 'British Journal Of Hospital Medicine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nBritish Journal of Hospital Medicine is the leading monthly multi-specialty review journal for hospital doctors. The journal has been at the forefront of medical education for over 45 years, publishing only the best and most authoritative clinical reviews, symposia, editorials and case reports available to doctors.\n\nSubscribe to the British Journal of Hospital Medicine today and benefit from:\n\n•Topical comment on important issues within hospital medicine from some of the world''s leading specialists\n•The best clinical articles available to hospital doctors, summarising all the latest research findings\n•Practical training issues of concern to all hospital doctors, whatever their grade or specialty, as well as unusual presentations and how they were resolved\n•The Core Training for Doctors section: Intended to provide clinical information in an easily accessible format to doctors in training. Articles cover clinical skills for postgraduate examinations, what you need to know about, tips from the shop floor and what they don''t teach you in medical school.\n\nBritish Journal of Hospital Medicine covers all specialties in hospital medicine, making it essential reading for doctors of all grades who want to ensure that their practice is evidence-based and up-to-date with all the latest clinical developments. The journal''s articles are concise, fully referenced, presented in an easy-to-read format and peer-reviewed by some of the world''s leading international authorities.\n', '', '', ''),
(1044, 1, 'British Journal Of Healthcare Management', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nBritish Journal of Healthcare Management is the independent monthly journal that makes essential reading for all health service managers, policymakers, influencers and commentators.\n\nSubscribe to British Journal of Healthcare Management today and benefit from:\n\n•Peer-reviewed management articles with interviews, analysis and comment to bring you a sharp, topical and valuable insight into what''s happening in and around the NHS\n•Clinical reviews outlining how managers can achieve optimum cost-effectiveness and improve patient outcomes\n•Insight into the latest developments in healthcare technology and advances in medicines\n•Commentaries from key figures and experts in the health service. BJHCM is written by leaders, for leaders\n•Expert clinical articles to help non-medically trained healthcare managers understand the issues behind their decisions\n\nWith a subscription to British Journal of Healthcare Management you can ensure that you keep up-to-date with articles on the latest issues and thinking surrounding the management of the NHS.\n', '', '', ''),
(1045, 1, 'Group Travel World', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGroup Travel World is the UK and Europe’s best-selling group travel magazine. A subscription is the essential read for all Group Travel Organisers, school trip organisers, work and social travel clubs and tour and coach operators, as it features special familiarisation trips, exclusive group rates and organiser incentives that won’t be found anywhere else. It is the best source of inspiration for anyone who needs to plan and organise days out or group breaks, with attractive ideas and helpful detailed contact information. The magazine is full of the latest tourism and travel industry news, celebrity interviews, feature articles, reviews and insider information. Subscribing gives readers access to the website, which in addition to extended versions of everything in the magazine, has a comprehensive directory of attractions, hotels, tourist boards, restaurants and coach operators offering exclusive group rates and incentives.\n', '', '', ''),
(1046, 1, 'Country Smallholding', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Country Smallholding Magazine?\n\nThis is one of the most useful gardening magazine subscriptions for smallholders who want to improve their self-sufficient lifestyle.\n\nIt focuses on all types of livestock, with special monthly features from veteran smallholder Tim Tyne, giving you an in-depth overview of his favourite breeds.\n\nThere are hundreds of top tips for animal breeders, with regular Q&amp;A sessions with industry experts and fellow farmers, giving you unique tips to help you get the best from your herd.\n\nWith a Country Smallholding magazine subscription you''ll also have access to exceptional organic farming techniques, plus advice on how you can make the most of sustainable energy.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCountry Smallholding is Britain’s biggest-selling magazine for smallholders and is all about self-sufficiency. It has a strong focus on livestock, with regular features on sheep, pigs, goats, alpacas and bees.\n\nCountry Smallholding also includes advice on growing crops and vegetables, home produced food, machinery and equipment and renewable energy. A team of experts answer readers’ questions and there is an extensive breeders'' directory.There is also a free Poultry magazine with every issue! Poultry, is packed full of advice on keeping chickens, and covers many breeds, shows and products, with special features and real life stories.\n', '', '', ''),
(1047, 1, 'Flyer', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Flyer Magazine?\n\nIf you love British light aircraft, this magazine is the perfect way to get up-to-date reports on the latest innovations, along with plenty of features on classic models still going strong today.\n\nWith a subscription to Flyer magazine, you can read all about the cutting-edge inventions set to change the future of flying, and enjoy nostalgic reminisces on great planes from ages past.\n\nYou’ll get in-depth flight tests and reviews of the latest models and gadgets, making sure you''re equipped in style. In each issue you can enjoy fantastic aviation stories from the readers and write in with your own, as well as finding out about the cheapest places to land and how to fix common flight malfunctions.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Flyer is a must-have for pilots of light aircraft and for airline pilots who wish to remind themselves what real flying is all about! Flyer magazine brings you news and articles on new and established aircraft, flying techniques, ideas of places to visit (and how to get to them), exhibition and rally reports, maintenance issues, humour, opinions. Read about the most scenic, exotic or remote locations, the best safety advice, flying tips, travel guides, product references and much, much more!\n', '', '', ''),
(1048, 1, 'Practical Poultry', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Practical Poultry magazine subscription is an essential monthly read for anyone interested in poultry. Practical Poultry is a full-colour magazine written and produced by an enthusiastic team of poultry experts and professional journalists, dedicated to providing a high quality, informative monthly publication. Practical Poultry is a specialist title that caters for enthusiasts at all levels – from beginners with a few chickens in the garden, to established breeders working on small-scale commercial production. A Practical Poultry magazine subscription covers a vast array of topics each month, ranging from incubation to housing, feeds to breeds, and shows to husbandry issues. The magazine content is geared specifically to supporting the novice keeper, but each issue contains plenty to interest the more experienced owner too. Practical Poultry magazine really is an essential read for anyone interested in poultry, whether you own three or 300 birds!\n', '', '', ''),
(1049, 1, 'Marketing ', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nFounded in 1931, Marketing has become the magazine that truly gives the big picture of what''s going on in the marketing industry. Through news, insightful analysis and powerful comment, the publication continues to showcase exciting content from the media and advertising industries.\n\nSubscribe to Marketing for:\n\n•Stories from the marketing industry, delivered to your home or office\n•Access to monthly downloads of Marketing iPad edition, plus archived editions of the magazine\n•Strategy and analysis from the world’s leading marketers and brands – giving you relevant insight for future marketing campaigns\n•Opinion from the UK’s top thought leaders, including chief executives Arianna Huffington and Camila Batmanghelidgh ', '', '', ''),
(1050, 1, 'Home Trends', 'TRENDS, first published in New Zealand, is one of the most widely read architecture and design magazines in the world today. Currently in 10 countries, India is the 11th edition of this magazine. Launched in India as the Home TRENDS series, the magazine aims to meet the demand for a world-class reference source on architecture and design for the both professionals and home makers.\n\nPrice includes posting &amp; handling charges of Rs. 100 per publisher policy', '', '', ''),
(1051, 1, 'Bbc Good Homes', 'Launched in 2008, Good Homes has grown into a reputed brand that reaches not only to designers, architects but also to a growing number of home-makers seeking inspiration to adorn their homes. With a host of chic yet simple ideas, DIY tips and expert advice, it combines the best of international interiors with Practical design ideas.Price includes posting &amp; handling charges of Rs. 120 per publisher policy', '', '', ''),
(1052, 1, 'Inside Outside', 'INSIDE OUTSIDE is India''s first, and foremost monthly magazine on interior design and architecture.Launched in 1978 by the Business India Group, BIG bought it over from its original owners when it had published only 4 issues. The Group turned the magazine around and made it a monthly with content that was more relevant and exciting.Over the years the magazine has grown to be the bible in the community of Indian architects and professional interior designers. It is revered for its authority and selection of coverage. Professionals consider it an honour to be published in the pages of this premier interior design magazine.The magazine focuses on well designed interiors. Be it residential or commercial, INSIDE OUTSIDE covers the exclusive and luxurious, to the low cost and space conscious. Designing on small budgets and problem solving is a special area of editorial interest, and even the lavish apartments featured are replete with ideas that can be emulated in more modest homes.', '', '', ''),
(1053, 1, 'Design Today', 'Design Today features home and work space décor solutions that reflect the taste, moods, lifestyle and aspirations of people, architects'' facts and profiles, industry news and updates, product information and profiling, international perspectives in interior designs • all in all, your one-stop shop to meet and stay in sync with the interior design and the broad spectrum it encompasses.', '', '', ''),
(1054, 1, 'Better Interiors', 'Spaces that speak for themselves could very well be the hallmark for a well-designed interior and that’s just what the doctor or rather, the interior designer ordered for, in the form of Better Interiors - a special interest monthly magazine that focuses on interior design. A team of proven professionals has put their minds together to create a quality magazine on Interiors with superior production values.Better Interiors features home and work space decor solutions that reflect the taste, moods, lifestyle and aspirations of people, architects'' facts and profiles, industry news and updates, product information and profiling, international perspectives in interior designs • all in all, your one-stop shop to meet and stay in sync with the interior design and the broad spectrum it encompasses.', '', '', ''),
(1055, 1, 'Beautiful Kitchens', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBeautiful Kitchens showcases inspirational, real-life designs, features invaluable planning advice and selects the best of all the latest kitchen products and must-have appliances - providing you with everything you need to plan your dream design.', '', '', ''),
(1056, 1, 'Period Homes &amp; Interiors', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Period Homes &amp; Interiors Magazine?\n\nFrom Edwardian to Victorian, Period Homes &amp; Interiors looks inside beautiful, traditional properties like impressive town houses and quaint cottages that will inspire you to give your home interior a classic overhaul. Every issue features photo shoots of four real period homes that can help to give your traditional home decoration efforts a prod in the right direction. A subscription to Period Homes &amp; Interiors magazine will bring you loads of period-style decorating tips straight from British craft experts, as well as problem solving advice for renovation projects and auction news on precious antiques. If you''re desperate to recreate your favourite period, Period Homes &amp; Interiors is the ideal home improvement magazine for you.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Period Homes &amp; Interiors magazine is a must-have for anyone who appreciates traditional, classic and vintage-inspired homes, interiors and gardens.\n\nEvery issue of Period Homes &amp; Interiors magazine features four beautifully photographed real homes, such as country mansions, pretty cottages, barn conversions and town houses.\n\nPlus the latest period-style decorating trends, gorgeous shopping ideas for a traditional home, expert advice on period properties, in-depth features on treasured antiques, traditional British crafts, stunning gardens and renovation problem solving.\n\nWhether it’s the latest news on shopping, gardens, auctions and antiques, or clever ideas and practical solutions for a period property, Period Homes &amp; Interiors magazine is the indispensable source for the discerning homeowner.\n', '', '', ''),
(1057, 1, 'Harpers Bazaar Australia', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAustralia''s No. 1 Fashion magazine, Harper''s BAZAAR is\n', '', '', ''),
(1058, 1, 'Triathlon &amp; Multi Sport', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTriathlon &amp; Multi Sport Magazine has inspirational articles from the world''s top athletes. It provides training and nutritional tips, triathlon news and updates and an event calendar. Triathlon &amp; Multi Sport Magazine should be an essential part of your training for the next big race.\n', '', '', ''),
(1059, 1, 'Recipes +', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRecipes + magazine is a national monthly based in Australia, aimed at women (and men) looking for a magazine that shows how to make exciting &amp; new recipes to cook for their family and friends. Each issue has over 300 recipes, which shows easy step by step instructions on how to make simple meals, to something exotic for those romantic evenings at home, to how to host a dinner party. This magazine caters for all those who love to cook, or who have a family and need to cook on a low budget, great money saving ideas inside each issue. ', '', '', ''),
(1060, 1, 'Australian Tennis Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAustralian Tennis Magazine is packed with exclusive interviews, pictures/posters of your favourite Australian and overseas players. Read all about what the latest equipment, Grand Slam previews and reviews, national and international tournaments, on and off court news, stats, facts and rankings. Learn more about your game with monthly coaching tips.\n', '', '', ''),
(1061, 1, 'Real Living', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nReal Living is a monthly homes and lifestyle magazine helping you to live a stylish, enjoyable, real life.\n\nEach issue is packed with pages of inspiring images, easy DIY projects, the hottest products in the stores and all the advice you could need to get transforming your bricks and mortar into a home for you.\n\nIdeas and projects are affordable and stylish, practical and pretty and cater for anyone looking to add a personal touch. .\n\nFor handy household hints, great food ideas, outdoor tips, real shopping opportunities and how to steal some &quot;me time&quot;, there’s simply no other magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(1062, 1, 'Australian Country Style', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAustralian Country Style celebrates the diversity of Australian country life andexplores what ''country'' means. The magazine is filled with evocative stories and stunning photography, bringing to life the multiplicity and depth of modern country living. There are stories about homes, both grand and small. There are stories about beautiful gardens you just want to walk through. And there are features on fashion, decorating and the arts - all covered from a uniquely ''country'' approach', '', '', ''),
(1063, 1, 'Australian Womens Weekly (Uk Edition)', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Australian Women''s Weekly is celebrating over seven decades as the country''s premier monthly magazine ... and is still the number-one selling monthly.\n\nThe magazine has been called many things ... an icon, a jewel in Australia''s crown, part of this country''s folklore.\n\nIn an ever-changing magazine market, The Australian Women''s Weekly continues to stand above its rivals. It entertains, it informs, it is contemporary and relevant to Australian women today with experts in every field (fashion/beauty/health/home/craft/gardening/cooking). But most of all, it is credible. It is a trusted friend that entertains and informs with the best of everything.\n', '', '', ''),
(1064, 1, 'Earth Movers &amp; Excavators', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEarthmovers and Excavators is the heavy industry''s most important monthly business guide and is used by mining corporations, contractors and government instrumentalities to keep abreast of equipment appreciation and technological tends.\n', '', '', ''),
(1065, 1, 'Creating Country Threads', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThis magazine was called before: Australian Country Threads. Each 148 page issue features 12 inspirational country projects from Australia''s leading craft talents - including patchwork, applique, stitchery, dolls and cross stitch.\n\nMotivating stories and new ideas to ignite your personal country style make it a must have.- Full-size pattern sheets- Profile a leading craft talent - Behind the Seams- Women we Admire- Vintage Threads- Country Collections- Our Obsession- PLUS great feature stories every issue\n', '', '', ''),
(1066, 1, 'Premiere French', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPREMIERE (FRENCH) is the up-to-date magazine for the cinema enthusiast. PREMIERE reports on movie-of-the-month, movie reviews as well as interviews and portrays on stars.\n', '', '', ''),
(1067, 1, 'Africa Report', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Africa Report is a pan-African English-language bimonthly magazine, covering politics, economy, society and culture, published by the Paris-based Groupe Jeune Afrique. In-the-field writers report from every region to guarantee in-depth, on-the-ground reportage.\n\nCompany profiles and CEO interviews, as well as essential maps and data, complete the editorial offer that has been praised as a reliable factual source by decision-makers and investors active in Africa.\n', '', '', ''),
(1068, 1, 'Jalouse French', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nJALOUSE (French) is a women''s magazine who''s topics are always exclusive, elegant and extraordinary. This editorial embodies the age-old mantra by featuring feminine frocks and girly getups.\n', '', '', ''),
(1069, 1, 'Tele 7 Jeux', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWord games and puzzles for the whole family.\n', '', '', ''),
(1070, 1, 'Sante', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSANTE is a French womens magazine covering womens lifestyle, health and beauty.\n', '', '', ''),
(1071, 1, 'Glamour French', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGLAMOUR FRENCH is a magazine published by Les Publications CondeNast U.S.A. It is the French version of the well known U.K. Glamour. Glamour French will feature the latest fashion and beauty tips to make it''s readers feel and look glamourous.\n', '', '', ''),
(1072, 1, 'Cosmopolitan French', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFrench edition of this popular women''s lifestyle magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(1073, 1, 'Top Sante Fr', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTOP SANTÉ is the expert health magazine women can trust. Dedicated to health, psychology, anti-ageing, diet and nutrition, it''s the authoritative choice for women who want to make positive changes to help them look and feel healthier and happier.\n', '', '', ''),
(1074, 1, 'Capital-French', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCAPITAL (FRENCH) analyses the world markets and businesses and offers a view behind the curtains. As well as information and aspects in all main questions about economy and finance.\n', '', '', ''),
(1075, 1, 'Be Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBe Magazine is a French language magazine featuring women’s lifestyle, celebrities, Fashion and beauty.\n\nBe Magazine covers holidays and how to look good, plus tips on make-up and hairstyles.\n\nSubscribe now and keep up to date and on trend for all the latest news and ideas.\n', '', '', ''),
(1076, 1, 'Entrevue', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA French men''s magazine covering sport, cars, music, women and cinema\n', '', '', ''),
(1077, 1, 'Lire', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLIRE is a high quality magazine for everyone who enjoys reading book reviews, author portraits and information from the book world.\n', '', '', ''),
(1078, 1, 'Biba', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n.Similar to such Women’s magazines as Marie Claire, this publication has everything you need to know about women’s lifestyle; health, fashion, beauty, family, sex, make-up tips and men are all crammed between the glossy pages of this comprehensive guide to toutes choses femmes (that’s all things female, but as this glossy’s in French, hopefully you know that!).\n\nFeaturing some big names in fashion, this magazine has some great advice on how to primp and perfect any outfit. Celeb gossip’s also in there, and the obligatory and sometimes horrifically fascinating problem pages.\n', '', '', ''),
(1079, 1, 'Magazine Litteraire', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLe Magazine Littéraire is France''s best guide to the world of literature, both modern and classical. Each issue offers a world of new authors and historical publications to explore.\n\nSubscribe to Le Magazine Littéraire to receive 12 issues of this informative magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(1080, 1, 'Am-Afrique-Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAM AFRIQUE MAGAZINE contains interesting articles about the countries of Africa with focal point on politics, economy, culture, literature, music and movies.\n', '', '', ''),
(1081, 1, 'Gq French', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFrench version of the men''s magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(1082, 1, 'Elle Decoration French', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nELLE DECORATION (FRENCH) showcases the very best of what''s modern, new, and beautiful in the world of interior design, whether it is high street or designer.\n', '', '', ''),
(1083, 1, 'Luxe Immo French', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFrench Language Edition: Luxe Immo is a high quality publication that feature some fantastic real estate for sale and to rent throughout Europe, North America and Asia. This is coupled with major features from the world of contemporary art and design that also features interviews with some of the biggest names in this field. Luxe Immo is a luxury publication, produced to high quality and in 2 years has built a great reputation.\n', '', '', ''),
(1084, 1, 'Psychologies French', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPSYCHOLOGIES (FRENCH) takes information from the latest research in the field of psychology and makes it useful to people in their everyday lives. Its coverage encompasses self-improvement, relationships, the mind-body connection, health, family, the workplace and culture.\n', '', '', ''),
(1085, 1, 'Marie Claire French', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nMarie Claire France was the first edition of Marie Claire.\n', '', '', ''),
(1086, 1, 'Beaux Arts', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBeaux Arts magazine makes you experience the news in art, through all periods of creation, to the most contemporary. With an eclectic look, alive and engaged, it prompts you to understand the genius of a great master and to inspire young talent ... Every month, more than 150 richly illustrated pages: the complete records, portraits of artists and collectors, historical movements, deciphering trends ... But also: a guide to all the exhibitions to see around the world and most of the art market comment and analysis for you.\n', '', '', ''),
(1087, 1, 'Top Model', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWritten in English, published in Germany, TOP MODEL is a creative Girls magazine. It encourages girls aged 8-12 to get creative and design clothes and accessories aided by templates and stickers. It also has a flavour of the latest teen idols.\n', '', '', ''),
(1088, 1, 'Glamour German', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGerman edition of the UK Glamour.\n', '', '', ''),
(1089, 1, 'Neon', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNEON is the magazine for the young reader. NEON covers topics on society and politics, fashion, relationship and sexuality, job and career, travelling as well pop culture.\n', '', '', ''),
(1090, 1, 'Cosmopolitan Ger', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe German edition of COSMOPOLITAN, the No 1 young woman''s magazine in the world.\n', '', '', ''),
(1091, 1, 'Myself Gm', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMYSELF is a German language women''s lifestyle magazine.\n\nSubscribe to MYSELF for styling tips, beauty news, interior design inspiration, fashion, recipe ideas and more.\n', '', '', ''),
(1092, 1, 'Gq German', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGerman edition of the popular men''s magazine, GQ.\n', '', '', ''),
(1093, 1, 'Instyle German', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nIn Style Germany is the German counterpart to In Style magazine. This German edition of In Style magazine is a glossy women’s monthly magazine featuring celebrity news and the finest fashion. It features fashion, hair, beauty and celebrity news and advice for the modern woman who wants to stay on top of the current trends. Subscribe or buy a single copy and get the low-down on how to look like the stars, and get the look you want.\n', '', '', ''),
(1094, 1, 'Elle German', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe German edition of Elle, the womens lifestyle magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(1095, 1, 'Vogue German', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThis is the German edition of Vogue, the fashion and style bible.\n', '', '', ''),
(1096, 1, 'Architectural Digest Gm', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGerman edition of the UK magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(1097, 1, 'Ait Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAIT is one of the most famous internationally oriented technical journals. public buildings and their internal architecture are the core of its coverage.\n\nAIT is devoted to a particular architectural topic, which is addressed by in international architects and designers, both academics and practioners.\n\nThe buildings discussed are documented with numerous photographs, outlines,longitudinal and cross sections and sketch maps\n', '', '', ''),
(1098, 1, 'Style International It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nItalian luxury lifestyle magazine\n', '', '', ''),
(1099, 1, 'L''Uomo Vogue', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\nL''uomo Vogue is the men''s fashion magazine for the Italian speaking fashion conscious male.\n', '', '', ''),
(1100, 1, 'Elle-Decor-It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nItalian Magazine covering home furnishings, decorating techniques, news on latest trends. English text supplement\n', '', '', ''),
(1101, 1, 'Interni It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nINTERNI (ITALY) is an Italian magazine which offers many ideas about modern living.\n', '', '', ''),
(1102, 1, 'Tutto Enigmistica', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nItalian puzzle magazine\n', '', '', ''),
(1103, 1, 'Il Blocco Enigmistico', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIL BLOCCO ENIGMISTICO is an Italian brainteaser magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(1104, 1, 'Forza Milan It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFORZA MILAN (ITALIA) is an Italian football magazine and offers football trivia, facts and backgrounds all around the popular sport.\n', '', '', ''),
(1105, 1, 'Gq Italian', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGQ ITALIAN is the Italian language version of the hugely successful International men''s lifestyle magazine GQ. Content and style is in the same vein as the English GQ.\n', '', '', ''),
(1106, 1, 'Cosmopolitan It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Italian edition of COSMOPOLITAN, the No 1 young woman''s magazine in the world.\n', '', '', ''),
(1107, 1, 'Grazia Casa It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHome interiors, decor, designs and designers\n', '', '', ''),
(1108, 1, 'Guerin Sportivo It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGUERIN SPORTIV is an Italian language football magazine for all footie fans. Containing funny comic strips and interviews with footballers, club managers and footballing legends. Other articles cover team profiles, league tables and the history of football, in addition to book reviews, fantastic action colour photographs and more!\n', '', '', ''),
(1109, 1, 'Focus It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFOCUS (ITALIA) is well known for its reports on science and the environment as well as picture stories.\n', '', '', ''),
(1110, 1, 'Marie Claire It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nItalian edition of the UK''s Marie Claire\n', '', '', ''),
(1111, 1, 'La Mia Boutique', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLA MIA BOUTIQUE offers complicated patterns of the most beautiful dresses as well as ideas on fashion, cosmetics and interior.\n', '', '', ''),
(1112, 1, 'Elle Italian', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAs with its English counterpart, the Italian edition of ELLE magazine focuses on the world of fashion, beauty and style. Each glamorous, glossy issue highlights the latest trends around the world and offers self-help articles, celebrity profiles and interviews, and practical how-to information.\n', '', '', ''),
(1113, 1, 'Amica It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAMICA IT offers a broad range of subjects, spectacular reports and interviews.\n', '', '', ''),
(1114, 1, 'Architectural Digest It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nARCHITECTURAL DIGEST ITALIAN is one of the most prestigious magazines, covering home interiors and design. This Italian-language magazine is a monthly publication.\n', '', '', ''),
(1115, 1, 'Vogue Italian', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVOGUE ITALIAN is THE style bible for the fashion conscious Italian speaking female.Recognised the world round for setting the fashion standard, VOGUE ITALIAN pushes the limits of fashion and beauty reporting surprising, challenging and ultimately entertaining pieces to its readers.As well as packed with all the latest hot off the catwalk styles, VOGUE ITALIAN is packed with great features, interviews with style icons and more.\n', '', '', ''),
(1116, 1, 'Domus', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDOMUS is an Italian-language magazine about art, architecture and interior design. It''s full of contemporary designs and ideas, reviews of outstanding architecture, new products on the market and museums to visit around the world. Topical articles cover current events such as the aftermath of events like September 11th and the rebuilding of New York. DOMUS is a magazine for the modern designer.\n', '', '', ''),
(1117, 1, 'Casabella It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCASABELLA (ITALIA) MAGAZINE : CASABELLA is an Italian architectural and product design magazine with a focus on modern, radical design.\n\nIt includes interviews with the world''s most prominent architects.\n', '', '', ''),
(1118, 1, 'Vogue Nippon', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVOGUE NIPPON magazine, the fashion &amp; style bible, packed with great features. If it''s in VOGUE magazine, it''s in fashion. This is the Japanese version of VOGUE magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(1119, 1, 'Ancient Warfare', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Ancient Warfare magazine, which is the only English language magazine to deal with the military history of the ancient Mediterranean. Every issue in a subscription to Ancient Warfare magazine is packed with articles around a different central theme, photography of original artifacts, exclusive artwork and maps. Ancient Warfare magazine is read by historians, wargamers, modellers and reenactors. A subscription to Ancient Warfare is suitable for readers at many levels - it does not bow down to its readers, but you don''t need a PhD in ancient history to understand what is going on either. Within the pages of each installment in a subscription to Ancient Warfare magazine you will find in depth and excellent articles, news and information, authoritative and independent reviews, exciting games an dmodels, quizzes, readers letter and lots more. So if you are a history buff, or want to know more about ancient Mediterranean warfare, then a subscription to Ancient Warfare magazine is not to be missed.\n', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `oc_product_description` (`product_id`, `language_id`, `name`, `description`, `meta_description`, `meta_keyword`, `tag`) VALUES
(1120, 1, 'Medieval Warfare', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe NEW magazine about conflict in the middle ages Medieval Warfare explores the age of warlords and castles Medieval Warfare Magazine is a unique publication focused exclusively on soldiers, battles and tactics between AD 500 - 1500. The chronological successor to the popular Ancient Warfare magazine, each issue of Medieval Warfare is centered around a historic theme: from camp life during the Hundred Years War to the campaigns of Charlemagne, the new magazine takes an in-depth look at every aspect of Medieval military history. Every copy of the magazine is illustrated with original, beautiful artwork by a variety of talented artists. Photos are selected from museum collections around the world and include numerous unusual and rarely seen artworks and artifacts. Articles in Medieval Warfare are written by professionals and passionate amateurs alike. Thoughtful, informative, and original, writing in Medieval Warfare is always accessible while still providing readers with the latest ideas and scholarship on each topic.\n', '', '', ''),
(1121, 1, 'Glamour Russian', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRussian version of the UK Glamour.\n', '', '', ''),
(1122, 1, 'Tatler Russian', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTatler Russian features interviews with most asked-for celebrities and the latest trends.Tatler has become the most up-to-date magazine about fashion and the high life.\n', '', '', ''),
(1123, 1, 'Gq Russian', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGQ (RUSSIA) is the premier men''s magazine which addresses the people, places, ideas and issues that shape men''s personal expression, development and experiences. Each issue features fashion, journalism, contemporary fiction and service articles on fitness, grooming and health.\n', '', '', ''),
(1124, 1, 'Vogue Russian', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVOGUE Russian edition is the fashion authority. Setting the standard for over 100 years has made Vogue the best selling fashion magazine in the world. Each issue delivers the latest in beauty, style, health, fitness and celebrities. Before it''s in fashion, it''s in Vogue!\n', '', '', ''),
(1125, 1, 'Lanas Stop Hand Knitting', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLanas Stop is a major brand name in wool manufacture and retail and are based in Rioja, Spain. Each issue of Lanas Stop Handknitting is produced on high quality paper and features high quality photographic content of new knitted fashion garments and in addition to the stunning photography you will find all the patterns and details to knit these designs in your own homes. Each pictorial comes with the pattern to knit with full easy to follow instructions in English. They also contain French and Spanish text which may open additional markets internationally such as South America and would also appeal better to the hispanic population in North America\n', '', '', ''),
(1126, 1, 'Downtown', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDOWNTOWN is a Spanish language magazine for men. Inside readers will find topical features, fashion, sport, cars, celebrity interviews, product tests and reviews, useful web addresses, health and fitness advice, delicious recipes and album and film reviews.\n', '', '', ''),
(1127, 1, 'Neo 2', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNEO 2 is a groundbreaking style magazine. Each issue contains reviews on a variety of products such as computer games, shoes, travel, art, drink and music. Other features include revealing interviews with top DJs, fashion designers, film directors and other high profile figures within the media and fashion industry. In addition NEO 2 looks at fine restaurants, has topical editorial, unveils the latest fashion and reports on the movers and shakers within the art world.\n', '', '', ''),
(1128, 1, 'Conde Nast Traveller Sp', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Spanish-language edition of CONDE NAST TRAVELLER contains travel secrets and advice, money-saving tips, and profiles of exotic places, resorts, and events around the world.\n', '', '', ''),
(1129, 1, 'Muy Interesante', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMUY INTERSANTE is a Spanish language current affairs magazine. Inside readers will find topical features on subjects such as NASA, health checks, new advances in technology, wildlife around the world, fashion production lines, product tests and reviews, crosswords, book and film reviews, comic sketches and a look back at people in history such as Albert Einstein and more.\n', '', '', ''),
(1130, 1, 'El-Mueble-Arquitectura', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEl Mueble Arquitectura is a Spanish architectural title\n', '', '', ''),
(1131, 1, 'Patrones', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPatrones is a fashion magazine in which every pattern is offered in a natural shape pattern as well as three sizes. The patterns essentially come from PrÃªt-Ã -porter fashions and come labelled by the different brands, thus enabling the reader to create her own fashionwear at a much more accessible price. In addition to the patterns, it also provides explanations and cutting plans that arrange the different sections in a manner that allows the reader to save fabrics.\n', '', '', ''),
(1132, 1, 'Vanity Fair Spanish', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVanity Fair is the magazine for women that includes interviews with people of note, articles on news items of current interest, books, health, beauty, crime and hot gossip. The Spanish edition is not a translation of the U.S. magazine and the majority of its content is produced by an editorial team in Spain.\n', '', '', ''),
(1133, 1, 'Instyle Spanish', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIn Style Spain is the Spanish edition of In Style magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(1134, 1, 'Gq Spanish', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGQ is a glossy mens  magazine with regular features on fashion, style, health, &amp; the latest trends. Every issue includes interviews with major celebrities, film, music, book reviews, details on professional sports, &amp; other subjects of interest to men of fine taste.\n', '', '', ''),
(1135, 1, 'Elle Spanish', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSpanish edition of the popular UK title, focusing on the world of fashion, beauty and style. Each glamorous, glossy issue highlights the latest trends around the world and offers self-help articles, celebrity profiles and interviews, and practical how-to information.\n', '', '', ''),
(1136, 1, 'Esquire Spanish', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nESQUIRE (SPANISH) is the original and leading men''s lifestyle magazine. Esquire''s award winning editorial covers everything a man needs to know each month including the latest on style and clothes, what''s new in cars, culture and entertainment and advice on money matters.\n', '', '', ''),
(1137, 1, 'Architectural Digest Sp', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThis is the Spanish-language edition of ARCHITECTURAL DIGEST. In an average of 250 pages each issue, it features fine examples of interior design, art, furnishings and antiques.\n', '', '', ''),
(1138, 1, 'Vogue Spanish', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVOGUE Spanish edition is the fashion authority. Setting the standard for over 100 years has made Vogue the best selling fashion magazine in the world. Each issue delivers the latest in beauty, style, health, fitness and celebrities. Before it''s in fashion, it''s in Vogue!\n', '', '', ''),
(1139, 1, 'El Mueble', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEL MUEBLE is a Spanish house and garden title.  \n', '', '', ''),
(1140, 1, 'Climbing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nClimbing Magazine provides readers with important information for their next climb. Climbing gives details about climbing destinations, equipment needed, as well as training and techniques to use. Climbing also features captivating first-hand accounts of climbs, compelling profiles and beautiful photography. Climbing gives readers motivating editorials, special how-to articles and information about new equipment. In each issue of Climbing, readers will find contacts for guide services, and climbing schools--along with a Marketplace and Suppliers list for easy reference.\n', '', '', ''),
(1141, 1, 'M Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to M magazine is perfect for all teenage girls who love celebrity music and movie industry gossip.\n\nInside M magazine readers will find star features, celebrity style, quizzes, gossip, news, song cards, true life tales, embarrassing stories, horoscopes and more! See celebs caught on camera, find out if there is any truth in recent rumours and check out who''s the best and worst dressed at the moment.\n\nEach issue includes 35 posters and pin-ups and 6 super large posters along with games, quizzes and, of course, the inside scoop on all your favorite stars.\n', '', '', ''),
(1142, 1, 'Jp Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nJP Magazine is America''s first publication dedicated to Jeep owners and enthusiasts. a subscription to JP magazine Covers the entire world of Jeep, from technical how-to articles and backcountry adventures to the latest Jeep upgrades and performance modifications.\n\nPractical, highly technical articles provide expert insight into all types of hardware for every model, from military to modern. Colorful features explore rare and collectible models covering general, historic and rare jeeps.\n\nJP is the magazine for committed Jeep owners and fans turn to for comprehensive info on the repair, restoration and modifications of their Jeeps.\n', '', '', ''),
(1143, 1, 'Analog', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nANALOG SCIENCE FICTION &amp; FACT provides an insight into the infinite world of Science. Gain endless knowledge and pleasure through viewpoints of the most respected authors in the Science field.\n', '', '', ''),
(1144, 1, 'Twist', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTWIST is bulging with coolness! Jam packed with articles on teen fashion, entertainment, trends, love, guys, relationships, real life stories and tons of other cool stuff!\n', '', '', ''),
(1145, 1, 'Diehard', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDiehard Magazine provides comprehensive\n', '', '', ''),
(1146, 1, 'J 14', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nJ-14 is the ultimate magazine subscription for teenage girls!\n\nThe teen Celebrity magazine focuses on interviews with your favourite celebrities from 1D to Justin Bieber, fun quizzes for you and your friends and fashion tips.\n\nWith tons of posters and behind the scene stories on all your favourite stars a subscription to J14 magazine will keep you up to date with all of the latest news and gossip to impress your mates with!\n', '', '', ''),
(1147, 1, 'Popstar Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPopstar! Magazine is a nationally recognized teen-entertainment magazine for kids ages 10 to 16.\n', '', '', ''),
(1148, 1, 'Paper', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPAPER looks at the New York scene. Featuring interviews with celebrities and new music stars, previews of art exhibitions and a diverse assortment of reviews covering food, bars, clubs, films and shops. PAPER has topical discussions, fashion spreads, must-have products and more!\n', '', '', ''),
(1149, 1, 'Slam', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSlam magazine is, simply put, the premiere basketball magazine on the market today.\n\nYour subscription to Slam magazine covers NBA, WNBA, NCAA Men''s, NCAA Women''s, the international game, high-school, and even street ball. Every issue has in-depth, exclusive interviews with top basketball stars and coaches and fascinating opinion/editorial pieces from the editors.\n\nSlam Magazine is hip and edgy and dedicated to the sport of basketball.\n', '', '', ''),
(1150, 1, 'Finescale Modeler', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFINESCALE MODELER is packed full of models, trains, planes, boats and military models. Articles include modelling projects, new products, kits and accessories, as well as everything on building, repairing, maintaining and collecting models. FINE SCALE MODELER features tips on creating realistic roads and runways and features on painting complex graphics\n', '', '', ''),
(1151, 1, 'Jewelry Artist', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nWith a subscription to Jewelry Artist magazine, you''ll enjoy fantastic projects with easy to follow full-color photos and diagrams, a featured gemstone, a design challenge and the ever popular Cool Tools and Hip Tips.\n\nJewelry Artist magazine will keep you up to date on the latest jewelry design trends and help you create your own one-of-a-kind jewelry.\n\nReaders will continue to find much of the same content, written by many of the same experts, that they value in Lapidary Journal today. Answers to technical questions, clever tool adaptations, innovative designs and practical design advice.\n\nJewelry and lapidary projects, tips and in-depth explanations on using materials and applying techniques, guidance on how to sell jewelry, new products, an event calendar, and much more with every issue of your subscription.\n', '', '', ''),
(1152, 1, 'Dance Spirit', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDANCE SPIRIT is a full-colour magazine covering all aspects of dance for all ages. DANCE SPIRIT features competitions, scripts, interviews, book and video reviews.\n', '', '', ''),
(1153, 1, 'Sound &amp; Vision', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSOUND &amp; VISION is America''s number one audio magazine for people who share a love of music and its faithful reproduction. Each monthly issue offers balanced coverage of audio equipment of all component types and all price ranges, technical developments, recordings on disc and tape, world-famous laboratory evaluations and equipment test reports.\n', '', '', ''),
(1154, 1, 'Sport-Fishing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSPORT FISHING is a US title all about saltwater fishing. The magazine covers a varierty of topics on different fishes to look out for, it covers topical issues such as overfishing and habitat destruction, features government legislation and new laws brought into control the sport and the ill effects this is having on fishermen today.\n', '', '', ''),
(1155, 1, 'Fitness', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFITNESS is a health, nutrition and beauty magazine for health conscious women. It features the latest exercise trends and offers tips on exercise and diet to help you to look good and feel great. If you want to tone certain areas of your body up FITNESS is a magazine which helps you target the right parts. It is the must-have magazine for all round fitness and health.\n', '', '', ''),
(1156, 1, 'Sport Rider', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSport Rider magazine helps riders get maximum performance from their motorcycles. Each issue of Sport Rider magazine features track tests, comparisons of the newest and hottest bikes and helpful tips on riding skills and techniques for maximizing performance without compromising safety.\n', '', '', ''),
(1157, 1, 'Seventeen', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSeventeen Magazine has been an icon since 1944, pioneered the young women''s magazine market, and is still the leader with the 12-24 age group, and a dominant force in the culture. Seventeen is best described as a mix between just Seventeen and Company magazines.\n\nSeventeen magazine is the most popular magazine for teenage girls featuring the latest scoop on Style, Friends, Guys, College, Careers, the Stars and Love.\n\nEach issue of your Seventeen magazine subscription includes hot tips on beauty, fashion, fitness and relationships. Seventeen Magazine provides exciting features including fiction, quizzes, music, videos, trends, and cool articles like Trauma-Rama!\n', '', '', ''),
(1158, 1, 'Boating', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA BOATING magazine subscription is indispensable to the serious power boatman. The magazine is dedicated to sportsmen, distributors &amp; manufacturers in the powerboat industry, written by people in the know.\nEvery issue is packed with nautical adventure, practical tips and accounts of major racing events, as well as regular articles on boat buying and financing, powerboat accessories, seamanship, maintenance, sport fishing, racing, and sport cruising.\nBuy a subscription to BOATING magazine today to get every issue delivered directly to your door, ensuring you never miss an issue!\n', '', '', ''),
(1159, 1, 'Fast Company', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFAST COMPANY magazine covers all aspects of business, finance and technology. Every issue contains interviews with those making the business and highlights the latest e-developments\n', '', '', ''),
(1160, 1, 'The Horse Back St Choppers', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Horse Street Back Choppers has established itself as a high quality publication with an intensity loyal readership.\n\nThe riding public is thirsty for a publication that satisfies the craving for home built chops, bobbers and creative custom and The Horse Backstreet Choppers delivers.\n\nWhile other publications cater to the so called “master builders”, we here at The Horse recognize that the real master builders are not the rhinestone bikers, but the average Joe who struggles to make ends meet.\n', '', '', ''),
(1161, 1, 'Hgtv', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to HGTV makes a perfect gift!\n\nHGTV Magazine gives readers inspiring, real-life solutions for all the things that homeowners deal with every day — from painting to pillows to property values — in an upbeat and engaging way.\n\nSubscribe to HGTV and you can spruce up your porch, brighten up your lounge or personalise the playroom. Packed full of bright ideas.\n', '', '', ''),
(1162, 1, 'Food Network', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFood Network is a new food magazine from Hearst USA which features scores of mouth-watering recipes and top tips from the professionals in every issue.\n', '', '', ''),
(1163, 1, 'Peloton', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWe are about racing and the joy of riding. About the product and the people behind the technology. About the glory of cycling and the riders who test the limits of their human capacity. About discovering the nuances and sharing the sport we love. We delve into the history and explore the future to bring every angle to life. We are an enthusiastic collective of writers, photographers, designers and bike junkies who are not here to impose our tastes, but instead share the sport with you as we see and live it. We present this in a clean, thoughtfully designed format with a modern aesthetic and appreciation for beautiful imagery that flows seamlessly across our print, film and digital productions. We shy away from the clutter, disruption and noise to get to the heart of cycling. Peloton is biking speak for a pack of riders and this magazine as the name suggest is perfect for the experienced road bike racer.\n', '', '', ''),
(1164, 1, 'Details', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMen''s Lifestyle magazine from the US, Details is one of our favourites in this category.\n\nAimed at the 25+ market it''s a good mix of all the usual topic that are important to this male audience.\n', '', '', ''),
(1165, 1, 'Interview', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nINTERVIEW is a mixture of fashion, music and movies and is one of America''s most highly respected fashion magazines.\n', '', '', ''),
(1166, 1, 'Nylon', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNYLON covers everything from fashion and music to film, celebrities, gossip, chat and more!\n', '', '', ''),
(1167, 1, 'Inked', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nINKED is a tattoo and lifestyle magazine, that focuses on the latest in art, music, entertainment, style and culture and delivers them to a savvy generation of forward thinking individuals. Rather than just concentrating on tattoos it appeals to a lifestyle with in depth articles on areas of interest for forward thinking free spirits.\n', '', '', ''),
(1168, 1, 'W Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA W magazine subscription is perfect for anyone with a real interest in fashion. W magazine is a bible for all real fashionistas.\n\nIt tells you what you should be wearing and how you should be wearing it.\n\nThe W magazine reader is sophisticated and affluent, interested in fashion, beauty, travel, prominent people and stylish living.\n', '', '', ''),
(1169, 1, 'Homiletic &amp; Pastoral Review', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHomiletic &amp; Pastoral Review Magazine is the premiere publication for clergy and laity interested in pastoral issues, offering practical insights into living, celebrating and spreading the Catholic Faith today. HPR provides pastors and the lay faithful up-to-date, yet authentically Catholic articles on pressing moral, theological and liturgical matters. Each issue includes outstanding homilies for Sundays and holy days by some of today''s top homilists. Also included are book reviews and practical, insightful questions and answers by one of America''s leading moral theologians, Msgr. William Smith, as well as informative, faith-filled articles.\n', '', '', ''),
(1170, 1, 'Art News', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nART NEWS brings you all the latest news from within the world of art. ARTWORLD takes the reader on a visually stimulating tour of some of the world''s finest paintings. ART NEWS keeps you well informed with the goings on, ensuring you don''t miss a thing!\n', '', '', ''),
(1171, 1, 'Discover', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDiscover magazine is a science publication which brings new technologies to our attention, examines scientific and medical breakthroughs and explains and explores the world around us and the laws by which it is governed in a scientific way.\n\nDiscover more about the world and learn about those on the forefront of technology: pushing back the boundaries of ignorance with every issue, this publication may be slim, but it will change and inform your perspective on everything.\n', '', '', ''),
(1172, 1, 'Out', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nOUT is America''s foremost gay &amp; lesbian publication. All aspects of life are covered including news, fashion, health and fitness\n', '', '', ''),
(1173, 1, 'Bicycling', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBicycling magazine covers the entire spectrum of cycling from road cycling to mountain biking to leisurely biking.\n\nEach issue of Bicycling magazine features training plans, product reviews and expert advice. A US magazine covering the cycling world.\n', '', '', ''),
(1174, 1, 'Popular Mechanics', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Popular Mechanics magazine is great for all mechanic lovers from cars to web and space technology.\n\nPopular Mechanics magazine is a chronicle of emerging technology and innovation, looking at cars, trucks, motorcycles, and other automobiles issues. It delves into different areas explaining how things work in a way that everyone can understand . The magazine also features a column by &quot;Tonight Show&quot; host and biker Jay Leno.\n\nPOPULAR MECHANICS really does cover everything!\n', '', '', ''),
(1175, 1, 'Lucky', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Lucky Magazine is the monthly guide to the world of shopping! If you love to shop, you''ll adore Lucky magazine.\n\nEvery fun, fabulous issue has the passion, the pleasure, and the personal style of shopping your way, including thousands of incredible finds for you, your home and your life NOW.\n\nWhere to get the look for less, the best of each season in every color, style and shape. Plus complete buying information to get what you want at the best price now!\n\nOrder a subscription to Lucky today and start shopping!\n', '', '', ''),
(1176, 1, 'Folio', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFolio Magazine has been recognized as the magazine of magazine management since 1972. Each issue features industry news, trends and newsmakers, as well as the latest techniques and technology influencing the industry. Whether your primary interest is in management, editorial, advertising or circulation this magazine is an essential tool of the trade\n', '', '', ''),
(1177, 1, 'Art In America', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA monthly subscription to Art In America magazine showcases the best the world has to offer in contemporary art. Art in America magazine is designed for artists, dealers, collectors and professionals from the art world. It has a large critique section where various forms of art from sculpture to painting to photography are extensively covered. Regular features in Art in America magazine include profiles of artists and genres, updates on modern art movements as well as a number of show reviews and exhibition reviews. This subscription for Art in America is great for people who have a real appreciation of contemporary and modern art.\n', '', '', ''),
(1178, 1, 'True Confessions', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTRUE CONFESSIONS a magazine about love and romance\n', '', '', ''),
(1179, 1, 'True Story', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTRUE STORY is a magazine aimed at women about romance and Love\n', '', '', ''),
(1180, 1, 'Prevention', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPrevention magazine offers smart ways to live well! Prevention magazine has been providing readers with the most current information on health, fitness, nutrition and cutting edge medical news for more than 50 years; it is the most authoritative, trustworthy and innovative magazine for practical health information.\n\nA prevention magazine subscription informs nearly 12 million readers each month on new developments in nutrition, fitness, weight control, food preparation and body care. Prevention magazine also motivates readers to take charge of their health.\n', '', '', ''),
(1181, 1, 'High Performance Pontiac', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHigh Performance Pontiac Magazine is edited for enthusiast who love Pontiacs, old and new. The magazine covers the world of Pontiacs- collecting, restoring, modifying for more performance and customizing for show. Each issue of High Performance Pontiac features Pontiacs from the early 50''s fuel injected cars, through the muscle cars of the 60''s and 70''s, and right through to today''s Trans-Am.\n', '', '', ''),
(1182, 1, 'Hot Rod Bikes', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHot Rod Bikes Magazine is the authority for Harley builders. Hot Rod Bikes consistently delivers a comprehensive, instructional, technically accurate editorial package that informs and inspires readers to change, modify and improve their Harley-Davidsons.\n', '', '', ''),
(1183, 1, 'Cotswold Style', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA monthly luxurious lifestyle magazine, which captures both the traditional and modern way of life. It is the essential guide to enjoying the best this region can offer. Each issue cover s area features, fashion, interiors, property, real life interviews, social events, motoring, sport, business and much more... ', '', '', ''),
(1184, 1, 'Tiger Beat', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTIGER BEAT is an American magazine for teenagers. Inside readers will find celeb gossip, posters, celebrity advice and interviews, superstar embarrassing moments, celebrity couples, quizzes, song lyrics, star looks and style, film, TV show and music reviews, horoscopes and more!\n', '', '', ''),
(1185, 1, 'Soldier Of Fortune', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSOLDIER OF FORTUNE has in-depth features on terrorism, weapons and defence, in addition to revealing articles on conflict in countries around the globe, weapon reviews, a bulletin board, supply addresses and classified ads.\n', '', '', ''),
(1186, 1, 'Log Home Living', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLog Home Living is for the passionate log home enthusiast. Whether you are dreaming of, remodeling, or building a log home you will find indispensable advice, how-to guides, building plans, and inspirational photo features and interviews with people who own log homes.\n', '', '', ''),
(1187, 1, 'Railfan &amp; Railroad', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe finest contributors in the field share their excitement and provide an insight into the subject of their passion. Each issue includes book and video reviews and uses quality colour photography throughout.\n', '', '', ''),
(1188, 1, 'Transworld Motocross', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to TRANSWORLD MOTOCROSS magazine offers both hardcore riders and casual fans one source for comprehensive news on the people, places and products that make motocross exciting and unique.Every issue in a subscription to TransWorld Motocross Magazine targets the mainstream motocross enthusiast. Progressive art direction, spectacular photography, and all 4-color editorial content make this a leader in the field.\n', '', '', ''),
(1189, 1, 'Dressage Today', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThis is an American publication with reviews on competitions and riding tips as well as interviews with those who have excelled in the world of horse dressage.\n\nDressage Today magazine features profiles of the leading dressage riders, along with techniques, guidance and encouragement from the experts.\n\nThe magazine is released every month and is ideal for readers looking to improve their techniques and hopefully compete in competitions and pass tests with ease.\n', '', '', ''),
(1190, 1, 'Sister 2 Sister', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSISTER 2 SISTER is a black woman''s guide to classy gossip and hot secrets. It covers music, interviews and celebrities.\n', '', '', ''),
(1191, 1, 'Massage Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMassage Magazine is the definitive massage and touch-therapy resource for practitioners, instructors, students, and consumers around the world. Massage has a team of professional journalists, editors, massage practitioners, artists, and designers that are dedicated to covering the art and science of touch therapies. Founded in 1985, Massage Magazine is the first and only independent magazine dedicated to this purpose.\n', '', '', ''),
(1192, 1, 'Miniature Collector Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMiniature Collector is the world''s favorite dollhouse and miniatures magazine. Twelve times a year readers on five continents delight in our full-color editorial coverage of artisans, collections, shows and projects. Master artisans'' exquisitely detailed furniture, accessories and dollhouses epitomize the magazine''s standard of excellence while beautifully photographed settings showcase collectors'' outstanding taste.\n', '', '', ''),
(1193, 1, 'Womans Day', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWoman''s Day is one of the oldest and most beloved of all the traditional women''s magazines, although it has evolved to fit the needs of modern readers. Each issue of a Womans Day magazine subscription is packed with recipes, homemaking tips, and poignant articles. Woman''s Day provides discussions, advice, and a new perspective on how the modern woman lives her life today. Topics covered within Woman''s Day include relationships, health, nutrition, dating, beauty, and family.\n', '', '', ''),
(1194, 1, 'The Writer', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe Writer Magazine was founded in Boston in 1887 and ever since then has been an invaluable resource for professional writers. Every issue of your subscription to The Writer magazine helps hopeful scribes become the writer they''ve always wanted to be - and help them produce the kind of writing that people will pay money to read! Discover how to use the internet to further writing careers...learn the techniques that helped other writers get published...get the latest market listings...hear about upcoming contests and conferences...and much more!\n\nEach month The Writer magazine is full of features you can use to improve your writing, including before-and-after examples of improved writing, more literary markets than ever before, practical solutions for writing problems, selected literary magazine profiles, tips from famous authors and hands-on advice.\n', '', '', ''),
(1195, 1, 'Dirt Rider', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGet all the excitement that comes from the world of motorcross with each issue of Dirt Rider, covering the thrilling world of off-road motorcycling and motorcross for professionals and amateurs alike.\n\nCourse and equipment reviews, personalities and profiles of motorcross newsmakers and cutting-edge photography color this most informative US publication.\n', '', '', ''),
(1196, 1, 'Car Craft', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIf you’ve got a burning desire for speed and a love for American cars, then a copy of Car Craft magazine is exactly what you need\n\nIf your love is for a Ford, your devotion is to a Daimler or you’re crazy about Chryslers and Corvettes, and you love tuning an engine to within an inch of its life then you will fell at home.\n\nFilled with reviews of the latest motors and equipment, great articles on motor-racing and instructive tips and guides to restoring and getting the very best out of your car, this magazine is for those who aren’t afraid of getting their hands dirty and know their prop-shafts and torque-converters. A real men’s magazine for those who appreciate the art and power of the car.\n', '', '', ''),
(1197, 1, 'Dirt Wheels', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDirt Wheels magazine is produced in America, the publication covers the entire world of dirt biking, racing, dune blasting, trail riding, the latest must-have gear and so much more.\n\nDirt Wheels magazine also does the toughest testing, so you know everything about the ATV or product you want to buy is accurate and independently accessed.\n\nThe magazine is released on a monthly basis and is a must-read for any fan of dirt biking who is hungry for more information\n', '', '', ''),
(1198, 1, 'Mental Floss', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMENTAL FLOSS is the premier publication for making knowledge accessible. People love to feel smart but don''t have enough time to work for that knowledge. By blurring the lines between education and entertainment, MENTAL FLOSS takes the chore out of learning by presenting information in quick, simple quirky and fun manner ceased hidden 06/03/12\n', '', '', ''),
(1199, 1, 'Railroad Model Craftsman', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRailroad Model Craftsman Magazine delivers the best in model railroading twelve times a year. Our goal is to inspire the creativity and craftsmanship of modellers from the first-time novice to the experienced\n', '', '', ''),
(1200, 1, 'Popular Hot Rodding', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Popular Hot Rodding Magazine is for the American automotive enthusiast with articles on projects, performance, technical items, products and upcoming events.\n\nEach issue of Popular Hot Rodding magazine provides readers with technical articles on high performance engine building plus exactly what products and services the enthusiast must have to complete his project.\n\nOther topics covered in Popular Hot Rodding magazine include tuning secrets, new and innovative product announcements and interior and exterior treatments for the enthusiast who is modifying, racing or restoring his American made performance car. High profile event coverage is also a critical element of Popular Hot Rodding Magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(1201, 1, 'Baggers', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBaggers Features section showcases motorcycle shops and builders, customized Harley Davidson motorcycles, Buell and chopper bikes.\n\nFind softail, hardtail and rigid choppers, and custom motorcycles built by American motorcycle builders.\n', '', '', ''),
(1202, 1, 'Car &amp; Driver', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCAR &amp; DRIVER is America''s No.1 automobile magazine subscription with a legion of dedicated readers. The magazine is for automobile enthusiasts interested in domestic and imported autos. Each monthly issue celebrates the automobile in all its forms - from sleek sports cars and racers to classic autos and sturdy sedans. Authoritative road tests, articles on performance, details of innovative engines and accessories are presented in a blend of ironic humour and technical credibilty that makes CAR &amp; DRIVER unique. If you’re looking for any more reasons to subscribe, just remember that you’ll never miss an issue and the latest copy will be delivered to your door every month. So what are you waiting? Order a CAR &amp; DRIVER magazine subscription today!\n', '', '', ''),
(1203, 1, 'Guns &amp; Ammo', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe Guns and Ammo magazine subscription is edited for sportsmen with an interest in the practical application of sporting firearms and emphasizes their safe and proper use.\n\nGuns and Ammo magazine delivers an editorial mix that includes hunting, shooting, reloading, antique and modern arms, ballistics and arms legislation. As well, it contains information about natural resource and environmental protection, new products and trends.\n', '', '', ''),
(1204, 1, 'Harpers', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHARPER''S MAGAZINE is an award-winning journal of opinion and thought, edited to speak to readers looking for perspectives not generally found in mainstream media.\n', '', '', ''),
(1205, 1, 'Astronomy', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe world''s best-selling astronomy magazine offers you the most exciting, visually stunning, and timely coverage of the heavens above.\n\nEach monthly issue includes expert science reporting, vivid colour photography, complete sky coverage, spot-on observing tips, informative telescope reviews, and much more! All this in an easy-to-understand, user-friendly style that''s perfect for astronomers at any level.\n', '', '', ''),
(1206, 1, 'Downbeat', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDown Beat magazine, the monthly\n', '', '', ''),
(1207, 1, 'Four Wheeler', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFeaturing articles on travel and adventure, technical advice and how-to guides as well as test results.\n', '', '', ''),
(1208, 1, 'Trains', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nTrains magazine is the USA''s leading magazine on railroading. It contains the most authoritative features on trains in the USA both past and present.\n\nWith a subscription to Trains magazine, experience the power, history, and drama of America''s railroads, the best inside information, industry news, and award-winning photography- all these factors make this leading publication the favorite magazine of railroad enthusiasts!\n', '', '', ''),
(1209, 1, 'American Iron', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAmerican Iron Magazine is an American based motorcycle magazine. The magazine specialises in the coverage of American-made motorcycles. The magazine covers articles on bikes such as Harley-Davidson and Big Dog Motorcycles. Typical articles include how to repair most minor problems with the bikes. It also contains features on custom built bikes, reviews on new models and reviews on the latest related gear in the industry.\n', '', '', ''),
(1210, 1, 'Cycle World', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCovering every area of motorcycles, from off-road to superbike, Cycle World (USA) is no pedalling based publication.\n\nThis US based publication looks at every aspect of motorcycling – you will find coverage Harleys, off-roaders, high-performance road bikes and more in each issue, with great features looking at prolific riders, bikes, and the future of motorcycling.\n\nThere are tests and evaluations of the latest kit, with new bikes put through their paces and gear such as tire warmers reviewed, looks at racing, and columns and editorials looking at the world of cycling, making this perfect for anyone who loves motorbikes whatever the type\n', '', '', ''),
(1211, 1, 'Rc Heli', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe world''s best selling magazine dedicated to the world of Radio Controlled Helicopters. RC Heli features articles each month by the world''s top RC helicopter authors. Each issue is packed with unbiased product tests, reviews, news, informative how-to articles written for beginners to experts, and features you can''t find anywhere else.\n', '', '', ''),
(1212, 1, 'Tattoo Ideas', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEvery issue of TATTOO IDEAS includes hundreds of exclusive designs, created by professional artists for readers to choose a real tattoo from. TATTOO IDEAS us a much-imitated, permanent fixture in Tattoo and Body Art studios everywhere.\n', '', '', ''),
(1213, 1, 'Ultimate Mma', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nULTIMATE MMA (FORMALLY GRAPPLING) has in-depth interviews and provides analysis of the great Martial Arts Legends of past and present, describing how they shaped the world of Martial Arts and what made them so great. Each issue focuses on a different aspect of Martial Arts.\n', '', '', ''),
(1214, 1, 'Outside Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCreated for the active reader, Outside is the magazine devoted to travel, fitness, outdoor gear and sports. Whether you like rock climbing or mountain biking, each issue provides the best coverage of these an other exciting outdoor activities. Vacation tips and profiles of outdoor enthusiasts, along with colourful action photography make this a great resource for the active soul!\n', '', '', ''),
(1215, 1, 'Sail', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSAIL is edited for both novice and expert sailors alike. Its feature articles are written for both large and small boat sailors covering an array of topics including design, rigging, tuning, sail trim, spinnaker handling, wind and water conditions and the practical considerations of owning a sailboat. Its regular departments include boat and equipment design commentary, new boat and product news, racing news, seamanship, boat handling, navigation and piloting.\n', '', '', ''),
(1216, 1, 'The Ring', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTHE RING is the boxing bible in the United States, and well established in the U.K. market. A4, glossy and full colour, THE RING provides an exciting and authoritative account of what is happening in the boxing world.\n', '', '', ''),
(1217, 1, 'Drum U S A', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe leading magazine for today''s young drummers and hand percussionists. Each issue is packed with lessons, product reviews, helpful equipment tips and no-holds-barred artist interviews. When something new happens in the world of drumming read about it first in Drum!\n', '', '', ''),
(1218, 1, 'Jazztimes', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nJazz Times,features daily news, CD reviews, discussion forums, festival listings, merchandise, and contests.\n', '', '', ''),
(1219, 1, 'Popular Science', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPopular Science magazine translates complex scientific and technological jargon into everyday language. Popular science is the ''what''s new'' magazine concentrating on science and technology.\n\nEach issue of Popular Science magazine features new projects, discoveries and advances in technology including cars, electronics, aviation, communications, tools, space, science and much more.\n\nSubscribe to Popular Science magazine today and keep updated with all the latest technology news!\n', '', '', ''),
(1220, 1, 'Velo', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVelo is the home of Competitive Cycling, covering both European and American Road racing. Every issue of VeloNews is filled with comprehensive news, exclusive rider interviews, expert training advice, unbiased gear reviews and the best race analysis\n', '', '', ''),
(1221, 1, 'Flying', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFLYING is the world''s most widely read aviation magazine. Featuring in-depth articles on pilot proficiency, navigation, weather safety, new equipment, travel and more! FLYING provides the latest FAA and industry news and covers both private and business flying.\n', '', '', ''),
(1222, 1, 'Rider', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRIDER-The premier motorcycle magazine for travel tour and adventure. Each issue showcases extensive road tests, tips on the best places to go and how to get there, up to date new models and hot products in the motorcycle industry. RIDER is the must - read magazine for the serious motorcycle rider.\n', '', '', ''),
(1223, 1, 'Bass Player', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBass Player magazine is the world''s number one bass publication around at the moment. Each month the magazine will bring the readers amazing interviews with the world''s top bassists around as well as useful hints and tips on technique.\n\nThe readers will also be treated to fascinating hands-on lessons in every style of playing imaginable. Bass Player magazine will also offer the reader comprehensive reviews of basses, amps, effects and much more.\n', '', '', ''),
(1224, 1, 'Model Airplane News', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMODEL AIRPLANE NEWS is a pioneering aeromodelling publication, having been in print since 1929. From detailed reviews of kits to clearly laid out how-to articles, MODEL AIRPLANE NEWS reflects the excitement of building and flying models and covers the evolving technology of engines, electric motors, building techniques and control systems.\n', '', '', ''),
(1225, 1, 'Shape Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPublished by Weider, SHAPE USA magazine covers all aspects of fitness and health. These include in depth articles on nutrition, diet, exercise and how to cope with stress. Every issue is jam packed with health, beauty, fitness and lifestyle ideas\n', '', '', ''),
(1226, 1, 'Muscular Development Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMUSCULAR DEVELOPMENT USA is the magazine for men who want to build muscle and burn fat. Each issue profiles new exercises and bodybuilding techniques designed to get the most out of your body.\n', '', '', ''),
(1227, 1, 'Redbook', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nREDBOOK is the total-life guide for every woman blazing her own path through adulthood and taking on new roles- wife, mom, homeowner, without letting go of the unique woman she''s worked so hard to become. REDBOOK offers a vibrant mix of just-for-her fashion and beauty coverage. Get-stuff-done, from money and mealtime to health and home. Thoughtful features on marriage, relationships and family.\n', '', '', ''),
(1228, 1, 'Skin &amp; Ink', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSkin &amp; Ink celebrates the world of Tattoos.\n', '', '', ''),
(1229, 1, 'American Bagger', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAmerican Bagger magazine focuses on the hottest new products for enthusiastic motorcycle fans.\n\nAmerican Bagger features technical advice, upcoming events and a photo gallery of past events.\n\nSubscribe now and follow all the events and news over the coming year.\n', '', '', ''),
(1230, 1, 'Motocross Action', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMOTOCROSS ACTION is America''s leading Motocross magazine, covering events from around the world. There are interviews with the major riders and championship contenders, together with the inside track on the latest motocross news.\n', '', '', ''),
(1231, 1, 'Success Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSUCCESS magazine is designed specifically to serve the growing entrepreneur, the home-based and small-business markets. SUCCESS magazine is not only inspirational but also instructional in taking a balanced approach to success by offering guidance and insight into improving one s entire life. Our mission is for SUCCESS to become the foremost trusted source for personal achievement resources. Total success requires developing all areas of your personal and professional life, and each issue will focus on five key areas for achieving success: business, relationships, wealth, well-being and making a difference\n', '', '', ''),
(1232, 1, 'Audioxpress', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAudioXpress Magazine is devoted to do-it-yourself audio. From speakers to amplifiers and preamps, vacuum tube technology to the newest in digital, audioXpress features construction projects to build, along with tips and tweaks to upgrade equipment, as well as articles and reviews to inform. Each issue of AudioXpress is filled with design ideas, projects to build, and articles on cutting-edge audio topics.\n', '', '', ''),
(1233, 1, 'Hot Rod', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHot Rod Magazine from the US gives you all the news from the Hot Rod world along with new and established hot rodding techniques.\n', '', '', ''),
(1234, 1, 'Ride Bmx Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRIDE BMX features the last word in BMX. It is aimed at BMX enthusiasts who want more from their BMX. It is packed full of photos and descriptions of how to do the latest cool moves. It gets up close to BMX champions and shows you now to be the best. RIDE BMX gives you the latest in cool gear that you will need to look your best\n', '', '', ''),
(1235, 1, 'Juxtapoz', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to JUXTAPOZ magazine, The brainchild of renowned cartoon surrealism artist Robert Williams, presents a gallery of influential, underground artists who shape today''s fashion, graphics and new art movements.\n\nEach issue of Juxtapoz magazine includes full colour layouts from painters, sculptors, cartoonists and photographers, as well as interviews, rare portfolios sketches and reviews.\n', '', '', ''),
(1236, 1, 'Popular Communications', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPOPULAR COMMUNICATION features authoritative information on scanner monitoring of police, fire, utility and aircraft transmissions as well as short wave listening, monitoring short wave digital, fax and teletype broadcasts, CB radio, alternative radio, clandestine radio, telephones and wiretapping\n', '', '', ''),
(1237, 1, 'Ebony', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEBONY is an essential buy for the black women of today offering advice on relationships and love. Each issue features fashion, hot beauty tips, health issues, food, travel, book reviews and more\n', '', '', ''),
(1238, 1, 'Modern Drummer', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMODERN DRUMMER is the world''s most widely-read drum magazine. Each issue includes interviews and features with the world''s top drummers. Also included are reviews of the latest drum equipment and tutorials from the experts. MODERN DRUMMER is the only magazine for the modern day drummer.\n', '', '', ''),
(1239, 1, 'Motor Trend', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMOTOR TREND is a contemporary world car magazine which provides evaluations of automotive products for all varieties and styles of cars. Its feature material includes motor sport and technical departments, auto industry news, styling and engineering details, safety reports, race car reviews, equipment and accessory buyers  guides and impressions of new trucks and off-road vehicles.\n', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `oc_product_description` (`product_id`, `language_id`, `name`, `description`, `meta_description`, `meta_keyword`, `tag`) VALUES
(1240, 1, 'Mountain Bike Action Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMOUNTAIN BIKE ACTION USA covers all aspects of the sport and leisure pursuit from the serious rider to the weekend user. Its features include hints and tips on maintenance and in-depth new product reviews.\n', '', '', ''),
(1241, 1, 'Hot Bike', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\na subscription to Hot Bike Magazine is for the new breed of Harley rider.\n\nHot Bike magazine includes regular features on technical information, how-to articles and event coverage as well as road tests.\n\nEach issue of Hot Bike magazine also reviews high performance components, riding apparel and accessories, and provides product evaluations, in-depth tech help designed to provide the Harley enthusiast all the information necessary to make an informed purchase.\n', '', '', ''),
(1242, 1, 'House Beautiful Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBuy a subscription to House Beautiful magazine and make your home the house you have always dreamt of. Packed full of inspirational tips and advice. From where to find what you are looking for to tips on how to create the look you wish to achieve on a budget.A subscription to House Beautiful magazine introduces possibilities in the context of individuality, diversity and simplicity with an emphasis on comfortable rooms that are lived in.The editorial in House Beautful magazine encompasses interior design, remodeling, architecture, travel, entertaining, gardening and more.Purchase a magazine subscription to House Beautiful today and let your creativity run wild.\n', '', '', ''),
(1243, 1, 'Self', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSelf magazine is aimed at active and professional women between 25-35 who lead demanding lives and need to read something thought-provoking and informative.\n\nEach issue of your Self magazine subscription provides information to help women attain individual satisfaction and features articles on beauty, health, fitness, psychology, food, fashion, culture, careers, politics and the environment.\n', '', '', ''),
(1244, 1, 'V-Twin', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nV-TWIN is a biker lifestyle magazine from the same publisher as EASYRIDERS magazine. Published in California, V-TWIN has close links to Harley Davidson, providing readers with the latest news as well as the Tattoo and Biker events from around the world.\n', '', '', ''),
(1245, 1, 'American Cinematographer', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAMERICAN CINEMATOGRAPHER is the international journal of film and digital production techniques. Inside each issue readers will find in-depth features on subjects such as film icons, film studios, new technologies in cinematography, film and book reviews, new products and services, classified ads, an ad index, a filmakers forum and more!\n', '', '', ''),
(1246, 1, 'Entrepreneur', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEntrepreneur magazine is the leading authority for growing businesses.\n\nEntrepreneur brings readers invaluable tips,innovations,technology, updates, moner management ideas, marketing solutions and management insights and more.\n', '', '', ''),
(1247, 1, 'Rue Morgue', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRue Morgue magazine outlines those cinematic gems you may have missed, classic and contemporary, mainstream and obscure, home made and foreign and those films that simply need to make your viewing list.\n\nRue Morgue is the worlds leading horror in culture and entertainment.\n', '', '', ''),
(1248, 1, 'Tattoo', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTATTOO is devoted to the age-old art of body tattooing. Regular features include designs from some of the world''s most famous tattoo artists, along with an update of some of the biggest tattoo events world-wide.\n', '', '', ''),
(1249, 1, 'Golf Digest', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to GOLF DIGEST magazine will keep you up to date with all of the latest golf news from both sides of the Atlantic. With in depth coverage from both the American and European Tour events including stats and player information, keep up to date with this monthly magazine subscription and impress your friends on the golf course.\n\nEach month your golf Digest Magazine will include top tips for all levels from beginners right up to scratch players along with interviews and opinions from the pros.\n\nBuy a Golf Digest magazine subscription today and keep your passion for golf alive!!\n', '', '', ''),
(1250, 1, 'Sky &amp; Telescope', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNominated the world''s best astronomy magazine by Patrick Moore, SKY &amp; TELESCOPE is essential reading for anyone keeping abreast of the sky at night.\n', '', '', ''),
(1251, 1, 'Alternative Press', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Alternative Press magazine subscription focuses on American alternative rock music. Alternative Press magazine provides its readers with a variety of content that includes band interviews, photos, and info on up and coming gigs as well as releases. Alternative Press magazine was started by Mike Shea in 1985 in an attempt to give more media coverage of underground music. Monthly features include ''In the Studio'', ''10 Essential'', ''Chalkboard Confessional'' and ''AP &amp; R (Unsigned band of the month)''. A subscription to Alternative Press is a must for all dedicated to alternative, indie, ska, electronic, dub, punk, techno, underground, rock and experimental.\n', '', '', ''),
(1252, 1, 'Model Railroader', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Model Railroader magazine shows readers how to design and build realistic model railroad layouts. Every issue is packed with ideas, plans, expert tips and inspiring colour photos.\n\nModel Raiolroader magazine, the world''s most popular model railroading magazine, is ideal for beginning or expert hobbyists. It features step-by-step modeling projects, fascinating photo tours of model train layouts, insightful reviews, tips from the experts, and so much more.\n\nModel Railroading magazine includes how to guides and reviews of the newest and best products. Published since 1934 it is the USA''s leading model train magazine with subscribers the world over. It is a must for all enthusiastic model railway builders.\n', '', '', ''),
(1253, 1, 'Robb Report', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nROBB REPORT is the magazine for the luxury lifestyle, featuring only the finest homes, boats, cars and planes.\n', '', '', ''),
(1254, 1, 'Better Homes And Gardens', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBetter Homes &amp; Gardens magazine is a US based magazine which focuses on helping readers to give their homes and garden a design overhaul.\n\nThe magazine will give useful decorating, building and remodelling ideas. It will also provide interesting features on the latest crafts, the best way to entertain and delicious cooking ideas. br/&gt;\nThe magazine likes to give readers simple ideas to improve their lives at home and make everyday routines much easier\n', '', '', ''),
(1255, 1, 'Country Living Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCOUNTRY LIVING USA is much more than a country lifestyle magazine. Published by the Hearst Corporation it has the high-quality production and editorial values you expect from a prestigious publisher.\n', '', '', ''),
(1256, 1, 'Radio Control Car Action', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRADIO CONTROL CAR ACTION is a colourful new magazine specially for dedicated radio control hobbyists worldwide. HIDDEN AS CEASED PUB FROM JAN 11 ISSUE\n', '', '', ''),
(1257, 1, 'Road &amp; Track', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nROAD &amp; TRACK is the single most important newsstand magazine for auto lovers, appealing to consumers and professionals alike. Every issue is packed with important information and road tests, highlighting the best of the auto industry.\n', '', '', ''),
(1258, 1, 'Stereophile', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nStereophile magazine is devoted to high-end audio and features equipment reports describing how hi-fi components actually sound, regardless of their specifications.\n\nEach issue of your Stereophile magazine subscription also includes articles on audio and recorded music, interviews with audio engineers and musicians, news on the developments in sound reproduction, and scholarly and entertaining record reviews.\n\nThe experts at Stereophile magazine perform detailed technical assessments using state-of-the-art equipment, and manufacturers of tested products respond to reviews in the same issue.\n', '', '', ''),
(1259, 1, 'Surfing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFull colour, action shots, women in bikinis - SURFING magazine is the ultimate sports accessory for surfers.\n', '', '', ''),
(1260, 1, 'Transworld Skateboarding', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTRANSWORLD SKATEBOARDING contains everything that today''s skateboarders need to know - the latest cool moves, skateboarding gear, accessories and music. This is THE complete skateboarding guide that fans will not want to miss out on!\n', '', '', ''),
(1261, 1, 'Locus Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLocus Magazine has coverered the science fiction and fantasy field since 1968. Locus publishes news of the Science Fiction publishing field with extensive reviews and listings of new science fiction books and magazines.\n', '', '', ''),
(1262, 1, 'Cq Amateur Radio', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe communication based magazine for those interested in or running their own radio station.\n\nAmateur Radio has everything one needs to know about the latest technologies and methods for running a radio station anywhere, from your own front room to a TV sound stage.\n\nTips and tricks on how to build and put together your equipment in the bet way and how to fix it if it goes wrong, this magazine really does inform the reader on all the maths and equations needed to understand this complicated field of technology.\n\nIt’s filled with interesting advice pages and techno-based anecdotes for the interested reader to get stuck into! CQ - The Radio Amateur''s Journal has been serving amateur radio for more than 50 years.\n', '', '', ''),
(1263, 1, 'Dna', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA great lifestyle magazine aimed at gay men, DNA is a long-running and well established publication.\n\nDNA magazine not only brings you the photo-shoots and interviews with some of the sexiest guys around, it also deals well with some of the tougher issues gay men face.\n\nThis high-quality magazine contains excellently written articles that get right to the heart of what it means to be gay, and gives great advice on how to live your life the way you want to. Not only that, but it covers fashion, grooming, fitness, travel and news – what more could you ask for?\n', '', '', ''),
(1264, 1, 'Road Iron', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRoad Iron showcases Americas hottest custom Harley-Davidson. Baggers and features the latest products and insightful articles.\n\nRoad Iron is a magazine for motorcycle builders and enthusiasts of Custom Harley &amp; Davidson Baggers..', '', '', ''),
(1265, 1, 'Popular Photography', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPOPULAR PHOTOGRAPHY is the world''s pre-eminent photography magazine. Each month, avid photographers will find the latest in all the aspects of photography including composition technique, the dark room, industry news and exhibitions.\n', '', '', ''),
(1266, 1, 'Good Housekeeping Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA GOOD HOUSEKEEPING USA magazine subscription provides readers with inspiration to make the most of themselves and their homes.\n\nWith monthly tips for home decor, fashion and beauty and features covering travel, food and consumer affairs Good Housekeeping magazine has been the premier women''s service magazine since 1885! People from around the world read and love Good Housekeeping making it one of the most trusted and well know magazines globallyThe winner of three prestigious National Magazine Awards for Personal Service, Good Housekeeping also includes articles on social issues and human interest stories, making it a well-rounded magazine ideal for the modern woman!\n', '', '', ''),
(1267, 1, 'Mens Journal', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Men''s Journal magazine is perfect for active men who are interested in sports, travel, fitness and adventure. From the publishers of the highly popular Rolling Stone, Men''s Journal magazine contains in depth, innovative features on sport, travel, fitness and adventure.\n\nEach issue of Mens Journal magazine features practical, informative articles on how to spend quality leisure time, full feature articles with real life stories and advice. The magazine also includes information on food and drink providing recipes for delicious meals, and fashion and style.\n', '', '', ''),
(1268, 1, 'Esquire Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nESQUIRE U.S.A. covers the full spectrum of a man''s passions. For six decades, the finest writers of each generation have fascinated readers with provocative journalism, compelling action and incisive coverage of sports, clothes, culture and the arts - all with a literary grace. ESQUIRE USA proudly continues this tradition by introducing readers to the best new journalists and authors of our time.\n', '', '', ''),
(1269, 1, 'Marie Claire Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Marie Claire magazine is a must for all fashionistas wanting to keep up to date with all the latest trends and fashion news.\n\nMarie Claire magazine also includes tips and advice on make up and beauty products from the professionals. Along with fashion and beauty Marie Claire features real life stories and ground breaking journalism.\n\nMarie Claire magazine was founded in 1937 and is now published in over 30 countries making it an iconic magazine loved by women globally.\n', '', '', ''),
(1270, 1, 'Guitar Player', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to GUITAR PLAYER Magazine is for serious guitarists who want to become better, more informed players.\n\nGuitar Player is one of America''s most popular guitar magazines - it has in-depth profiles of top US guitarists together with the latest new releases.\n\nEach issue of your Guitar Player magazine subscription features tips on how to improve your technique and free sheet music. GUITAR PLAYER magazine also reviews the latest Rock singles and albums and is a must-buy for all guitarists!\n', '', '', ''),
(1271, 1, 'Mac Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAward-winning MAC LIFE was launched in 1996 as the ultimate hands-on guide. LIFE''S mission is to provide readers with the most comprehensive range of information possible, from upgrading to troubleshooting to customising a Macintosh desktop. It is the only magazine for Mac enthusiasts and professionals, offering its readers a complete multimedia experience.\n', '', '', ''),
(1272, 1, 'Surfer', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSurfer is the No.1 surf magazine! If it matters in the sport of surfing, Surfer has it first and has it best. Each issue of your Surfer magazine subscription entertains with great photos, big waves, hot moves and travel stories. You''ll find more action, substance, humor, more of the energy that makes surfing so addictive, within the pages of Surfer.\n\nSurfer magazine answers the eternal question: is surfing too cool for words? This is the magazine that attempts to answer that question.\n', '', '', ''),
(1273, 1, 'Truckin', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe magazine for truckers offering articles on how to improve the look of their trucks.\n', '', '', ''),
(1274, 1, 'Easyriders', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEASYRIDERS is the ultimate lifestyle magazine for Harley Davidson owners. Published in California, EASYRIDERS has close links with Harley Davidson and so provides readers with the very latest news and information, making it the definitive Harley magazine on the newsstand. EASYRIDERS also covers the Tattoo and Biker events from around the world and gives readers in-depth technical information on customising Harleys.\n', '', '', ''),
(1275, 1, 'Town &amp; Country', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTOWN &amp; COUNTRY describes itself as the true modern general interest lifestyle magazine. Read by both men &amp; women TOWN &amp; COUNTRY readers are affluent, discerning, well educated and cosmopolitan.\n', '', '', ''),
(1276, 1, 'Allure', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nALLURE is the magazine for today''s woman with features on health, beauty and fashion. There is serious advice on how to look fabulous and feel fantastic! Including quality editorial, superb production - ALLURE is essential reading for sophisticated women.\n', '', '', ''),
(1277, 1, 'Street Rodder', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSTREET RODDER magazine is from California and is packed full of glossy colour photographs, the latest products for customising your car and useful maintenance tips.\n', '', '', ''),
(1278, 1, 'Bon Appetit', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBon Appetit magazine is from the US and contains information on the best way for readers to eat well and savour life. The magazine will take the reader on a trip around the world looking at the best restaurants currently available.\n\nIt will also give readers tips on how to plan the perfect dinner party. The recipes will be tried and tested and set out in a clear and informative way\n', '', '', ''),
(1279, 1, 'Wired Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWired USA magazine is daring, compelling, innovative, courageous, and insightful. It speaks to those who see the landscape of the 21st century and think: possibility, hope, new opportunity, and a wide-open frontier. A subscription to Wired USA magazine is a must-have.\n', '', '', ''),
(1280, 1, 'Conde Nast Traveller Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe US edition of what is probably the world’s leading travel magazine, Conde Nast Traveller USA looks around the world to bring you information on some of the greatest holiday destinations.\n\nThis well-written publication is a great monthly dose of informative escapism; it has a truly pan-global outlook covering everything from Asia to the Americas, Europe to the Middle East.\n\nInside you’ll find articles exploring the local culture, details of where to stay, what to do, what to eat and more for places both well-known and a little off the beaten track, with every story accompanied by some stunning photography. Top quality travel journalism from a well-established name.\n', '', '', ''),
(1281, 1, 'La Cucina Italiana It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLa Cucina Italiana magazine is the ultimate authority on Italian food and cooking. La Cucina Italiana magazine provides step-by-step recipes, ingredient guides, wine pairings and chef features.\n', '', '', ''),
(1282, 1, 'Cosmopolitan Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe No 1 young woman''s magazine in the world - the brand leader. The heart of COSMOPOLITAN USA lies within the advice pages and relationship articles. Other features cover health and beauty, fashion, homes and entertaining. It provides a guide to being happier, healthier, attractive and fulfilled; inspiring women who have or want careers, from secretaries to high flying executives.\n', '', '', ''),
(1283, 1, 'The Skateboard Mag', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Skateboard Mag covers everything from music fashion and of course skateboarding\n', '', '', ''),
(1284, 1, 'Bloomberg Markets', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBloomberg Markets is a US based magazine for financial professionals throughout the world.\n\nGlobally the largest publication of its kind, Bloomberg Markets magazine can keep you up to date on commodities, rates and bonds, futures and currencies.\n\nBloomberg Markets includes detailed explorations of the current stock market and financial markets, outlines financial strategies, and features articles on some of the most successful businesses and affluent personalities in the world.\n\nThe magazine has earned numerous accolades, scooping awards for its journalism and editorial and design distinction\n', '', '', ''),
(1285, 1, 'Guitar World', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nEvery issue of a Guitar World magazine subscription, the world’s best-selling guitar magazine, is jammed with song transcriptions and lessons that allow the reader to play today’s most popular classic rock, metal, punk and blues songs.\n\nGuitar World magazine also features exclusive artist interviews, hot superstar columns, as well as the latest guitar news and gear reviews.\n\nAnd now, in every issue, Guitar World comes with an incredible CD-ROM that brings these action-packed interviews and lessons to life. Hear and see your favorite superstars play their greatest riffs right on your home computer.\n', '', '', ''),
(1286, 1, 'Glamour Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Glamour magazine USA is the perfect treat for you or a friend, covering a huge variety of topics from fashion and beauty to real life dramas and celebrity stories! Glamour magazine was founded in 1939 in the USA, it is one of the best-selling fashion magazines for women around the globe. Regular Glamour features include tips on health, food and exercise, celebrity beauty secrets, high street fashion advice and styling tips. Glamour magazine also covers real life stories and relationship and romance advice. As well as producing 12 issues of the magazine each year, every June Glamour organize and host the “Glamour Woman of the Year Awards”. These annual awards recognize influential women in the public eye. Previous winners of this prestigious award include Cheryl Cole and Kylie Minogue.\n', '', '', ''),
(1287, 1, 'Harpers Bazaar Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nHarper''s Bazaar USA is the fashion bible of America. Averaging 200 pages Hapers Bazaar USA features the latest and best collections from leading designers.\n', '', '', ''),
(1288, 1, 'Elle Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLaunched in 1986, ELLE USA was an instant hit and has become one of the legendary success stories in magazine publishing. ELLE USA impacted upon the women''s fashion sector in such a way that it has created a brand new niche in the women''s upscale fashion category. ELLE not only covers fashion but does so from a new perspective, daring to view women''s fashions in bold new ways and letting women create their own individual looks.\n', '', '', ''),
(1289, 1, 'Dupont Registry Cars', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDUPONT REGISTRY CARS is a buyers gallery of fine automobiles. The magazine features the finest cars and motorbikes around. Each issue covers exotic cars such as Aston Martins, Lamborginis and Vipers; motorcycles such as Harleys and Ducatis; collectibles such as old Mercedes, Chryslers and Jeeps; a shoppers guide of the best buys around and where to find them, as well as featuring a comprehensive classified gallery.\n', '', '', ''),
(1290, 1, 'O The Oprah Magazine', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Oprah Winfrey''s magazine ''O'' is the personal growth guide for women in the new century.\n\nWith the best loved and most trusted woman in America inspiring the editorial content, this new magazine will transform women''s lives.\n\nEvery issue of O the Oprah magazine includes inspirational real life stories, empowering ideas and articles on health and fitness. There are also sections on food and travel, fashion and beauty, home design, career and relationship advice.\n', '', '', ''),
(1291, 1, 'Architectural Digest', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO ARCHITECTURAL DIGEST Magazines From Abroad?\n\nThis is the ideal monthly mag for professional architects and interior designers alike. With an Architectural Digest magazine subscription you''ll get a unique insight into some of the most luxurious and stylish buildings from around the world, as well as a number of other distinct structures including award-winning yachts and bespoke pieces of furniture. You''ll be inspired by the editor''s monthly picks of on-trend furnishings and home decorations, helping you to build up your very own style portfolio for use in your own projects.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Architectural Digest magazine is perfect for anyone who has a genuine interest in design and interior design. Whether you have a degree in related subjects or if you simply love the pictures, you''ll enjoy the fascinating and eclectic styles that this Architectural Design magazine subscription offers. Readers of Architectural Design magazine appreciate great design in all forms, from a chair to a yacht to a house. This subscription offers spectacular photos to match its informative and in-depth features about extraordinary interiors and architecture. A subscription to Architectural Digest would be loved by all those with a real love for design.\n', '', '', ''),
(1292, 1, 'Dupont Registry Homes', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDUPONT REGISTRY HOMES searches the world for your perfect home so that you don''t have to! Each issue features luxurious properties such as mansions and farmhouses from places like the Bahamas, desert islands, Florida and other exotic locations. Due to the popularity and interest in waterfront real estate, DUPONT REGISTRY is now running two issues a year.\n', '', '', ''),
(1293, 1, 'Gq American Edition', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGQ (AMERICAN) is the premier men''s magazine which addresses the people, places, ideas and issues that shape men''s personal expression, development and experiences. Each issue features fashion, journalism, contemporary fiction and articles on fitness, grooming and health.\n', '', '', ''),
(1294, 1, 'Vogue Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVOGUE USA is ''younger'' and more ''trendy'' than its English counter part, much like Marie Claire or Elle, but still retains its quality editorial, superb photogrpahy and feel of the most famous magazine brand in the world.\n', '', '', ''),
(1295, 1, 'Interior Design Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nUS interior design title\n', '', '', ''),
(1296, 1, 'Elle Décor', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nELLE DÉCOR is the ultimate elegant, upscale guide to keeping up with the exciting, fast-changing world of home decoration and design. ELLE DÉCOR covers all styles from traditional looks to bold new concepts. It features the world''s most dynamic and influential designers and personalities, trend-setters and taste-makers and provides creative ideas and solutions, helping to make fantasy a reality in the home.\n', '', '', ''),
(1297, 1, 'Abitare It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nABITARE is an Italian magazine, containing both Italian and English text. Its contents include sculpture, art, modern technology, fascinating new and unusual products on the market, furniture, fridges and even cutlery! ABITARE visits exhibitions and shows, documents their findings and features fabulous architecture and interior design ideas!\n', '', '', ''),
(1298, 1, '5.0 Mustang &amp; Super Fords', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n5.0 Mustang &amp; Super Fords Magazine specializes in information for pony car enthusiasts who are interested in those V8-powered Mustangs from 1979 to the present day. 5.0 Mustang &amp; Super Fords is dedicated to late model Fords and provides readers with an array of performance how-to''s, technical advice, competition tips, new product evaluations, and the latest innovations in street performance.\n', '', '', ''),
(1299, 1, 'Equine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAn independent monthly magazine, equine is full of knowledgeable and practical advice about caring for the health and wellbeing of horses and ponies, improving performance and having fun!\n\nThere''s news from around a large region of Northern England and Scotland, fabulous prizes to win, ''Tried &amp; Tested'' reports from a team of professional and semi-professional riders, exclusive expert veterinary comment, training tips, competition news, horsebox and trailer updates, yard, stable and paddock advice plus a busy classified section.\n', '', '', ''),
(1300, 1, 'Local Rider', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLocal Rider magazine for the local rider in the South East. Covering Kent, Sussex, Surrey, Hampshire, Berkshire, and The Isle of Wight. Each issue is packed with the latest news, reviews and tips for the local rider. Localrider Magazine is the only paid for glossy magazine dedicated to equestrianism in the South East. It has a wonderful mix of well reported regional and national show reports, interesting and educational features, reader and rider profiles, news, pictures and results. This high quality Magazine has built an estimated following of over 15,000 readers. Localrider sponsors the BSJA Southern and South East Regional Amateur Championships. The Local Rider Team own and ride their own horses and can often be found at key equestrian events in the South East\n', '', '', ''),
(1301, 1, '4 Wheel Off Road', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThis subscription for 4 Wheel &amp; Off Road magazine is devoted to all things 4X4 and Off Road. The 4 Wheel &amp; Off Road magazine subscription features information on truck purchasing, racing, events, travel and 4x4 related product reviews. This magazine subscription is great for people wanting to master the sport of rough terrain driving and those who are interested in truck personalisation. The 4 Wheel &amp; Total Off Road magazine has many ''how to'' features that are a must read for all real enthusiasts and are focused on all aspects of the off road lifestyle and its community.\n', '', '', ''),
(1302, 1, 'Master Detective', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMaster Detective is for those who like to lose themselvesin a world of crime and criminology, where the facts and minutiae of a case more often than not are the critical factor in it''s solution. MD specialises in tales of detection, painstaking police work and the relentless pursuit of wrongdoers, with a strong sense of justice pervading each and every story.\n', '', '', ''),
(1303, 1, 'True Crime', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTRUE CRIME(First published in UK in 1981). True Crime monthly is the youngest of the monthly magazines, dating from 1981. From the beginning it had more of a human-interest focus than it''s sister magazines, pioneering first person\n', '', '', ''),
(1304, 1, 'True Detective', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTrue Detective, the original true crime magazine, established 1924 in the US and 1950 in the UK. Authorative reports on today''s criminals and the increasingly advanced techniques used to battle them, along with facinating articles on\n', '', '', ''),
(1305, 1, 'Motorcycle Racer', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMotorcycle Racer magazine is the world''s No.1 road race magazine. MCR is focused on the riders, the teams, the bikes they ride and the competitive element of motorsport. Race meetings throughout the world are covered in the pages of the magazine with coverage and imagery from the world''s best motorsports writers and photographers.\n', '', '', ''),
(1306, 1, 'Dance Magazine ', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDance Magazine keeps its readers in step and on top of all the current dance trends. Every beautiful issue brings in-depth coverage of all disciplines of dance from ballet to broadway and tap to hip hop. Also included is the annual summer study guide, scholarship guide and auditions guide - all valuable resources for aspiring dancers\n', '', '', ''),
(1307, 1, 'Lexpansion', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nL''EXPANSION is a French economy magazine which covers everything you need to know about economy.\n', '', '', ''),
(1308, 1, 'Racer X Illustrated', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRACER X ILLUSTRATED is a magazine for all motorbike racing enthusiasts. Each issue comes packed with news and interviews, upcoming events, race reviews, readers letters, clothes spreads, stunt specials, gossip from the track, crossword competitions, classified sections, superb editorial and photography and more!\n', '', '', ''),
(1309, 1, 'India Today Travel Plus', 'India Today Travel Plus has emerged as the country''s finest travel and lifestyle magazine. Going beyond touristy cliches, it presents straight from the heart travelogues written by the best known names in the country. It also showcases the finest in cuisine, shopping and leisure for the up market traveler. This publication is a panoramic visual feast. The magazine regularly features a handy travel file that contains news and information on hotel, cruise and travel packages. Every article is accompanied by a resource file on the destination covered, which includes visa information, weather information, hotel recommendation, local transport and sightseeing tips.', '', '', ''),
(1310, 1, 'Hello', 'HELLO! covers the world of celebrity from a completely different angle, making it the world''s most loved celebrity magazine. HELLO! is invited into the palaces and homes of some of the most elusive royal families, movie stars and celebrities to get a view from the inside. The result: intimate, never-seen-before private moments away from the glare of the paparazzi and interviews that are as insightful and interesting as they are exclusive.\n\nPrice includes posting &amp; handling charges of Rs. 120 per publisher policy', '', '', ''),
(1311, 1, 'Society', 'Month after month, Society serves up a provocative mélange of ideas, happenings, predictions and personalities, in a style that’s elegant and lucid, gives the reader a handle on the mood of the moment', '', '', ''),
(1312, 1, 'Smart Life', 'SMART life is a lifestyle health magazine which covers from fitness gear to beauty tips to the latest healthcare trends. Smart life aims to keep you in the best of health, and also keeps you updated on the latest nutrition and rejuvenation. With content that gives every Indian all new perspective to healthy living, Smart life isn''t just another magazine.', '', '', ''),
(1313, 1, 'Womens Health', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Women''s Health Magazine?\n\nWhy should you buy a subscription?\n\nAlready a popular read in the US, Women''s Health brings you the usual combination of celebrity features, relationship and sex advice, and coverage of current fashion and beauty trends. Where this health and fitness magazine stands out from the crowd, however, is its expert guidance on health issues affecting women today. So whether you need tips that really work to get a flat stomach, recipes to help you lose weight or you want to find out which vitamins you should be getting more of to boost your energy, a subscription to Women''s Health magazine could be just what you''re after.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\nThe wait is over. Finally the world’s fastest-growing women’s magazine has arrived on British shores – and in style.\n\nWomen’s Health is the first UK lifestyle magazine to bring you the best in health, beauty, fashion, weight loss, fitness, nutrition, celebrity, love and sex, all wrapped up in one super glossy lifestyle title.\n\nThink of her as the girl who has it all – but isn’t afraid to share it. And of course, like all nice girls, you’ll never want her to leave your side. We promise. Unlock the secret to a better you with Women’s Health.\n', '', '', ''),
(1314, 1, 'Om Yoga &amp; Lifestyle Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO OM Yoga &amp; Lifestyle Magazine Magazine?\n\nFocusing on more than just yoga poses, this health and fitness magazine is perfect for any yogi looking for advice on how to keep their mind as flexible and relaxed as their body.\n\nA subscription to OM Yoga &amp; Lifestyle magazine will not only bring you exercise guides from certified yoga coaches, but it will also offer you healthy-eating advice from nutritional experts, as well as reviews of essential yoga kit.\n\nThe regular ''Ask OM'' feature allows readers to get their yoga and lifestyle-related questions answered, while the ''OM Spirit'' section focuses on topics ranging from how to get better sleep to how to minimise stress.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDesigned to inspire and to energise, OM magazine wants to help you enjoy a more active and rewarding life, drawing on the physical and mental disciplines of yoga, an ancient practice just as popular today as it was thousands of years ago. We take our exercise seriously but this is more than a health and fitness magazine. At OM, our goal is to both entertain and to enrich, to nurture your soul at a time when the world around you may be pre-occupied with more material concerns. In every issue we aim to nourish body, mind and spirit, to galvanise you into action, and to challenge how you feel about the world around you and the people and things in it. OM magazine is not just about doing yoga – it’s about living yoga.\n', '', '', ''),
(1315, 1, 'Square Mile', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSquare Mile is the luxury lifestyle monthly for the City of London. It delivers high-quality design and highly relevant editorial from the very best in the business. Having the right mix of people, enjoyment and interaction all adds up to one thing: engagement with the magazine by its target readers. Martin Deeson is our highly-respected editor who comes to us as senior editor of GQ, as well as one of the co-founders of Loaded. Our diverse field of contributors include a mixture of industry experts and renowned journalists, including: Alex Bilmes, features director of GQ; James Gurney, editor of QP magazine; Fiona Duncan of the Telegraph. This is quality that speaks for itself. We also have regular contributions from the likes of mayor Boris Johnson, Angela Knight (BBA) and Cityboy (aka Geraint Anderson). We think the old adage that you can’t mix business with pleasure is nonsense; if that were true, there would be no golf courses and business class flights wouldn’t exist. In Square Mile, we profile leaders who are not just big in business, but also within the community of the City. Whether we''re covering luxury travel, high-end watches, top motors, property investment, fashion or technology, we make it our priority to understand who the readers are and more importantly, what their needs are.\n', '', '', ''),
(1316, 1, 'Men''S Health', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Men''s Health Magazine?\n\nWhy should you buy a subscription?\n\nWhen it comes to developing an effective fitness regime and diet, a Men''s Health magazine subscription is the perfect place to start.\n\nEach issue is packed with training guides and workout tips to help you get the most out of your time at the gym, plus buying guides for everything from protein supplements to the latest training aids.\n\nYou''ll find advice and guidance from ripped celebrities and sportsmen, as well as expert tips from the best personal trainers in the industry. This magazine gives you everything you need to perfect and maximise your workout, helping to keep you fit and healthy.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Men’s Health magazine, the UK’s best-selling quality men’s magazine. Every month Men’s Health magazine are on hand with all the tips and expert advice you’ll ever need to get you into peak condition. A Men’s Health magazine subscription delivers unrivalled coverage on the subjects that matter most, it really is a must-have read. There’s fitness, weight-loss, health and nutrition plus you’ll also get the latest on sex and relationships, gear, travel, style and grooming. Subscribe now and start saving! Launched in 1987 as a health-oriented service magazine, Men’s Health magazine is the world’s largest men’s magazine brand and has 38 editions globally Men’s Health magazine has evolved over the years into more of a lifestyle magazine for men and covers all aspects of a man’s life, including health, fitness, relationships, travel, nutrition, technology, finance and fashion. David Zinczenko has been the editor-in-chief of Men’s Health since 2000 and during his 10 year tenure the magazine’s circulation has increased by 30 percent. In 2004, Zinczenko began putting celebrities and athletes on the cover, such us David Beckham, Jason Statham and Josh Duhamel, and more controversially, with their shirts on—a big departure from the cover look of the 1990s. For its 20th Anniversary issue in November 2008, Men''s Health scored its biggest cover get ever with their exclusive interview and photo shoot with future President-elect Barack Obama. &quot;He''s the prototypical Men''s Health guy: fit successful, a good dad, a good husband, and a guy who could put up big numbers on the electoral board, and the backboard. He was a natural for the cover of the magazine during this important time for our nation,&quot; said David Zinczenko. &quot;Obama understands that Men''s Health has a massive reach and when you want to get a message to men, there''s no better place to communicate with them than within the pages of our magazine.&quot;\n', '', '', ''),
(1317, 1, 'Surrey Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSurrey Life is packed full with everything you need to make the most of life in the area.\n\nWhether it’s a new restaurant to try, inspiration for what to do at the weekend, top pub recommendations, the best museums to visit or where to find the most quirky and interesting shops.\n\nWe also interview well-known local characters to find out their favourite places to visit, feature monthly columns from a range of regional experts such as the National Trust, Surrey Wildlife Trust and BBC Surrey’s Nick Wallis and then there’s all our regular favourites such as our homes &amp; gardens section, art &amp; antiques, property and much more.\n', '', '', ''),
(1318, 1, 'Dorset', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEveryone who loves Dorset will find something to interest them in this glossy monthly publication that brings you the very best from around the county. Dorset Magazine prides itself on superb photography and articles written by people who live in county so can give you an exclusive local insight. Areas we cover include fabulous Dorset properties, award-winning food and drink, local walks and wildlife, the county’s vibrant arts scene, beautiful Dorset gardens, country pursuits and county events.\n', '', '', ''),
(1319, 1, 'The Countryman', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The Countryman Magazine?\n\nIf you live in the country, you''re sure to love The Countryman magazine, with articles on all the most important rural issues as well as fascinating features looking at the past and future of the land.\n\nYou can read about historic country pastimes, beautiful undeveloped areas, traditional recipes and remedies, and even suggested rides and walks across the country. Key issues like nature conservation, pesticides, traffic pollution and urban development are all discussed and debated by informed writers who really understand country dwellers'' concerns.\n\nYou can also enjoy stunning photography in every issue, with an annual award for the most impressive nature and wildlife photographer.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGet a subscription to The Countryman magazine – The Voice of the countryside. The Countryman magazine focuses on the rural issues of today, and tomorrow, as well as including features on the people, places, history and wildlife that make the British countryside so special. The Countryman is one of the oldest, most respected countryside magazines in the world. It appears every month and is read by over 80,000 people throughout Britain and overseas, who share its concerns for the countryside, the people who live and work in it, and its wildlife. The Countryman has been embracing all that''s important in the British countryside for more than 75 years. This magazine is the lively and independent voice debating the future of rural Britain celebrating the people, landscapes, traditions and wildlife.\n', '', '', ''),
(1320, 1, 'Sussex Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSussex Life is the magazine for enjoying life in Sussex. If you love the county and want somewhere to go, something to do, or just a good read, then this is the title for you. We have regular food and drink pages, items for your diary, interviews with local characters, articles about our towns and villages and much, much more. Every month there is something different to enjoy, all with a special Sussex flavour. Love Sussex? You’ll love Sussex Life.\n', '', '', ''),
(1321, 1, 'Cosmopolitan Travel Size', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Cosmopolitan Travel Size Magazine?\n\nWhy should you buy a subscription?\n\nIf you want a fashion magazine that can help you figure out everything from what to wear on Saturday night to how to dress for your next interview, then a Cosmopolitan magazine subscription is for you. With their dedicated fashion updates and guides to every new hair and beauty trend, you’ll always be the first to know about each season''s new styles and influences. You''ll also find loads of fascinating features and articles on a range of glamour topics, all written with their trademark humour and honesty, giving you genuinely helpful advice on everything from work to sex and relationships, inspired by real life stories and events.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Cosmopolitan magazine inspires young women to be the best they can be.\n\nSubscribe now, save and receive the handy travel size edition that fits perfectly into your handbag each month!\n\nCosmopolitan, also known as Cosmo, celebrates fun, glamour and a passion for life. It provides readers with great relationship and sex advice, health news, careers, self-improvement and celebrities, as well as the latest fashion trends and top beauty tips.\n\nEach issue also provides readers with a stunning collection of fashion photography, celebrity interviews, great competitions, fun horoscopes and takes you into the lives of similar young women with compelling real life reads and a section specifically dedicated to answering questions from readers.\n\nWith 58 editions, printed in 34 languages and available in more than 100 countries, Cosmo has been a favourite amongst young women all around the world, for over a century!\n\nCosmopolitan serves women with insight, ideas and courage. Subscribe now, save and receive the handy travel size edition that fits perfectly into your handbag each month!\n', '', '', ''),
(1322, 1, 'Woman &amp; Home', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Woman &amp; Home Magazine?\n\nEvery month Woman &amp; Home magazine brings you a wealth of helpful advice and suggestions to help brighten up both your home and your mood.\n\nWith a Woman &amp; Home magazine subscription, you’ll be inspired in the kitchen by a whole number of delicious and healthy recipes, whilst also receiving tips on how to liven up your wardrobe with this season''s must-have statement pieces.\n\nThis women''s magazine even has its own Diet Club to help you get in shape, and prides itself on organising exclusive events throughout the year for Woman &amp; Home subscribers.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWoman &amp; Home magazine brings you everything for the way you live. It’s packed full of fashion you’ll love to wear, beauty to make you look glam, exercise and wellbeing to help you feel great inside and out, fabulous food, exciting travel, new directions and career tips, beautiful home ideas and much, much more.\n\nIt’s a brilliant read for women who want to make the most of life. Here at Woman &amp; Home magazine we believe it''s all about attitude not age and so every issue in a subscription to Woman &amp; Home magazine is packed with inspiring stories about real women, just like you. As well as all this, we also bring you fashion for every shape, problem-solving beauty features, delicious recipes, travel, health, wellbeing and much more. We know you''ll love it! As the fastest-growing lifestyle publication for women, Woman &amp; Home magazine is a real success story. The magazine epitomises a ‘brand new attitude’ for women aged 35 and over. Woman &amp; Home magazine was the first magazine to echo this new spirit and present a stylish mix of content reflecting the way women live and work today. This monthly magazine covers every area of a woman’s life in a fresh, modern style.\n', '', '', ''),
(1323, 1, 'Psychologies', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPsychologies Magazine is the positive living bible focused on all aspects of personal potential and wellbeing, offering genuine food for thought and tools for living.\n\nCovering in-depth articles on today’s society, relationships, happiness, parenting and family advice, health, self knowledge and communication, Psychologies has something for every woman!\n\nEach issue also includes a Q&amp;A section which offers advice to readers on the different issues women face, exclusive and interesting interviews with celebrities, latest news on beauty and fashion, travel, food and wine and much, much more.\n\nPsychologies is a unique magazine and is an essential read for all women. ', '', '', '');
