(1324, 1, 'Psychologies Travel Size', 'WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Psychologies Travel Size Magazine?\n\nLooking beyond concerns about what we wear and what we look like, a Psychologies magazine subscription is filled with fascinating insights into our decisions and behaviour. If you want to learn more about yourself and others, as well as discovering techniques to improve your quality of life, then this intelligent monthly magazine is perfect for you. Each issue focuses on ways to help you become a better friend, colleague and person, by revealing new perspectives and helping you to realise your full potential. You’ll also find articles analysing today’s society, as well as personality quizzes and career advice to give you a greater insight into what makes you tick.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nTravel Sized Edition\n\nA Psychologies magazine subscription is perfect for women who want to improve their lives and develop their potential.\n\nPsychologies Magazine is the positive living bible focused on all aspects of personal potential and wellbeing, offering genuine food for thought and tools for living.\n\nCovering in-depth articles on today’s society, relationships, happiness, parenting and family advice, health, self knowledge and communication, Psychologies has something for every woman!\n\nEach issue also includes a Q&amp;A section which offers advice to readers on the different issues women face, exclusive and interesting interviews with celebrities, latest news on beauty and fashion, travel, food and wine and much, much more.\n\nPsychologies is a unique magazine and is an essential read for all women.', '', '', ''),
(1325, 1, 'Country Living', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Country Living Magazine?\n\nWhy should you buy a subscription?\n\nWhether you’re seeking an escape from a hectic city life or looking to gain a greater understanding of the countryside, Country Living magazine is the perfect choice for you.\n\nEach month this home interest magazine brings you the very best of what the British countryside has to offer, with everything from features on topical rural issues to seasonal recipes to try at home. Every issue takes you inside a number of spectacular country homes and gardens, whilst also brining you tips for arts and crafts, travel ideas, health advice and ways to make handy home improvements.\n\nThere''s also dozens of fun competitions and how-to guides to keep you entertained every month.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Country Living magazine, the ideal magazine for those of us whose hearts are firmly set in the country. Every page of Country Living magazine is filled with inspiring houses, beautiful country gardens, country crafts, cookery, travel and rural issues, making a subscription to Country Living magazine a must have essential for countryside lovers all across the country. Published by British publishing house Hearst Magazines UK, Country Living magazine offers its readers a wealth of inspiration and practical advice on homes and decorating, gardening, seasonal food and recipes and crafts, all alongside up-to-the-minute information of rural affairs, nature, health and the environment. PLEASE NOTE that your subscription copies may not include all the promotional items packaged with the magazine when bought at retail outlets.\n', '', '', ''),
(1326, 1, 'Yorkshire Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIf you love Yorkshire you''ll love Yorkshire Life. Packed full of features on the county''s interesting people and places as well as what''s on it really is Yorkshire''s essential read.With its famed society pages - we photograph all the county''s finest charity balls and events - Yorkshire Life is also about glamour.You''ll find the finest fashions, best places to eat out and much, much more.\n', '', '', ''),
(1327, 1, 'History Today', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO History Today Magazine?\n\nHistory Today is the world’s longest running history monthly, with the first issue hitting the shelves in January 1951.\n\nWith its international reputation for excellent writing, you''ll find dozens of engaging articles from a number of the world''s foremost scholars and researchers. You''ll enjoy features on topics as diverse as gender and religion, right through to food, fashion and warfare, plus special reports on periods ranging from the ancient world to the 21st century.\n\nA History Today magazine subscription will keep you abreast of all the latest developments in historical thought, all accompanied by fantastic illustrations and historical photographs.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFollow an essential signpost to the present from the past with a subscription to History Today magazine.Every issue is packed with intelligent writing and is a visual and literary feast of well-written features, absorbing analysis and fascinating images.History Today magazine is world''s longest running history monthly and has been published in London since January 1951. History today includes fascinating articles and extensive features on all historical events from all around the world, during different periods in time.Written by leading scholars and researchers, History Today Magazine is a pleasurable read for everyone who has an interest in world history. This beautifully illustrated magazine also comes with extensive book reviews film reviews and website links for you to enjoy. Never feel like you have missed out on the past, with a magazine subscription to History Today.\n', '', '', ''),
(1328, 1, 'Good Housekeeping', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Good Housekeeping Magazine?\n\nWhy should you buy a subscription?\n\nA subscription to Good Housekeeping magazine will bring you useful, monthly tips to help with the challenge of balancing a family, housework, a social life and time to yourself.\n\nThis multi-tasking women''s magazine brings together loads of savvy homemaking experts to give you the best advice on nearly all aspects of life, from beauty and health to fashion and decorating.\n\nEvery issue comes with consumer testing reports to show you which products are worth buying, and beautiful interior design spreads to inspire your renovation efforts. You’ll also learn how to make delicious recipes, read about riveting, real life stories, and discover the latest travel hotspots.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Good Housekeeping magazine has provided hundreds of thousands of women with vital information and genuinely useful advice on a broad range of subjects relevant to their lives. From food to fashion, beauty to home buys, relationships, health, financial tips and great interviews with interesting women, a subscription to Good Housekeeping magazine has got the lot. THESE SUBSCRIPTIONS MAY NOT INCLUDE ALL PROMOTIONAL ITEMS PACKAGED WITH THE MAGAZINE.\n', '', '', ''),
(1329, 1, 'Wiltshire Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nWiltshire Life is Wiltshire''s leading county magazine. It was established in 1946 and has gathered a strong following over the decades. Relaunched in 2002 to great acclaim, it keeps its readers informed, entertained and engaged, from Swindon in the north to Salisbury in the south.\n\n\n\nSubsribe to Wiltshire Life today and enjoy: •A magazine that brings you a stimulating blend of Wiltshire tradition and innovation\n•A winning formula of stunning photography, well written features and strong design\n•Interesting and topical features on village life, walking, local history, food and drink, the arts, the countryside and much more\n•Special features on independent schools, care, weddings, motoring, interiors and home improvements\nWiltshire Life embodies the essence of Wilshire and is, quite simply, the best magazine that covers all aspects of life in the county.\n', '', '', ''),
(1330, 1, 'Yoga Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nYoga Magazine is the UK''s favourite yoga and natural living title! Every issue is filled with inspiring yoga poses by leading yoga teachers to suit all levels. Not stopping there, the magazine embraces a natural and organic lifestyle with regular articles on Meditation, Ayurveda, Mind, Body and Spirit and the best in eco-friendly Beauty, Fashion and Travel!\n\nIt gets even better, every month be enlightened by in-depth features and EXCLUSIVE interviews with inspirational celebrities and spiritual leaders. Let’s not forget, our great reader offers – every issue is filled with great prizes and offers, not to mention our competition where you can win anything from free holidays to the best in fashion! If you want to achieve greater balance, wellbeing and health Yoga Magazine is your perfect guide.\n', '', '', ''),
(1331, 1, 'Hertfordshire Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\nIf you love Hertfordshire you''ll love a subscription to Hertfordshire Life magazine. Packed full of features on the county''s interesting people and places as well as what''s on, a subscription to Hertfordshire Life magazine really is Hertfordshire’s essential read. With its famed society pages - we photograph all the county''s finest charity balls and events – a subscription to Hertfordshire Life magazine also brings you glamour. You''ll find the finest fashions, best places to eat out and much, much more.\n', '', '', ''),
(1332, 1, 'Essex Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIf you love Essex you''ll love Essex Life. Packed full of features on the county''s interesting people and places as well as what''s on, it really is Essex''s essential read.\n\nWith it''s famed society pages - we photograph all the county''s finest charity balls and events, Essex Life is also about glamour. You''ll find all the latest fashions, best places to eat out and much more.\n', '', '', ''),
(1333, 1, 'Devon Life', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDevon Life is the county magazine offering hundreds of pages of articles and superb photography every month.\n\nEveryone who loves Devon will find something to interest them on a whole host of local subjects, with features on the finest Devon property, antiques, history and heritage, countryside and wildlife, town and village features, country shows, regattas, sports and leisure, interiors, fashion and motoring. Devon gardens and gardening are beautifully featured in each issue.\n', '', '', ''),
(1334, 1, 'Ibelieve', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\niBelieve is a great new Christian lifestyle magazine for all believers everywhere. We believe faith is too good just for Sundays. Faith is a seven-day event – and our aim is to capture it all in one great new Christian lifestyle magazine. In short, we believe iBelieve is what you believe.\n\nOur three aims are simple. Fun. Family. Faith.\n\niBelieve is unashamedly Christian but never churchy. Like you, we love Sundays. But like you, we also love holidays, work days, birthdays, shopping days and lazing-about-at-home days. We also know there are sad days, lonely days and downright dark days.\n\niBelieve is perfect for people who believe – and for people who want to believe.\n\nThat’s why we’ll report on the stories that separate the spiritual from the secular. It could be the testimony of a Hollywood superstar, a Premiership footballer, or someone who lives on your street. What makes their story stand out from those in other magazines is one name – Jesus. We believe he is present in every day of our lives – seven days a week.\n\nSo we’ll write about the commonplace as much as chapter and verse. We’ll focus on holidays and healing. We’ll feature faith and fashion. We’ll be positive in everything we do and all we write about. Even the difficult issues. Because we know our readers are people who understand that the Bible is for believing, not for bashing.\n\nAbove all, we have created this magazine for the same reason you’ll enjoy reading it. iBelieve.\n', '', '', ''),
(1335, 1, 'Gurgle', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Gurgle Magazine?\n\nHelping you with every step of motherhood, a Gurgle magazine subscription provides you with expert guides on everything from conception and pregnancy to weaning and potty-training. You''ll find solutions to common problems and advice on family life, as well as key skills every mum should know. There are nutritious recipes to suit even the fussiest eaters and information on where to find the best toys and baby equipment. A parenting magazine that''s not just about being a parent, Gurgle also has features on fashion, beauty, celebrities, interiors and travel.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGurgle is a glossy lifestyle magazine designed for busy, modern mums who want an irresistible treat packed with fashion and beauty, health and well-being, food and nutrition, real-mum experiences, celebrity exclusives and brilliant buys to inspire them from birth and through the early years.\n\nCreated for mums by mums, Gurgle delivers expert advice and practical solutions for the woman who wants her own life to be as happy as her baby’s; because you don’t stop being you, just because you’re a mum.\n', '', '', ''),
(1336, 1, 'Gq India', 'Look Sharp. Live Smart. Right now. GQ Magazine, featuring the best in Style, Cars, Gadgets, Babes and The Good Life. You’ll be able to enjoy all our in-depth articles and great photo shoots, instantly delivered in stunning high resolution. GQ (originally Gentlemen''s Quarterly) is a monthly men''s magazine focusing on fashion, style, and culture for men, through articles on food, movies, fitness, sex, music, travel, sports, technology, and books. It is the male equivalent of Vogue. A men''s fashion magazine for the clothing trade, aimed primarily at wholesale buyers and retail sellers. Initially it had a very limited print run and was aimed solely at industry insiders to enable them to give advice to their customers.', '', '', ''),
(1337, 1, 'Mandate', 'MANDATE - the ultimate bible for men, is not just a magazine. It is a way of life. It is a commitment to understand what a new age man wants. Right from detailed profiles of the ruling male to snippets about upcoming gadgets, fashion labels and automobiles, exotic holiday destinations,business, sports andhot babes, it will not only cover things that a young Indian man desires but would also let him know, what’s worth his desire!', '', '', ''),
(1338, 1, 'The Man', 'A complete entertainment magazine for men. Monthly English magazine which covers wide topics on fashion, gadgets, automobile, travel, art and adventure.', '', '', ''),
(1339, 1, 'Fhm (For Him Magazine)', 'The magazine began publication in 1985 in the United Kingdom under the name For Him and changed its title to FHM in 1994 when Emap Consumer Media bought the magazine, although the full For Him Magazine continues to be printed on the spine of each issue. Founded by Chris Astridge, the magazine was a predominantly fashion-based publication distributed through high street men''s fashion outlets.', '', '', ''),
(1340, 1, 'Maxim', 'US based MAXIM is the best selling men''s lifestyle magazine in the world, with over five million copies sold globally every month. Becoming the very first international men’s magazine to foray in the market, MAXIM magazine launched in India in Jan 2006. Its 30th international edition, MAXIM in India is published under an exclusive license agreement with Media Transasia. MAXIM India received a rocking welcome in India, has a print order of 110,000 copies.In line with its world wide positioning of “Largest selling men’s lifestyle magazine” and “Among the top 10 globally most influential international media brands”, Maxim India launch is historic in many ways.The magazine has seen unprecedented response from the collective Indian advertising community and reader community. The launch of Maxim was preceded through a notice taken by both the national and international press – Financial Times (London), The Guardian (London), CNN, AOL, Campaign Magazine (UK), Asians in Media (Hong Kong), etc', '', '', ''),
(1341, 1, 'Mw', 'Admired for being a locally created magazine which is suffused with the best international sensibility.  MW''s reputation has only got bigger over the years. It  is  admired by its loyal readership for being a  lively, vibrant,  authoritative and detail-rich magazine that pulsates with the energy of  the successful  new  urban Indian man. MW prides in the quality of its writing, the richness of its coverage, the excellence of its photography and the elegance of  its design and production.  Whatever men  are looking for these days-clothes, cars, gizmos, electronics, books, movies, wines, music, fitness, relationship, adventure, travel -- MW  arms  them with information and advise to help lead life to the fullest.  MW  is India''s classiest men''s magazine, reaching out  to lakhs of  men in the nation''s major cities  every month. It is no exaggeration to say that over the last eight years, MW has made a niche for itself in the world of publishing with its refusal to compromise on quality and its constant innovations, which have won it a loyal and growing tribe of readers and advertisers. ', '', '', ''),
(1342, 1, 'Prog', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Prog Magazine?\n\nWhether you’ve loved the genre since it first appeared or have only just stumbled upon the classics, Prog is a great magazine for all appreciative fans. You''ll be introduced to upcoming bands as well as reading fascinating retrospectives on vintage favourites, with musicians from both groups regularly interviewed. You can read reviews of the best prog rock being produced around the world, with Norwegian, American and British bands all featured and critiqued. A subscription to Prog magazine also gives you access to all of the latest news and concert listings from the prog rock scene, so you''ll always know when your top acts are back on the road.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFormerly ''Classic Rock Presents Prog.'' Prog is the only music magazine solely devoted to progressive music in all it''s many guises. Prog rock has undergone such a renaissance in the past three years it now forms a major and respected part of rock music as a whole, it''s influence ranging from as far as the original practitioners like Pink Floyd, King Crimson, Yes, Genesis and co through ''80s standard bearers like Marillion and Asia through to the progressive movers and shakers of today; bands like Porcupine Tree and Dream Theater, Muse and Radiohead, The Mars Volta and Coheed &amp; Cambria. ...Classic Rock Prog reflects this in it''s broad coverage of the genre. In any one issue you can find an old master like Mike Oldfield, Keith Emerson or Steve Hackett sharing their thoughts whilst young guns like Pain Of Salvation, Anathema, Touchstone or The Reasoning are outing forward their own case for creating a modern slant on the game. Packed to the hilt with informative and entertaining interviews with prog musicians old and new and with the most comprehensive reviews and news section a prog fan could possibly hope for...Prog has consistently proved since it''d inception in January 2009 that it serves prog rock fans every need.\n', '', '', ''),
(1343, 1, 'Froots', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO fRoots Magazine?\n\nWhether you love Gaelic ceilidh music, Slavic soul or African gospel, fRoots magazine will bring you the very best of each genre. The name stands for folk roots, so you''ll learn all about folk and world music and its historical and cultural significance in each country of origin. You''ll get to hear about exciting new genres and pick up lots of new favourite artists, as well as hearing about what the musicians you already loved have been up to. Each issue has interviews with popular artists, reviews of all the latest releases and news reports from around the world, and there are even free CDs included in some issues with compilations of recent top tracks.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nfRoots – pronounce it “eff-roots” – is the world''s leading and longest continually published magazine covering folk, roots and world music, from Anglo folk to Zanzibar pop, from the latest evolutions to the totally traditional.\n\nEarlier titled Folk Roots, it has been at the sharp end of the scene since 1979, dealing with an incredible diversity of music – the first place you''ll read about new names who later go on to establish strong reputations, and often the first to highlight previously under-exposed local musics. fRoots’ readers constantly praise the magazine for changing their musical lives! It’s read by everybody of importance in the roots music business and beyond.\n\nEvery issue is packed with in-depth interviews and features, huge amounts of news, reviews, columns and information on the UK and international scene. Four a year come with very sought-after, exclusive compilation albums to download, and the April issue always contains the definitive diary and supplement on the UK and Europe’s festivals.\n\nfRoots is also keenly activist, campaigning on numerous issues over the years and involved in live music promotion and music production at grass roots level as well as the official media partner to important festivals.\n\n“I doubt if the huge audience that now exists for world and roots music would be there if it weren''t for fRoots.” (Joe Boyd)\n\n“fRoots is a definitive part of the UK music scene – the only published port of call to embrace such an eclectic range of music.” (Thomas Brooman MBE, WOMAD founder)\n\n“Incredibly stimulating.” (Robert Plant)\n', '', '', ''),
(1344, 1, 'Music Teacher', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Music Teacher, the magazine that will inform, assist, inspire and entertain anyone who is involved in teaching instrumental or vocal music, whatever the context they are working in. Written by a mixture of practitioners at the forefront of teaching and professional journalists, each issue in a subscription to Music Teacher magazine includes news, features, sheet music and book reviews as well as notes on specific aspects of teaching and snapshots of the working lives of teachers and their pupils. Three great reasons to invest in a subscription to Music Teacher magazine: -Never miss an issue -Free delivery straight to your door -Great savings on the cover price Don’t hesitate – sign up for a subscription to Music Teacher magazine today!\n', '', '', ''),
(1345, 1, 'Mojo', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Mojo Magazine?\n\nIf David Bowie, Pink Floyd and Jimi Hendrix are regulars on your playlist, you''re sure to love Mojo - a magazine dedicated to music of all varieties, from prog-rock to post-punk.\n\nEach issue includes the latest music industry news, from EP and album launches to video releases and tour announcements.\n\nWith a Mojo magazine subscription you''ll also find exclusive interviews with rock''s best established acts as well as emerging talents from the UK and across the pond.\n\nPlus, there are reviews of all the latest releases and free album downloads, making this a great value read for music lovers.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSubscribe to the World’s finest music magazine, Mojo if you are the ultimate music lover. Designed for those who truly love music, every month MOJO provides you with exclusive encounters with music’s greatest icons, while celebrating tomorrow’s stars today.MOJO’s definitive reviews section provides you with the ultimate buyer’s guide. All in all, it adds up to the world’s finest music magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(1346, 1, 'Music Tech Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Music Tech Magazine Magazine?\n\nThis is the perfect music magazine if you want to work on the technical side of the music industry, or even if you already do.  A subscription to Music Tech magazine gives you access to reviews of the latest recording equipment as well as advice on sound proofing, studio acoustics and tutorials on essential computer programmes. You''ll love the regular Ten Minute Masters section, which gives you an in depth look at a specific technical skill you might be unfamiliar with, and the insightful interviews with musicians and studio artists. There''s also a free CD each issue, with a great mix of sample tracks, demos and free software.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Music Tech magazine - the most practical magazine on the market for recording musicians, sound engineers and producers. Including more features, artist interviews and tutorials, every issue of a subscription to Music Tech magazine also comes with a DVD packed full of pro samples and the best free software and demos. Within each installment of a subscription to Music Tech magazine will be a two page spread titled Ten Minute Masters, that provides a detailed look into a technical area of the music industry, breaking down technical jargon and making the topic more easy to understand and digest. As well as all this there is news, reviews, features and interviews. So why wait? Take advantage of the fantastic savings on offer and invest in a subscription to Music Tech magazine today.\n\nIf you know any aspiring music producers then MusicTech is for them, helping to take their productions to the next level and make it in the music business.\n', '', '', ''),
(1347, 1, 'Drummer Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Drummer Magazine Magazine?\n\nFilled with features on drumming all around the world as well as plenty of guidance and advice for new players, Drummer Magazine is the ideal read for any enthusiastic percussionist. In every issue you can read interviews with internationally well-known players, from Chad Smith to Will Calhoun, covering genres from rock to dance to world music. With your subscription to Drummer magazine, you''ll get access to some of the best teachers around, with tuition pages catering for every level so that no matter how much you improve, you can still find a new challenge every month.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nDrummer Magazine, run by a team of expert drummers and highly experienced music journalists led by professional drummer Nick Carter, takes a mixture of drumming legends and hot new players to form what has quickly become the contemporary bible for drummers, young and old.\n\nIn every issue you can read interviews with internationally well-known players, from Chad Smith to Will Calhoun, covering genres from rock to dance to world music. Also included are tips and advice from acknowledged specialists as well as reviews and news. Some of the best teachers around provide you with tuition pages that cater for every level so that no matter how much you improve you will still find a new challenge every month.\n', '', '', ''),
(1348, 1, 'Acoustic Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAcoustic Magazine is the UK''s No.1 magazine for acoustic music. It features exclusive interviews with the biggest artists as well as expert columns from respected acoustic musicians such as Martin Taylor, Gordon Giltrap, Clive Carroll, Doyle Dykes and Martin Simpson. Acoustic Magazine also includes reviews of products and gear ranging from £100 to £20,000 from the world''s most well-known brands as well as elite bespoke luthiers and tips, techniques and advice for players for every level. You''ll also find advice on purchasing your own acoustic guitar.\n', '', '', ''),
(1349, 1, 'Bass Guitar Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Bass Guitar Magazine Magazine?\n\nWhether you’re a professional player or just beginning to learn, Bass Guitar Magazine is a great read for anyone who loves the instrument. They interview some of the biggest names in bass, so your heroes are pretty likely to appear inside with some expert advice and incredible stories.\n\nYou''ll get to read countdowns of the best bass players and tracks, as well as reviews of instruments, accessories and equipment.\n\nTo help you improve your own playing, each issue has transcriptions and tuition put together by a team of dedicated professional players to make sure you keep learning and can nail those all-important bass lines.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBass Guitar Magazine is the UK''s only title devoted to the bass in all its forms for professional players and those just beginning to learn. Using expert writers and reviewers who know their subject in incredible detail, it provides the latest educational columns, news and reviews of instruments, accessories and equipment. Every issue has transcriptions and tuition put together by a team of dedicated professional players so that every reader can learn and nail those all-important basslines. You''ll even find genuine rock, jazz, metal and funk stars writing their own columns too. Edited by Joel McIver who was labelled by Classic Rock Magazine as &quot;by some distance Britain''s most prolific hard rock/metal author&quot;.\n', '', '', ''),
(1350, 1, 'The Wire', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The Wire Magazine?\n\nIf your taste in music leans toward the experimental end of the spectrum, subscribe to The Wire magazine to hear all the latest  sounds from a variety of genres. Whether it’s electronica, hip-hop or contemporary classical, anything that pushes the boundaries is welcome. You''ll find expert reviews and news articles as well as interviews with the industry''s leading innovators. This music magazine also delves into the visual arts, so you can enjoy amazing event photography and edgy graphic design as well as features on emerging and established music acts. Plus, the Wire Tapper CD that occasionally accompanies the magazine has a cult following of its own.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSubscribe to The Wire and receive the world’s leading alternative music monthly magazine.\n\nThe Wire is the leftfield music magazine to read and its Wire Tapper free CDs that come three times a year have become cult classics.\n\nEach issue contains unique coverage of the world’s most exciting, innovative musicians in the areas of electronic music, avant rock, new jazz, noise, traditional music and beyond.\n\nThe Wire is the only magazine to bring you all the latest developments and news from these areas. With stunning imagery that fits alongside the alternative aspect of this magazine, a subscription to The Wire is a one of its kind.\n\nA subscription to The Wire guarantees you delivery to your door on a monthly basis and subscribers say that this is something they really look forward to every month, as a subscription is brought to you a few days before it is released in the shops.\n', '', '', ''),
(1351, 1, 'Opera Now', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBuy a subscription to Opera Now magazine for all the latest news from the Opera Scene.\n\nOpera Now magazine provides a unique and all-encompassing perspective on the international opera scene through its lively and colourful mix of news, reviews, interviews, travel articles and commentary. Read about new productions, festivals, performance previews and world premieres, as well as reviews of all the latest opera CDs, DVDs, books, websites and films.\n\nWith our mixture of celebrity interviews, leadership profiles and behind-the-scenes features, you''ll appreciate the diversity, passion and dynamism of the people who make opera happen. Opera Now magazine is the global platform for opera, reaching out to opera lovers worldwide, but also into the heart of the industry from the grassroots to the glamorous.\n\nGreat reasons to buy a subscription to Opera Now magazine: •Never miss an issue\n•Free delivery to your door\n•Save off the cover price\n\nSubscribe to Opera Now magazine today for you or a friend and get free delivery to your door.\n', '', '', ''),
(1352, 1, 'Rock Sound', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Rock Sound Magazine?\n\nThis music magazine keeps you up to date with the biggest news and releases from a range of rock acts. The emphasis is on metal and punk, but you''ll also get coverage of indie and alternative acts - if it’s loud, it''s pretty much guaranteed to be in Rock Sound. There''s a close focus on what''s happening in the British underground scene as well as updates on established acts, so it''s ideal if you want to be the first to know about the best upcoming bands in the industry. You''ll also get free posters and CDs, with an eclectic mix of new and exciting tracks included every month.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nTake out a subscription to Rock Sound, the most cutting-edge music magazine on the planet.   Rock Sound creates rather than follows trends was the first magazine to cover the likes of Paramore, Lostprophets and My Chemical Romance. With a subscription to Rock Sound you will discover the best and biggest new bands first.\n\n  Rock Sound magazine has all the styles of alternative music from punk, emo and indie to hardcore and heavy metal. Rock Sound magazine is the ultimate magazine for those that want to know all that’s going on in the world of rock.\n\nThe latest albums, the hottest new gigs and in depth interviews with the greatest stars and personalities of rock that get you closer to the music than ever before are all within the pages of this magazine.  Each issue is already bursting with prizes, competitions, reader insights, questions, amazing photography and giveaways.  Plus it comes with a free sampler featuring the best of the bands covered inside so that you can hear as well as read about the best new acts, as well as a set of exclusive posters.\n\nRock Sound''s aim is simple - to bring you the best new music - first!\n\nRock Sound is a British magazine which champions alternative music and has been 100% independent since its launch back in 1999.\n', '', '', ''),
(1353, 1, 'Metal Hammer', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Metal Hammer Magazine?\n\nGet all the updates from the world of heavy metal every month with a subscription to Metal Hammer magazine.\n\nWhether you''re into Viking, prog, or nu metal, you''ll find all your favourite bands, as well as updates on the best new up and coming acts.\n\nIn every issue of this music magazine you''ll enjoy interviews with your metal heroes, retrospective features on some seriously impressive careers, and reviews of all the latest releases.\n\nWith free giveaways regularly including stickers, posters and limited-edition CDs, there''s no delay between reading about an amazing track and hearing it for yourself.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Metal Hammer magazine, Britain''s only monthly music magazine which covers both traditional and contemporary metal bands, hardcore, gothic rock, punk and alternative. Every issue of Metal Hammer magazine reports on the burgeoning British scene as well as all the latest bands Stateside and around the world. It’s loud, it’s rude and it makes no apologies. Here at Metal Hammer magazine, our aim is to satisfy fans of established, traditional metal bands as well as to break new bands, and to keep our readers informed of everything happening in the world of metal. Treat yourself to a subscription to Metal Hammer magazine today!\n', '', '', ''),
(1354, 1, 'Rhythm', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Rhythm Magazine?\n\nWhether you’ve drummed in six bands already or are just getting to grips with your sticks, Rhythm is the percussionist''s Bible.\n\nRead by professional musicians around the world, each issue of Rhythm includes a monthly tuition CD to help you improve your skills, often with a high-profile guest artist showing off their innovations and techniques.\n\nYou can read interviews with top drummers and hear how they got started, with equipment reviews making sure you only buy the best.\n\nYou''ll learn how to play great new releases as well as classic tracks, get info on setting up your kit, and read countdowns of the greatest drummers, rhythm sections and bands the world has ever heard.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRhythm is the UK’s leading magazine for drummers and percussionists and now comes complete with the new Play Drums CD, packed full of tutorials, play alongs, techniques and practise tools to help you improve your playing. Every issue of Rhythm is jam packed with exclusive interviews with the hottest players in the world, brilliant features covering every aspect of the drumming universe, independent advice on the latest gear from our team of experts, and all the news, reviews, gigs and gossip you could ever possibly want.\n', '', '', ''),
(1355, 1, 'Record Collector', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nRecord Collector – RC to our friends – is Britain’s longest-running rock and pop music monthly. There’s a reason for that. Our motto is “Serious about music”, because we know our readers are totally passionate about what they listen to. Not that RC is po-faced: we love the thrills and spills of rock’n’roll as much as any veteran roadie. But we think that if you’re serious enough about music to read a magazine dedicated to it, then you deserve one that goes as deep as you do.\n\nAlthough it started as purely a magazine for vinyl fans, and while a love of building an enviable, valuable and unique collection is still at the heart of what we do, you don’t have to be a vinyl freak to love Record Collector. We pride ourselves on bringing you the best features about music on the planet, with artist interviews, discographies and all the inside knowledge that only RC can deliver. Who did this? What album was it on? What is an original copy worth? Does it rock? You’ll find the answers here. And it’s not only rock’n’roll: we cover pop, soul, 80s, psychedelia, folk, rockabilly… If it’s good enough, it has a place in Record Collector.\n\nThe magazine boasts a formidable reviews department in which modern gems nestle alongside classic reissues; there’s our remarkable Digging For Gold and Value Added Facts sections, which sift the musical treasures from retro rubbish; we tell you what’s happening in the world of music auctions, where vinyl of the kind you might discover in your attic can attract incredible prices, and there’s all the news that any discerning music fan could want. Plus you might find a few bargains in our classified ads, which are still heaving with the kind of records that you’d struggle to unearth on the internet.\n\nNot yet convinced? This might tip the balance: although RC is officially published monthly, the magazine is actually out every four weeks, which means your annual subscription delivers 13 issues of pure musical pleasure. Go on, try it!\n\nRecord Collector: because we are as serious about music as you are.\n', '', '', ''),
(1356, 1, 'Future Music', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Future Music Magazine?\n\nWith reviews on newly released gear and tutorials on how to use it, Future Music is the ideal resource for technological music producers.\nYou''ll get loads of tips and inspiration, with guides on how to get the most out of your music production software and hardware and which new programmes are worth investing in.\nYou''ll especially love the amazing ''In The Studio'' section, which sees artists take their hit songs apart on DVD to give you step by step insight into how their sounds are created and blended.\nYou''ll also get free samples and audio accompanying all the lessons, so you can start trying things out immediately every time your subscription arrives.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\nTake out a subscription to Future Music - The world''s premier magazine for music production.\nFuture Music magazine delivers the technique and technology behind the hits.\nPacked with inspiration for today''s modern musician each issue features reviews of hot new gear, tons of tutorials to help you get the most out of your hardware and software.\nFuture Music magazine brings you the most in-depth reviews by respected industry professionals plus news on all the latest hardware and software releases.\nFuture Music also interviews musicians at the cutting edge of technology, to give you all the advice, music and free samples you could need.\nA subscription to Future Music magazine is a must have for anyone who wants to get the most out of their existing set-up or improve their music making.\n', '', '', ''),
(1357, 1, 'Total Guitar', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Total Guitar Magazine?\n\nThis brilliant magazine for guitarists has regular profiles of inspiring musicians and their styles as well as tablature for songs from a wide range of genres. If you''re new to guitar or want to work on your technique, a subscription to Total Guitar magazine is the easiest way to do so. You''ll get six songs to learn in each issue, accompanied by a page explaining how to hit the right sound, so you''re always totally equipped to start practising as soon as your copy arrives. You can also enjoy a review section covering the latest equipment and accessories, along with songwriting advice and features looking back at some incredible tracks, albums and musicians.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Total Guitar magazine is ideal for anyone wanting to become a better guitarist as well as keep up to date with all the latest products and music news. Every issue of Total Guitar magazine features product reviews, artist profiles and interviews as well as techniques and tutorial pages. The magazine provides a comprehensive guide for guitarists and guitar enthusiasts of all abilities. Total Guitar magazine features all music from Rock, Acoustic, Punk, Blues, Classic Rock and Metal, as well as detailed profiles of guitarists and their specific techniques and playing styles. Total Guitar magazine is aimed at players who would like to learn how to play guitar, with dedicated beginner tutorials in acoustic and electric guitar, as well as helping those who can already play guitar to develop their playing style and learn new techniques and songs. With a big focus on tuition, every issue features an expert gear reviews section that looks at the latest guitar equipment including guitars, amplifiers, pedals and accessories. Total Guitar also contains many exclusive interviews with guitarists from all kinds of genres and levels of playing, and has an in-depth features section. The Learn To Play section of Total Guitar magazine covers songs from beginner level through to intermediate and each is comes with a free CD! The magazine celebrated it''s 200th issue in April 2010, with Jimi Hendrix on the cover.\n', '', '', ''),
(1358, 1, 'Guitarist', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Guitarist Magazine?\n\nGreat reading for dedicated guitarists, this music magazine has regular reviews of new guitars and all the equipment that goes along with them.With your subscription to Guitarist magazine, you can read stories from industry insiders and interviews with professional musicians. If you''re looking to pick up a new guitar to add to your collection, they''ve got loads of expert reviews to help you decide, along with some seriously special features on instruments most of us can only dream of owning.You''ll learn loads of new songs too, with tablature for music from several different genres making sure you find new challenges every month.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Guitarist magazine is ideal for anyone interested in both electric and acoustic guitar playing.\n\nGuitarist is the longest established UK guitar magazine, offering gear reviews, artist interviews and techniques lessons, tips and tricks.\n\nA Guitarist magazine subscription covers both electric and acoustic guitar playing and each month has a comprehensive reviews section covering the definitive guitars and gear that have released that month.\n\nThe magazine also covers both low- mid- and high-end products for the expensive and rare instrument. In addition to the guitars, amplifiers and accessories, the magazine regularly reviews electric basses.\n\nGuitarist offers the world’s most authoritative guitar, amplifier and effects reviews, plus a CD or DVD every month. As ''the guitar buyer''s bible'', Guitarist enthuses, informs and entertains. Want to know more about guitars or the guitar market? Choose Guitarist and subscribe today!\n', '', '', ''),
(1359, 1, 'Guitar Techniques', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Guitar Techniques Magazine?\n\nThis monthly music magazine features exclusive advice from some of the UK''s most talented teachers and guitar players, helping you to develop your skills in a whole range of different styles and genres.\n\nYou''ll find interviews with some of the most prolific guitarists in the world, as well as easy to follow tabs and full transcripts of your favourite songs to make it easy to learn new chords and start playing at an advanced level.\n\nA Guitar Techniques magazine subscription is a one-size-fits-all solution for budding musicians, with special features on everything from the biggest rock hits to classic jazz and blues.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Guitar Techniques magazine is a must-have for anyone who wants to become a better guitarist. Guitar Techniques occupies a unique position in a market place crowded with guitar publications. It was a formula that was bound to succeed from the start: take the UK''s foremost guitar teachers and players, and transfer their finesse and passion for music into a magazine! The magazine has established itself with guitarists who wish to better themselves as musicians in both the UK, Europe and as far afield as the USA and Hong Kong! When it comes to choosing music, GT''s Abba to Zappa policy means that there''s always something for everyone! Every month Guitar Techniques magazine features full transcriptions of guitar songs and intrumentals in every genre, from blues and rock, to acoustic and jazz. Guitar Techniques takes pride in providing the most accurate transcriptions around, and cover a full range of styles. A subscription to Guitar Techniques magazine inspires readers to become greater musicians.\n', '', '', ''),
(1360, 1, 'Rolling Stone', 'Rolling Stone India, is the local edition of Rolling Stone, the world''s greatest music magazine, and the the authoritaive voice on music and popular culture for over 12 million young people in over a dozen countries around the world. Rolling Stone was founded in 1967 by Jann Wenner with a unique vision: treating the interests of the increasingly vocal youth with a seriousness unknown before. As Wenner mentioned in the very first edition, &quot;Rolling Stone is not just about the music, but about the things and attitudes that music embraces.&quot; And in the 40 years since, the magazine has consistently embraced this same philosophy across its editions around the globe. Rolling Stone''s sphere of influence reaches into entertainment, movies, television, fashion, television, technology and national affairs. Rolling Stone covers everything that''s important, trend setting, and newsworthy to the thought leaders among young adults.', '', '', ''),
(1361, 1, 'Alive', 'Alive is a general interest magazine that covers varied topics ranging from politics, economy, lifestyle, business and fiction to travel and entertainment, and draws its core readership from amongst seasoned readers.', '', '', ''),
(1362, 1, 'The Caravan', 'The Caravan is a literary magazine dedicated to politics, culture, art and literature. Modeled on the narrative style, it focuses largely on domestic and international politics and social issues. Targeted at the curious mind, the magazine tells interesting and important stories through rich, detailed, insightful reporting and smart commentary.', '', '', ''),
(1363, 1, 'India Safe', 'India SAFE , a niche monthly magazine has emerged as the leading magazine in its genre in India. With a strong focus on Security, Safety and Fire, India SAFE was launched in September 2004 and for well over two years, enjoyed the privilege of being the only monthly magazine of its kind in the Indian market. India SAFE has grown from a 60 page magazine to a respectable 80 page publication and by its third anniversary, is committed to bringing you quality content worth 100 pages every month.', '', '', ''),
(1364, 1, 'New African', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBy some distance the biggest-selling pan-African magazine in English, New African brings an African perspective to international reporting on the continent.\nInspiring and always enlightening, New African aims to cover real issues often ignored elsewhere and to correct the many misconceptions associated with the continent.\nEach month, New African delivers the best features and commentaries on Africa and its people.\nAn essential read for anyone serious or curious about Africa.\n', '', '', ''),
(1365, 1, 'Le Monde Diplomatique', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe English Language Version. Subscribe today to Le Monde diplomatique newspaper and save money plus get FREE access to our searchable archive.\n\nMeet a major international paper that is truly independent. Le Monde diplomatique sees the world in fresh ways and from a different viewpoint. That focuses on places no other publications reach. That makes clear what is happening globally, and why, every month.\n\nLe Monde diplomatique specialises in authoritative journalism – things nobody else knows about until we’ve exposed them and important stories other papers miss altogether. And we publish wonderful writing that illuminates the state of our planet.\n\nIn a world noisy with misinformation, where independent voices have to fight even harder to be heard, Le Monde diplomatique brings you passionate yet objective reporting of global events and sharp analysis from international thinkers.\n\nSubscribe to Le Monde diplomatique today and save up to 28% on the cover price. What’s more, you’ll receive FREE online access to our complete, searchable archive of articles published since 1997.\n', '', '', '');
