(1366, 1, 'Storybox', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO StoryBox Magazine?\n\nIf your child loves to read, then this is the perfect kid''s magazine subscription for you, with plenty of fun tales and fact files in every issue.\n\nThere''s loads for kids to do every month, with short stories and comic strips that you can both enjoy together, plus lots of other features to encourage them to learn to read on their own.\n\nEven the youngest child will enjoy the bright, colourful pictures, whilst junior scientists will find plenty of cool trivia and amazing nature facts to satisfy their curious minds.\n\nWith puzzles and activities in every edition, this is an interactive and educational magazine that your little one is sure to love.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA StoryBox magazine subscription provides great entertainment for you and your child. With a StoryBox magazine subscription there is so much to do together in every issue! Share quality time with your child with StoryBox. This high-quality, educational and fun magazine is especially designed for children aged 3 to 6 years old. Each issue features a book-lengh story to read aloud, always beautifully illustrated by top artists. This is followed by an introduction to science that answers children’s questions about the world, a section about animals, two lovely picture stories with heroes that children will love (SamSam and Polo), an illustrated poem, games... All this in a single issue! ''The whole family thinks it''s a great magazine. We previously have tried other magazines for kids but this is the best yet, it is something the whole family can get involved with. We get a great story to read together, the 2 comic strips, the different themed activities every month, and it''s educational too in a fun way. There isn’t one part of it our daughter doesn''t enjoy and it''s advert free and feels great quality that will last forever which keeps me paying out of my wallet for it''. Mother of Lucia, 4, Ellesmere Port, UK. Explore the world through reading with a subscription to Storybox.\n', '', '', ''),
(1367, 1, 'Discoverybox', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO DiscoveryBox Magazine?\n\nYour children are bound to love showing off everything they learn from this magazine, with fascinating facts and features about everything from the fall of Pompeii to life as a classical dancer. Each issue of Discovery Box has loads of brilliantly illustrated comic strips, games, puzzles, and posters for their bedroom walls, plus some cool science experiments to do at home. It''s a great homework helper too, with loads of National Curriculum history and science topics, all looked at in a fun and entertaining way to make them easily memorable. Kids can even go online afterwards to find extra info on their favourite features, with videos and links on the magazine''s website.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA DiscoveryBox magazine subscription provides great entertainment for you and your child. A journey of discovery through nature, science and history! DiscoveryBox is a high-quality, educational and fun magazine especially designed for the children aged 9 to 12 years old. In every issue of a subscription to DiscoveryBox magazine you will find a section about Animals with beautiful photographs and gripping short texts, Science through fascinating topics and experiments, Historical events presented in a lively and informative way, a trip around the globe with the World section, as well as games, comic-strips and a lot of other fun stuff! A subscription to DiscoveryBox magazine stimulates children''s curiosity with every issue and whets their appetite for learning!\n', '', '', ''),
(1368, 1, 'Your Cat', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nYour Cat is the must-have monthly magazine for all cat lovers.\n\nIt is packed full of information to help owners keep their cats happy, safe and healthy. Articles help readers understand their pet better and to provide him with all the elements he needs to be a well-behaved contented cat.\n\nIn the Cat Care section, the Your Cat panel of seven leading experts provide advice and answers to queries from readers on health (conventional and holistic) behaviour, grooming, nutrition, and even bereavement issues.\n\nThe Your Kitten section includes advice on choosing the right kitten, gorgeous pictures in the kitten gallery, veterinary advice, a breeder diary and info on different pedigree cats. Also within this section is the Find a Kitten section which showcases over 100 breeders countrywide who have kittens ready and waiting for a new home.\n\nAs well as practical content, Your Cat also delivers entertaining features and articles, plus true cat tales, and fictional exclusives from best-selling novelists, an hilarious Confessions of a cat sitter column, celebrity interviews and much more.\n\nThere are also buyers’ guides featuring tried and tested essentials for cats and an exciting shopping section with feline-inspired items for the cat lover, their cats and their home.\n', '', '', ''),
(1369, 1, 'Candis', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Candis Magazine?\n\nIf you want a women''s magazine which really acknowledges all the responsibilities of looking after a family, you need a subscription to Candis magazine.\n\nYou''ll get inspirational stories from a range of women both in the media spotlight and out of it, covering topics like divorce, weight problems and family illnesses. Every issue also has loads of great ideas on easy ways to save money, as well as exclusive offers from the Candis team themselves.\n\nYou could find yourself on a fabulous cruise or sunny Spanish holiday courtesy of their fantastic deals, or if you feel like staying home, their cooking, gardening and fiction sections are sure to keep you entertained.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCandis magazine is the liveliest, most informative and friendly family magazine you can buy. Filled with a mix of celebrity interviews, amusing features, authoritative health information, cooking, gardening, fashion, competitions and much more. With monthly donations to charities plus exclusive reader offers, money saving benefits and the chance to win up to £2,500 every month in the Candis free prize draw. Included in the subscription price is £9.95 Candis Club membership which entitles you to access for 1 year to a vast array of special club benefits.\n', '', '', ''),
(1370, 1, 'Your Dog', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nYour Dog is Britains best-selling, most-loved monthly dog publication and a subscription to the magazine is essential reading for any dog lover! Every issue of Your Dog is packed with information you need to keep your dog happy, healthy and entertained, with 116 pages devoted to just that. In the 20-page Dog Answers section, the unrivalled Your Dog panel of experts respond to your queries on training, health, behavioural, legal, grooming, feeding and breed issues. Your Dog also includes extended breed profiles, puppy buying guides, entertaining, informative and emotive features, the latest doggie gear guide reviewed and rated, dog photo galleries, the latest news from around the canine world, fantastic freebie giveaways and competitions and much, much more! Take out a subscription to Your Dog magazine today and save money on cover price delivery is free!\n', '', '', ''),
(1371, 1, 'Your Horse', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nYour Horse magazine celebrates everything about why we keep, ride and enjoy horses. It provides a community for riders to be involved in and offers inspiration and practical advice. We help readers improve their riding, care for their horses, keep up to date and encourage them to try new things with their horse. Your Horse magazine comes with expert advice, written by professionals, who share their tips on training, grooming and healthcare for your horse. A subscription to Your Horse magazine will provide you with monthly articles detailing every aspect of how to care for your horse. The Direct Debit GuaranteeThe minimum subscription term for the direct debit offer is 12 months.The amount paid by Direct Debit may change over time. If and when it does you will be notified in advance by at least 10 days. If an error is made by Bauer Media Ltd or by bank/building society, you are entitled to a full and immediate refund. You can cancel the Direct Debit at any time by writing to your bank/building society and send a copy to Bauer Media Ltd at: Magazine Subscriptions, Tower House, Sovereign Park, Market Harborough, Leicestershire LE94 7ZT. Please note that banks and building societies may not accept Direct Debit instructions from some types of account.\n', '', '', ''),
(1372, 1, 'Horse', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHorse is the perfect magazine for the serious leisure rider who wants to get the most out of their horse and riding. Horse is packed with news and features covering subjects from horse care to alternative therapies, veterinary advice to celebrity training master classes. HORSE Magazine is dedicated to real riders'' experiences. Essential reading each month for every rider, a HORSE magazine subscription can help you get the most out of your time with your horse. Each month HORSE magazine offers training advice from top riders, opportunities to win training sessions with the big names, interviews with leading personalities from the horse world and new product reports. HORSE Magazine also features practical horse care advice, news, diary dates, horses for sale and great competitions.\n', '', '', ''),
(1373, 1, 'Practical Reptile Keeping', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWith a subscription to Practical Reptile Keeping magazine, every month the magazine is packed with snakes, lizards, tortoises, amphibians and bugs. As well as stunning photographs, each issue of your subscription to Practical Reptile Keeping magazine features technical help, product information and health care advice to keep your pet in tip top condition. Practical Reptile Keeping magazine is one of the best selling titles dedicated to all those who love bugs and reptiles. Published by Kelsey Publishing Group, a subscription to this magazine is delivered directly to your door packed full of essential news and information about the world of reptiles. Practical Reptile Keeping is a unique magazine that brings you informative owner’s experience, essential advice and top tips, precious pythons, club profile and many other regular features in every issue of a subscription. All reptile lovers find this magazine a must read, so don’t hesitate, treat yourself to a subscription to Practical Reptile Keeping magazine now!\n', '', '', ''),
(1374, 1, 'Your Family Tree', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFind out more about your family roots with a subscription to Your Family Tree magazine. Balancing the use of PCs and the Net with the many traditional means of research, Your Family Tree magazine makes tracing family history accessible and rewarding for everyone. Your Family Tree magazine offers practical advice, written by experts, on all areas of family history research. The magazine also covers an array of old documents, answers reader’s questions, and puts family historians in touch with one another.\n', '', '', ''),
(1375, 1, 'Child', '&quot;The 81-year-old Parenthood group at the Meredith Corporation, USA, invented the parenting category in publication decades ago and has been the top choice of parents over generations with its complementary parenting publications Parents, American Baby and Child, along with family magazine, Family Circle.So Child is born of the foremost parenting publications in the USA that make up the single largest parent community anywhere in the world. Child is the world''s leading parenting magazine has been launched in India by Media Transasia in April, 2008. Child caters to the burgeoning numbers of educated, professional first- and second-time parents who are tuning into sources beyond traditional knowledge for raising happy, healthy kids. Child combines world wisdom with local content relevant to the Indian family, school and environment. It fills a huge void in parenting resources in India as the thinking choice for the new generation of parents who seek the best for their child and themselves. Child India will combine both the informational and emotional aspects of parenting, by being a comprehensive and authoritative resource for parents, by addressing parents'' concerns, answering their questions, voicing their opinions, advocating their causes and helping them celebrate and enjoy the many joys of parenthood. Child will cover every stage and age of Children from pre birth to 12 years of age.\nChild is a friendly, positive, complete parenting magazine embracing all aspects of parenting: pregnancy, birth, development, health, discipline, behaviour, education, activities and games as well as new products and practices. Rather than preaching or firefighting, Child approaches parenthood as a time to be enjoyed.\n\nChild provides parents with choices and possibilities of how best to bring up their Children today in tune with their lifestyle. Child is a comprehensive guide to positive parenting.&quot;\n', '', '', ''),
(1376, 1, 'Mother And Baby', 'To celebrate motherhood at every step through positive articles and inspiring, beautifully shot pictures. To be the reader''s friend and hold her hand through the most trying times.  To devote time and energy (which the pregnant woman or new mother does not have) to get expert advice, be on the cutting edge of baby and product news, and give it to the mother in an easy-to- read format.To make the mother feel like she belongs to a mum''s club, which offers personal insights from other mothers instead of being coldly clinical. To be the quick, one-stop consultant for everything related to pregnancy, birth and child care.', '', '', ''),
(1377, 1, 'Eco Kids Planet', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nEco Kids Planet is the new nature and environment magazine for children aged 6-11. In a series of colourful and informative magazines, Eco Kids Planet explores the wonders of the natural world and our intricate relationship with it.\n\nEach issue is dedicated to a different eco region and is packed with fascinating facts, beautiful photographs, puzzles and exciting projects. It’s engaging, thought provoking, and challenging.\n\nEach issue includes a free postcard from an exotic animal addressed to your child. Collect all 12 postcards and write back to us to receive a free gift.\n', '', '', ''),
(1378, 1, 'Wacky But True', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Wacky But True Magazine?\n\nChildren who are forever asking questions will be entertained for hours with a Wacky But True magazine subscription.\n\nKids can find out about the most weird and wonderful things that history, nature and archaeology have to offer, all in a playful style that will engage them in their learning.\n\nNot only will your kids get to read an exciting monthly mag, but they''ll also have access to a safe online environment, helping them to get even more info on their favourite topics.\n\nIt''s not all about education, though, with fun drawings and crazy competitions in each month''s issue.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Wacky but true magazine is great for teaching children general knowledge. Wacky but true magazine is the BEST value for money on the market. A fun, general knowledge magazine for children ages 8 to 15, it features articles on history, nature, people and places. There are NO ads - just quality information written in a fun and entertaining style. This cool magazine for kids is the BEST value for money on the market. Each issue of Wacky But True magazine contains short articles on history, nature and archaeology, written in a fun and entertaining way. Kids enjoy reading them so much they don''t even know they are LEARNING something. Aimed at 8-15 year olds this magazine is a winner with boys and girls alike - all for the cost of just one hamburger a month!\n', '', '', ''),
(1379, 1, 'Neo', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nIn every issue of Neo magazine, you''ll find features, previews, reviews and guides for the latest Anime, Manga, Asian movies and games, all written by our team of expert journalists from the UK, the US and Japan. Alongside this exciting line-up, you’ll also find profiles on the hottest names in the Asian music world, exclusive interviews and much more.\n', '', '', ''),
(1380, 1, 'Gurgle', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Gurgle Magazine?\n\nHelping you with every step of motherhood, a Gurgle magazine subscription provides you with expert guides on everything from conception and pregnancy to weaning and potty-training. You''ll find solutions to common problems and advice on family life, as well as key skills every mum should know. There are nutritious recipes to suit even the fussiest eaters and information on where to find the best toys and baby equipment. A parenting magazine that''s not just about being a parent, Gurgle also has features on fashion, beauty, celebrities, interiors and travel.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGurgle is a glossy lifestyle magazine designed for busy, modern mums who want an irresistible treat packed with fashion and beauty, health and well-being, food and nutrition, real-mum experiences, celebrity exclusives and brilliant buys to inspire them from birth and through the early years.\n\nCreated for mums by mums, Gurgle delivers expert advice and practical solutions for the woman who wants her own life to be as happy as her baby’s; because you don’t stop being you, just because you’re a mum.\n', '', '', ''),
(1381, 1, 'Pocket World', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Pocket World Magazine?\n\nInspired by the games and cartoons your kids love, each issue of Pocket World magazine is crammed with the latest news and reviews about all things monster, from Pokémon to Moshi Monsters, Bakugan to Beyblades, Yu-Gi-Oh!, Power Rangers and more. With a monthly subscription, your kids will get all the rumours and reviews on the latest collectable trading cards, computer games and cartoons, plus competitions and puzzles to keep them entertained. They can also get creative, with loads of games and drawing guides to try out their artistic talents, as well as free gifts such as pull-out posters, stationary, and treats to keep your kids sweet.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEvery issue of Pocket World magazine is packed full of the latest news about Pokemon, Moshi Monsters, Beyblades, Power Rangers, Yu-Gi-Oh and Bakugan. With games, quizzes, trading cards, posters plus free gifts with every issue Pocket World is the place to be!\n', '', '', ''),
(1382, 1, 'Dennis &amp; Gnasher Epic', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSuccinctly, (The Beano presents)Dennis the Menace and Gnasher’s Epic Magazine celebrates the coolest stuff in kid-dom, as selected by our eponymous stars! Every issue is packed with facts, ‘Power Hour’ puzzles, pranks, posters, prizes and - of course- hilarious D&amp;G comics(including the first ever choose-your-own-ending comic strip in the World!). Every issue will be accompanied by a gift that is menace approved. Something Dennis actually owns and uses to menace. You’ll see him building his stash of menacing gadgets issue by issue and will constantly discover new and innovative ways to use them!It’s MENACE TIME…subscribe now!\n', '', '', ''),
(1383, 1, 'Lng Industry', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to LNG Industry magazine is published quarterly, with issues coming out every Spring, Summer, Autumn and Winter. A subscription to LNG Industry magazine covers the entire LNG chain from liquefaction to transportation and regasification. A subscription to LNG Industry magazine is an essential purchase for all those involved in the LNG sector and includes country/regional reports, detailed industry analysis and in depth technical and case study articles as well as up to date news and industry comment. Three great reasons to take out a subscription to LNG Industry magazine: -Free delivery straight to your door every quarter! -Never miss an issue of this must-have magazine! -Great savings off the cover price! So why wait? Invest in a subscription to LNG Industry magazine today!\n', '', '', ''),
(1384, 1, 'Digital Photo', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Digital Photo Magazine?\n\nWhether you''re just getting started or have been dabbling with digital photography for a while, this magazine will definitely provide the guidance you need to really get to grips with your camera.\n\nDigital Photo has loads of  project suggestions to kick start your creativity and expand your photography skills, with detailed step-by-step guides to help you get great results shooting any subject you choose.\n\nWriters cover everything from special effects to landscape shooting and intimate close-ups, so you''ll find new challenges every month to keep you motivated and learning. You''ll even get a free CD of video tutorials in every issue, letting you see for yourself exactly how it''s done.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Digital Photo magazine, Britain’s best-selling photo magazine. A subscription to Digital Photo magazine is the first choice for photographers looking to take and make better pictures. With easy-to-follow projects, tips and techniques, every issue of your subscription to Digital Photo magazine comes with a free CD-ROM packed with video lessons so you can learn new photo and imaging skills the smart way. If you’re looking to take your photography further, then a subscription to Digital photo magazine really is the one for you. Don’t hesitate, invest in your photography with a subscription today. The Direct Debit Guarantee The minimum subscription term for the direct debit offer is 12 months. The amount paid by Direct Debit may change over time. If and when it does you will be notified in advance by at least 10 days. If an error is made by Bauer Media Ltd or by bank/building society, you are entitled to a full and immediate refund. You can cancel the Direct Debit at any time by writing to your bank/building society and send a copy to Bauer Media Ltd at: Magazine Subscriptions, Tower House, Sovereign Park, Market Harborough, Leicestershire LE94 7ZT. Please note that banks and building societies may not accept Direct Debit instructions from some types of account.\n', '', '', ''),
(1385, 1, 'Digital Camera Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Digital Camera Magazine Magazine?\n\nAnyone with an interest in photography as a hobby or profession will enjoy a Digital Camera magazine subscription.\n\nThis magazine is an authoritative source of all things digital SLR, offering tips and advice on everything from buying your next digital camera to taking the perfect shots in a range of different settings.\n\nA technology mag focused solely on digital photography, Digital Camera magazine will help you to build all of the skills and knowledge you need to take top-quality photos, as well as hints on how to edit and develop them for use in your own portfolio.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGet the most from your digital camera by subscribing to Digital Camera Magazine, the practical guide to creating better photographs. Digital Camera magazine is the definitive guide to digital SLR photography and will show you how to improve any digital photo. It’s packed with practical photography advice and Photoshop tutorials to help you become a better digital photographer. With buying advice to help you understand and choose what digital camera, compact system camera, lens, tripod, printer, or camera bag is right for you, it covers all DSLRs including Canon EOS/Rebel and Nikon systems. Keep up to date with the latest cameras, accessories and software. A Digital Camera magaznie subscription is perfect for both amateur and pro photographers as well as digital photography enthusiasts!\n', '', '', ''),
(1386, 1, 'Photoplus', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO PhotoPlus Magazine?\n\nWith great tutorials on every aspect of photography, PhotoPlus magazine lets you understand your Canon camera perfectly.\n\nWhether you''re interested in a specific form of artistic photography or just want to perfect your family photos, you''ll get details on the best lenses and settings for a range of conditions and subjects.\n\nThey send their writers out on missions to capture great stills of everything from car races to roses, so you can learn from their mistakes and successes next time you set up a shoot.\n\nYou''ll get plenty of expert advice without any off-putting jargon, and can even send in your own photos for feedback.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPhotoPlus magazine is the only digital photography magazine 100% dedicated to Canon camera users.\nPractical photography advice and Photoshop tutorials will help you improve shots taken with your Canon EOS and Rebel DSLR and all types of photography are covered, including landscape, portrait, black &amp; white, fine art and outdoor photography.\n\nBuying advice reveals the best Canon cameras, lenses and accessories, and jargon-free tips and advice from expert Canon users means it’s perfect for beginners. With a subscription to PhotoPlus magazine , we guarantee you''ll be taking better photos, using Photoshop like a pro and making great prints to share, to frame or sell.\n\nA subscription to PhotoPlus magazine is perfect for anyone interested in digital photography and users of Canon SLRs.\n', '', '', ''),
(1387, 1, 'Better Photography', 'Better Photography has been at the forefront of providing cutting-edge, informative and comprehensive content to photography enthusiasts across the Indian sub-continent for nearly a decade now, and continues to enthrall a cross-section of readers.Keeping in sync with the transition in the fast-moving photography industry, Better Photography has advanced itself with more research, insight and in-depth analysis of each development. The magazine took form when professional photography was all about fully manual cameras with mysterious dials and levers, which needed an expert to handle. With time, as the process evolved into daily affair with the Point-and-Shoots and Auto-Focus SLRs, BP also evolved and took a new shape, never losing focus.\nBetter Photography has always been perceived as a friend, philosopher and guide for photography enthusiasts and remains a forum for the growth of photography in the country. Our all-new look, complimented with exhaustive sections, is designed to appeal to both amateur and professional photo enthusiasts, thereby bringing to you ‘better pictures, better techniques and better insight.’', '', '', ''),
(1388, 1, 'Smart Photography', 'Unlike other photography magazines, Smart Photography has to its credit names that have been synonymous with defining and recognizing benchmarks in the industry. ', '', '', ''),
(1389, 1, 'British Journal Of Photography', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAt the forefront of the photography market for over 150 years, British Journal of Photography is the authoritative source for industry news and comment, technical reviews and business developments for all photographers. Now published in premium monthly format, BJP showcases a comprehensive range of contemporary photography from across the globe in stunning colour and reproduction.\n\nBJP provides crucial intelligence on the whole of the photographic industry through:\n\n- A diverse feature programme including reports on the latest projects and assignments - In-depth reviews of the latest equipment\n\n- Profiles of established photography legends as well as new talent to watch, including exclusive images\n\n- Exhibition, competition &amp; diary listings\n\n- Special reports from key events and relevant, up-to-the-minute market sector information.\n', '', '', ''),
(1390, 1, 'Digital Photographer', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Digital Photographer Magazine?\n\nThis excellent photography magazine is ideal for anyone who knows their shutter speed from their ISO. Digital Photographer magazine has plenty of practical advice in every issue, with features helping you understand light and composition along with detailed photo editing how-to guides taking you through each step of the process. Your subscription lets you enjoy a monthly master class in digital photography, from framing beautiful shots to finding stunning images hidden in unexpected circumstances. You''ll get advice on handling challenging set-ups like low-light environments or fast-paced subjects, making sure you know exactly how to capture precise moments perfectly every time.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Digital Photographer is the ultimate subscription for enthusiasts and semi-pro photographers. Every issue of Digital Photographer includes high-end reviews of the latest cameras, lenses and accessories, in-depth interviews, cutting edge imagery, practical tutorials, reader portfolios as well as all the current industry news and hands-on technique advice straight from the professionals to help you become a better photographer. Digital Photographer is dedicated to helping you shoot your best ever images, so every issue is packed with stunning shots, details on how to take them yourself and how to go from a hobbyist to a professional photographer. With tips from the top, a subscription to Digital Photographer is the ideal launch pad for your career.\n', '', '', ''),
(1391, 1, 'Games Tm', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Games TM Magazine?\n\nIdeal for the all-round gamer, a subscription to Games TM magazine gives you an in-depth view of what''s going on across all of the most popular platforms.\n\nWith its 164 pages, this gaming magazine is packed full of the latest news and reviews, along with a funky retro section, which gives you a slice of history''s classic games and offers ''battles'' between your favourite older consoles.\n\nThere are also columns from overseas games developers and journalists in Japan and America, and larger multi-page focus features on particular games or companies.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Games TM magazine subscription provides readers with the most trusted guide to gamers.Highly respected within the industry by both publishers and development studios alike, games™ has proved itself as one of the most esteemed and trusted magazines in the field. The soaring production values and highly knowledgeable team have already secured four industry awards, and the unflinching and unbiased opinion has elevated the magazine’s status to one of the most trusted in the business.GamesTM is a pioneering games magazine that offers trustworthy previews, news and reviews for every gaming format, including PS2, PS3, Xbox 360, Nintendo Wii, DS, PC, online and retro gaming. GamesTM magazine is aimed at older gamers and is a high quality and well informed monthly read.So at a massive 180 pages and with dedicated sections for retro gaming, market news, and recruitment, Games TM is the easily the most comprehensive videogame magazine on the market and the perfect choice for anyone who takes gaming seriously.\n', '', '', ''),
(1392, 1, 'Gamesmaster', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Gamesmaster Magazine?\n\nWidely respected as one of the finest gaming magazines in the business, GamesMaster''s prestige and longevity ensures quality content for its readers, whilst games developers worldwide hope to secure a GamesMaster “Gold Award” (given to reviews of 90% and above) to place on their packaging.\n\nAs well as the standard previews, features and reviews, you''ll also find plenty of additional extras in a GamesMaster magazine subscription, including monthly competitions and free posters.\n\nFrom the PC to the PS3 and every console in between, this is the perfect magazine for all of your gaming needs.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to GamesMaster magazine - the only magazine to offer comprehensive coverage of the biggest and best games on every machine, in every month of the subscription. With a subscription to GamesMaster magazine, the world’s most exciting multi-format games magazine, you will have regular access to the only magazine to offer comprehensive coverage of the biggest and best games on every machine, every month. GamesMaster magazine’s enthusiastic, unbiased approach is aimed at those who love games. Within the pages of every installment of your subscription to Gamesmaster magazine you will also discover invaluable reviews on the latest games written by our team of experienced of gaming experts. With a GamesMaster magazine subscription you will be able to buy in confidence! In every issue you''ll find the biggest scoops across all the formats – Xbox 360, PS3, Wii, 3DS, DSi, PSP and PC. And of course all the latest developments on the next wave of hardware including Wii U &amp; PS Vita. Stuck on a tricky level? Let GamesMaster magazinehelp you complete every game with our essential cheat and tips books. Inside every issue of our tips books there are a massive 4,000 cheats and tips to help you make the impossible, possible. Don’t hold off, get a subscription to GamesMaster magazine today!\n', '', '', ''),
(1393, 1, 'Miniature Wargames', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMiniature Wargames is Britain’s oldest and best-selling independent wargames magazine and has showcased the hobby at its grassroots for over 25 years.Each issue features articles by expert wargamers on how to improve your performance on the tabletop battlefield across the full range of popular periods as well as a dedicated section on sci-fi and fantasy wargaming and regular features on painting and modelling plus reviews of the latest rules, figures, books and products for wargamers.\n', '', '', ''),
(1394, 1, 'Making Cards', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nMaking Cards magazine, the UK''s best value card making magazine, is packed full of 16 FREE craft papers ready to download each issue, plus detailed step-by-step card projects created by a team of highly talented contributors demonstrating a vast array of techniques to bring you a wide range of beautiful projects that are unique to Making Cards readers.\n\nAll this teamed with competitions galore, friendly interviews, celebrity crafters, reader letters and shopping pages showcasing the newest products makes Making Cards one not to miss!\n', '', '', ''),
(1395, 1, 'Puzzler Crossword', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPuzzler Crossword is a compact, conveniently sized magazine that will appeal to all crossword enthusiasts, especially those who appreciate a departure from an emphasis on celebrity-related clues. While two-thirds of the puzzles are crosswords with straightforward clues, the following puzzles also appear: skeleton crosswords, cryptic crosswords, general knowledge crosswords, piecewords, codewords, arrowords and more. And for those solvers keen to enhance their vocabulary, a fascinating selection of unusual words, both old and new, is included within various puzzles, accompanied by an explanation from the editor.\n', '', '', ''),
(1396, 1, 'Puzzler Killer Sudoku', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThis magazine is dedicated to the most challenging of Japanese puzzles, Puzzler Killer Sudoku and will appeal to all sudoku enthusiasts. Each 68-page issue is packed with over 100 puzzles including 88 Killers, plus Kakuro, MinuPlu and Hidoku.\n\nThe puzzles are categorised into five levels: mild, medium, tricky, extreme and deadly, and are printed in colour on high-quality paper. The stylish design and convenient A5 size make it easy to carry wherever you go.\n\nSubscribe today – it’s dangerously good fun!\n', '', '', ''),
(1397, 1, 'Lucky Seven Wordsearch', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nLucky Seven Wordsearch is packed with more than 100 straightforward wordsearches with big-print clues and answers – perfect for those with eyesight problems as well as the younger reader. There’s also a super £1,500 cash competition to try your hand at.\n', '', '', ''),
(1398, 1, 'Puzzler Sudoku', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe first and best sudoku magazine featuring the original Japanese handcrafted puzzles. As well as sudoku, each 84-page issue features equally challenging brainteasers such as Killer Sudoku, Loop-the-Loop, Bridges and Tatami. New and creative puzzles are also showcased from time to time. Designed to suit solvers with a range of abilities, the puzzles are categorised into three levels, mild, medium and hard, with puzzles ascending in difficulty in each section. Sudoku fans will also love the stylish design and convenient A5 size, making it easy to carry around.\n', '', '', ''),
(1399, 1, 'Q Code Words', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCode words are crosswords but without the clues! In each puzzle every letter of the alphabet has been replaced by a number. You just need to crack the code by solving which letter each number relates to.\nThe standard puzzles are based on a 15x15 grid and starter letters are provided to help you get going. A subscription to Q Code Words is a must for all code word fans.\n', '', '', ''),
(1400, 1, 'Q Kriss Kross', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nQ Kriss Kross is one of the longest-established puzzle magazines and is the essential magazine for all kriss kross enthusiasts. Each issue contains 100 pages with over 60 fill-in puzzles on a variety of amusing themes, plus a selection of other puzzles including piecewords, arrowords, and wordsearches. Readers also have the chance to win a share of £2,000! Don’t delay, subscribe today!\n', '', '', ''),
(1401, 1, 'Q Word Search', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe ideal choice for all wordsearch fans! Q Word Search is the UK’s best-selling wordsearch magazine and has entertained puzzle enthusiasts for over 30 years. Each 100-page issue offers hours of fun with an irresistible selection of quality wordsearches on a broad range of themes. Enjoy fun-shaped puzzles, hidden messages, word trails and more! Readers also have the chance to win a share of £2,000 in every issue.\n', '', '', ''),
(1402, 1, 'Play', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Play Magazine?\n\nThis magazine offers the finest collection of information on the latest Sony products, helping to keep you fully up to date with all the most important news and reviews across the full range of Sony consoles. As Britain''s only independent magazine focussed solely on Playstation consoles and games, you''ll find interesting features on all aspects of the organisation, from indie titles to the big blockbusters.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Play Magazine, the UK’s first ever independent PlayStation magazine. Play was first launched in 1995 and is considered to be the number one independent Playstation magazine. Over the years Play magazine has built a reputation for writing honest, hard-hitting reliable reviews, previews and and news for all PlayStation formats – PS3, PS2 and PSP, delivering its readers the very best cover-exclusives.\n', '', '', ''),
(1403, 1, 'Construction World', 'Construction World, 15 year old monthly magazine, is the largest circulated construction business publication in with two separate editions in India and the Gulf. CW is the first preference of professionals across the strata of decision making process as it delivers the most authentic and timely information on construction business. Each issue presents a comprehensive updates and articles that are well-researched, analytical and insightful.', '', '', ''),
(1404, 1, 'Infrastructure Today', 'Infrastructure Today is the most read magazine in India on the infrastructure sectors, and partners in the nation’s building process by offering valuable information, insights and analyses. The magazine covers physical infrastructure and related construction activities in roads, railways, ports, airports, water, energy and telecom. The magazine presents objective analysis in its domains, focusing on policy, finance and implementation issues. Every issue has the presence industry captains and top institutional analysts in the form of independent contributions and incisive interviews.', '', '', ''),
(1405, 1, 'Estate World', 'Estate World is India’s first monthly premier magazine, caters to each and every stakeholder attached with real estate sector. It provides intensely researched, enriched and authenticated information &amp; updates from industry, which is furnished by our exemplary talented &amp; qualified copy editors. A foremost effort to take real estate sector to a next level of excellence where everyone attached to this sector gets equal opportunity to enhance their business opportunities.', '', '', ''),
(1406, 1, 'Property For Sale', 'Property for Sale is India''s first and only Monthly Lifestyle magazine featuring Properties. With three editorial pillars of People, Places and Perspectives, content is showcased unlike any other magazine.The Property For Sale magazine *continues to impress and improve with each issue. The list of readers and accolades speak for themselves and show the magazine''s dedication to giving the reader more every time.', '', '', ''),
(1407, 1, 'Construction Week', 'Winner of the CIDC Vishwakarma Award for ‘Best News Magazine’ covering the Construction Industry for two consecutive years (2010 and 2011), Construction Week India is today amongst the top publications in its category. Launched in November 2008 by ITP India, this B2B monthly has carved out a niche amongst its readers in a very short span of time. With a well balanced focus on infrastructure as well as real estate, Construction Week India brings out the latest and the best by covering a wide range of subjects that include industry issues, latest projects, construction equipment, building materials, construction technology, construction finance, project management, policies and regulations, and so on. It is the only magazine to have dedicated sections for Plants, Machinery &amp; Vehicles (PMV) and Mechanical, Electrical &amp; Plumbing (MEP). Circulated across the country, Construction Week India reaches out to the key decision makers in the industry. Whether it is the interviews with leading industry professionals or in-depth analysis and well-directed research, Construction Week India emphasises on ‘need to know’ information &amp; insights. It is one-of-its-kind magazine that provides the latest and reliable data with an international edge but without losing the local touch. Further, it clearly stands out with its world class print &amp; paper quality.Another USP of the magazine is its controlled number of pages (currently 64) as opposed to the industry trend of magazines running into 200+ pages (where both the editorial content and the advertisements are lost).', '', '', ''),
(1408, 1, 'French Property News', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to French Property News - The leading UK magazine covering the French property market. French Property News magazine features a surprisingly wide spectrum of topics each month, including the buying process in France, financial and legal advice, inspiring real life stories, in-depth regional reports and a whole host of entertaining and informative regulars. With access to tens of thousands of properties throughout France, as well as helpful advice and contact details for everyone from solicitors and surveyors to removal companies and car hire. If you’re looking for your dream home in France then look no further! A subscription to French Property News magazine is just what you need.\n', '', '', ''),
(1409, 1, 'National Geographic Kids', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO National Geographic Kids Magazine?\n\nAn excellent read for curious kids, National Geographic Kids magazine is full of fun and educational articles about the planet''s natural wonders. Readers can learn all about ancient cultures and civilisations, including curriculum staples like the Ancient Egyptians and Romans, as well as important issues like endangered species and global warming, introducing them to serious ideas in a straightforward way. With a subscription to this kids'' magazine, readers can enter competitions to win great prizes, and you''ll find loads of puzzles and projects in every edition to keep the kids busy at weekends.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n  Jam-packed with the fascinating features and amazing images you''d expect from the National Geographic brand, National Geographic Kids is everything an inquisitive young mind needs. Every month, readers go on new adventures - exploring the wonders of the natural world, getting up close with exotic wildlife, discovering different cultures and getting creative with exiting things to make and do. Plus, there are fun puzzles and quizzes, fantastic posters and a high quality gift with every issue.\n', '', '', ''),
(1410, 1, 'Geographical', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Geographical Magazine?\n\nThis award-winning science and nature magazine is brought to you by the Royal Geographical Society, giving you an intelligent insight into the world around us.  Regular features include Worldwatch, which sums up the most important geographical events from around the globe, Hotspot, bringing you the latest political news, and an excellent Kit feature, which explains everything you need to know when planning your next trip abroad. You''ll also find a number of well-written reports on endangered wildlife, a stunning gallery of nature photography, and a rare first-hand insight into some of the most interesting cultures in the world each month with a Georgraphical magazine subscription.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA Geographical magazine subscription is perfect for the nature enthusiast; packed with stunning photography and award winning journalism every month. Published since 1935, Geographical is the magazine of the Royal Geographical Society. Learn about the rich diversity of our planet with fascinating cultural stories, superb travel features, scientific breakthroughs, the latest reports on expeditions worldwide, nature, wildlife and issues affecting our environment. Each issue of Geographical magazine brings you face to face with rare species, fascinating cultures and enchanting locations. With a Geographical magazine subscription you''ll get regular features, such as: * Worldwatch - a digest of geographical events from around the world. * Areas of Outstanding Natural Beauty - amazing places to visit in the UK. * Climatewatch - a look at our ever changing climate. * Hotspot - The place to find the future political hotspots from around the globe. * In Society - The latest from The Royal Geographical Society. * Archive - images of the past from the RGS archives. * Kit feature - All you need to know before embarking on an adventure of a lifetime.\n', '', '', ''),
(1411, 1, 'Fancy Fowl', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAvailable only on subscription, Fancy Fowl magazine is the leading publication dedicated entirely to Poultry and Waterfowl. Established in 1980, Fancy Fowl magazine offers something for everyone from the most novice to the most experienced poultry breeder. Show dates, letters to the Vet, Breeders directory, Breed Club directory and much much more! With over 40 pages, Fancy Fowl magazine is packed with the latest news, photographs, profiles, breed reviews, and club news. Fancy Fowl magazine has various regular features including Juvenile Fancier pages, Classified Advertisements, Exhibitor diary, Breeders Directory, Ornamental waterfowl, and ''Around the Shows'' reports.\n', '', '', ''),
(1412, 1, 'Bbc Wildlife', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO BBC Wildlife Magazine?\n\nIf you have a keen interest in the natural world and the animals that inhabit it, then this nature magazine makes a fascinating read.\n\nFeaturing spectacular photography of everything from British birds to African lions, alongside coverage of the latest zoology news and discoveries, a BBC Wildlife magazine subscription is a must for animal enthusiasts.\n\nIn each issue you''ll find seasonal features on animal activity such as migration, spotlight articles on individual species and discussion of important environmental issues facing animals around the world.\n\nPlus, there are also exclusive interviews with important wildlife figures like Sir David Attenborough, and a regular ''Big Question'' feature that answers some of nature''s most enduring mysteries.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nYour essential guide to the natural world, showcasing the wonder and beauty of wildlife and helping you to experience and enjoy nature more.\n\nPacked full of breathtaking images, informative features, British wildlife, practical advice and much more. This is a must have read for everyone with a passion for the natural world. If you like feeding the birds in your garden, spotting wildlife in the British countryside or going on safari, then it''s the magazine for you!\n\nExperience the wonder and beauty of nature through the inspirational images of the world''s finest wildlife photographers and enjoy fascinating features on the animals and the world around us.\n\nPlus, all of our practical advice, expert tips and ideas for great days out will help you to understand, experience and enjoy nature more.\n', '', '', '');
