(1413, 1, 'Trail', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Trail Magazine?\n\nWith your subscription to Trail magazine you''ll get all the news from the world of British climbing, as well as exciting interviews with mountaineering personalities and reviews of the latest products.\n\nThere are great features on UK activities such as ''bothying'' in Scotland, with some pieces venturing farther afield to explore volcano walking in Iceland and beyond.\n\nThe monthly bushcraft section will get you unleashing your inner Ray Mears, and experts give advice on everything from fitness training to useful camping recipes.\n\nFinally, every issue contains twelve route ideas, each with a description, step by step guide and pull-out map to set you off on your next challenge.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Trail magazine subscription , your inspirational walking guide - full of routes, advice and reviews. Trail magazine that brings the Spirit of Adventure to your home. Bringing you everything you need to get out there. The routes, the gear and the advice. If you want to enjoy the mountains and hills it''s easier than you think and we bring it to you every month.\n', '', '', ''),
(1414, 1, 'World Of Animals', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nWorld of Animals is the only magazine to offer a truly entertaining, visually engaging and accessible exploration of this widely-loved and explored subject. Each issue includes stunning photography and illustrations of the world''s favourite animal wildlife displayed alongside fun facts and captivating stories.\n\nWorld of Animals features a wide variety of species, with rich and diverse content for information-hungry enthusiasts who want to experience all the animal kingdom has to offer.\n', '', '', ''),
(1415, 1, 'How It Works', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO How it Works Magazine?\n\nWhy should you buy a subscription?\n\nIf you have a passion for science and want to learn more about the environment, history, technology and science, then a How it Works magazine subscription is a great choice.\n\nThis exciting mag has been created and developed by a number of leading experts, providing a fun and accessible way to learn about the world around us. The mysteries of the universe are explained in easy-to-follow features, detailed cut-away images and awe-inspiring photography.\n\nThere''s also digital and online versions of this great mag, helping to keep you informed and entertained for hours on end.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGet a subscription to How It Works magazine - a brand new type of magazine dedicated to feeding the “QI” generation of inquiring minds. How It Works magazine is a new, accessible, entertaining science and technology magazine, which delivers interesting articles and is packed full with fact and opinion to fuel the imagination. With sections dedicated to science, technology, transportation, space, history and the environment, no subject is too big or small for How It Works to explain. How do sharks hunt? What is a black hole? What is inside a nuclear submarine? How was the London Underground built? How do iPhones work? With every month of your subscription, How It Works magazine answers hundreds of fascinating questions like these; educating and enlightening knowledge-hungry readers around the world. So if you have a thirst for knowledge, and just can’t get enough of fun facts and interesting insights, then take advantage of this fantastic offer to get How It Works magazine delivered straight to your door every month.\n', '', '', ''),
(1416, 1, 'Cricket Today', 'Cricket Today is a monthly cricket magazine in English and is published by a Delhi-based company, Diamond Magazines, which has the support of very experienced professionals. It is backed by a publishing house that has always excelled in its ventures - be it Diamond Comics, Grehlakshmi, Cricket Today, Osho World and the books division. Since their first issue in February 2003, the publishers have strived to become an integral part of the lives of their 23.44 lakh readers.', '', '', ''),
(1417, 1, 'Golf Digest', 'GOLF DIGEST INDIA is published by the India Today Group under license from Golf Digest, the best known and the largest-circulated golf magazine in the world. Golf Digest''s main strength and appeal lies in the instructional section, which has lessons and tips from golfing superstars like Tiger Woods, Ernie Els and Phil Mickelson, and teaching pros like David Lead better and Butch Harmon. Golf Digest also has a highly interactive format where readers write in with queries about their game, golf rules and equipment. GOLF DIGEST INDIA incorporates all these features and supplements them with customized local content. Top names in the Indian golfing scene share their experiences while playing in the country and abroad. One of India''s best known gifts to the world, yoga, is a unique feature in this Indian edition.', '', '', ''),
(1418, 1, 'Sports Illustrated India', 'An Indian edition of Sports Illustrated, the American magazine best known for its annual swimsuit edition is now made available to you by Media Transasia, India. The content mix of the Indian edition is a mix of guest columns, in depth analysis of sports and photography. Cricket and other sports such as football, tennis, Formula1 and boxing are covered as well. The magazine comprises audience in the age group of 25 to 45 years, and the secondary target group is everyone who is a sports fan. ', '', '', ''),
(1419, 1, 'Bowls International', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe World''s Number One Bowling Magazine...\n\nLaunched in 1981, Bowls International has established itself as the number one magazine for all bowlers in the UK and beyond.\n\nWhether playing at the highest level on the world stage or content with life at the grassroots of our sport, Bowls International prides itself on providing all bowlers with an ideal blend of interesting, entertaining, informative and instructional articles, supported by the latest news and views from some of the sport''s biggest and influential names. Apart from coverage of all the world''s major championships, international and national tournaments, there''s a bowls holiday guide each month, super prizes to be won in easy-to-enter competitions, and the Hot Shots Club, which has become over the years one of the most recognised bowls awards anywhere in the world.\n\nSubscribers Get:\n\nPriority Delivery - subscriber copies go first\nPrice Freeze - guaranteed no price rise during the term of your subscription\nSpecial Discounts - subscriber-only discounts on special magazines and products\n', '', '', ''),
(1420, 1, 'Sporting Shooter', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Sporting Shooter Magazine?\n\nWhichever you prefer out of wild fowling, pigeon shooting and deer stalking, if it involves a shotgun or a rifle, it''s in this magazine.\n\nA Sporting Shooter magazine subscription keeps you up to date with news and shoot reports, and includes features on gundogs, ferreting and vermin control to cover every aspect of the sport.\n\nYou''ll love the interviews with experienced shooters, telling tales of their greatest days in the field, and the comprehensive reviews section. You''ll even find guides to curing and tanning skins along with delicious game cookery recipes, so you can make sure you get the very best out of your hard-earned catches.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBuy a Sporting Shooter magazine subscription for all the latest news on shotgun and rifle shooters. Sporting Shooter magazine is the new magazine for today''s shotgun and rifle shooters. Every issue of Sporting Shooter magazine features the best in shooting - from syndicate game to sporting clay, stalking and wildfowling to rough and pigeon shooting - with gundogs, ferreting, keepering and vermin control. Sporting Shooter magazine brings you the latest news, shoot reports, views and inside knowledge from the cutting edge of the sport. The magazine is packed with quality photos, reports, game cookery, and features by the sport''s leading lights and top writers. With a Sporting Shooter magazine subscription you will have everything you need to know about your favourite sport.\n', '', '', ''),
(1421, 1, 'Canal Boat', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Canal Boat magazine is the essential guide to the wonderful world of British Waterways. With every month of your subscription to Canal Boat magazine, we review the most up to the minute boat designs; cruise along the country''s canals, journey into the fascinating history of life afloat and bring you up to date with the latest news. Canal Boat magazine has been championing the UK’s wonderful waterways and boating for well over a decade and provides news, views, practical advice, boat tests, cruising ideas and updates on canal restorations with every issue of your subscription. With such a wealth of information all wrapped up in one magazine any Canal Boat fan can’t afford to miss an issue. Don’t be sorry – take out a subscription today.\n', '', '', ''),
(1422, 1, 'Moto', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Moto magazine – the specialist magazine for dirt bike enthusiasts. MOTO magazine is Britain’s No1 for motocross, celebrating the whole world of motocross from grass roots to top level internationals, and is the only publication to be backed up by the UK’s biggest forum site for dirt bike fans, and its own website and online video channel – all aimed at driving sales of the best-looking and best value motocross magazine in the market. Through breathtaking photography and passionate editorial, MOTO magazine has paved the way for how motocross should be documented in the UK. With a fresh, relevant and intelligent approach, MOTO celebrates motocross and the lifestyle that surrounds the sport. Driven by this content the magazine and its associated websites have gone from strength to strength.\n', '', '', ''),
(1423, 1, 'Ride Bmx', ' About Ride BMX magazine:\n\nRide UK BMX is the UK’s biggest selling BMX magazine. The magazine has developed enormously over the last 5 years; bigger, better and bolder than the rest, Ride UK BMX offers something for everyone and is read by absolute beginners through to professional riders. Featuring mind-blowing photography, exclusive rider interviews, in-depth product reviews, national and international event highlights, and scene reports from the UK and the rest of the world, Ride UK BMX magazine covers every exhilarating moment of today’s BMX riding and helps support one of the fastest growing and exciting youth sports in the UK.\n\nA subscription to Ride BMX magazine covers the whole BMX spectrum and captivates the true essence of the sport. Appeal ranges from the salty old weekend warrior to the eager new rider who lives on his bike every single day of the week. ', '', '', ''),
(1424, 1, 'Cycling Active', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Cycling Active Magazine?\n\nIf you''re always on your bike but want more information on where to ride and what gear to use, then a subscription to Cycling Active magazine could be just what you need. With helpful Q&amp;A features covering common cycling-related questions, and ''How to'' guides on keeping your fitness levels up or improving your riding technique, this cycling magazine is ideal for anyone looking to learn more about the sport. In each issue you''ll read detailed reviews of new bikes, and equipment tests of everything from bottles to sunglasses, helping you to make sure that you''re getting value for money. With detailed route guides in its ''Rides and Maps'' section, this magazine will help you to get the most from your bike.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSubscribe to Cycling Active magazine and each month you will receive expert cycling advice and news delivered to your home. Cycling Active magazine is the all-new magazine for today''s bike rider.\n\nFrom complete beginner to expert, Cycling Active aims to inform and entertain with a mix of bike and tech reviews, health and fitness advice, how-to guides, routes to ride and what''s on info. Cycling Active is the magazine for people who love riding their bikes. From sport bikes to sunglasses, shorts and bike locks - we''ve tested them so you know what to buy. We''ve also got advice from top nutritionists on how to fuel your riding before, during and after your ride; no matter what type of riding you do.\n', '', '', ''),
(1425, 1, 'Yachts &amp; Yachting', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Yachts &amp; Yachting magazine is the ideal way for keen sailors to improve their skills and ensure they are up to speed with the latest developments in the sport.\n\nYachts &amp; Yachting is the leading magazine dedicated to competitive dinghy and keelboat sailing.  Known as ‘the sailor’s bible’, Yachts &amp; Yachting has provided inspiration and practical advice for dinghy and keelboat sailors for over 60 years, earning a worldwide reputation as one of the best reads available.\n\nEach issue is packed full of inspirational images and high quality journalism, imparting a blend of inspiration, information, news and comment from some of the biggest names in sailing ... and a subscription means you won’t miss out on a single issue! Besides technique and coaching tips from Olympic medallists and world champions, the magazine’s writers include some of the world’s top sailing journalists such as Bob Fisher, Andy Rice, Stuart Childerley and Andi Robertson.\n\nYachts &amp; Yachting’s boat tests and regular guides to the dinghy, keelboat and yacht classes, coupled with widespread coverage of the huge range of classes and their events, makes it a valuable tool for everyone considering buying a boat or changing class. Continually testing new designs and go-faster kit, from hi-tech wing sails to the latest drysuit or navigation tools, the magazine ensures its readers are the best informed in the sport. As a regular Yachts &amp; Yachting reader you will be keen to maximize your time on the water, and our health and fitness section is full of helpful advice and insight to help you do just that!\n\nYachts &amp; Yachting’s extensive event coverage spans Optimist and Laser racing, through to major regattas like Cowes Week, Key West and beyond to comprehensive, up-to-the minute previews and reports on the Olympic sailing events, America’s Cup, Volvo Ocean Race and solo racing scenes. It features the sport’s most famous characters such as Ben Ainslie, Sarah Ayton, Paul Goodison and Ellen MacArthur to name but a few – many of whom also subscribe to the magazine themselves!\n\nFor anyone who is serious about their sailing – from club sailors, to those with aspirations to compete at a higher level, whether you sail a small dinghy on an inland reservoir, a hi-tech yacht on the coast, or are just back from trying the sport on holiday – Yachts &amp; Yachting is essential reading. Indeed, Yachts &amp; Yachting is a title that many enthusiasts pick up when they first start sailing and continue reading throughout their lives as it continues to provide insight and inspiration.\n', '', '', ''),
(1426, 1, 'Classic Boat', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Classic Boat magazine is ideal for anyone interested in the world’s most classic yachts and traditionally-designed work boats Every month, Classic Boat magazine showcases the world''s most classic yachts and traditionally-designed work boats. Classic Boat magazine is the leading magazine devoted to traditional boating, carrying news reports and features from around the globe, and reflecting how vibrant and inspiring the world of traditional boating has become. Classic Boat magazine covers boats of all sizes and type, from any era, and made from any material. The magazine is photographically-led and design-led taking inspiration from, and providing inspiration for, all builders and users of beautiful boats.\n', '', '', ''),
(1427, 1, 'Shooting Sports', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Shooting Sports Magazine?\n\nWith your subscription to this multi-discipline shooting magazine, you can make absolutely sure you stay up to date with all the new releases on the market.\n\nShooting Sports tests all the latest firearms, shot guns and air guns, looking at them up-close as well as taking them out into the field to get a real sense of their capabilities.\n\nAlong with comprehensive reviews, you''ll get shooting news and hunting tips, letting you in on the best locations around, as well as giving practical hints on tanning hides.\n\nWith your subscription, you can make absolutely sure you won''t miss out on any highlights of the shooting social calendar, with all the major events listed and reviewed.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Shooting Sports magazine and read about all the latest airguns, firearms and shotguns, all rigorously tested and reviewed for the keen shooting sportsman. Every issue of a subscription features accessory product information and up to the minute news from the shooting world, Shooting Sports magazine contains everything you need to know. As well as news and reviews, you will also get with your subscription to Shooting Sports magazine plenty of in depth and interesting features focusing on all aspects of hunting, shooting and other more general elements of shooting sports, helping to provide readers with in depth knowledge of the sport. Shooting Sport magazine also contains information about all the hot and up coming events in the shooting world, all of which are well covered by the magazine. So with so many great reasons, take out a subscription to Shooting Sports magazine today.\n', '', '', ''),
(1428, 1, 'Sport Diver', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGet a subscription to Sport Diver magazine for access to one of the fastest growing recreational scuba magazines. Sport Diver magazine is also the official magazine of PADI''s International Diving Society. As part of your subscription to Sport Diver magazine you will also receive 12 months membership to the PADI Diving Society. PADI is the world''s largest scuba diving association and Sport Diver has teamed up with them to bring you a whole host of member benefits including: • Discounts on diving holidays • Discounts on dive equipment • Discounts on travel insurance The newly redesigned Sport Diver magazine includes travel features, tales of diving extremes, humorous stories, technical articles, equipment tests and all the latest news from the worldwide diving industry in every issue of your subscription. With its outstanding underwater photography and its commitment to diving on both a UK and a Global scale, a subscription to Sport Diver magazine provides everything the discerning diver would want.\n', '', '', ''),
(1429, 1, 'Fsm', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nEndorsed by the one and only &quot;Stone Cold&quot; Steve Austin, Fighting Spirit Magazine (FSM) is unlike any other pro wrestling you''ve ever read, each issue brings you the best of the current product with a nod to the sport''s fascinating past. Read by the major players in the industry, FSM covers the biggest stories with thought-provoking columns, from the biggest stars including &quot;The Rattlesnake&quot; himself. Subscribe now for the only companion you''ll ever need to the sport you love.\n', '', '', ''),
(1430, 1, 'Total Carp', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nTotal Carp is the fresh-faced, up-to-the-minute magazine for the modern carp angler striving for success. It’s no surprise that it''s also the biggest selling carp fishing magazine in Europe. Whether it''s your first carp or your next carp we''ll help you catch it!\n\nAnd, being a subscriber to Total Carp doesn''t just mean your magazine turns up early – you''ll be part of the team with a whole host of extra benefits.\n» 10% discount on all purchases at Angling Direct\n» FREE access to the experts at anglinganswers.com\n» 10% off Angler''s First Insurance\n', '', '', ''),
(1431, 1, 'Total Flyfisher', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nTotal FlyFisher features the latest tips and techniques to give you success in every fly-fishing situation. To helping fly fishers catch more and better fish, through new techniques, methods flies and tackle.\n\nAnd, being a subscriber to Total FlyFisher doesn''t just mean your magazine turns up early – you''ll be part of the team with a whole host of extra benefits.\n» 10% discount on all purchases at Angling Direct\n» FREE access to the experts at anglinganswers.com\n» 10% off Angler''s First Insurance\n', '', '', ''),
(1432, 1, 'Classic Land Rover', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nClassic Land Rover is an exciting monthly magazine dedicated to Series and the classic Land Rovers. Written by enthusiasts, it is the complete guide to buying, owning, running, driving, repairing, modifying and restoring pre-nineties Land Rovers and Range Rover classics. In fact, it is everything authentic series owners have been waiting for from their first completely devoted magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(1433, 1, 'Match Fishing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe magazine that ALL the best anglers read! Whether it is a small knock up between mates, or a World Championship - Match Fishing has it all!\n\nAnd, being a subscriber to Match Fishing doesn''t just mean your magazine turns up early – you''ll be part of the team with a whole host of extra benefits.\n» 10% discount on all purchases at Angling Direct\n» FREE access to the experts at anglinganswers.com\n» 10% off Angler''s First Insurance\n', '', '', ''),
(1434, 1, 'Pole Fishing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe only magazine dedicated to helping YOU catch more fish on the pole and get you more bites and your elastic stretching every session. Pole Fishing is stacked full of the very best tips, tactics and top tackle to whet your appetite.\n\nAnd, being a subscriber to Pole Fishing doesn''t just mean your magazine turns up early – you''ll be part of the team with a whole host of extra benefits.\n» 10% discount on all purchases at Angling Direct\n» FREE access to the experts at anglinganswers.com\n» 10% off Angler''s First Insurance\n', '', '', ''),
(1435, 1, 'Classic American', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Classic American Magazine?\n\nIf you love the culture and beauty of the USA''s car manufacturing industry, then a Classic American magazine subscription is for you.This unique classic cars magazine gives you a window into the best American cars of today and yesteryear, and also opens up a vibrant marketplace for classic car parts.Whether you''re looking to purchase, renovate or just read about these iconic American motors, you''ll enjoy the in-depth features on the machines and individuals that defined the American auto industry over the last century, as well as engaging reader''s letters, competitions and product reviews.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nClassic American magazine featuring Classic American muscle and Classic American styling. Don''t miss out, immerse yourself each month in a little part of the American Dream.\n\nClassic American is the biggest American car and lifestyle magazine in the UK featuring Classic American cars from the Twenties to the Seventies, as well as being the number one place for buying and selling cars, trucks and parts.\n\nIf you love the glamour and excitement of American cars, then enter the world of Classic American; a land of chrome-tipped tailfins, rip-snorting V8 engines and some of the biggest, sexiest cars ever built.\n\nClassic American has been serving the American car community in the UK for almost a quarter of a century and apart from providing a valuable resource with informative in-depth features, it also is the number one marketplace for cars and parts in the UK.\n', '', '', ''),
(1436, 1, 'Racing Ahead', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nRacing Ahead is the UK &amp; Ireland’s best-selling horse racing monthly magazine offering information on all aspects of horse racing.\n\nIn Racing Ahead you will find feature articles on hunt and flat racing, horse racing events, racecourses and in depth interviews with horse racing experts.\n\nThe full colour publication is targeted toward anyone who loves horse racing from the owners of race horses to the person who bets on the outcome of the races. There are tips on races, profiles of horses with good chances of winning, and reports of scouts.\n\nA subscription to Racing Ahead gives you the inside story about horse racing in the UK. You get behind the scenes interviews with jockeys and owners in Racing Ahead. There are also articles on stable tours, new horses to the track, betting systems, and industry experts with horseracing trend reports.\n\nIf you love horseracing or betting on horses then Racing Ahead Magazine is a must subscribe to publication. The magazine will keep you informed on everything that is happening with hunt and flat horse racing in Great Britain. See how good the predictions are on the horses to watch, and check out reports on how individual horses are running so you can make bets with confidence. Subscribe today for all the news in UK horse racing.\n', '', '', ''),
(1437, 1, 'Motorcycle Sport &amp; Leisure', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Motorcycle Sport &amp; Leisure Magazine?\n\nThis is a motorcycle magazine that really does cover all the bases.\n\nIn every issue you''ll find feature articles focusing on new models, profiles of iconic riders in motorcycle history, and nostalgic looks back at well-loved classic bikes.\n\nA subscription to Motorcycle Sport &amp; Leisure magazine will also give you access to helpful second-hand buyers'' guides for specific models, and detailed test drive features of both retro and modern motorbikes.\n\nThe mag''s ''Touring'' section is especially informative, offering suggestions on the best places in the world to enjoy your machine, as well as inviting you to send in your own advice for memorable riding trips.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMotorcycle Sport &amp; Leisure has more world scoops and exclusives than any other motorcycle magazine. It’s got the latest news, test rides and in-depth interviews with the top figures in the world of motorcycling – from championship winning racers to engineers and executives from the bike manufacturers. There are touring tales from every corner of the globe too and strong views from our expert columnists. It doesn’t matter what type of bike you’ve got, how you like to ride it or how experienced you are, MSL is your one-stop shop for sheer motorcycling pleasure.\n', '', '', ''),
(1438, 1, 'Fly Fishing &amp; Fly Tying', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Fly Fishing &amp; Fly Tying Magazine?\n\nThis the ideal fishing magazine for anyone who wants to make sure they get insightful, practical advice from the experts on a regular basis. A Fly Fishing and Fly Tying subscription brings you monthly updates on innovative tips, tricks and little-known secrets that give you that all-important edge in the water. Focusing mainly on game fishing in freshwater and saltwater across the British Isles, this magazine also provides high-quality coverage from exotic angling destinations, taking you wherever the action is according to the time of year. You''ll also read regular news, comment and advice pieces, with interviews, reviews and great competitions in every issue.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Fly Fishing and Fly Tying allows fly fishers to stay ahead of their game. Every month, the award-winning magazine features the most up-to-date tactics, techniques and fly patterns that today''s anglers and fly tyers are using for trout, salmon, sea trout, grayling, coarse fish and saltwater species. Tastefully and cleanly designed, Fly Fishing and Fly Tying takes the angler to wherever the action is - anywhere in the world. It also covers innovations, casting advice, interviews, conservation issues, travel features, humorous articles, news and comment from the most informed, qualified and authoritative writers in fly fishing. Fly Fishing and Fly Tying focuses on the details which will help fly fishers catch more fish and therefore derive more enjoyment from their sport. It takes an in-depth look at the tactics used by successful anglers, and each month, features a stage-by-stage fly tying demonstration, coupled with instruction on how best to fish the fly. The magazine also features unique fly tying competitions which encourage reader participation. Fly Fishing and Fly Tying is at the forefront of the latest tackle, materials and gear which comes onto the market, and it is recognised within the industry as offering fair, forthright and independent reviews. Whether an angler fishes fly on rivers, streams, reservoirs, lakes, Irish loughs, Scottish loughs, or in the sea at him and abroad, a subscription to Fly Fishing and Fly Tying will equip him or her with all they require to enjoy their sport to the maximum.\n', '', '', ''),
(1439, 1, 'Champions', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Champions Magazine?\n\nThis magazine follows the UEFA Champions League competition from the qualification stage, right through to the nail biting final.\n\nWith a Champions magazine subscription, you''ll get insights from some of the world''s best sports journalists, including Gabriele Marcotti and Guillem Balague, as well as in-depth features and interviews with some of the competition''s best players, managers and referees.\n\nThe mag also takes a retrospective view of the biggest events in the tournament''s history, plus a behind the scenes look into some of the most successful clubs to have lifted the coveted trophy.\n\nYou''ll also find exclusive tournament predictions from a range of guest pundits, including football legends Sandro Mazzola, Zico and Ruud Gullit.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBuy a subscription to CHAMPIONS magazine today and keep up to date with all the glory of the UEFA Champions League. CHAMPIONS magazine is the critically acclaimed magazine, that reflects the drama, the passion and the wonder of the UEFA Champions League, offering an unequalled insight into the tournament that is enthralling football fans across the world. The official magazine of the UEFA Champions League, CHAMPIONS magazine offers unprecedented insight into each stage of the competition. Champions magazine features exclusive interviews with the tournament''s biggest stars and most influential coaches from around the world, in-depth features on the issues that shape European football and expert opiniosn from the best football writers in Europe. Get inside the world''s greatest club tournament with a subscription to the award-winning official magazine of the UEFA Champions League.\n', '', '', ''),
(1440, 1, 'Total Off-Road', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTotal Off-Road - the off-roader''s choice for more than ten years! Total Off-Road is the UK''s only dedicated off-road magazine. With features on all kinds of modified 4x4s, green laning guides and information, workshop stories, product and equipment reviews and tests plus so much more.\n', '', '', ''),
(1441, 1, 'Park Home &amp; Holiday Caravan', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEstablished in 1960, Park Home &amp; Holiday Caravan is the best-selling and biggest magazine dedicated to park homes. Also featured are leisure lodges and static holiday caravans for those interested in buying an affordable second home in the UK or abroad.\n\nA subscription to Park Home and Holiday Caravan magazine includes 12 issues a year home delivered. Each issue is page after page of news, buying and selling advice, legal help, new model review, small garden advice, free garden plants offer, park reviews, DIY advice, Holiday news, buying a static caravan advice, static caravan parks, holiday home news and much more- this really is the essential guide to caravan and holiday homes.\n', '', '', ''),
(1442, 1, 'Rugby World', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRugby World is the voice of global rugby and the biggest-selling rugby magazine anywhere. It offers an all-round comprehensive package of rugby action, timely results and fixtures along with hundreds of images that capture the excitement and passion of this high-impact sport. Rugby World also delivers a monthly local focus on the british national teams and fascinating in-depth interviews with all the key players, giving an unrivalled, behind-the-scenes insight into rugby as it''s played today. A Rugby World magazine subscription delivers readers all the latest news, views and in-depth interviews from all areas of the game. This, alongside the best photographs, the most respected writers, leading columnists and a campaigning edge puts Rugby World at the forefront of its sport. Rugby World is not just the best-selling rugby magazine, it’s also the most trusted source for the whole rugby community. Readers enjoy a comprehensive round-up of all the news and results, along with dynamic photographs of the action. There are expert articles and columns written by rugby’s most respected names, together with star player interviews. Rugby World is also famous for plain-speaking, and is never shy of tackling a campaign or two. Rugby World magazine is read by more players, coaches and fans than any other. In fact, it''s head and shoulders above the opposition.\n', '', '', ''),
(1443, 1, 'Lady Golfer', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Lady Golfer Magazine?\n\nThis magazine is packed with news and features from the sport''s most successful women, with practical advice for pros and amateurs alike.\n\nThe UK''s only monthly women''s golf magazine features top tips to help you improve your technique, as well as inspiring interviews with leading international players to motivate you every month. International course reviews let you plan your dream golfing holiday, whilst regular competitions give you the chance to make it a reality.\n\nYou''ll also find showcases of the latest equipment to help you pick the best new clubs, plus helpful fashion tips to keep you looking stylish on the course.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nLady Golfer is Britain''s leading magazine for women players and the only one published monthly.\n\nPacked with great fashion tips and the most stylish looks, it offers all the latest news and views from the ladies'' game - all put together by a team of expert writers.\n\nInside every issue:\n\n- Interviews and features with the game’s biggest names\n- Fashion features - The latest fashion trends on the course &amp; in the clubhouse, we showcase all the hottest and latest clothing and accessories\n- Read our informative course reviews - whether you are looking for a 9-holer to play while on holiday in Scotland, where to go to on a spa weekend, or where to visit &amp; play in the UK and abroad\n- Brilliant instruction from the professionals - real club pros who know how to help the average player offer easy to understand hints and tips; while tour pros can help you gain finesse to save shots and hit the ball further and straighter.\n- Great competitions that are free to enter - you can win all sorts of amazing prizes every month, from sets of top of the range clubs to your dream holiday\n- Regular reviews and showcases of all the latest equipment - if you are looking for new clubs then check out our reviews first\n- Funny, informed, entertaining and expert comment on all aspects of the game\n- And much, much more in every issue!\n\nLady Golfer - an in depth and lively read every month!\n', '', '', ''),
(1444, 1, 'Gun Mart', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Gun Mart Magazine?\n\nThis shooting magazine covers each manufacturer and almost every model of firearm in the country, so with a subscription to Gun Mart you can be sure that you’re getting the best possible advice on starting or restocking your gun collection.\n\nIn each issue of this magazine you''ll get at least ten gun tests and plenty more reviews and classifieds, along with fascinating features on antique gun collecting, re-enactments, knives and other weaponry.\n\nYou can also enjoy a thorough round-up of available clothing and equipment for the military, law enforcement and intense outdoor sports.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGun Mart magazine is the biggest and most diverse shooting publication in the UK.\nThe only magazine that caters for sports shooting, gun collecting and the militaria market, Gun Mart magazine is the most comprehensive title in its field. Established over 25 years ago, Gun Mart magazine has more than ten gun tests in every issue. Every issue of Gun Mart magazine features expert gun reviews and also includes:\n\n- Country and Shotgun – tests, reviews and news plus a Clay Shooting Ground Guide and major event coverage.\n- Firearms – Reviews of hunting and target air rifles plus everything from ammunition to scopes and reloading equipment.\n- Airguns - hunting and target rifle reviews, air and CO2 pistol reviews, lamping and nightvision, scopes and more.\n- Militaria Mart - geared towards antique weapons collecting, re-enactment and military history.\n- Field Cutlery - four pages of knives and other edged tools.\n- Practical &amp; Tactical - a monthly round-up of equipment and clothing for heavy duty outdoor sports and pursuits, military and law enforcement.\n', '', '', ''),
(1445, 1, 'Vw Bus T4&amp;T5', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nVW Bus is the only magazine dedicated to the late model VW buses from the T4 and T5 on.\n\nVW Bus magazine acknowledges the evolution of the VW Bus and spotlights where this symbol of freedom and adventure has now arrived: The T4 and T5 - taking their rightful place in the family of VW models and carrying on the tradition of quality and innovation that is the ever iconic VW Bus.\n', '', '', ''),
(1446, 1, 'Practical Sportsbikes', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Practical Sportsbikes Magazine?\n\nIdeal for anyone that loves riding two-wheelers from the golden age of the superbike, this motorcycle magazine encourages you to take a hands-on approach to your hobby. With a subscription to Practical Sportsbikes magazine, you''ll get in-depth road tests of big name marques like Kawasaki, Yamaha and Suzuki, plus expert workshop advice on every aspect of restoring and maintaining your vehicle. Each issue also provides a buyers'' guide concentrating on a specific model, and feature articles looking at readers'' own real-life restorations. Knowledgeable and reliable, Practical Sportsbikes is a helpful handbook for your next project.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPractical Sportsbikes magazine is about buying, improving, restoring and riding the best motorbikes from the 1970s, 80s and 90s.\n', '', '', ''),
(1447, 1, 'The Cricketer', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\nThe Cricketer is the world’s No.1 cricket magazine and the sport’s most-inclusive and best read.\n\nEvery month you’ll find exclusive interviews with our cover stars, the likes of Stuart Broad, James Anderson and Shane Warne. Plus top analysis from experts such as Simon Hughes and Mike Selvey.\n\nEnjoy the best club cricket coverage, plus ‘The Game’ section, which boasts comment from top pros and is the magazine’s own special ‘How to’ guide. You''ll also find fantastic competitions, news, views and gossip from international and county dressing rooms.\n', '', '', ''),
(1448, 1, 'Classic &amp; Sports Car', 'WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Classic &amp; Sports Car Magazine?\n\nWhether you''re looking to buy, maintain or just read about classic automobiles, a Classic &amp; Sports Car magazine subscription will give you a fascinating insight into this enjoyable hobby.\n\nThis magazine has been running for more than 30 years, and aims to provide you with an ideal monthly companion to your classic car interest, with sale listings, features and the popular ''Our Classics'' page, where contributors discuss their own favourite models.\n\nYou will also find dozens of nostalgic pictures in each issue, as well as interviews with the owners of some of the most exquisite classic sports cars in the world.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Classic &amp; Sports Car magazine subscription is the perfect read for anyone interested in classic cars! A Classic &amp; Sports Car magazine subscription features the best buying advice, road tests and features on classic cars.\n\nLaunched in 1982, Classic &amp; Sports Car magazine is equally interesting for both an owner and devotee of classic cars. From the modern day to decades past, Classic &amp; Sports Car magazine compares models from an era sadly gone. A Classic &amp; Sports Car magazine subscription features restorations, car and product tests, readers models and buying advice to keep the classic car fan interested and entertained every month. The magazine also features a classified section and buyers guide which provides a rich source of valuable price and contact for all makes and models. Classic &amp; Sports Car magazine has earned a reputation for being the most respected title on the subject. The magazine also includes the finest cars from around the world and combines unrivalled editorial with stunning photography and beautiful design. Classic &amp; Sports Car magazine is the perfect guide for buying and selling classic and sports cars with thousands advertised in the magazine every month. A Classic &amp; Sports Car magazine subscription is all a classic enthusiast needs.', '', '', ''),
(1449, 1, 'F1 Racing', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO F1 Racing Magazine?\n\nWith race reports and previews of upcoming Grand Prix events, this motorsport magazine is the best way to get the inside scoop on what''s going on off the track.\n\nA subscription to F1 Racing magazine brings you in-depth interviews with the teams and drivers, giving you an insight into exactly what''s happening behind the scenes.\n\nWith profiles of current Formula 1 cars and features looking back at key moments and figures in racing history, this monthly magazine offers coverage of everything F1, both past and present.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAn F1 Racing magazine subscription is perfect for the Formula 1 enthusiast. F1 Racing magazine is the world’s best-selling F1 magazine dedicated to the glamorous and adrenaline-fuelled sport of Formula 1. F1 Racing magazine gets right under the skin of the world''s fastest sport , explores and anatomises the world''s fastest, most exciting sport, with many well respected journalists and photographers contributing to the magazine. An F1 Racing magazine subscription provides a magazine with all the exclusive, unrivalled coverage, no-nonsense writing, and outstanding award-winning photography on the sport. Launched in 1996, F1 Racing is now published in 18 languages across 26 local market editions and is available in more than 100 countries.\n\nShould you wish to cancel your subscription it will be cancelled on expiry of the current term which will not be refundable, other than in exceptional circumstances.\nThe issues you receive during this trial period are covered by your first Direct Debit payment. You can cancel the subscription (your next Direct Debit payment) at any time during this trial period. However, once the 2nd payment has been claimed from your bank account, should you wish to cancel your subscription it will be cancelled on expiry of the current term.\n', '', '', ''),
(1450, 1, 'Fourfourtwo', 'WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO FourFourTwo Magazine?\n\nWhy should you buy a subscription?\n\nThis monthly football magazine takes an in-depth look at the game''s biggest issues and brightest stars. Every edition is packed with opinion pieces from respected pundits and former professionals, as well as feature articles and interviews with the world''s best players, who discuss everything from their relationship with their teammates to their pre-match superstitions. With a subscription to FourFourTwo magazine, you''ll be able to read the popular ''The Player'' column every month, which gives you an insight into the things you don''t normally get to see in the professional football world, such as alcohol abuse and other off-field misbehaviour, providing an interesting backdrop to the other talking points covered in the magazine.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\nSign up for a subscription to FourFourTwo magazine, the glossy, stylish and provocative football magazine. A FourFourTwo magazine subscription will bring you everything the magazine has to offer every month. Feature articles and superb action photography will keep you gripped for more than just the first half, and with big name interviews with the stars, from today, tomorrow and yesteryear, you will definitely need extra time to finish it! Published by Haymarket, FourFourTwo magazine is a monthly magazine that has been running for 16 years so far. Taking its name from the football formation of the same name, which is considered to be a trustworthy formation in football, the magazine aims to echo this sentiment, providing consistent and trustworthy content. Don’t miss out, catch all the action all season long and invest in a subscription to FourFourTwo magazine today! ', '', '', ''),
(1451, 1, 'Vintage Roadscene', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nVintage Roadscene, Britain''s leading road transport history magazine, takes readers on a nostalgic trip back to the good old days of motoring as it used to be, when any road journey was a grand adventure. In the 20th Century, automobile, buses and commercial vehicles changed the way we all lived and the road system progressed from horse-carts on country lanes to the eight lane motorways of more recent times.\n\nIt has been a journey of massive development, technologically and socially, and not always for the good. Vintage Roadscene reflects on that wide-ranging history, using a team of transport historians presenting a series of lively, well-informed articles supported by unique period photographs; it truly is a trip down memory lane.\n', '', '', ''),
(1452, 1, 'Classic Motoring', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nClassic Motoring, formerly Classic Cars for Sale.\n\nLive your dreams with hundreds of the great classics to buy and sell every month.\n\nPlus features on shows, rallies and car makers together with club owners and automobilia.\n', '', '', ''),
(1453, 1, 'Ships Monthly', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nShips Monthly magazine continues to be the world''s top selling UK published specialist shipping magazine for enthusiasts and maritime professionals.\n\nShips Monthly constantly returns worldwide sales exceeding 18,000 copies per month and presents a balanced view of the fast-changing world of deep sea and coastal shipping. Printed in full colour throughout, each issue of Ships Monthly remains a valuable source of reference and is referred to time and time again.\n', '', '', ''),
(1454, 1, 'Yachting World', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nYachting World - the most authoritative international yachting magazine. Everything you need to know about yachting - from blue water cruiser to super-yacht. The best in nautical writing and photography and up-to-the-minute technical reports, equipment valuation, new boat tests and informed comment. Synonymous with quality, authority and excellence, Yachting World is known world-wide, being bought and read in over 100 countries. Ranging from blue water cruisers to super-yachts, Yachting World provides the best in nautical writing and photography, up-to-the-minute technical reports, equipment valuation, new boat tests and informed comments. Yachting World is renowned for its coverage of international regattas, round the world races and other events, the magazine also has the latest sailing news, first-hand cruising accounts and practical advice, our ever popular Great Seamanship series re-living epic sailing stories, new yacht equipment news and tests and offers a glimpse at the exotic world of super-yachting.\n', '', '', ''),
(1455, 1, 'Which Motorhome', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nBuy a subscription to Which Motorhome , the magazine to help you buy your perfect motorhome.\n\nIn every issue of Which Motorhome, you can enjoy:\n\nMore motorhome tests than any other magazine, and Which Motorhome is often the first to test new motorhomes as they are launched\n\n\nTests on all types and sizes of motorhomes from A-classes to campervans so there is something to suit all budgets\n\n\nTests on new and second-hand motorhomes and motorhome bargains across the country\n\n\nExtensive comparison tests, with up to 15 vehicles compared in one test, giving our verdict on each motorhome and an overall winner!\n\n\nWhich Motorhome also performs in-depth, long-term tests on specific motorhomes', '', '', ''),
(1456, 1, 'Waterways World', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Waterways World Magazine?\n\nFull of current waterways news and information, expert advice on boat buying, ownership, planning and fitting out, fascinating reports on the canals, heritage and modern cruising articles. Whether you live on them, enjoy cruising or holidaying on them, or study their remarkable history, no waterways enthusiast should be without Waterways World: Britain''s best-selling inland waterways magazine.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\n- Free Waterways World Annual every year your Direct Debit continues\n- Free digital subscription and access to digital back issues for the length of the postal subscription\n- 10% off tickets to Crick Boat Show\n- 10% off all books ordered from Waterways World\n- Free postage and packaging on all orders from Waterways World\n- Each issue delivered to your door\n', '', '', '');
