(1457, 1, 'Crafty Carper', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Crafty Carper Magazine?\n\nThis fishing magazine is the perfect choice if you want to develop your skills with help from some of the world''s leading carp fishers. In Crafty Carper you can read advice from Britain''s top-ranking fishermen, spilling the secret tricks and tools they use to land their impressive catches. You''ll get step-by-step tutorials and guides on how to improve your technique, with the opportunity to send in photos of your catch to the ''Crafty Carpers Catch Column'' to potentially win some great prizes. Each issue also has competitions, kit reviews and seasonal advice, helping you to fish successfully all year round.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIf you want to learn how to catch more carp then this is the magazine for you.\n\nPacked full of hints and tips from the UK''s top carp anglers. We show you the best tackle, bait &amp; rigs to keep you catching even in the hardest months.\n\nRead Crafty Carper and you will become a better angler.\n', '', '', ''),
(1458, 1, 'Eventing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEventing magazine is the only monthly magazine for the sport of horse trials. Eventing includes news, results, features, opinions and instructional articles. There are also commentaries and results from all major events, plus training features and profiles. Eventing suits everyone from the amateur to the professional rider, to those who help to run the sport as well as fans of the sport Eventing is a unique magazine, a sister publication to the UK''s leading equestrian weekly Horse &amp; Hound, and the only monthly publication in the world dedicated to providing detailed coverage of horse trials in the UK and abroad. Eventing magazine is full of action-packed reports, in-depth profiles of the people who are making news in the sport of horse trials, training articles which are relevant to serious horse owners wherever they live, a special gossip page, and world news. Eventing magazine offers an insight into the world of eventing, including news, results, features, opinions and instructional articles. There are also commentaries and results from all major events, together with training features and profiles. Subscribe to Eventing and every month you will be entertained and informed with an extensive coverage of the UK scene, as well as all major events around the world.\n', '', '', ''),
(1459, 1, 'Seahorse International Sailing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSeahorse is unique in that it is very deliberately written from no national perspective. Dedicated to sailboat racing, Seahorse''s pool of contributors are drawn from the ranks of the finest minds, opinion formers, movers, shakers and has the voice of those at the very apex of the sport.\n\nEvery issue brings you news from around the world, with interviews and opinions from those most respected in the sport, RORC updates and a race calendar and the Seahorse Sailor of the month competition.\n\nSeahorse magazine is a must have for those serious about sailboat racing.\n', '', '', ''),
(1460, 1, 'Motor Boat &amp; Yachting', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Motor Boat and Yachting magazine is a must for any boating enthusiast wanting the latest motor boat news, motor boat reviews and videos. Europe''s premier yachting magazine, Motor Boat and Yachting magazine features boat tests which are acknowledged as the most authoritative in the business. It’s technical coverage is without equal, plus no other publication offers so many motorboats for sale. Now in its 100th year, Motor Boat &amp; Yachting magazine provides a directory to the many motorboats on offer. Core editorial coverage focuses on boats up to 80ft, while four times a year MBY also carries Custom Yachting, a special focus on 80ft+ boats.\n', '', '', ''),
(1461, 1, 'Sporting Gun', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Sporting Gun Magazine?\n\nAll the features in Sporting Gun are written by professional shooters to give you great first-hand advice on pigeon and game shooting, wildfowling and even gun dog training. When you subscribe to this magazine, you’ll also be able to read up to date reviews to help you choose your next gun or equipment, as well as loads of game recipes to turn your catch into a delicious dinner. If you''re new to the sport, there are regular tuition sections to help even shooting beginners get an edge on the competition.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSporting Gun is Britain''s biggest selling shooting magazine thanks to a team that''s as passionate about the sport as its readers - professionals who love guns, gundogs, cartridges and conservation just as much as you do! It provides a practical editorial approach on techniques, equipment, dog training, pigeon shooting, shotgun tests and game cookery. Sporting Gun is the natural first choice for all levels to improve their shooting and understanding of this exhilarating sport.\n\nSporting Gun magazine provides its readers with a practical editorial approach on a broad range of gun-related topics, including techniques, equipment, dog training, pigeon shooting, shotgun tests and game cookery. A subscription to Sporting Gun magazine is the natural first choice for all levels to improve their shooting and understanding of this exhilarating sport. If you are looking for great gun reviews, dog training tips, shooting tuition, answers to shooting problems and 101 other ways to boost your sporting enjoyment all wrapped up in one essential bible, get a copy of the Sporting Gun magazine every month.\n', '', '', ''),
(1462, 1, 'Mountain Bike Rider', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Mountain Bike Rider Magazine?\n\nIf you spend hours tearing about on your bike across hilly terrain, then MBR could be a great addition to your mag collection.\n\nThis useful monthly title is packed with practical and helpful advice to ensure that mountain bikers know their stuff about where and what to ride.\n\nEach issue brings you bike reviews and buying guides, equipment and accessories tests, and riding tips to help you stay in control when you''re on a trail.\n\nSign up for a subscription to Mountain Bike Rider magazine and you''ll also get regular pull-out maps and route guides to show you where''s best to push yourself and your bike to the limit.\n\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWelcome to Britain’s best mountain bike magazine — MBR. Now in its tenth year — and with a host of top awards — mbr continues to be the most comprehensive, credible and informative bike mag this country has ever seen! Whether you’re a beginner or expert biker, MBR magazine is a must-read. For serious mountain bike enthusiasts who just want to go out and ride it. MBR has practical and technical content along with product ratings best buys equipment tests and consumer guidance. Subscribe to Mountain Bike Rider Magazine today and receive an ‘all you need to know’ guide to mountain biking.\n', '', '', ''),
(1463, 1, 'Trek &amp; Mountain', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Trek &amp; Mountain Magazine?\n\nThe world''s most impressive mountain ranges are the backdrop for all the reports, advice, and real-life stories you''ll find in Trek &amp; Mountain magazine. Whether you''re choosing tents for your first Alpine trek or want some final pointers for a Himalayan expedition, you''ll find plenty of wisdom to help you inside.\n\nTheir writers have summited an impressive collection of mountains themselves, and with a team including doctors, guidebook authors and even a few who''ve conquered Everest itself, you''ll be getting expert advice on every aspect of your climb.\n\nWith a subscription, you''ll get the benefit of all your fellow mountaineers'' experiences, and enjoy incredible tales from the peaks that are sure to motivate you to aim even higher next time.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTrek &amp; Mountain is the UK''s leading magazine dedicated to overseas trekking and mountaineering.Whether your goal is to trek to the top of Kili, or to Everest Base Camp, or to climb Mont Blanc, Aconcagua or one day even Everest itself, Trek &amp; Mountain gives you the knowledge, advice and inspiration to make it happen.Featuring contributions from qualified mountain guides, world-famous mountaineers and destination/route experts, Trek &amp; Mountain is dedicated to helping you ''reach your peak''. Whether you need advice on what gear to buy, what mountain skills you need, and which treks and mountains to attempt, there is no better place to find it than in Trek &amp; Mountain.\n', '', '', ''),
(1464, 1, 'Boat International', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nFor over 30 years we’ve brought boat owners and enthusiasts all the groundbreaking new yacht launches and the biggest and the best superyachts to take to the waves. This world leading coverage will always be at the forefront of the magazine, but now includes the lifestyle that goes with it.\n\nThe magazine is still the authority on the world’s best superyachts, but you can also expect fashion, watches, first-class columnists such as Sir Ben Ainslie, Eddie Jordan and Tina Green, plus an extended travel section.\n\nAlso, with our new club of superyacht owners we bring you extraordinary access to the passion and lives of some of the world’s greatest yachting advocates. Unlike any other magazine in the marketplace we go inside the community, to bring you fascinating features that other publications simply can’t offer.\n', '', '', ''),
(1465, 1, 'National Club Golfer', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nNational Club Golfer is the leading magazine for the serious player in Britain. It is the magazine of choice for the committed golfer and is packed with useful information, reviews and features - all put together by a team of expert writers. NCG provides an insightful &amp; trustworthy guide to all aspects of the game.\n\nInside every issue:\n\n- Fantastic coverage of equipment - read independent reviews and tests of all the latest gear from top brands like TaylorMade, Ping, Titleist, Callaway, Mizuno, Cleveland, Cobra and many more\n- Interviews and features with the game''s biggest names\n- Read our informative course reviews - whether you are looking for a 9-holer to play while on holiday in Scotland, an in-depth guide to an Open Championship venue or the best places to play &amp; visit in the UK and abroad.\n- Tips, methods &amp; gadgets to improve your game\n- Who to back in the next Major\n- Brilliant instruction from the professionals - real club pros, who know how to help the average player offer easy-to-understand hints and tips; while tour pros can help you gain finesse to save shots and hit the ball further and straighter\n- Great competitions that are free to enter - you can win all sorts of amazing prizes every month, from sets of top of the range clubs to your dream holiday\n- Funny, informed, entertaining and expert comment on all aspects of the game\n- And much, much more in every issue!\n\nNational Club Golfer - an in-depth and lively read every month!\n', '', '', ''),
(1466, 1, 'Race Tech', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Race Tech Magazine?\n\nFor those passionate about every stage of racing car production, a Race Tech magazine subscription is essential. Keeping its focus on topical developments in the world of motorsport technology, Race Tech offers a monthly look at everything from engines, tyres and electronics to wind tunnels and safety equipment. Whether your interest lies in Formula 1 or rally car racing, this magazine covers all the major competitions, with detailed analysis of the components and design behind the latest models and interviews with the technical elite in the motorsport industry.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEvery month RACE TECH is hot off the press with all the latest news, stories, new products and general development in the world of motorsport technology and industry.\n\nAn international publication read by the top executives, engineers, drivers, team owners and suppliers in the motorsport industry, RACE TECH magazine is the only independent, technology led motorsport magazine that focuses on every aspect of motorsport engineering.\nTotally international in its outlook, it covers everything that can be found competing on the track from Formula One to Clubman’s single-seaters, from Le Mans Prototypes to the low-cost GT racers and from 750Formula racecars and weekend hillclimb specials.\nTopics covered include Engine Components, Aerodynamics, Bearings, Brake Technology, CADCAM, CFD and simulation software, Coatings, Composites, Connectors, Cooling Systems, Control Systems, Data Acquisition, Drivetrain, Chassis and Transmission Dynos, Gearboxes, Hoses, Hybrid Systems, Electronics,Fabrication, Fluid Systems, Gauges and Instrument Panels, Ignition Systems, Lubricants, Machine Tools, Materials, Powertrain, Radiators, Safety Equipment, Simulation, Suspension Systems, Testing, Track equipment, Transmissions, Turbochargers, Tyres, Water Pumps and Wind Tunnels.\n\nIf you want to reach those parts of the industry that no other publication can, then look no further than RACE TECH.\n', '', '', ''),
(1467, 1, 'Carpworld', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Carpworld Magazine?\n\n\n\nAs a reader of Carpworld magazine, you''ll benefit from a variety of columns written by some of the most qualified experts in the sport.\n\nThe mag provides dozens of detailed reviews on equipment and locations, as well as top tips for improving your technique and picking the best fishing holiday destination.\n\nYou''ll also find the unique International Carper 32-page supplement, which features carp fishing news and opportunities beyond British waters, helping you to branch out and expand your fishing adventures farther afield.\n\nWhat''s more, there''s dozens of feature articles and guest pieces written by some of the sport''s most famous faces, including Simon Crow and Dave Lane.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCarpworld is the biggest read in carp fishing and is consistently packed with well-written, informative, entertaining and revealing material.\n\nCarpworld still leads the way in quality, size and the line-up of high-profile contributors including Terry Hearn, Dave Lane, Ian Chillcott, Simon Crow and many more!\n', '', '', ''),
(1468, 1, 'Scuba', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to SCUBA magazine brings you the official magazine of Britain''s biggest diving club, the British Sub-Aqua Club. SCUBA magazine is published monthly and is circulated to BSAC members. A subscription to SCUBA magazine means you get all the latest news, views and features on UK and BSAC club diving, snorkelling and all the important developments in our sport, straight to your door, every month. As well as ground-breaking diving articles, a SCUBA magazine subscription features the latest diving kit all reviewed by our dedicated in-house experts.Don''t miss out, take out a subscription to SCUBA magazine today.\n', '', '', ''),
(1469, 1, 'Dirt Mountain Bike', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Dirt Mountain Bike Magazine?\n\nFeaturing all the key international mountain bike action from the last month, Dirt MTB brings you a selection of the best downhill and 4X racing in the world.\n\nWith analysis and photography of recent events, this mountain bike magazine is ideal for anyone looking for detailed updates on how competitions have gone.\n\nOn top of all the latest action, a subscription to Dirt Mountain Bike magazine will also give you access to the regular ''Fresh Produce'' section, which includes reviews of new biking gear, plus travel ride guides and interviews with the most prominent names in the competitive mountain biking scene.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Dirt Mountain Bike magazine brings you is a mountain bike magazine aimed at the core riders in the sport, every month. Now in its 13th year, Dirt MTB continues to be the magazine of choice for the mountain biker who knows the score. Mixing the best downhill and 4X racing in the world, with dirt jumping, freeride and ‘bombing’ around on bikes. Whether it is down the local woods or on the top of an alpine mountain, Dirt MTB is there. Featuring work from the world’s top mountainbike journalists and photographers, the essence and energy of the sport is captured perfectly. As well as the action, it features the latest specialist gear, the personalities and promotes the subculture and lifestyle of modern day off-road riding.\n', '', '', ''),
(1470, 1, 'Air Gunner', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Air Gunner Magazine?\n\nIf you''re new or just returning to the world of air gunning and want to brush up your knowledge, Air Gunner magazine is the perfect way to do so.\n\nYou''ll love the reviews and advice from experts in the field, and the Airgun Guru problems page is sure to provide answers to all your questions.\n\nWith your subscription to this shooting magazine, you’ll get in-depth gun and equipment tests as well as the chance to participate in monthly swap shops and competitions.\n\nThere''s a section dedicated entirely to collectors'' guns sure to get you saving up to start your own, and even news on air gun activity from all over the world.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAn Air Gunner magazine subscription is ideal for anyone with a keen interest in airguns. Packed with reviews, advice and hunting features from emerging experts in the field, Air Gunner covers every aspect of the sport and would suit novice and seasoned shooter alike. Each month there are in depth gun tests, action-packed hunting features, monthly swap shop and competitions, pages dedicated to answering readers’ questions, crafts and maintenance tips PLUS all the latest guns and gear! Subscribing is a great way to get your favourite magazine delivered to your door every month or if you know someone who loves airguns, a subscription makes an affordable and ideal gift!\n', '', '', ''),
(1471, 1, 'Airgun World', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Airgun World Magazine?\n\nThis shooting magazine is run by a team of airgun experts, so you can be sure all the writing is from shooters as enthusiastic as you are.\nWith a subscription to Airgun World magazine, you''ll get reviews on all of the latest airguns and accessories, and you''re sure to love the monthly ‘Mega Test’ - a complete guide to all the latest top of the range airguns.\nYou can enjoy cutting edge news, views and analysis on airguns, with regular field tests and informed features including tales of real life hunting experiences.\nIssues from vermin control to D.I.Y. gunsmithing are also covered, along with advice on buying second hand guns from market professionals.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAirgun World is filled with articles and editorial by top gun experts: Britain''s best - former GP shooter Paul Bentley; World Class - World Champion Nick Jenkinson; Top tests by respected Terry Doe! PLUS Monthly ''Mega Test'' ~ your comprehensive guide to the latest top-of-the-range airguns! Airgun World magazine brings to you news, views and analysis from the world of airguns. Coming with gun tests, field tests, features, tips, techniques and informative features, Airgun World magazine is the best source of inspiration and knowledge for everyone who adopts this special hobby. Airgun World magazine will provide you with all of the latest airgun equipment which available from major manufacturers. In addition you will read about real life hunting experiences which contribute to making this magazine a one of it’s kind.\n', '', '', ''),
(1472, 1, '100% Biker', '&lt;p&gt;WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO 100% Biker Magazine? This monthly motorcycle magazine offers great coverage of everything going on in the world of custom bikes. If you subscribe to 100% Biker magazine, not only will you get reports from biker rallies and events from across the country, but you''ll also find profiles of some of the best custom bikes out there. You''ll read about Britain''s standout custom shops and their teams, and will be given handy ''How to'' guides to help you modify your own vehicle. With a range of reader letters, biker babes, and classified listings in every issue, this magazine is a great way for any custom bike fan to stay up-to-date with the biking scene. FROM THE PUBLISHER A subscription to 100% Biker magazine is the perfect choice for the true biker enthusiast. Whether you are customizing your bike or you want to know about biking events happening around the UK, 100% Biker has your name on it.A custom bike magazine - custom built for bikers. 100% Biker Magazine has been in the newsagents for over six years now and has an ever-growing loyal reader base. We cover the complete UK custom bike scene, including a diverse mix of bikes from Chops to Streetfighters, Trikes and even some great Classics. Read about rallys, learn about new biking products and gain access to the world of the custom build.100% Biker is published by Jazz publishing and is the magazine of choice for true bikers who love knowing everything about their favorite hobby. Learn how to customize your own bike with a subscription to 100% Bike magazine.&lt;/p&gt;\n', '', '', ''),
(1473, 1, 'Today''S Golfer', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Today''s Golfer Magazine?\n\nIf you want a magazine that helps you to immerse yourself in the world of your favourite sport, then a subscription to Today''s Golfer magazine is just the thing for you. This title covers everything from competition and tour news, to reviews of all the latest gear and tips to improve your golf. You''ll also find expertly written equipment buying guides to help your find the perfect clubs and accessories, plus player reviews of some of the best courses in the UK. A subscription to Today''s Golfer magazine also gives you access to the exclusive online environment, where you''ll find everything from Fantasy Golf to a cutting-edge handicap tracker.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\nToday''s Golfer is about giving you information on playing better, buying better gear, and choosing better courses.\n\nToday''s Golfer magazine team wants to give you the tools to play better golf, whether that means giving you the best golf instruction, pointing you in the direction of the best golf equipment, or making sure you''re playing the right golf courses.\n', '', '', ''),
(1474, 1, 'Golf World', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Golf World Magazine?\n\nWith a contemporary twist to traditional golfing publications, a Golf World magazine subscription covers a range of engaging topics, from international championships to celebrity players. This leading mag combines everything you need to know about golfing techniques and the latest equipment, as well as news from the world''s top tours and competitions. Knowledgeable authorities from the world of golf offer their opinions on the sport, providing you with a fascinating insight into some of the game''s greatest moments. You''ll also find interesting features on the latest trends in golfing fashion, and a behind the scenes look at some of the world''s best courses.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nEvery month, this golf magazine has exclusive tips from the biggest names in the game, advice on the best gear for you, reviews of the best courses in the world and brilliant features by the best writers in golf.\n', '', '', ''),
(1475, 1, 'Improve Your Coarse Fishing', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Improve Your Coarse Fishing Magazine?\n\nThis dedicated fishing magazine focuses on developing your technique and helping you to increase the size of your daily catch, with detailed how-to supplements for those keen to perfect their craft. You''ll also find plenty of articles on a range of topics that celebrate the best of British fishing, plus amazing photography to remind you why you love the sport so much. This magazine caters to fishers of all abilities, covering a diverse range of locations and species. What''s more, an Improve Your Coarse Fishing magazine subscription will provide you with lots of reviews on the latest kit and tackles.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nEven better value for money, Improve Your Coarse Fishing is now split in two separate publications that complement each other perfectly.\n\nIn the main ‘Improve’ you’ll find a new slant on modern fishing as we emphasise the great things about our sport and celebrate why we go angling. The best in fishing photography, more descriptive writing, longer features to let the pictures breathe and less hard core instruction have made the magazine a more relaxed read where every page reminds you how great fishing is.\n\nThere’s now a 23-page tackle section that has doubled in size and gives a lot more exposure to new kit hitting the market.\n\nThe second part of the new IYCF is a 48-page collectable supplement called Tips &amp; Tactics – this is a technical, mechanical and explicitly ‘How To’ magazine that’s aimed solely at improving angler’s skills. Each issue contains expert instructional features on float, feeder, pole, carp and specialist fishing so no matter what type of fishing the reader is interested in there’s something to put into practice\n', '', '', ''),
(1476, 1, 'Sea Angler', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Sea Angler Magazine?\n\nThis top fishing magazine is known for its meticulous and comprehensive coverage of all things angling, and has established a reputation as something of a bible for keen sea fishermen.\n\nA Sea Angler magazine subscription will bring you news, views and reviews from the sea-fishing community each month, as well as thrilling stories and expert tips to help you improve both your technique and your catch.\n\nYou''ll find features on every angle of saltwater fishing, with a main section focused on shore and beach fishing, plus major supplements covering angling.\n\nThere''s even some excellent coverage of the increasingly popular sport of kayak fishing.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSea Angler is the leading magazine for sea fishing news, tackle, tactics and marks to fish. If you''re a beach or boat angler thirsty for news, fishing stories, tackle tests, where to fish guides, and tips from the experts, then look no further! Sea Angler magazine gives you everything you need to catch fish!\n', '', '', ''),
(1477, 1, 'Cycling Plus', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Cycling Plus Magazine?\n\nRoad cyclists should look no further than a subscription to Cycling Plus magazine if they want a monthly title that offers bike reviews, equipment tests and helpful buying guides.\n\nEvery issue includes riding advice and nutrition tips in its ''Know How'' section, with the Q&amp;A feature letting you write in to have your questions answered on everything from cycling technique and fitness concerns to the most suitable bike upgrades.\n\nThe regular ''Routes'' section of this cycling magazine takes an in-depth look at cycle rides across the nation, categorising them as ''classic'', ''expert'', ''medium'' or ''easy'' so that you know whether they''re appropriate for your level.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Cycling Plus magazine is a must-have for all you cycle enthusiasts out there. A Cycling Plus subscription is the manual for the modern road cyclist. Whether you''re cycling weekly, an occasional new rider or a Tour de France fan you’ll find everything you need. Each issue is packed with buying advice and tests of essential cycling gear - everything from bikes to bags! Cycling Plus is the place to find training advice, nutrition secrets and practical tips guaranteed to improve your bicycling. It''s also full of inspirational rides, real-life cycling stories and entertaining riding-related features. If you are a cycling enthusiast who is just starting out and keen to learn more or a seasoned pro looking to feed their appetite for all things cycling, then a subscription to Cycling Plus magazine is the one for you.\n', '', '', ''),
(1478, 1, 'Trout &amp; Salmon', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Trout &amp; Salmon Magazine?\n\nLoved for its stunning photography, this fishing magazine is the go-to guide for serious game fishermen.A subscription to Trout &amp; Salmon magazine brings you product reviews of the latest tackle as well as tips on the best fishing locations in the UK and helpful technique guides for beginners.You''ll also find historical features on traditional fishing techniques and gear from years gone by, as well as more exotic pieces delving into the depths of waters from around the world, and the types of fish to be found there.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nTrout and Salmon magazine has been the Voice of Game-Fishing since 1955. Every month the finest contributors in the sport deliver informative, inspirational and entertaining writing, offering sage advice on locations, tackle and tactics with beautiful photography.\n\nIf you are searching for a new place to fish, Trout and Salmon’s Fishing Reports are a collectable record of the state of Britain and Ireland’s major game fisheries and have become an important archive for all fly-fishers.\n\nTrout and Salmon magazine is also a forum for debate of the most contentious issues that dominate fly-fishing today.\n', '', '', ''),
(1479, 1, 'Trout Fisherman', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Trout Fisherman Magazine?\n\nThis fishing magazine focuses on landing trout, with tutorials, reviews and retrospectives of fishing through the ages all combining to make great reading for enthusiastic anglers. Serious fishermen will love the detailed technical content, as well as hints and tips on everything from tackle and equipment to the best locations. All of the advice for improving your technique comes from expert still water anglers with lots of experience, so if you''re keen to improve the quality of your catch, a Trout Fisherman magazine subscription could be just the thing to boost your skills.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTrout Fisherman magazine will fulfil your tackle, instruction and where to fish needs. If you’re into still-water fly fishing, it’s a must read, comprehensively covering techniques to catch even more fish, with detailed, informative and friendly advice.\n', '', '', ''),
(1480, 1, 'Country Walking', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Country Walking Magazine?\n\nThis handy magazine makes a great companion for any dedicated countryside explorer.\n\nNot only does every issue of Country Walking have plenty of detailed descriptions of popular and less well known walking routes, it also provides illustrated Ordnance Survey maps in a handy pull-out guide, helping you stick to your chosen path without worrying about getting lost.\n\nAs well as expert advice on where to walk, there are tips on health and fitness, and checklists for essential kit so you can make sure you set off fully equipped for every adventure. Special features include walks around famous filming locations, suggestions for international trails and in-depth explorations of routes in the beautiful National Parks.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Country Walking magazine subscription is perfect for the outdoors enthusiast. Britain''s best-selling walking magazine, Country Walking magazine shares and celebrates your passion for walking and inspires reader’s to get the best from the UK’s great outdoors. Country Walking is packed with stunning photography, great writing, brilliant, practical advice, expert kit tests, and a superb pull-out guide of walks around the UK, each route illustrated with an Ordnance Survey map. Country Walking magazine maximises the fitness and health benefits of the walks by providing professional advice with expert kit reviews so reader’s know the right gear to buy. Subscribe today with a Country Walking magazine subscription - It''s your perfect walking companion! The Direct Debit Guarantee The minimum subscription term for the direct debit offer is 12 months. The amount paid by Direct Debit may change over time. If and when it does you will be notified in advance by at least 10 days. If an error is made by Bauer Media Ltd or by bank/building society, you are entitled to a full and immediate refund. You can cancel the Direct Debit at any time by writing to your bank/building society and send a copy to Bauer Media Ltd at: Magazine Subscriptions, Tower House, Sovereign Park, Market Harborough, Leicestershire LE94 7ZT. Please note that banks and building societies may not accept Direct Debit instructions from some types of account.\n', '', '', ''),
(1481, 1, 'Pro Cycling', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Pro Cycling Magazine?\n\nProCycling magazine will give you genuinely exclusive access to the world of professional racing.\n\nWith a monthly subscription to Pro Cycling magazine, not only will you get detailed previews of upcoming tours and competitions, with expert analysis of the courses and favourites, but you''ll also get reports focusing on recent events, which come with stunning race photography.\n\nYou''ll read rider diaries written by professional cyclists throughout the season, covering topics as wide-ranging as fitness levels, personal highs and lows, and planned team changes, and you''ll also find road tests of new bikes, frames, wheels and race jerseys, making this the ideal mag for both active cyclists and armchair cycling fans.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to ProCycling magazine and get the colour, action and drama of the world''s most spectacular sport in a glossy and dynamic monthly magazine. With a subscription to ProCycling magazine you will get access to exclusive features and spectacular photography. ProCycling magazine brings to life the complexities, rivalries and hardships of the European professional scene.\n', '', '', ''),
(1482, 1, 'World Soccer', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO World Soccer Magazine?\n\nIf you''re looking for detailed match reports, transfer rumours and back office stories from some of the world''s biggest clubs, then this is the perfect football magazine for you. With contributing writers from countries around the world, you''ll get expert answers to the questions you''ve argued over with your friends for years, with features on everything from which country has the best league, to the club with the most exciting young players, as well as the Player, Manager and Coach of the Year. You''ll also find interviews with legendary footballers, expert analysis of team strategy and management, and the latest news from international competitions taking place across the globe.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWorld Soccer is the magazine for the football fan who wants to know everything about the beautiful game. Considered as THE authority by professionals and fans, it contains all the latest news about the game’s biggest stars, teams and competitions, plus what the future holds for the sport.\n\nIf you are Football mad, or know someone who is, place a subscription to World Soccer magazine today! World Soccer is the magazine for people who are serious about football. Inside, you''ll find comprehensive coverage and intelligent analysis of the global game. Every month, our worldwide network of correspondents bring you the latest news and stories on the events that matter. Subscribe to World Soccer and you''ll join a special club that includes John Motson and Martin Tyler and you’ll see why Reuters calls us “the bible of international football”.World Soccer Magazine is the best-selling monthly magazine that covers all aspects of International football. Published by IPC Media, this magazine reaches you with all essential news and information from the world of football. This magazine comes with a detailed description on all football matches from across the globe. An experts team of the month is announced each month, where teams are analysed in depth and features include interviews with your favourite stars.Subscribe to World Soccer magazine today and receive your monthly fix from your favourite sport.\n', '', '', ''),
(1483, 1, 'Cycle Sport', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Cycle Sport Magazine?\n\nEvery issue of this cycling magazine comes with in-depth analysis of key stages in recent professional tours and road events, including the Tour de France and Vuelta a España.\n\nWith a subscription to Cycle Sport magazine, you''ll read interviews with road racing''s most prominent figures, and opinion pieces on current issues in the professional scene.\n\nThe ''Our Man in the Bunch'' feature brings you monthly insights from an anonymous cycling pro about everything from handling the media to what life''s really like in the peloton, while the retro ''I love...'' articles focus on a particular year in road cycling''s history, making this a great read for both new and longstanding cycling fans.\n\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCycle Sport is well established as the leading magazine for fans of professional road racing. Comprehensive coverage of the world''s leading pro events, coupled with a unique ability to get the inside story, big interviews and stunning action photography, ensures that Cycle Sport is the most comprehensive magazine in the field. Take out a subscription to Cycle Sport magazine. Cycle Sport magazine is well established as the leading magazine for fans of professional road racing. Every issue in a subscription to Cycle Sport magazine comes with comprehensive coverage of the world''s leading pro events, top inside stories, big name interviews and stunning photography all help to make the magazine the leading authority on the international racing scene. Cycle Sport magazine, published by IPC Media, is a fantastic magazine for road cycling enthusiasts. In your subscription to Cycle Sport magazine you will get access to the very best cycle tests, kit reviews, race coverage, events information and interviews. And as well as all this, each installment of a Cycle Sport magazine subscription comes with travel stories, route ideas, health and fitness advice and much more. Don’t miss out – get yourself a subscription to Cycle Sport magazine today!\n', '', '', ''),
(1484, 1, 'Miniworld', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMini World magazine is dedicated to the car we all love- the Mini. A subscription comes with 13 issues per year delivered to your door.\n\nEach issue is packed full of the latest mini news, pages dedicated to vintage models, a huge mini classifieds section, test driving, latest show events and photos and commentary of events just gone.\n\nIf you or a friend are a Mini fan, don''t miss out on the essential Mini World magazine subscription.\n', '', '', ''),
(1485, 1, 'Retro Cars', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRetro Cars is a monthly car magazine for drivers who prefer tinkering and driving to polishing and picnic hampers. Aimed at the practical-minded hands-on owner, it offers a mix of material which can’t be found in either the mainstream car magazines or the older classic car titles. Covering vehicles from the early 1960s to the mid 1980s, Retro Cars is aimed at imaginative enthusiasts with real-world budgets.\n', '', '', ''),
(1486, 1, 'What Mountain Bike', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO What Mountain Bike Magazine?\n\nThis monthly cycling magazine will provide you with everything you need to make the most of your mountain bike.\n\nIf you subscribe to What Mountain Bike magazine, you''ll find answers to common bike maintenance questions in every issue, plus a detailed ''Ride Guide'' that gives you an in-depth look of some of the best mountain bike routes in Britain, so that you know where to ride.\n\nYou''ll also read bike test reviews in the magazine''s ''First Rides'' section, where experts try out the latest bikes on the terrain they were made for, and if you want information on which clothes or bike accessories to buy, you''ll definitely appreciate the ''Trail Tested'' articles.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to What Mountain Bike magazine is ideal for all cross-country and trail riders. What Mountain Bike shows readers what to ride, where to ride and how to ride. Packed with inspiring writing and photography and more pages devoted to totally impartial testing than any other magazine, including a brand new 23-page Buyers Guide and a 14-page location-focused Routes Guide you can be sure you’ll find all the information you need to make the right choice on everything from tyres to complete full suspension bikes. It is the essential magazine to consult before you spend your cash.\n', '', '', ''),
(1487, 1, 'Mountain Biking Uk', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Mountain Biking UK Magazine?\n\nWith 25 years'' experience in giving mountain biking enthusiasts all the info they need to enjoy the activity even more, this cycling magazine is ideal for any level of rider.\n\nA monthly subscription to Mountain Biking UK magazine will not only bring you handy ''How to'' riding guides to make sure you stay in control on any terrain, but it''ll also offer in-depth tests of bikes and accessories in different price ranges, keeping you informed on how to get the best equipment for your money. With pull-out maps or detailed route guides in every issue, covering both the UK and abroad, this practical magazine will show you the best places to ride.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to MBUK magazine is made by mountain bikers to inform, excite, and inspire other mountain bikers. We combine supreme authority and massive commitment with an enthusiasm that frequently crosses over into the mildly insane.\nFrom outrageous adrenaline-driven stunts to world-taming expeditions, if it’s driven by mountain biking, we''ll be there to offer encouragement and have some fun. Firmly established as the market leader, MBUK magazine aims to tell the whole truth about radical mountain biking, bikes and equipment in an uncompromising manner. Regular editorial features grime time, test and reviews, news, world and domestic racing coverage and lifestyle. Mountain Biking magazine is UK''s top magazine for mountain biking enthusiasts. The magazine brings you the passion, liveliness and knowledge of renowned mountain biking enthusiasts, who go to different dirt tracks, adrenaline rushing trails and impossible mountain tracks to give you the most exciting writing on mountain biking. The magazine also comes with the most stunning action photography and quick comparison of bikes and bike products which you look to buy. The magazine has something for all bikers, no matter what their riding styles or skill levels are.\n', '', '', ''),
(1488, 1, 'Yachting Monthly', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nYachting Monthly - essential reading for those who actively sail their boats Written by sailors for sailors who want to discover new horizons. Readers’ real-life experiences in our Sailing Skills section and ''Confessional'' page. Authoritative reports on yachting equipment, new technology and new and second-hand boats by one of the most trusted test teams in the business. A Yachting Monthly subscription will provide you with an all you need to know guide to sailing.Written by sailors, for sailors, Yachting Monthly is at the heart of the British yachting market for people who actively sail their boats. Yachting Monthly provides an authoritative, yet entertaining, mix of information for yachtsmen with any level of experience.Each issue contains informative and inspirational articles, readers share real-life experiences in the Sailing Skills section and the ''Confessional'' page. Plus read authoritative reports on yachting equipment, new technology and new and second-hand boats by one of the most trusted test teams in the industry.Yachting Monthly magazine is at the heart of the British yachting market and is for people who actively sail in their spare time, whether cruising across the coast or further afield in blue waters. It provides an entertaining mix of vital information for cruising yachtsmen with all levels of experience which maximises their enjoyment, increases their skills and gives them the confidence to broaden their horizons.Subscribe today to Yachting Monthly magazine and keep up-to-date with the goings on in the world.\n', '', '', ''),
(1489, 1, 'Practical Boat Owner', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPractical Boat Owner is Britain''s biggest-selling boating magazine and a brand readers really trust. A source of useful and helpful information for boat owners, both power and sail, it helps them get the most from their chosen leisure activity. Its affluent, but practically-minded consumers find PBO is a forum for interacting with like-minded individuals. A Practical Boat Owner magazine subscription is an essential monthly read for anyone with a passion for sailing and motorboating. Practical Boat Owner magazine features a mix of expert advice, readers'' experiences and tests of the latest boats and gear that makes Practical Boat Owner Britain''s most popular boating magazine. Practical Boat Owner magazine brings you expert tips for better boat-handling, how to get your boat into top gear, major tests of the latest electronics and life saving gear, plus lots of advice to help you get the most from your boating budget. Plus, Practical Boat Owner also boasts a special Motorboat section in every issue. Practical Boat Owner magazine makes a perfect gift subscription for anyone with a passion for sailing and motor boating. With a Practical Boat Owner magazine subscription you’ll ensure you never miss an issue.\n', '', '', ''),
(1490, 1, 'Golf Monthly', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Golf Monthly Magazine?\n\nWhy buy a subscription to Golf Monthly?\n\nWritten by golfers for golfers, a Golf Monthly magazine subscription is the ideal way to keep up-to-date with your favourite sport. This well-established and entertaining publication was founded in 1911, and has slowly become the most reliable source of golfing news and advice in the UK.\n\nIn addition to reviews of all the latest equipment and interviews with today''s top players, you''ll find exclusive betting guides and top tips to help you make the most of the sport''s biggest championships. There''s also plenty of advice from 25 of the golfing world''s leading coaches in each issue, and dozens of hints for how to improve your game.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGolf Monthly, quite simply, is the quality brand for golfers. It includes tips, drills and advice from the UK''s Top 25 coaches and the leading names on Tour; find the best gear for your game reviewed; read reviews on where to play and stay, both in the UK and abroad and interviews with the stars of the European and PGA Tours. Plus, there is up-to-date news and views from every level of the game. A subscription to Golf Monthly magazine is packed full of all the help and information you need to improve your game every month. Golf Monthly magazine is your complete guide to golfing, whether you play on the driving ranges or in tournaments, dabble or get serious. Golf Monthly magazine is the world’s oldest monthly golfing magazine and was established in 1911 by double Open Champion, Harold Hilton. Golf Monthly magazine is written by golfers, for golfers.\n', '', '', ''),
(1491, 1, 'Super Yacht World', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSuperYacht World is a luxury magazine breathing fresh life into the superyacht market. From helping readers choose the best charter vessel for that holiday of a lifetime, to highlighting designer watches made out of recycled steel from the Titanic, SuperYacht World provides the access for readers to share in the privilege of being on board the world''s finest yachts.\n', '', '', ''),
(1492, 1, 'Sailing Today', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWith every issue of Sailing Today you will see our passion for cruising throughout the magazine. Keeping in step with all the latest trends, boats and products, Sailing Today is the UK’s magazine for hands on cruising sailors. Launched in 1997, Sailing Times broke the mould from day one, quickly establishing a loyal following by offering a younger, more dynamic and appealing mix of content than the old, mature, niche titles. Known especially for its in-depth boat, gear and equipment articles, every issue includes 12 pages of new and used boat tests and up to 30 pages of gear tests, reviews and explanations.\n', '', '', ''),
(1493, 1, 'Advanced Carp Fishing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nAdvanced Carp Fishing is aimed at the aspirational carper. If you''ve caught your first twenty, or if you simply want to catch much bigger fish, this is the magazine for you. It''s packed full of easy-to-read features, eye-pleasing photos and loads of top tips from the best carp anglers in England.\n\nAnd, being a subscriber to Advanced Carp Fishing doesn''t just mean your magazine turns up early – you''ll be part of the team with a whole host of extra benefits.\n» 10% discount on all purchases at Angling Direct\n» FREE access to the experts at anglinganswers.com\n» 10% off Angler''s First Insurance\n', '', '', ''),
(1494, 1, 'Coarse Fishing Answers', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nCoarse Fishing Answers is the place where you can put your questions to the best angling minds in the UK, safe in the knowledge that you''ll get good advice that will really help your fishing. Unlike any other magazine out there, Coarse Fishing Answers belongs to you as it is you that drives the content of the magazine and ensures that it is kept relevant always interesting.\n\nBeing a subscriber doesn''t just mean your magazine turns up early – you''ll be part of the team with these extra benefits:\n\n» 10% discount on purchases at Angling Direct\n» FREE access to the experts at anglinganswers.com forum\n» 10% off Angler''s First Insurance\n', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `oc_product_description` (`product_id`, `language_id`, `name`, `description`, `meta_description`, `meta_keyword`, `tag`) VALUES
(1495, 1, 'Total Carp', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nTotal Carp is the fresh-faced, up-to-the-minute magazine for the modern carp angler striving for success. It’s no surprise that it''s also the biggest selling carp fishing magazine in Europe. Whether it''s your first carp or your next carp we''ll help you catch it!\n\nAnd, being a subscriber to Total Carp doesn''t just mean your magazine turns up early – you''ll be part of the team with a whole host of extra benefits.\n» 10% discount on all purchases at Angling Direct\n» FREE access to the experts at anglinganswers.com\n» 10% off Angler''s First Insurance\n', '', '', ''),
(1496, 1, 'Total Sea Fishing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSea angling is about having fun and is for the whole family and we at Total Sea Fishing love nothing more than helping you by offering top tips and tricks, as well as expert advice from the best in the business.\n\nTotal Sea Fishing will keep you abreast of the hottest news and gossip, check out our no-holds barred reviews on all the latest tackle, detailed step-by-step features on how to catch the fish you seek, plus several pages dedicated to your catch reports.\n\nAnd, being a subscriber to Total Sea Fishing doesn''t just mean your magazine turns up early – you''ll be part of the team with a whole host of extra benefits.\n» 10% discount on all purchases at Angling Direct\n» FREE access to the experts at anglinganswers.com\n» 10% off Angler''s First Insurance\n', '', '', ''),
(1497, 1, 'Education World', 'Education World, established in 1999, is a magazine addressing the topics of human development and education. The monthly magazine provides a source for India and beyond.', '', '', ''),
(1498, 1, 'Youth Incorporated', 'Youth Incorporated is a monthly magazine that offers a dual focus on education and entertainment, encompassing career and lifestyle stories and catering to the aspirations of today’s youth. The magazine showcases relevant information and articles on education in India and abroad. With campus reviews, student profiles, professor interviews and a strong focus on careers and entrepreneurship, the magazine aims to empower the youth in today’s competitive world. Also interesting entertainment features and articles on fashion, beauty, technology, health &amp; fitness, food, sports and other relevant subjects makes it a one stop shop for the youth. Our goal is to provide well-rounded content for the innovators of today.', '', '', ''),
(1499, 1, 'Teen Vogue', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nFrom the editors of VOGUE USA comes TEEN VOGUE, the fashion magazine for teens.\n\nCheck out the major trends and the season''s essentials, celebrity info, movies, music and shopping. TEEN VOGUE offers great advice on peer pressure, body image and self identity.\n\nTEEN VOGUE focuses on beauty and fashion, retaining all the style of Vogue while remaining affordable.\n', '', '', ''),
(1500, 1, 'Engineering In Miniature', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Engineering in Miniature Magazine?\n\nIdeal for anybody who likes to dabble in any kind of miniature engineering, this modelling magazine covers all the bases, with information on working with marine, petrol and hot-air engines as well as locomotives, steam-road vehicles and even clocks.\n\nYou''ll love the how-to guides written by experts with extensive and detailed drawings, and there are regular hints and tips sections to give you those all-important pointers.\n\nEngineering in Miniature has great features in every issue, including Model Engineering Club, Society Newsround, and a special section for Young Engineers just starting out, as well as book reviews and a comprehensive guide to events and clubs nationwide.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSince its launch in 1979, Engineering in Miniature has established a reputation for its quality of articles and drawings and is read by professional and amateur engineers throughout the world. Published monthly it features construction articles on all aspects of model engineering. These articles describe the construction of scale model locomotives, steam road vehicles, stationary, marine, petrol and hot air engines, clocks, plus of course numerous model engineer workshop projects. Regular features include Model Engineering Club and Society News, Young Engineers, Readers Letters, Book Reviews, Hints and Tips and a comprehensive Diary of Events.\n', '', '', ''),
(1501, 1, 'Classic Plant &amp; Machinery', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nInvest in a subscription to Classic Plant &amp; Machinery magazine - the biggest selling classic plant and machinery magazine in the world. Every issue of a subscription to Classic Plant &amp; Machinery magazine features dumptrucks, excavators, loading shovels, forklifts, mining machinery, backhoe loaders - whether you love Caterpillar, JCB, Ruston-Bucyrus or International, you will find it in this magazine. Brought to you by Kelsey Publishing Group, a subscription to Classic Plant &amp; Machinery magazine brings, direct to your door, plenty of information about vintage construction, mining and ancillary equipment. The writers of Classic Plant &amp; Machinery magazine scour the world searching for old tractors, mining equipment, earth moving equipment and other heavy-duty equipments especially for the vintage machinery enthusiast. If you have a love for classic production machinery then a subscription to Classic Plant &amp; Machinery magazine is the ideal subscription for you.\n', '', '', ''),
(1502, 1, 'Good Woodworking', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Good Woodworking is perfect for keen woodworking hobbyists and professional woodworkers alike.Each month it offers advice and guidance on a wide range of woodworking topics, via stage-by-stage project articles, in-depth technical features, workshop tips and product tests. A dedicated turning section caters for this important group of woodworkers, while readers can use the free Q&amp;A service to have their questions answered by experts.The Woodworker aims to put across even the more complicated techniques in an accessible, easy-to-read style which is authoritative but at the same time conversational in tone.\n', '', '', ''),
(1503, 1, 'World Pipelines', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to World Pipelines magazine, the international b2b publication tailored to meet the specific needs of the global oil and gas pipeline industry, covering all aspects of pipeline engineering, construction and maintenance, as well as the technical and business issues that pertain to the industry. With a subscription to World Pipelines magazine, you will benefit from the in-depth coverage and analysis of international oil and gas pipeline activity, which will enable you to gain greater insight into the issues affecting your industry. Published twelve times a year, each issue in a subscription to World Pipelines magazine includes a comprehensive regional review, detailed industry commentary, the latest pipeline project reports and expert technical articles. Don’t miss out, invest in a subscription to World Pipelines magazine today!\n', '', '', ''),
(1504, 1, 'World Coal Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nTake out a subscription to World Coal, the leading monthly industry magazine that covers the entire coal chain, from the mine to the power plant. World Coal magazine provides regular features covering every step of the process, including: both underground and opencast mining technique, coal preparation, transportation and end use, as well as regular news, comment, regional reports, penetrating analysis of the key issues in the industry today and the development of new and cleaner coal-based fuels and technologies. Each month also features a regional report, which focuses on a specific coal producing region in depth, as well as monthly news and editorial comment. A subscription to World Coal magazine provides everything you need to know about the industry.\n', '', '', ''),
(1505, 1, 'World Cement', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to World Cement magazine, which is a leading source of business, technical and analytical information for all who are involved in the day-to-day business of manufacturing cement and lime. World Cement magazine is fully international, with every issue in a subscription containing monthly regional overviews, expert analysis and case studies, as well as in-depth technical articles and features. In addition, we publish an annual Bulk Materials Handling Review, focusing on materials handling in and around cement plants, aggregate plants, terminals and ports. A subscription to World Cement magazine is essential reading for decision makers such as Chief Executives, Technical Directors, Plant Managers, Procurement Managers, Cement Terminal Operators, and Maintenance Managers. Three great reasons to take out a subscription to World Cement magazine: - Free delivery, straight to your door every month - Never miss an issue - Great savings off the cover price So don’t hesitate, invest in a subscription to World Cement magazine today!\n', '', '', ''),
(1506, 1, 'Italia!', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO ITALIA! Magazine?\n\nExplore all things bellísimo about Italy by taking advantage of a subscription to ITALIA! magazine.\n\nYou''ll find detailed and in-depth guides to everything from the best restaurants to the most important museums, as well as interesting places to shop and gorgeous countryside vineyards to explore.\n\nIf you’re looking to buy a villa or a holiday home, ITALIA! magazine will provide you with expert advice on property prices and the buying process, plus handy hints and tips from the locals.\n\nSo, whether you''re looking to plan a short break, move your family or simply keep up to date with the Italian way of life, this is the mag for you.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nItalia is the award-winning magazine for everyone who has a passion for Italy.\n\nEach month, you’ll find a wide variety of beautifully photographed and intelligently written articles to inspire and inform you. Covering every aspect of Italian life, from travel, holidays and property to food, wine and culture, we bring Italy closer to English-speaking readers across the world.\n', '', '', ''),
(1507, 1, 'Lonely Planet Traveller', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Lonely Planet Traveller Magazine?\n\nThe contributors to this leading travel magazine have scoured the globe in order to bring you amazing first-hand insights into hundreds of holiday destinations from across the globe, as well as local knowledge to help you make the most of your next trip abroad.Detailed feature articles are complemented by stunning photography, whilst handy pull-out mini guides provide you with a compact travel companion.With dozens of must-see sights and attractions, guides to the best local delicacies and hundreds of tips for everything from hostels to hotels, a Lonely Planet Traveller magazine subscription will guide you through the process of booking your next luxury holiday or last-minute break.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\nLonely Planet Traveller magazine is packed to the brim with in-depth features from Lonely Planet’s experienced travel writers and is illustrated with stunning photographs that are guaranteed to ‘take you there’, even when you’re sitting at home.\n\nCovering everything from exotic long-haul trips to destinations much closer to home, each month Lonely Planet Traveller magazine will give you insider knowledge and expert advice, with pull-out Mini Guides and maps so you can refer to them when you’re planning your next trip.\n\nLonely Planet Traveller Magazine is packed with:\n\n• Inspirational travel features\n• Stunning photography\n• Mini guides to pull out and keep\n\nLonely Planet is the largest travel guide book and digital media publisher in the world and also has its own television production company, which has produced a number of TV series, including ‘Lonely Planet Six Degrees, he Sport Traveller’ and ‘Lonely Planet: Roads Less Travelled’.\n', '', '', ''),
(1508, 1, 'Vw Camper &amp; Bus', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nJoin The World''s best-selling VW Camper magazine! VolksWorld Camper and Bus offers everything for the Bus fan from camping kit, news and products, history on various models and also includes a useful step by step ‘How To’ section to help the reader perform regular maintenance procedures and must have upgrades.\n\nThere are features on fantastic Buses from standard Campers to modified custom Vans from the ‘50s right up to modern examples.\n', '', '', ''),
(1509, 1, 'Conde Nast Traveller', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Conde Nast Traveller Magazine?\n\nGet ideas for your next trip away, or indulge in some armchair travel with the most glamorous recommendations from a team of independent travel writers. You can keep up to date with the latest luxury travel news with a Condé Nast Traveller magazine subscription, making it easy to perfectly time your next escape. This magazine takes a unique look at the world of travel, catering exclusively to those with a taste for luxury. It features only the best restaurants, hotels and resorts, with hand-picked tropical islands and chic local destinations making a regular appearance each month.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\nA Condé Nast Traveller magazine subscription is a must for the luxurious traveller. Condé Nast Traveller magazine is packed with great destinations, a range of places to stay to suit all budgets, loads of informative travel tips, plus plenty of surprises abroad and closer to home. The magazine features stunning photography with Unique and exclusive hand picked holiday recommendations for every traveller! Condé Nast Traveller magazine has a ’no freebies, no travel press trips’ policy and reports on how places really are. This means that you can trust us as the leading independent authority when it comes to planning a holiday or business trip. Exciting, inspiring, and authoritative, a Conde Nast Traveller magazine subscription presents more than 100 editorial pages each month by top writers and photographers and offers a wealth of inside information. Don’t miss your passport to the best in the world!\n', '', '', ''),
(1510, 1, 'Camping', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Camping Magazine?\n\nWith reviews of all the tents, camping equipment and travel essentials you''ll need for a great rural getaway, a subscription to Camping magazine is a great present for anyone looking to plan their next adventure.\n\nEnjoy features from regular contributors for handy tips and advice on the best campsites, gear and camping accessories, and keep an eye out for great competitions and tenting holiday giveaways.\n\nWhether you''re planning a short weekend break, or a summer camping holiday for all the family, this mag is the perfect monthly read for dedicated tent campers.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCamping, the only magazine in the UK for tent campers, has a brand new look for 2012. With 100 pages packed full of even more camping content, each month we bring you more campsites, travel features, gear and tent reviews, plus camping advice to complete your camping life.\n', '', '', ''),
(1511, 1, 'Caravan', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Caravan magazine is a must have read for any caravan enthusiast.\n\nWritten by caravanners for caravanners. Caravan magazine entertains, informs and gives its readers the confidence to really enjoy their caravanning.\n\nMore than ever, it’s packed with great reader tips, fascinating insights and entertaining reader stories.\n\nIncluded in every issue of a subscription to Caravan magazine, you will find loads of great caravan holiday ideas, the best equipment to buy, news of the latest caravans and comprehensive towcar and caravan buying guides.\n\nBritain''s first caravanning magazine offers friendly, hands-on advice and practical tips for every aspect of this popular hobby.\n', '', '', ''),
(1512, 1, 'Living France', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Living France Magazine?\n\nIf you’re planning to move across the Channel, then subscribe to Living France magazine for a comprehensive monthly guide to everything from buying property to finding your very first job.\n\nYou''ll find plenty of first-hand advice from a range of expats, with regular interviews and real-life tales designed to help you settle in to your new surroundings. There''s also a number of practical, straight-forward guides to make your move as smooth as possible, with legal advice, cultural tips and FAQ''s from relocation experts.\n\nYou''ll even find money-saving tips and handy budgeting tools each and every month.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Living France is essential for anyone considering the move to France. Living France gives you the information and advice so you can start planning for your dream home in France now no matter when you might be moving. Living France magazine is packed with hundreds of fresh properties for sale and rent, as well as friendly and uncomplicated advice covering all aspects of living and working in France, region by region guides to help you choose the right region for you, tips from the experts and real-life stories from those who have made the move. By subscribing you can make sure you don’t miss any of the important and helpful advice and tips as well as saving money! So subscribe to Living France magazine today for the life you’ve always dreamed of!\n', '', '', ''),
(1513, 1, 'Practical Motorhome', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Practical Motorhome Magazine?\n\nPractical Motorhome is your definitive guide to motorhome holiday lifestyle. Inside you''ll find travel features, product reviews, advice and columns to bring essential information to experienced motorhome owners and potential buyers. Practical Motorhome magazine has just the right mix of enthusiasm and true authoritative content, delivering an exciting, aspirational and informative approach to motor caravanning. Subscribe to Practical Motorhome magazine today and stay up to date on everything to do with your favorite past time.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPractical Motorhome is the complete and entertaining guide to getting the most from your motorhome.\n\nEach issue is packed with holiday tips, technical advice, reader reviews, superb photography, reader offers, and much more.Practical Motorhome is your definitive guide to motorhome holiday lifestyle. Inside you''ll find travel features, product reviews, advice and columns to bring essential information to experienced motorhome owners and potential buyers.Practical Motorhome magazine has just the right mix of enthusiasm and true authoritative content, delivering an exciting, aspirational and informative approach to motor caravanning.Subscribe to Practical Motorhome magazine today and stay up to date on everything to do with your favorite past time.\n\nShould you wish to cancel your subscription it will be cancelled on expiry of the current term which will not be refundable, other than in exceptional circumstances.\nThe issues you receive during this trial period are covered by your first Direct Debit payment. You can cancel the subscription (your next Direct Debit payment) at any time during this trial period. However, once the 2nd payment has been claimed from your bank account, should you wish to cancel your subscription it will be cancelled on expiry of the current term.\n', '', '', ''),
(1514, 1, 'Practical Caravan', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Practical Caravan Magazine?\n\nPractical Caravan, the UK’s best-selling caravan magazine, is a complete A-Z guide to caravanning, with every issue providing you with all you need to know about what to buy, where to go and how to get the most from your hobby. Written by enthusiasts for enthusiasts, every issue provides insight, hints, tips and reviews. With varied content, in-depth tests and Great Escape holiday features it makes essential reading for anyone interested in the practical side of caravanning.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA magazine subscription to Practical Caravan will provide you with all you need to know about Caravans. For Inspirational ideas on where caravanners go on holiday, Practical Caravan is packed with advice and information. Written by enthusiasts for enthusiasts, the magazine is a complete guide to touring. Practical Caravan now has a new look with some brand new features, such as our Travel and Showroom sections. Caravan Genius is another new section that features over 40 pages of advice, insights, hints, tips and reviews. It makes essential reading for anyone interested in the practical side of caravanning. Finally, the new Data section comprises three great Buyer’s Guides: new caravans, new and used towcars and dealer specials. Every issue has something for everyone. Its unrivalled Great Escapes holiday guide is packed with attractions and tips to help caravanners get the most from a holiday destination. Apart from its touring information, its tests of caravans, tow cars and equipment are the most thorough and in-depth, and are backed by a comprehensive buyers’ guide. Practical Caravan magazine is a complete A-Z guide to caravanning, with every issue providing readers with a great guide on what to buy, where to go and how to get the most from their hobby. The varied content, in-depth tests and Great Escape holiday features ensures there is always something that will appeal to every caravanning holidaymaker. An essential monthly read for caravanners. Practical Caravan magazine is easily the UK’s best-selling newsstand caravan magazine, and is growing fast as the hobby gains in popularity.\n\nShould you wish to cancel your subscription it will be cancelled on expiry of the current term which will not be refundable, other than in exceptional circumstances.\nThe issues you receive during this trial period are covered by your first Direct Debit payment. You can cancel the subscription (your next Direct Debit payment) at any time during this trial period. However, once the 2nd payment has been claimed from your bank account, should you wish to cancel your subscription it will be cancelled on expiry of the current term.\n', '', '', ''),
(1515, 1, 'India Today Travel Plus', 'India Today Travel Plus has emerged as the country''s finest travel and lifestyle magazine. Going beyond touristy cliches, it presents straight from the heart travelogues written by the best known names in the country. It also showcases the finest in cuisine, shopping and leisure for the up market traveler. This publication is a panoramic visual feast. The magazine regularly features a handy travel file that contains news and information on hotel, cruise and travel packages. Every article is accompanied by a resource file on the destination covered, which includes visa information, weather information, hotel recommendation, local transport and sightseeing tips.', '', '', ''),
(1516, 1, 'India Today Travel Plus', 'India Today Travel Plus has emerged as the country''s finest travel and lifestyle magazine. Going beyond touristy cliches, it presents straight from the heart travelogues written by the best known names in the country. It also showcases the finest in cuisine, shopping and leisure for the up market traveler. This publication is a panoramic visual feast. The magazine regularly features a handy travel file that contains news and information on hotel, cruise and travel packages. Every article is accompanied by a resource file on the destination covered, which includes visa information, weather information, hotel recommendation, local transport and sightseeing tips.', '', '', ''),
(1517, 1, 'Discovery Channel Magazine', 'Discovery Channel Magazine India, published by the India Today Group, is a monthly magazine boasting premium content based on original and in-depth left-field research. Featuring world-class photography and infographics, the stories are presented with a good dose of humour, insight and attitude, making the eclectic range of topics, from history and mathematics to forensics and gaming, immediately accessible to readers. Plus, there’s behind-the-scenes access to some of the most popular shows on Discovery. The world is just awesome — your magazine shouldn''t be anything less. ', '', '', ''),
(1518, 1, 'Discover India', 'Discover India, India''s premium travel and culture magazine, was launched in 1988 by Media Transasia India Limited in active cooperation with the Ministry of Tourism, Government of India. With a view to cater primarily to the inbound tourist, It is a beautifully presented glossy monthly, widely circulated and available at all our missions abroad. Discover India reflects the diverse aspects of India. It deals with India''s philosophy, history, culture, architecture, fashion, art and folklore in both the ancient and modern context. It is a magazine with something for everyone - the gourmet, the scholar, the architect.', '', '', ''),
(1519, 1, 'Saevus', 'SAEVUS is India’s premium wildlife and natural history magazine showcasing her natural beauty through compelling stories and stunning visuals in a never-seen-before quality, depth and vibrancy.Saevus is a magazine aimed at creating awareness about the rich bio-diversity of our country. We truly believe that once each of us love nature, conservation will be a spontaneous outcome. We endeavour to reach out to every Indian home through lucid and engrossing storytelling and images which stay with you.', '', '', ''),
(1520, 1, 'Lonely Planet', 'The world’s most trusted source on travel, Lonely Planet has made its way to India. Through vivid writing and stunning color spreads from celebrated and seasoned traveller-writers and photographers, Lonely Planet Magazine India Inspires travelers to sample different cultures first-hand, discover new people, And learn fascinating stories about every place.\n\nPrice includes posting &amp; handling charges of Rs. 120 per publisher policy', '', '', ''),
(1521, 1, 'National Geographic Traveller', 'This magazine is the Indian edition of National Geographic Traveler (USA) the travel magazine of the National Geographic Society. The original was started in 1985 and currently has a readership of 7.6 million worldwide. National Geographic Traveller India is a magazine that focuses on Real Travel for Real People. It aims to be inclusive and would like to draw a large segment of the magazine reading public to it. We are about travel experiences, about family travel, about variety and unusual elements in travel, as well as new ways of covering older destinations, and to have eco-tourism insights.\n\nTraveller''s publishing goals are to find new things to say about travel, to showcase fresh travel opportunities, to be an advocate for travellers. Traveller''s tag line is &quot;Nobody knows this world better,&quot; and accordingly, a Traveller story attempts to capture a place''s essence in a way that inspires readers to follow in the writer''s footsteps—and equip them to do so with useful destination information. National Geographic Traveller India eschews fashion and fluff in favour of fantastic photography, insightful articles and reader-friendly service. Our aim is to be inclusive and not exclusive. We are very much about family travel, about travel experiences and insights, about real, travel for everybody. Above all we are about immersed travel and authentic story-telling; we are also about seasoned expertise, unprecedented access and local connections.\n\nNational Geographic Traveller India tries to cover India better than and more interestingly than any other travel magazine, it also aims at making this information accessible so that more people will be inspired to travel and to go to newer destinations. It short it is meant to be inspirational', '', '', ''),
(1522, 1, 'Travel+Leisure', 'Travel+Leisure is the world''s leading travel magazine. Sophisticated, modern, and always intelligent.Travel + Leisure examines the way we travel now and where we''ll be going years from now, putting into context all the elements of the traveler''s experience—from hotels, restaurants, and shopping to architecture, culture, and politics—while delivering the latest news on security, health, trends, and innovations. Brought to India and South Asia under licence from American Express Publishing by Media Transasia, the arrival of the edition of Travel + Leisure in India, marked the sixth international edition of the world''s leading travel magazine. The magazine was launched with a cover price of Rs 150/-.In line with its world wide positioning of “the largest selling travel and lifestyle magazine”, the Travel + Leisure India launch has been historic in many ways. The magazine has seen an unprecedented response from the collective Indian advertising and reader communities. Travel + Leisure makes a clear departure in terms of its positioning by focusing on the “lifestyle behind the travel” rather than “the destination” as the specific editorial thrust and hence the acknowledgement of the title across world markets as the right medium for high-end luxury and lifestyle products.', '', '', ''),
(1523, 1, 'Outlook Traveller', 'India''s premium travel publication, Outlook Traveler takes you through an incredible journey across the world. Outlook Traveler is a monthly magazine from the stable of Outlook Publishing India Pvt. Limited and a significant magazine aimed at the travel reader. Every month OT introduces readers to the wonders of unknown destinations while also encouraging travelers to take a fresh look at familiar places. Whether people are planning a holiday, or simply dreaming of one, Outlook Traveler continues to take them closer to their destinations.', '', '', ''),
(1524, 1, 'Grihshobha - Bangla', 'Grihshobha is a women magazine . The magazine was started in 1979 as a monthly by the Delhi Press Group published in different languages . Since its inception,it carries features on housekeeping, cookery, knitting, interior decoration, beauty care, dress designing, hobbies and handicraft, besides helping women understand social, national as well as universal issues. It focuses on women''s issues, and often features racy short stories, fashion, recipes, advice columns, and comments on socialites and current events. The total readership is estimated to be about 98, 63,000.', '', '', ''),
