(1533, 1, 'Saras Salil - Tamil', 'Saras Salil is a popular Indian magazine . It contains unique mix of commentaries on social and political issues, and varied articles on society, sex, fiction and entertainment. Saras Salil is published in 5 languages (including Hindi) and has a highest readership according to IRS 2009 R1 in India . Incidentally, Saras Salil is placed second in the all magazines chart.', '', '', ''),
(1534, 1, 'Saras Salil - Telugu', 'Saras Salil is a popular Indian magazine . It contains unique mix of commentaries on social and political issues, and varied articles on society, sex, fiction and entertainment. Saras Salil is published in 5 languages (including Hindi) and has a highest readership according to IRS 2009 R1 in India . Incidentally, Saras Salil is placed second in the all magazines chart.', '', '', ''),
(1535, 1, 'Suman Sourabh', 'Magazines for the inquisitive teenager who is slowly growing up to the serious concerns of life.It carries features on science, History, Sports, education, carrier, famous personalities, and many engrossing stories.', '', '', ''),
(1536, 1, 'Wedding Vows', 'GNT Media Pvt. Ltd. is a 360 Degree media house started in the year 2010. In 2011, GNT Media came out with its first product “Wedding Vows – Magical Moments &amp; More” India’s favourite wedding lifestyle magazine. Wedding Vows is a National Magazine with its base in Chennai; it is a complete guide to the Indian wedding market and has already created a buzz in the wedding industry within a short span time. In addition, GNT Media has several other lifestyle related products in the pipeline to explore.\n\nWhen it comes to Indian weddings, everyone’s involved – from the couple themselves to the parents, siblings, cousins and aunts! Here’s a stylish, innovative wedding magazine for everyone in the family that covers just about everything to do with Indian weddings – before, during and even after the big day. Find out the latest trousseau trends through breath taking fashion spreads; get up-to-date on the latest in the beauty scene; explore the perfect spots around the world for shopping or destination weddings;get personalized tips from acclaimed industry experts on doing up a new home or making investments as a new couple. Meet celebrity couple sand find out how they made their wedding an affair to remember and where they honeymooned; get insightful advice on relationships (yes, even handling your mother-in-law!), sex and marriage; and take a ride around the world of wedding rituals. Aspirational, intelligent and mind-blowing, Wedding Vows will have you fall in love with the bling and drama of the Indian Wedding.\n', '', '', ''),
(1537, 1, 'Harmony Celebrate Age', 'Harmony celebrates age. It is published by Harmony for Silvers Foundation - founded by Tina Anil Ambani. It is a non-government organization working to enhance the quality of life of the elderly in India. It visualizes the elderly persons as silver citizens of India. The magazine provides a unique opportunity for elderly people to interact with their peers in a space of their own. It also aims to educate the general public about issues pertaining to the elderly. The articles published in the magazine include test-drives of products and services, technology and health to travel, books, hobbies, legal help, inspiring profiles, puzzles, and national and international news', '', '', ''),
(1538, 1, 'Savvy', 'India’s leading women’s magazine, dares to be different. It has been instrumental in making women all over India aware of not just their rights, but their potential too in all spheres of life. ', '', '', ''),
(1539, 1, 'Casaviva', '&quot;Design. Style. Trends. Luxury. Casaviva is where it all comes together. Reaching a target audience of sophisticated, discerning and well-heeled women in the age group of 24-44 years, Casaviva - Italy''s highest selling interiors and lifestyle magazine - will target a new genre in India, that of 360-degree living. Because, we believe, luxury is not about how you spend - it''s about the way you live. So whether it''s home couture or collectibles, furniture or gadgets, travel or wellness, fashion or beauty, art or entertaining, Casa Viva is your definitive guide to a stylish life.\nOwned by the Mondadori Group, the largest consumer magazine publisher in Italy,Casa Viva enjoys an average circulation of 2,36,341 copies and a total readership of 10,20,000. For more than 35 years, this distinctive magazine has captivated ultra-affluent readers, its unique formula setting our private spaces in the context of the larger world we live in - how we dress, socialize, eat, drink, shop or travel - because a home is defined by all our sensibilities. In India, Casaviva is published in partnership with Media Transasia, whose portfolio includes market leaders like Travel &amp; Leisure. This is the seventh international edition of Casaviva.\nCasaviva focuses on the home as the ultimate status symbol, providing inspirational ideas and cutting-edge concepts from the design capitals of the world. Top-notch writers and photographers cover subjects of design importance, from antiques and collectibles to product design, architecture, entertaining, gardens, fashion, beauty, cuisine, cocktails, accessories, technology and all things luxury in a global perspective for its readers.\nEach issue is a visual feast, layered with information on the latest in interiors and style, a peak into some uber-stylish homes and a plethora of features like: How to recreate your vacation back home? How to transform your scarves into stunning wall hangings? How to showcase your collection of perfumes, jewellery or books? How to lay out the perfect wardrobe or dressing table? How to reach a décor compromise with your husband? How to pair wine and caviar? How to get your home photographed?\nThe magazine speaks to the reader as an up-to-the-minute friend, in language that''s direct and engaging, rather than ultra-technical and inaccessible. The content is an informed mix of Indian and international, reflecting our reader''s universal sensibilities. Its unique editorial mix resonates with the country''s most influential consumers, who have the desire, taste and means to own the very best. &quot;', '', '', ''),
(1540, 1, 'Hair', 'HAIR is your complete guide to great hair and beauty. Get your monthly dose of the hottest trends, latest products, inspiring styles, expert advice, tips and more. UK''s biggest-selling hair magazine is published in India by Spenta Multimedia under an exclusive licensing arrangement with IPC Media, UK. HAIR in India is the only specialist magazine on hair and beauty', '', '', ''),
(1541, 1, 'Perfect Wedding', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Perfect Wedding Magazine?\n\nWhether you''re thinking about an intimate beach wedding, a vintage-inspired party or an elegant reception at a stately home, Perfect Wedding magazine has expert advice to answer all your wedding-related worries.\n\nEvery issue includes the hottest new trends, including catwalk reports and ideas to suit your budget, as well as imaginative honeymoon destinations, celebrity brides, competitions and exclusive new bride offers.\n\nA subscription to Perfect Wedding magazine will help to inspire you with its real life wedding stories, photos and tips from newlyweds across the country, all helping you to achieve the stress-free day of your dreams.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA Perfect Wedding magazine subscription is essential for planning your big day. Whatever your dreams are for your wedding, a Perfect Wedding subscription covers every element of a wedding day; with gorgeous wedding dresses and stylish A-list inspiration, the hottest new trends, must-have products and accessories, exclusive expert advice and planning essentials, real-life wedding inspiration, honeymoon hotspots, plus much more!\n\nWith free UK delivery, you’ll never miss an issue of the UK’s best monthly wedding magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(1542, 1, 'Golf Course Architecture', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Golf Course Architecture magazine is an essential guide for anyone who is involved in building and designing a Golf Course.Golf Course Architecture is a quarterly publication focused on the design and modification of golf courses. The magazine is essential reading for any golf course manager, resort developer, golf course architect or golf course supplier.Golf Course Architecture magazine has been serving its subscribers and readers with the very best of golf course architecture since June 2005. Published by Tudor Rose this magazine is one great choice for golf club managers, developers and architects looking for insight into golf course designing and modification.\n', '', '', ''),
(1543, 1, 'Cover: Modern Carpets &amp; Textiles For Interiors', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCover is a new quarterly magazine that echoes the vibrancy of the design-carpet and artist-textile markets.Focusing on innovation and trends, the magazine is dedicated to all that ‘covers’ other surfaces, as well as different aspects of design, interiors, art and craft - a rich resource of inspirational work from around the globe.\n', '', '', ''),
(1544, 1, 'Hali', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHALI puts the text in textile… The world’s leading magazine devoted to antique textiles, carpet and Islamic art, HALI is essential reading for anyone who has an interest in the history of textiles and the Islamic world. Every issue is filled with fascinating articles, reviews and commentary from leading scholars, as well as providing an overview of what’s happening in the market, museums and salerooms and invaluable resources such as the auction price guide.\n', '', '', ''),
(1545, 1, 'Mix Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSubscribe to Mix magazine and receive your quarterly design fix from the most reliable such source from the design world.A subscription to Mix magazine is ideal for the design professional wanting to keep up to date with latest on trend and design information. Mix magazine is the colour, trend and design magazine for professionals! Published four times a year in March, June, August and December, Mix magazine brings you new trend updates in design, colour, materials, products and architecture. Mix magazine features inspirational imagery which provides reader’s with a complete overview on new trends and innovative projects, making this publication a working tool for those who need accurate trend information. Mix magazine uses NCS, RGB and Lab values in all of its colour trends making it easier for you to find and apply them. Mix magazine is a leading publication in the industry where you can take fresh and innovative ideas. A subscription to Mix readers is mainly enjoyed by professionals from the design sector but also savvy consumers which are looking for the latest update on trend and design information. Purchase a subscription to Mix for yourself or a friend today and get the magazine delivered free to your door, four times a year!\n', '', '', ''),
(1546, 1, 'Art Business Today', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nArt Business Today est. in 1905 is the UK''s leading magazine for the art and framing industry. It is aimed at professional artists, framers, galleries, art publishers, trade suppliers, art agents, printers and everyone in between.\n\nIn 2003, Art Business Today won Magazine of the Year in the Trade Association Forum Best Practice Awards.\n', '', '', ''),
(1547, 1, 'Trike', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Trike Magazine?\n\nIf you firmly believe that motorcycling doesn''t begin and end with two wheels, then you''ll love this motorcycle magazine.\n\nEvery issue of Trike brings you loads of photos and profiles of both classic and modern trikes, with readers encouraged to send in pictures of their own vehicles for the regular features on readers'' trikes.\n\nWhether you''ve owned a three-wheeled motor for years or you''re looking to purchase one for the first time, a Trike magazine subscription will bring you in-depth reports on trike club rallies from across Europe, as well as giving you all the information you need to buy a three-wheeler in the mag''s extensive sales section.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Trike is the perfect magazine for trikers.A trike magazine built for trikers. The new magazine for all things three-wheeled! Covering all things tricycular, it looks at both full custom builds and bike conversions, disabled options, legalities, trike events, news, products. Trike Magazine is an exclusive and best selling magazine which is dedicated to Trikers. By subscribing to Trike magazine you will get all the latest news, new products, in depth and informative features, authoritative and independent reviews, hot events and lots more. The magazine has expert and experienced writers who contribute to making this magazine as good as it is.With all these ingredients the magazine has become unique and special among Triker enthusiasts.Subscribe to Trike magazine today and get your quarterly three-wheeled fix.\n', '', '', ''),
(1548, 1, 'Practical Farm Ideas', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPurchase a subscription to: Practical Farm Ideas magazine, the most comprehensive source of cost-cutting ideas for farmers in the UK.It features innovative machinery built and adapted in farm workshops, workshop methods and techniques which cut costs, time and frustration as well as In-depth financial, management and farm diversification reports.\n\nPractical Farm Ideas magazine is unique in that it carries no display or classified advertising.Each issue of Practical Farm Ideas Magazine includes all the latest news and information from the world of farming. It brings all up date news from world wide agricultural developments and technology. This magazine is the best guide to aid you to upgrade your farming knowledge and skills.Subscribe to Practical Farm Ideas magazine today and stay up to date with all the goings on in the world of farming.\n', '', '', '');
