(1549, 1, 'Classic Dirt Bike', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Classic Dirt Bike Magazine?\n\nClassic Dirt Bike is all about motorcycles made for the rough stuff and those who ride them.\n\nOff-road events from across the world are given full coverage and legendary riders are interviewed too.\n\nThe magazine is illustrated with photographs of classic machines in action, both newly taken and from the extensive Publisher Archive.\n\nWorkshop guides are part of the package and technical features offer advice on how to get the best out of a classic dirt bike.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Classic Dirt Bike magazine, dealing with the thrilling world of classic off road sport. In every issue of a subscription to Classic Dirt Bike, the magazine looks behind the scenes at the legendary men and machines that have formed the worlds of motocross, trials and enduros worldwide. Each installment in your subscription to Classic Dirt Bike magazine covers everything from feature bikes, projects and stories from the sport’s glorious past and exciting present – all beautifully photographed and compellingly written. Classic Dirt Bike has become the world’s leading publication for fans of classic and twinshock sport. A Classic Dirt Bike magazine subscription belongs to a very special category. It is not for everyone, but for a selected few, who contemplates on the classic motocross, twinshocks, enduros and other classic bikes. A subscription to Classic Dirt Bike magazine is the best choice on information about Classic Dirt Bikes. You will also get advice on restoration and painting works. Also get information about classic racing machines, the jumpers and the skidders.\n', '', '', ''),
(1550, 1, 'Audi', 'Audi India is one of the premier automobile magazines in India. It talks about everything that the brand is doing- new car launches, new models, showrooms, service centers, car reviews, etc. Apart from interesting news from the brand, there’s also a story dedicated to sports (golf, football etc.) since Audi and motor sports is very closely linked. While it’s a magazine solely dedicated to the brand, it is also infused with some lifestyle element by roping in celebrity interviews (like Abhishek Bacchan, Katrina Kaif, and Bipasha Basu etc.). The magazine is sporty, progressive and an interesting mix of cars and lifestyle elements like travel, fashion and soft features- everything that an Audi fan/owner would want to know about.', '', '', ''),
(1551, 1, 'Supply Business', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nIf you work in procurement and supply, Supply Business is the trade magazine for you. An official magazine of the Chartered Institute of Purchasing &amp; Supply (CIPS), Supply Business provides the latest analysis for those at the top of procurement and supply.\n\nBuilding upon its former title CPO Agenda, this quarterly publication is for the most senior executives in the profession. In addition to chief procurement officers, it is also relevant to chief executives, financial directors and others concerned with the procurement and supply operations of their business.\n', '', '', ''),
(1552, 1, 'Energy Manager', 'Each issue of energyη manager focuses on one most appropriate topic of contemporary relevance on energy efficiency and energy conservation as its cover feature, with a national/ international domain expert as the guest editor. Other regular columns include best practices, research and innovation, renewable energy, energy management, energy audit, global focus and focus India among others, contributed by some of the leading personalities in the energy sector. energyη manager is circulated among a focused audience of about 5000 including State and Union Ministries of Power, New and Renewable Energy, Industries, Agriculture, etc, Forum of Regulators, State Electricity Boards, Energy Development Agencies, Power Generation, Transmission and Distribution Agencies, Energy Development Agencies, Energy Intensive Industries, Energy Service Companies, State Designated Agencies, Industry Associations, Designated Consumers, Energy Consultants, Energy Auditors and Managers, etc, Energy Researchers &amp; Academicians, Engineering &amp; Technical Institutions, Consultants, Planners and Architects, Energy Equipment Manufacturers, Distributors and Marketing Agencies, UN agencies and other International Organizations.', '', '', ''),
(1553, 1, 'Fine Wine And Champagne India', 'Fine Wine &amp; Champagne India is a recently launched state of the art wine magazine, which has wowed all. This coffee-table read informs, educates, connects and inspires its readers – who could be anyone from wine lovers, enthusiasts, connoisseurs, students to just about anybody who wishes to know more about wine. Fine’s quarterly issues cover insights into the vineyards, privileged exchanges with wine moguls, commentary on exclusive wine tastings, drink ability of rare and fine wines, and much more... Get your subscription today.', '', '', ''),
(1554, 1, 'Cakes &amp; Sugarcraft', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA Cakes &amp; Sugarcraft magazine subscription is perfect for both beginners and experienced cake decorators. Cakes &amp; Sugarcraft magazine provides an inspirational guide to the popular hobby of sugarcraft, with each issue featuring a wide range of seasonal cake decorating projects from the world''s top sugarcrafters. Each issue of Cakes &amp; Sugarcraft magazine includes articles, news features and book releases, plus details about organisations and the latest products in sugarcraft. The magazine also regularly features iconic cakes from Britain’s top finalists and keep’s readers busy with a huge range of step-by-step guides to the creating the loveliest cakes of the year voted by the country’s experts. From Wedding cakes to birthday cakes Cakes &amp; Sugarcraft magazine makes a great gift subscription for all occasions.\n', '', '', ''),
(1555, 1, 'Seasoned By Chefs', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSeasoned by Chefs magazine is brought to you by family-run publishing house We R Publishing Limited. The magazine, which aims to bring readers a behind-the-scenes insight into the world of the UK’s best chefs, is in partnership with chef restaurateur Brian Turner CBE, who we are proud to have on board in an advisory role position. Familiar faces that form our editorial board, we have tops chefs Michel Roux Jr. Theo Randall, Arnaud Stevens and Sam Williams - so you can be assured this publication will build into one to keep and collect.\n\nEach edition, meet the chefs as we catch up with some of the UK’s gastronomic greats, cook and develop your skills like the pros by following the delicious recipes inside, and find that perfect wine to compliment your favourite seasonal dishes . . plus much more! ', '', '', ''),
(1556, 1, 'Film International', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nFilm International is devoted to bringing the reader all the latest news and developments in the world of international cinema.\n\nFilm International covers film culture as part of the broader culture, history and economy of society. We address topics of contemporary relevance from historically informed perspectives. We wish to bridge the gap between the academy and the outside world, and encourage the participation of scholars from a variety of disciplines.\n\nWe refuse the facile dichotomies of ''high'' and ''low'', Hollywood and independent, art and commercial cinema. We discuss Hollywood films seriously, and ''art'' movies critically. We aim at becoming a truly international publication recognising local specificities, but also the ultimate interconnectedness of an increasingly globalised world.\n', '', '', ''),
(1557, 1, 'Timeless Jewels', 'The International Watch &amp; Jewellery Magazine in India got its first official magazine in Timeless Jewels, which celebrates beauty, crafted to precise perfection. Presenting every quarter, in the flawless Vintage tradition, this magazine brings centrestage, through its lavish spreads, design, technical features, regional and alien influences, the art of gemstone cutting and setting, the different schools of jewellery design, traditional versus the contemporary. Timeless Jewels is a connoisseur''s delight. One-year-old, the magazine has already achieved a unique feat: it is the only official magazine from India to have become the official magazine at the world-renowned BASEL FAIR of Switzerland. This multi-multi-billion dollar industry which touches, and in fact, revolves around the quick-changing tastes and trends in the world of watches and jewellery, finds a platform, and a SHOWCASE in Timeless Jewels. The Quarterly glossy, benchmarking with only highest global parameters, and watching the brand equity all the top end off products that it will showcase, fulfils the void on the exclusive watch and jewellery segment by quality-driven information and presentation.', '', '', ''),
(1558, 1, 'Upper Crust', 'UpperCrust- Indias Finest Food &amp; Wine Magazine is one of the leading trade fair organizers in India.', '', '', ''),
(1559, 1, 'Wedding Affair', 'Wedding Affair magazine is a complete guide and planner for all brides and grooms-to-be that brings the latest tidings and expert views on jewellery and beauty. Whats more? We even inform you about venues, caterers, beauticians, photographers, shops, jewellery and fashion designers, honeymoon destinations, travel companies, event planners etc. So, get your copies today to keep your guests wondering about the secrets of your ''talk-of-the-town'' wedding ceremony.', '', '', ''),
(1560, 1, 'Sleek Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSleek magazine for art and fashion is an independent quarterly presenting a thematically curated investigation of contemporary art and fashion.\n\nPublished in Berlin and distributed internationally, Sleek is printed in English. Each issue contains a monothematic dossier centered on a topic comprising two opposite concepts and selected as a playful approach to tackling the intricacy of contemporaneous culture.\n', '', '', ''),
(1561, 1, 'Asiana Wedding', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Asiana Wedding Magazine?\n\nMake your big day extra special with Asiana Wedding magazine: a fantastic source of inspiration on every aspect of the ceremony, whether you''re looking to stay up-to-date on the latest fashion trends in wedding outfits or find out where to buy the best flowers, fabrics or bridal jewellery.\n\nWith a subscription to Asiana Wedding magazine you''ll find plenty of ideas on themes, as well as real-life stories from happily married couples, health and beauty tips, celebrity interviews and even advice on etiquette and how to manage your guests.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Asiana Wedding magazine brings readers essential advice and inspiration to make their big day extra special. Asiana Wedding Magazine is the biggest selling Asian glossy wedding magazine in the UK. Packed with over 340+ pages, Asiana Wedding magazine delivers an amazing array of features relating to celebrities, fashion trends, health and beauty tips, social issues and expert advice to make planning the big day that little bit easier. Every issue of Asiana Wedding Magazine features inspiring bridal fashion, traditional Asian jewellery, stunning photography and flower arrangements. Asiana Wedding Magazine also provides a list of top caterers for all budgets and great wedding venues across the country. Published 4 times a year, Asiana Wedding Magazine also makes a great gift subscription for any bride looking for a little inspiration and help to make their big day perfect.\n', '', '', ''),
(1562, 1, 'Wonderland', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWonderland magazine is a uniquely positioned, independent, bi-monthly publication for both men and women spotlighting contemporary visual culture - art, design, film - both the influences and the developments, together with the very latest fashion, shot by some of the most innovative photographers working today. Published out of London, but with worldwide distribution, Wonderland entertains, challenges and informs - assisting the reader rather than dictating to them, so that they may decide for themselves how to spend those two most valuable of commodities: their time, and their money. By combining new talent with new ideas and higher standards, we push the boundaries and exceed expectations of what a magazine today can be.\n', '', '', ''),
(1563, 1, 'Energy Manager', 'Each issue of energyη manager focuses on one most appropriate topic of contemporary relevance on energy efficiency and energy conservation as its cover feature, with a national/ international domain expert as the guest editor. Other regular columns include best practices, research and innovation, renewable energy, energy management, energy audit, global focus and focus India among others, contributed by some of the leading personalities in the energy sector. energyη manager is circulated among a focused audience of about 5000 including State and Union Ministries of Power, New and Renewable Energy, Industries, Agriculture, etc, Forum of Regulators, State Electricity Boards, Energy Development Agencies, Power Generation, Transmission and Distribution Agencies, Energy Development Agencies, Energy Intensive Industries, Energy Service Companies, State Designated Agencies, Industry Associations, Designated Consumers, Energy Consultants, Energy Auditors and Managers, etc, Energy Researchers &amp; Academicians, Engineering &amp; Technical Institutions, Consultants, Planners and Architects, Energy Equipment Manufacturers, Distributors and Marketing Agencies, UN agencies and other International Organizations.', '', '', ''),
(1564, 1, 'Archaeology Ireland', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nWhether you have a passing interest or are a professional archaeologist. People from all disciplines all over the world enjoy this magazine for its broad range of well-researched topics and lavishly illustrated articles.\n\nArchaeology Ireland covers many fascinating topics spanning all the sub-disciplines of archaeology, including science, art, architecture, history, geography, economics, sociology, anthropology, technology, religion and more...\n', '', '', ''),
(1565, 1, 'The Square', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe independent Masonic magazine brought to you by the world''s oldest Masonic publisher.\n\nThe Square magazine with its large format, brings you in-depth and thought provoking articles on all aspects of Freemasonry written by the leading Masonic writers in the world.\n\nMasons and non-Masons alike will find something of interest in the wide variety of articles and special features, which cover the whole spectrum of Freemasonry, including historical, social, charitable, esoteric, other Orders, collecting, ephemera, philately, book reviews, poetry, news and events, and on a lighter note Masonic humour.\n', '', '', ''),
(1566, 1, 'Irish Roots', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIrish Roots magazine is the only genealogy and family history magazine dedicated entirely to Irish ancestral research.\n\nIrish Roots magazine features indepth articles on all aspects of Irish family history with articles written by many of Ireland''s leading genealogists. A subscription to Irish Roots aims to assist readers to overcome the ''brick wall'' so often found in Irish ancestral research and have some fun along the way. Irish Roots magazine is a powerful educational resource for all those involved in tracing their Irish ancestors from the beginner to the more experienced family history researcher.\n\nIrish Roots magazine is a celebration of Irish ancestry, heritage, culture and traditions.\n\nTake a step back with Irish Roots magazine!\n', '', '', ''),
(1567, 1, 'Scots Heritage Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Scots Heritage Magazine Magazine?\n\nExpatriate Scots will love this magazine, specifically designed to keep them in touch with their heritage and culture.\n\nWherever you are in the world now, with your subscription this glossy magazine will arrive at your door four times a year filled with news and stories from all over Scotland. There are several pages of beautiful photography in each issue, depicting the ancient castles, glens and lochs in such breathtaking high quality, you''ll be booking your next flight home as soon as possible to see them again yourself.\n\nYou can also read fascinating stories of daily life from across Scotland, with in-depth portraits set everywhere from Aberdeen to Barra.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIf you love Scotland you will love a subscription to Scots Heritage Magazine. Scots Heritage magazine is the only magazines aimed specifically at people of Scotland descent - based overseas. Eachquarter a subscription to Scots Heritage Magazine delivers 128 glossy full colour pages of the finest writing and photography on Scotland exploring the magical castles, lochs and glens, rich heritage of the clans and families of Scotland. Put Scotland in your pocket! This magazine captures the essence of Scotland from the people and places to the history and culture. A subscription to this handy sized Scots Heritage Magazine is perfect for those wanting to more about Scotland or Scotland enthusiasts! With an attractive blend of striking photography and in depth stories the Scots Magazine will take you to the heart of Scotland past and present. The Scots Heritage Magazine is a colourful and vibrant magazine with thousands of readers worldwide who have a passion for all things Scottish!\n', '', '', ''),
(1568, 1, 'On Religion Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nOn Religion Magazine provides insightful and informed commentary on religion, faith and current affairs. The Quarterly magazine has contributors from academics, faith leaders and opinion makers.\n', '', '', ''),
(1569, 1, 'Montessori International Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Montessori International Magazine is ideal for anyone with an interest in children''s natural development and the Montessori philosophy. Every issue of Montessori International magazine is full of bright ideas for use in the classroom and offers ways to support children''s development at home. With readers in 40 different countries, subscribing to Montessori International ensures you are part of a growing global community. Regular features include: Montessori at home, brain and behaviour, activity ideas, child development articles, Q&amp;A section, Montessori around the world, book and product reviews, special needs updates, news and events and recruitment and training. Montessori International Magazine raises the bar for quality and standards in early education across the world. If you’re ever stuck for activity ideas for home and school, take out a subscription to Montessori International Magazine!\n', '', '', ''),
(1570, 1, 'This England', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThis England quarterly magazine takes readers on an exciting seasonal journey, with fascinating articles and beautiful photographs reflecting England’s heritage, countryside, people and places, both past and present\n', '', '', ''),
(1571, 1, 'Poetry Review', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Poetry Review Magazine?\n\nWith literary criticism on current developments in the poetry genre and a diverse selection of verse in every issue, as well as profiling and dissecting of classic works, Poetry Review is a must-read for anyone interested in this literary form. If you’re hoping to master the technical or creative aspects of poetry writing, a subscription to Poetry Review magazine will be a great help, with advice from established writers on everything from structure to metaphor. There''s also a lively writers'' platform which gives readers the opportunity to be published, plus the opportunity to get expert feedback on your work from the magazine''s Poetry Prescription service.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe world-class Poetry Review, founded in 1909, is published quarterly by the Poetry Society. It is the UK’s most widely-read poetry periodical, presenting the very best verse and writing about poetry to be found in Britain today, across all generations and schools. An indispensible read, it identifies trends and drives the direction of contemporary poetry. Here exciting newcomers rub shoulders with Geoffrey Hill, Louise Gluck, Don Paterson and Mahmoud Darwish. Each handsome 128pp issue includes essays, features and reviews.\n\nIn the latest issue- The cover is newly commissioned from award-winning illustrator Matthew Richardson, represented by Heart. Guest editor George Szirtes brings readers an eclectic and witty issue of Poetry Review, the world’s foremost poetry magazine, with new poems including: A.B. Jackson’s ‘Of Elephants’, moving between sources and languages; Philip Gross’s ‘Variations On A Theme From The Cornish’; Matthew Sweeney’s ‘The One-eyed Philosopher of Katmandu’; Carolyn Jess-Cooke’s hand-grenade baby, ‘Boom!’; Paul Batchelor’s ‘Pit Ponies’; Shazea Quraishi''s ‘The Mummy of Hor’ and and a passage from Owen Sheers’s radio play, ‘Pink Mist’. In the essays section, Simon Armitage introduces Poetry Parnassus, Carrie Etter explores prose poetry, Emily Critchley writes about Denise Riley and Adam Piette on Geraldine Monk. Peter Scupham reviews Elizabeth Jennings, Pascale Petit writes on Jane Hirshfield, while Grahame Davies is in the audience for Gwyneth Lewis’s stage play, Clytemnestra. And there’s much more\n\n“Poetry Review is both open-minded and passionate about poetry. A rare combination and that’s why I always read it.” – Helen Dunmore\n\n“The contemporary poetry magazine of record.” – The Guardian\n', '', '', ''),
(1572, 1, 'The Musical Times', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEstablished in 1842, the oldest continuously published music journal in the world, The Musical Times magazine is dedicated to the best in contemporary writing about classical music. Concentrating on feature articles, book reviews, obituaries and news round-ups, written by the world''s leading authorities, each copy of The Musical Times brings over 80 pages of stimulating comment and analysis. The determination of The Musical Times to publish only the liveliest contributions in an attractive format, sets it apart, now as ever, from the other, purely academic music magazines. Subscribe to The Musical Times today and have each issue delivered direct to your door!\n', '', '', ''),
(1573, 1, 'Mix Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSubscribe to Mix magazine and receive your quarterly design fix from the most reliable such source from the design world.A subscription to Mix magazine is ideal for the design professional wanting to keep up to date with latest on trend and design information. Mix magazine is the colour, trend and design magazine for professionals! Published four times a year in March, June, August and December, Mix magazine brings you new trend updates in design, colour, materials, products and architecture. Mix magazine features inspirational imagery which provides reader’s with a complete overview on new trends and innovative projects, making this publication a working tool for those who need accurate trend information. Mix magazine uses NCS, RGB and Lab values in all of its colour trends making it easier for you to find and apply them. Mix magazine is a leading publication in the industry where you can take fresh and innovative ideas. A subscription to Mix readers is mainly enjoyed by professionals from the design sector but also savvy consumers which are looking for the latest update on trend and design information. Purchase a subscription to Mix for yourself or a friend today and get the magazine delivered free to your door, four times a year!\n', '', '', ''),
(1574, 1, 'Cycling Fitness', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nCycling Fitness focuses on the practical aspects of developing a healthy body and improving cycling performance.\n\nEvery issue contains a wide range of features by leading fitness experts looking at the latest in nutrition, training and health advice.\n\nEvery issue also contains a new 12-week training plan for readers to follow until the next quarterly issue is on sale.\n', '', '', ''),
(1575, 1, 'Caduceus', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBuy a subscription to Caduceus magazine and save up to 15%. Caduceus magazine is a healing, spiritual magazine, based in the UK, that focuses on psychological, emotional, spiritual, ecological and environmental health, therapy and growth, including natural, holistic, energy and complementary medicine.\n\nCaduceus magazine explores the frontiers of sacred science and topics covered include climate change, swine flu, Codex Alimentarius, vitamin D, sunlight health benefits, sound healing and therapy, vitamins and minerals, homoeopathy, fluoridation, iodine treatment of breast cancer, electromagnetic fields and pollution, animal communication, 2012, Mayan prophesies, psychic healing, megalithic sites, crop circles, shamanism, reincarnation and mysticism.\n\nFounded in 1987 by acupuncturist and Sufi, Sarida Brown, the magazine is published quarterly and independently and is now run and edited by medical journalist/editor Simon Best, co-author (with biophysicist Dr Cyril Smith) of the award-winning Electromagnetic Man: Health and hazard in the electrical environment (Dent, London, 1989).\n\nCaduceus magazine has recently launched into North America, where it is available in over 1,200 outlets in Canada and the USA.\n\nIn the Winter issue (no. 80), due out just before or after Christmas, articles include:\n\n* Raw milk - the huge nutritional benefits, much of which are destroyed by pasteurization\n* Tapping into healing - the major healing potential of EFT and TFT\n* Ghost Dance in Glastonbury - exploring the history of the modern presentation of the dance and its importance today\n* Ending a relationship - how to break energetically when a relationship ends.\n* The great swine flu con - the dubious science and agendas behind the emergence of the H1N1 vaccine\n... and other regular features on poetry, book reviews and news.\n\nWe look forward to welcoming you as a new reader. All new subscribers get a free back issue and can buy others at half price.\n', '', '', ''),
(1576, 1, 'Juno', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Juno Magazine?\n\nA parenting magazine with a difference, this quarterly title looks at the key discussions on a range of social and ethical issues affecting modern families. Hoping to share insightful experiences rather than just giving prescriptive advice, a Juno magazine subscription will enrich your household by encouraging personal growth, and get you thinking about social justice, non-violence and conscientious parenting. Beautifully illustrated, each issue also contains inspiring interviews, book reviews, recipes and craft pages, and on top of these features, you''ll also find regular columns on birth, home education and nutrition.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nJUNO is a magazine with “a natural approach to family life”. Since 2004 it has inspired and supported parents as they journey through the challenges of parenting by sharing fresh perspectives in this fast-paced technological world and creating a non-judgemental community. There are regular columns on teens, birth, home-education, natural health and nutrition as well as book reviews, craft ideas, interviews and recipes. A wide range of features bring many voices to readers with beautiful images and unique illustrations to inspire and lift the soul.\n\nJUNO is a different magazine because it focuses on families sharing experiences rather than experts telling you “how to”. The thought provoking content is relevant for families with children of all ages and recognises that family life can mean different things to different people. The JUNO ethos is that you do not need to “buy” to be a good parent and what works for some might not work for others.\n\nIt is run by a small, family team with young children themselves and is committed to sustainable and more natural living. It is printed on FSC paper in the UK.\n', '', '', ''),
(1577, 1, 'Mims Dermatology ', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to MIMS Dermatology magazine is an essential read for anyone with an interest in dermatology.\n\nMIMS Dermatology is an exciting journal for health care professionals with a special interest in dermatology, providing high quality educational material in a practical, accessible format.\n\nSubscribe now and receive:\n•Four issues a year\n•News Forum\n•Clinical review\n•Diagnostic Forum\n•Therapeutic Forum\n•Medical Education\n•Exclusive access to MIMS online\n\nBuy a subscription to MIMS Dermatology magazine today and keep up to date with all the industry news and latest developments in treatment.\n', '', '', ''),
(1578, 1, 'Midwives Journal', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nMidwives is the official publication of the Royal College of Midwives and is published every six months. Exploring issues at the heart of the profession, the magazine provides midwives and students with significant news, comment, research analysis and relevant health features on topics affecting their work and those in their care.\n\nRecognised as a key publication for aiding readers’ professional growth and development, Midwives provides practical content to help practitioners and students achieve and maintain professional excellence.\n\nExplore your vocation and enhance your potential by subscribing to Midwives today.\n', '', '', ''),
(1579, 1, 'Mims', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nEvery issue of MIMS includes four chapters specifically designed for busy healthcare professionals.\n\n•Tables – drug comparison and compatibility charts.\n\n•Guidelines – concise summaries of national guidance on chronic disease including new treatment algorithms.\n\n•Palliative care – opioid equivalence charts, WHO analgesic ladder and other resources.\n\n•Visual guides – pictorial guides to diabetes and respiratory devices.\n\nPlus trusted MIMS-style prescribing information for branded and generic drugs, incorporating over 200 changes every month.\n\nGreat reasons to subscribe to MIMS magazine:\n\n•Never miss an issue\n•Free delivery to your door\n•Save off the cover price\n\nAs a subscriber you will also gain exclusive access to MIMS online! The quarterly print version will include all the news and updates from the corresponding three months of online updates and the online component will be constantly updated with over 300 changes per month. With MIMS online subscribers can quickly search for drug information by brand or generic name, drug class or manufacturer and browse the drug listings by therapeutic area. The predictive search function means subscribers do not need to remember the spelling of complicated drug names. Online only content includes prescribing information for dressings and specialist drugs, printable patient fact sheets and clinical calculators\n', '', '', ''),
(1580, 1, 'Apollo Life', 'Apollo Wellness (an Apollo Hospitals initiative) has come up with a premium line of magazine, which has been named as ‘Apollo Life’. Apollo Life magazine is a quarterly publication with every issue being a collector’s item and each issue comprising of a particular ailment common amongst the masses with extensive research on it. Each of its articles, written by specialist doctors and experts from related field aims to make the readers aware about the ailment which they may encounter at any point of their life.', '', '', ''),
(1581, 1, 'Practical Pigs', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPractical Pigs magazine is published four times a year in collaboration with the British Pig Association (BPA) and aims to provide an informative and entertaining magazine for the domestic pig keeper with straightforward, down-to-earth content covering all the essentials. Each issue will provide in-depth buying features, practical articles on key aspects such as housing, feeding and welfare, owners’ stories, answers to readers’ health and welfare-related questions, competitions, a breeders’ directory and much more.\n', '', '', ''),
(1582, 1, 'Permaculture', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPermaculture, practical solutions for self-reliance, has been in print since 1992. Every issue brings you the best ideas, advice and inspiration from people who are actually creating a better world.\n\nPermaculture''s 88 full colour pages are packed with informative articles, readers'' solutions, DIY designs, news, reviews, letters, classifieds and details of courses. it is also a hub for online as well as print media and a must have networking tool for all green and ethical businesses, social enterprises and projects.\n\nEach issue of Permaculture has over 100,00 readers, it features practical articles on organic gardening, sustainable agriculture, agro forestry, climate change, peak oil, eco villages, alternative technology, eco-architecture, personal and community development and much more.\n\n&quot;I love Permaculture magazine, it''s a rare and beautiful publication which offers actual solutions and inspirations. You are a real breath of fresh air and I look forward to you being around for a long time.&quot; Corrina Gordon-Barnes.\n\n&quot;I think Permaculture is a wonderful publication, really appreciate that the photos are of real gardens, projects in startling contrast to virtually all publications addressing gardening, limited resources etc, here in the US, thank you!&quot; Vicky Burwell.', '', '', ''),
(1583, 1, 'Hospitality Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Hospitality magazine, the quarterly publication for management professionals in the hospitality, leisure and tourism industries. Published by the Institute of Hospitality, the leading professional body for the industry, a subscription to Hospitality magazine offers a passionate take on all things influencing and driving change in hospitality in every issue. Each quarterly issue in a subscription to Hospitality magazine reports on key issues affecting hotels and restaurants, contract caterers and SMEs. The magazine delivers an intelligent and informed selection of expert advice articles, news and interviews with prominent business leaders and innovators to encourage the very best in business practice and management techniques, whatever your level of expertise. With such fantastic content, anyone involved in the hospitality industry should invest in a subscription to this must-have magazine today!\n', '', '', ''),
(1584, 1, 'Energy Manager', 'Each issue of energyη manager focuses on one most appropriate topic of contemporary relevance on energy efficiency and energy conservation as its cover feature, with a national/ international domain expert as the guest editor. Other regular columns include best practices, research and innovation, renewable energy, energy management, energy audit, global focus and focus India among others, contributed by some of the leading personalities in the energy sector. energyη manager is circulated among a focused audience of about 5000 including State and Union Ministries of Power, New and Renewable Energy, Industries, Agriculture, etc, Forum of Regulators, State Electricity Boards, Energy Development Agencies, Power Generation, Transmission and Distribution Agencies, Energy Development Agencies, Energy Intensive Industries, Energy Service Companies, State Designated Agencies, Industry Associations, Designated Consumers, Energy Consultants, Energy Auditors and Managers, etc, Energy Researchers &amp; Academicians, Engineering &amp; Technical Institutions, Consultants, Planners and Architects, Energy Equipment Manufacturers, Distributors and Marketing Agencies, UN agencies and other International Organizations.', '', '', ''),
(1585, 1, 'Miniature Railway Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Miniature Railway Magazine?\n\nWhether you''re a hobbyist or a professional, Miniature Railway magazine makes a great read for anyone interested in these quirky locomotives. Covering everything in between 5&quot; and 15&quot; gauge railways, with your subscription you''ll get to read regular news and historical studies on both commercial and garden miniatures. Expert advice for scale engineers and modellers can help you to get your personal project completed, and with readers'' letters playing an important part in every issue, you can send in your own story for inclusion. Book reviews, letters and fascinating profiles of miniature lines across the country complete this fantastic package, arriving at your front door three times a year.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIf you are a Miniature Railway enthusiast then a subscription to Miniature Railway is the perfect magazine for you.Miniature Railway Magazine fills the gaps left by other publications.\n', '', '', ''),
(1586, 1, 'Practical Sheep, Goats And Alpacas', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPractical Sheep, Goats &amp; Alpacas is an informative and entertaining ‘one-stop-shop’ for enthusiasts, providing straightforward, down-to-earth features and news covering all the essentials owners and potential owners need to know. Not only will it help readers with a passion for these animals decide on the right breed for them, but will assist them in sourcing breeders too. Readers will enjoy the in-depth livestock buying features, practical articles on key aspects such as breeding, housing, feeding and husbandry, owners’ stories, health and welfare-related Q&amp;As, delicious recipe ideas, regular competitions and a unique breeders’ directory. This directory will be a first point of contact for people wanting to keep these farm animals.\n\nAn informative and entertaining ‘one-stop-shop’ for small field animals enthusiasts.\n', '', '', ''),
(1587, 1, 'Full Ahead', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nQuarterly magazine from the Merchant Navy Association. Includes stories, letters from members, information about branch activities etc. Supported by a fantastic pair of websites full of information for seafarers past and present.\n', '', '', ''),
(1588, 1, 'Africa And Middle East Textiles', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAfrican &amp; Middle East Textiles reviews new industry developments in textile machinery and materials throughout the world, in order to provide comprehensive coverage of the apparel and textile industries to a pan-African and Middle Eastern readership. These readers include buyers and executives in textile mills, garment manufacturers and distributors, importers and exporters, and personnel in government and development organisations.\n', '', '', ''),
(1589, 1, 'Learning Spaces', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nUK price is inclusive of VAT. Single User entitles the named person to 12 months of 24/7 online access (via teaching times website) to the content, online issues, library archive, education zones and knowledge banks.\n\nLearning Spaces magazine focuses on how schools are attempting to improve their environments for learning.\n\nUsing exciting case studies of new and refurbished schools, we look at the most creative attempts to match design with new developments in teaching and learning. Our key mission is to give school staff and pupils – the users – more say over design and development.\n\nThere is a strong emphasis on maintenance, refurbishment and managing the Primary Capital programmes, but the magazine also offers critical advice on what designs work best for learning, buying products and materials, as well as legal and technical advice.\n', '', '', ''),
(1590, 1, 'African Journal Of Midwifery And Woman''S Health', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nAJM (African Journal of Midwifery and Women''s Health) is a quarterly peer-reviewed and evidence-based journal for midwives and nurses. It is aimed at those who wish to keep up-to-date with developments relating to midwifery and women''s health in Africa.\n\nSubscribe to AJM today and benefit from:\n\n•Discussion on the complexity of midwifery and women''s health in Africa\n•Focus on maternal and infant health issues faced by different countries across the continent\n•Topical debates on clinical and professional issues\n•Interested writers from outside the continent and within Africa, providing African midwives and nurses with a new voice\n•Research and education, encouraging advanced skills, knowledge transfer and academic discussions\n\nIf you wish to remain informed on the latest developments in African midwifery and women''s health, as well as further your professional development, then AJM is for you.\n', '', '', ''),
(1591, 1, 'Professional Development Today', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nUK price is inclusive of VAT. Single User entitles the named person to 12 months of 24/7 online access (via teaching times website) to the content, online issues, library archive, education zones and knowledge banks.\n\nFocusing on good practice, research and staff development, Professional Development Today online magazine provides the latest thinking of writers in professional development who are world-class calibre as well as testimonies from practitioners who make it happen in their schools. This combination of grounded practice, challenging technique and research insights make PDT the journal to support professional learning for your practitioners.\n', '', '', ''),
(1592, 1, 'Midirs Midwifery Digest', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMIDIRS highly regarded, quarterly academic journal, provides an in-depth exploration of maternity topics ranging from the antenatal to postpartum period.\n\nAccessed by over 3,000 practising midwives and students each quarter, the Digest presents a range of original articles and updates on contemporary research and social policy and has a particular focus on worldwide research. It is also a point of reference for further studies at graduate and postgraduate level.\n', '', '', ''),
(1593, 1, 'Evidence Based Midwifery (Ebm)', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEvidence Based Midwifery (EBM) is a standalone quarterly journal, which aims to promote the distribution, implementation and evaluation of midwifery evidence locally, nationally and internationally. The journal publishes papers that report findings from qualitative or quantitative research studies, philosophical analyses and systematic reviews.\n\nIt is a 36-page, double-blind peer-reviewed journal with a national and international editorial panel. Panel members were appointed on their academic, professional or subject expertise. Reviewers are invaluable and the editors seek to ensure that each article submitted is reviewed by at least one expert in the subject area and where possible an expert reviewer on the method.\n\nThis high-profile journal is essential reading for all research midwives, academics, students and professionals wanting to familiarise themselves with the latest cutting-edge midwifery research.\n', '', '', ''),
(1594, 1, 'Underlines', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAn Underline magazine subscription is the UK’s best selling trade magazine for under garments.Underlines Magazine is the premier trade publication for professionals in intimate apparel, swimwear, nightwear and legwear. Established in 1989, it is a founder member of Network Dessous, the independent European network of trade publishers.Underlines comes with the best industry trends and tips to succeed in the industry of designing intimate apparel, swimwear, nightwear and leg wear. Unique to Underlines magazine are industry insiders who share with readers their thoughts on emerging trends as and when they develop in the market. Underlines is a unique publication and is an essential read for anyone who works or is interested in the under garment cloth trade.Subscribe to Underlines magazine today and keep up to date with everything to do with the under garment trade.\n', '', '', ''),
(1595, 1, 'Practical Pigs', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPractical Pigs magazine is published four times a year in collaboration with the British Pig Association (BPA) and aims to provide an informative and entertaining magazine for the domestic pig keeper with straightforward, down-to-earth content covering all the essentials. Each issue will provide in-depth buying features, practical articles on key aspects such as housing, feeding and welfare, owners’ stories, answers to readers’ health and welfare-related questions, competitions, a breeders’ directory and much more.\n', '', '', ''),
(1596, 1, 'Heavytorque', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHeavyTorque, your dedicated quarterly title delivering latest innovation, sector knowledge, technical features, interviews, comment, news &amp; legislation from across the heavy and abnormal load sector. HeavyTorque in conjunction with the Heavy Transport Association (HTA) is the authoritative voice of the industry, written by professionals for professionals. HeavyTorque is the essential purchase for those with an interest in the heavy and abnormal load sector.\n', '', '', ''),
(1597, 1, 'Large', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLarge was originally created by Harry Rekas in the late 1990''s and quickly became a runaway success. The new Large is provocative in nature with a blend of irony, satire, politics, images, essays, fashion, interviews and stories....vice and virtue done in an irreverent manner.\n', '', '', ''),
(1598, 1, 'Wp Healthy Eating Series', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWP Healthy Eating will be a series of magazines each focusing on a specific subject for healthy eating and a guide to vitamins.\n\nAs many people lead buy lifestyles and hectic schedules miss out on optimal vitamins and mineral intake.\n\nVitamins and minerals are a key factor in our health and energy levels.\n', '', '', ''),
(1599, 1, 'Wp Diabetes Series', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThere is good news and bad news about diabetes. The bad news is that type 2 diabetes is swamping the world like a tsunami and is becoming a leading cause of unnecessary death and disease.\n\nThe world get a new diabetic every 10 seconds, according to the International Diabetic Federation, and there is one death from diabetes every seven seconds. Soon the waves will overwhelm some health systems.\n\nThe good news is that individuals can easily avoid the wave by following a few simple life saving rules. If you let the wave catch you, it is impossible to get off.\n', '', '', ''),
(1600, 1, 'Wp Good Living Series', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n• A book of beautiful and delicious recipes that just happen to be gluten free.\n\nWritten for both those on a gluten free diet or those wishing to reduce the amount of gluten in their diet. .\n\n• Recipes complimented by beautiful food photography..\n\nHigh-interest food topic as more people reduce or eliminate gluten from their diet. .\n\nVariety of recipes to suit low-skilled to experienced home cooks. .\n\nWHAT IT’S ABOUT: Having been diagnosed with Coeliac Disease as a child, Venetia has spent years perfecting her gluten free recipes and is ready to share them in Gorgeous Food Gluten Free..\n\nThis delicious collection of recipes covers breakfast ideas, lunches, entrees, dinners, savoury items, sweets and desserts. .\n\nThe recipes in Gorgeous Food Gluten Free are suited to home cooks of varying skill levels and each section is opened with a thoughtful passage by Venetia, sharing her gluten free journey and antidotes\n', '', '', ''),
(1601, 1, 'Mens Style', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMen s Style is the essential magazine for the stylish Australian man interested in staying up-to-date and on-trend with the latest in fashion, culture, design, grooming, arts, lifestyle and society. A reader of Men s Style is an informed, sophisticated reader   a guy who knows exactly where he s going in life and how to look good getting there. From our annual Men of Style and Men of Influence lists through to some of the most elegant-looking men''s fashion shoots seen anywhere in the world, Men s Style Australia is a magazine designed for the man who sets trends, who influences those around him, and who does it all with the inner confidence of a man who understands how to enjoy life s finer offerings.\n', '', '', ''),
(1602, 1, 'Wp Action Series', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWP ACTION SERIES promises to be an exciting quarterly publication. Celebrating 50 years of Harleys in words and iconic images. From the first Harleys to the most popular recent releases.\n\nExpert reviews, insights, accurate technical specifications from the team that rides and writes about Harleys every day and has done for more than 20 years..\n\nMore than 150 images, including double page spreads on quality paper stock and presented to the highest standard. A true collector’s series..\n\nIssue NI will feature the Classic Harley Peashooter. In 1926, as sales of large-capacity motorcycles started to decline, Harley-Davidson released a series of side-valve and overhead-valve 350cc single-cylinder machines with an eye to the export market, and in particular England, Australia and New Zealand..\n\nWith the advent of speedway tracks – a craze that began in Australia – Harley decided to introduce a purpose-built racer which became known at the ‘Peashooter’, due to its unusual exhaust note.\n', '', '', ''),
(1603, 1, 'Tank Moto', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTank Moto is a quarterly publication focused on motorcycle culture, the people who live it, and the machines that they build.\n\nEach issue is over 140 pages long, is printed using high quality stocks and binding in Melbourne, Australia.\n\nInside each issue will showcase bikes from every custom genre, making this magazine a must have for the bike enthusiast.\n', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `oc_product_description` (`product_id`, `language_id`, `name`, `description`, `meta_description`, `meta_keyword`, `tag`) VALUES
(1604, 1, 'Dumbo Feather', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDumbo Feather is an iconic Australian magazine. Hailed around the world as a design leader, it is a magazine like no other. It s readers are people who want to be told a different story than the one they hear every day. Each quarterly issue features five extended (20 page) profiles of people worth knowing, across enterprise, science, politics, fashion and the arts. Whether they ve touched millions, or just those around them, we take the time to get to know these people, and ask them to tell us their stories. We combine award-winning, often radical art direction with a commitment to photographic storytelling every bit as strong as we have to the written word. The result is a magazine that is as beautiful as it is smart every issue is a gift', '', '', ''),
(1605, 1, 'Cielo', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCIELO is a high quality international fashion magazine from Australia. CIELO covers all the usual fashion stories but also features quality coverage of\n', '', '', ''),
(1606, 1, 'Inspirations', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFilled with step-by-step instructions and photographs, a center liftout pattern, and a wealth of information and advice, Inspirations is by far the world’s best embroidery magazine. Whether you want to decorate your home, give unique gifts or simply try something new, Inspirations is full of creative and beautiful works of art.\n', '', '', ''),
(1607, 1, 'Cio', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCIO Magazine, winner of the Australian Business Publishers ''Best Business Magazine of the Year'' award 2001, focuses on providing the information executives need to successfully use Information Technology (IT) to empower the enterprise.\n\nIt''s readership includes CEOs, CIOs and CFOs who are seeking information about the benefits of technology and how it can streamline business processes and enhance profitability.\n\nKey areas of concern at this level are e-commerce, CRM, outsourcing and using the IT investment to reduce costs, increase revenues and gain a competitive advantage.', '', '', ''),
(1608, 1, 'Nordic Man', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNordic Man is a mens magazine with the idea to create new and exciting graphics, photography, fashion editorials, portraying the Nordic man and his lifestyle. The magazine also focuses on discovering new photographers, models, designers, writers and the insight into life of real people. There is currently worldwide interest in Scandinavian design and fashion, food and sustainable beliefs. Nordic Man is to be the first magazine to focus on all things of interest in Scandinavian life.\n', '', '', ''),
(1609, 1, 'Elephant', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nElephant is a quarterly magazine on contemporary art and visual culture published by Frame. Featuring up-to-the-minute visual material, fresh faces and original voices, Elephant covers and uncovers new trends and talent in contemporary visual culture.\n', '', '', ''),
(1610, 1, 'L.I.Art (Was Luxe Immo) English', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEnglish Edition: Luxe Immo is a high quality publication that feature some fantastic real estate for sale and to rent throughout Europe, North America and Asia. This is coupled with major features from the world of contemporary art and design that also features interviews with some of the biggest names in this field. Luxe Immo is a luxury publication, produced to high quality and in 2 years has built a great reputation.\n', '', '', ''),
(1611, 1, 'Technologist ( French )', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTechnologist contains special reports exploring major scientific topics in the news with in-depth articles on scientific debates.\n\nContents include news items on research, innovation and start-ups.\n\nThe magazine appears four times a year in English, French and German. Technologist is for those who are interested in how science is changing the world. its readers are university graduates, including entrepreneurs and innovators..\n\nArticles analyze the impact of science on modern societies Provocative opinions and analyses with reviews of technological products aimed at the mass market..\n\nTechnologist publishes high-quality articles that are meant to circulate as widely as possible, digitally and in print. the magazine’s format, with its removable pages, encourages readers to share articles or save them for future reference. .', '', '', ''),
(1612, 1, 'Maisons Cote Est', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMAISONS COTE EST is an international architecture and living magazine from France.\n', '', '', ''),
(1613, 1, 'Steel', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe magazine that evolved from the blog of Steel Magazine. Steel is the new global fixed gear and single speed french cultural quarterly magazine dedicated to the lovers, the professionals and the setters of the very specific field of bikes. This new trend that keeps on changing and evolving is full of promises. Steel will reveal every single aspect of this international and cultural trend by highlighting different subjects such as art, fashion and much more. The content includes portfolios, news, interviews, fashion editorials etc. Steel aims to be the most complete and comprehensive magazine created and managed by a team of professionals from the world of cycles but also skilled and passionate riders in order to provide some of the highest quality editorial and photography available\n', '', '', ''),
(1614, 1, 'Dreams (Fr)', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA gorgeous bilingual quarterly French/English jewellery magazine from the elegant nation of France, Dreams magazine is a stunningly well produced look at the world of high class jewellery, watches and jewellery making.\n\nFeaturing the very best designers and jewellers, this high quality magazine shows off the cream of French jewellery with some wonderfully opulent pieces in every issue.\n\nIt includes interviews with the creators, what is currently fashionable and trendy, awards looks at specific watches, earrings, necklaces and more.\n', '', '', ''),
(1615, 1, 'Tranoi', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTranoï : [TRANOY], Italian word for ''between us'', is a state of mind whose style is representative of a mixed culture. It''s fashion spirit, conveyed by its designers, flirts inexpressibly with the trends\n', '', '', ''),
(1616, 1, 'Milk Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMILK MAGAZINE is a French magazine which focuses on parenthood, childrens issues and fashion for kids.\n', '', '', ''),
(1617, 1, 'Crash', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCRASH is a French language magazine covering style, music, fashion, food and more! CRASH goes backstage at the catwalk shows and behind the scenes at parties. Inside readers will also find innovative and artistic photography.\n', '', '', ''),
(1618, 1, 'Wad Fr We Are Different', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWE ARE DIFFERENT is a French quarterly magazine subscription about urban fashion and culture with fantastic covers. Provocative. Interesting. Innovative. And yes, WAD is DIFFERENT. WAD FRENCH is a French language title with English transcripts. An up to date fashion lifestyle title with excellent production values.\n', '', '', ''),
(1619, 1, 'Quilt Mania Special', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFollowing the hugely successful format of the regular bi-monthly publication, one of the world s leading quilt/patchwork publications, each issue will be seasonal, featuring season quilts. Each issue comes with up to 15 pull out patterns, significant value on their own. This series will appeal to regular issue readers and other quilters, amateur or professional. ', '', '', ''),
(1620, 1, 'Sabrina Fashion Knits', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSABRINA Fashion Knits magazine is a new launch, produced on a Quarterly basis. Each issue contains tips, techniques, fashion trends and comes complete with patterns featuring stunning designs to knit. Each issue will feature over 25 stunning new designs and not only contain pictures but will also contain the complete patterns to make these for yourself and offers huge savings over buying individual patterns in a craft store. Each pattern is delivered in an easy to follow format that will result in a quality garment first time around. Filled with the latest European designs, Sabrina Fashion Knits is sure to be a great success.\n', '', '', ''),
(1621, 1, 'Technologist ( German )', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTechnologist contains special reports exploring major scientific topics in the news with in-depth articles on scientific debates.\n\nContents include news items on research, innovation and start-ups The magazine appears four times a year in English, French and German..\n\nTechnologist is for those who are interested in how science is changing the world. its readers are university graduates, including entrepreneurs and innovators..\n\nArticles analyze the impact of science on modern societies Provocative opinions and analyses with reviews of technological products aimed at the mass market..\n\nTechnologist publishes high-quality articles that are meant to circulate as widely as possible, digitally and in print. the magazine’s format, with its removable pages, encourages readers to share articles or save them for future reference.\n', '', '', ''),
(1622, 1, 'Material Girl', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nMaterial Girl is a dreamy, romantic magazine for girls of all ages written in the German language.\n\nMaterial Girl is well known for its inspiring fashion editorials by internationally renowned photographers, make-up artists and stylists. Material Girl topics range from fashion and beauty to jewellery and sweets.\n', '', '', ''),
(1623, 1, 'Indie Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nEnjoy each issue of Indie magazine for your quarterly dose of...er, you know, ...stuff!\n\nINDIE is an independent style magazine with a focus on edgy fashion editorials by internationally renowned photographers, make-up artists and stylists, portraits of budding talents from the fashion, music, art and film scene...and always a pinch of weird stuff too!\n', '', '', ''),
(1624, 1, 'Qvest Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nQVEST is a fashion magazine which is well known in Europe for its special fashion mottos.\n', '', '', ''),
(1625, 1, 'Hypebeast', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHypebeast is all about prints and patterns. With its theme accordingly, the “impression” issue has a renown street wear brand at its helm with formidable subjects.\n\nHypebeast talks to unique lifestyle and cultural figures like Yasuhiro, Craig Ford and more,\n\nSubscribe to Hypebeast for a high quality men’s lifestyle and fashion magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(1626, 1, 'Mink Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Essential Makeup and Skincare Magazine For Asian Women\n\nMink is an essential curated resource for Asian woman seeking expert advice and practical guidance on a range of looks, from radiant natural-looking skin and contouring to stunning day and evening looks, as well as edgy, avant-garde catwalk looks.\n\nEach issue features leading international makeup artists and edgy, up-and-coming talent from the hot spots of the global fashion world.\n\nA visual guide to giving Asian women a choice of classical looks they can choose from to suit their personality and lifestyle ,and to provide inspiration by showing them what can be accomplished and how to make the best of their own femininity.\n', '', '', ''),
(1627, 1, 'Bologna For Connoisseurs', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBologna For Connoisseurs the magazine about Bologna for the connoisseur traveller, is aimed at a sophisticated international readership compromising of global travellers for both business and leisure, luxury hotel guests, art lovers, food lovers and people of influence on an international scale. Bologna magazine will be produced to the highest standards with editorial and pictorial based around Bolognas history and cultural history and lifestyle.\n', '', '', ''),
(1628, 1, 'Nautica Superyacht International', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNautica Superyacht International is an editorial project of Nautica Publications to address yachts over 24 meters.\n', '', '', ''),
(1629, 1, 'Vogue Gioiello It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to VOGUE GIOIELLO magazine brings you a bi-monthly Italian guide fundamental to the season''s latest jewellery accessories. From watches to engagement rings, to that essential tiara. Printed in Italian, each issue of a subscription to Vogue Gioiello magazine is devoted to the design and production of fine jewelry, goldsmithing, and watchmaking.\n', '', '', ''),
(1630, 1, 'Vogue Sposa It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to VOGUE SPOSA magazine takes an Italian look at some of the most gorgeous wedding gowns. Every issue of this quarterly magazine subscription is packed full of outfit ideas for the bride and groom, bridesmaids and the bride''s mum, VOGUE SPOSA magazine also features wonderful ideas for wedding gifts, inspirational fashion stories and the most romantic honeymoon destinations, contemporary features on marriage and directional features for the home.\n', '', '', ''),
(1631, 1, 'Ofarch It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nOFARCH IT is an international magazine about architecture and design. Inside readers will find ancient and modern architectural reviews, news and event information, interviews with up-coming and leading designers. In addition OFARCH IT features superb examples of interior design excellence, gives advice and tips on materials to use, technology available and more.\n', '', '', ''),
(1632, 1, 'Dhd', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDHD is an international magazine for the diffusion of hospitality and restoration design. DHD is used as a source of reference for architects, designers, hotel chains, contractors and buyers.\n', '', '', ''),
(1633, 1, 'Muse World Style', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMUSE WORLD STYLE is a luxury women''s magazine which always shows the newest trends in international fashion, beauty and design. A quarterly magazine published in Italy, MUSE WORLD STYLE is a high-end magazine for the fashion-forward female.\n', '', '', ''),
(1634, 1, 'Yacht Premiere', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nYacht Premiere is an International Quarterly luxury magazine devoted to 100ft plus yachts. These yachts are the ultimate luxury. The mission of Yacht Premiere is to showcase only 100ft plus yachts in their entirety and in all their glory. First class professional photography added to excellent editorial content will result in a fantastic coffee table read. ', '', '', ''),
(1635, 1, 'Maglieria Italiana', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMAGLIERIA is an Italian fashion magazine for women. It tells you everything you need to know about the latest fashion.\n', '', '', ''),
(1636, 1, 'Flow', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFlow. A magazine that takes its time… Celebrating creativity, imperfection, and life''s little pleasures.\n\nFlow is a magazine for women who live busy yet happy lives, and who want to make different kinds of choices. They enjoy making things by hand, practical philosophy, positive psychology, and living in the moment..\n\nFlow has four themes:\n\n-Feel Connected: Make contact with the people and the world around you.\n\n-Live Mindfully: Experience the conscious life.\n\n-Spoil Yourself: Take a little time for the things that make you feel good.\n\n-Simplify Your Life: It need not be so complicated.\n', '', '', ''),
(1637, 1, 'Objekt International', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nOBJEKT readers are urban upscale modernists with a passionate eye for detail and design. Architects interior designers, young metropolitans and the passionate design - oriented consumer. From very modern to very antique, interior architecture and landscape gardens, the topics of the magazine are varied, up-to-date and always inspirational. An essential reference piece for creative designers and armchair readers alike.\n', '', '', ''),
(1638, 1, 'Perspective', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPerspective magazine is an international foreign affairs magazine produced in English by the Norwegian Refugee Council. Each issue explores major world news, events and major issues that affect us all. Written by experts, Perspective is the must have read for anyone who has an interest in major world issues whether famine or environmental issues etc.\n', '', '', ''),
(1639, 1, 'Novaya Evropa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNovaya Evropa is a Russian language quarterly magazine published by the Jan Nowak-Jezioranski College of Eastern Europe.\n\nThe aim of the magazine is to present the Russian reading audience around the world with insight and analyses on issues relating to Poland, and also Western Europe, Central and Eastern Europe and the United States.\nbr/&gt; The magazine will aim to serve Russian readers through the promotion and dissemination of knowledge about Europe, including topics of politics, culture and history.\nbr/&gt; A discussion of the changes taking place in the Western world (foreign policy, social changes and cultural trends) a dialogue of culture and debates on literature and art and the creation of a platform to facilitate debate between the East and the West\n', '', '', ''),
(1640, 1, 'Haute Muse', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHAUTE MUSE content will differ from issue to issue, featuring a lot of sectors . . . . fashion / red carpet / culture &amp; beauty. HAUTE MUSE will also cover the lifestyle section, which will be every woman s guide to the most luxurious destinations, restaurants, spa s and the latest fashion related technologies in the world.\n', '', '', ''),
(1641, 1, 'All Hollow', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAll Hollow is an international glossy quarterly magazine established in September 2012 with offices in Bucharest and Los Angeles, which is set out to curate highly original and relevant content from creative communities around the world.\n\nWritten in English, it walks and talks on the fine line between the glam of mainstream style publications and the lively exciting world of arts and culture.\n\nAll Hollow blends the most compelling fashion editorials, from all over the world with features on music, literature and film, as well as profiles of the most revered artists of the moment, making the magazine and essential read for a trendsetting audience with refined aesthetics and interest in culture.\n', '', '', ''),
(1642, 1, 'Dorian', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWelcome to Dorian s extravagant world of style and substance. Scandinavia s leading glossy, quarterly fashion- and lifestyle gay magazine is created by an award winning editorial team that add bold European appeal to world class editorials and features, seducing cosmopolitan readers globally.\n\nDORIAN features international fashion editorials shot by renowned photographers with top male models, opulent art and design, unique celebrity portraits, extreme beauty (from cosmeceuticals to the latest plastic surgeries) and exotic gay travel destinations.\n\nThought provoking articles complete the decadent Dorian universe, presented in a unique and visually stunning package.\n', '', '', ''),
(1643, 1, 'Vav Mag', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWelcome to the most widely read textile and weaving magazine in Scandinavia. Scandinavian Weaving Magazine meets textile artists who use many differrent techniques, from traditional methods to the more experimental. Each issue contains ten weaving projects specially designed for Scandinavian Weaving Magazine. We cover courses and exhibitions.\n', '', '', ''),
(1644, 1, 'Gallop Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGallop Magazine has a job – and that is to create a fascination for horse racing.\n\nTo spread the word to those who did not know. We tell stories that you don’t have to be an expert to read. Show the photos that you just want to keep looking at..\n\nShare the knowledge that people didn’t know that they missed..\n\nWe call ourselves the world’s first horse racing lifestyle magazine!.\n\nOur goal is not only to sell magazines It is to sell the concept of horse racing, to make racing once again get the place in the public heart that it once had, to make it grow and to be loved and 2012 will see it happen.\n', '', '', ''),
(1645, 1, 'African Hunting Gazette', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nFrom cover to cover, the African Hunting Gazette brings you everything you need to know about hunting the great continent of Africa.\n\nWe bring you the thrill and freedom of African hunting right into your living room. There is simply no other African hunting magazine of the same caliber. Let African Hunting Gazette be your guide.\n', '', '', ''),
(1646, 1, 'Bop Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBop, one of the best magazine’s for young teens in the US, carries the latest celebrity gossip, news, and the hottest pictures you’ll find.\n\nFollow the stars and their fashion triumphs – and disasters, with scoops on everyone from Miley Cyrus to the gorgeous Justin Bieber. Find out whether your secret crush is also crushing on you, or pin up the included posters all round your room and just gaze adoringly as they look down on you.\n', '', '', ''),
(1647, 1, 'Classic Trains', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nClassic Trains is a quarterly magazine which says itself that it wants to celebrate the ‘golden years of railroading’.\n\nThe magazine is primarily concerned with the North American railroad scene from the 1920s all the way through until the 1970s.\n\nThe magazine will feature proud steam giants, colourful streamliners, great passenger stations, local train lines with exciting unknown history as well as recollections of railroaders and train-watchers.\n', '', '', ''),
(1648, 1, 'Victorian Homes', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVICTORIAN HOMES magazine, established in 1982,features the romantic lifestyle of the Victorian,Revival. Articles explore the decoration and architecture of the 19th century and early 20th century homes restored, decorated and lived in by real people, as well as tours of beautiful period museum houses. Every issue is edited for a discerning.\n', '', '', ''),
(1649, 1, 'Designer Knitting', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBy buying Designer Knitting magazine, you will be getting a great insight into how the top stars of the designer knitting world ply their trade.\n\nPreviously known as VK Magazine, each issue will give you stylish patterns to copy as well as fashion shoots concentrating on the latest major knitwear designer lines. Tips and trick required to recreate them are also thrown in, so you''ve no excuses.\n', '', '', ''),
(1650, 1, 'Flyfishing-&amp;-Tying-Journal', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFLYFISHING &amp; TYING JOURNAL has the finest writers detailing how to overcome the challenges faced by fly fishermen. With in-depth features on techniques and the best step-by-step tying instruction in print. Edited for action-oriented fly fishermen, articles cover both fresh and saltwater fly fishing and fly tying.\n', '', '', ''),
(1651, 1, 'Quilters World', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMake fabulous projects from feature fabrics\n', '', '', ''),
(1652, 1, 'Beadwork Stringing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCreate your own jewellery - earrings, bracelets &amp; necklaces galore!\n', '', '', ''),
(1653, 1, 'Brain World', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBrain World explores the very best cutting-edge science and how its findings can affect human health, culture, education and more global issues.\n\nIt’s written for the general reader; thankfully you don’t have to be a neuroscientist to appreciate this magazine.\n\nThe creators say that they believe that neuroscience is the next great scientific border, and that advances in understanding the nature of the brain, perception, behaviour and health will transform our lives in the near future.\n', '', '', ''),
(1654, 1, 'Die Cast', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDiecast collector magazine covers all aspects of the UK''s diecast scene. It should be the first port of call for all collectors of diecast models.\n\nIn every issue of the glossy magazine readers are given the latest news and new model releases from Corgi &amp; Hornby, EFE and Oxford Diecast.\n\nThere will also be regular features on the latest toy fair dates and auctions. The magazine will also feature articles on limited edition models and other rare finds.\n', '', '', ''),
(1655, 1, 'In The Wind', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIN THE WIND features all the latest news and events for those into the biker lifestyle. Covering past events, upcoming rallies and more!\n', '', '', ''),
(1656, 1, 'Smooth Girl', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSmooth girl magazine covers music,lifestyles,girls and cars\n', '', '', ''),
(1657, 1, 'Interweave Knits', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFrom cover to cover a subscription to Interweave Knits Magazine gives you great projects from the beginner to the advanced knitter.\n\nEvery issue of Interweave Knits magazine is packed full of captivating smart designs, step by step instructions, easy to understand illustrations, plus well written lively articles sure to inspire.\n\nInterweave Knits Magazine is for knitters who fill their lives and dreams with knitting. Each issue features original designer patterns for garments and home decor, ranging from super-simple to challenging and from traditional to cutting edge, plus revealing designer profiles, enlightening explorations of knitting around the world, and in-depth technical articles.\n\nInterweave Knits celebrates the heart, mind, and hands with style.\n', '', '', ''),
(1658, 1, 'Romantic Country', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRomantic Country brings the best of living with comfort and beauty home to you.\n\nWe will treat you to pages brimming with the versatile ideas and boundless inspiration that define the many facets of this most heartfelt style.\n\nWe will invite you to dreamy and timeless homes, show you how to incorporate soft and soothing elementsand create sweet and simple crafts that will help you achieve your own gentle settings.\n', '', '', ''),
(1659, 1, 'Under The Radar', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nUNDER THE RADAR, the solution to music pollution,is the next generation of music magazines, and is embraced amongst indie music fans for its in-depth articles on past and present musical legends, a keen sense of the best new artists to watch and its intelligent writing that is free from pretension - but not devoid of humor\n', '', '', ''),
(1660, 1, 'Urbanglass Art Qtly', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nURBANGLASS ART QTLY is a glossy art magazine published four times a year by UrbanGlass in Brooklyn, New York. The magazine has provided a critical context to the most important work being done in the medium of glass. Its contributors include some of the most important critics and curators in the field.\n', '', '', ''),
(1661, 1, 'Filati Handknitting', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEach edition of this lovely produced magazine carries around 20 fabulous knitting designs from jumpers to dresses to bikini s etc. Each issue comes complete with the knitting instructions to knit these latest designs for yourself\n', '', '', ''),
(1662, 1, 'Nvision', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNVISION, The magazine that celebrates and examines the world of digital graphics in entertainment. In every dynamically designed issue, we''ll showcase the latest visual technology in videogames, film, art, special effects, and more.\n', '', '', ''),
(1663, 1, 'Guitar One', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGUITAR ONE features interviews with some of the top U.S. guitarists. Each issue contains 12 music transcriptions to improve your techniques. These are from stars such as Led Zeppelin, Van Halen, The Who and Eric Clapton. These are revolutionary and streamlined to get you on the fast track!\n', '', '', ''),
(1664, 1, 'Just Cards Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nJust Cards magazine is a craft magazine with all the details you need to create beautiful Cards for every occasion, with examples and step by step instructions.\n\nJust Cards is just that –just cards, with ‘just because’ cards, birthday cards, holiday cards, thank you cards and ones that cover all the big occasions.\n', '', '', ''),
(1665, 1, 'Knitters Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA quality magazine from CMG combining quality editorial with step by step projects for expert and novice knitting fans alike.\n', '', '', ''),
(1666, 1, 'Respect', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHip hop magazine aimed at capturing world class images of the best known figures in the rap world\n', '', '', ''),
(1667, 1, 'Skeptic', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSkeptic magazine examines extraordinary claims,explores revolutionary ideas and promotes good science. Each issue delves into a specific theme, while also lokking at a wide variety of social scientific and paranormal controversies.\n', '', '', ''),
(1668, 1, 'Water', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWATER is produced quarterly, on the highest quality paper. Explore 100+ pages of editorial including: extensive interviews, photographs and artist profiles, unique travel pieces and features on towns that continue to shape American surf culture.\n', '', '', ''),
(1669, 1, 'Troon Golf &amp; Travel', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTROON GOLF &amp; TRAVEL is a brand new quarterly print magazine geared to  avid  golfers who love the game and the lifestyle that surrounds it. Unlike GOLF and Golf Digest, we are a\n', '', '', ''),
(1670, 1, 'Ghettoblaster', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSmart, Innovative, Edgy and Effective. Ghettoblaster Magazine puts its reader ahead of the curve, giving them &quot;what''s next&quot; in underground music, film &amp; culture. Through impeccable coverage of underground and mainstream tastemakers in all genres, Ghettoblaster is a barometer for independent, punk, hip hop &amp; rap music genres.\n', '', '', ''),
(1671, 1, 'Harvard International Review', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThis Quarterly is the leading authority on internal relations.\n', '', '', ''),
(1672, 1, 'Ski', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nUS magazine dedicated to skiing, techniques, places to stay, skiing gear, general fitness\n', '', '', ''),
(1673, 1, 'Primitive Quilts', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHundreds of quilt ideas in every issue\n', '', '', ''),
(1674, 1, 'Mountain Flyer Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMOUNTAIN FLYER Magazine showcases the riders, racers, events, and culture of Mountain Cycling. Covering cross country, downhill, cyclo-cross, road racing and adventure riding. “We’ll Take You There” ... MOUNTAIN\n\nFLYER delivers the excitement through action-packed articles and stunning photography of events &amp; participants in the mountain regional cycling scene.\n\nMOUNTAIN FLYER is a top resource for cyclists, providing in-depth data on advances in cutting-edge gear/equipment, and the businesses and manufacturers who provide it.\n\nMountain FLYER brings this Mountain Adventure Sport to life!\n', '', '', ''),
(1675, 1, 'Alo', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nALO is a stunning lifestyle Magazine, presenting the finest in Beauty, Fashion, Dining, Entertainment, Art, Business, Culture with an insider''s eye toward the unique aspects of the dynamic and diverse worldwide community interested in the Middle Eastern, North African &amp; Mediterranean culture and Heritage. ALO translates to &quot;hello&quot;, embraces gracious living, and showcases enjoyment of an upscale lifestyle, shattering misconceptions about Middle Eastern-American Culture\n', '', '', ''),
(1676, 1, 'Strategy &amp; Business', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSTRATEGY &amp; BUSINESS features articles written by some of the finest thinkers in business, consulting, academia and journalism from around the world. The articles are challenging, thorough and thought-provoking.\n', '', '', ''),
(1677, 1, 'Antenna', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAntenna is the first mainstream magazine to target individuals who are on a constant quest for the newest and coolest products on the horizon. A guidebook, allowing readers to navigate the most extensive collection of products ever compiled in a single publication, while championing the people who create, sell and collect them-all in one comprehensive, artful, elegant and innovative format. Featuring everything from dress shirts and travel to jeans and well, snacks of course. It has created a space for people to voice their obsessions and connect with products through personal stories found in the commentary section and through sections such as process or lab where the reader is allowed behind the scenes. Antenna is considered to be a non-disposable magazine in a disposable world. And you cannot ask for more than that.\n', '', '', ''),
(1678, 1, 'Motor Trend Classics', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMotor Trend Classic celebrates the great cars of the past 65 years and the people who created them, owned them, raced them, and loved them. Every issue will put the reader in the driver s seat of some of the world s most fascinating cars. The automotive mix will be eclectic. You ll find million-dollar Ferraris fender to fender with thousand-dollar Fords, all brought to life by some of the best writers and photographers in the business. With Motor Trend s auto industry connections, Classic will offer unique insights into the seminal moments of the development of the automobile over the past six decades.\n', '', '', ''),
(1679, 1, 'Make', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMake (or MAKE) is an American quarterly magazine published by O''Reilly Media which focuses on do it yourself (DIY) and/or DIWO (Do It With Others) projects involving computers, electronics, robotics, metalworking, woodworking and other disciplines. The magazine is marketed to people who enjoy\n', '', '', ''),
(1680, 1, 'Crush Fanzine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCRUSH Fanzine is a quarterly, New York and Paris based fanzine that explores the finite detail of obsessions. Once someone said,\n', '', '', ''),
(1681, 1, 'Majestic Disorder', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nmajestic disorder is a quarterly arts and culture magazine producing original thought provoking journalism for creative entrepreneurs and urban professionals. Sprawling across fashion, film, travel and public affairs, majestic disorder features an eclectic mix of intimate stories and stunning photography encapsulating people and places around the globe.\n', '', '', ''),
(1682, 1, 'Christie''S International Real Estate', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCHRISTIES GREAT ESTATES is an international magazine which showcases distinctive properties from around the world. For many, real estate represents a sense of place and permanence. It is a place where friends and family congregate, share good times, and participate in meaningful gatherings. Perhaps this is one of the reasons why, in these unsettling times, the acquisition of a home takes on an even greater importance than many other investments. CHRISTIES GREAT ESTATES magazine features the world''s most extraordinary properties offered for sale. The real estate companies affiliated with CHRISTIES GREAT ESTATES invite reader inquiries about the homes they feature and other fine homes they represent.\n', '', '', ''),
(1683, 1, 'Cinefex', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCinefex is a quarterly magazine devoted to motion picture special effects. Since 1980, it has been the bible for effects professionals and enthusiasts, covering the field like no other publication. Profusely illustrated in color, with as many as 180 pages per issue, Cinefex offers a captivating look at the technologies and techniques behind many of our most popular and enduring movies.\n', '', '', ''),
(1684, 1, 'Inside Weddings', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nINSIDE WEDDINGS was created for style-conscious brides who love to read the newest and hottest trends from respected industry professionals. The editorial of INSIDE WEDDINGS covers all aspects of planning the honeymoon and everything in between. Each issue includes features articles on invitations, cakes, bouquets and floral arrangements, while providing a voyeuristic glimpse into some of the most beautiful real weddings held within the past year.\n', '', '', ''),
(1685, 1, 'Mit Sloan', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMIT Sloan Management Review''s mission is to lead the conversation among thinkers, professors and managers about the coming changes in management practice that will transform how people innovate and lead. MIT SMR captures the creativity, excitement and opportunity created by rapid societal, economic and technological change, and brings it home to thoughtful managers.\n', '', '', ''),
(1686, 1, 'Aperture', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAn Aperture magazine subscription is must for all photographers. Aperture magazine has been described as ''the most serious and the most valuable periodical in the photographic world'' and ''essential for anyone who takes photography seriously''. The printing and binding of this Aperture magazine subscription is of an especially high quality which helps to portray its images in the way the photographers intended them to be viewed. The Aperture magazine aims to serve the needs of photographers and photography enthusiasts from around the world. A subscription to Aperture is a great for anyone with a genuine passion for photography.\n', '', '', ''),
(1687, 1, 'Florida Design', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFlorida''s housing industry continues to be a hotbed of activity, thanks to several contributing factors. Topping the list is the state''s desirable climate, which continues to attract large numbers of seasonal and permanent residents. Lower taxes, enticing mortgage interest rates and a host of recreational amenities are also compelling buyers to make their move now rather than later. From the Gulf Coast to the Atlantic Coast and all points inbetween, nearly every community has experienced increased growth. This of course, spells only good news for architects, designers, craftsmen, furniture showrooms and other related design businesses. For everything you need to know about elegant interior design, FLORIDA DESIGN, whatever your taste, showcases it all.\n', '', '', ''),
(1688, 1, 'The Wild', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe WILD was founded on the premise that fashion, design and style are not mutually exclusive from the so- cial and cultural issues that impact our world. While pre- senting visually striking content, our international team of talented writers, photographers, designers and artists aims to focus on selfless, modern day heroes; artists with a vision; innovative, sustainable initiatives and fash- ion with a conscienceThe WILD is more than a magazine. It’s a conceptfor a generation of visionaries—a rendezvous point for progressive and optimistic ideas for the world we live in.\n\nThe WILD Magazine targets the fash- ionable yet environmentally and so- cially conscious reader: covering the latest fashion trends and designers alongside world and cultural issues. Readers update themselves with dai- ly content on recently released music videos, albums, art exhibitions and movies.\n\nThe WILD readers are highly afflu- ent and international. They associate themselves with luxury and experi- ences. The WILD Magazine expresses their desire for all things in fashion, art, music and culture.\n', '', '', ''),
(1689, 1, 'The Rodders Journal', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTHE RODDER''S JOURNAL is published for the Custom Car and Hot Rod enthusiast with numerous photos!\n', '', '', ''),
(1690, 1, 'The Knot', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe ultimate bridal source, ''The Knot'' is filled with all the information to-be-weds need to shop for their weddings.\n\nThe Knot Weddings’ revolutionary format combats traditional bridal magazine clutter with organized directories to help couples find the things they seek the most - from wedding gowns - to honeymoons - to ideas and products for the home.\n', '', '', ''),
(1691, 1, 'Harvard Onpoint', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHARVARD BUSINESS REVIEW ONPOINT Executive Series makes it faster and easier to put HBR''s ideas to work. Selected by HBR''s editors to bring readers the most relevant ideas and strategy on a single business topic, ONPOINT articles include the full text article, a summary of key points and company examples, and a bibliography to guide further exploration\n', '', '', ''),
(1692, 1, 'Man Of The World', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMAN OF THE WORLD is the new paradigm of magazines. It’s a vintage inspired handbook for the modern lifestyle. A truly innovative guide for the sophisticated man, MAN OF THE WORLD provides the ultimate in fashion, leisure, inspiration and excitement, and showcases the undiscovered and rediscovered.   Inspired by icons such as Paul Newman and Steve McQueen, each issue will feature men who embody the MAN OF THE WORLD aesthetic ...... innovators, humanitarians, artists, men who are fearless, confident, strong …... men who know what they want and are at the top of their game.   Photography, style editorials and stunning pictorial essays from mesmerizing locations all over the world create a magazine that will be treasured. Beyond the stories, the items showcased in MAN OF THE WORLD (vintage chronographs, classic cars, period home furnishings, custom designed artisanal objects, the best in fashion and much more) along with exclusive travel experiences will be made available to the readers via customized concierge services.   MAN OF THE WORLD addresses a niche market base in the overall landscape of men’s magazines. It bridges editorial and retail content to a booming segment of the luxury market. Through a passion and quest for excellence, its aim is to provide ideas for distinctive modern luxury living with a vintage perspective, for the sophisticated and cultured man.\n', '', '', ''),
(1693, 1, 'Celebrity Hairstyles Presents', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThis magazine is devoted to bringing the reader the latest celebrity hair trends. Celebrity Hairstyles magazine offers pages of new hair ideas for readers to experiment with.\n\nIt will also provide styling tips and free products give aways. The magazine will regularly feature articles by expert hairdressers who honestly give their opinions on the latest celebrity trends.\n', '', '', ''),
(1694, 1, 'Plaza', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHigh quality bi - monthly covering the field of modern decoration/interior, design and fashion.\n', '', '', ''),
(1695, 1, 'Tmrw', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTMRW is a high in quality publication covering music, fashion and lifestyle.\n\nIt has matured and developed into an industry recognised brand with many strings to its’ creative bow. A content heavy website and a digital watered down. .\n\nEach issue of TMRW deserves love and attention. It‘s unique paper and clean designs makes it perfect for coffee table or commute. .\n\nSince our launch we have maintained a clean, modern and fresh approach to our copy and design. We use a very thick paper stock which gives us an exclusive niche in the global publication market and will allow TMRW to run succesfully alongside the digital age..\n\nEach copy of TMRW also has consumer longevity as it’s high quality ethos begs to be looked after. .\n\nThrough passion and a drive to succeed we have become a creative hub for musicians, artists, illustrators, photographers, entrepreneurs and writers.\n', '', '', ''),
(1696, 1, 'Murder Most Foul', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMURDER MOST FOUL, published four times a year, provides hardcore crime buffs with a high-value package of murder cases both classic and modern from Britain, America and around the world. It draws its material both from today''s headlines and from the extensive True Crime Library archive. It specialises in facinating, detailed accounts of cases both solved and unsolved, and illustrates it''s stories with astonishing contemporary photos.\n', '', '', ''),
(1697, 1, 'Vna Magazine', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVNA (Very Near Almost) is a well established publication featuring Street Art and Graffiti, which is becoming increasingly popular worldwide. VNA is a quarterly street art publication. Basically documenting street art/graffiti/illustration/design from such Cities as London and featuring artists and designers from across the world. What makes it different to the rest? VNA is not specific&amp; It s a street art magazine with a twist. It s not a graffiti magazine but it features graffiti artists we admire and up and coming artists/designers/photographers that we as a team have kept our eyes on and want to share in printed media not just on the internet. ', '', '', ''),
(1698, 1, 'Prowl', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe aim of PROWL is to shed light on the current counter-culture by melting together exciting independent art, fashion, beauty, music, lifestyle and literature that reflects the mood of the moment.\n\nPunctuated with poetry and illusions, the content reveals the next big creative movements.\n', '', '', ''),
(1699, 1, 'Libas International', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAn exotic fashion and lifestyle magazine LIBAS INTERNATIONAL covers international events and activities in countries such as the United States, Pakistan, India, Dubai, etc. as well as the UK. With special features on music, art and literature and a primary focus on fashion, beauty and health.\n', '', '', ''),
(1700, 1, 'Technologist ( English )', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTechnologist contains special reports exploring major scientific topics in the news with in-depth articles on scientific debatesTechnologist contains special reports exploring major scientific topics in the news with in-depth articles on scientific debates.\n\nContents include news items on research, innovation and start-ups The magazine appears four times a year in English, French and German..\n\nTechnologist is for those who are interested in how science is changing the world. its readers are university graduates, including entrepreneurs and innovators..\n\nArticles analyze the impact of science on modern societies Provocative opinions and analyses with reviews of technological products aimed at the mass market..\n\nTechnologist publishes high-quality articles that are meant to circulate as widely as possible, digitally and in print..\n\nThe magazine’s format, with its removable pages, encourages readers to share articles or save them for future reference..\n\nContents include news items on research, innovation and start-ups The magazine appears four times a year in English, French and German. Technologist is for those who are interested in how science is changing the world. its readers are university graduates, including entrepreneurs and innovators..\n\nArticles analyze the impact of science on modern societies Provocative opinions and analyses with reviews of technological products aimed at the mass market..\n\nTechnologist publishes high-quality articles that are meant to circulate as widely as possible, digitally and in print. the magazine’s format, with its removable pages, encourages readers to share articles or save them for future reference.\n', '', '', ''),
(1701, 1, 'Wp B Smart Series', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSELLING POINTS: 201 wedding projects, budget tips and trends with up to date worldwide supplier lists and links.\n\nExpert advice on planning your big day without the big price tag from a small-budget bride .\n\nSave the hassle and cost of buying all those wedding magazines – Big Day Small Budget Wedding is advertising free, full colour and a bride-to-be’s best friend for thinking outside the wedding industry box.\n\nCost saving tips for wedding dresses to venues, catering and even the honeymoon without compromising on your dream day.\n\nWHAT IT’S ABOUT: Planning a wedding should be memorable, special and fun, after all it is supposed to be the “happiest day of your life”. Unfortunately for many couples the financial burden of planning a wedding can be vexing, with a quarter of couples putting some of the costs on their credit card and taking out personal loans.\n\nOften the desire to have the “perfect day” overshadows cost. This book is a bride-to-be’s best friend. It shows you how easy it is to save money and still have the wedding of your dreams and offers hundreds of useful tips and links to vendors and suppliers worldwide\n', '', '', ''),
(1702, 1, 'Pompom', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPOM POM is a quarterly, collectable publication for smart, creative types who like knitting patterns with a modern aesthetic, great photography and interesting writing.\n\nAlso into lots of other types of crafts and of course music, fashion, art, food and just generally making the world a little more beautiful with the things to make! Over the last year and a half, Pom Pom has established itself as the go-to publication for lovers of independent craft. .\n\nCommitted to supporting and showcasing independent designers, yarn dyers and craftspeople .\n\nHighlights - Beautiful styling and gorgeous pattern photography by Juju Vail. - Stunning layouts, advertising and typography by award-winning designer M Wyse. .\n\n- Knitting and crochet patterns by some of the best and well-respected names in the industry. - A focus on a well-made, hand-made and ethical lifestyle. - Quality printing on heavy, matt stock.\n', '', '', ''),
(1703, 1, 'Suitcase', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA quarterly fashion and travel publication, SUITCASE MAGAZINE is for women who not only have a huge appetite for travel, but are also thirsty for design and culture.\n', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `oc_product_description` (`product_id`, `language_id`, `name`, `description`, `meta_description`, `meta_keyword`, `tag`) VALUES
(1704, 1, 'Next Level', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNext Level is an art magazine dedicated to showcasing photographic art, creativity and culture, the essential source for cutting-edge contemporary photographic art. This has developed into a uniquely important national and international art resource. The primary aim is to bring awareness and debate to contemporary issues and culture, showcasing and celebrating emerging and established artists, across various disciplines and alongside inspiring, provocative and critical writing. Next Level magazine, founded by Sheyi Antony Bankale and Jimo Toyin Salako was launched in March 2002 at the Institute of Contemporary Art, London. Each edition of Next Level is published quarterly; March, June, September and December; an underlined theme is explored by the contributors in collaboration with Next Level to produce a personal interpretation. Ceased!! last issue 10/2012 ', '', '', ''),
(1705, 1, 'The Horse Riders Journal', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Horse Rider s Journal is the equestrian style bible, offering an elegant and insightful look into the beautiful world of horses and the lifestyle that surrounds them. Set within a fashion-related framework of stunning imagery and observant writing, the magazine features equestrian-inspired fashion and gorgeous stable interiors, while profiling the biggest equestrian icons and stars of tomorrow. The Horse Rider s Journal presents outstanding content from the best photographers, writers and stylists, be it from a polo match or a pony club. Whether you re a horse owner or simply admiring the equestrian universe from the sidelines, The Horse Rider s Journal invites you inside the captivating realm of horses via interviews, fashion editorials, features and trend pieces, all delivered with an originality never before seen in an international horse magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(1706, 1, 'Bomb', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBOMB Magazine has been publishing conversations between artists of all disciplines since 1981. BOMB''s founders—New York City based artists and writers—created BOMB because they saw a disparity between the way artists talked about their work among themselves and the way critics described it.\n\nBOMB Magazine is a print quarterly publishing in-depth interviews between artists alongside artists’ essays, literature, and portfolios.\n', '', '', ''),
(1707, 1, 'Bdm''S Seniors Series', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThis quarterly publication is completely unique in this marketplace offering content aimed directly at senior iPad owners.\n\nThe content offers a blend of jargon free user guides and targeted application reviews for use on the apple iPad. .\n\nWith high quality up-to-date expert editorial and focused design, this publication will be an un-missable purchase for all iPad owners aged over 60\n', '', '', ''),
(1708, 1, 'Bdm''S Senior Special Series', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThis quarterly publication is completely unique in this marketplace offering content aimed directly at senior I Pad owners. The content offers a blend of jargon free user guides and targeted application reviews for use on the apple I Pad..\n\nWith high quality up-to-date expert editorial and focused design, this publication will be an unmissable purchase for all I Pad owners aged over 60\n', '', '', ''),
(1709, 1, 'Slide', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWhat is SLIDE Magazine? The most comprehensive international surf magazine in the world? Perhaps.\n\nFor me, it’s easier to urge readers to flip through an issue and see what we are, rather than me tell you what we think we are. Have a look, and you tell me what SLIDE is. .\n\nBut, I can say this much: SLIDE is grounded in the ride-everything ethos, unbound by label or stigma, born in the classic longboard aesthetic while showcasing the vast range of today’s surf craft, their riders, their craftsmen, and the surf culture surrounding this communal vibe. .\n\nOccasionally, SLIDE even includes a bit of the mainstream shortboard thruster crew, though, truth be told, that ASP Top 44 side of our sport is better left to the corporate mags..\n\nWe believe gathering the best content possible from all points of the compass is paramount, away from the influence of corporate leaning. Surfers, photographers, and scribes, the world over, have noticed our tact, and we’re stoked to have attracted your attention and to receive your imagery, stories, and ideas, making for features that range from timely to timeless. .\n\nWe believe SLIDE is a wondrous auditorium for our side of the sport to perform and make some noise in, but, without talent to sing and dance within, it would be an empty black space, just a place to hear our own echoes..\n\nConsidering this great support system, it is our duty to maintain SLIDE’s high level of content and production, with tasty twists to further set us apart from the current surf mag amalgam. Our goal is enhancement with each edition, yet we can never be completely satisfied. And we are pretty sure you, the reader, would not want it any other way.\n', '', '', ''),
(1710, 1, 'Glass Fashion', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGLASS magazine exists at the increasingly collaborative intersection of art, fashion, music and design. GLASS aligns itself with the sophisticated consumer who is aware of the need for a more sustainable approach to comfortable living. Instead of being aspirational, we seek to be inspirational: we believe that in these turbulent times, ''luxury'' is governed by the intelligent, discerning choices we take to meet our needs, without compromising future generations. To this end, GLASS aims to transcend form, type or genre within its artistic endeavors to provide and promote timeless works of clarity, integrity and beauty.\n', '', '', ''),
(1711, 1, '74 The Hair Bible', '&lt;p&gt;FROM THE PUBLISHER 74 The Hair Bible, is a high quality glossy magazine. The magazine has in-depth features on hair &amp;amp; beauty, including the latest fashion &amp;amp; lifestyle tips. This magazine is a must have, featuring superb pictures on the modern hairstyles, with informative tips on how to achieve each hairstyle. 74 is The Hair Bible for the latest hairstyles and the best products on the market to use.&lt;/p&gt;\n', '', '', ''),
(1712, 1, 'Schon!', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSchon was and is created online by the people behind the Nineteen 74.com fashion website. Until now, Schon was only available on the internet and by  on demand printing , individual copies for individual orders. Coming to the worlds newsstand, each issue will showcase new talent to the fashion industry with contributors both photographic and editorially on a global scale. As Schon has grown and is becoming increasingly popular not only to clients but to anyone interested in the creative industry, we make sure we produce the best possible product. ', '', '', ''),
(1713, 1, 'Luxure', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLuxure is focused only on Fashion. The objective of Luxure Magazine is to define the aesthetics of high-end fashion from an innovative perspective, combining timeless and distinctive design, beautiful photography and creative writing. Luxure Magazine is a fusion of the luxurious and the understated, a marriage of opulence and serenity. ', '', '', ''),
(1714, 1, 'Mix Future Interiors', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMix Magazine is far more than just a design magazine; this quarterly publication is inspired by the Japanese idea of Mooks (magazine books).\n\nThe colorful layouts and incisive editorial of a magazine are merged with the detail and quality of a book, creating a long lasting and invaluable publication for anyone within the design industry.\n\nThe magazine offers the reader 130 pages of information on design, color trends, fabrics, contract, exhibitions, technology, and industry news, up to one year ahead of the season.\n\nIt is published four times a year in March, June, August and December. This is a vital publication for any professional who needs trend information ahead of the season, beautiful images and unique color palettes make this an essential source of inspiration.\n', '', '', ''),
(1715, 1, 'Art India', 'ART India is India''s premier art magazine: over the last eleven years, it has been responsible for the promotion of a critical discourse around diverse art forms, activities and disciplines.As an important forum for discussing, interrogating and appreciating art practices, ART India has been responsible for giving a platform to artists and critics to engage in a mutually replenishing intellectual dialogue with each other. This has led to the fostering of a vibrant atmosphere of sustained debate around crucial issues linked to the theory and practice of painting, sculpture, installation art, new media art, photography and architecture.', '', '', ''),
(1716, 1, 'Take On Art', 'TAKE On Art is an art quarterly published from New Delhi. It caters to artists, art collectors, dealers, educators, students, historians, architects, film makers, poets, designers and museum curators wherein each issue promises to comprehensively publish reports and critiques on art and cultural events from India and abroad. TAKE addresses in a comprehensive and candid tone relevant issues encompassing varied genres ranging from painting, photography and new media to the burgeoning art market, international fairs and changing art trends, both in India and abroad. ', '', '', ''),
(1717, 1, 'Woman &amp; Home Feel Good You', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nAimed at 35-plus women, woman&amp;home Feel Good You is the only wellbeing and fitness title on the market that offers women of any shape and any fitness level, the inspiration to feel fabulous every day.\n\nSimple changes that fit real life are the prescription to help women make the most of their looks, feel younger, fitter, slimmer, reduce stress, increase vitality and live a healthier life.\n\nThe magazine is divided into sections focusing on wellbeing, beauty, diet, fitness, health and ‘inner you'' and is packed with tips, expert advice and best buys.\n', '', '', ''),
(1718, 1, 'Irish Tatler Man', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIrelands ONLY Men’s Lifestyle Magazine, Irish Tatler Man features exclusive interviews with iconic and stylish men and expert advice on how men can look and feel their best. With more than one hundred and twelve pages packed full of fashion and grooming tips, Irish Tatler Man delivers the same high quality interviews and photography that is synonymous with it’s sister title Irish Tatler.\n', '', '', ''),
(1719, 1, 'Aga Living', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nAGA Living is the must-read magazine for AGA lovers everywhere. Packed full of interesting lifestyle features, AGA Living magazine covers everything from celebrity interviews to mouth-watering recipes and from new design to the latest AGA products.\n', '', '', ''),
(1720, 1, 'Hedge', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHedge magazine is the bi-monthly title for the Mayfair''s hedge fund community. Hedge offers a combination of the very best in luxury lifestyle as well as intelligent commentary on the hedge fund industry. Hedge boasts an eclectic range of contributors, including: George Soros (Soros Fund Management), Mrs. Moneypenny (FT), Caragh McKay (Telegraph), Simon Mills (GQ), Simon de Burton (FT), and George Magnus (UBS). Hedge understands its audience; featuring exclusive columns and content that – like its readers – pushes the boundaries. Whether focusing on philanthropic acts from key industry players such as Stanley Fink and Arki Busson, or James Doran’s innovative profile of the move of hedge fund investments in Hollywood, Hedge intimately understands its readership and provides hedge fund managers with an intelligent view on the world in which they live, work and play.\n', '', '', ''),
(1721, 1, 'Woman &amp; Home Feel Good Food', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Woman &amp; Home Feel Good Food Magazine?\n\nThis quarterly food and drink magazine offers a range of exciting recipe ideas, from quick fix suppers to creative dinner party dishes, making it perfect for those with a flair for food but little time to experiment. The easy-to-follow recipes contain locally sourced seasonal ingredients so you can enjoy plenty of fresh produce in every meal.\n\nGet the inspiration you need to brighten up your daily meals, and explore fresh new suggestions for traditional holiday cooking at Easter and Christmas.\n\nEvery recipe is beautifully illustrated to give you a great idea of what each delicious dish should look like, helping you to make your food look fantastic on the plate.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFour times a year, woman&amp;home Feel Good Food magazine brings you quick and easy food recipes, healthy eating tips and seasonal food ideas. Plus recipes and tips from top celebrity chefs. As ‘your seasonal cookbook'' each issue of Feel Good Food showcases what''s great about that season, helping you to make the most of ingredients when they are at their absolute best.\n\nGreat reasons to subscribe to woman&amp;home Feel Good Food magazine ...\n\n• Great savings on the full subscription price\n\n• Guaranteed delivery direct to your door every quarter\n\n• Never miss an issue!\n\n• Great gift idea for a foodie friend that lasts all year round.\n\n• Subscribers receive 10% off purchases from the woman&amp;home shop\n', '', '', ''),
(1722, 1, 'Transliving International', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nTransLiving International magazine is the world''s largest cross-dressing and transgender lifestyle magazine. It is A4 format, 84 pages and full colour throughout with a stylish design by Kim Argel.\n\nIn every issue you will find:\nAmazing real life TV/TS stories and photos- to inspire you by reading others experiences.\nEvent reports and listings- keeping you informed on all TG social events.\nBrilliant fashion and beauty editorial- boost your confidence and look with our specialist fashion and image consultants.\nTV/TS contacts- probably the biggest list of contacts worldwide.\nPartner''s corner- yes. Transliving is published for partners too!', '', '', ''),
(1723, 1, 'Town', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTown is the new quarterly magazine for London. Every season, it celebrates and curates the best of London life, covering everything from fashion, style, arts and culture to events, openings, food and drink. Drawing on the best photographers, writers and stylists, and produced to the highest specifications, Town is your essential guide to the world''s greatest city.\n', '', '', ''),
(1724, 1, 'The Gentlemans Journal', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe Gentleman''s Journal provides the latest in style and grooming, food and drink, business, lifestyle, culture, sports, restaurants, nightlife, travel, power and last but not least, intriguing private interviews with popular public figures\n', '', '', ''),
(1725, 1, 'Asiansuk Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\nAsiansUK magazine is the UK’s leading Asian Business and Lifestyle publication.\n\nAsiansUK magazine recognises the diverse British Asian culture by showcasing features on business, literature, arts, technology, finance, gadgets, food, entertainment, music, fashion and everything British Asian.\n\nAsiansUK magazine has unparalleled access to the most exceptional business tycoons and the most glamorous icons.\n\nIt also gives you access to prestigious events. The magazine showcases this via exclusive features that are insightful, entertaining and presented with style.\n\nBritish Asian dignitaries have long awaited such a publication and have all rallied round to show their support, these include; James Caan (celebrity entrepreneur), Faisal Butt (entrepreneur and investor), Rami Ranger MBE (Chairman Sun Mark Ltd) - who has also invited AsiansUK to his Annual Queens Dinner, Azhar Siddique (former Apprentice), Zeeshaan Shah (former Apprentice), Jas Jassal MBE, to name a few.\n\nFurthermore, the AsiansUK editorial team has been joined by talented individuals such as; Mandy Sanghera (FRSA International Development Consultant &amp; Global Human Rights Activist), Dal Dhaliwal (TV Presenter - BritAsia), DJ Limelight (Radio Presenter on BBC Asian Network and an Award winning DJ &amp; producer). At the British Curry Awards 2013, David Cameron stated curry restaurants alone contribute a remarkable £3.6 billion to the economy annually and employ more than 80,000 people. Clearly signifying Asian prosperity in the UK plays a prominent role within the economy in terms of job creation, innovation and contribution.\n\nDistinguished by wit and flair, AsiansUK magazine is fast becoming an indispensible part of life for British Asians. Our well-heeled readership shape opinions and trends. This affluent and influential group is almost impossible to reach – except through the pages of AsiansUK magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(1726, 1, 'Innowin', 'Innowin is India’s first magazine dedicated to innovation. Promoted by Marico Innovation Foundation—India’s preeminent platform for innovation and entrepreneurship, and conceptualised and produced by Spenta Multimedia—India’s largest custom publisher, Innowin is a quarterly committed to creating a culture of innovation. Based on the combination of two powerful action words—Innovate and Win—Innowin reinforces the idea that in today’s world, innovating is the only way to win.\n\nDesigned to cater to various social and professional classes—heads of innovation functions, business decision-makers, aspiring entrepreneurs and sociopreneurs, high-level government officials and policymakers, researchers, students, etc.—Innowin analyses what innovation actually is and propagates the ‘Can Do’ approach by telling people that anyone interested in making a difference can innovate.\n\nWhile there are many magazines on business and entrepreneurship, there is none dedicated exclusively to innovation. Innowin will thus create a unique, much-needed space for conversations on innovation in the Indian media.\n\nThe inaugural issue, available on stands from March, includes first-person contributions by the likes of Anand Mahindra, Nandan Nilekani, Arun Maira, Ganesh Natarajan, Ram Charan, Santosh Desai, and many more innovation stalwarts.', '', '', ''),
(1727, 1, 'Creative Steps', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Creative Steps Magazine?\n\nIf you want to give your children plenty of opportunities to enjoy imaginative and wholesome entertainment, then a Creative Steps magazine subscription will provide you with heaps of great ideas. There are over 80 projects in each quarterly issue, and all of them come with step-by-step instructions that are simple and easy to follow. The activities in this parenting magazine are suitable for children looking to have fun with their grandparents, childminders and early year teachers alike, and each is divided into three age categories (0-5, 5-7 and 7-11), making it easy to find the most appropriate project. You''ll also find book reviews and environmentally-friendly recycling ideas, giving your child hours of educational fun.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe WINTER 2014 issue is packed with more than 75 cool seasonal crafts and creative activities to inspire you and encourage your kids to learn through creative play; including Christmas crafts, ideas for Chinese New Year, international crafts, the results of the 2014 Creative Play Awards, tasty treats and loads more!\n\nPlus check out the fabulous toys, books and resources to be won in the free to enter competitions - including your chance to win fantastic Drumond Park games ''bundles''! Just complete and return the coupon on page 78 for your chance to win these great prizes.\n', '', '', ''),
(1728, 1, 'Teacher', 'Published by Australian Council for Educational Research, Teacher brings you articles by leading educators for leading educators, publishing the latest in professional development on teaching and learning, curriculum and assessment, educational research, leadership and management issues, education policy, resources, opinion and news. The magazine provides teachers and school leaders with opportunities to speak with each other and learn more about best practices being used &amp; what their colleagues are doing across the world.', '', '', ''),
(1729, 1, 'Great Golf Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nFirmly placed as\n', '', '', ''),
(1730, 1, 'Ten2Teens Magazine', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nTen2Teens Magazine is a positive publication that is inspired by 10-19 year-olds of black and mixed- race origins and is for ALL teens regardless of race, culture or background. Its mission is to present a more positive publication that reflects a balanced perception of our teens. It is RELEVANT, RELATABLE &amp; READABLE!\n\nContents in the Ten2Teens magazine includes the inspirational corner, girls and guys corner, teen features, interviews with inspirational young people who are making it out there, showcase of female and male role models, career options, music corner, health corner as well as our chill out zone with word searches, jokes, riddles and poems. This magazine is seen as being informative, educative, inspirational and fun as well to read.\n\nAre you a parent, guardian, youth group leader or a head teacher / teacher in search of a positive publication that would be relevant, relatable, readable and of great benefit to 10-19 year-olds? Then look no further, it’s right here!\n\nTEN2TEENS MAGAZINE – Inspiring to change perceptions\n', '', '', ''),
(1731, 1, 'European Communications', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIf you work in the telecoms sector or need the latest information on this rapidly changing market, European Communications magazine will deliver all the information you need. EC provides unrivalled analysis of the business challenges changing the industry as well as reporting on the revenue, generation opportunities, real-life applications, standards and legislative issues.\n\nIf you’re interested in new technologies, or solutions for corporate users, European Communications is the magazine to read.\n\nSubscribe today and save up to 20% off the cover price\n\nYour subscription includes:\n•Quarterly magazine in print and digital formats\n•Daily email e-newsletters\n•Our monthly top stories\n•Occasional topical Supplements.\n•Free access to ours webinars and seminars\n', '', '', ''),
(1732, 1, 'Travel Africa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nExplores The World''s most exciting continent from the comfort of your own home! A subscription to Travel Africa magazine gives you:\n\n* Quarterly editions of Travel Africa magazine delivered to you door.\n* Savings on the cover price\n* Unlimited access to every article we''ve ever published ( over 800 articles)\n\nComing up for subscribers: * Unique additional editorial features for subscribers only.\n* Savings on some great African products available exclusively from our shop. * Savings on special reader events.\n', '', '', ''),
(1733, 1, 'Natur Cymru - Nature Of Wales', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNatur Cymru is a quarterly bilingual magazine dedicated to the environment and wildlife of Wales. Each issue has a theme and a range of feature articles typically written by people living and working in Wales and covering wildlife stories, people and nature, the politics of the environment and examples of conservation in action. It is the definitive guide to what’s happening in the world of nature within Wales.\n\nThe Winter 2014 issue discusses the search for harvest mice in Wales, rare spider fauna, bat conservation in Wales, Cadair Idris and much more.\n\nEvery New subscriber will receive TWO BACK ISSUES of Natur Cymru FREE!!\n', '', '', ''),
(1734, 1, 'Outlook Traveller Luxe', 'Outlook Traveller Luxe provides privileged access to a world of luxury travel for well-heeled travellers who like to savour the finest globe-trotting experiences. It is the ultimate luxury companion you’ll need to make your holidays exceptionally extravagant – whether you’re looking for spa getaways, exotic beaches, wildlife sanctuaries, desert safaris or mountain hideways. Outlook Traveller Luxe - your passport to the most enchanting and enriching journeys at home and abroad!', '', '', ''),
(1735, 1, 'Celebrating Vivaha Magazine', 'The Wedding Magazine of the New Millennium, Vivaha is more than a magazine. It''s a guide, a companion. Celebrating Vivaha gives you the how to, where to and what to of weddings. Its global reach gives you a panoramic canvas to choose from. The secret of a great wedding lies within its glossy confines. Planning to the last detail, putting it all together and perfecting the occasion with food, fun, flowers; venue, wardrobe, vacation; make-up, makeovers and magic i what the magazine specialises in. Taking the toil out of the sweetest occasion of your life, it brings together all the elements that go into the making of a perfect wedding. Celebrating Vivaha lends you an understanding of delicate relationships, in-laws, friends, relatives and the warp and wefts of marriage. Gently initiating you into the various nuances, the magazine negotiates the rough and smooth with an exquisite sensitivity. Creating a path from which flows a mellifluous melody of togetherness and lasting happiness.', '', '', ''),
(1736, 1, 'Wedding Affair', 'Wedding Affair magazine is a complete guide and planner for all brides and grooms-to-be that brings the latest tidings and expert views on jewellery and beauty. Whats more? We even inform you about venues, caterers, beauticians, photographers, shops, jewellery and fashion designers, honeymoon destinations, travel companies, event planners etc. So, get your copies today to keep your guests wondering about the secrets of your ''talk-of-the-town'' wedding ceremony.', '', '', ''),
(1737, 1, 'Wedding Cakes - A Design Source', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Wedding Cakes - A Design Source Magazine?\n\nThe cake is the centrepiece of any big day, and this specialist wedding magazine offers a guide to all the latest wedding cake styles, with inspiring photo spreads of incredible sponge and icing creations to help you pick a design that''s sure to impress your guests.\n\nA subscription to Wedding Cakes – A Design Source magazine will also bring you top tips on how to brief your cake maker successfully, choosing a cake to suit the season and making sure that your cake fits with your overall theme.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA unique and extensive portfolio of hundreds of new wedding cakes, accompanied by a directory of the designers'' contact details. Additional features include projects from top sugarcrafters for making wedding cakes, plus book reviews, website listings, giveaways and competitions. Wedding Cakes – A Design Source magazine is an exclusive cake magazine that contains three issues per annual subscription. Published by Squires Group, every issue of a subscription to Wedding Cakes – A Design Source magazine contains over hundred different wedding cake designs and ideas. If you are planning a wedding then a subscription to this magazine is ideal. Wedding Cakes – A Design Source will bring to you all the new styles and designs of wedding cakes, enabling you to make your wedding cake the perfect edition to your special day. A subscription to Wedding Cakes – A Design Source magazine includes in depth and inspirational features on all aspects of wedding cakes, attractive projects, details of latest styles and designs, listings of designers, exciting competitions and giveaways and lots more. On the whole the magazine is a perfect guide for all who loves variety and stylish wedding cakes. Take out a subscription today!\n', '', '', ''),
(1738, 1, 'Scottish Wedding Directory', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Scottish Wedding Directory Magazine?\n\nPublished every quarter, this wedding handbook will ensure you’re connected to the right suppliers for everything you need to make your celebration a truly memorable occasion. From creative cake makers and imaginative florists, to talented wedding dress designers and exceptional caterers, a subscription to Scottish Wedding Directory magazine will help you to find the dreamiest Scottish wedding venues and source all of the materials you need to suit your theme. This is the perfect guide to help you piece together your perfect day, with a comprehensive list of suppliers and planners to suit any budget.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nScottish Wedding Directory magazine is an essential subscription for anyone who is planning their ‘big day’.The Scottish Wedding Directory magazine is Scotland’s leading wedding magazine and is filled to the brim with fantastic fashion pages, features bursting with tips and advice on everything you need to know about getting married. Is it any wonder the Scottish Wedding Directory is known as the ‘brides bible’?Bursting with information a subscription to Scottish Wedding Directory is your how to guide to making your wedding day a resounding success. You will find all the latest fashion trends, informative and useful planning guides, health and beauty tips, venues, honeymoon packages and lots lots more.A subscription to Scottish Wedding Directory magazine is the perfect gift for anyone who is planning their wedding or has recently got engaged.\n', '', '', ''),
(1739, 1, 'Asiana Wedding', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Asiana Wedding Magazine?\n\nMake your big day extra special with Asiana Wedding magazine: a fantastic source of inspiration on every aspect of the ceremony, whether you''re looking to stay up-to-date on the latest fashion trends in wedding outfits or find out where to buy the best flowers, fabrics or bridal jewellery.\n\nWith a subscription to Asiana Wedding magazine you''ll find plenty of ideas on themes, as well as real-life stories from happily married couples, health and beauty tips, celebrity interviews and even advice on etiquette and how to manage your guests.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Asiana Wedding magazine brings readers essential advice and inspiration to make their big day extra special. Asiana Wedding Magazine is the biggest selling Asian glossy wedding magazine in the UK. Packed with over 340+ pages, Asiana Wedding magazine delivers an amazing array of features relating to celebrities, fashion trends, health and beauty tips, social issues and expert advice to make planning the big day that little bit easier. Every issue of Asiana Wedding Magazine features inspiring bridal fashion, traditional Asian jewellery, stunning photography and flower arrangements. Asiana Wedding Magazine also provides a list of top caterers for all budgets and great wedding venues across the country. Published 4 times a year, Asiana Wedding Magazine also makes a great gift subscription for any bride looking for a little inspiration and help to make their big day perfect.\n', '', '', ''),
(1740, 1, 'Tate Etc.', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO TATE ETC. Magazine?\n\nThis is an innovative and exciting tri-yearly publication, inspired by one of Britain''s most loved art institutions, the Tate galleries. You can delve deep into the history of art, discover contemporary works, and flick through interviews, archive highlights and debates on some of the most interesting topics in the art world. With a TATE ETC. magazine subscription, you''ll experience the visual arts scene on an international scale, and get access to exclusive features and interviews from the world''s most celebrated artists, including Tracey Emin and Lou Reed.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPurchase a subscription to TATE ETC magazine and share your interest with the most prevalent figures in the creative world.Published three times a year, TATE ETC. brings focus, depth and original insight to the work of international artists celebrated in the Tate galleries and beyond.Each issue presents exclusive, in-depth features and conversations with internationally acclaimed writers and artists - from Rem Koolhaas and Tracey Emin, to John Banville and Lou Reed - in a showcase for outstanding design and fresh imagery.Keep up with a subscription to TATE ETC. and spend each year in the exclusive company of the artists and authors of the moment.The main aim of this magazine is to explore the visual art scene on an international scale. It includes in depth and informative features, excellent debates, editors note, poem of the month, hot events and much more.Along with all these high quality and well written contents the magazine carries stunning and fascinating artworks and photography. Subsribe to TATE ETC magazine today and make your creative life compete.\n', '', '', ''),
(1741, 1, 'Magnet', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nMagnet is an independent Christian resource for men and women. Each issue provides regular features including Bible study, a prayer focus, personal stories, worship material and a focus on world and justice issues.\n\nSubscribe today for just £12!\n', '', '', ''),
(1742, 1, 'Jill Oxton Cross Stitch &amp; Bead Weaving', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nJill Oxton''s Cross Stitch and Bead Weaving is a high quality cross stitch magazine and was first published in May 1990. From that time the title has enjoyed fantastic reader loyalty. There are three issues a year, each issue containing at least twenty five designs which range from the small to the large and cover a wide variety of subjects. ', '', '', ''),
(1743, 1, 'Fuel', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFUEL is a bookazine quality publication devoted to Hot Rods, Customs, Bikes, Girls, Tattoos, Art and events! FUEL magazine takes a slice through Australian motor culture and delivers it the reader s door 3 times a year. With 132pages, FUEL magazine is packed full of cool photos, art works and stories.......and more. ', '', '', ''),
(1744, 1, 'Lofficiel Hommes', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nL''OFFICIEL HOMMES is a French male lifestyle magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(1745, 1, 'Sposabella', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA stylish Italian language wedding magazine, SPOSABELLA is packed with beautiful glossy photographs and stylish ideas for the big day.\n', '', '', ''),
(1746, 1, 'Commons &amp; Sense', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCOMMONS &amp; SENSE is packed with high fashion and fantastic photography. The pictures inside have an unusual take on society and fashion - setting it apart from other fashion bibles such as Vogue. So if you''re into funky styles and want inspiration from photography and art, COMMONS &amp; SENSE is the magazine for you.\n', '', '', ''),
(1747, 1, 'Hairstyle', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHAIRSTYLE features all the tips and advice you need to have beautiful hair. With regular articles on popular new looks of today and 100''s of pretty new styles you''re bound to find the look you''re searching for.\n', '', '', ''),
(1748, 1, 'Hair Cut &amp; Style', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHAIR CUT &amp; STYLE is the magazine aimed at women looking to change their hairstyle. This magazine aims to help you decide which is the best style for you. Also featured are some of the hottest new styles from the top stars in Hollywood.\n', '', '', ''),
(1749, 1, 'Knit Simple', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIt''s simple: Knitting is fun. When so many of us seek out needles, hooks and yarn to help melt away the stress of our daily lives, the last thing we need is even more stress creeping in to the one thing that, frankly, keeps us sane. KNIT SIMPLE. Geared to two very distinct groups: the new knitter ready to graduate from scarf school and move on to more challenging projects, and the busy knitter (like most of us) who has just enough time (and energy) to tackle projects requiring a minimum of fuss and bother. Inside you''ll find patterns for house and home - quick approachable projects to inspire knitters of all skill, information about the hottest trends and techniques, and helpful tips and advice.\n', '', '', ''),
(1750, 1, 'Woodcarving Illustrated', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWood Carving Illustrated is a woodworking magazine for all woodworker enthusiasts. From the beginner to the advanced woodworker, all will love this magazine full of inspiring ideas. Projects of all kinds, from simple designs to intricate details. A subscription to Wood Carving Illustrated magazine promotes woodcarving as a pleasurable pastime and recognized art form. Both beginner and advanced carvers find a variety of how-to articles, illustrations, step-by-step instructions, patterns. tool reviews, and more.\n', '', '', ''),
(1751, 1, 'Skiing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nUS skiing magazine focusing on skiing, skiing equipment. Interviews, places to stay and more\n', '', '', ''),
(1752, 1, 'Urban Ink', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAs ROLLING STONE was to rock, and THE SOURCE was to hip-hop, URBAN INK MAGAZINE is the franchise on the cusp of this newest art form of self-expression for young adults and urban culture. URBAN INK is the only magazine offering a cutting edge look and bringing readers the unique coverage that they thirst for.\n', '', '', ''),
(1753, 1, 'Tattoo Flash', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTATTOO FLASH is designed as a pictorial tribute to the finest in skin art, featuring state of the art flash (tattooing designs) and will highlight designs by readers as well as professional photographers.\n', '', '', ''),
(1754, 1, 'Plaza Watch', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTop quality 2 per annum magazine covering the area of watches and jewellery.\n', '', '', ''),
(1755, 1, 'Golf Teaching Pro', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGolf Teaching Pro Magazine is the only publication that is committed to keeping golf teaching professionals informed on industry news, the latest techniques in teaching, and other issues relevant to the profession. Each issue of Golf Teaching Pro is full of instructional drills and tips, insights on fitness and the mental game, as well as advice encompassing business, technology, and professionalism. Golf Teaching Pro is the official publication of the United States Golf Teachers Federation.\n', '', '', ''),
(1756, 1, 'Jfw Uk', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nJF-W not only showcases the worlds best jewels and watches, it is presented in high fashion photo shoots. JF-W also contains articles on major cities in its HOT SPOT section. Also included are interviews with celebrities on their fashion.\n', '', '', ''),
(1757, 1, 'Tv Repartee', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTV Repartee is the UK’s leading transgendered and cross-dressing lifestyle magazine.Our readership ranges from those who simply cross-dress for fun on an occasional weekend right through to those who live full-time in a female role.\n\nRepartee is a fun magazine but treats cross-dressing seriously. With a great stylish design and full colour throughout, it is renowned for its excellent standard of production and varied content.\n\nThree times a year, each issue is packed with useful information and advice, lots of fabulous photos and readers’ letters, features, stories and contact ads. In Repartee we encourage the view that transvestism is something positive to be enjoyed rather than treated as a shameful problem. We try to present a good balanced view of all aspects of ‘dressing’ and without being pornographic; adopt a down-to-earth, open-minded approach to cross-dressing and ‘dressing up’ generally.\n\nBecause of its original lively approach to transvestism, Repartee grew rapidly from an initial 100 copies with photocopied pages into what is now generally regarded as the leading magazine for transvestites and cross-dressers in the UK, if not the world. It has a growing international readership and is consistently voted “Best Lifestyle magazine from UK” by The Tranny Guide.\n', '', '', ''),
(1758, 1, 'Magnet', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nMagnet is an independent Christian resource for men and women. Each issue provides regular features including Bible study, a prayer focus, personal stories, worship material and a focus on world and justice issues.\n\nSubscribe today for just £12!\n', '', '', ''),
(1759, 1, 'Vogue + Gq + Conde Nast Traveller (India)', 'Vogue India : Everything you need to know about fashion, trends, beauty, people and lifestyle, Vogue India is your ultimate style guide. In these pages you’ll find the hottest, newest and latest from the world of fashion and beyond, both in India and from across the world, making it the must-have accessory for the modern, fashionable Indian woman. Vogue India is India''s best women''s fashion magazine offering access to the latest fashion news, trends, accessories, celebrity photos, beauty tips.Vogue’s wide-reaching influence stems from various sources, including the persona and achievements of its most famous editor, its various charitable and community projects, its ability to reflect political discourse through fashion and editorial articles, and its move to emerging economies.\n\nGQ: Look Sharp. Live Smart. Right now. GQ Magazine, featuring the best in Style, Cars, Gadgets, Babes and The Good Life. You’ll be able to enjoy all our in-depth articles and great photo shoots, instantly delivered in stunning high resolution. GQ (originally Gentlemen''s Quarterly) is a monthly men''s magazine focusing on fashion, style, and culture for men, through articles on food, movies, fitness, sex, music, travel, sports, technology, and books. It is the male equivalent of Vogue. A men''s fashion magazine for the clothing trade, aimed primarily at wholesale buyers and retail sellers. Initially it had a very limited print run and was aimed solely at industry insiders to enable them to give advice to their customers.\n\nConde Nast Traveler: This is Traveller, inviting you to join me on another journey into the realm of mystery and suspense. This time the trip is to be made in the pages of a magazine, rather than on the air. This Conde Nast Traveller Magazine is the answer. Some of the stories are real retold for your enjoyment in fiction form by the finest writers of today.', '', '', ''),
(1760, 1, 'Campaign ', '\n\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAbout Campaign magazine: \n\nCampaign is the leading weekly magazine for the advertising and communications industry – bringing you, opinion, analysis and news from across adland. \n\nSubscribe to Campaign for:\n\n•Weekly stories from the creative industry, delivered to your home or office \n•Access to weekly downloads of the Campaign iPad edition, so you can read the latest developments wherever it suits you \n•Valued opinion from key industry players – helping you operate at the cutting edge of the communications industry\n•New-business rankings, across the creative and media sectors – keeping you up-to-date with your competitors billings \n\nPlus, regular specials throughout the year including; The A-List, School Reports and Half-Term Reports.', '', '', ''),
(1761, 1, 'Marketing Week', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Marketing Week Magazine?\n\nThis business management magazine gives you a weekly summary off all latest market trends, strategies and developments to keep you informed on international news. With your subscription to Marketing Week, you''ll read about important innovations, compelling case studies and diverse company strategies. You''ll also enjoy special reports, including the Salary Survey and the Content Marketing Essays Supplement, and unlimited access to marketingweek.co.uk. If you''re considering a change of role, you can take advantage of access to hundreds of marketing job advertisements with leading brands and agencies, as well as early invitations to great networking events like Market Week Live.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMarketing Week is the perfect magazine subscription for anyone who works or is interested in the world of marketing.Marketing Week delivers first hand news and in-depth analysis of the most significant shifts in major brands’ strategies, product launches, industry breakthroughs and key appointments and departures from all industry sectors. Every issue carries opinions by the most respected experts in the industry.A subscription to Marketing Week includes:•Weekly copies of the magazine direct to your desk.•Unlimited access to MarketingWeek.co.uk – breaking news, interactive features, trend reports and blogs.•Supplements and special reports throughout the year.•Hundreds of sector-by-sector marketing jobs in print &amp; online. •VIP invitations to marketing shows &amp; events including Marketing Week Live.Marketing Week is magazine for media, advertising, PR and marketing professionals. Bringing you all the information you need from the world of marketing.\n', '', '', ''),
(1762, 1, 'Amateur Photographer', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Amateur Photographer Magazine?\n\nThis weekly photography magazine is an ideal choice if you’re an amateur photographer looking for some simple advice or great inspiration to kick start your career in photography. With reviews on the latest equipment, as well advice on buying and comparing products, you’ll be well informed with this helpful title.\n\nYou can also check that your camera skills are up to scratch with handy tips and tricks on photo and editing techniques, and an Amateur Photographer magazine subscription even comes complete with an annual competition for readers just like you, with a prize of £5,000 worth of Canon vouchers up for grabs.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAmateur Photographer is the world''s oldest weekly photographic magazine, established in 1884. It is the respected authority for news and reviews, with detailed tests and investigations on the latest equipment. The weekly contents includes interviews and columns from many of the world''s leading photographers and practical technique to inspire and enthuse the devoted readership, to whom taking photos is far more than just a hobby. The world''s oldest consumer weekly photographic magazine, Amateur Photographer magazine is the most authoritative and influential photographic magazine in the UK. With its unique weekly format, it is the first for news and equipment tests. Amateur Photographer magazine contains regular features on reader portfolios, darkroom, digital, black &amp; white and photographer profiles ensure all areas of photography are covered.\n', '', '', ''),
(1763, 1, 'Classic Car Weekly', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Classic Car Weekly Magazine?\n\nIf you''re looking for the latest vintage car trade information, then a Classic Car Weekly newspaper subscription is exactly what you need. Each edition has listings of hundreds of cars for sale, and is also a great resource for finding the spare parts you need to complete your restoration project. You''ll also find detailed advice on everything from buying and maintaining classic cars to accident-proofing your garage, plus reviews of road-tested vintage vehicles. If you''re looking for a comprehensive classic car newspaper with up-to-date information every seven days, then this is the title for you.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Classic Car Weekly , the No1 weekly newspaper for classic enthusiasts. Classic Car Weekly is packed with hundreds of classic cars and parts for sale every week with news stories that matter to real enthusiasts. It is a trusted source of information for buying guides, latest news, road tests, auction reports and contains the most comprehensive and up-the-minute classic car events guide. . The newspaper comes out weekly on a Thursday and runs regular articles on buying, selling, maintaining and driving classic cars along with a mixture of private-seller advertising and editorial articles. . Classic Car Weekly was launched in 1990 by Emap and now reaches over one million readers a year! . Don’t miss out, subscribe to Classic Car Weekly today and received the newspaper direct to your door each week. There''s no bettter place to track down classic car parts!\n', '', '', ''),
(1764, 1, 'Commercial Motor', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSubscribe to Commercial Motor magazine and receive the road transport industry''s best-selling weekly, giving its readers focused industry news, road tests, features, special supplements and the biggest and the best used vehicle classified section in the business.Commercial Motor tests every type of commercial vehicle available from vans to top weight trucks with its own team of experienced HGV drivers. Commercial Motor helps its readers stay profitable, professional and legal every week.This weekly magazine by Road Transport Media reaches fleet owners, partners, managers and fleet engineers with special focus on construction, retail, agriculture, manufacturing, engineering and commercial transport of all kinds. Commercial Motor magazine comes with market reports, classified ads, event news, product tests and buyer guides.\n', '', '', '');
