(1765, 1, 'Motorcycle News', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Motorcycle News Magazine?\n\nA fantastic resource of up-to-date news from the biking world, with a Motorcycle News magazine subscription you''ll get insights and advice from the biggest stars in motor sport through in-depth interviews and first-hand reviews.\n\nThe MCN team personally put every new model through its paces, with world exclusive test drives making sure you get to read professional opinions on every industry development.\n\nIn each issue you''ll find insider info from the biggest brands, features on trends and travel, and of course, the weekly buying guide, with loads of great deals on bikes, accessories, parts and insurance.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGet a subscription to Motorcycle News magazine - The world''s number one motorcycle publication. Each week Motorcycle news magazine (MCN) delivers all the road and sports news for every biker, from commuters to Grand Prix racers. If you want to know what''s happening on Planet Motorcycle and how it affects your wallet, enjoyment, knowledge or rights, then MCN tells you first. Motorcycle News magazine has been in publication for over 50 years. Not only does it help readers make a decision on which bike to buy, but it is also an integral part of making it happen too. Millions of bikers have used MSN to get hold of their dream machines, and the Bikemart classified ads section is still the only major British publication for used bikes which is written and run by motorcyclists. Every year hundreds of thousands of machines are bought and sold from within MCN magazine. Motorcycle News magazine understands what reader’s want, when it quizzes manufacturers about inflated prices, tests new bikes, writes race reports, or launches a riders’ right campaign, they are thinking of their reader’s and the questions they would want answered. Subscribe to Motorcycle News magazine today to benefit from exclusive subscriber offers!\n\nThe Direct Debit Guarantee\n\nThe minimum subscription term for the direct debit offer is 12 months. The amount paid by Direct Debit may change over time. If and when it does you will be notified in advance by at least 10 days. If an error is made by Bauer Media Ltd or by bank/building society, you are entitled to a full and immediate refund. You can cancel the Direct Debit at any time by writing to your bank/building society and send a copy to Bauer Media Ltd at: Magazine Subscriptions, Tower House, Sovereign Park, Market Harborough, Leicestershire LE94 7ZT. Please note that banks and building societies may not accept Direct Debit instructions from some types of account.\n', '', '', ''),
(1766, 1, 'The Publican''S Morning Advertiser', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Morning Advertiser and The Publican have merged to bring you the best of both publications in, The Publican''s Morning Advertiser\nThe new title continues to act as the voice of the industry, campaigning and fighting your corner with a unified, stronger voice.\n\nReading The Publican''s Morning Advertiser is now the best way to stay ahead in the UK pub industry, giving you:\n\n• All the breaking news stories\n• Informed comment\n• Practical tips and case studies to boost your business\n• Expert legal advice and opinions\n• All the latest products and services\n• Menu ideas to drive your food business\n', '', '', ''),
(1767, 1, 'Flight International', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Flight International Magazine?\n\nThis weekly aviation magazine brings you information on developments in aerospace and aviation from the last seven days.\n\nWith news coverage from military, business and general aviation, plus interviews of key figures in the industry, including airline CEOs and aeroplane pilots, this publication gives you an insight into all areas of flying.\n\nIf you subscribe to Flight International magazine, not only will you get a wide selection of editorial and comment articles, but you''ll also find recruitment sections, job classifieds and information on available training, making this the perfect magazine for aerospace or aviation professionals.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Flight International magazine will keep you up to date with the latest aviation and aerospace industry news. Flight International magazine is the leading weekly news magazine for the international aviation and aerospace industry. Every issue of Flight International magazine brings you objective coverage of the latest news, products, aircraft and regulations, plus detailed features, technical reports and reference directories. Flight International magazine contains regular features on employment and training are designed to help you develop your career along with all the very latest aviation and aerospace vacancies. With a Flight International magazine subscription reader’s can enjoy special issues throughout the year that feature over 20 Flight International directories and guides.\n', '', '', ''),
(1768, 1, 'Bloomberg Businessweek', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Bloomberg Businessweek Magazine?\n\nIt''s easy to keep on top of the latest business news with a weekly Bloomberg BusinessWeek magazine subscription. Get key insights from a number of well-respected business professionals, with inside information on some of the world''s biggest companies and dozens of lifestyle and gadget tips to keep you ahead of the technological trend. This mag takes a focussed approach to the weekly news, with in-depth features and analysis on the key political and economic talking points, plus interesting interviews with some of the most successful entrepreneurs in the world, giving you an insight into their drive and motivation.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSUBSCRIBE NOW to Bloomberg Businessweek, the one magazine that gives you a fresh look at the latest international business news, global economic, technology and industry trends, company profiles, government policy and much more.\n\nWhen you subscribe to Bloomberg Businessweek you get:\n\nOPENING REMARKS - A richly reported essay on one of the week’s most important stories.\n\nCOMPREHENSIVE COVERAGE - The latest must-know global news in sections such as Markets &amp; Finance, Companies &amp; Industries, Global Economics, Politics &amp; Policy, and Technology.\n\nINSIGHTFUL FEATURES - In-depth stories that go beyond the headlines to offer broader perspective on critical topics shaping the world today.\n\nINTELLIGENT PURSUITS - A new section covering the culture of business and the rewards success brings including travel, money, gadgets, books, and more.\n\nVITALITY - From the bold covers, to the engaging layout, to the more contemporary design, you will want to read it.\n\nWe know you’ll be impressed.\n\nEvery week Bloomberg Businessweek keeps you a step ahead of today’s business world with complete coverage of critical issues: •Business News •International Business •Stock Market News •Global Economy •World Markets •Financial News •Company Profiles •Industry Trends •Technology News •Energy Trends •Political Policies •Government Regulation •Corporate Law •Financial Advice •International Exchanges •Corporate Leadership\n\nPrepare for your week ahead.\n', '', '', ''),
(1769, 1, 'Money Marketing', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nOver the past 25 years Money Marketing has forged a reputation as the leading independent source of news and information for the financial services industry. Delivering weekly:\nNews - you won’t miss a thing with our team of award-winning journalists keeping you up-to-date with the very latest reporting on financial services stories, as they happen.\nAnalysis - look beyond the news with real insights from leading industry figures. Every week you’ll get expert analysis of the key issues affecting your business. Opinion - top industry professionals share their thoughts and experiences keeping you in touch with the latest trends and thinking in the financial sector.\nMoney Marketing is the choice of weekly newspaper for professionals working in financial services.\n', '', '', ''),
(1770, 1, 'Mortgage Strategy', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMortgage Strategy is the first weekly intermediary title in the mortgage market. It is written for professional mortgage advisers.\n\nBecause it is published weekly, it can react to regulation issues, product launches, and industry moves, as and when they happen.\n', '', '', ''),
(1771, 1, 'The Lawyer', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to The Lawyer, the definitive source of news and market information, focusing on important developments in every aspect of law.\nThe Lawyer is the market leading title for commercial lawyers and corporate directors providing news and analysis of market strategies, and keeping readers at the forefront of new practice management techniques. Each week The Lawyer''s award-winning editorial team brings you all the news stories, both domestic and global, that are shaping the world of legal business.\nThe Lawyer features a dedicated news section, International Lawyer, uncovering the major stories from around the world. A weekly section, The Lawyer Deals, providing the most comprehensive and up-to-date deals reporting in the market. And a new litigation section gives up-to-the-minute reports and analysis on all the key cases of the moment.\nThe Lawyer also includes business updates in specialist areas of the law, plus weekly reports that focus on human resources, marketing, IT and in-house issues, form a specially-tailored management section.\nWith a subscription to The Lawyer you will receive 50 Special Reports - in-depth features on regional and overseas issues, practice areas and business markets such as e-commerce, insolvency, property and alternative dispute resolution.\n', '', '', ''),
(1772, 1, 'Farmers Weekly', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSubscribe to Farmers Weekly magazine today, the weekly glossy that’s full of all there is to know about farming and agriculture.\n\nPacked with news, views and technical information from the Farmers Weekly team and independent experts, every issue is designed to help you manage your business more effectively.\n\nWith a weekly digest of facts and figures about British, European and world agriculture, a Livestock, Arable and Machinery section reporting on the latest technical developments, a land section that reviews farm sales and analyses factors effecting price, market analysis, legal advice and a selection of ads for anything from sheep dogs to second hand tractors, milking equipment to mobile mixers, if you need to know it, it’s in Farmers Weekly.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSubscribe to Farmers Weekly magazine today, the weekly glossy that’s full of all there is to know about farming and agriculture.\n\nPacked with news, views and technical information from the Farmers Weekly team and independent experts, every issue is designed to help you manage your business more effectively.\n\nWith a weekly digest of facts and figures about British, European and world agriculture, a Livestock, Arable and Machinery section reporting on the latest technical developments, a land section that reviews farm sales and analyses factors effecting price, market analysis, legal advice and a selection of ads for anything from sheep dogs to second hand tractors, milking equipment to mobile mixers, if you need to know it, it’s in Farmers Weekly.\n', '', '', ''),
(1773, 1, 'Investors Chronicle', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWhether you’re a seasoned investor or just getting started, a subscription to Investors Chronicle magazine, a Financial Times Group publication, brings you the authoritative source of market-beating fund &amp; share tips, analysis and independent and comprehensive coverage of the UK stock market, and has been helping investors make their money work harder for over 150 years. However, we cover more than just shares, a subscription to Investors Chronicle magazine means that you can enjoy all of this: - Tips of the week. Uncover four exciting shares plus a bond tip and a fund tip every Friday morning. - Weekly features on big investment themes such as energy markets, commodities and how to boost your income. - Funds coverage. Interviews with leading fund managers plus our in-depth research to help you find the best funds for growth and income. - Tips updates. Throughout the week we publish updates on our past stock picks, online. - Ideas to take advantage of tax-efficient savings vehicles, including ISAs and SIPPs. - Economic analysis. We''ll give you the bigger picture, and help you understand the factors that affect your saving and investments. - Trading ideas. ‘The Trader’ will show you with clear charts how he uses technical analysis to anticipate marketing moves and inform his strategy. - Comprehensive companies’ coverage. We analyse nearly 2,000 company results each year to help you conduct through research when making investment decisions. Please note our subscription packages mentioned above provide you with the following: Print only – includes print magazine plus access to our digital edition (available on your PC or laptop) Print + Digital - includes print magazine plus full digital access: weekly iPad edition, website (both desktop and mobile versions) and digital edition (available on your PC or laptop)\n', '', '', ''),
(1774, 1, 'Shares', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nShares magazine is a weekly publication aimed at the serious private investor, and can help you make the most out of your investment during these volatile times.\n\nWritten by industry experts – our Editor, Russ, has 18 years experience within the industry, most recently Managing Director of UBS – we can help guide you on where the markets are going, not just report on what has happened. Every article in Shares features actionable content and suggestions for trades to make you a profit with our famous BUY, SELL recommendations.\n\nShares magazine covers much, much more than stocks and shares. Each week you get comprehensive coverage, guidance and analysis on listed companies from FTSE, AIM and PLUS markets, as well as industry insight from the people that count in our Griller interviews, features, sector reports, funds, charts &amp; trend spotting, Forex updates and analysis, commodities news, small caps and more. We also provide instruction and insight into instruments including ETFs, CFDs and spread betting to help you make profit regardless of market trends.\n\nAs well as all of this, each issue has a comprehensive cover story and a feature section reflecting the latest, most critical areas of discussion as they happen. .\n', '', '', ''),
(1775, 1, 'Coach &amp; Bus Week', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Coach &amp; Bus Week magazine is a must-have for coach and bus operators, suppliers, officials and anyone involved in the coach and bus industry. Each issue in a subscription to Coach &amp; Bus Week magazine features all the latest industry news, as well as in-depth articles covering all aspects of this sector, including industry leaders, operators, suppliers and various industry bodies and organisations. The magazine also covers recent deliveries, vehicle and product launches, legal updates and current debate that affects the industry, while the classified section advertises huge numbers of the latest products, services and vehicles for sale as well as including its very own driver section. Package includes: - 12 issues of Group Travel World (monthly tourism magazine) - Quarterly Essential Guide industry supplement - Monthly minibus supplement - Annual wallplanner - FREE online subscriber access to Coachandbusweek.com\n', '', '', ''),
(1776, 1, 'Fund Strategy', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe first publication catering solely for the top end of the investment intermediary market.\n\nIt is a quick read, delivering everything retail investment professionals need to know about how world market shifts and industry moves are affecting the funds they recommend in an easy to read, concise format, published at the start of the business week.\n', '', '', ''),
(1777, 1, 'Advertising Age (Adage)', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFor more than 65 years, Advertising Age has been the preeminent source of marketing, advertising and media news, information and analysis. We formed The Ad Age Group to respond to the ever-changing needs of today''s marketers. Through a variety of marketing publications and new-media platforms, The Ad Age Group has expanded the magazine''s scope and industry leadership with unparalleled coverage of marketing to consumers, business-to-business, marketing across borders and the creative world.\n', '', '', ''),
(1778, 1, 'Business Week', 'Business Week was first published in September 1929, only weeks before the Stock Market Crash of 1929. Its original purpose was to provide information and opinions as to what was happening in the business world, at the time. Initially, the magazine published sections that included topics such as marketing, labor, finance, and management, among others.Consequently, Business Week pioneered the action of covering national political issues that directly impacted the business world. In 1950, the magazine published its first executive pay survey, which it still does today.', '', '', ''),
(1779, 1, 'Antiques Trade Gazette', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Antiques Trade Gazette Magazine?\n\nThis highly readable weekly mag will keep you up to date with the national and international art scene, with analysis and breaking news from fine arts markets across the world.\n\nYou''ll find in-depth reports on upcoming events and auctions, as well as a comprehensive insight into the vibrant world of antiques.\n\nAn Antiques Trade Gazette magazine subscription is packed full of expert interviews, auction price guides and a whole number of special interest features to keep you fully informed about all of the latest developments in the world of antiques and fine art.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nKnown as the Bible of fine art, a subscription to Antiques Trade Gazette magazine is a must have for anyone who loves antiques, whether it be their trade or their passion.Antiques Trade Gazette is the acknowledged ‘Bible’ of the fine art, antiques and collectables industry – a weekly that provides all the latest in market information, news and analysis to art and antiques trade professionals as well as collectors since 1971.Each week you will receive the Gazette’s authoritative view on all that’s happening in the fine art and antiques markets, along with the latest UK and international news, comprehensive listings of forthcoming auctions and fairs, auction prices, and special interest features – all printed in high-quality paper in finely-detailed, vibrant colour.Place a subscription to the Antiques Trade Gazette magazine today and do not miss a trick.\n', '', '', ''),
(1780, 1, 'My Weekly', 'WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO My Weekly Magazine?\n\nIf you''re looking for a top women''s weekly that takes a more considered approach to the glossy world of showbiz, then a My Weekly magazine subscription is a great option for you.\n\nAs a warmer and more inspiring publication, this mag mixes celebrity interviews and fashion spreads with tasty recipes, inspiring travel guides, health advice and gardening tips.\n\nOne of the more unique features you''ll find with a My Weekly magazine subscription is an engaging short story in every issue, plus challenging puzzles and great knitting patterns to keep you entertained each week. There''s also a whole range of real-life stories and fashion buying guides in every issue, keeping you up to date with the latest trends.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA My Weekly magazine subscription is essential for women who enjoy good reading. Each week My Weekly magazine, delivers relaxing fiction, great food and cookery, inspirational real life articles, and stylish fashion, beauty and shopping. A My Weekly magazine subscription is also a perfect gift for women wanting a bit of everything from short stories, reader contributions, knitting or sewing patterns to entertaining celebrity gossip. Please note that there is a 12 month minimum term for all direct debit subscriptions.', '', '', ''),
(1781, 1, 'Hello!', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO HELLO! Magazine?\n\nA more sympathetic kind of celebrity and gossip magazine, HELLO! invites you into the fabulous lives of the people behind the headlines.\n\nWith gorgeous photoshoots and revealing interviews with some of the most talented and beautiful stars of showbiz from the UK and abroad, you''ll get all the intimate details of their biggest life events: from engagements and weddings to babies and divorces.\n\nWith a subscription to HELLO! magazine you can take a tour of some of the most luxurious celebrity homes and even get a glimpse of their secret fitness and health tips.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA HELLO! magazine subscription is exactly what you need - if you''re looking for a great-quality, glossy weekly, that is! Featuring stories on everyone who''s anyone in British society - whether it''s supermodels, musicians and Hollywood actresses or lords, ladies and even royalty. If they''re A-List, they''ll be in your weekly HELLO! magazine. With exclusive coverage of the biggest events, interviews with the most rich and famous and beautiful photo shoots that will make you green with envy, there''s no denying it''s a fantastic read. HELLO! magazine has a great reputation as a reliable source of news - not just idle gossip - which is why it''s the magazine the stars trust. If you take out a HELLO! magazine subscription, your weekly read will include:\n\n• Diary of the Week - Topical photo-coverage of high society events: cocktail parties, receptions, gallery openings, charity dinners. The place to be and be seen in the social calendar.\n• Panorama and World in Pictures - A topical, pictorial review of world events.\n• Inside Story - The essential insight into the daily lives of the rich and famous.\n• Cinematters - The weekly round up of news and celebrities from the entertainment industry.\n• Puzzles - and Teasers\n• Fashion - Beautiful people and beautiful clothes! With over 32 pages a month dedicated to fashion HELLO!''s unique coverage combines haute couture, with shopping pages highlighting key collections, accessories and new ranges.\n• Beauty - Written by our award-winning beauty editor, Nadine Baggott, we cover the latest products and best buys with tailored solutions for all your beauty needs.\n• Health - sound advice for a healthy lifestyle.\n• Cookery - Recipes as well as advice on preparation, nutrition and accompaniments.\n• Horoscopes - with Jonathan Cainer.\n• Win! - a chance to win a prize worth at least £2,500!\n\nA subscription to HELLO! magazine makes the perfect gift for somebody special, or even just a lovely treat for yourself!\n', '', '', ''),
(1782, 1, 'Kerrang!', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Kerrang! Magazine?\n\nIf you like your music loud and heavy, you can be sure to find it inside the pages of Kerrang! magazine. Punk, rock, emo and grunge are all covered extensively in the magazine’s seven-day gig listings, making sure you never miss a show in your city.\n\nRegular features include pull-out posters, interviews with internationally renowned acts, and the innovative Pandora comic strip, giving you a satirical take on the biggest events in the music world. You''re also given a chance to share your views on your favourite new artists, with reader reviews and feedback pages featuring prominently in every issue.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Kerrang! Magazine, the world''s biggest selling rock magazine. Each issue of Kerrang! will cover all forms of music with attitude from Slipknot to Marilyn Manson, Limp Bizkit to The Offspring and everything in between. Kerrang! Magazine also includes a satirical comic strip called Pandora, whose main character is seen every week making fun of recent events in the rock world. The band or person who is featured on the cover of the previous months issue is usually featured in the Pandora comic strip. The Direct Debit Guarantee The minimum subscription term for the direct debit offer is 12 months. The amount paid by Direct Debit may change over time. If and when it does you will be notified in advance by at least 10 days. If an error is made by Bauer Media Ltd or by bank/building society, you are entitled to a full and immediate refund. You can cancel the Direct Debit at any time by writing to your bank/building society and send a copy to Bauer Media Ltd at: Magazine Subscriptions, Tower House, Sovereign Park, Market Harborough, Leicestershire LE94 7ZT. Please note that banks and building societies may not accept Direct Debit instructions from some types of account.\n', '', '', ''),
(1783, 1, 'Nme', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO NME Magazine?\n\nDedicated to uncovering the latest bands from across the globe, NME magazine gives you the chance to get to know the hottest news acts before they become famous.\n\nYou’ll find exclusive interviews with break out artists and established indie legends in each weekly instalment of an NME magazine subscription, as well as opinions and reviews from some of the music industry''s most respected journalists and critics.\n\nThis magazine has been promoting bold and exciting new acts and trends at a grass-roots level for more than 60 years, with weekly gig listings and live reviews making sure you''re the first to know who''s playing in your city.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe most legendary music magazine of them all, NME is the weekly destination for any serious music fan. With a team of writers and photographers dedicated to unearthing the most exciting stories and scenes from across the globe, each issue is packed with big-name interviews, new band info, in-depth music news debate and the UK''s most comprehensive gig guide. Launched in 1996, NME magazine has been there when all of the great bands emerged - from The Smiths and Libertines to The Artic Monkeys. Every week with a NME magazine subscription readers receive the most exciting and authoritative coverage of the very best in contemporary music as well as a regular look back through the magazine''s incredible 58 year heritage. First for music news, NME magazine also makes a great gift subscription with its wide range of music styles – something for everyone! If it''s not in the NME then it''s not worth listening to!\n', '', '', ''),
(1784, 1, 'Heat', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Heat Magazine?\n\nFind exclusive interviews, jaw-dropping photos and the hottest A-list news from Chelsea, Essex, Hollywood and everywhere in between with a subscription to Heat. For anyone who enjoys a celebrity and gossip magazine fix, this weekly glossy comes with star style tips and photos from the world''s most glamorous red carpets, as well as candid snaps of celebs on holiday and out and about. There are also plenty of fashion and beauty features to keep you up to date on the latest trends, plus revealing photoshoots with some of the hottest guys in showbiz and ''weird crushes'' of the year for giggle-worthy entertainment.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to Heat magazine brings you everything you need to know about Britain’s favourite celebrities. Heat magazine loves celebrities, but, it doesn’t mean they put them on a pedestal. Sure, they love their TV shows, films and music, but love them even more when they turn up on the red carpet wearing hideous frocks or fall over drunk outside the latest celeb hangout. It’s the sense of humour and irreverent take on the showbiz world that makes Heat unique. Heat magazine is always on hand to catch celebrities’ most embarrassing moments, and with the juiciest jaw-dropping gossip, exclusive interviews, hot fashion spreads and a brilliant TV guide, Heat is the ultimate celebrity bible.\nHeat was launched in February 1999 as a general interest entertainment magazine, however, over the years and after a series of revamps it has quickly become a less serious, more gossip-oriented magazine for women and is now one of the biggest selling weeklies in the UK. So, if you can see yourself flicking through Heat’s addictive pages with breathless anticipation shouting “OMG have you seen this!&quot; at anyone who will listen, then you need to treat yourself and get subscription today!\n', '', '', ''),
(1785, 1, 'Tv Times', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to TVTimes magazine, one of the UK’s best-known magazine brands, with over fifty years of TV heritage. With each week of your TVTimes magazine subscription there are big star interviews, more soap coverage than any other TV weekly magazine, and the most easy to use digital listings for simpler navigation. First published in 1955 as a regional magazine, TVTimes magazine is now a national TV listings magazine published by IPC Media in the UK. TVTimes magazine is well known for its access to television actors and their programmes and places an emphasis on big star interviews and coverage of soaps.\n', '', '', ''),
(1786, 1, 'Woman''S Way', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIreland''s leading weekly women''s magazine, Woman''s Way maintains a vibrant combination of real-life stories, fashion, beauty, cookery, home style, celebrity interviews, travel and competitions.\n', '', '', ''),
(1787, 1, 'Ok!', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO OK! Magazine?\n\nBringing you all you need to know to keep up-to-date with the juiciest gossip from the world of celebrity, OK! magazine is for anyone who''s mad about Madge or crazy about Kate Middleton.\n\nCovering everything from babies to boyfriends, break-ups to bikini bodies, an OK! magazine subscription will give you the inside scoop on the biggest stories, with a glossy mix of exclusive interviews, wedding photoshoots and snaps of your favourite singers, actors and reality TV stars on the red carpet, on holiday and on the move.\n\nPlus, you''ll find fashion and beauty features and the latest television and film reviews in every issue.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nOK! magazine is world famous for its exclusive celebrity interviews, glamorous photo shoots and the scoop on all of the latest gossip in the world of showbiz and entertainment. If you subscribe today, you will have every celeb-packed issue delivered directly to your door, every week. The magazine’s tag line is “first for celebrity news” because it covers all of the most-talked about celebrities, before any other weekly magazine. OK! Magazine is most well-known for its coverage of celebrity weddings. Some of its biggest wedding exclusives were David and Victoria Beckham, Britney Spears and Kevin Federline and of course, Jordan and Peter André. Originally launched as a monthly publication, the first issue of OK! Magazine was published in 1993, but soon it was turned into the weekly magazine we all recognize today. OK! Magazine is the best-selling celebrity gossip magazine in the UK, with 30 million readers worldwide and appearing in 19 different countries.\n', '', '', ''),
(1788, 1, 'Radio Times', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER ?\n\nPlease select your region to ensure you receive the correct regional version of Radio Times!\n\nGet a subscription to Radio Times magazine, the ultimate digital TV and radio guide - it is the very best way for you to catch the week''s essential digital TV and radio, with clearer listings, brighter features and inspiring choices. Plus there are great recommendations for the week''s unmissable music, DVDs and downloads!\n\nWherever your interests lie, a Radio Times magazine subscription will help you find your perfect programme on one of over 85 digital TV and radio channels every week. The simple and easy-to-understand TV listings and inspiring recommendations mean you''ll have no trouble discovering those hidden gems. Plus there are exclusive interviews with the biggest names in the business for you to enjoy, behind-the-scenes specials providing fascinating insights into the nation''s favourite programmes and exclusive photo shoots which you''ll only see in Radio Times magazine.\n\nRadio Times magazine was founded back in 1923 as a response to newspaper boycotts of radio listings amid fears that people would then listed to the news on the radio instead of buying newspapers. Also, until the deregulation of television listings in 1991 Radio Times magazine only carried information for BBC channels whilst ITV published their own listings in TVTimes.\n\nAt one time, Radio Times magazine had the largest circulation in Europe and to this day is the most comprehensive source of UK radio listings in print.\n\nPlease note overseas subscriptions are only for the London edition\n', '', '', ''),
(1789, 1, 'The Stage', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Stage is the weekly newspaper for budding performing arts students and experienced entertainment professionals alike. With the very latest jobs, auditions, castings, training courses, news, analysis, listings, as well as reviews and opinion pieces, it''s essential for everyone interested in the performing arts. The Stage covers all aspects of the performing arts including theatre, light entertainment, backstage and technical plus every issue includes the renowned recruitment and training pages. Each issue gives performing arts professionals and students the information edge required to grow and sustain successful careers. Subscribe and save money on the shop price, receive every issue directly to your door, and enjoy the edge to help you succeed.\n', '', '', ''),
(1790, 1, 'Hola!', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHOLA! magazine subscription will deliver all the best celebrity news and interviews direct to your door each week. HOLA! is a glossy weekly featuring stories on royalty, supermodels, Hollywood stars and all the A-List. We cover exclusive stories on international stars. HOLA! is the magazine that celebrities trust.\n', '', '', ''),
(1791, 1, 'Grazia', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Grazia Magazine?\n\nOffering a fab mix of high-end and high street fashion, Grazia is a weekly must-read for women who want to stay on top of the latest trends and street style.\n\nWith a subscription to Grazia magazine you''ll read about all the hottest A-list celebrity gossip, with plenty of coverage from glamorous red carpet events. \n\nYou can create your own celebrity-inspired look with help from the hair and beauty sections, and be ready to debate today''s hot topics with features on important issues and headlines affecting women globally.\n\nIn each issue you''ll also find reviews of the latest film and book releases, keeping entertainment as well as fashion covered.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGet a subscription to Grazia magazine, for fashion as it happens. Be the first with all the front page stories, stunning designer fashion, fantastic shopping, hot gossip and much more with a subscription to Grazia magazine delivered to your door every week!\n', '', '', ''),
(1792, 1, 'The Bookseller', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The Bookseller Magazine?\n\nFor avid readers or for those looking to enter the publishing industry, a subscription to The Bookseller magazine is a must.\n\nThis books and literature magazine contains listings of the best publishing jobs available in the UK, as well as opinion articles, profiles of leading authors and publishing houses, and extensive features on the book selling business.\n\nThe Bookseller has been the leading resource for those in publishing since 1858, and this subscription-only magazine also has fun, quirky features such as its annual prize for the oddest book title of the year.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to The Bookseller magazine provides a weekly source of incisive, objective industry news and analysis, reaching all major booksellers and publishers in the UK and in nearly 100 countries worldwide. First launched in 1858, The Bookseller has the leading business magazine for the book industry for over 150 years. Each issue of The Bookseller magazine includes sales figures, publisher news, but is also great for simple lovers of literature featuring book launches and bestseller charts! The magazine also has an active seminar programme and the Bookseller retail awards. A subscription to The Bookseller magazine is an invaluable resource for anyone involved in or interested in the sale of books.\n', '', '', ''),
(1793, 1, 'Tls', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO TLS Magazine?\n\nIf you’d like to broaden your cultural horizons, a magazine subscription to the Times Literary Supplement is just the thing for you. The TLS is widely considered as one of the world''s leading literary magazines, established in 1914. The magazine typically includes poems, reviews and essays by some of the most exceptional writers of the moment, giving you an authoritative view on today’s most pressing literary and cultural issues. To discover what to read, what to see, and for insights into fantastic cultural days out, subscribe to the Times Literary Supplement magazine.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nGet a subscription to the Times Literary Supplement (TLS) - the leading paper in the world for literary culture. For more than a hundred years, the TLS has sought and found what is best in our literary culture, providing a unique pleasure - as well as a necessary resource to readers around the world. A mix of fine writing, literary discoveries and incisive debate has ensured its status as mandatory reading for many of today''s top writers and thinkers. The TLS offers comprehensive coverage not just of the latest and most important publications, in every subject, in several languages - but also current theatre, opera, exhibitions and film. Every week, readers of the TLS will find new poems, occasional short stories and regular columns and some two-dozen detailed reviews of new books in a wide range of subjects.\n', '', '', ''),
(1794, 1, 'The People''S Friend', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The People''s Friend Magazine?\n\nIf you like to curl up with a short story at the end of a long week, then a subscription to The People’s Friend magazine is definitely for you.\n\nFirst published in 1869 as ''a weekly miscellany of popular and instructive literature,'' the magazine continues to publish both fact and fiction to keep you entertained and informed. Each issue includes a variety of short stories penned by a host of talented writers from around the world, as well as a number of reader''s letters and entertaining puzzles.\n\nYou''ll also find lifestyle tips and regular travel features exploring Britain''s undiscovered gems, plus informative articles on gardening, interiors and health.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPeople’s Friend magazine is a true friend with dramatic short stories, craft projects and tips on good housekeeping and gardening and tempting recipes. This famous story magazine was first produced in 1869 and has a distinct Scottish feel.The People’s Friend provides a strong base of captivating fiction, a dash of crafts, a sprinkling of gardening and of course a good dose of tempting recipes. The People’s Friend subscription is the perfect ingredient to brighten any woman’s day.\n', '', '', ''),
(1795, 1, 'The Tablet', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to The Tablet provides a British Catholic weekly newspaper on current affairs, politics, religion, social issues, literature and the arts.\n\nFounded in London, England, 170 years ago, The Tablet newspaper has a long-standing international reputation unique in the English-speaking world.\n\nEach week The Tablet newspaper seeks to inform on religious affairs, politics, society, literature and the arts, considered in the light of Catholic principles and belief.\n\nIn every issue of The Tablet newspaper you can read articles, by writers of international standing, which will help enrich and explore your faith; we discuss practical and spiritual issues within the parish in our ‘Parish Practice'' section, reflect on prayer in our ‘Living Spirit’ column and you will be uplifted by our window on the beauty of nature in our ‘Glimpses of Eden’.\n\nGreat reasons to buy a subscription The Tablet newspaper: •Never miss an issue\n•Free delivery to your door each week\n•Save off the cover price\n\nSubscribe to The Tablet newspaper today for you or a friend and celebrate the catholic religion. Plus you can save up to 16%!\n', '', '', ''),
(1796, 1, 'Times Higher Education', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGet a subscription to Times Higher Education (THE) - The UK''s prime destination for academic news, analysis and employment. Since 1971, Times Higher Education (THE) has been the trusted source of authoritative information about higher education. Every issue delivers all the breaking news, sharp analysis, lively debate in a way no other title can. THE covers policy issues and developments worldwide through a specialist staff of reporters and many contributors from within the academic community. Times Higher Education provides high-quality information and analysis as well as a forum for debate for the academic community on higher education policy issues — public funding, tuition charges, quality assurance, institutional governance, student assessment, postgraduate training etc — and on intellectual developments, personalities and debates. Coverage also includes a large number of book reviews of both specialised texts and books of general interest to an academic audience. Free access to the new app\n\nIf you own an iPhone® / iPad™ / iPod touch® and you are a subscriber to the THE print edition you can explore the world of higher education on the move with our new app – it’s like having in your pocket. If you’re a current subscriber to simply visit www.exacteditions.com/print/the and enter your surname and subscriber number to download the app today!\n\nIf you don’t have an iPhone/iPad/iPod touch you can still receive a digital edition…\n\nSubscribers to the print edition also automatically qualify for free access to our brand new digital edition which can be conveniently and securely emailed to you every Thursday. Plus you will gain full access to the back issues digital archive at no extra charge.\nIf you’re a current subscriber to simply register your email address with us so that we can send you the access link. Go to www.subscription.co.uk/help/tsl to add, confirm or amend your details and start to receive digital every week!', '', '', ''),
(1797, 1, 'Country Life', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Country Life Magazine?\n\nWhether you''re looking to buy your own rural property or find the inspiration to add a touch of the countryside to your own home, you''ll love a Country Life magazine subscription.\n\nThis weekly mag covers all things country, and each issue is crammed with the latest property news and expert advice on buying and maintaining countryside homes.\n\nIn addition to the detailed images of home décor and rural style ideas, you’ll find the latest news from the world of fine art, as well as practical, professional gardening tips and feature articles delving into issues that affect the British countryside.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA weekly Country Life subscription will ensure that you can always enjoy the magnificent country properties across the United Kingdom - those for sale and those just to admire. You''ll see gardens that will make you green with envy, along with tips for your own. You''ll discover the topical issues affecting the countryside, and spend time appreciating the arts, antiques, field sports and the wonders of our wildlife. With incisive opinion and exceptional photography, Country Life is the voice and champion of the countryside and the ultimate place to find your dream home. Country Life is the definitive weekly magazine that covers the finest aspects of British life. Each issue of Country Life features magnificent country properties both for sale or just to admire. You’ll see gardens that will make you green with envy, along with tips for your own. You’ll discover the topical issues affecting the countryside, and spend time appreciating the arts, antiques, field sports and the wonders of our wildlife. Country Life is a unique and eclectic blend of news, features, country houses &amp; culture. If you love the Countryside then Country Life is the weekly fix for you - subscribe today.\n', '', '', ''),
(1798, 1, 'Tes', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGet your hands on the magazine everyone is talking about!\n\nInside every issue you will find all the news, features and analysis you would expect from the country’s leading education publication, the new TES includes:\n\n·TESpro – a new pull-out guide to the best practice in teaching\n·Resources – highlights of the best lesson plans and content devoted to the main subject areas\n·Analysis – more in-depth analysis of the latest news and developments in education\n·Jobs – an enhanced jobs supplement that is easier to use, colour-coded and an expanded international jobs section.\n\nFor a very limited time we are offering you your first 6 issues for £1 plus receive this free TESpro folder worth £9! This useful folder will store a whole year’s worth of TESpro – a brand new pull-out-and-keep guide to the best practice in teaching - so that you can start to build up your personal CPD library.\n\nSubscribe to a new professionalism!', '', '', ''),
(1799, 1, 'Tes Scotland', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe TESS has been the trusted voice in education for over 40 years and continues to provide an unrivalled depth of information and coverage every week. Setting the agenda in education, it’s at the heart of the teaching community, delivering the latest news, analysis, opinion and practical advice, as well as 100''s of jobs, all in one place.\n\nAs a subscriber, your weekly subscription includes: the TESS newspaper and the TES professional magazine delivered direct to your door every week by first class post!', '', '', ''),
(1800, 1, 'The Spectator', 'WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The Spectator Magazine?\n\nFilled with political and cultural commentary from a number of leading left and right wing journalists, this news and current affairs magazine will keep you up to date on the world''s most important talking points. A Spectator magazine subscription will give you an intelligent and often satirical overview of contemporary British society, as well as reviews on the latest film releases and literary debuts. In addition to receiving this leading publication to your door each week, you''ll also get free access to the magazine''s full suite of iPad and iPhone apps, as well as invitations to a number of subscriber-only events, including wine tastings and exclusive debates. Please note, no refunds will be given on any subscriptions cancelled within the first year.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLove great writing? Then a subscription to The Spectator magazine is perfect for you! Inside every weekly issue you’ll find the latest current affairs, politics, books, arts, life, laughter – everything that’s big news!\n\nThe Spectator magazine has a 184-year history, having assembled Britain’s greatest writers and entertaining, informing, delighting and infuriating its subscribers – and they make no apologies for doing so.\n\nSomething Spectator writers won’t do is send you to sleep. They have the freedom to write exactly what they want. Their politics range from left to right, their circumstances from high life to low life. The most perceptive political analysis comes as standard. There is no party line, the sole allegiance is to originality of thought and elegance of expression. The result is a quality of argument not to be found in any other publication.\n\nThe likes of Matthew Parris, Charles Moore and Rod Liddle are regulars in the magazine. The literary pages are awash with the very best reviews, and the arts coverage gives the final word on Britain’s galleries, shows and films. And all of this is spiced with the funniest cartoons in print.\n\nA subscription to The Spectator also includes membership of SpectatorPlus, the subscribers’ club. This gives you free access to The Spectator apps, the chance to attend free events such as wine tastings, and discounted tickets to Spectator debates as well as other special subscriber-only offers.', '', '', '');
