(1801, 1, 'Cycling Weekly', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Cycling Weekly Magazine?\n\nEach issue of this cycling magazine features ''News'', ''Fitness'', ''Tech'' and ''Rides'' sections, giving you a comprehensive roundup of what''s going on in the cycling scene. In its ''News'' section, you''ll find reports from recent bike festivals and professional tours, as well as updates from cycling teams and bike manufacturers to keep you up-to-date with the cycling circuit. If you subscribe to Cycling Weekly magazine, you''ll also get access to expert fitness and dietary advice, plus reviews of the latest bikes and kit, and helpful bike buying guides for specific price ranges. You''ll also find in-depth ride guides, covering cycle routes from across the country, to show you where''s best to take your bike.\n\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nStay up to date with all the cycling news and improve your cycling fitness with our expert training and nutrition advice. Learn about the latest bikes and cycling products on the market. Cycle guides to try for all levels, from weekend cyclists to team riders. Coverage of the professional riding scene with all the national and international results. Exclusive interviews with cycling’s superstars. Every issue in a subscription to Cycling Weekly magazine comes packed full of up-to-date news, fitness advice, product tests, race reports, exclusive interviews with all the top pros and expert advice, plus great routes to ride complete with pull-out map. Travel in tandem with Cycling Weekly? If you like getting on your bike, a subscription to Cycling Weekly magazine is just the thing for you. Britain’s best-selling and best-loved cycling magazine is the perfect companion for anyone who rides for fun, for fitness or for a living.\n', '', '', ''),
(1802, 1, 'Beano', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Beano Magazine?\n\nBeano has been rocking the shelves of newsagents since the 1930s, and hasn''t lost any of its appeal for kids today.\n\nWith comic strips, silly jokes and plenty of mischief, your kids are sure to burst into giggles with every issue. Introduce your kids to all your childhood heroes, with Dennis the Menace, Minnie the Minx and Billy Whiz still going strong, along with modern favourites like Beano Manga.\n\nThe bite-sized stories and pictures are easy for even reluctant readers to follow, and this weekly dose of stories, quizzes, games, and awesome drawing how-tos will keep your kids busy and entertained for hours.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDon’t tell the children, but reading can be fun! Britain’s favourite comic enjoys its 75th anniversary this year and continues to deliver a weekly comic that’s loaded with laughs and jumping with jokes! Home to comic legends the Bash Street Kids, Minnie the Minx and of course Dennis and his hound Gnasher and now seen on the smash hit CBBC TV show! A subscription to The Beano is the cheapest and fastest way to get every weekly issue and makes an ideal treat!\n', '', '', ''),
(1803, 1, 'Tv &amp; Satellite Week', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTV&amp;Satellite Week is the ultimate guide to TV for the discerning multi-channel viewer. Whether you''re a fan of US shows, soaps, film or sports, TV&amp;Satellite Week is your must-have guide keeping you up to date with what''s on each week. TV &amp; Satellite Week magazine is the ultimate guide to digital TV. The magazine carries easy-to-follow daily listing for more channels than any other TV guide, including all the major HD channels. TV&amp;Satellite Week magazine subscription also features weekly previews of all the week''s best new shows, films and live sport events, plus comprehensive guides to the best kids'' channels and the week''s football on TV. TV&amp;Satellite Week magazine features pages specially designed for digital TV, which allows you at a glance to see what''s on and when. This means that you will never miss your favourite shows! TV&amp;Satellite Week magazine covers all sections from films, soaps, sports and news – making it a great gift subscription for anyone with any interest! Plus, enjoy the convenience of having TV &amp; Satellite Week delivered straight to your door by subscribing today!\n', '', '', ''),
(1804, 1, 'Cage And Aviary Birds', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nCage &amp; Aviary Birds is the world''s only weekly newspaper dedicated to birdkeeping.\n\nEstablished in 1902 and published every Wednesday, in each issue you are reading expert advice written by leading birdkeepers.\n\nFrom up to date news on birds, colourful pictures of collections of birds from all over the world, to advice on breeding, feeding and general upkeep of these beautiful animals.\n', '', '', ''),
(1805, 1, 'Garden News', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Garden News Magazine?\n\nIf you want to stay on top of all the latest developments in the world of horticulture, then this is the ideal gardening newspaper subscription for you.\n\nIt’s written by gardeners for gardeners, so it’s full of easy to follow instructions and advice, as well as comprehensive information about gardening events taking place up and down the country. There are also plenty of great tips on when you should be pruning or planting, helping you to map out your gardening calendar for the whole season.\n\nYou''ll even get the chance to take part in a number of exciting competitions and prize draws, making it a great way to save money on a number of other gardening essentials.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGarden News - Britain’s only weekly gardening newspaper written by gardeners for gardeners.\n\nGarden News is the newspaper for every gardener, bringing you everything you need to know in your garden each week. Each issue of Garden News magazine is packed full of practical, down-to-earth gardening tips, grow-your-own advice and ideas and inspiration.\n\nYou’ll also find all the latest news, new plants and products, plus great money-saving offers and free gifts.to help you get the very best from your plot.\n\nBritain’s top gardeners including Carol Klein, Terry Walton, Nigel Colborn and Stefan Buczacki can also be found in Garden News magazine each week offering up to the minute expert advice on everything from growing bedding plants to fruit and vegetables.\n\nA subscription to Garden News magazine is a must-have for all gardeners wanting to get the best from their gardens.\n', '', '', ''),
(1806, 1, 'Projects Info', 'PROJECTS INFO, a weekly publication, is one of the largest circulated projects-related publications in India. It takes a comprehensive peek into the various projects planned, underway and completed in India. Apart from covering engineering, real estate, construction, energy &amp; transport, it also updates readers on contracts awarded that week, industry events coming up, finance, and more. Each week it carries a special report on an interesting project, interactions with project heads, and a special feature on a pre-selected industry sector. A must refer publication for decision makers in organizations that provide products and services to the infrastructure projects.', '', '', ''),
(1807, 1, 'Property Week', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nIncludes VAT on the digital elements only. Digital subscriptions are delivered via email\n\nAs the most respected magazine in the commercial property sector, a subscription to Property Week magazine brings you the publication that is the modern face of Property. Every week of a subscription to Property Week magazine brings you cover stories that trigger the big water-cooler conversation of the week, breaking exclusive news on the most significant stories we know you''ll want to read. Centring on regional and national significant issues and matters of public policy, Property Week is the trusted voice of the industry, informing the UK''s commercial property market by providing up-to-the minute news, features, comments and in-depth analysis. With a print or premium subscription, in addition to the weekly print edition, subscribers enjoy free access to propertyweek.com for the latest daily news, comments and extensive archive of property deals and transactions. They also save up to 20% on the print cover price, receive 49 digital and print editions every Friday and regular supplements.\n', '', '', ''),
(1808, 1, 'The Grocer', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nPrices include VAT for the digital elements\n\nThe Grocer has been publishing for over 150 years. It is still the UK''s most trusted source of independent information about the grocery retail and fmcg market and continues to move with the times, providing a range of services to keep you up to date with the latest industry developments.\n\nMembership\nMembership of The Grocer provides you with unique and cutting edge market intelligence. It delivers this information across a range of media, including a website, mobile, tablet, newsletters and magazine. And with our new web-first news policy, members are also informed of new developments instantaneously.\n\nThe Grocer Platinum Membership\nOnline and Print magazine. The Grocer: total market and financial coverage of the grocery industry, whenever and however you need it. The Grocer Platinum Membership provides the deepest most comprehensive coverage of the entire fmcg market – keep abreast of key changes to the market ahead of your competitors! You’ll always be in the loop on everything fmcg. With The Grocer Platinum Membership, experience the deepest level of fmcg market analysis with access to exclusive insightful editorial content; competitor intelligence; financial forecasting; price trend analysis; consumer testing and much more.\n\nThe Grocer Finance Membership\nOnline membership. The Grocer brings together insight and analysis to the financials from the fmcg market. Beyond the big names, The Grocer Finance Membership digs deeper. The Grocer is bigger and better than ever before – and now with The Grocer Finance Membership access competitive intelligence in the same place as all the news and analysis you need.\n\nThe Grocer Gold Membership\nOnline and Print. The Grocer is the leading fmcg brand bringing you the most up-to-date analysis, insights and research from the biggest industry in the UK. The Grocer Gold Membership provides total market coverage and will allow you to access information you simply won’t be able to get elsewhere. Access your membership however, wherever you want allowing you to make the most of your time. Not only can you read The Grocer in magazine format, but you can look at it online through your mobile or tablet whether you have a moment at work or at home.\n', '', '', ''),
(1809, 1, 'Mortgage Strategy', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMortgage Strategy is the first weekly intermediary title in the mortgage market. It is written for professional mortgage advisers.\n\nBecause it is published weekly, it can react to regulation issues, product launches, and industry moves, as and when they happen.\n', '', '', ''),
(1810, 1, 'Optician', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Optician magazine, which is the industry''s only weekly title. A subscription to Optician magazine brings you all the latest information first, with every single issue. As the leading publication covering the whole optical profession, a subscription to Optician magazine is essential reading and is dedicated to your professional development. Everyone with a subscription to Optician magazine will get our FREE approved CET programme giving you the opportunity to earn up to 50 points a year - all counting towards your continued registration. So now your subscription to Optician is more beneficial than ever before.\n', '', '', ''),
(1811, 1, 'Marketing Week', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Marketing Week Magazine?\n\nThis business management magazine gives you a weekly summary off all latest market trends, strategies and developments to keep you informed on international news. With your subscription to Marketing Week, you''ll read about important innovations, compelling case studies and diverse company strategies. You''ll also enjoy special reports, including the Salary Survey and the Content Marketing Essays Supplement, and unlimited access to marketingweek.co.uk. If you''re considering a change of role, you can take advantage of access to hundreds of marketing job advertisements with leading brands and agencies, as well as early invitations to great networking events like Market Week Live.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMarketing Week is the perfect magazine subscription for anyone who works or is interested in the world of marketing.Marketing Week delivers first hand news and in-depth analysis of the most significant shifts in major brands’ strategies, product launches, industry breakthroughs and key appointments and departures from all industry sectors. Every issue carries opinions by the most respected experts in the industry.A subscription to Marketing Week includes:•Weekly copies of the magazine direct to your desk.•Unlimited access to MarketingWeek.co.uk – breaking news, interactive features, trend reports and blogs.•Supplements and special reports throughout the year.•Hundreds of sector-by-sector marketing jobs in print &amp; online. •VIP invitations to marketing shows &amp; events including Marketing Week Live.Marketing Week is magazine for media, advertising, PR and marketing professionals. Bringing you all the information you need from the world of marketing.\n', '', '', ''),
(1812, 1, 'Music Week', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nData, insight and essential analysis Music Week has been the voice of the music business for more than 50 years. Now it is building on that legacy with a series of changes to ensure it provides a service for the needs of a rapidly evolving business. The emphasis of our work is on providing the information, insight and analysis essential to understanding the digital environment, today’s global market and fresh opportunities in live and recorded music. For unlimited access to Music Week and musicweek.com and other exclusive content, you now need to subscribe and there has never been a better time to subscribe to Music Week. Only subscribers receive exclusive access to: •Unlimited online access •Weekly print edition •A digital version sent to your inbox every Monday morning •The Music Week directory •Daily newsletter •Free iPad and iPhone apps •And other new media services Digital only package also available Digital Packages rates are inclusive of VAT.\n', '', '', ''),
(1813, 1, 'Pariscope', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPARISCOPE covers the current and forthcoming entertainment events in Paris over the next week, including theatre, music and films.\n', '', '', ''),
(1814, 1, 'Frau Im Spiegel', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFRAU IM SPIEGEL reports weekly about European royalty and celebrities as well as health, fashion, cosmetics and travel.\n', '', '', ''),
(1815, 1, 'Ici Paris', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nICI Paris is a colourful magazine on celebrity and entertainment. Each issue brings candid news and richly illustrated features on the rich and famous in France and abroad with interviews and columns.\n\nIn ICI Paris the contents also include ample sections on love, health and beauty, travel, cuisine and current issues. Core readership is young active women.\n', '', '', ''),
(1816, 1, 'Tele 7 Jours', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTELE 7 JOURS is a French television forecast magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(1817, 1, 'Voici', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVOICI is a French magazine of popular culture.\n', '', '', ''),
(1818, 1, 'Point De Vue', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPOINT DE VUE is a French weekly women''s magazine focused on current events, culture, fashion, relationships and entertainment.\n', '', '', ''),
(1819, 1, 'Paris Match', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nParis Match magazine is THE iconic French news and current affairs weekly periodical. Internationally renowned for it s coverage of major events, topical news stories and international personalities, a subscription to Paris Match magazine covers major national and international news along with celebrity lifestyle features.\n\nParis match magazine is the French alternative to OK! or Hello! magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(1820, 1, 'Marianne', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMARIANNE is a French language weekly magazine covering technology, global culture and politics, and the arts. Regular columns include reviews of books, music, and film, commentary and opinion, and readers'' letters.\n', '', '', ''),
(1821, 1, 'Vsd', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVSD is a French magazine which covers everything you need to know about the stars and our society. With VSD you''ll get documentations and reports which are always up-to-date.\n', '', '', ''),
(1822, 1, 'Public Fr', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPUBLIC (French) reports weekly about the stars out of rock, pop, film and tv.\n', '', '', ''),
(1823, 1, 'Jeune Afrique Lintellige', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nJEUNE AFRIQUE L''INTELLIGE is printed in French and covers African news in politics, economics, society and culture as well as sports and health.\n', '', '', ''),
(1824, 1, 'Courrier International', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCourrier International is not only a newspaper reference to originality concept, which reflects the best of e''stranere press.\n\nIt is a choice of openness, the confrontation of viewpoints invite for a ''more tolerance. With Courrier International, freedom of information makes sense, and it is a chance to enjoy The news without bias.\n', '', '', ''),
(1825, 1, 'Le Point', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLE POINT is a politic weekly magazine from France and offer reports on national and international politics.\n', '', '', ''),
(1826, 1, 'Femme Actuelle', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFEMME ACTUELLE, printed in French, is a women''s lifestyle magazine that covers diet, exercise, fashion, beauty, health and travel.\n', '', '', ''),
(1827, 1, 'Nouvel Observateur', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNOUVEL OBSERVATEUR presents the latest reports on politics, economy, culture, science and technique.\n', '', '', ''),
(1828, 1, 'Gala French', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGALA French magazine covers the latest news in film, music, concerts, television and other performances.\n', '', '', ''),
(1829, 1, 'Chi', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nChi is a women''s magazine, featuring stories, interviews, exclusive photographs and prestigious anticipations on the lives of the protagonists from the worlds of television, politics and sport, in a tone that avoids scandal and gossip.\n\nIt also pays a great deal of attention to the quality of photography and exclusive stories. Chi is one of the groundbreaking editorial formulas of recent years and has a constantly growing circulation\n\nFrom its launch, Chi established its position thanks to an original formula which, together with personalities in their &quot;natural surroundings&quot;, has consistently given space also to fashion and beauty\n', '', '', ''),
(1830, 1, 'Elle French', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nElle in French!\n', '', '', ''),
(1831, 1, 'Donna Moderna', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nItaly''s most successful women''s title, Donna Moderna, has been, since its launch 16 years ago, the absolute leader both in terms of circulation and readership.\n\nTogether with its two monthly supplements, Casa Idea and Donna In Forma, and a special supplement Donna in Cucina it is the leading women''s weekly for advertising revenues.\n\nThe service-based editorial formula features variety and completeness, quality journalism and makes the magazine the preferred choice of dynamic, curious and modern women.In Italian.\n', '', '', ''),
(1832, 1, 'Das Neue Blatt', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDAS NEUE BLATT reports weekly about European royalty and celebrities as well as health, cooking, fashion, travel, and better living.\n', '', '', ''),
(1833, 1, 'Neue Post', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNEUE POST is a German language women''s weekly covering celebrity lives, interviews, crosswords, holiday destinations, health and fitness, flower arranging, horoscopes, recipes to tantalise your tastebuds, fantastic fashion spreads, creative ideas to give character to your home and more!\n', '', '', ''),
(1834, 1, 'Freizeit Woche', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe weekly FREIZEIT WOCHE informes on current news reports and interviews on national and international celebrities from the show, music, film and television business, and presents exciting stories and background reports from the European noble houses. Particularly extensive is the competent service and advice with a focus on sub-health, travel and cooking. Informative and to the point are also advice pages on the subject of fashion, financial, legal and daily life guidance.\n', '', '', ''),
(1835, 1, 'Tina', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe German womens weekly magazine\n', '', '', ''),
(1836, 1, 'Kicker Montag', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nKICKER covers everything you need to know about the Bundesliga matches.\n', '', '', ''),
(1837, 1, 'Bunte', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBUNTE is the German weekly magazine covering the newest information on celebrities, gossip, news and lifestyle.\n', '', '', ''),
(1838, 1, 'Gala German', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGALA German is an ambitious womens magazine which focuses on celebrities and has a great picture quality in a large format.\n', '', '', ''),
(1839, 1, 'Focus German', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFOCUS (GERMAN) is one of the largest news magazines in Germany. Focus is well known for its colour images and use of information graphics. The special style of journalism is perfect for readers short of time.\n', '', '', ''),
(1840, 1, 'Der Spiegel', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDer Spiegel is a German weekly magazine and has been similarly compared to the American publications Time and Newsweek.\n\nWith a weekly circulation of more than one million, Der Speigel has a reputation for its superior journalism, academic writing style, and a tendency to challenge those in power, keeping its finger on the pulse of current politics.\n\nWith exposés on anything from Germany''s history to the Catholic church, Der Spiegel is one of the most respected and influential magazines of its kind in the world.\n', '', '', ''),
(1841, 1, 'Stern', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSTERN is one of Germany s largest weekly news magazines. STERN''s strongpoint is the extraordinary journalism and the classic reports, as well as its picture series and the celebrity reports.\n', '', '', ''),
(1842, 1, 'Die Zeit Weekly', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDIE ZEIT Weekly is Germany s largest weekly liberal newspaper and reports on politics, dossier, economy, knowledge and sciences, feuilleton, literature, life (style) and traveling.\n', '', '', ''),
(1843, 1, 'Telepiu It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTELEPIU is an Italian magazine which covers everything you need to know about television, TV forecast and news.\n', '', '', ''),
(1844, 1, 'Domenica Quiz', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDomenica Quiz is packed full of all the usual cross-words, anagram games and word-searches.\n\nA useful way to get those dusty neurons firing in the morning, and more than enough to keep you going through a few espresso breaks.\n\nAlternatively, if you are a student of the Italian language this would make a great alternative or complimentry method to enjoy learning the language by playing with the letters.\n', '', '', ''),
(1845, 1, 'La Settimana Enigmistico', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLA SETTIMANA ENIGMISTICO, a well-known Italian magazine that features crossword puzzles, vocabulary tests, cartoons and a variety of other linguistic brain-teasers.\n', '', '', ''),
(1846, 1, 'Nuova Cronaca Vera', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNUOVA CRONACA VERA reports on the life and stories from the reader as well as tragic experiences. In addition it offers horoscopes, TV forecast and a whole lot more.\n', '', '', ''),
(1847, 1, 'Novella 2000', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNOVELLA 2000 is a womens magazine with interesting celebrity interviews.\n', '', '', ''),
(1848, 1, 'Confidenze', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nConfidenze magazine is an Italian woman’s weekly that brings you the latest in entertainment and current affairs in a fresh, light-hearted tone that any woman will enjoy.\n\nWith articles on all kinds of subjects, from the importance of exercising regularly and why it’s quite a challenge, to why Richard Gere must be loved by all.\n\nConfidenze magazine is one of many magazines aimed at your enjoyment in those rare moments of downtime for the busy woman. .\n', '', '', ''),
(1849, 1, 'Visto', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVISTO (ITALY) is targeted at the wider public, featuring entertainment, educational and practical topics with several sections of family interest written by famous show-business personalities.\n', '', '', ''),
(1850, 1, 'Sorrisi Canzoni', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nItalian language TV listings.\n', '', '', ''),
(1851, 1, 'Il Mondo', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIL MONDO is an Italian magazine supplement to Corriere della Sera and a highly authoritative source of information on the performance of the Italian economy, offering a complete panorama of the main events and players.\n', '', '', ''),
(1852, 1, 'Intimita', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nINTIMITA is a weekly women''s magazine with articles on fashion, cosmetics, family and health.\n', '', '', ''),
(1853, 1, 'Grand Hotel It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGRAND HOTEL (Italy) informs you about the life of the stars and is pure entertainment. It also offers picture stories as well as the latest recipes and a weekly television programme listing.\n', '', '', ''),
(1854, 1, 'Tu Style', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTU Style is the magazine for young woman, educated, lively, demanding and interested in news, shows and fashion topics. TU Style reaches out to its readers, with news, stories of ordinary women and face to face interviews with celebrities. Column after column dedicated to fashion, health, beauty and travel. It''s a magazine in accordance with today''s needs.\n', '', '', ''),
(1855, 1, 'Gente', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGENTE is a weekly Italian magazine with articles on politics, current times and culture.\n', '', '', ''),
(1856, 1, 'Oggi It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA best selling weekly from italy\n', '', '', ''),
(1857, 1, 'Dipiu It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAn Italian womens weekly\n', '', '', ''),
(1858, 1, 'Grazia It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nGRAZIA (IT) is Italy''s most prestigious women''s weekly magazine. Known as a reference point for style and journalistic quality, it is mainly aimed at educated, elegant and refined women. It offers supplements including Casa, Accessory and Fragrances as well as features from top Italian designers.\n', '', '', ''),
(1859, 1, 'Vanity Fair Italian', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVANITY FAIR (ITALIAN) is packed with 240 pages of Italian celebrities. All the shoots are natural and approved by the celebrities. Photos are by Mario Testino. Over 1 million investment has been spent on the advertising and launch of VANITY FAIR (ITALIAN).\n', '', '', ''),
(1860, 1, 'Starbene It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSTARBENE is an Italian-language magazine focused on health issues, including diet, exercise, cooking, and proper relaxation.\n', '', '', ''),
(1861, 1, 'Panorama It', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nPANORAMA (Italy) Italy''s leading newsmagazine providing readers with relevant background information and news around the world. It covers politics, arts, economics, as well as lifestyle and leisure.\n', '', '', ''),
(1862, 1, 'Diez Minutos', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDIEZ MINUTOS is a Spanish language weekly womens internet magazine. It covers news and international celebrities such as Brooke Shields, Jennifer Lopez, Carmen Electra, Drew Barrymore, Tony Santos, Alvaro de Marichalar and many more. It provides readers with all the gossip from the celebrity world, interviews, health and fitness advice, fashion spreads, recipes, fim reviews, crosswords, holiday destinations, horoscopes and more!\n', '', '', ''),
(1863, 1, 'Semana', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSEMANA is a women''s weekly magazine. Inside readers will find interviews with celebrities, star style, star lives, recipe ideas, fashion styles straight from the catwalk, fashion accessory ideas, beauty products and advice, health tips, film, video, book and music reviews, horoscopes, crosswords and other puzzles. You''ll find all this and more inside every issue of SEMANA!\n', '', '', ''),
(1864, 1, 'New Yorker', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nNEW YORKER is aimed at artistic, well-educated and astute readers who have the desire to gain a wider understanding of current affairs.\n\nThe emphasis is less on theory and more on real life with the added flavour of culture and the arts.\n', '', '', ''),
(1865, 1, 'Closer French', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFrench version of the popular UK womens weekly.\n', '', '', ''),
(1866, 1, 'Us Weekly', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nUS WEEKLY is a celebrity gossip magazine, featuring all the latest news from within the entertainment world. Each issue uncovers scandal, interviews, great pictures and more!\n', '', '', ''),
(1867, 1, 'The Hollywood Reporter', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe world''s most complete entertainment and information source for the film industry, HOLLYWOOD REPORTER provides news and in-depth national and international articles. Includes profiles and specialised features essential to industry professionals around the world. THE HOLLYWOOD REPORTER provides readers with a real insight to Hollywood life. It gives an in-depth view of all things movie related, whether it be interviews with film driectors and actors, looking at what''s in production, shooting venues, what''s on at the box office and gossip from inside the industry. THE HOLLYWOOD REPORTER doesn''t miss a trick and is your ultimate guide to life in Hollywood.\n', '', '', ''),
(1868, 1, 'Billboard', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Billboard magazine is a newsweekly subscription that is completely devoted to the music industry. Billboard magazine is especially famous for its music charts that track both the most popular songs and albums in a wide variety of categories each week. A Billboard magazine subscription also includes features on all the latest news and reviews from inside the music industry. This subscription is great for anyone with a real interest in music and the music industry.\n', '', '', ''),
(1869, 1, 'Variety', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nVariety is the bible of the showbiz industry. Whether it''s film or television, music or radio, interactive media or publishing, Variety delivers unparalleled insight into the fast aced world of entertainment. Variety is recognised throughout the world as the entertainment industry''s newspaper of record. Variety covers the global media and entertainment marketplace in 84 countries, including the major entertainment capitals - Los Angeles, New York, London, Paris, Tokyo and Rome. With its seasoned editorial team and the largest news gathering staff in the industry, Variety delivers breaking news, exclusive scoops, box office reports, and film and TV production charts. Variety provides an insider''s perspective on the latest developments and trends in film, television and music with concise, provocative insight.\n', '', '', ''),
(1870, 1, 'Eastern Eye', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWHY SHOULD YOU SUBSCRIBE TO EASTERN EYE?\n\nDon''t go without it, be sharp, be informed, understand the world we live in ...every week ...\n\nAn invaluable source of news, sport, information and entertainment ...only in Eastern Eye.\n\nHard-hitting exclusive news stories that set, shape and reflect the British Asian community.\n\nThe best, biggest and “baddest” from the world of Bollywood. An unrivalled focus on the stories that shake, make and break the Bollywood bubble. You cannot be without EE''s unique take and breath of coverage.\n\nThe best sports coverage with exclusives from British Asian sports stars and the inside track on the stories making it big on the sub-continent. No South Asian sports fan can afford to be without it.\n\nBusiness that matters: here, there and everywhere. A spotlight on the entrepreneurial, the markets and how the economic order is changing.\n\nEntertainment and fashion – no one covers it like we do, week-in-week out – read about the stars of today, tomorrow and yesteryear and the styles of the week.\n\nFor the news and feature stories that matter on the subcontinent – all the news you need to know.\n\nRead our brilliant columnists who have privileged access to some of the most exclusive events and personalities in Britain today.\n', '', '', ''),
(1871, 1, 'Lexpress', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nL''EXPRESS is a French magazine and reports weekly about the latest news on French and world politics.\n', '', '', ''),
(1872, 1, 'Les Inrockuptibles', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLES INROCKTIBLES is a French magazine which covers everything you need to know about culture.\n', '', '', ''),
(1873, 1, 'Woman''S Weekly', '&lt;p&gt;FROM THE PUBLISHER Get a subscription Woman''s Weekly, the magazine that celebrates the home, family and lives of grown-up women, providing you with expert health advice and the know-how on how to feel fantastic whatever your age. Woman’s Weekly magazine inspires you to get creative with irresistible cookery, fantastic home, gardening and craft ideas. With fiction you can’t put down and heart-warming real life, a subscription to Woman’s Weekly magazine guarantees hours of great reading every week. Take out a subscription today and get Woman''s Weekly delivered direct to your door and never miss an issue! The arrival of your Woman’s Weekly magazine subscription is always a cause for celebration. Each issue is full of practical and positive ways to live a better, healthier life. When you get a subscription to Women’s Weekly magazine, you will enjoy page upon thrilling page of inspirational ideas, with wonderful recipes to try, great fashion tips and ways to get creative around the house and garden. As well as all this, there is expert health advice too - covering diet and exercise, and the medical conditions our readers want to know about. And if all of that wasn’t enough, you can also settle back with a good short story or two, as well as share the real life experiences of women with their own amazing stories to tell. If you think every week deserves a Woman’s Weekly magazine, then don’t hesitate, get a subscription today!&lt;/p&gt;\n', '', '', ''),
(1874, 1, 'Time', 'TIME ALL ACCESS – Enjoy the print magazine, iPad® edition and subscriber-only content on TIME.com including the 20th century archive. TIME, the world’s most respected weekly news magazine, is trusted by over 23 million readers for its insightful and reliable reporting on global events, politics, business, finance, technology, education and more. TIME speaks authoritatively on important issues, interest and concerns in Asia and the world. In today’s fast paced environment, TIME provides a clear, concise and forward-looking take on the world, allowing you to make the most of your TIME.\n\nTIME publishes six double issues. Each counts as two of 52 issues in an annual subscription. TIME may also publish occasional extra Issues.\n\niPad® is a registered trademark of Apple Inc. registered in the US and other countries. ', '', '', ''),
(1875, 1, 'Open', '&lt;p&gt;Open, is a weekly current affairs &amp;amp; features magazine. Open aims at addressing the needs of evolved Indian readers who are well-informed, well-traveled and identify themselves as global citizens. Open wants to redefine the way the news, perspective and insights are presented to these readers&lt;/p&gt;\n', '', '', ''),
(1876, 1, 'Outlook', '&lt;p&gt;Outlook, a weekly news magazine headed by Vinod Mehta, galvanized a sluggish market reeling under the impact of satellite TV. Outlook quickly carved a significant niche for itself among discerning readers who value its in-depth, investigative reporting as well as its stylish visual format. Known to be fiercely independent, Outlook has shaken the establishment on events ranging from Kargil to Kashmir to cricket, sensitized the reading public to important issues like big dams, education and gender, and provided an unremitting focus on South Asian geopolitics.&lt;/p&gt;\n', '', '', ''),
(1877, 1, 'Tehelka', 'Tehelka is an iconic media house and the fastest growing English weekly magazine in India. It is independent, fearless and stands strongly for public interest journalism. It has very quickly established an enviable reputation — national and international — for the quality of its reportage, the eminence of its writers and the refinement of its analyses and ideas.', '', '', ''),
(1878, 1, 'India Today', 'India Today has covered India developments without fear or favour, with insight, accuracy, thoroughness and a well rounded perspective on a variety of subjects - be it the economy, politics, lifestyle, the arts, entertainment, travel, science, technology or health. India Today is the country''s most widely read publication, a position it has held for more than a decade. And these are just some reasons to subscribe to India Today!', '', '', ''),
(1879, 1, 'The Week', 'The Week  is the largest selling General Interest English Magazine in the country. The Week brings out the truth behind stories. Perspectives unseen. Paths never taken. THE WEEK goes that extra mile to help you see news in a new light. The stories we covered didn''t just create a buzz across the nation, but won various prestigious awards for uncovering the truth behind them. Thus proving that journalism with a human touch is truly rewarding .', '', '', ''),
(1880, 1, 'India Today - Hindi', 'India Today has covered India developments without fear or favour, with insight, accuracy, thoroughness and a well rounded perspective on a variety of subjects - be it the economy, politics, lifestyle, the arts, entertainment, travel, science, technology or health. India Today is the country''s most widely read publication, a position it has held for more than a decade. And these are just some reasons to subscribe to India Today!', '', '', ''),
(1881, 1, 'India Today - Malayalam', 'India Today has covered India developments without fear or favour, with insight, accuracy, thoroughness and a well rounded perspective on a variety of subjects - be it the economy, politics, lifestyle, the arts, entertainment, travel, science, technology or health. India Today is the country''s most widely read publication, a position it has held for more than a decade. And these are just some reasons to subscribe to India Today!', '', '', ''),
(1882, 1, 'India Today - Tamil', 'India Today has covered India developments without fear or favour, with insight, accuracy, thoroughness and a well rounded perspective on a variety of subjects - be it the economy, politics, lifestyle, the arts, entertainment, travel, science, technology or health. India Today is the country''s most widely read publication, a position it has held for more than a decade. And these are just some reasons to subscribe to India Today!', '', '', ''),
(1883, 1, 'India Today - Telugu', 'India Today has covered India developments without fear or favour, with insight, accuracy, thoroughness and a well rounded perspective on a variety of subjects - be it the economy, politics, lifestyle, the arts, entertainment, travel, science, technology or health. India Today is the country''s most widely read publication, a position it has held for more than a decade. And these are just some reasons to subscribe to India Today!', '', '', ''),
(1884, 1, 'Gujarat Samachar', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nUK''s favourite newsweeklies delivered to your doorstep. Are you a subscriber to Gujarat Samachar? If not, here are a few compelling reasons why you should:\n\n40 pages of the most comprehensive, in-depth and unique coverage across the UK, India, Asia and the rest of the World.\n\n\nWe take great caret cater to a wide target audience- male, female, young and old. There is something for the entire family.\n\n\nOur popular periodic theme based special issues are unmatched by any other title in the market. And you will receive them free of charge!\n\n\nWe are committed to a number of unique community events which receive wide publicity in our titles. This title is written in Gujarati ', '', '', ''),
(1885, 1, 'Asian Voice', 'FROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nUK''s favourite newsweeklies delivered to your doorstep. Are you a subscriber to Asian Voice? If not, here are a few compelling reasons why you should:\n\n32 pages of the most comprehensive, in-depth and unique coverage across the UK, India, Asia and the rest of the World.\n\n\nWe take great care to cater to a wide target audience- male, female, young and old. There is something for the entire family.\n\n\nOur popular periodic theme-based special issues are unmatched by any other title in the market. And you will receive them free of charge!\n\n\nWe are committed to a number of unique community events which receive wide publicity in our titles. ', '', '', ''),
(1886, 1, 'New Statesman', 'WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO New Statesman Magazine?\n\nA subscription to New Statesman magazine will give you an informative breakdown of the issues that matter to you, with feature pieces and commentary on the biggest political and economic stories of the week.\n\nYou can stay ahead of the curve with contemporary debates and leading analysis, as well as regular updates on developing news items. You''ll also find a progressive attitude from the publication''s award-winning journalists, who come together to bring you everything from independent political opinion to reviews of the latest films, theatre debuts and artistic masterpieces.  \n\nThere''s also an active online blog, exclusive subscriber-only events and lively comment pages to keep you entertained in between issues.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe New Statesman is Britain’s leading, most elegant and best written weekly political, cultural and current affairs magazine. The magazine''s award winning team of editors and contributors seek to engage readers with great writing, arresting photography, intelligent analysis, bold campaigns and trenchant argument. The New Statesman magazines provocative and acclaimed reports, columns and essays explore the issues that lead our national conversation, from politics to economics, the arts to sport. Every issue is celebrated for its progressive politics, boldness, independence and scepticism. Reading the New Statesman puts you right at the heart of the debate. The New Statesman is essential reading for anyone interested in the news that matters. Subscribe to the New Statesman magazine today and save up to 52% on the cover price!\n', '', '', ''),
(1887, 1, 'The Weekly News', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The Weekly News Newspapers?\n\nA subscription to The Weekly News guarantees you real-life dramas, celebrity interviews, an in-depth guide to the latest TV shows and films, up-to-the-minute medical news, puzzles, prize competitions, cartoons, gardening, short stories, top sports coverage and much, much more.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to The Weekly News guarantees you real-life dramas, celebrity interviews, an in-depth guide to the latest TV shows and films, up-to-the-minute medical news, puzzles, prize competitions, cartoons, gardening, short stories, top sports coverage and much, much more.\n', '', '', ''),
(1888, 1, 'The Sunday Post', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The Sunday Post Newspapers?\n\nUK’s favourite choice for every Sunday - Save time and money subscribing to the Newspaper of the Year! You’ll get views, travel, real life stories, showbiz, sport and Scotland news delivered to your door. Now including fantastic TV &amp; celebrity supplements!\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nUK’s favourite choice for every Sunday - Save time and money subscribing to the Newspaper of the Year! You’ll get views, travel, real life stories, showbiz, sport and Scotland news delivered to your door. Now including fantastic TV &amp; celebrity supplements!\n', '', '', ''),
(1889, 1, 'First News', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO First News Magazine?\n\nThis award-winning publication is perfect for introducing your child to the world of news. Your kids will find hundreds of real-life news stories, all written in an easy to follow and engaging style. Topics include politics, education, and science, as well as plenty of fun articles on everything from animals to entertainment. What''s more, your child can enter a number of exciting competitions, and even try writing their very own article. A First News subscription comes complete with free access to the paper''s exclusive online environment, giving your child even more fun-filled content to help stimulate their minds.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nWinner of the Weekly National Newspaper of the Year award and Niche Market Newspaper of the Yearaward at the 2012 Newspaper Awards!\n\nA subscription to First News is a must-have for children aged 7-14.\n\nThe award-winning weekly newspaper is produced in a traditional, full colour, tabloid newspaper format, First News opens children’s minds to the issues of today, informing, entertaining and stimulating them to take an active interest in the world around them.\n\nIn 24 fun and vibrant pages, First News features a blend of stories about world and home affairs, the environment, sports, entertainment and puzzles - all selected to engage young minds. It’s fun design brings the stories to life, and competitions and a sprinkling of celebrities hold the reader’s attention from cover to cover.\n\nNowhere else can you find all the important stories in an easy and digestible format, in a voice aimed at inquisitive children – the very children who in turn will grow up to be the country’s great communicators.\n\nFirst News was launched in 2006 by editorial director Piers Morgan and has since has become the widest read weekly children’s publication in the UK.\n\nWhat the parents say:\n\n&quot;Responsible, informative and fun – my daughter loves it!&quot;\n\n&quot;Presents the news without dumbing down and is enjoyed by all the family.&quot;\n\n&quot;Great news for children without the hysteria of modern media outlets\n\nWhat the children say:\n\n&quot;It’s a newspaper that I can understand&quot;\n\n‘Getting a subscription to First News was the best present I got! I love it because it makes me feel very grown up.’\n\n''I love First News because they tell you news first before anyone else and they tell facts about technology, hospitals, around the world and space''\n', '', '', ''),
(1890, 1, 'The Phoenix', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The Phoenix Magazine?\n\nThis exciting magazine is a great choice for children of all ages, with colourful story strips and magical characters just waiting to surprise and delight them every week. The Phoenix magazine is more than just a comic book, with 32 pages of imaginative stories and engaging non-fiction pieces, as well as puzzles and full-text stories for kids who are curious to learn more about the world. It''s a children’s magazine with a difference, aiming to get their imaginations racing and inspire their creative side. There''s also fresh stories and new characters every week, making sure that your inquisitive child is constantly entertained.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\n“Children will love The Phoenix - and Mums and Dads will doubtless want to sneak a peek too.” Dame Jacqueline Wilson.\n\nThe Phoenix is the brand new weekly story comic for children! Packed full of new, original and sensational story-strips, The Phoenix will have children trembling with excitement every week!\n\nNow if there’s one thing that we all know from school, it’s that cats make the best editors and pigs simply ADORE comics, which is why The Phoenix is run by feline Editor in Chief Tabs Inkspot and assistant editor Chops Piggerton. These two, along with a crack team of comic creating creatures, ensure that each weekly issue of The Phoenix is filled with the most exciting, thrilling, magical and moving story-strips!\n\nThink of The Phoenix as a TV studio – ‘transmitting’ all kinds of wonderful stories that include everything from Pirates and dinosaurs, bleach haired boys with talking crows and even the odd deep space adventure. There are serials with meaty plots and epic settings, one-off thrillers to be swallowed whole and oodles of others strips too. All are stonkingly-good fun!\n\nEvery week with a subscription to the Phoenix children can expect to quiver with anticipation, as their copy will fly through the letterbox in its own unique Phoenix envelope. Each issue offers an exciting, quality and most importantly fun reading experience which will not only fire children’s imaginations and excite their interests but can inspire their creativity too.\n\nA subscription to The Phoenix will offer you 32 pages of unparalleled story excitement every week including epic adventures, comedy, non-fiction, puzzles and even full text stories.\n', '', '', '');
