(1891, 1, 'Estates Gazette', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEvery week Estates Gazette provides an overview of the commercial property market that is second to none. For over 150 years it has been essential reading for commercial property professionals who recognise the value of its broad coverage, incisive commentary and accurate data. Our award winning magazine offers you: •In-depth commercial property information including financial deals and advice, funds information, economic commentary, commercial property jobs and more. •Special commercial property supplements and in-depth features delving deeper into the issues that affect your profits, from retail to finance. •Detailed analysis of the people, firms and legal cases driving change in commercial property – so you always know what’s happening, why, and what that means for your property business. “The new look Estates Gazette is great. Contemporary, easy to read and providing tremendous insight into our market. A vital tool, reflective of our ever changing and sophisticated industry.” Martin Samworth, managing Director, CB Richard Ellis Ltd\n', '', '', ''),
(1892, 1, 'New Scientist', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO New Scientist Magazine?\n\nEach issue of this fascinating science and nature magazine is packed full of detailed and insightful articles that delve deeper into the scientific developments that matter, as well as a number of entertaining opinion pieces and honest reader letters.\n\nA New Scientist magazine subscription gives you a weekly update across a range of different subject matters, with everything from climate change to the big bang explained and critiqued by a team of expert journalists, all in an easy-to-follow format that makes staying informed a pleasure.\n\nYou''ll also get access to the exclusive online environment, featuring lively blogs and a comprehensive jobs section giving you an in-road into a career in science or technology.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA New Scientist magazine subscription will keep you up-to-date with the latest scientific and technological news, innovations and ideas in the exciting, ever-changing world of science - from the wonderful, the worrying, to the downright weird. New Scientist is the world´s leading science and technology weekly magazine. With in-depth articles, cogent analysis and informed, entertaining comment, New Scientist is essential reading if you really want to get behind the headlines. Every issue advertises hundreds of jobs in science from all around the world. Founded in 1956, New Scientist now has UK, US and Australian editions and is read by both scientists and non-scientists, as a way of keeping track of developments outside their own fields of study or areas of interest. The magazine also regularly includes features, news and commentary on environmental issues, such as climate change. With a subscription to New Scientist you can also enjoy FREE unlimited access to the entire content of NewScientist.com - including breaking news, features, blogs and archived articles.\n', '', '', ''),
(1893, 1, 'Match', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Match Magazine?\n\nYou''ll love the posters, quizzes and jokes inside each issue of Match magazine, as well as the brilliant skills pages and trick guides to help you improve your game and impress your friends on the pitch. Each issue comes with exclusive photos and match previews of the weekend''s upcoming fixtures, plus interviews with some of the biggest names in football. You''ll also find unrivalled coverage of the UK''s Premier and Football Leagues in a Match magazine subscription, in addition to a comprehensive run down of the top players to watch and crunch matches of the weekend ahead.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA Match magazine subscription is essential for the football enthusiast! MATCH magazine gives you the complete rundown on the Premier league every week guaranteeing you all the latest news, results and reports on YOUR favourite team. Each week MATCH magazine provides reader’s with MATCHFACTS detailing the teams, scorers and rating of every team in both the Premier and Nationwide leagues. Plus, all the latest pictures and football related news YOU WANT TO READ. The Direct Debit Guarantee The minimum subscription term for the direct debit offer is 12 months. The amount paid by Direct Debit may change over time. If and when it does you will be notified in advance by at least 10 days. If an error is made by Bauer Media Ltd or by bank/building society, you are entitled to a full and immediate refund. You can cancel the Direct Debit at any time by writing to your bank/building society and send a copy to Bauer Media Ltd at: Magazine Subscriptions, Tower House, Sovereign Park, Market Harborough, Leicestershire LE94 7ZT. Please note that banks and building societies may not accept Direct Debit instructions from some types of account.\n', '', '', ''),
(1894, 1, 'Angler''S Mail', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Angler''s Mail Magazine?\n\nRecreational coarse fishermen will love an Angler’s Mail magazine subscription, with plenty of top tips for tweaking your technique and improving the size of your catch. In addition to reviews of the latest fishing equipment and news on competitions and match results, you''ll also find advice on the best fishing spots in the country. This top mag also caters to carp and pike specialists, with the low down on the best tackle and bait, plus instructional articles helping you to improve your game. You''ll love the vibrant letters section which gives the angling community the chance to voice their views, as well as the “Tales from the Riverbank”, where keen fishermen write about their latest adventures.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCatch Angler’s Mail - Britain’s brightest weekly fishing magazine. The latest news coverage on the biggest fish caught - and where to catch them. Reviews of the latest tackle and the best advice for the Carp hunter. Match fishing results. Indispensable instruction features. Improve your fishing skills and be entertained. Every issue of your subscription to Angler’s Mail magazine includes news coverage on the biggest fish caught - and where to catch them - along with match fishing results, instruction features, reviews of the latest tackle and the best advice for the Carp hunter. First published in 1964 by Echo Publications, today’s incarnation of Angler’s Mail magazine is published by IPC Media and comes out every Tuesday. The magazine covers aspects of modern coarse fishing, and contains news, reviews, features and great true stories! Take out a subscription to Angler’s Mail to improve your fishing skills and be entertained. Three great reasons to take out a subscription: -never miss a single issue -delivery direct to your door every week -earn fantastic savings Don’t miss out – get your subscription today!\n', '', '', ''),
(1895, 1, 'Boxing News', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nTake out a subscription to Boxing News magazine - the longest running boxing magazine, dating back to 1909.\n\nA subscription to Boxing News magazine provides the sport with unmatched coverage to keep fight fans and industry figures up to date with the latest news, previews, reports and opinions in boxing, straight to your door every week. Published every Thursday we provide definitive coverage meaning that a subscription to Boxing News magazine is the only magazine that you will ever need.\n', '', '', ''),
(1896, 1, 'Shooting Times &amp; Country', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Shooting Times &amp; Country Magazine?\n\nYou can make sure you’re getting all of the latest news from the shooting world as and when it happens with a subscription to this brilliant weekly magazine.\n\nShooting Times &amp; Country has played an important part in rural affairs for years, so if you want to get behind country causes in your area, this is the perfect way to do so.\n\nWith your subscription, you''ll be able to read reviews of new equipment, get expert shooting advice, and tips on training an obedient guide dog. All the features are illustrated beautifully with some amazing photographic shots of dogs, hunts and landscapes, making this magazine visually impressive as well as a great read.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nShooting Times &amp; Country Magazine has been at the forefront of the shooting scene for over 125 years. Shooting Times is the clear first choice for shooting sportsmen, with editorial covering all disciplines, including game, rough and stalking. Shooting Times &amp; Country Magazine''s involvement in its community includes attendance at many country fairs and acting as a voice within the countryside movement. Shooting Times and Country Magazine is one of the oldest and best selling titles which cover all aspects of shooting. Published by IPC Media, the magazine reaches you every week packed full essential news and information regarding the sport of shooting. This magazine includes all latest happenings, authoritative and independent reviews, in depth and informative features, exclusive and interesting profiles, essential advice and top tips, and lots more. Along with all this high quality content, the magazine comes with stunning photographs that are attractive and thoroughly interesting.\n', '', '', ''),
(1897, 1, 'Motorsport News', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Motorsport News Magazine?\n\nEach issue of this motorsport magazine brings you a roundup of the week''s action from the world of motor racing.\n\nFocusing predominantly on British motorsport, this mag also offers coverage of the international F1 circuit and the World Rally Championship, alongside karting news from closer to home. If you subscribe to Motorsport News you''ll get expert comment and opinion pieces on current issue in the Motorsport world, and keep up-to-date with upcoming events with the weekly &quot;What''s On&quot; diary.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMotorsport News is the first with the news, views and reports and is the voice of British motorsport and a must-read for all motorsport fans. Britain''s only weekly motorsport newspaper, Motorsport News delivers up-to-date, entertaining and reliable news, reports and results.\nWith a strong focus on the British racing and rallying scenes, it''s the essential companion for all motorsport fans. Motorsport News magazine is the best and leading weekly motor sport magazine in Britain. Published by Haymarket Publishing Services Ltd it provides its readers with all essential news and information from the world of motor sports. This magazine is a must read for all motor sport enthusiasts.\n\nShould you wish to cancel your subscription it will be cancelled on expiry of the current term which will not be refundable, other than in exceptional circumstances.\nThe issues you receive during this trial period are covered by your first Direct Debit payment. You can cancel the subscription (your next Direct Debit payment) at any time during this trial period. However, once the 2nd payment has been claimed from your bank account, should you wish to cancel your subscription it will be cancelled on expiry of the current term.\n', '', '', ''),
(1898, 1, 'Autocar', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Autocar Magazine?\n\nWith an Autocar magazine subscription you''ll get a high-octane mixture of news, features and reviews, with compelling articles on everything from the latest supercars to economical family run-arounds.\n\nAutocar offers regular scoops and insider information, printing photographs of the latest models still in the testing phase and previews of upcoming concept cars.\n\nPlus, you''ll find coverage of a wide range of motorsports including Formula 1 and British Touring Cars. Should you wish to cancel your subscription it will be cancelled on expiry of the current term which will not be refundable, other than in exceptional circumstances. The issues you receive during this trial period are covered by your first Direct Debit payment. You can cancel the subscription (your next Direct Debit payment) at any time during this trial period. However, once the 2nd payment has been claimed from your bank account, should you wish to cancel your subscription it will be cancelled on expiry of the current term.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAutocar is the car nut''s weekly fix, delivering a unique mix of the latest news, opinion, features, first drives of new cars and in-depth road tests - all complemented by the best photography in the business.From Ferraris and Lamborghinis through to the latest electric and hydrogen-powered superminis, Autocar is obsessed with cars and the industry that makes them.No other magazine covers the subject with such enthusiasm, insight and quality every week of the year.\n', '', '', ''),
(1899, 1, 'Autosport', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Autosport Magazine?\n\nMake sure that you''re always up-to-date with the latest racing action with a weekly subscription to Autosport magazine. Whether you’re a fan of F1, MotoGP or the World Rally Championship, Autosport has you covered with current news, opinions and technical analysis from a wide range of competitions. This weekly motorsport magazine brings you the top stories from on and off the track and takes a look at how key issues affect the drivers, the fans and the growth of the sport. As well as reports of key races from the past week, you''ll also find detailed previews and track guides for upcoming events.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEvery week, AUTOSPORT magazine keeps you up to speed with everything that''s happening in the world of motorsport with world-class news, reports, interviews and analysis\n\nFor more than 60 years AUTOSPORT has been providing comprehensive coverage of national and international motorsport events from around the globe, keeping you in touch with everything on and off the track.\n\nShould you wish to cancel your subscription it will be cancelled on expiry of the current term which will not be refundable, other than in exceptional circumstances.\nThe issues you receive during this trial period are covered by your first Direct Debit payment. You can cancel the subscription (your next Direct Debit payment) at any time during this trial period. However, once the 2nd payment has been claimed from your bank account, should you wish to cancel your subscription it will be cancelled on expiry of the current term.\n', '', '', ''),
(1900, 1, 'Classic Car Buyer', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nFor those who love classic cars – owning, buying, driving, restoring – Classic Car Buyer is the most informative read there is. Published every Wednesday it keeps readers up-to-date with the very latest classic car and club news, follows the important issues affecting this popular market and has pages and pages of buying, owning and practical features. The classic car market remains buoyant and readers can track the latest prices with regular auction reports, along with the weekly Free Ads section that’s packed with 100s of cars and parts for sale. This is truly the best place to buy and sell classic cars.\n\nIf it’s happening in the classic car world, it’s happening in Classic Car Buyer – every week.\n', '', '', ''),
(1901, 1, 'Angling Times', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Angling Times Magazine?\n\nAs one of the most successful weekly fishing magazines in the UK, Angling Times will provide you with up to the minute news updates on a whole range of fishing styles, competitions and venues, as well as all the latest stories, equipment reviews and bait guides to keep you informed and entertained each week.You''ll also find stunning photography from fishing events across the UK, plus money-saving tips for your next angling holiday and vouchers for the best bait and equipment shops in the country.There''s also seasonal free gifts, enjoyable competitions and exciting features helping you to make the most out of the sport you love.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBritain’s biggest-selling fishing weekly delivers exclusive, cutting edge stories and tactics from the sport’s most important fish captures. Specimen, carp, predator, sea and game – every significant fish will hit the headlines.\n\nWe’ve also got a dedicated team of writers bringing you the week’s money-saving deals from the nation’s fisheries, tackle shops and holiday companies.\n\nIf you money’s tight this year we’ll get you a bargain. Plus now includes new sections; bargain hunter, under a tenner, last minute holiday offers, and 2 for 1 deals at fisheries and tackle shop tokens.\n\nEvery week we’ll be dedicated to bringing you the best competitions - giving away all the hottest new launches on the market.\n', '', '', ''),
(1902, 1, 'Horse &amp; Hound', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nHorse &amp; Hound is Britain''s equestrian weekly ''Bible''. It offers comprehensive news, events coverage and in-depth reports from top writers across the major equestrian disciplines, accompanied by the best photography and extensive classified section, every week. Horse &amp; Hound magazine offers comprehensive news, events coverage and in-depth reports from top writers across all the major equestrian disciplines, accompanied by the best photography, every week. Horse &amp; Hound magazine features an extensive classified section covering every equestrian requirement, including jobs, property and a huge number of horses for sale. Horse &amp; Hound magazine also contains horse industry news, latest updates from equestrian events and veterinary advice on caring for horses. A Horse &amp; Hound magazine subscription also has the latest news on fox hunting, eventing, dressage, show jumping, horse racing, showing, carriage driving and endurance riding are all regular features in the magazine. Horse &amp; Hound magazine also includes commentaries from top riders and trainers from around the globe.\n', '', '', ''),
(1903, 1, 'Athletics Weekly', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nAthletics Weekly is the world''s leading weekly running and athletics magazine.\n\nAthletics Weekly is the No.1 magazine for track and field, cross country and road running and gives you the best news, comment, event coverage, results, fixtures, coaching advice and product reviews available.\n\nEvery run, every jump, every throw.\n\nKeep close to the world of athletics and running, subscribe now and have AW delivered direct to your door.\n', '', '', ''),
(1904, 1, 'Shooting Times &amp; Country', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Shooting Times &amp; Country Magazine?\n\nYou can make sure you’re getting all of the latest news from the shooting world as and when it happens with a subscription to this brilliant weekly magazine.\n\nShooting Times &amp; Country has played an important part in rural affairs for years, so if you want to get behind country causes in your area, this is the perfect way to do so.\n\nWith your subscription, you''ll be able to read reviews of new equipment, get expert shooting advice, and tips on training an obedient guide dog. All the features are illustrated beautifully with some amazing photographic shots of dogs, hunts and landscapes, making this magazine visually impressive as well as a great read.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nShooting Times &amp; Country Magazine has been at the forefront of the shooting scene for over 125 years. Shooting Times is the clear first choice for shooting sportsmen, with editorial covering all disciplines, including game, rough and stalking. Shooting Times &amp; Country Magazine''s involvement in its community includes attendance at many country fairs and acting as a voice within the countryside movement. Shooting Times and Country Magazine is one of the oldest and best selling titles which cover all aspects of shooting. Published by IPC Media, the magazine reaches you every week packed full essential news and information regarding the sport of shooting. This magazine includes all latest happenings, authoritative and independent reviews, in depth and informative features, exclusive and interesting profiles, essential advice and top tips, and lots more. Along with all this high quality content, the magazine comes with stunning photographs that are attractive and thoroughly interesting.\n', '', '', ''),
