(1906, 1, 'Angler''S Mail', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Angler''s Mail Magazine?\n\nRecreational coarse fishermen will love an Angler’s Mail magazine subscription, with plenty of top tips for tweaking your technique and improving the size of your catch. In addition to reviews of the latest fishing equipment and news on competitions and match results, you''ll also find advice on the best fishing spots in the country. This top mag also caters to carp and pike specialists, with the low down on the best tackle and bait, plus instructional articles helping you to improve your game. You''ll love the vibrant letters section which gives the angling community the chance to voice their views, as well as the “Tales from the Riverbank”, where keen fishermen write about their latest adventures.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCatch Angler’s Mail - Britain’s brightest weekly fishing magazine. The latest news coverage on the biggest fish caught - and where to catch them. Reviews of the latest tackle and the best advice for the Carp hunter. Match fishing results. Indispensable instruction features. Improve your fishing skills and be entertained. Every issue of your subscription to Angler’s Mail magazine includes news coverage on the biggest fish caught - and where to catch them - along with match fishing results, instruction features, reviews of the latest tackle and the best advice for the Carp hunter. First published in 1964 by Echo Publications, today’s incarnation of Angler’s Mail magazine is published by IPC Media and comes out every Tuesday. The magazine covers aspects of modern coarse fishing, and contains news, reviews, features and great true stories! Take out a subscription to Angler’s Mail to improve your fishing skills and be entertained. Three great reasons to take out a subscription: -never miss a single issue -delivery direct to your door every week -earn fantastic savings Don’t miss out – get your subscription today!\n', '', '', ''),
(1907, 1, 'Modern Mini', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Modern MINI Magazine?\n\nYou can stay up-to-date with what''s going on in the new MINI scene across the globe with a subscription to Modern MINI magazine. If you count yourself as a MINI fanatic, you''ll love this title filled with news, feature articles, and road tests, which are all centred on the small and iconic cars. Each issue includes handy step-by-step guides on how to look after or customise your MINI, while the regular ''Our Cars'' and ''Your Cars'' sections allow magazine staff and readers to share their own MINI adventures. You''ll also find information about the latest models, and test drive reviews to show you how certain cars perform on the road.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Modern MINI magazine provides essential reading for any MINI fan. With over 68-pages, Modern MINI magazine is the UK’s only monthly magazine dedicated to the new MINI. Published Bi-monthly, Modern MINI provide the best roundup of the new MINI scene. Each issue covering the latest news, the technical advice and detailed practical articles, offering step-by-step guidance on maintenance and modifying topics of interest to any owner whether you''re handy with a spanner or not. Modern MINI magazine also features a comprehensive club section, The Vibe, providing an excellent roundup of the owner''s clubs and forums, with show reports, events diary and more. Plus the magazine also contains real owners'' cars, covering enthusiasts from around the world. Great reasons to subscribe to Modern MINI magazine today: •Never miss an issue •FREE delivery to your door each month •Save on the cover price\n', '', '', ''),
(1908, 1, 'Crops', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nSubscribe to Crops magazine today, the leading specialist journal for the arable farming industry.\n\nEditorial coverage from the whole of the arable industry – from pesticides to politics, machinery to markets, seeds to store – means that you’ll get the facts and figures you need to make sound business decisions, identify new business opportunities, reduce production costs and increase output.\n\nIn every issue, Crops magazine gives you information on the crops and seeds you need to allow you to reap good profits. With reviews of the different crop varieties available, a complete breakdown on seed suppliers and analysis of market potential, cost effective crop growing techniques and the choice of pesticides, herbicides and fertilisers, a subscription to Crops magazine means you won’t miss a trick when it comes to your field.\n', '', '', ''),
(1909, 1, 'Race Engine Technology', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Race Engine Technology magazine brings you in depth research insights probing significant contemporary race engine projects.Race Engine Technology includes comprehensive coverage of all new developments along with revealing interviews with those central to the on-going evolution of technology. Race Engine Technology has established itself and continues to be, the communications hub of the global racing engine industry.This magazine is published by High Power Media Ltd and reaches your door eight times a year.Race Engine Technology Magazine contains authoritative and independent analysis on all the developments and issues prevailing in the race engine industry.Subscribe to Race Engine technology magazine today and keep up to date with this ever evolving industry.\n', '', '', ''),
(1910, 1, 'Charity Times', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Charity Times, the leading business and management magazine for the UK charity sector. If you are involved in management or strategy within a UK charity, not-for-profit organisation or a company with strong community involvement, Charity Times will keep you up-to-date with best practice for your organisation. Charity Times Online complements the printed publication, offering breaking news, jobs, factsheets, full diary listings, archives and access to the largest marketplace of services for non-profit organisations. This total package combines to offer comprehensive coverage of all the financial, legal, fundraising, marketing and technology management issues facing charities, voluntary groups and non-profits. Advice, information and news from business experts and leading figures in the charity sector make Charity Times essential reading for every non-profit professional. Receive the latest industry developments direct to your door every two months with a subscription to Charity Times.\n', '', '', ''),
(1911, 1, 'Craft Business', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Craft Business magazine subscription is an essential purchase for anyone who makes crafting their profession.The premier trade magazine for the crafts industry (art, craft, needlecraft, fashion &amp; crafts fabrics, haberdashery, hobby materials &amp; equipment, sewing machines and ancillary crafts). Reporting on the latest news, business advice, the profiling of successful companies, and looking at new technology and case studies.Craft Business is a magazine which comes with industry trends, interviews, features, retail strategies, product reports and much more. Craft Business magazine is specially aimed at crafting professionals and gives you fresh perspectives on current business trends, tools, products and market news. Published by Aceville Publications Ltd, a Craft Business magazine subscription will be delivered to your door every month.Subscribe to Craft Business magazine and receive your craft ‘Bible’ every single month, a couple of days before it hits the shops.\n', '', '', ''),
(1912, 1, 'Speciality Foods', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nIf you are a true ‘foodie’ then a subscription to Speciality Food magazine is the magazine for you.Providing industry developments and news, movers &amp; shakers, reports and reviews from buyers for all the top fine food companies. Recipe advice, how to increase revenue through new ingredients, Speciality Food promotes food &amp; drink exhibitions throughout the world - with a strong emphasis on the ever popular market of speciality foods in delicatessens and from around the world.Do not hesitate, place a subscription to Speciality Food magazine today and enter the exciting and evolving world, that is the food industry.\n', '', '', ''),
(1913, 1, 'Whisky Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Whisky Magazine Magazine?\n\nEach issue of a Whisky Magazine subscription has all the latest news from the world of whisky, from in-depth descriptions of new blends to interviews with leading whisky experts.\n\nYou''ll receive regular tasting notes from the UK''s finest distilleries, as well as regional guides and breakdowns of the latest whisky awards and conferences from around the world.\n\nA subscription to this unique food and drinks magazine will help you to find hidden local whiskies, and also teach you how to pair your favourite tipple with seasonal dishes.\n\nThere''s also regular interviews with leading experts, plus top lists to give you the low-down on some of the best beverages from around the world.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Whisky magazine, the authoritative voice of everything whisky related. Often described as the ''whisky bible'', Whisky is the only magazine devoted exclusively to whisky all over the world. Buy a subscription to Whisky magazine today and you''ll find yourself on a magical whisky tour, meeting some of the leading personalities in the industry, learning about the finest and rarest malts and blends, discovering the best whisky bars, lost distilleries and much more. Whether you want to learn more or enhance your existing knowledge of whisky, a subscription to Whisky Magazine will be your ideal drinking companion.\n', '', '', ''),
(1914, 1, 'Macworld', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nMacworld is the world’s best-selling Mac magazine. Every issue is packed with expert advice and practical guides to Apple and Mac products, as well as in-depth and impartial advice to ensure you buy the right products for your needs. Every issue is packed with expert advice and practical guides to Apple and Mac products, as well as in-depth and impartial advice to ensure you buy the right products for your needs. Macworld magazine is full of the very latest Mac and Apple news, plus Masterclass tutorials to help you develop new skills. Each month Macworld magazine carry out their famous Group tests where six best selling products are put through the same rigorous tests and rated. Secrets and Mac help will show you to get the best out of your Mac and the 20 plus pages of MacWorld’s famous reviews will help you make the best purchase decision for your needs and price range. And its not just Macs, Macworld also covers the iPad, iPhone and everything in between, a subscription to Macworld allows you to keep up to date with all Apple products. Another great reason to subscribe to Macworld magazine is for its buyer’s guide that gives the pros and cons for a variety of products plus their useful star rating system will show you the top rated products at a glance.\n', '', '', ''),
(1915, 1, 'Hairstyles Only', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe ultimate lookbook for finding the perfect cut and colour, Hairstyles Only is packed with hundreds of sexy style solutions, from flirty fringes and luscious layers, to cutting edge crops and mid-length manes.\n\nColour-coded sections for long styles, short styles, colours, catwalk looks, black hair, brunettes, red heads and blondes makes it easy to use and the picture only format gives instant access to the latest trends.\n\nHairstyles Only''s A5 size also means it''s the ideal choice to pop in your handbag and take along to the salon.\n', '', '', ''),
(1916, 1, 'Commando', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Commando magazine provides exciting action and adventure stories in pictures. Packed with great action and adventure stories which will keep you glued from cover to cover, it’s no surprise that Commando is as popular and relevant to today as it was when it was first published in 1961. Almost all ages will be fascinated by the stories featured including the First World War, the Boer War and Korean War to name but a few. You may even be surprised to find Vikings and Romans lurking on the pages! Every issue of Commando magazine features a different story taking you to the heart of battle everywhere from land, air and sea. With 8 issues a month delivered straight to your door (4 new, 4 reprints) - you’ll never be bored! Don’t miss out! Subscribe today!\n', '', '', ''),
(1917, 1, 'Keep The Faith', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nKeep The Faith is Britain’s leading Black community-focused publication promoting faith and family values, it provides the community with a voice, highlights the need for unity, creates a better understanding in an ever-changing environment and has been reaching the heart of the Black community since 2004. Every issue is packed with local and regional news, features, interviews, profiles of community figures and role models, Gospel music and events, business and IT news, politics, human interest, health &amp; lifestyle plus much more!\n\nOur editorial policy is informative, educational, aspirational and inspirational. Our contributors are some of the most powerful and influential movers and shakers and successful entrepreneurs within the BME community and include Rev David Shosanya (Director, London Baptist Association), Bishop Dr Joe Aldred (Churches Together in England), Rev Wale Hudson-Roberts (Racial Justice Co-ordinator, Baptist Union), Dionne Gravesande (Head of Church Advocacy, Christian Aid), Arthur Torrington OBE (Historian)\n\nand Dr Robert Beckford (Theologian) to name a few. David Cameron PM contributed an article in the August 2012 issue.\n\nFor over 50 years Britain’s Black churches have provided hope, support, direction, inspirational gospel music, moral guidance and increasingly also run a wide range of community projects which are designed to help the vulnerable and disadvantaged members of the Black community.\n\nBritain’s Black Pentecostal churches are among the largest in the country, many having a regular attendance of 3,000+. Due to their longevity and the social and spiritual impact they have on their members, Black churches are viewed as the most stable, prosperous and influential institution within Britain’s African and Caribbean communities.\n\nKeep The Faith is the only publication of its kind in the UK and a must read for every Christian, it keeps you abreast from the best perspective and is a great resource for ministry.\n', '', '', ''),
(1918, 1, 'Scrapbook Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Scrapbook Magazine Magazine?\n\nStart turning your boxes of memories into a work of art using the guides and tutorials in Scrapbook Magazine. With a subscription to this great crafts magazine, you''ll get tips on how to use your materials in different artistic ways, with pop-up outlines in every issue for you to copy as well as brand new layout ideas.\n\nYou''ll get great advice to help you whether you''re starting from scratch or working with years of memorabilia, so whether it''s a scrapbook to commemorate an anniversary or a work in progress following your baby''s first year, this magazine will make sure you end up with a perfect finished product.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nScrapbook Magazine shows you how to bring your photos and memories to life!\n\nIt''s published every two months, and each issue brings you:\n• 84 pages of inspirational layouts\n• Step-by-step guides to help you master scrapbooking techniques\n• Tips and tricks from talented designers\n', '', '', ''),
(1919, 1, 'Cross Stitch Gold', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nCross Stitch Gold is the ultimate collection of cross stitch designs for experienced stitchers. With eight inspirational projects from the world''s best designers in every issue, you''ll be spoilt for choice of glorious gifts to stitch for friends and family.\n', '', '', ''),
(1920, 1, 'Landscape', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nLandScape magazine reflects the interests of people living rurally or semi-rurally in the landscape and nature around them, the uniqueness of British traditional crafts, the satisfaction of growing and cooking their own food, and the joy of simple activities within their circle of family, friends and community.\n\nThe magazine covers seasonal gardening, cookery, craft, people and places in the British countryside, and its nature. Each issue delivers a wealth of information in an easy-to-read style, with simple layouts and an expansive page allocation for each subject, illustrated with beautiful images.\n', '', '', ''),
(1921, 1, 'Teach Nursery', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA Teach Nursery subscription will support any nursery practitioner in creating an outstanding environment for early years education. Teach Nursery''s practical and accessible articles provide easily digested and forward thinking advice, making it a frequent point of reference for professionals in search of inspiration. Written by a team of early years experts, a Teach Nursery subscription delivers successful plans for play based learning, an insight into educational psychology and advice on how you can contribute to placing your nursery at the heart of the community. A Teach Nursery subscription is a must-have for any current or up and coming nursery professionals.\n', '', '', ''),
(1922, 1, 'Teach Secondary', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nNever miss advice, inspiration and experience from some of the most exciting and innovative thinkers and practitioners in the sector.\n\nHighlighting examples of the best practice, encouraging lively, relevant (and at times, controversial) debate, putting new products through their paces, and providing a regular collection of edgy and original lesson plans that can be adapted for any classroom. Teach Secondary is an essential resource- not to mention an entertaining and enlightening read- for anyone involved in education at Key Stage 3 and 4.\n', '', '', ''),
(1923, 1, 'Cowmanagement', '&lt;p&gt;FROM THE PUBLISHER A subscription to CowManagement magazine is must-have for all progressive UK dairy producers. Published eight times a year, CowManagement magazine covers all aspects of dairy herd management with comprehensive coverage of the latest technological developments. With a subscription to CowManagement magazine, readers are kept well-informed and up-to-date with information showing them how the latest ideas and techniques can be applied effectively on their dairy units. It is specifically aimed at producers, vets and advisers who are looking to maximise herd productivity and business efficiency. Written by an award-winning team of agricultural journalists, CowManagement is recognised for its ‘hands-on’ approach, combining a mixture of regular columns, such as the vet column that takes a timely look at current herd heath issues, with exclusive features and unique herd reports from the UK or abroad. Cow Management also publishes special features throughout the year on subjects including milking equipment, feeding, cow health, housing, calf rearing, fertility, and grassland management. CowManagement prides itself on being different to other dairy farming magazines. It has a fresh design, it’s easy to read and it endeavours to keep its readers up to date with new management ideas and technical developments within the industry. Don’t hesitate, invest in a subscription to CowManagement magazine today.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '', '', ''),
(1924, 1, 'Teach Primary', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nEvery issue of Teach Primary is brimming with ideas to help you with your teaching career.\n\nPacked with ideas and activities that will take the monotony out of lesson planning, with special features, lesson plans and product reviews. With articles written by teachers fresh from the chalkface, you won’t find another magazine more insightful and relevant.\n\nWe also have regular articles from educational experts to aid your professional development and keep you abreast of the latest changes to the KS1&amp;2 curriculums.\n', '', '', ''),
(1925, 1, 'Architectural-Digest-Fr', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThis is the French-language edition of ARCHITECTURAL DIGEST. In an average of 250 pages each issue, it features fine examples of interior design, art, furnishings and antiques.\n', '', '', ''),
(1926, 1, 'Wine Spectator', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWine Spectator Magazine is the magazine that makes wine entertaining and accessible. Each issue of a subscription not only features reviews of more than 500 newly released wines, but also helps you indulge yourself with news of great restaurants, terrific resorts, and world-class cuisine. Special, best-selling issues include The Annual Cabernet Report, The Restaurant Grand Award Winners, The Top 100 Wines of the Year, and Great Wine Values! Wine Spectator magazine is a guide to help wine lovers create a nurturing environment, with advice on how to build a cellar and tips for stocking it. Also featuring tasting reports, wines from around the world, wines to accompany your menu and letters from readers.\n', '', '', ''),
(1927, 1, 'Acoustic Guitar', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Acoustic Guitar magazine offers a wide range of information for all levels of acoustic guitar players. An Acoustic guitar magazine subscription focuses on various areas of interest of the acoustic musician community. Each issue of your Acoustic Guitar magazine subscription will teach you how to improve your technique, contain in-depth profiles of guitar legends, reviews of the latest releases and features sheet music for you to play. This magazine is a must for anyone with a genuine interest in Acoustic Guitar.\n', '', '', ''),
(1928, 1, 'Forbes', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO FORBES Magazines From Abroad?\n\nIf you want sound financial advice from people with some seriously impressive credentials behind them, you need a subscription to Forbes. Best known for features on industry and investment, each issue also has plenty of news on technology, media and science to keep you well-informed on world developments. This American business management magazine has been published every two weeks since 1917, so with your subscription you''ll know you''re getting the benefit of several years of first-hand experience. You''ll also read plenty of innovative and inspiring business suggestions, humorous and satirical articles and of course, the infamous Rich Lists.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nFORBES is a business person''s guide to management and corporate strategies. The format is extremely user-friendly and it is a well-balanced combination of both theory and international news. Each issue of FORBES is full of the latest news, in-depth money articles, investing, law, science and technology and readers views. FORBES GLOBAL also provides readers with useful facts and comments from people within the field.\n', '', '', ''),
(1929, 1, 'New York Review Of Books', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO NEW YORK REVIEW OF BOOKS Magazines From Abroad?\n\nIf you can''t stop talking about the books you read, consider a subscription to The New York Review of Books. Established during the New York publishing strike of 1963, this title believes that the discussion of important writing is, in itself, a literary art. This means that this books and literature magazine is brimming with intellectual discourse for the discerning reader, helping enrich your understanding of the world''s greatest novels. Past and present contributors range from Gore Vidal and Truman Capote to Zadie Smith and Mary Beard, and its longer articles regularly allow writers to roam across a number of books on the subject in question.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to The New York Review Of Books magazine is a must for all looking for an intelligent read.\n\nThe New York Review Of Books has established itself, in Esquire''s words as the premier literary intellectual magazine in the English language. The New York Review began during the New York publishing strike of 1963 when the present editors, Robert Silvers and Barbara Epstein, and their friends, decided to create a new kind of magazine - one in which the most interesting and qualified minds of our time would discuss current books and issues in depth.\n\nIt is the journal where the most important issues are discussed by writers who are themselves a major force in world literature and thought.\n\nEvery two weeks, these and other writers publish essays and reviews of books and the arts, including music, theatre, dance, and film-from Woody Allen''s Manhattan to Kurosawa''s version of King Lear.\n', '', '', ''),
(1930, 1, 'Sophisticates Hairstyle', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSOPHISTICATE''S HAIRSTYLE is an essential purchase for the beauty conscious woman. Each issue offers advice on styling and caring for your hair. Features include hot looks, beauty products and the make up secrets of the stars.\n', '', '', ''),
(1931, 1, 'Scale Auto', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSCALE AUTO opens up the world of model car making. Offering practical advice on model building techniques as well as reviews on the very best international models around. SCALE AUTO is published by Kalmbach.\n', '', '', ''),
(1932, 1, 'Sophisticates Black Hair Guide', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSOPHISTICATE''S BLACK HAIR GUIDE features all the latest hair styles and fashions along with the techniques to create styles at home. A question and answer section covers the day to day problems encountered.\n', '', '', ''),
(1933, 1, 'Scuba Diving', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSCUBA DIVING contains all the latest news and developments in the world of scuba. It comes jam packed with reviews of the latest equipment, kit maintenance tips and training and safety guides. SCUBA DIVING is the only magazine for all scuba abilities from the entusiast to the beginner.\n', '', '', ''),
(1934, 1, 'Short Hair', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSHORT HAIR magazine covers all the most famous celebrities'' short hair styles. Features include 15 short cuts to a new you, Top 10 celebrity short cuts and how to achieve the style you want.\n', '', '', ''),
(1935, 1, 'Air And Space', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nAIR &amp; SPACE covers the world of Aviation including advances in technology and new aircraft. It features the latest technolgy, product tests and reviews, classic features, fantastic photography, flying tips and advice, upcoming events and more!\n', '', '', ''),
(1936, 1, 'Trail Runner', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTrail Runner is the only magazine dedicated to the off-road running community, encouraging runners of all ages and abilities to experience the outdoors and achieve a healthier lifestyle through off-road running. Trail Runner magazine inspires and informs with accurate, intelligent and in-depth writing and compelling photography.\n', '', '', ''),
(1937, 1, 'Bike The Mag', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBike Magazine is the leading Mountain Biking title, with news reviews, meets and equipment suggestions in every issue.\n', '', '', ''),
(1938, 1, 'Rebel Ink', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nThe Tattoo Magazine that takes ink to the extreme! Tattoos have always been a staple of rebellion, and now there''s a magazine that celebrates the ink and attitude of the biggest tattooed rebels of the ink culture. Each issue of REBEL INK delivers page after page of tattooed rock stars, hard-core inked entertainment and sports\n', '', '', ''),
(1939, 1, 'Creative Woodworks &amp; Crafts', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nEvery issue of Creative Woodworks &amp; Crafts is a gold mine for people who love creating detailed, decorative wood crafts. The magazine is filled with full-size patterns, the latest tools and equipment, tips and techniques, and project how-tos.\n', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `oc_product_description` (`product_id`, `language_id`, `name`, `description`, `meta_description`, `meta_keyword`, `tag`) VALUES
(1940, 1, 'Combat Handguns', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nCombat Handguns magazine is a US publication detailing the latest shooting equipment, techniques, and other vital information for the Hand Gun enthusiast, whether you are interested in Guns for their own sake, personal protection or self-defence, every issue is packed with information on these topics.\n\nWith special features on various aspects of guns, for example guns of the Old West, Combat Hand Guns is not only about practical matters, but caters to everyone, whatever their interest in Guns\n', '', '', ''),
(1941, 1, 'Road Bike Action', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRoad Bike Action is the rider''s destination for the newest innovations and first-ride exclusives; it is a rider''s new coach for training tips and guidance that will enable dedicated readers to reach their next fitness and technical levels. Road Bike Action is the only road bike magazine to focus on products, a complete product buyer''s guide for the road bike rider; with in-depth articles inspiring riding/racing stories and great how-to features for all levels.\n', '', '', ''),
(1942, 1, 'Rock &amp; Ice', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nROCK &amp; ICE covers the most challenging and rigorous climbs in America and the rest of the world. It s topics include real life adventures, practical climbing advice and stunning location photography.\n', '', '', ''),
(1943, 1, 'Bhg Traditional Home', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTraditional Home magazine is created by The Better Homes and Gardens publishers in the US. The publication aims to capture the heart of elegant homes in a more direct way than any other magazine of its genre.\n\nIt''s the one place that readers will be able to find the tasteful style and do-able interiors that allow for a comfortable and beautiful home.\n\nSome home based magazines offer completely unattainable ideas, thankfully this publication tries to provide ideas which are easy to recreate and which would fit well into almost any home.\n', '', '', ''),
(1944, 1, 'Transworld Snowboarding', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTransworld Snowboarding is a magazine about snowboarding and the snowboarding culture. It is published 10 times per year and features the very best of the sport-culture-lifestyle that is modern snowboarding. The magazine features award winning photography and design\n', '', '', ''),
(1945, 1, 'Black &amp; White', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBLACK AND WHITE is all about capturing the beauty of black and white photography. Inside readers will find up-to-date news, an events diary, highlights and reviews from past shows, profiles of celebrated photographers, interviews, modern and historic photography, a classified section and more.\n', '', '', ''),
(1946, 1, 'Wine &amp; Spirits', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nWine &amp; Spirits Magazine is published eight times a year and read by over 200,000members of America''s wine community. Consumers and wine professionals read the magazine for information on wine and spirits, including articles on established and up-and-coming regions and producers, the art and science of viticulture, restaurants and industry happenings and food and wine pairings. Wine and Spirits is the only American wine publication to win the James Beard Award for excellence in wine writing. The magazine evaluates more than 8,000 bottlings every year.\n', '', '', ''),
(1947, 1, 'Brides Usa', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nBrides USA magazine is the American take of the ever-present wedding preparation magazine.\n\nFull of great ideas and styles from over the pond, it’s always interesting to have an overseas view for a different take on what can and can''t look great for your wedding.\n\nThere will be great dress ideas as well as venue suggestions and features on the best bridal trends in America at the moment.\n', '', '', ''),
(1948, 1, 'Polymer Cafe', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nExploring the art and craft of polymer clay.\n', '', '', ''),
(1949, 1, 'Hype Hair', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Hype Hair magazine from the publishers of Today''s Black Woman and Word Up, is all you need for great styling tips for afro Caribbean hair.\n\nHype Hair magazine contains quality editorial and full colour photographs giving young readers new and exciting ideas for their hair.\n\nIt also features advice on care and styling hair for women of color, as well as cosmetics tips and information on new beauty products. Hype Hair also includes relaxation, color, weaving and braiding techniques.\n', '', '', ''),
(1950, 1, 'The Atlantic', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nThe Atlantic is an American magazine founded (as The Atlantic Monthly) in Boston in 1857. It was created as a literary and cultural commentary magazine.\n\nThe Atlantic Monthly Magazine has been a voice for the literate reader interested in the world around them for two centuries, and has won more National Magazine Awards than any other monthly magazine. Atlantic Monthly will place readers at the very epicenter of contemporary issues, and it also features the very best in fiction, travel, food and humor. Atlantic is a thoughtful news and literary magazine that focuses on politics, foreign affairs, economics, arts events, and personalities.\n', '', '', ''),
(1951, 1, 'Dwell', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nDWELL brings fresh and sophisticated coverage of home and design to a growing and influential younger audience.\n', '', '', ''),
(1952, 1, 'People''S Friend Special', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nSubscribe to People’s Friend Special and receive seventeen packed issues featuring great fiction, features articles, beautiful poetry and fantastic reader offers!   People’s Friend specials make the perfect gift for anyone you know who would like to receive a varied magazine coving all of the aspects which appeal to readers of the weekly publication. So, if you want even more fantastic fiction stories, make sure you don''t miss out on The People''s Friend Specials.\n', '', '', ''),
(1953, 1, 'Vintage Life Magazine', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Vintage Life Magazine Magazine?\n\nCovering everything from the glamorous styles of the 1920s through to the groovy 1970s, this mag is a fantastic read for anyone interested in eras gone by. A subscription to Vintage Life Magazine offers inspiration and tips on how to recreate the fashion, hair and beauty looks and interiors of the past, as well as recommendations for classic music and films to add to your collection. This monthly mag also explores the lives of iconic Hollywood starlets, alongside guides to vintage markets and reviews of the latest period dramas - offering a nostalgic trip down memory lane and fun ways to bring the past back to life.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to Vintage Life Magazine will keep you up to date with the past, in the present. &quot;Vintage Life Magazine is a magazine aimed at revisiting and rekindling the wonderful years gone by - bringing those memories alive again! From style and fashion, hair and make-up to house and home, toys and collectables to music and film, everything great about the 20s, 30s, 40s, 50s, 60s through to the 70s - all in one great magazine!” With a wide collection of experts sharing their knowledge and many featured articles each issue, a subscription to Vintage Life Magazine really puts you in touch with memories past and brings them alive all over again. Concentrating on the 1920s, through to the 1970s, Vintage Life Magazine really does cover YOUR past. Let us take you down memory lane to revisit those cherished times. Not only do we look at the past, but Vintage Life Magazine is full of how you can recreate styles and more, today in the present! Keeping you up to date with the past, in the present with a subscription to Vintage Life Magazine.\n', '', '', ''),
(1954, 1, 'Wwe Kids', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO WWE Kids Magazine?\n\nYoung wrestling fans will enjoy this bimonthly kids'' magazine that offers exciting WWE match reports and mid-fight photography.\n\nEvery issue is filled with interviews with the WWE''s biggest superstars, keeping your wrestling-mad children up-to-date with what''s going on outside the ring.\n\nA subscription to WWE Kids magazine will also bring your youngsters loads of tips on healthy eating and sports performance, helping them to follow in the footsteps of their favourite wrestlers.\n\nThere are also regular video game reviews and wrestling comic strips, while the popular ''Mind Slammers'' section features puzzles and picture challenges to keep young readers entertained until the next time they get to watch their heroes on TV.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nA subscription to WWE Kids magazine is a must for all WWE superfans! The one and only official WWE Kids magazine brings readers all the latest slammin’ ringside access and interviews with all their favourite WWE wrestlers! As well as all the non-stop action from WWE, a subscription to WWE Kids magazine contains puzzles, comic strips, competitions, WWE wrestlers’ profiles and wicked posters! So, if they are totally crazy about WWE, they’ll never need another mag! Subscribe today to the original and the best WWE kids’ magazine! WWE Kids’ magazine also makes a great gift subscription!\n', '', '', ''),
(1955, 1, 'The Official Jacqueline Wilson', 'WHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO The Official Jacqueline Wilson Magazine?\n\nFor kids who endlessly re-read their Jacqueline Wilson books in between new releases, this magazine is the perfect bridge to her wonderful world.\n\nEach issue of The Official Jacqueline Wilson magazine has colourful illustrations, exciting craft ideas, extra info about the author herself and, of course, lots of fun facts about your child''s favourite characters.\n\nThere''s loads of tips and advice to help your girls through life, including pocket guides to different aspects of friendship and socialising, plus shopping ideas, cool competitions and great games to play.\n\nGet your girls reading, writing and exploring a fantastic world of fiction with this great monthly magazine.\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\n\n\nA subscription to The Official Jacqueline Wilson Mag is a perfect treat for girls who love to read, write and create based with access to the best-selling author Dame Jacqueline Wilson, her books and characters.\n\nEvery issue includes an exclusive free gift along with special stories and tips written by Jacky, how to draw with Nick Sharratt.\n\nPlus lots of fun and inspiring activities to make and do!', '', '', ''),
(1956, 1, 'Whitelines Snowboarding', '\nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nTake out a subscription to Whitelines snowboard magazine, the UK’s premier snowboard magazine. With a 14 year publishing history under its belt, Whitelines Snowboarding Magazine has long been regarded as the magazine of choice for the UK snowboarder. Published in seven monthly installments throughout the winter season (October through March), the very best of snowboard journalism and photography are crafted together within glossy, oversized pages to provide the reader with a truly unique insight into all aspects of the sport. From technical product reviews and in-depth travel information to awe-inspiring photo galleries and road trip documentaries, White Lines guarantees inspirational appeal for snowboarders of all abilities and ages. This first class content and accessibility enables White Lines to continue forging ahead as the most respected and indispensable magazine for the UK’s most exhilarating winter pastime.\n', '', '', ''),
(1957, 1, 'Rouleur', '\nWHY BUY A SUBSCRIPTION TO Rouleur Magazine?\n\nIf competitive cycling is your thing and you appreciate the art of photography and writing, then Rouleur magazine is the best subscription for you. This top cycling magazine reviews the world’s biggest road cycling races, with exceptional photographs that capture the fast-paced nature of the sport sitting alongside quality editorial pieces and cycler profiles. If you want to learn more about the most famous cycling tours, a subscription to Rouleur magazine will give you a behind the scenes look at the most prestigious routes in Europe, covering everything from the Tour de France to the Giro d''Italia. \nFROM THE PUBLISHER\n\nRouleur is an award-winning road cycling magazine established in 2006. It features exquisite photography and incisive writing, using the best photographers and journalists in the business.\nThe magazine is highly collectable and is fast becoming a classic - with cutting edge design, superb production values and printing using the finest quality paper.\n\nRouleur goes behind the scenes at the world’s biggest road cycling races, recording the workings of this incredible traveling circus – a speeding cavalcade that circles Europe each year.\nWhether it is the Paris–Roubaix, Tour of Flanders, Tour de France, the Vuelta a España or the Giro d’Italia, Rouleur provides unique insight into the Classics and Grand Tours, and into many of the other single day and great stage races that form the pinnacle of cycle sport.\n\nRouleur conveys the essence, imagery, passion and beauty of road cycle racing.\nIt is essential reading for all cycling fans, so why not join us by subscribing today? And, for as little as £36.00, you can get the magazine delivered to your door.\n', '', '', '');
